)@@G@@D))^@)^@)^@)^@) 0)C9 E))C1DC(GC-[E-[^[GD9[C))E-[*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/     KD
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THIS ROUTINE HANDLES THE BITWISE LOGICALKE
)@@G@@ OPERATIONS OF AND,     @F@@@@. OR, AND EXCLUSIVE OR.  THE ARGUMENTS AREKF
)@@G@@ TAKEN DIRECTLY WITH NO @D@@@@. TYPE CONVERSION, AND THE RESULT IS TYPEDKG
)@@G@@ INTEGER.   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@M$SEMBITAND*       .    @D@@@@          L KH
)@@G@@        A0,BITAND         . GET AND INSTR @B@@@@          J         BIT0KI
)@@G@@10            .   @^@@@@M$SEMBITOR*        .    @D@@@@          L       KJ
)@@G@@  A0,BITIOR         . GET OR INSTR  @B@@@@          J         BIT010    KK
)@@G@@        .   @^@@@@M$SEMBITXOR*       .    @D@@@@          L         A0,BKL
)@@G@@ITXOR         . GET XOR INSTR @[@@@@BIT010@#@[@@          ROUTINE @^@@@[KM
)@@G@@          SUBROUTINE    @E@@@@BITXQT    LOCAL     1                 . LOKN
)@@G@@GICAL ROUTINE     @E@@@@BITLEN    LOCAL     1                 . LENGTH OKO
)@@G@@F LEFT ARG  @F@@@@          S         A0,BITXQT         . SAVE INSTRUCTIKP
)@@G@@ON TO DO IT @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. MAKE SURE CORE LENGTHS ARE EQUAL. @[@@@@KQ
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@          PIKLEFT   BIT999            . SETUP LEFT ARG FETCHKR
)@@G@@@E@@@@          SA        A0,BITLEN         . SAVE CORE LENGTH    @F@@@@KS
)@@G@@          PIKRITE   BIT999            . SETUP RIGHT ARG FETCH     @G@@@@KT
)@@G@@          LA        A1,BITLEN         . RECOVER LEFT ARG CORE LENGTH    KU
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A5,BITELN         . GET LENGTH ERROR MESSAGE  KV
)@@G@@@F@@@@          TE,U      A0,1              . ALLOW SCALAR EXTENSION    KW
)@@G@@@B@@@@          TNE,U     A1,1              .   @F@@@@          LA,U    KX
)@@G@@  A5,0              . UNEQUAL LENGTHS NOW OK    @D@@@@          TE      KY
)@@G@@  A0,A1             . LENGTHS EQUAL @F@@@@          JNZ       A5,BIT999 KZ
)@@G@@        . IF NO SCALARS, THEN ERROR @G@@@@          TLE       A0,A1     LA
)@@G@@        . MAKE SURE A0 HAS GREATER LENGTH @C@@@@          LA        A0,ALB
)@@G@@1             . IT DOES @F@@@@          PUTANS    BIT999 MODSIN A0  . SELC
)@@G@@TUP FOR RESULT STORE    @D@@@@          J         BIT030            . ANLD
)@@G@@D ENTER LOOP@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. PERFORM LOGICAL OPERATION BETWEEN CORRESLE
)@@G@@PONDING WORDS.    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@BIT020    . @D@@@@          L       LF
)@@G@@  A3,0,*X9          . GET LEFTARG   @E@@@@          EX        BITXQT    LG
)@@G@@        . PERFORM OPERATION   @D@@@@          S         A4,0,*A1        LH
)@@G@@  . STORE RESULT  @D@@@@BIT030    JGD       A0,BIT020         . COUNT RELI
)@@G@@SULT  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          POP       2                 . POP STACLJ
)@@G@@K     @E@@@@          L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR CODE    LK
)@@G@@@]@@@@BIT999    . @#@@@@          RETURN  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          LILL
)@@G@@TS      .   @D@@@@BITAND    AND       A3,0,*X7          . LOGICAL AND   LM
)@@G@@@D@@@@BITIOR    OR        A3,0,*X7          . LOGICAL OR    @D@@@@BITXORLN
)@@G@@    XOR       A3,0,*X7          . LOGICAL XOR   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@      LO
)@@G@@    LITS                        .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@BITELN    PCW     LP
)@@G@@  ;                 .   @C@@@@          'ARGUMENTS ARE NOT OF SAME LENGTLQ
)@@G@@H.' . @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          END                         .   ___@@@LR
)@@G@@9*K #;R]0@[H9/K T0/K@ RV/K@ R2C@K@[GC8@ L+%8K@@[C8@ L0C@)@@G&;)@@[C80^\5LS
)@@G@@&;0@@[N8K@@DM#\)@@9!D@@]9(G@@D9!D@@A9(G@@FC00^\;*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@#/     LT
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@#.     @E@@@#. M$ITEMLENGTH - RETURN WORD LENGTH OCCUPILU
)@@G@@ED BY AN ITEM.    @[@@@#.     @A@@@#.  A0 = VALUE DESCRIPTOR ADDRESS    LV
)@@G@@@^@@@#.  LMJ  X11,M$ITEMLENGTH@^@@@#.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @^@@@#.  A0 LW
)@@G@@= # WORDS IN VALUE@[@@@#.     @^@@@#M$ITEMLENGTH*       .   @D@@@#      LX
)@@G@@    L         A2,VDM,A0         . GET ITS MODE  @D@@@#          L       LY
)@@G@@  A5,PCL('DATA ITEM REQUIRED.')     @F@@@#          LA        A1,VMEBS,ALZ
)@@G@@2       . GET THE ELEMENT BIT SIZE  @E@^@#          JZ        A1,LEN999 MA
)@@G@@        . IF NOT DEFINED, EXIT@E@@@^          JZ        A1,0,X11        MB
)@@G@@  . IF NOT DEFINED, EXIT@C@@@^          LA,U      A5,0              . NOMC
)@@G@@ ERROR@D@@@#          L         A0,VDL,A0         . GET LENGTH    @G@@@#MD
)@@G@@          MI        A0,A1             . ELEMENT LENGTH * ELEMENT SIZE   ME
)@@G@@@G@@@#          DI,U      A0,36             . A0 = # WORDS; A1 = REMAINDMF
)@@G@@ER    @D@@@#          TZ        A1                . ANY REMAINDER?@F@@@#MG
)@@G@@          AA,U      A0,1              . YES, ADD ANOTHER WORD     @C@@@#MH
)@@G@@LEN999    J         0,X11             . ALL DONE@[@@@#.     @G@@@#. M$ITMI
)@@G@@EMINDEX - ROUTINE TO COMPUTE WORD & PARTWORD INDEXES FOR AN ITEM. @[@@@#MJ
)@@G@@.     @^@^@#.         A0 = MODE     @]@@@^.  A0 = MODE@^@^@#.         A1MK
)@@G@@ = INDEX    @#@@@^.  A1 = INDEX     @^@^@#.         A2 = LENGTH   @#@@@^ML
)@@G@@.  A2 = LENGTH    @ @^@#.         LMJ  X11,M$ITEMINDEX@^@@@^.  LMJ  X11,MM
)@@G@@M$ITEMINDEX @ @^@#.         A5 = ERROR OR 0     @#@@@^.  A5 = ERROR OR 0MN
)@@G@@@ @^@#.         A2 = WORD INDEX     @#@@@^.  A2 = WORD INDEX@ @^@#.     MO
)@@G@@    A3 = PARTWORD INDEX @^@@@^.  A3 = PARTWORD INDEX  @ @^@#.         A4MP
)@@G@@ = ADJUSTED LENGTH@^@@@^.  A4 = ADJUSTED LENGTH @ @^@#.         A0,A1 UNMQ
)@@G@@CHANGED.    @^@@@^.  A0,A1 UNCHANGED.     @[@@@#.     @]@@@#M$ITEMINDEX*MR
)@@G@@@D@@@#          LA        A5,PCL('ITEM CANNOT BE INDEXED.') @H@^@#      MS
)@@G@@    JEZ       VMPWX,A0 0,X11    . RETURN IF NO PARTWORD INDEX FOR ITEM  MT
)@@G@@@G@@@^          TNZ       VMPWX,A0          . IS ITEM A STANDARD PARTWORMU
)@@G@@D?    @G@@@^          TZ        VMEWS,A0          . NO, IS IT A MULTIPLEMV
)@@G@@ WORD SIZE? @F@@@^          J         $+2               . YES, IT CAN BEMW
)@@G@@ INDEXED    @E@@@^          J         0,X11             . NO, CAUSE AN EMX
)@@G@@RROR  @E@@@#          SA        A2,A5             . SAVE THE LENGTH     MY
)@@G@@@F@@@#          LA        A2,A1             . GET THE ELEMENT INDEX     MZ
)@@G@@@D@@@#          LA,U      A3,0              . NO OFFSET     @F@@@#      NA
)@@G@@    JZ        A2,NDX010         . IF TRIVIAL INDEX, SKIP    @D@@@#      NB
)@@G@@    MI        A2,VMEBS,A0       . = BIT INDEX   @I@@@#          DI,U    NC
)@@G@@  A2,36             . A2 = WORD INDEX; A3 = BIT OFFSET IN WORD    @E@A@#ND
)@@G@@          JZ        A2,NDX010         . SKIP IF NO OFFSET   @E@@@A      NE
)@@G@@    JZ        A3,NDX010         . SKIP IF NO OFFSET   @ @@@#          DSNF
)@@G@@L       A3,36     @E@@@#          DI        A3,VMEBS,A0       . A3 = PARNG
)@@G@@TWORD OFFSET@E@@@#NDX010    LDSL      A4,36             . A4 = LENGTH; ANH
)@@G@@5 = 0 @E@^@#          TZ        VMEWS,A0          . WORD SIZE MULTIPLE? NI
)@@G@@@E@ @^          TZ        VMPWX,A0          . STANDARD PARTWORD?  @E@@@ NJ
)@@G@@          TNZ       VMPWX,A0          . STANDARD PARTWORD?  @F@^@#      NK
)@@G@@    MSI       A4,VMEWS,A0       . YES, CORRECT THE LENGTH   @G@@@^      NL
)@@G@@    MSI       A4,VMEWS,A0       . NO, COMPUTE WORD LENGTH OF ITEM @C@@@#NM
)@@G@@          J         0,X11             . DONE    @[@@@^.     @F@@@^. M$ITNN
)@@G@@EMADDR - ROUTINE TO SETUP ITEM ADDRESSES AND FETCH INDEX    @[@@@^.     NO
)@@G@@@A@@@^.  A1 = VALUE DESCRIPTOR ADDRESS    @#@@@^.  A2 = WORD INDEX@^@@@^NP
)@@G@@.  LMJ  X11,M$ITEMADDR  @^@@@^.  A0 = PARTWORD INDEX  @D@@@^.  A1 = DATANQ
)@@G@@ BASE WORD INDEX (INCR, FIRST WORD ADDR)  @C@@@^.  A2 = INDEXED WORD INDNR
)@@G@@EX (INCR, INDEXED WORD) @[@@@^.     @]@@@^M$ITEMADDR* @E@@@^          LANS
)@@G@@        A0,VDM,A1         . GET THE VALUE MODE  @E@@@^          LA      NT
)@@G@@  A1,VDA,A1         . GET THE VALUE ADDR  @F@@@^          LXI       A1,VNU
)@@G@@MEWS,A0       . GET THE ELEMENT WORD SIZE @F@@@^          TNE,U     A1,,NV
)@@G@@A1            . NONZERO ELEMENT WORD SIZE?@H@@@^          LXI,U     A1,1NW
)@@G@@              . NO, SUPPLY DEFAULT WORD SIZE INCREMENT@F@@@^          AUNX
)@@G@@,U      A1,,A2            . ADD IN THE WORD INDEX     @F@@@^          LANY
)@@G@@        A0,VMPWX,A0       . GET THE PARTWORD INDEX    @F@@@^          JNNZ
)@@G@@Z       A0,0,X11          . RETURN IF INDEX PRESENT   @E@@@^          LAOA
)@@G@@,U      A0,PWX36          . SUPPLY DEFAULT INDEX@C@@@^          J       OB
)@@G@@  0,X11             . DONE    @[@@@#/.    @F@@@#. M$ITEMPIK - ROUTINE TOOC
)@@G@@ SETUP ELEMENT FETCH OF ANY VALUE ITEM.   @[@@@#.     @^@@@#.  A0 = VALUOD
)@@G@@E DESCRIPTOR@#@@@#.  A1 = INDEX     @#@^@#.  A2 = LENGTH    @#@@@^.  R1 OE
)@@G@@= LENGTH    @^@@@#.  LMJ  X11,M$ITEMPIK   @^@@@#.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  OF
)@@G@@@^@@@#.  A0,A1 = FETCH INDEXES@#@^@#.  R1 = LENGTH    @^@@@^.  R1 = ADJUOG
)@@G@@STED LENGTH @^@@@#.  A2,A3,A4 UNCHANGED.  @[@@@#.     @ @B@#M$ITEMPIK* ROH
)@@G@@OUTINE  A2,A3,A4  @A@@@BM$ITEMPIK* SUBROUTINE  A2,A3,A4     @#@@@#PIKVDAOI
)@@G@@    LOCAL   @E@@@#          SA        A0,PIKVDA         . SAVE VD ADDRESOJ
)@@G@@S     @E@@@#          LA        A0,VDM,A0         . GET THE VALUE MODE  OK
)@@G@@@D@@@^          LA        A2,R1             . GET THE LENGTH@E@@@#      OL
)@@G@@    CALL      M$ITEMINDEX       . COMPUTE THE INDEXES @B@@@#          JNOM
)@@G@@Z       A5,PIK999         .   @G@@@#          LR        R1,A4           ON
)@@G@@  . SAVE THE ADJUSTED LENGTH HERE   @E@@@#          LA        A1,PIKVDA OO
)@@G@@        . RECOVER THE VD ADDR @E@@@^          CALL      M$ITEMADDR      OP
)@@G@@  . SETUP ITEM ADDRESSES@H@^@#          LX        X11,VMPWX,A0      . GEOQ
)@@G@@T THE PARTWORD INDEX FOR THE MODE   @F@^@#          AA        A2,VDA,A1 OR
)@@G@@        . COMPUTE INITIAL WORD INDEX@G@^@#          AA        A3,*M$LTXTOS
)@@G@@,X11    . COMPUTE INITIAL PARTWORD INDEX  @G@@@^          AA        A3,MOT
)@@G@@$LTX,A0       . COMPUTE INITIAL PARTWORD INDEX  @E@@@#          DL      OU
)@@G@@  A0,A2             . LEAVE THEM IN A0,A1 @#@@@#PIK999    RETURN  @[@@@#OV
)@@G@@.     @F@@@#. M$ITEMPUT - ROUTINE TO SETUP INDEXED STASH OF ANY VALUE ITOW
)@@G@@EM.   @[@@@#.     @#@@@#.  A2 = VD ADDRESS@#@@@#.  A3 = INDEX     @#@@@#OX
)@@G@@.  A4 = LENGTH    @^@@@#.  LMJ  X11,M$ITEMPUT   @^@@@#.  A5 = ERROR PCW OY
)@@G@@OR 0  @^@@@#.  A2,A3 = STORE INDEXES@^@@@#.  A4 = ADJUSTED LENGTH @^@@@#OZ
)@@G@@.  A0,A1,R1 UNCHANGED.  @[@@@#.     @ @B@#M$ITEMPUT* ROUTINE  A0,A1     PA
)@@G@@@ @@@BM$ITEMPUT* SUBROUTINE  A0,A1  @#@@@#PUTVDA    LOCAL   @E@@@#      PB
)@@G@@    SA        A2,PUTVDA         . SAVE DESCRIPTOR ADDR@E@@@#          LAPC
)@@G@@        A0,VDM,A2         . GET THE VALUE MODE  @E@@@^          DL      PD

)@@G@@EMINDEX       . COMPUTE THE INDEXES @ @@@#          JNZ       A5,PUT999 PF
)@@G@@@F@@@#          LA        A1,PUTVDA         . RECOVER THE VD ADDRESS    PG
)@@G@@@E@@@^          CALL      M$ITEMADDR        . SETUP ADDRESSES     @G@^@#PH

)@@G@@@F@^@#          AA        A2,VDA,A1         . COMPUTE INITIAL WORD INDEXPJ

)@@G@@NDEX  @G@@@^          AA        A3,M$STX,A0       . COMPUTE INITIAL PARTPL
)@@G@@WORD INDEX  @#@@@#PUT999    RETURN  @[@@@#/.    @C@@@#. M$ITEMCOPY - ROUPM
)@@G@@TINE TO COPY A VALUE ITEM.    @C@@@#. M$ITEMSKIP - ROUTINE TO SKIP A VALPN
)@@G@@UE ITEM.    @[@@@#.     @^@@@#.  A0,A1 = FETCH INDEXES@^@@@#.  A2,A3 = SPO
)@@G@@TASH INDEXES@^@@@#.  R1 = COPY LENGTH     @^@@@#.  LMJ  X11,M$ITEMCOPY  PP
)@@G@@@A@@@#.  A0,A1 = UPDATED FETCH INDEXES    @A@@@#.  A2,A3 = UPDATED STASHPQ
)@@G@@ INDEXES    @]@@@#.  R1 = -1  @[@@@#.     @^@@@#.  A0,A1 = FETCH INDEXESPR
)@@G@@@^@@@#.  R1 = SKIP LENGTH     @^@@@#.  LMJ  X11,M$ITEMSKIP  @A@@@#.  A0,PS
)@@G@@A1 = UPDATED FETCH INDEXES    @]@@@#.  R1 = -1  @^@@@#.  A2,A3 UNCHANGEDPT
)@@G@@.     @[@@@#.     @D@@@#M$ITEMSKIP* LXI     X11,BML(17)       . SET SKIPPU
)@@G@@ FLAG @D@@@#          J         CPY020            . START LOOP    @D@@@#PV
)@@G@@M$ITEMCOPY* LXI,U   X11,0             . SET COPY FLAG @D@@@#          J PW
)@@G@@        CPY020            . START LOOP    @D@@@#CPY010    EX        0,*APX

)@@G@@C@)  Z[4I@@F/\) OYC)) ^[*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/         M$DEF   @[@@@@.     RW
)@@G@@@G@@@@. THIS ROUTINE IMPLEMENTS THE 'TRIM', 'RTRIM', AND 'LTRIM' FUNCTIORX
)@@G@@NS.   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE CONFIGURATION DEFINITIONS SHOULD SET THE FRY
)@@G@@UNCTION SUBCODE TO@C@@@@. ONE OF THE FOLLOWING VALUES FOR EACH ROUTINE. RZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@.  RTRIM - SUBCODE = 1; TRIM THE TRAILING BLANKS.     SA
)@@G@@@C@@@@.  LTRIM - SUBCODE = 2; TRIM THE LEADING BLANKS.@F@@@@.  TRIM  - SSB
)@@G@@UBCODE = 3; TRIM BOTH LEADING AND TRAILING BLANKS.    @[@@@@.     @#@]@@SC
)@@G@@M$FUNTRIM* ROUTINE@^@@@]M$FUNTRIM* SUBROUTINE   @H@@@@TRIMCOL   LOCAL   SD
)@@G@@                    . THE LEFTMOST COLUMN OF THE SUBSTRING  @F@@@@      SE
)@@G@@    LA        A0,VDA+SRA        . GET THE STRING ADDRESS    @D@@@@      SF
)@@G@@    LA        A1,M$XASL         . GET LOAD TABLE@D@@@@          LR      SG
)@@G@@  R1,VDL+SRA        . GET THE LENGTH@I@@@@          DSL       A2,72     SH
)@@G@@        . A2 = LAST NON-BLANK, A3 = FIRST NON-BLAN    @D@@@@          LASI
)@@G@@,U      A4,0              . A4 = COLUMN # @F@@@@          J         TRIMSJ
)@@G@@020           . START THE EXAMINATION     @E@@@@TRIM010   EX        0,*ASK
)@@G@@1             . GET THE NEXT CHAR   @E@@@@          AA,U      A4,1      SL
)@@G@@        . COUNT THE COLUMN #  @C@@@@          TE,U      A5,$CAS(' ')    SM
)@@G@@  . BLANK?  @G@@@@          LA        A2,A4             . NO, REMEMBER LSN
)@@G@@AST NON-BLANK     @G@@@@          JNZ       A3,TRIM020        . IF FIRSTSO
)@@G@@ NON-BLANK SET, SKIP    @C@@@@          TE,U      A5,$CAS(' ')      . BLSP
)@@G@@ANK?  @F@@@@          LA        A3,A4             . NO, SET FIRST NON-BLSQ
)@@G@@ANK   @F@@@@TRIM020   JGD       R1,TRIM010        . COUNT CHARS & KEEP LSR
)@@G@@OOKING@G@@@@          JZ        A3,TRIM030        . IF STRING ALL BLANK,SS
)@@G@@ SKIP AHEAD @E@@@@          LA        A0,VDFS+SFN       . GET FUNCTION SST
)@@G@@UBCODE@E@@@@          TOP,U     A0,1              . RIGHT TRIM BIT SET? SU
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LA        A2,VDL+SRA        . NO, USE LENGTH AS RIGHT LISV
)@@G@@MIT   @E@@@@          TOP,U     A0,2              . LEFT TRIM BIT SET?  SW
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LA,U      A3,1              . NO, USE FIRST CHAR AS LEFTSX
)@@G@@ LIMIT@F@@@@          AN,U      A3,1              . GET ORIGIN ZERO INDESY
)@@G@@X     @F@@@@          SA        A3,TRIMCOL        . REMEMBER FIRST CHAR SZ
)@@G@@INDEX @F@@@@          AN,U      A2,,A3            . COMPUTE SUBSTRING LETA
)@@G@@NGTH  @F@@@@TRIM030   LA,U      A1,MODASC         . GET TYPE OF SUBSTRINTB
)@@G@@G     @E@@@@          PUTANS    TRIM999           . CREATE RESULT SPACE TC
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LR,U      R1,,A2            . SAVE SUBSTRING LENGTH HERETD
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LA,U      A2,,A1            . SAVE NEW SUBSTRING ADDRESSTE
)@@G@@ HERE @F@@@@          LA        A3,M$XASS         . GET STORE TABLE ADDRTF
)@@G@@ESS   @F@@@@          LA        A0,TRIMCOL        . RECOVER FIRST CHAR ITG
)@@G@@NDEX  @G@@@@          DSL       A0,2              . COMPUTE WORD INDEX+CTH
)@@G@@HAR OFFSET  @F@@@@          SSL       A1,34             . = CHAR OFFSET TI
)@@G@@IN WORD     @E@@@@          AA        A0,VDA+SRA        . COMPUTE WORD ITJ
)@@G@@NDEX  @E@@@@          AA        A1,M$XASL         . SET LOAD TABLE INDEXTK
)@@G@@@E@@@[          CALL      M$ITEMCOPY        . COPY THE SUBSTRING  @F@[@@TL
)@@G@@          J         TRIM050           . START SUBSTRING COPY LOOP @D@[@@TM
)@@G@@TRIM040   EX        0,*A1             . GET A CHAR    @D@[@@          EXTN
)@@G@@        0,*A3             . PUT A CHAR    @F@[@@TRIM050   JGD       R1,TTO
)@@G@@RIM040        . COUNT & COPY TILL DONE    @E@@@@          CALL      M$BLTP
)@@G@@ANKWORD       . BLANK THE LAST WORD @C@@@@TRIM999   RETURN              TQ
)@@G@@        . ALL DONE@[@@@@.     @#@@@@          END     ___@@@/K@ S9C0@ ^[TR
)@@G@@/@@ S9G8@@@[/,0@,1[@K #'C8@ ^[&;@@@[&;K@@[C0) ^[G8)@@[[@)@[[M#W)@@R]) PRTS
)@@G@@/KE@@[9?@^?O9*@ V)C@@ VZ*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/         M$DEF   @[@@@@.     TT
)@@G@@@D@@@@. THIS ROUTINE IMPLEMENTS THE TYPE QUERYING FUNCTIONS:@[@@@@.     TU
)@@G@@@D@@@@. $QI $QFL $QDI $QDFL $QNUM $QFD $QASC $QSTR $QVAL    @]@@@@. $QT TV
)@@G@@$QL   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. THE SUBFUNCTION CODE MUST BE THE MODE OR BITS TW
)@@G@@TO TEST FOR.@[@@@@.     @#@@@@M$FUNTESTYPE*     @ @@@@          LMJ     TX
)@@G@@  A1,TEST   @D@@@@          TE,U      A0,,A2            . MODES EQUAL?  TY
)@@G@@@#@@@@M$FUNTESTSTR*     @E@@@@          LMJ       A1,TEST           . TETZ
)@@G@@ST FOR A STRING   @E@[@@          TOP,U     A2,ALPBIT         . TEST FORUA
)@@G@@ STRING BIT @E@@@[          TSTR      A2                . TEST FOR A STRUB
)@@G@@ING   @^@@@@M$FUNTESTNUM*           @E@@@@          LMJ       A1,TEST   UC
)@@G@@        . TEST FOR NUMERIC    @F@[@@          TG,U      A2,MODDFL+1     UD
)@@G@@  . TEST FOR ANY NUMERIC MODE @F@@@[          TNUM      A2              UE
)@@G@@  . TEST FOR ANY NUMERIC MODE @#@@@@M$FUNTESTNOD*     @F@@@@          LMUF
)@@G@@J       A1,TEST           . TEST FOR LIST OR TABLE    @E@@@[          TNUG
)@@G@@OD      A2                . TEST FOR A NODE     @ @[@@          LMJ     UH
)@@G@@  A1,$+1    @D@[@@          TE,U      A2,MODLST         . IS IT A LIST? UI
)@@G@@@E@[@@          TNE,U     A2,MODTBL         . NO, IS IT A TABLE?  @D@[@@UJ
)@@G@@          J         1,A1              . RETURN YES    @D@[@@          J UK
)@@G@@        0,A1              . RETURN NO     @#@@@@M$FUNTESTDAT*     @E@@@@UL
)@@G@@          LMJ       A1,TEST           . TEST FOR NON-NODE   @D@@@[      UM
)@@G@@    TDAT      A2                . TEST FOR DATA @ @[@@          LMJ     UN
)@@G@@  A1,$+1    @D@[@@          TE,U      A2,MODLST         . IS IT A LIST? UO
)@@G@@@E@[@@          TEP,U     A2,PSVBIT         . NO, IS IT A PSUEDO? @E@[@@UP
)@@G@@          J         0,A1              . RETURN NOT DATA     @D@[@@      UQ
)@@G@@    J         1,A1              . RETURN YES    @[@@@@.     @#@]@@TEST  UR
)@@G@@    ROUTINE @^@@@]TEST      SUBROUTINE    @E@@@@          LA        A0,VUS
)@@G@@DFS+SFN       . GET FUNCTION SUBCODE@E@@@@          LA        A2,VDM+SRAUT
)@@G@@        . GET THE MODE TO TEST@E@@@@          LA,U      A4,1            UU
)@@G@@  . ASSUME GOOD RESULTS @D@@@@          EX        0,A1              . TEUV
)@@G@@ST THE TYPE @D@@@@          LA,U      A4,0              . TEST FAILED   UW
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LA        A0,A4             . GET THE RESULT@F@@@@      UX
)@@G@@    CALL      M$RESULTINT       . CREATE THE INTEGER RESULT @C@@@@      UY
)@@G@@    JNZ       A5,TST999         . DONE    @E@@@@          DS        A0,VUZ
)@@G@@D+SLA         . POST THE RESULT     @C@@@@TST999    RETURN              VA
)@@G@@        . DONE    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@          END     ___@@@/K@ Q\C[K PQVB
)@@G@@[[K^?KC8@^?K&;@@@]%9@@@]*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/         M$DEF   @[@@@@.     VC
)@@G@@@D@@@@. M$FUNSSS - THE 'SUBSTRING SUBSTITUTION' FUNCTION.   @[@@@@.     VD
)@@G@@@A@@@@.   $SSS(<STR1>;<INDEX>;<STR2>)     @[@@@@.     @#@^@@M$FUNSSS* ROVE
)@@G@@UTINE @^@@@^M$FUNSSS* SUBROUTINE    @D@@@@SUBSTR1   LOCAL     2         VF
)@@G@@        . SOURCE STRING @C@@@@SUBNDX    LOCAL     2                 . INVG
)@@G@@DEX   @E@@@@SUBSTR2   LOCAL     2                 . INSERTION STRING    VH
)@@G@@@G@@@@SUBRLEN   LOCAL                       . SOURCE STRING REMAINING LEVI
)@@G@@NGTH  @D@#@]          ARGCHK    SUB999 SUBSTR1 ;  . PROCESS ARGS  @G@#@]VJ
)@@G@@                    (ARGMSK MODASC,'CVT' MODSIN MODASC,'OPT','CVT') 3 . VK
)@@G@@@E@@@#          ARGCHK    SUB999 SUBSTR1 SUBMSK 3 . PROCESS ARGS  @E@]@@VL
)@@G@@          LA,U      A0,VD+SRA         . GET ARG LIST ADDRESS@G@]@@      VM
)@@G@@    LA,U      A1,SUBSTR1        . GET LOCAL SPACE BASE ADDRESS    @E@]@@VN
)@@G@@          LA,U      A2,3              . # OF ARGS EXPECTED  @F@]@@      VO
)@@G@@    CALL      M$ARGXFER         . CHECK & TRANSFER ARGUMENTS@ @]@@      VP
)@@G@@    JNZ       A5,SUB999 @E@]@@          LA        A0,VDM+SUBSTR1    . CHVQ
)@@G@@ECK STRING MODES  @A@]@@          LA        A1,VDM+SUBSTR2  @F@[@@      VR
)@@G@@    TEP,U     A0,ALPBIT         . ARE THE ARGUMENTS STRING? @B@[@@      VS
)@@G@@    TOP,U     A1,ALPBIT         .   @D@]@@          LA        A5,PCL('ARVT
)@@G@@GUMENT MODE ERROR.')    @F@]@[          TSTR      A0 SUB999         . IFVU
)@@G@@ ARGS NOT STRING, ERROR @B@]@[          TSTR      A1 SUB999         .   VV
)@@G@@@D@[@@          JNZ       A5,SUB999         . IF ERROR, QUIT@H@]@@      VW
)@@G@@    CONVASC   SUB999 SUBSTR1    . ENSURE THAT ALL STRINGS ARE ASCII     VX
)@@G@@@B@]@@          CONVASC   SUB999 SUBSTR2    .   @G@@@@          LA,U    VY
)@@G@@  A0,SUBSTR1        . NOW CHECK THE INDEX FOR STR1    @B@@@@          LAVZ
)@@G@@,U      A1,SUBNDX         .   @G@@@@          CALL      M$INDEXCHECK    WA
)@@G@@  . CHECK & COMPUTE EFFECTIVE INDEX @D@@@@          JNZ       A5,SUB999 WB
)@@G@@        . OOPS (MAYBE)  @E@@@@          DS        A1,SUBNDX         . SAWC
)@@G@@VE EFFECTIVE INDEX@F@@@@          LA        A2,VDL+SUBSTR1    . GET SOURWD
)@@G@@CE STRING LENGTH  @F@@@@          AN        A2,SUBNDX+1       . MINUS SUWE
)@@G@@BSTRING LENGTH    @H@@@@          ANU       A2,SUBNDX         . A3 = REMWF
)@@G@@AINDER LENGTH OF SOURCE STRING@F@@@@          AA        A2,VDL+SUBSTR2  WG
)@@G@@  . A2 = RESULT STRING LENGTH @G@@@@          SA        A3,SUBRLEN      WH
)@@G@@  . SAVE REMAINDER STRING LENGTH    @E@@@@          PUTANS    SUB999 MODWI
)@@G@@ASC     . SETUP RESULT AREA   @G@@@@          LA        A2,A1           WJ
)@@G@@  . GET DESTINATION STRING ADDRESS  @F@@@@          LA        A3,M$XASS WK
)@@G@@        . GET STORE TABLE ADDRESS   @G@@@@          LA        A0,VDA+SUBWL
)@@G@@STR1    . GET SOURCE STRING BASE ADDRESS  @F@@@@          LA        A1,MWM
)@@G@@$XASL         . GET LOAD TABLE ADDRESS    @G@@@@          LR        R1,SWN
)@@G@@UBNDX         . COPY SOURCE UP TO THE INDEX     @B@#@@          CALL    WO
)@@G@@  M$COPYSTR         .   @B@@@#          CALL      M$ITEMCOPY        .   WP
)@@G@@@H@@@@          LR        R1,SUBNDX+1       . SKIP SOURCE STRING UP TO TWQ
)@@G@@HE LENGTH   @D@#@@          CALL      M$SKIPSTR         . SKIP CHARS    WR
)@@G@@@D@@@#          CALL      M$ITEMSKIP        . SKIP CHARS    @G@@@@      WS
)@@G@@    DS        A0,SUBSTR1        . SAVE INDICES TO SOURCE STRING   @H@@@@WT
)@@G@@          LA        A0,VDA+SUBSTR2    . GET BASE ADDRESS OF INSERTION STWU
)@@G@@RING  @F@@@@          LA        A1,M$XASL         . GET LOAD TABLE ADDREWV
)@@G@@SS    @G@@@@          LR        R1,VDL+SUBSTR2    . GET INSERTION STRINGWW
)@@G@@ LENGTH     @G@#@@          CALL      M$COPYSTR         . COPY THE ENTIRWX
)@@G@@E INSERTION STRING@G@@@#          CALL      M$ITEMCOPY        . COPY THEWY
)@@G@@ ENTIRE INSERTION STRING@G@@@@          DL        A0,SUBSTR1        . REWZ
)@@G@@LOAD SOURCE REMAINDER INDICES @G@@@@          LR        R1,SUBRLEN      XA
)@@G@@  . GET REMAINDER STRING LENGTH     @F@#@@          CALL      M$COPYSTR XB
)@@G@@        . COPY THE REMAINDER STRING @F@@@#          CALL      M$ITEMCOPYXC
)@@G@@        . COPY THE REMAINDER STRING @E@@@@          CALL      M$BLANKWORXD
)@@G@@D       . FINISH UP THE STRING@C@@@@SUB999    RETURN                    XE
)@@G@@  . ALL DONE@]@@@#          . @F@@@#SUBMSK    ARGMSK    MODASC,'CVT' MODXF
)@@G@@SIN,'CVT' MODASC,'OPT','CVT'  @]@@@@          . @#@@@@          END     XG
)@@G@@___@@@ISABLED     @]F UMOUTPUT FILE COULD NOT BE ASSIGNED BECAUSE:@[B UYXH
)@@G@@OUTPUT WILL BE PUT IN TEMPORARY FILE MED$$RECOVR*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/     XI
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. THIS ROUTINE IMPLEMENTS THE RETYPING FUNXJ
)@@G@@CTIONS.     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.  TI$ TASC$ TFD$ TDI$ TFL$ TDFL$   @[@@@@XK
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. THE ARGUMENT MAY BE OF ANY DATA TYPE; THE RESULT TYPE IS DXL
)@@G@@ETERMINED BY@B@@@@. THE PARTICULAR FUNCTION BEING CALLED.   @[@@@@.     XM
)@@G@@@]@@@@M$FUNRETYPE*@#@[@@          ROUTINE @^@@@[          SUBROUTINE    XN
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA,U      A0,VD+SRA         . GET WORD LENGTH OF THE ARGXO
)@@G@@@B@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$ITEMLENGTH  .   @E@@@@          JNZ     XP
)@@G@@  A5,RET999         . CHECK FOR ERRORS    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. FUNCTION SXQ
)@@G@@UBCODES ARE DEFINED TO BE 12 X THE ACTUAL CORE FACTOR.@D@@@@. THIS MAKESXR
)@@G@@ THE CODES DEFINABLE IN INTEGER VALUES.   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          MIXS
)@@G@@,U      A0,12             . SETUP FOR DIVIDE    @E@@@@          DI      XT
)@@G@@  A0,VDFS+SFN       . COMPUTE WORD COUNT  @F@@@@          DSL       A0,1XU
)@@G@@8             . MOVE LENGTH TO UPPER A1   @E@@@@          LXM       A1,VXV
)@@G@@DA+SRA        . GET ADDRESS OF DATA @G@@@@          SA        A1,VDAW+SLXW
)@@G@@A       . POST THE RESULT ACCESS WORD     @[@@@@RET999@#@@@@          REXX
)@@G@@TURN  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@          END     ___@@@EM            5401  @@@@XY
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/         M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THIS ROUTINE IMPXZ
)@@G@@LEMENTS THE $MODE FUNCTION WHICH RETURNS AN     @F@@@@. INTEGER VALUE FOYA
)@@G@@R THE MODE OF THE ARGUMENT. THE RETURNED VALUES @ @@@@. AND CORRESPONDINYB
)@@G@@G MODES ARE:@[@@@@.     @#@@@@.  0 = INTEGER    @#@@@@.  1 = FLOATING   YC
)@@G@@@^@@@@.  2 = DOUBLE INTEGER   @^@@@@.  3 = DOUBLE FLOATING  @^@@@@.  4 =YD
)@@G@@ FIELDATA STRING  @^@@@@.  5 = ASCII STRING     @]@@@@.  6 = LIST @]@@@@YE
)@@G@@.  7 = TABLE@]@@@@.  8 = NULL @[@@@@.     @#@#@@M$FUNMODE* ROUTINE@^@@@#YF
)@@G@@M$FUNMODE* SUBROUTINE   @F@@@@          LA        A0,VDM+SRA        . GEYG
)@@G@@T THE ARGUMENT MODE     @F@@@]          CALL      M$RESULTINT       . CRYH
)@@G@@EATE AN INTEGER RESULT  @E@@@]          DS        A0,VD+SLA         . POYI
)@@G@@ST THE RESULT     @C@@@]          RETURN                      . DONE    YJ
)@@G@@@]@@@]          . @G@]@@          TSE,H1    A0,,A1 1,MODES,MODET . FIND YK
)@@G@@THE MODE & VALUE RESULT @H@]@@          J         $+2               . IFYL
)@@G@@ NOT FOUND, RETURN MODE AS RESULT   @H@]@@          LA,H2     A0,,A1    YM
)@@G@@        . RETURN ASSOCIATED VALUE AS RESULT     @F@]@@          CALL    YN
)@@G@@  M$RESULTINT       . CREATE AN INTEGER RESULT  @E@]@@          DS      YO
)@@G@@  A0,VD+SLA         . POST THE RESULT     @C@]@@          RETURN        YP
)@@G@@              . ALL DONE@]@]@@          . @E@]@@          .         TABLYQ
)@@G@@E OF MODES AND ASSOCIATED VALUES    @]@]@@          . @G@[@@ML        EQYR
)@@G@@U       $L1(MODSIN,MODDFL,MODDIN,MODDFL,MODALP,MODASC,;     @G@]@[ML    YS
)@@G@@    EQU       $L1(MODSIN,MODSFL,MODDIN,MODDFL,MODALP,MODASC,;     @C@]@@YT
)@@G@@                        MODLST,MODTBL,MODNUL)   @D@]@@MODET,MODES DO ML YU
)@@G@@, + ML(MODES),MODES-1 . GEN TABLE   @]@]@@          . @#@@@@          ENYV
)@@G@@D     ___@@@@[E U"EDITOR*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/         M$DEF   @[@@@@.     YW
)@@G@@@E@@@@. THIS ROUTINE IMPLEMENTS THE MIN AND MAX FUNCTIONS.  BOTH  @G@@@@YX
)@@G@@. FUNCTIONS ARE CALLED BY THE SAME ENTRY POINT, BUT THE SUBFUNCTION     YY
)@@G@@@B@@@@. CODE MUST BE 0 FOR MIN AND 1 FOR MAX.   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@M$FUNMYZ
)@@G@@INMAX*@#@^@@          ROUTINE @^@@@^          SUBROUTINE    @F@@@@      ZA
)@@G@@    LA        A5,PCL('ARGUMENT MUST BE A NUMERIC VECTOR')   @F@@@@      ZB
)@@G@@    LA        A1,VDM+SRA        . GET THE ARGUMENT MODE     @G@[@@      ZC
)@@G@@    JL,U      A1,MODDFL MAX999  . TAKE ERROR EXIT IF NOT NUMERIC  @E@@@[ZD
)@@G@@          TNUM      A1 MAX999         . ERROR IF NOT NUMERIC@G@@@@      ZE
)@@G@@    LX        X9,VDFS+SFN       . GET SUBCODE (MIN OR MAX INDEX)  @E@@@@ZF
)@@G@@          PIKRITE   MAX999            . SETUP ARG FETCH     @F@@@@      ZG
)@@G@@    LA,U      A2,1              . POST NEW LENGTH OF RESULT @E@@@@      ZH
)@@G@@    PUTANS    MAX999            . SETUP RESULT AREA   @D@@@@          LRZI
)@@G@@        R1,VDL+SRA        . GET ARG LENGTH@E@@@]          LA        A1,VZJ
)@@G@@DM+SLA        . GET RESULT MODE     @E@@@@          DL        A4,,*X7   ZK
)@@G@@        . GET FIRST VALUE     @F@@@@          DS        A4,R2           ZL
)@@G@@  . USE AS FIRST COMPARATOR   @C@@@@          JGD       R1,$+1          ZM
)@@G@@  . COUNT IT@F@@@@          J         MAX020            . SKIP AND COUNTZN
)@@G@@ NEXT VALUE @E@@@@MAX010    DL        A2,,*X7           . GET THE NEXT VZO
)@@G@@ALUE  @E@@@@          EX        COMPARE,A1        . COMPARE BY MODE     ZP
)@@G@@@G@@@@          DS        A2,R2             . ONLY IF EXECUTED TEST FAILZQ
)@@G@@S     @D@@@@MAX020    JGD       R1,MAX010         . KEEP GOING    @F@@@@ZR
)@@G@@          LA        A0,VDA+SLA        . RECOVER RESULT ADDRESS    @F@@@@ZS
)@@G@@          SR        R2,0,A0           . POST THE RESULT VALUES    @D@[@@ZT
)@@G@@          TEP,U     A1,DBLBIT         . DBL BIT SET?  @F@@@[          TNZU
)@@G@@DBL     A1                . DOUBLE PRECISION VALUE?   @G@@@@          SRZV
)@@G@@        R3,1,A0           . YES, STORE SECOND WORD ALSO     @E@@@@      ZW
)@@G@@    LA,U      A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR REG     @D@@@@MAX999    REZX
)@@G@@TURN                      . THAT'S IT     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. COMPARE VEZY
)@@G@@CTOR: INDEX WITH MODE; SKIP NI IF A2,A3 NOT DESIRED   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ZZ
)@@G@@COMPARE   EX        COMPSIN,X9        . MODSIN: COMPARE SINGLE WORDS    AA
)@@G@@@G@@@@          EX        COMPSFL,X9        . MODSFL: COMPARE SINGLE WORAB
)@@G@@DS    @G@@@@          LMJ       X11,COMPDIN       . MODDIN: COMPARE DOUBAC
)@@G@@LE INTEGER  @G@@@@          LMJ       X11,COMPDFL       . MODDFL: COMPARAD
)@@G@@E DOUBLE FLOATING @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. COMPARE SINGLE INTEGER, FLOATING; AE
)@@G@@@D@@@@. INDEX WITH 0=MIN 1=MAX; SKIP NI IF A2,A3 NOT DESIRED@[@@@@.     AF
)@@G@@@#@@@@COMPSIN,COMPSFL   @I@#@@          TLE       A4,R2             . MIAG
)@@G@@N FUNCTION: SKIP NI IF R2,R3 <= A4,A5     @H@@@#          TLE       A2,RAH
)@@G@@2             . MIN FUNCTION: SKIP NI IF R2 <= A4     @H@#@@          TGAI
)@@G@@        A4,R2             . MAX FUNCTION: SKIP NI IF R2,R3 > A4,A5@G@@@#AJ
)@@G@@          TG        A2,R2             . MAX FUNCTION: SKIP NI IF R2 > A4AK
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @#@@@@COMPDIN,COMPDFL   @E@@@@          DL        A4,A2     AL
)@@G@@        . DON'T TRASH A2,A3   @E@@@@          EX        SUBTRACT-2,A1   AM
)@@G@@  . FORM (A4,A5)-(R2,R3)@E@@@@          JNO       $+2               . SKAN
)@@G@@IP IF NO OVERFLOW @E@@@@          LN        A4,A4             . FLIP THEAO
)@@G@@ SIGN BIT   @F@@@@          JN        A4,*LESS,X9       . TAKE A2,A3 < RAP
)@@G@@2,R3 EXIT   @F@@@@          J         *GTR,X9           . TAKE A2,A3 >= AQ
)@@G@@R2,R3 EXIT  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@SUBTRACT  DAN       A4,R2             . MOAR
)@@G@@DDIN  @C@@@@          DFAN      A4,R2             . MODDFL  @[@@@@.     AS
)@@G@@@F@@@@. THIS TABLE SHOULD BE INDEXED BY THE FUNCTION CODE: 0 OR 1 FOR   AT
)@@G@@@ @@@@. MIN OR MAX, RESPECTIVELY.   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@LESS      J       AU
)@@G@@  1,X11             . A4,A5 < R2,R3 @D@@@@GTR       J         0,X11     AV
)@@G@@        . A4,A5 > R2,R3 @D@@@@          J         1,X11             . A4AW

)@@G@@ FILE OBTAINED, RECOVERY ENABLED    @[E U"EDITOR*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/     EW
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. ROUTINE TO PERFORM THE CSF$ FUNCTION: CSEX
)@@G@@F$(<IMAGE>).@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. THE VALUE RETURNED IS THE STATUS FROM CSEY
)@@G@@F$.   @[@@@@.     @#@[@@M$FUNCSF* ROUTINE @^@@@[M$FUNCSF* SUBROUTINE    EZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          PIKRITE   CSF999            . SETUP RIGHT ARG FETCH     FA
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LXI,U     A0,,X7            . GET ADDR IN H1@D@@@@      FB
)@@G@@    SSC       A0,18             . A0=(LEN,ADDR) @D@@@@          ER      FC
)@@G@@  ACSF$             . DO THE CSF    @F@@@@          CALL      M$RESULTINFD
)@@G@@T       . CREATE INTEGER RESULT     @ @@@@          JNZ       A5,CSF999 FE
)@@G@@@D@@@@          DS        A0,VD+SLA         . POST RESULT   @#@@@@CSF999FF
)@@G@@    RETURN  @]@@@@          . @#@@@@          END     ___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@FG
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@FH
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/         M$DEF   @[@@@@.     FI
)@@G@@@B@@@@. THIS ROUTINE PERFORMS THE CHR$ FUNCTION:@[@@@@.     @H@@@@.  CHRFJ
)@@G@@$(<INTEGER VECTOR>) CONVERTS THE INTEGER VECTOR TO A CHARACTER VECTOR,  FK
)@@G@@@H@@@@. ONE INTEGER TO ONE CHARACTER AT A TIME.  THIS ALLOWS STRINGS OF FL
)@@G@@ARBITRARY   @H@@@@. VALUES TO BE BUILT; HOWEVER, THE RESULTING STRING WIFM
)@@G@@LL BE TYPED AS ASCII.   @H@@@@. OF COURSE, THE RESULTING STRING MAY BE RFN
)@@G@@ETYPED AS FIELDATA VIA THE TFD$     @]@@@@. FUNCTION. @[@@@@.     @]@@@@FO
)@@G@@M$FUNCHR*   @#@#@@          ROUTINE @^@@@#          SUBROUTINE    @F@@@@FP
)@@G@@          PIKRITE   CHR999            . SET UP RIGHT ARG FETCH    @E@@@@FQ
)@@G@@          PUTANS    CHR999 MODASC     . SETUP RESULT AREA   @G@@@@      FR
)@@G@@    LR        R1,A2             . GET # OF CHARS TO FETCH & STORE @F@@@@FS
)@@G@@          LA        A2,A1             . GET WORD INDEX TO RESULT  @F@@@@FT
)@@G@@          LA        A3,M$XASS         . SETUP FOR ASCII STORE     @G@[@@FU
)@@G@@          LA,U      A1,CHRLOD         . GET ADDRESS OF LOAD ROUTINE     FV
)@@G@@@G@@@[          LA,U      A1,(LA A5,,*X7)   . GET ADDRESS OF LOAD ROUTINFW
)@@G@@E     @F@[@@          CALL      M$COPYSTR         . COPY A 'STRING' OF NFX
)@@G@@UMBERS@F@@@[          CALL      M$ITEMCOPY        . COPY A 'STRING' OF NFY
)@@G@@UMBERS@F@@@@          CALL      M$BLANKWORD       . BLANK OUT THE LAST WFZ
)@@G@@ORD   @#@@@@CHR999    RETURN  @]@[@@          . @E@[@@CHRLOD    LA      GA
)@@G@@  A5,0,*X7          . GET THE NEXT INTEGER@[@[@@.     @[@@@@/.    @B@@@@GB
)@@G@@. THIS ROUTINE PERFORMS THE INT$ FUNCTION.@[@@@@.     @G@@@@.  INT$(<CHAGC
)@@G@@R VECTOR>) RETURNS AN INTEGER VECTOR COMPRISED OF THE ASCII @B@@@@. VALUGD
)@@G@@ES OF THE CHARACTERS AS INTEGERS.   @[@@@@.     @#@]@@M$FUNINT* ROUTINE GE
)@@G@@@^@@@]M$FUNINT* SUBROUTINE    @E@@@@          PIKRITE   INT999          GF
)@@G@@  . SETUP ARG FETCH     @E@@@@          PUTANS    INT999 MODSIN     . SEGG
)@@G@@TUP RESULT AREA   @F@@@@          LA        A0,X7             . GET STRIGH
)@@G@@NG WORD INDEX     @F@@@@          LX        X7,A1             . GET INT GI
)@@G@@VECTOR ADDRESS    @G@@@@          LR        R1,A2             . GET THE GJ
)@@G@@# OF CHARS TO STORE     @F@@@@          LA        A1,M$XASL         . SEGK
)@@G@@TUP FOR ASCII FETCH     @H@[@@          LA,U      A3,INTSTOR        . GEGL
)@@G@@T ADDRESS OF INTEGER STORE ROUTINE  @H@@@[          LA,U      A3,(SA A5,GM
)@@G@@,*X7)   . GET ADDRESS OF INTEGER STORE ROUTINE  @G@[@@          CALL    GN
)@@G@@  M$COPYSTR         . COPY A STRING & STASH AS INTEGER@G@@@[          CAGO
)@@G@@LL      M$ITEMCOPY        . COPY A STRING & STASH AS INTEGER@D@@@@      GP
)@@G@@    LA,U      A5,0              . NO ERRORS     @E@@@@INT999    RETURN  GQ
)@@G@@                    . RETURN TO CALLER    @]@@@@          . @E@[@@INTSTOGR
)@@G@@R   SA        A5,0,*X7          . STASH THE INTEGER   @[@[@@.     @#@@@@GS
)@@G@@          END     ___@@@9*K^?T9*K^?V[@K^?X[40^?K*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/     GT
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. M$COMWAIT - ROUTINE TO PERFORM THE 'WAITGU
)@@G@@ <N>' COMMAND.    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@WAITLIMIT EQU       15*60           GV
)@@G@@  . MAXIMUM IS 15 MINUTES     @G@@@@TWAIT$LIMIT EQU     30*1000         GW
)@@G@@  . MAXIMUM FOR TWAIT$ IS 30 SECS   @[@@@@.     @#@[@@M$COMWAIT* ROUTINEGX
)@@G@@@^@@@[M$COMWAIT* SUBROUTINE   @F@@@@          CALL      M$MORECMD       GY
)@@G@@  . SCAN FOR MORE COMMAND     @E@@@@          JZ        A0,WAIT010      GZ
)@@G@@  . SKIP IF NO ARGUMENT @E@@@@          CALL      M$SCANINT         . SCHA
)@@G@@AN FOR THE INTEGER@ @@@@          JNZ       A5,WAIT999@D@@@@WAIT010   LAHB
)@@G@@        A5,PCL('ILLEGAL WAIT VALUE.')     @ @@@@          JN        A0,WHC
)@@G@@AIT999@H@@@@          JLE,U     A0,WAITLIMIT+1 WAIT999 . CHECK THE LIMITHD
)@@G@@ OF THE WAIT TIME @E@@@@          LA        A2,A0             . GET THE HE
)@@G@@VALUE HERE  @G@@@@          MSI,U     A2,1000           . TURN SECONDS IHF
)@@G@@NTO MILLISECONDS  @F@@@@WAIT020   LA,U      A1,TWAIT$LIMIT    . SET THE HG
)@@G@@MAX TWAIT$ TIME   @F@@@@          TG        A1,A2             . IS USER HH
)@@G@@AMOUNT GREATER?   @F@@@@          LA        A1,A2             . NO, USE HI
)@@G@@THE USER'S AMOUNT @F@@@@          TNZ       M$BREAK           . IS AN @@HJ
)@@G@@X C OUTSTANDING?  @F@@@@          ER        TWAIT$            . NO, DO THK
)@@G@@HE REQUEST AMOUNT @F@@@@          AN,U      A2,TWAIT$LIMIT    . SUBTRACTHL
)@@G@@ THE AMOUNT WAITED@D@@@@          JP        A2,WAIT020        . KEEP WAIHM
)@@G@@TING  @D@@@@          LA,U      A5,0              . POST NO ERRORS@^@@@@HN
)@@G@@WAIT999   RETURN        @]@@@@          . @#@@@@          END     ___@@@HO
)@@G@@^[BG(,G(2GD?@^@@@@CL\I--H19 ))C9>H1>IL-H))@#@@@@CL-GT4G(2HD\H-\G99@^@@@@HP
)@@G@@E[-I-*H9?H9$JC?^[KH--H14@^@@@@E[?GD,I))E[-I-*H9?H9$JC)@ @@@@E[*GD2H(-GT\HQ
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/         M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THIS ROUTINE IMPHR
)@@G@@LEMENTS THE 'STORAGE' COMMAND, WHICH PRINTS HOW @G@@@@. MUCH FREE STORAGHS
)@@G@@E IS AVAILABLE. THIS IS A DEBUGGING COMMAND TO CHECK  @H@@@@. TO SEE IF HT
)@@G@@THERE ARE ANY BUFFERS BEING LOST DURING A PARTICULAR COMMAND.     @[@@@@HU
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. IDEALLY, THE FREE STORAGE BEFORE A COMMAND SHOULD BE EQUALHV
)@@G@@ TO THE     @A@@@@. FREE STORAGE AFTER A COMMAND.     @[@@@@.     @^@]@@HW
)@@G@@M$COMSTORAGE* ROUTINE   @ @@@]M$COMSTORAGE* SUBROUTINE      @F@@@@AMTSIZHX
)@@G@@E   LOCAL                       . # OF WORDS IN FREE STORAGE@E@@@@AMTALLHY
)@@G@@OC  LOCAL                       . AMOUNT ALLOCATED    @G@@@@AMTTOTAL  LOHZ
)@@G@@CAL                       . TOTAL # OF WORDS IN STORAGE POOL@H@@@@      IA
)@@G@@    LA        A0,(1,M$BUFPOL)   . GET AN INDEX INTO THE BUFFER POOL     IB
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LA,U      A2,0              . INITIALIZE THE # OF FREE WIC
)@@G@@ORDS  @E@@@@AMT010    LA,H2     A1,0,A0           . GET THE FREE LINK   ID
)@@G@@@H@@@@AMT020    JZ        A1,AMT030         . IF NO MORE BUFFERS, GO TO IE
)@@G@@NEXT SIZE   @F@@@@          AA,H1     A2,0,A0           . ADD IN THE FIBIF
)@@G@@ONACCI SIZE @F@@@@          LA,H2     A1,1,A1           . LINK TO THE NEIG
)@@G@@XT BUFFER   @E@@@@          J         AMT020            . TRY THE NEXT BIH
)@@G@@UFFER @E@@@@AMT030    JGM,U     A0,M$PSGNXT-1 AMT010 . DO ALL SIZES     II
)@@G@@@F@@@@          SA        A2,AMTSIZE        . SAVE SIZE OF FREE STORAGE IJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A0,M$PSGNXT       . GET NEXT AVAILABLE ADDRESSIK
)@@G@@@E@@@@          AN        A0,M$COREPRMORG   . SUBTRACT THE ORIGIN @F@@@@IL
)@@G@@          SA        A0,AMTTOTAL       . SAVE THE TOTAL STORAGE    @F@@@@IM
)@@G@@          AN        A0,A2             . SUBTRACT THE FREE STORAGE @F@@@@IN
)@@G@@          SA        A0,AMTALLOC       . SAVE AMOUNT ALLOCATED     @D@@@@IO
)@@G@@          M$EOPEN   M$EPKT M$IMAGE    . BEGIN EDITING @E@@@@          E$IP
)@@G@@MSG     ('FREE: &  ALLOCATED: &  TOTAL: &'L)    @E@@@@          E$DECV  IQ
)@@G@@  AMTSIZE           . INSERT THE SIZE     @#@@@@          E$MSGR  @F@@@@IR
)@@G@@          E$DECV    AMTALLOC          . INSERT AMOUNT ALLOCATED   @#@@@@IS
)@@G@@          E$MSGR  @F@@@@          E$DECV    AMTTOTAL          . INSERT TIT
)@@G@@OTAL # OF WORDS   @C@@@@          M$EPRTX   . PRINT AND CLOSE EDITING   IU
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LA,U      A5,0              . NO ERRORS     @C@@@@      IV
)@@G@@    RETURN                      . ALL DONE@[@@@@.     @#@@@@          ENIW
)@@G@@D     ___@@@[@K^?R[@K^?S9*K^?T9*K^?V[@K^?X[40^?K*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/     IX
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE 'RETURN' COMMAND ESCAPES THE CURRENTIY
)@@G@@LY EXECUTING MACRO, UP  @^@@@@. TO THE NEXT LEVEL     @[@@@@.     @]@@@@IZ
)@@G@@M$COMRETURN*@#@[@@          ROUTINE @^@@@[          SUBROUTINE    @E@@@@JA
)@@G@@          LA,U      A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR FLAG    @E@@@@      JB
)@@G@@    TZ,H2     M$XQTMACRO        . IS THERE A MACRO?   @E@@@@          LMJC
)@@G@@J       X11,M$XQTPOPSTAK  . YES, POP THE STACK  @#@@@@          RETURN  JD
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @#@@@@          END     ___@@@C)) ^[*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/     JE
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. ROUTINE TO SET M$OPTS TO MASTER BIT NOTAJF
)@@G@@TION OF ANY OPTIONS SET @E@@@@. TIDE$ MUST BE OPEN AND POSITIONED AT FIRJG
)@@G@@ST CHAR IN OPTION @F@@@@. FIELD (IE: JUST PAST THE COMMA). IF M$COMMA ISJH
)@@G@@ CLEAR, NO OPTIONS@#@@@@. ARE SCANNED FOR.@[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         LAJI
)@@G@@        A0,<LEGAL OPTIONS>    @A@@@@.         LMJ       X11,M$COMOPTS   JJ
)@@G@@@ @@@@.         JNZ       A5,<ERROR>@ @@@@.         <A0 = OPTIONS SET>  JK
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @]@@@@M$COMOPTS*  @#@[@@          ROUTINE @^@@@[          SUJL
)@@G@@BROUTINE    @D@@@@LEGAL     LOCAL     1                 . LEGAL OPTIONS JM
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@          SA        A0,LEGAL          . SAVE LEGAL OPTJN
)@@G@@IONS  @E@@@@          LA,U      A5,0              . CLEAR OPTIONS SET   JO
)@@G@@@E@@@@          JEZ       M$COMMA OPT990    . RETURN IF NO OPTIONS@[@@@@JP
)@@G@@OPT010@G@@@@          T$CHAR    OPT990            . GET NEXT CHAR - QUITJQ
)@@G@@ IF NONE    @E@@@@          LA,U      A2,,A3            . GET FD CHAR INJR
)@@G@@ A2   @E@@@@          JE,U      A2,' ' OPT990     . QUIT IF BLANK ALSO  JS
)@@G@@@F@@@@          TLE,U     A2,'Z'+1          . SKIP IF NON ALPHABETIC    JT
)@@G@@@D@@@@          TLE,U     A2,'A'            . SKIP IF ALPHA @C@@@@      JU
)@@G@@    J         OPT900            . ERROR   @D@@@@          LA,U      A3,1JV
)@@G@@              . GET A BIT     @F@@@@          SSC       A3,' ',A2       JW
)@@G@@  . ALIGN THE BIT TO THE CHAR @G@@@@          AND       A3,LEGAL        JX
)@@G@@  . MASK WITH THE LEGAL OPTIONS     @H@@@@          JZ        A4,OPT900 JY
)@@G@@        . IF IT WENT AWAY, OPTION WAS ILLEGAL   @F@@@@          OR      JZ
)@@G@@  A4,A5             . PUT THEM ALL TOGETHER     @C@@@@          J       KA
)@@G@@  OPT010            . GET MORE@[@@@@.     @[@@@@OPT900@C@@@@          LAKB
)@@G@@        A5,PCL('ILLEGAL OPTION.')   @G@@@@          T$SKIP    -1        KC
)@@G@@        . BACK UP AND POINT AT THE CHAR   @F@@@@          T$COLN        KD
)@@G@@              . GET THE COLUMN POSITION   @E@@@@          CALL      M$ERKE
)@@G@@RMSGBLD       . BUILD THE MESSAGE   @D@@@@          J         OPT999    KF
)@@G@@        . TAKE AN EXIT  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. NORMAL EXIT - STASH THE OPTIKG
)@@G@@ONS FOUND   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@OPT990@D@@@@          SA        A5,M$OPTS KH
)@@G@@        . SET THEM HERE @E@@@@          LA        A0,A5             . REKI
)@@G@@TURN IN A0 ALSO   @C@@@@          LA,U      A5,0              . NO ERRORKJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@OPT999@#@@@@          RETURN  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@          END     KK
)@@G@@___@@@SREG$       @@@@]F*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/         M$DEF   @[@@@@.     KL
)@@G@@@ @@@@.         LOCAL VAR,VAR,VAR   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@M$COMLOCAL*       KM
)@@G@@  .   @#@]@@          ROUTINE @^@@@]          SUBROUTINE    @H@@@@LOCFLGKN
)@@G@@    LOCAL                       . NONZERO BEFORE ANY VARS ARE FOUND     KO
)@@G@@@D@@@@LOCNAM    LOCAL     2                 . NAME-LABEL    @F@@@@      KP
)@@G@@    SX        X11,LOCFLG        . SET NO SYMBOL FOUND FLAG  @F@@@@LOC010KQ
)@@G@@    CALL      M$SCANLIST        . SCAN A VARIABLE NAME LIST @D@@@@      KR
)@@G@@    JNZ       A5,LOC999         . SOME ERROR    @F@@@@          JZ      KS
)@@G@@  A4,LOC900         . TAKE NO MORE NAMES EXIT   @F@@@@          SZ      KT
)@@G@@  LOCFLG            . FOUND A NAME, CLEAR FLAG  @E@[@@          DS      KU
)@@G@@  A0,LOCNAM         . SAVE OVER TSRC CALL @D@[@@          CALL      M$MVKV
)@@G@@FIND          . LOOK IT UP    @E@[@@          JZ        A4,LOC050       KW
)@@G@@  . NOT FOUND, ENTER IT @E@[@@          L,H2      A2,M$XQTMACRO     . GEKX
)@@G@@T CURRENT PROC    @B@[@@          TNE       A2,A3             .   @F@[@@KY
)@@G@@          J         LOC010            . ALREADY LOCAL, IGNORE IT  @D@[@@KZ
)@@G@@LOC050    DL        A0,LOCNAM         . GET NAME AGAIN@F@@@[          CALA
)@@G@@LL      M$CDLEV           . GET THE CURRENT LEVEL     @E@[@@          L,LB
)@@G@@H2      A3,M$XQTMACRO     . GET CURRENT PROC    @D@[@@          CALL    LC
)@@G@@  M$MVLOCAL         . MAKE LOCAL    @H@@@[          CALL      M$DLI     LD
)@@G@@        . INSERT THE ITEM INTO THE DICTIONARY   @C@@@@          JNZ     LE
)@@G@@  A5,LOC999         . IF ERROR@D@@@@          J         LOC010          LF
)@@G@@  . LOOK FOR MORE @]@@@@          . @D@@@@LOC900    LA        A5,PCL('MILG
)@@G@@SSING VARIABLE NAME.')  @F@@@@          TNZ       LOCFLG            . DILH
)@@G@@D WE FIND ANY VARS?     @E@@@@          LA,U      A5,0              . YELI
)@@G@@S, CLEAR THE ERROR@#@@@@LOC999    RETURN  @]@@@@          . @B@@@@      LJ
)@@G@@    END                         .   ___@@@C@)@@L;G)@@[;C0@@<G@)@@GR'Y@@]LK
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/         M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. EVALUATE - ROUTILL
)@@G@@NE TO READ AND PRINT EXPRESSIONS UNTIL NULL LINE.     @[@@@@.     @#@[@@LM
)@@G@@M$COMEVAL* ROUTINE@^@@@[M$COMEVAL* SUBROUTINE   @F@@@@          CALL    LN
)@@G@@  M$SCANONOFF       . LOOK FOR AN 'ON' OR 'OFF' @D@@@@          JNZ     LO
)@@G@@  A5,CALC999        . QUIT ON ERRORS@E@@@@          LA        A1,M$CALCFLP
)@@G@@LAG     . GET CALCULATOR FLAG @F@@@@          SA        A0,M$CALCFLAG   LQ
)@@G@@  . POST NEW FLAG (0 OR 1)    @D@@@@          JP        A0,CALC999      LR
)@@G@@  . QUIT IF 0 OR 1@H@@@@          XOR,U     A1,1              . 'EVAL' CLS
)@@G@@OMMAND FLIPS CURRENT FLAG     @D@@@@          SA        A2,M$CALCFLAG   LT
)@@G@@  . POST NEW FLAG @C@@@@CALC999   RETURN                      . DONE    LU
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @#@@@@          END     ___@@@OTHER DATAPAC   SUBROUTINES NELV
)@@G@@EDED--NONE. @CCC@@C     FORTRAN LIBRARY SUBROUTI*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/     LW
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. 'ESCAPE ON' SET CXBESC IN CXFLAG IN THE LX
)@@G@@CURRENT MACRO EXECUTION FRAME.@H@@@@. 'ESCAPE OFF' CLEARS CXBESC IN CXFLLY
)@@G@@AG IN THE CURRENT MACRO EXECUTION FRAME.  @B@@@@. 'ESCAPE'  RETURNS TO KLZ
)@@G@@EYBOARD LEVEL.    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@M$COMESCAPE*        .   @#@[@@      MA
)@@G@@    ROUTINE @^@@@[          SUBROUTINE    @F@@@@          CALL      M$SCMB
)@@G@@ANONOFF       . LOOK FOR AN ON OR AN OFF  @D@@@@          JNZ       A5,EMC
)@@G@@SC999         . POST ERRORS   @I@@@@          JN        A0,ESC010       MD
)@@G@@  . IF NEGATIVE FLAG, BARE 'ESCAPE' COMMAND     @D@@@@          LA,U    ME
)@@G@@  A1,0              . ASSUME OFF    @D@@@@          TZ        A0        MF
)@@G@@        . WAS IT OFF?   @E@@@@          LA,U      A1,MXBESC         . NOMG
)@@G@@, ON SAYS ESCAPE  @C@@@@          LA        A5,PCL('NO MACRO ACTIVE')   MH
)@@G@@@A@@@@          LA,H2     A0,M$XQTMACRO   @D@@@@          JZ        A0,EMI
)@@G@@SC999         . TAKE AN ERROR @F@@@@          LA        A2,MXFB,A0      MJ
)@@G@@  . GET THE CURRENT FLAGS     @F@@@@          AND,U     A2,-MXBESC      MK
)@@G@@  . CLEAR THE 'ESCAPE' BIT    @I@@@@          OR,U      A1,,A3          ML
)@@G@@  . MERGE OTHER FLAGS WITH NEW 'ESCAPE' BIT     @E@@@@          SA      MM
)@@G@@  A2,MXFB,A0        . POST THE NEW BITS   @E@@@@          LA,U      A5,0MN
)@@G@@              . CLEAR THE ERROR REG @C@@@@          J         ESC999    MO
)@@G@@        . GO HOME @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. 'ESCAPE' COMMAND WITH NO ARGS     MP
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@ESC010@E@@@@          L,U       A5,0              . CLMQ
)@@G@@EAR ERROR FLAG    @]@@@@ESC020    . @E@@@@          TNZ,H2    M$XQTMACROMR
)@@G@@        . IS THERE A STACK ?  @D@@@@          J         ESC999          MS
)@@G@@  . NO : RETURN   @D@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$XQTPOPSTAK  . POP STACMT
)@@G@@K THEN@F@@@@          JZ        A5,ESC020         . IF NO ERROR TRY AGAIMU
)@@G@@N     @#@@@@ESC999    RETURN  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@          END     ___@@@MV
)@@G@@ANALYSIS' SESSION AT THE*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@]/         M$DEF   @[@@@].     MW
)@@G@@@E@@@]. THIS ROUTINE IS USED TO ERASE A LIST OF VARIABLES FROM THE@E@@@]MX
)@@G@@. USER SYMBOL TABLES.  CALLED ERASE VAR,VAR,VAR,VAR ...     @[@@@].     MY
)@@G@@@^@@@]M$COMERASE*         .   @#@A@]          ROUTINE @^@@@A          SUMZ
)@@G@@BROUTINE    @F@@@]ERSRTN    LOCAL     1                 . ADDRESS OF ERANA
)@@G@@SE ROUTINE  @E@@@]          LA        A0,OBL('M')       . GET LEGAL OPTINB
)@@G@@ONS   @E@@@]          LMJ       X11,M$COMOPTS     . CHECK THE OPTIONS   NC
)@@G@@@F@@@]          JNZ       A5,ERS999         . IF ERROR, TAKE QUICK EXIT ND
)@@G@@@G@@@]          LA,U      A1,ERSVAR         . DEFAULT ERASE IS FOR VARIANE
)@@G@@BLES  @F@@@]          TEP       A0,OBL('M')       . SKIP IF ERASING VARINF
)@@G@@ABLES @F@@@]          LA,U      A1,M$MDERASE      . NOW, LET'S ERASE A MNG
)@@G@@ACRO  @E@@@]          SA        A1,ERSRTN         . SAVE ERASE ROUTINE  NH
)@@G@@@G@@@]ERS010    CALL      M$SCANVLIST       . GET ANOTHER ITEM FROM THE NI
)@@G@@LIST  @D@@@]          JNZ       A5,ERS999         . QUIT ON ERRORS@G@@@]NJ
)@@G@@          JZ        A4,ERS999         . AND QUIT WHEN NO MORE NAMES     NK
)@@G@@@E@@@]          LMJ       X11,*ERSRTN       . CALL THE SUBROUTINE @E@@@]NL
)@@G@@          JZ        A5,ERS010         . LOOP IF NO ERRORS   @#@@@]ERS999NM
)@@G@@    RETURN  @]@@@]          . @A@@@]          .         ERASE A VARIABLENN
)@@G@@@]@@@]          . @H@@@]ERSVAR    JE,U      A3,$CAS('(') ERSVR . GO DO SNO
)@@G@@PECIAL ROUTINE IF SUBSCRIPTED @I@@@]          JNE,U     A3,$CAS('[') M$MNP
)@@G@@VERASE . DO NORMAL VAR ERASE IF NOT INDEXED     @#@A@]ERSVR     ROUTINE NQ
)@@G@@@^@@@AERSVR     SUBROUTINE    @#@@@]          SNOOPY  @H@@@]ERVVAL    LONR
)@@G@@CAL     2                 . VD OF VALUE BEING SUBSCRIPTED/INDEXED @E@@@]NS
)@@G@@ERVSUB    LOCAL     2                 . SUBSCRIPT/INDEX     @E@@@]ERVTMPNT
)@@G@@    LOCAL     2                 . TEMPORARY STORAGE   @D@@@]ERVLS     LONU
)@@G@@CAL     2                 . LOCAL STORAGE @D@@@]ERVCOL    EQUF      ERVLNV
)@@G@@S,,Q1         . COLUMN NUMBER @D@@@]ERVOPR    EQUF      ERVLS,,Q2       NW
)@@G@@  . ASCII OPERATOR@G@@@]ERVPTR    EQUF      ERVLS,,H2         . PTR TO FNX
)@@G@@INAL VALUE DESCRIPTOR   @G@@@]ERVVAR    EQUF      ERVLS+1,,H1       . PTNY
)@@G@@R TO ORIGINAL VALUE DESCRIPTOR@F@@@]          SA        A3,ERVOPR       NZ
)@@G@@  . SAVE THE ASCII OPERATOR   @H@@@]          CALL      M$MVFIND        OA
)@@G@@  . FIND THE VARIABLE IN THE USER TABLES  @C@@@]          LA        A5,POB
)@@G@@CL('UNDEFINED SYMBOL.') @C@ @]          JZ        A4,ERV900         . EROC
)@@G@@ROR   @C@@@           JZ        A2,ERV900         . ERROR   @D@@@]      OD
)@@G@@    DS        A0,ERVVAL         . SAVE THE VALUE@F@@@]          SA      OE
)@@G@@  A2,ERVVAR         . SAVE THE PTR TO THE VALUE @D@@@]          LA,U    OF
)@@G@@  A1,M$OPEROPENPA   . ASSUME '('    @E@@@]          LA        A3,ERVOPR OG
)@@G@@        . GET THE OPERATOR    @C@@@]          TE,U      A3,$CAS('(')    OH
)@@G@@  . CORRECT?@D@@@]          LA,U      A1,M$OPEROPENBR   . NO, IT WAS '['OI
)@@G@@@E@@@]          LA,U      A0,ERVVAL         . GET PTR TO VALUE    @E@@@]OJ
)@@G@@          CALL      M$SCANVARSUB      . SCAN FOR SUBSCRIPTS @C@@@]      OK
)@@G@@    JNZ       A5,ERV999         . ERROR   @G@@@]          DS        A0,EOL
)@@G@@RVSUB         . SAVE THE SCANNED SUBSCRIPTS     @F@@@]          SA      OM
)@@G@@  A3,ERVPTR         . SAVE FINAL DESCRIPTOR PTR @G@@@]          SA      ON
)@@G@@  A4,ERVCOL         . SAVE SUBSCRIPT COLUMN POSITION  @H@@@]          JEOO
)@@G@@,U      A2,M$OPEROPENPA ERV040 . SKIP IF ERASING TABLE SUBSCRIPTS @]@@@]OP
)@@G@@          . @D@@@]          .         ERASING ONE OR MORE LIST ELEMENTS OQ
)@@G@@@]@@@]          . @F@@@]          LA        A0,VDM+ERVVAL     . GET THE OR
)@@G@@MODE OF THE VALUE @H@@@#          TNOD      A0 ERV930         . IF ITEM OS
)@@G@@NOT A TABLE OR LIST, ERROR    @E@#@]          LA        A5,PCL('ITEM IS OT
)@@G@@NOT A LIST OR TABLE.')  @E@#@]          TE,U      A0,MODLST         . ISOU
)@@G@@ THE MODE CORRECT?@B@#@]          TNE,U     A0,MODTBL         .   @E@#@]OV
)@@G@@          LA,U      A5,0              . YES, KILL THE ERROR @D@#@]      OW
)@@G@@    JNZ       A5,ERV920         . ERROR IN VALUE@F@@@]          LA,U    OX
)@@G@@  A0,ERVVAL         . CHECK OUT THE INDEX VALUE @B@@@]          LA,U    OY
)@@G@@  A1,ERVSUB         .   @B@@@]          CALL      M$INDEXCHECK      .   OZ
)@@G@@@ @@@]          JNZ       A5,ERV910 @F@@@]          DS        A1,ERVSUB PA
)@@G@@        . POST UPDATED SUBSCRIPTS   @G@@@]          JE,U      A0,MODTBL PB
)@@G@@ERV010  . SKIP IF ERASING TABLE ENTRIES   @]@@@]          . @B@@@]      PC
)@@G@@    .         ERASING LIST ELEMENTS @]@@@]          . @F@@@]          LAPD
)@@G@@        A0,VDL+ERVVAL     . COMPUTE A NEW LIST LENGTH @E@@@]          ANPE
)@@G@@,U      A0,,A2            . MINUS SUBLIST LENGTH@E@@@]          SA      PF
)@@G@@  A0,VDL+ERVVAL     . POST NEW LENGTH     @F@@@]          ANU       A0,EPG
)@@G@@RVSUB         . A1 = REMAINING LIST LENGTH@F@@@]          SA        A1,EPH
)@@G@@RVTMP         . SAVE THE REMAINDER LENGTH @H@@@]          LSSL      A0,1PI
)@@G@@              . COMPUTE # WORDS NEEDED IN NEW LIST    @C@@@]          PGPJ
)@@G@@ET                        . GET THEM@ @@@]          JNZ       A5,ERV910 PK
)@@G@@@E@@@]          LXI,U     A1,VDSIZE         . SET THE INCREMENT   @F@@@]PL
)@@G@@          LA        A0,VDA+ERVVAL     . GET THE OLD LIST ADDRESS  @C@@@]PM
)@@G@@          SA        A0,ERVTMP+1       . SAVE IT @F@@@]          SA      PN
)@@G@@  A1,VDA+ERVVAL     . POST NEW LIST ADDRESS     @D@@@]          LXI,U   PO
)@@G@@  A0,VDSIZE         . SET LIST INCR @G@@@]          LA        A2,A1     PP
)@@G@@        . GET DESTINATION ADDRESS IN A2   @E@^@]          LA,U      A3,(PQ
)@@G@@DS A4,VD,*A2) . GET EXECUTE ADDR    @E@@@^          LA        A3,M$X72S PR
)@@G@@        . GET STORE INSTR     @E@^@]          LA,U      A1,(DL A4,VD,*A0PS
)@@G@@) . GET EXECUTE ADDR    @D@@@^          LA        A1,M$X72L         . GEPT
)@@G@@T LOAD INSTR@F@@@]          LR        R1,ERVSUB         . GET INITIAL COPU
)@@G@@PY LENGTH   @F@#@]          CALL      M$COPYSTR         . COPY SOME LISTPV
)@@G@@ ELEMENTS   @F@@@#          CALL      M$ITEMCOPY        . COPY SOME LISTPW
)@@G@@ ELEMENTS   @D@@@]          LR        R1,ERVSUB+1       . GET SKIP COUNTPX
)@@G@@@F@#@]          CALL      M$SKIPSTR         . SKIP SOME LIST ELEMENTS   PY
)@@G@@@F@@@#          CALL      M$ITEMSKIP        . SKIP SOME LIST ELEMENTS   PZ
)@@G@@@E@@@]          LR        R1,ERVTMP         . GET REMAINDER LENGTH@F@#@]QA
)@@G@@          CALL      M$COPYSTR         . COPY SOME LIST ELEMENTS   @F@@@#QB
)@@G@@          CALL      M$ITEMCOPY        . COPY SOME LIST ELEMENTS   @G@@@]QC
)@@G@@          LA        A3,ERVVAR         . GET THE ORIGINAL VARIABLE PTR   QD
)@@G@@@F@@@]          LA        A1,VDAW+ERVVAL    . GET THE NEW ACCESS WORD   QE
)@@G@@@G@@@]          LA        A2,ERVPTR         . GET THE LAST DESCRIPTOR PTQF
)@@G@@R     @F@@@]          SA        A1,VDAW,A2        . POST THE NEW ACCESS QG
)@@G@@WORD  @E@@@]          TNE,U     A2,ERVVAL         . DID WE DO A NOP?    QH
)@@G@@@I@@@]          SA        A1,MVDAW,A3       . YES, POST ACCESS WORD IN VQI
)@@G@@ARIABLE DESCRI    @G@@@]          LA        A0,ERVTMP+1       . RECOVER QJ
)@@G@@OLD LIST BUFFER ADDR    @D@@@]          LA,U      A5,0              . KIQK
)@@G@@LL ERRORS   @C@@@]          JZ        A0,ERV999         . ALL DONE@F@@@]QL
)@@G@@          PREL                        . RELEASE OLD LIST BUFFER   @C@@@]QM
)@@G@@          J         ERV999            . DONE    @]@@@]          . @D@@@]QN
)@@G@@          .         ERASE SOME INDEXED TABLE ENTRIES  @]@@@]          . QO
)@@G@@@F@@@]ERV010    AA,U      A1,1              . MAKE THE INDEX ORIGIN ONE QP
)@@G@@@E@@@]          SA        A1,ERVSUB         . POST NEW SUBSCRIPT  @E@@@]QQ
)@@G@@          LA,U      A1,ERVSUB         . CREATE A DESCRIPTOR @ @@@]      QR
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,MODSIN @^@@@]          LXI,U     A1,1@A@@@]          SAQS
)@@G@@        A0,VDM+ERVTMP   @A@@@]          SA        A1,VDAW+ERVTMP  @F@@@]QT
)@@G@@          J         ERV030            . START SEARCH & DELETE LOOP@D@@@]QU
)@@G@@ERV020    SA        A2,ERVSUB+1       . POST COUNT    @E@@@]          LAQV
)@@G@@,U      A0,ERVVAL         . GET THE VALUE PTR   @E@@@]          LA,U    QW
)@@G@@  A1,ERVTMP         . GET THE INDEX PTR   @G@@@]          CALL      M$SSQX
)@@G@@ENTRY         . FIND THE ENTRY FOR THIS INDEX   @ @@@]          JNZ     QY
)@@G@@  A5,ERV910 @D@@@]          LA        A5,PCL('INDEX OUT OF RANGE!')     QZ
)@@G@@@ @@@]          JZ        A2,ERV910 @E@@@]          LA,U      A1,,A2    RA
)@@G@@        . GET NODE ADDRESS    @G@@@]          CALL      M$SSNDELETE     RB
)@@G@@  . DELETE THE NODE FROM THE TABLE  @B@@@]          JNZ       A5,ERV910 RC
)@@G@@        .   @E@@@]          LA        A2,ERVSUB+1       . RECOVER LOOP CRD
)@@G@@OUNT  @G@@@]ERV030    JGD       A2,ERV020         . COUNT ENTRIES, LOOP RE
)@@G@@IF MORE     @C@@@]          J         ERV999            . DONE    @]@@@]RF
)@@G@@          . @C@@@]          .         ERASING TABLE SUBSCRIPTS    @]@@@]RG
)@@G@@          . @G@@@]ERV040    LA        A2,VDA+ERVSUB     . ASSUME A LIST RH
)@@G@@OF SUBSCRIPTS     @D@@@]          LXI,U     A2,VDSIZE         . GET THE RI
)@@G@@INDEX @E@@@]          LA        A3,VDL+ERVSUB     . = # OF SUBSCRIPTS   RJ
)@@G@@@F@@@]          LA        A0,VDM+ERVSUB     . GET THE SUBSCRIPT MODE    RK
)@@G@@@F@@@]          JE,U      A0,MODLST ERV060  . IF LIST, WE'RE SET TO GO  RL
)@@G@@@F@@@]          LA,U      A2,ERVSUB         . A SINGLE SUBSCRIPT IS ALL RM
)@@G@@@D@@@]          LA,U      A3,1              . DEFAULT COUNT @F@@@]      RN
)@@G@@    J         ERV060            . GO DELETE THE SUBSCRIPT   @D@@@]ERV050RO
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,ERVVAL         . GET THE VALUE @F@@@]          LA,U    RP
)@@G@@  A1,VD,*A2         . GET THE NEXT SUBSCRIPT    @F@@@]          DS      RQ
)@@G@@  A2,ERVTMP         . POST THE INDEX & COUNT    @E@@@]          CALL    RR
)@@G@@  M$SSDELETE        . DELETE THE SUBSCRIPT@ @@@]          JNZ       A5,ERS
)@@G@@RV910 @F@@@]          DL        A2,ERVTMP         . RECOVER INDEX & COUNRT
)@@G@@T     @G@@@]ERV060    JGD       A3,ERV050         . COUNT SUBSCRIPTS & LRU
)@@G@@OOP IF MORE @C@@@]          J         ERV999            . DONE    @]@@@]RV
)@@G@@          . @C@@@]          .         ERROR IN VARIABLE NAME LIST @]@@@]RW
)@@G@@          . @F@@@]ERV900    LA        A0,M$SCANCOLUMN   . GET THE COLUMNRX
)@@G@@ SCANNED AT @B@@@]          J         ERV990            .   @E@@@]ERV910RY
)@@G@@    LA        A0,ERVCOL         . RECOVER COLUMN #    @ @@@]          J RZ
)@@G@@        ERV990    @F@@@]ERV920    LA        A0,ERVCOL         . ERROR INSA
)@@G@@ VALUE (COL-2)    @B@@@]          AN,U      A0,2              .   @ @@@#SB
)@@G@@          J         ERV990    @E@@@#ERV930    LA        A5,PCL('ITEM IS SC
)@@G@@NOT A LIST OR TABLE.')  @D@@@#          J         ERV920            . ERSD
)@@G@@ROR IN VALUE@]@@@]          . @F@@@]ERV990    CALL      M$ERRMSGBLD     SE
)@@G@@  . BUILD AN ERROR MESSAGE    @C@@@]ERV999    RETURN                    SF
)@@G@@  . ALL DONE@]@@@]          . @B@@@]          END                       SG
)@@G@@  .   ___@@@@ @@@]          JNZ       A5,ERV910 @E@@@]          LXI,U   SH
)@@G@@  A1,VDSIZE         . SET THE INCREMENT   @F@@@]*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@C@B      SI
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @]@C@BM$COMEDIT*. @#@C@BM$EDITMACRO*.     @C@C@B          L SJ
)@@G@@        A5,NOEDPCW        . NO EDIT @D@C@B          J         0,X11     SK
)@@G@@        . AND RETURN    @B@C@BNOEDPCW   PCW       ;                 .   SL
)@@G@@@B@C@B          'CANNOT CALL EDITOR FROM EDITOR'@B@C@B          END     SM
)@@G@@                    .   @#@@@C/         M$DEF   @[@@@C.     @A@@@C. M$EDSN
)@@G@@ITMACRO - EDIT THE MACRO NAME.@C@@@C. M$COMEDIT - CALL EDITOR ON SCANNEDSO
)@@G@@ FILENAME.  @[@@@C.     @^@@@C.  LMJ  X11,M$EDITMACRO @^@@@C.  A5 = ERROSP
)@@G@@R PCW OR 0  @B@@@C.  A4 = 1 IF EDITING COMPLETED, 0 IF NOT. @B@@@C.  M$RSQ
)@@G@@EOF SET IF EDITOR RECEIVED HARD EOF.@[@@@C.     @ @@@C. DEFINE EDITOR LISR
)@@G@@NK BITS     @[@@@C.     @D@@@CELBNOS    EQU       BM(0)             . NOSS
)@@G@@ SIGNON     @C@@@CELBNOC    EQU       BM(1)             . NO CSF$ @F@@@CST
)@@G@@ELBZOR    EQU       BM(2)             . ZERO ORIGIN LINE NUMBERING@D@@@CSU
)@@G@@ELBALR    EQU       BM(3)             . ALLOW RECOVERY@F@@@CELBICM    EQSV
)@@G@@U       BM(4)             . INITIAL COMMAND SUPPLIED  @[@@@C.     @D@@@CSW
)@@G@@M$COMEDIT* LA,U     A0,1              . OPTIONS FLAG  @C@@@C          LASX
)@@G@@        A5,PCL('COMMAND DISABLED.') @^@@@C          J         EDIT@E@@@CSY
)@@G@@M$EDITMACRO* LA,U   A0,0              . NO OPTIONS FLAG     @E@@@C      SZ
)@@G@@    LA        A5,PCL('COMMAND ILLEGAL FROM KEYBOARD.')@#@F@CEDIT      ROTA
)@@G@@UTINE @^@@@FEDIT      SUBROUTINE    @B@@@CEDTINFOR  LOCAL     28        TB
)@@G@@        .   @F@@@C          JEZ       M$EDITORLINK EDT999 . IF NO LINKAGTC
)@@G@@E, ERROR OFF@F@@@C          JZ        A0,EDT010         . SKIP IF NO OPTTD
)@@G@@ION SCAN    @E@@@C          LA        A0,BSL(25,0)      . GET ALL OPTIONTE
)@@G@@S MASK@F@@@C          CALL      M$COMOPTS         . CHECK OUT ANY OPTIONTF
)@@G@@S     @ @@@C          JNZ       A5,EDT999 @E@@@CEDT010    SA        A0,ETG
)@@G@@DTINFOR       . POST THE OPTIONS    @G@@@C          DL        A0,DPLR(+(TH
)@@G@@0,1,6,,2,1),'ED'L) . INITIALIZE THE INFOR @C@@@C          DS        A0,ETI
)@@G@@DTINFOR+1     . POST    @G@@@C          CALL      M$SCANFILE        . SCTJ
)@@G@@AN THE COMMAND FOR THE SPEC   @E@@@C          JNZ       A5,EDT999       TK
)@@G@@  . ERROR OFF ON ERRORS @G@@@C          LA,U      A0,M$ELT$         . GETL
)@@G@@T THE SCANNED FILENAME PACKET @G@@@C          LA,U      A1,EDTINFOR+3   TM
)@@G@@  . GET THE STARTING PLACE IN INFOR @D@D@C          LA,U      A2,0101   TN
)@@G@@        . THE SPEC #    @D@E@D          LA,U      A2,01             . THTO
)@@G@@E SPEC #    @D@@@E          LA,U      A2,0101           . THE SPEC #    TP
)@@G@@@F@@@C          CALL      ELT$INFOR         . TRANSFER ELT$ TO INFOR    TQ
)@@G@@@F@@@C          LA,U      A0,EDTINFOR       . MAKE AN INFOR ACCESS WORD TR
)@@G@@@D@@@C          LXI,U     A0,3,A1           . SET THE LENGTH@F@@@C      TS
)@@G@@    LA,U      A1,ELBNOS+ELBALR  . NO SIGNON + ALLOW RECOVER @E@@@C      TT
)@@G@@    CALL      *M$EDITORLINK     . LINK TO THE EDITOR  @F@@@C          CATU
)@@G@@LL      M$IALL            . RESET CONTINGENCY HANDLER @C@@@C          JNTV
)@@G@@Z       A5,EDT999         . ERROR   @E@@@C          TNE,U     A1,2      TW
)@@G@@        . HARD EOF RETURN?    @E@@@C          SA        A1,M$REOF       TX
)@@G@@  . YES, POST THE FLAG  @F@@@C          LA,U      A4,1              . ASTY
)@@G@@SUME EDITING COMPLETED  @D@@@C          TE,U      A1,0              . NOTZ
)@@G@@RMAL STATUS @F@@@C          LA,U      A4,0              . NO, CLEAR COMPUA
)@@G@@LETION FLAG @#@@@CEDT999    RETURN  @]@@@C          . @#@@@C          ENUB
)@@G@@D     ___@@@C8@@@^/K@ SWC8@@@#/K@ SWC8@@@]/K@ SWC8@@@[/K@ SWC@)  )[4I@@FUC
)@@G@@C@)  Z[4I@@F/\) OYC)) ^[*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/         M$DEF   @[@@@@.     UD
)@@G@@@^@@@@. PROCESS CSF$ COMMAND  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. THE COMMAND SYNTAX IS:UE
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @#@@@@.  *<CSF$ IMAGE>  @[@@@@.     @#@]@@M$COMCSF* ROUTINE UF
)@@G@@@^@@@]M$COMCSF* SUBROUTINE    @F@@@@CSFTMP    LOCAL     2               UG
)@@G@@  . A0 BEFORE AND AFTER CSF$  @G@@@@          M$EOPEN   M$EPKT M$IMAGE  UH
)@@G@@  . OPEN EDITING FOR FIELDATA LINE  @C@@@@          E$CHAR    '@'       UI
)@@G@@        . EDIT @  @]@@@@STR020    . @F@@@@          T$CHAR    STR030    UJ
)@@G@@        . GET NEXT CHAR, EOF STR030 @D@@@@          E$CHAR    0,A3,U    UK
)@@G@@        . EDIT CHARACTER@B@@@@          J         STR020            .   UL
)@@G@@@]@@@@STR030    . @C@@@@          E$MSG     (' . &  ')        . END IT  UM
)@@G@@@D@@@@          E$WRDN                      . GET WORD COUNT@D@@@@      UN
)@@G@@    LSSL      A0,18             . MOVE TO H1    @E@@@@          LXM     UO
)@@G@@  A0,M$IMAGE        . GET IMAGE ADDRESS   @D@@@@          SA        A0,CUP
)@@G@@SFTMP         . SAVE A0 BEFORE@F@@@@          ER        CSF$            UQ
)@@G@@  . PASS STATEMENT TO EXEC    @D@@@@          SA        A0,CSFTMP+1     UR
)@@G@@  . SAVE A0 AFTER @D@@@@          L,U       A5,0              . SET NO EUS
)@@G@@RROR  @E@@@@          JZ        A0,STR999         . IF NO ERROR CONTINUEUT
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A2,M$XQTMACRO     . GET CURRENT MACRO ENTRY   UU
)@@G@@@F@@@@          $IF       EDPROCS           . SUPPORTING EDITOR PROCS?  UV
)@@G@@@E@@@@          JZ        A2,STR040         . SKIP IF NOT IN ONE  @H@@@@UW
)@@G@@          TZ        M$EDPROCS         . DOES THIS PROCESSOR SUPPORT ED PUX
)@@G@@ROCS? @F@@@@          TNZ       MXPF,A2           . YES, IS THIS AN ED PUY
)@@G@@ROC?  @F@@@@          J         STR999            . NO, DON'T CAUSE ERROUZ
)@@G@@RS    @D@@@@          $ELSE                       . NO PROC CODE  @H@@@@VA
)@@G@@          JNZ       A2,STR999         . IF IN A MACRO, DON'T CAUSE MESSAVB
)@@G@@GES   @#@@@@          $ENDF   @[@@@@STR040@D@@@@          DL        A0,CVC
)@@G@@SFTMP         . GET CSF WORDS @F@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$ERRCSF    VD
)@@G@@  . YES, DIAGNOSE THE ERROR   @D@@@@          LA,U      A5,0            VE
)@@G@@  . NO ERRORS     @]@@@@STR999    . @B@@@@          M$ECLOSE            VF
)@@G@@        .   @#@@@@          RETURN  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          END     VG
)@@G@@                    .   ___@@@'^@^Q(CC,@@@[^)^O[*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/     VH
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THESE ROUTINES COMPILE THE ALTERNATION CVI
)@@G@@ONTROL STRUCTURE.  THE  @A@@@@. FORMAT OF THIS STRUCTURE IS :     @[@@@@VJ
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@.         IF <EXPRESSION>     @^@@@@.           (BLOCK1)    VK
)@@G@@@#@@@@.         ELSE    @^@@@@.           (BLOCK2)    @#@@@@.         ENVL
)@@G@@DIF   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. IF THE EXPRESSION EVALUATES TO A TRUE VALUE BLVM
)@@G@@OCK1 IS EXECUTED  @F@@@@. AND BLOCK2 IS SKIPPED.  IF FALSE BLOCK1 IS SKIVN
)@@G@@PPED AND BLOCK2   @E@@@@. IS EXECUTED.  THE ELSE AND BLOCK2 ARE OF COURSVO
)@@G@@E OPTIONAL. @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. COMPILE 'IF' STATEMENT@[@@@@VP
)@@G@@.     @#@#@@M$CMPIF*  ROUTINE @^@@@#M$CMPIF*  SUBROUTINE    @E@@@@      VQ
)@@G@@    PUSH      IFF900            . PUSH ONTO STACK     @F@[@@          SDVR
)@@G@@FOGA    M$OUTPACKET       . GET ADDRESS OF IF STMT    @F@]@[          LAVS
)@@G@@        A1,PSNWA+M$OUTPACKET . GET ADDRESS OF IF STMT @F@@@]          LAVT
)@@G@@        A1,PSNWA+M$CMPPKT . GET ADDRESS OF IF STMT    @B@@@@          L VU
)@@G@@        A0,M$YLIN         .   @E@@@@          LXI,U     A0,MSGIFF       VV
)@@G@@  . SET TYPE TO 'IF'    @E@@@@          DS        A0,MSSTAK         . STVW
)@@G@@ORE ONTO STACK    @D@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$CMPOUTPUT   . OUTPUT IVX
)@@G@@MAGE  @ @@@@          J         IFF999    @D@@@@IFF900    LA        A5,MVY
)@@G@@$CPSOVR       . STACK OVERFLOW@#@@@@IFF999    RETURN  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@VZ
)@@G@@. COMPILE 'ELSE'  @[@@@@.     @#@#@@M$CMPELSE* ROUTINE@^@@@#M$CMPELSE* SWA
)@@G@@UBROUTINE   @#@@@@ELSTEMP   LOCAL   @B@@@@          L,U       A0,MSGIFF WB
)@@G@@        .   @E@@@@          TE        A0,MSTYPE         . GET STACKTOP IWC
)@@G@@TEM   @E@@@@          J         ELS910            . NO - STRUCTURE ERRORWD
)@@G@@@F@[@@          SDFOGA    M$OUTPACKET       . GET ADDRESS 'ELSE' IMAGE  WE
)@@G@@@G@]@[          LA        A1,PSNWA+M$OUTPACKET . GET ADDRESS OF 'ELSE' IWF
)@@G@@MAGE  @G@@@]          LA        A1,PSNWA+M$CMPPKT . GET ADDRESS OF 'ELSEWG
)@@G@@' IMAGE     @F@@@@          L         A0,MSMSAD         . GET 'IF' STMT WH
)@@G@@ADDRESS     @D@@@@          S         A0,ELSTEMP        . SAVE IT TEMP  WI
)@@G@@@B@@@@          L         A0,M$YLIN         .   @E@@@@          LXI,U   WJ
)@@G@@  A0,MSGELS         . SET STACKTOP TO ELSE@B@@@@          DS        A0,MWK
)@@G@@SSTAK         .   @D@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$CMPOUTPUT   . OUTPUT IWL
)@@G@@MAGE  @D@@@@          JNZ       A5,ELS999         . IF ERROR SKIP @G@[@@WM
)@@G@@          SDFOGA    M$OUTPACKET       . GET ADDRESS IMAGE AFTER 'ELSE'  WN
)@@G@@@H@]@[          LA        A1,PSNWA+M$OUTPACKET . GET ADDRESS IMAGE AFTERWO
)@@G@@ 'ELSE'     @G@@@]          LA        A1,PSNWA+M$CMPPKT . GET ADDRESS IMWP
)@@G@@AGE AFTER 'ELSE'  @D@@@@          L         A2,ELSTEMP        . RECOVER WQ
)@@G@@STACK @G@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$CMPUPDATE   . POINT 'IF' AT IMAGE WR
)@@G@@AFTER 'ELSE'@E@@@@          J         ELS999            . RETURN TO COMPWS
)@@G@@ILER  @F@@@@ELS910    LMJ       X11,M$ERRMSGCMP   . GENERATE ERROR MESSAWT
)@@G@@GE    @#@@@@ELS999    RETURN  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@. COMPILE 'ENDIF' @[@@@@WU
)@@G@@.     @^@#@@M$CMPENDIF* ROUTINE     @^@@@#M$CMPENDIF* SUBROUTINE  @B@@@@WV
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,MSGELS         .   @E@@@@          TNE       A0,MWW
)@@G@@STYPE         . STACK TOP ELSE ?    @C@@@@          J         EIF010    WX
)@@G@@        . YES     @D@@@@          L,U       A0,MSGIFF         . STACK TOWY
)@@G@@P IF ?@B@@@@          TE        A0,MSTYPE         .   @D@@@@          J WZ
)@@G@@        EIF910            . NO - OOPS     @F@[@@EIF010    SDFOGA    M$OUXA
)@@G@@TPACKET       . GET ADDRESS OF 'END' STMT @G@]@[EIF010    LA        A1,PXB
)@@G@@SNWA+M$OUTPACKET . GET ADDRESS OF 'END' STMT    @F@@@]EIF010    LA      XC
)@@G@@  A1,PSNWA+M$CMPPKT . GET ADDRESS OF 'END' STMT @B@@@@          L       XD
)@@G@@  A2,MSMSAD         .   @F@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$CMPUPDATE   . POXE
)@@G@@INT IF OR ELSE AT ENDIF @D@@@@          JNZ       A5,EIF999         . IFXF
)@@G@@ ERROR SKIP @B@@@@          POP       1                 .   @D@@@@      XG
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,M$CMPOUTPUT   . OUTPUT IMAGE  @E@@@@          J       XH
)@@G@@  EIF999            . RETURN TO COMPILER  @F@@@@EIF910    LMJ       X11,XI
)@@G@@M$ERRMSGCMP   . GENERATE ERROR MESSAGE    @#@@@@EIF999    RETURN  @[@@@@XJ
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@          LITS                        .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@XK
)@@G@@MSGIFF    'IF&ELSE\ENDIF&'            .   @B@@@@MSGELS    'ELSE&&'      XL
)@@G@@              .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          END                       XM
)@@G@@  .   ___@@@ MED$$RECOVRY,///1000 . MED$$RECOVRY@CAT    016118ALAN*MED$$XN
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@A@@@[@RUN,A AKS,016118ALAN,ALAN,30,999   @]@#@[@FREE TPF$  XO
)@@G@@@#@#@]@ASG,A EDRLIB     @#@#@]@USE ASM$PF,EDRLIB@^@#@[@ASG,T TPF$.,///99XP
)@@G@@99    @^@@@^@ASG,AX MACRO//EFS.     @[@^@#@WS,FC@#@ @^@WS,FC MACRO.     XQ
)@@G@@@[@@@ @WS,FT@ @@@#@LIB.USE,A ASM$PF,MAP$PF,RLIB.@#@^@[@ASG,A MACRO.     XR
)@@G@@@#@@@[@COPY,P MACRO.    @[@@@[@FLIST@]@@@[@PACK,P     @]@@@[@PRT,TL     XS
)@@G@@@]@@@^@SAVE,LP    @[@ @^@WS,D ___@@@    009   00000392955000035043021024XT
)@@G@@045032009041020016036034030032168264270   @O@@@@284278255205227280253267XU
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@#/         M$DEF   @[@@@#.     @C@@@#. M$CORETMPGET - RXV
)@@G@@OUTINE TO GET TEMPORARY CORE. @[@@@#.     @^@@@#.  A0 = # WORDS DESIRED XW
)@@G@@@^@@@#.  LMJ  X11,M$CORETMPGET@^@@@#.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @^@@@#.  A0 XX
)@@G@@= # WORDS OBTAINED@ @@@#.  A1 = (# WORDS, ADDRESS)    @[@@@#.     @ @^@#XY
)@@G@@M$CORETMPGET* ROUTINE A2,A3,A4@A@@@^M$CORETMPGET* SUBROUTINE A2,A3,A4   XZ
)@@G@@@F@@@#          AU        A0,NEXTD          . FIND NEW LAST ADDRESS     YA
)@@G@@@H@@@^          JZ        A0,TSG020         . IF REQUEST ZERO, RETURN CUYB
)@@G@@RRENT ADDR  @H@@@#          JNE       A1,A0 TSG020      . IF NEXTD NONZEYC
)@@G@@RO, USE CURRENT STACK   @F@@@#          SA        A0,NEXTD          . SAYD
)@@G@@VE REQUESTED WORD COUNT @F@@@^          LA        A0,M$DSTMAX       . GEYE
)@@G@@T MAXIMUM STACK SIZE    @F@^@#          PGET      DSTMAX            . GEYF
)@@G@@T A NEW TEMP DATA STACK @E@^@#          JNZ       A5,TSG999         . GOYG
)@@G@@ HOME ON ERRORS   @F@@@^          M$PGET    TSG999            . GET A NEYH
)@@G@@W TEMP DATA STACK @F@@@#          SA        A1,SZFRD          . SAVE SIZYI
)@@G@@E,BASE ADDRESS    @E@@@#          LA,U      A1,,A1            . CLEAR INYJ
)@@G@@CREMENT     @H@^@#          AU        A1,A0             . BASE ADDR + # YK
)@@G@@WORDS = LAST ADDRESS+1  @H@@@^          AU        A1,SIZED          . BAYL
)@@G@@SE ADDR + # WORDS = LAST ADDRESS+1  @F@@@#          SA        A2,LASTD  YM
)@@G@@        . POST FOR OVERFLOW CHECK   @F@@@#          LA        A0,NEXTD  YN
)@@G@@        . RECOVER REQ. WORD COUNT   @F@@@#          SA        A1,NEXTD  YO
)@@G@@        . POST NEXT AVAIL ADDRESS   @F@@@#          AU        A0,NEXTD  YP
)@@G@@        . A1 = NEXT AVAIL ADDRESS   @F@@@#TSG020    L         A5,PCL('TEYQ
)@@G@@MPORARY STACK OVERFLOW') . GET ERROR@D@@@#          TG        A1,LASTD  YR
)@@G@@        . WAS THERE ENUF@F@@@#          J         TSG999            . NOYS
)@@G@@ - TAKE ERROR RETURN    @E@@@#          LXI       A1,NEXTD          . GEYT
)@@G@@T ITS BASE ADDRESS@G@@@#          SA        A1,NEXTD          . SAVE NEXYU
)@@G@@T AVAILABLE ADDRESS     @E@@@#          SSL       A1,18             . MOYV
)@@G@@VE BASE TO H2     @F@@@#          LXI,U     A1,0,A0           . SET INCRYW
)@@G@@EMENT WITH LENGTH @E@@@#          L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERYX
)@@G@@ROR FLAG    @#@@@#TSG999    RETURN  @[@@@#.     @C@@@#. M$CORETMPALL - RYY
)@@G@@ELEASE ALL TEMPORARY STORAGE. @E@@@#. M$CORETMPREL - RELEASE TEMPORARY SYZ
)@@G@@TORAGE UP UNTIL A0.     @[@@@#.     @#@@@#M$CORETMPALL*     @E@@@#      ZA
)@@G@@    LA        A0,FRSTD          . GET FIRST AVAIL     @^@@@#M$CORETMPRELZB
)@@G@@*       .   @C@@@#          LA,U      A0,,A0            . CLEAR H1@E@@@#ZC
)@@G@@          LA,U      A5,0              . ASSUME NO ERRORS    @F@@@#      ZD
)@@G@@    TZ        A0                . IS RELEASED ADDRESS ZERO? @G@@@#      ZE
)@@G@@    TLE       A0,LASTD          . NO, CHECK REAL STACK LIMITS     @F@@@#ZF
)@@G@@          TLE       A0,FRSTD          . SKIP NI IF ADDRESS IS OK  @F@@@#ZG
)@@G@@          LA        A5,RELIAD         . BAD ADDRESS; GET ERROR PCW@E@@@#ZH
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,0,X11          . RETURN ON ERRORS    @E@@@#      ZI
)@@G@@    SA        A0,NEXTD          . FOR NEXT CALLER     @C@@@#          J ZJ
)@@G@@        0,X11             . RETURN  @[@@@#.     @#@@@#          LITS    ZK
)@@G@@@H@@@#RELIAD    PCW       'ATTEMPT TO RELEASE ILLEGAL ADDRESS TO TEMP DAZL
)@@G@@TA STACK'   @#@@@#          INSTRS  @[@@@#.     @G@@@#. M$CORETMPNEW - RZM
)@@G@@OUTINE TO RETURN INFO ON CURRENT TEMP DATA STACK AND  @C@@@#.           ZN
)@@G@@     SETUP A NEW TEMP DATA STACK.   @[@@@#.     @^@@@#.  LMJ  X11,M$COREZO
)@@G@@TMPNEW@A@@@#.  A0 = (FIRST ADDR, NEXT ADDR)     @C@A@^.  A1 = # WORDS REZP
)@@G@@MAINING IN OLD TEMP DATA STACK@^@@@A.  A1 = LAST ADDRESS+1  @[@@@#.     ZQ
)@@G@@@#@@@#M$CORETMPNEW*     @E@@@#          LA        A0,NEXTD          . GEZR
)@@G@@T NEXT ADDRESS    @F@@@#          LXI       A0,FRSTD          . GET BASEZS
)@@G@@ ADDRESS IN H1    @H@B@#          SZ        NEXTD             . CAUSE NEZT
)@@G@@XT ACQUIRE TO GET NEW STACK   @B@B@#          SZ        FRSTD           ZU
)@@G@@  .   @G@@@^          LA        A1,SIZED          . GET SIZE OF TEMP DATZV
)@@G@@A STACK     @E@@@A          AA        A1,FRSTD          . = LAST ADDRESSZW
)@@G@@+1    @H@@@B          SZ        NEXTD             . CAUSE NEXT ACQUIRE TZX
)@@G@@O GET NEW STACK   @B@@@B          SZ        FRSTD             .   @G@ @^ZY
)@@G@@          AN        A1,A0             . = # WORDS IN TEMP DATA STACK    ZZ
)@@G@@@G@A@           AN,U      A1,,A0            . = # WORDS IN TEMP DATA STAAA
)@@G@@CK    @D@@@#          LA,U      A5,0              . JUST IN CASE  @C@@@#AB
)@@G@@          J         0,X11             . DONE    @[@@@#.     @G@@@#. M$COAC
)@@G@@RETMPOLD - ROUTINE TO ESTABLISH A PREVIOUS TEMP DATA STACK, AND   @C@@@#AD
)@@G@@.                RELEASE THE CURRENT STACK.     @[@@@#.     @A@@@#.  A0 AE
)@@G@@= (FIRST ADDR, NEXT ADDR)     @^@@@#.  LMJ  X11,M$CORETMPOLD@^@@@#.  A5 AF
)@@G@@= ERROR PCW OR 0  @[@@@#.     @#@@@#M$CORETMPOLD*     @#@^@#          ROAG
)@@G@@UTINE @^@@@^          SUBROUTINE    @E@@@#          LA,U      A5,0      AH
)@@G@@        . ASSUME NO ERRORS    @F@@@#          LA        A1,FRSTD        AI
)@@G@@  . GET CURRENT BASE ADDRESS  @G@@@#          SA        A0,NEXTD        AJ
)@@G@@  . POST NEXT AVAILABLE ADDRESS     @F@@@#          SSL       A0,18     AK
)@@G@@        . SLIDE BASE ADDRESS DOWN   @F@@@#          SA        A0,FRSTD  AL
)@@G@@        . POST PREVIOUS BASE ADDRESS@E@@@#          AA        A0,SIZED  AM
)@@G@@        . COMPUTE LAST ADDR+1 @E@@@#          SA        A0,LASTD        AN
)@@G@@  . POST NEW LAST ADDR+1@F@@@#          JZ        A1,REL999         . IFAO
)@@G@@ NO PREVIOUS, QUIT EARLY@G@@@#          PREL      0,A1,U            . REAP
)@@G@@LEASE PREVIOUS TEMP DATA STACK@E@@@#REL999    RETURN                    AQ
)@@G@@  . MAYBE WITH ERROR    @[@@@#.     @I@@@#SZFRD     VAR       1 0       AR
)@@G@@        . SIZE, BASE ADDRESS OF CURRENT TEMP STACK    @E@@@#FRSTD     EQAS
)@@G@@UF      SZFRD,,H2         . FIRST DBANK ADDRESS @D@@@#SIZED     EQUF    AT
)@@G@@  SZFRD,,H1         . SIZE OF DBANK @G@@@#NXLSD     VAR       1 0       AU
)@@G@@        . NEXT AND LAST DBANK ADDRESSES   @G@@@#NEXTD     EQUF      NXLSAV
)@@G@@D,,H1         . NEXT AVAILABLE DBANK ADDRESS    @G@@@#LASTD     EQUF    AW
)@@G@@  NXLSD,,H2         . LAST AVAILABLE DBANK ADDRESS    @[@@@#.     @#@@@#AX
)@@G@@          END     ___@@@ REQUEST ZERO, RETURN CU*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@[@@AB    AY
)@@G@@@#@@@@          M$DEF   @ @@@]          $INCLUDE  'M$CONFIG'@A@@@@      AZ
)@@G@@    $PAR(4)='RESUME'->$RESUME @#@]@@.         $ASCII  @#@@@]          $ABA
)@@G@@SCII  @^@@@@          M$COMMANDS    @#@@@[          M$MODES @^@@@@      BB
)@@G@@    M$OPERATORS   @^@@@@          M$INTRINSICS  @^@@@@          M$LIBRARBC
)@@G@@IES   @^@@@@          M$CONFIGURE   @^@@@#          M$CHARTABLE   @^@@@^BD
