)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@DEBUG     EQU       1                 . CLBG
)@@G@@EAR CORE FOR NOW  @B@@@@TRACE     EQU       $PAR(4)='TRACE'   .   @A@@@@BH
)@@G@@SNOOP     EQU       $PAR(4)='SNOOPY'@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. CORE MANAGEMENT BI
)@@G@@ROUTINE WHOSE BUFFER SIZES ARE THE FIBONACCI NUMBERS  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@BJ
)@@G@@.    BY  KERN E. SIBBALD@[@@@@.     @C@@@@.    RIPPED OFF BY BEN CRANSTOBK
)@@G@@N FOR CPMD 9/23/75@[@@@@.     @F@@@[MININX    EQU       M$MININX        BL
)@@G@@  . CAPTURE M$CONFIG DEFS     @B@@@[MAXINX    EQU       M$MAXINX        BM
)@@G@@      @[@[@@.     @F@[@@. MIN AND MAX SIZ ARE THE SIZE OF DESIRED USER BBN
)@@G@@UFFERS IN WORDS   @[@[@@.     @H@[@@MINSIZ    EQU       2               BO
)@@G@@  . MINIMUM BUFFER REQUEST SIZE IN WORDS  @H@[@@MAXSIZ    EQU       3200BP
)@@G@@              . MAXIMUM BUFFER REQUEST SIZE IN WORDS  @[@[@@.     @B@[@@BQ
)@@G@@P         PROC      *0                .   @B@[@@FIB*      NAME          BR
)@@G@@              .   @G@[@@F         EQU       $L0(1,1)          . FIBONACCBS
)@@G@@I STARTERS 1,1,2,3,5,...@F@[@@MININX*   $EQU      0                 . POBT
)@@G@@ST MINIMUM INITIAL INDEX@E@[@@I         $REPEAT   2,999             . SEBU
)@@G@@QUENCE GENERATOR  @G@[@@F(I)      EQU       F(I-1)+F(I-2)     . GENERATEBV
)@@G@@ NEXT FIBONACCI NUMBER  @E@[@@          F(I)>MAXSIZ->$ENDI          . QUBW
)@@G@@IT IF TOO BIG     @F@[@@          F(I)<MINSIZ->$ENDR          . DON'T GEBX
)@@G@@N IF TOO SMALL    @E@[@@          $DO       MININX=0 ,;       . IF NOT SBY
)@@G@@ET YET,...  @E@[@@MININX*   $EQU      I                 . POST MINIMUM IBZ
)@@G@@NDEX  @F@[@@          $DISPLAY  'INDEX: ':EDEC(2,I):' SIZE: ':EDEC(3,F(ICA
)@@G@@))    @E@[@@          +         F(I),0            . OUTPUT A SIZE,LINK  CB
)@@G@@@C@[@@          $ENDR                       . NEXT    @E@[@@MAXINX*   EQCC
)@@G@@U       I-1               . CAPTURE LAST INDEX  @B@[@@          END     CD
)@@G@@                    .   @[@[@@/.    @[@[@@.     @B@[@@          VARS    CE
)@@G@@                    .   @[@[@@.     @I@[@@M$BUFPOL* FIB                 CF
)@@G@@        . GENERATE FIBONACCI NUMBERS AND LINK TABL    @[@[@@.     @F@[@@CG
)@@G@@. ADDITIONAL SPACE IS GOTTEN FROM ER MCORE$.  THIS VARIABLE POINTS@E@[@@CH
)@@G@@. TO THE BEGINNING ADDRESS OF THE NEXT BUFFER TO BE GOTTEN. @[@[@@.     CI
)@@G@@@B@[@@M$PSGNXT* VAR       1 0                  .@[@@@@.     @G@@@@FIBSIZCJ
)@@G@@    EQUF      M$BUFPOL-MININX,,H1 . BUFFER SIZE IN WORDS (TOTAL)  @H@@@@CK
)@@G@@FRELNK    EQUF      M$BUFPOL-MININX,,H2 . LINK TO FREE BUFFER OF GIVEN SCL
)@@G@@IZE   @H@@@@FIBMAX    EQUF      M$BUFPOL+MAXINX-MININX,,H1 . MAXIMUM FIBCM
)@@G@@ONACCI BUFFER SIZE@[@@@@.     @D@@@@CTLBIT    EQUF      0,,S1           CN
)@@G@@  . CONTROL BITS  @D@@@@CTLINX    EQUF      0,,S2             . SIZE INDCO
)@@G@@EX    @H@@@@CTLFRE    EQUF      0,,S3             . SIZE INDEX IF ALLOCACP
)@@G@@TED ELSE ZERO     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@FL        EQUF      1,,H2           CQ
)@@G@@  . FORWARD LINK TO NEXT FREE BUFFER@H@@@@BL        EQUF      1,,H1     CR
)@@G@@        . BACK LINK TO PREVIOUS FREE BUFFER     @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     CS
)@@G@@@F@@@@. IF PARAMETER TRACE IS SET TO ONE THESE ROUTINES PRINT OUT THE   CT
)@@G@@@C@@@@. BUFFERS AS THEY ARE BEING ASSIGNED AND FREED. @[@@@@.     @B@@@@CU
)@@G@@          $IF       TRACE             .   @E@@@@TRASAV    VAR       9   CV
)@@G@@              . A0-A5,R1-R3 SAVE    @F@@@@TRLOCN    VAR       1         CW
)@@G@@        . LOCATION COUNTER OFFSET   @F@@@@TRLC      VAR       1         CX
)@@G@@        . LOCATION COUNTER NUMBER   @C@@@@ALMSG     'REQ AT &,$(&)+&, & CY
)@@G@@WORDS, GOT & AT &'@B@@@@RELMSG    'REL AT &,$(&)+&, & WORDS AT &' @B@@@@CZ
)@@G@@EDPKT     E$PKT     22,LINE           .   @B@@@@LINE      RES       22  DA
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@EDPCW     +         0126,LINE         .   @D@@@@DB
)@@G@@          $ENDF     TRACE             . ***** DEBUG   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@DC
)@@G@@. PROCS TO TRACE ALLOCATION AND RELEASING @D@@@@. THE CODE IS PUT INTO PDD
)@@G@@ROCS TO PREVENT ADDITIONAL    @ @@@@. OBSCURRING OF THE REAL CODE @[@@@@DE
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC      *0                .   @B@@@@GETTRACE* NADF
)@@G@@ME                        .   @ @@@@%1:       $IF       TRACE     @D@@@@DG
)@@G@@          REGSAVE                     . SAVE THE REGS @B@@@@          E$DH
)@@G@@DIT     EDPKT             .   @B@@@@          E$MSG     ALMSG           DI
)@@G@@  .   @F@@@@          EDITADDR  PSGLNK,,H2        . EDIT THE CALL ADDRESDJ
)@@G@@S     @#@@@@          E$MSGR  @E@@@@          E$OCTV    TRASAV          DK
)@@G@@  . EDIT REQUEST SIZE   @B@@@@          E$MSGR                      .   DL
)@@G@@@D@@@@          E$OCTV    TRASAV+1,,H1      . EDIT GOT SIZE @B@@@@      DM
)@@G@@    E$MSGR                      .   @E@@@@          E$OCTV    TRASAV+1,,DN
)@@G@@H2      . EDIT BUFFER ADDRESS @C@@@@          E$DITX                    DO
)@@G@@  . END EDIT@E@@@@          L         A0,EDPCW          . GET CONTROL WODP
)@@G@@RD    @D@@@@          ER        PRINT$            . PRINT MESSAGE @D@@@@DQ
)@@G@@          REGLOAD                     . RESTORE REGS  @ @@@@%1:       $EDR
)@@G@@NDF     TRACE     @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@DS
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC      *0                .   @B@@@@RELTRACE* NADT
)@@G@@ME                        .   @ @@@@%1:       $IF       TRACE     @D@@@@DU
)@@G@@          REGSAVE                     . SAVE REGISTERS@C@@@@          E$DV
)@@G@@DIT     EDPKT             . EDIT    @C@@@@          E$MSG     RELMSG    DW
)@@G@@        . RELEASE @F@@@@          EDITADDR  PSGLNK,,H2        . EDIT THEDX
)@@G@@ CALL ADDRESS     @#@@@@          E$MSGR  @E@@@@          L         A0,TDY
)@@G@@RASAV         . GET BUFFER ADDRESS  @G@@@@          AN,U      A0,1      DZ
)@@G@@        . DECREMENT TO POINT TO CTL WORD  @D@@@@          L         A0,CEA
)@@G@@TLINX,A0      . GET INDEX     @C@@@@          L         A0,FIBSIZ,A0    EB
)@@G@@  . GET SIZE@C@@@@          AN,U      A0,1              . DEC     @B@@@@EC
)@@G@@          E$OCTV                      .   @B@@@@          E$MSGR        ED
)@@G@@              .   @E@@@@          E$OCTV    TRASAV            . EDIT BUFEE
)@@G@@FER ADDRESS @B@@@@          E$DITX                      .   @B@@@@      EF
)@@G@@    L         A0,EDPCW          .   @B@@@@          ER        PRINT$    EG
)@@G@@        .   @D@@@@          REGLOAD                     . RESTORE REGS  EH
)@@G@@@ @@@@%1:       $ENDF     TRACE     @B@@@@          END                 EI
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@          $IF       TRACE     @^@@@@P     EJ
)@@G@@    PROC      0,6 @^@@@@REGSAVE*  NAME      1   @^@@@@REGLOAD*  NAME    EK
)@@G@@  0   @A@@@@DX        EQU       P(0,0)->/DS!/DL @A@@@@XR        EQU     EL
)@@G@@  P(0,0)->/SR!/LR @ @@@@          DX        A0,TRASAV @A@@@@          DXEM
)@@G@@        A2,TRASAV+2     @A@@@@          DX        A4,TRASAV+4     @A@@@@EN
)@@G@@          XR        R1,TRASAV+6     @A@@@@          XR        R2,TRASAV+EO
)@@G@@7     @A@@@@          XR        R3,TRASAV+8     @#@@@@          END     EP
)@@G@@@^@@@@P         PROC      0,13@#@@@@EDITADDR* NAME    @E@@@@          LAEQ
)@@G@@,H2     A0,PSGLNK         . GET THE ADDRESS     @F@@@@          LMJ     ER
)@@G@@  X11,CRELAD$       . COMPUTE A RELATIVE ADDRESS@#@@@@          NOP     ES
)@@G@@@D@@@@          DS        A0,TRLOCN         . SAVE OFFSET,LC@F@@@@      ET
)@@G@@    E$FD2     A2                . EDIT THE ELEMENT NAME     @D@@@@      EU
)@@G@@    E$MSGR                      . MORE MESSAGE  @G@@@@          E$DECV  EV
)@@G@@  TRLC              . INSERT LOCATION COUNTER NUMBER  @#@@@@          E$EW
)@@G@@MSGR  @D@@@@          E$OCTF    6,TRLOCN          . INSERT OFFSET @#@@@@EX
)@@G@@          END     @ @@@@          $ENDF     TRACE     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@EY
)@@G@@P         PROC      *1,2*SNOOP@#@@@@SNOOPY*   NAME    @ @@@@%1:       $IEZ
)@@G@@F       SNOOP     @ @@@@          SLJ       SNOOPY    @ @@@@          + FA
)@@G@@        2,P(1,1)  @#@@@@%1:       $ENDF   @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@FB
)@@G@@/.    @B@@@@          INSTRS                      .   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@FC
)@@G@@. ALLOCATE A CORE BUFFER@[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         L         A0,SIZE   FD
)@@G@@@C@@@@.         LMJ       X11,M$COREPRMGET        .   @H@@@@.         JNFE
)@@G@@Z       A5,ERROR          . IF ERROR A5 COMES BACK NONZERO=PCW    @C@@@@FF
)@@G@@.         A0 - STILL HAS WORD COUNT REQUESTED   @F@@@@.         A1 - ACCFG
)@@G@@ESS WORD FOR BUFFER GOTTEN (COULD BE BIGGER).   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     FH
)@@G@@@^@@@@M$COREPRMGET*       .   @G@@@@          L,U       A1,0,A0         FI
)@@G@@  . GET NUMBER OF WORDS DESIRED     @F@@@@          L         A0,(1,MINIFJ
)@@G@@NX-1)   . PREPARE TO SEARCH TABLE   @E@@@@          L,U       R1,MAXINX-FK
)@@G@@MININX+1 . FOR FIB BUFFER KEY @E@@@@          L         A5,PSGSZE       FL
)@@G@@  . PCW FOR BAD SIZE    @F@@@@          SG        A1,FIBSIZ+1,*A0   . SEFM
)@@G@@ARCH FOR BUFFER BIG ENUF@F@@@@          J         0,X11             . NOFN
)@@G@@PE - CANNOT GET ONE     @E@@@@          LXI,U     A0,0              . CLFO
)@@G@@EAR INCREMENT     @B@@@@          J         PSG010            .   @^@@@@FP
)@@G@@M$COREPRMKEY*       .   @E@@@@          TLE,U     A0,MININX         . ISFQ
)@@G@@ BELOW MIN SIZE   @D@@@@          L,U       A0,MININX         . YES - GEFR
)@@G@@T MIN @E@@@@          L         A5,PSGSZE         . GET SIZE ERROR PCW  FS
)@@G@@@E@@@@          TG,U      A0,MAXINX+1       . IS IT WITHIN RANGE  @E@@@@FT
)@@G@@          J         0,X11             . NO - ERROR RETURN   @E@@@@      FU
)@@G@@    L         A1,FIBSIZ,A0      . GET BUFFER SIZE     @G@@@@          ANFV
)@@G@@,U      A1,1              . DON'T COUNT CONTROL WORD THOUGH @[@@@@.     FW
)@@G@@@C@@@@. SIZE KEY IN A0, NUMBER OF WORDS DESIRED IN A1.@[@@@@.     @]@@@@FX
)@@G@@PSG010    . @E@@@@          SNOOPY    PSG999+2          . ACTIVATE SNOOPFY
)@@G@@Y     @E@@@@          S         X11,PSGLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS FZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          DS        A0,PSGTMP         . SAVE REQUESTED SIZE @E@@@@GA
)@@G@@          DS        A2,PSGSAV         . SAVE IMPORTANT REGS @F@@@@      GB
)@@G@@    LA        A2,M$COREPRMORG   . GET ORIGIN OF PERM CORE   @E@@@@      GC
)@@G@@    TNZ       M$PSGNXT          . IS AVAIL LINK SET?  @G@@@@          SAGD
)@@G@@        A2,M$PSGNXT       . NO, SET IT TO PERM CORE ORIGIN  @[@@@@.     GE
)@@G@@@C@@@@. SEARCH UPWARDS UNTIL A FREE BUFFER IS FOUND.  @[@@@@.     @]@@@@GF
)@@G@@PSG020    . @F@@@@          L         A1,FRELNK,A0      . ARE THERE ANY GG
)@@G@@OF THESE    @F@@@@          JZ        A1,PSG030         . IF NOT TRY NEXGH
)@@G@@T SIZE UP   @F@@@@          LMJ       X11,UNLINK        . IF THERE IS ONGI
)@@G@@E UNLINK    @F@@@@          J         PSG050            . IT AND ENTER SGJ
)@@G@@PLIT LOOP   @]@@@@PSG030    . @E@@@@          A,U       A0,1            GK
)@@G@@  . MOVE TO NEXT SIZE UP@E@@@@          TLE,U     A0,MAXINX+1       . ATGL
)@@G@@ MAX SIZE YET     @E@@@@          J         PSG020            . NO - SEEGM
)@@G@@ IF ANY FREE@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. NO FREE BUFFERS AVAILABLE.  GET ANOTHER GN
)@@G@@ONE OF THE MAX    @E@@@@. SIZE FROM ER MCORE$.  BUILD DUMMY TO KEEP IT FGO
)@@G@@ROM BEING   @F@@@@. RECOMBINED WHEN FREED.  THE BANK IT MCORES OFF IS COGP
)@@G@@NTROLED     @A@@@@. BY THE INITIAL VALUE OF M$PSGNXT. @[@@@@.     @F@@@@GQ
)@@G@@          L         A0,FIBMAX         . FIND LAST ADDRESS NEEDED  @E@@@@GR
)@@G@@          A         A0,M$PSGNXT       . GET NEXT AVAIL ADDR @D@@@@      GS
)@@G@@    ER        MCORE$            . TRY TO GET IT @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. NOTEGT
)@@G@@ - CONTINGENCY HANDLER SETS A0 TO 0 ON MCORE$ ERRORS. @[@@@@.     @E@@@@GU
)@@G@@          JNZ       A0,PSG035         . SKIP IF NO ERROR    @F@@@@      GV
)@@G@@    L         A5,PSGMCE         . GET MCORE$ ERROR MESSAGE  @D@@@@      GW
)@@G@@    J         PSG999            . AND RETURN    @]@@@@PSG035    . @[@@@@GX
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@. IF DEBUG SET CLEAR NEWLY ACQUIRED CORE TO -0. @[@@@@.     GY
)@@G@@@ @@@@          $IF       DEBUG     @F@@@@          OR,U      A0,0777   GZ
)@@G@@        . LAST AVAIL ADDRESS IN A1  @F@@@@          AN        A1,A0     HA
)@@G@@        . = # WORDS ACQUIRED - 1    @E@@@@          LR,U      R1,1,A1   HB
)@@G@@        . = # WORDS ACQUIRED  @D@@@@          LXI,U     A0,1            HC
)@@G@@  . INCREMENT     @F@@@@          LA,U      A1,(-0)           . THING TOHD
)@@G@@ CLEAR CORE WITH  @F@@@@          BT        A0,,*A1           . CLEAR NEHE
)@@G@@WLY ACQUIRED CORE @#@@@@          $ENDF   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. INITIALIZEHF
)@@G@@ NEW CORE AS A BIG BUDDY WITH A DUMMY LITTLE BUDDY SO @A@@@@. RECOMBINATHG
)@@G@@ION WILL NOT TAKE PLACE.@[@@@@.     @G@@@@          LA        A1,M$PSGNXHH
)@@G@@T       . GET THE NEXT AVAILABLE ADDRESS  @F@@@@          SZ        0,A1HI
)@@G@@              . CLEAR THE NEW CONTROL WORD@F@@@@          LR,U      R1,0HJ
)@@G@@60            . INITIALIZE AS A BIG BUDDY @D@@@@          SR        R1,CHK
)@@G@@TLBIT,A1      . SET BUDDY BIT @G@@@@          AU        A1,FIBMAX       HL
)@@G@@  . COMPUTE LITTLE BUDDY'S ADDRESS  @E@@@@          SR        R1,CTLFRE,HM
)@@G@@A2      . POST AS ALLOCATED   @G@@@@          AA,U      A2,1            HN
)@@G@@  . & GET NEXT AVAILABLE ADDRESS    @C@@@@          SA        A2,M$PSGNXHO
)@@G@@T       . POST IT @G@@@@          LA,U      A0,MAXINX         . GET SIZEHP
)@@G@@ KEY FOR NEW BUFFER     @D@@@@          SA        A0,CTLINX,A1      . POHQ
)@@G@@ST THE INDEX@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. A0 IS THE SIZE KEY OF THE UNLINKED BUFFEHR
)@@G@@R A1. @G@@@@. SPLIT THE BUFFER IF IT'S UNECESSARILY LARGE, CREATING TWO HS
)@@G@@NEW SMALLER @A@@@@. BUFFERS. THEN SEE IF THEY'LL DO.  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@HT
)@@G@@PSG050    TE        A0,PSGTMP         . IS THIS THE RIGHT SIZE?   @E@@@@HU
)@@G@@          TNE,U     A0,MININX+1       . OR NEXT TO SMALLEST?@E@@@@      HV
)@@G@@    J         PSG060            . YES, RETURN TO USER @G@@@@          ANHW
)@@G@@,U      A0,1              . COMPUTE INDEX OF NEW BIG BUDDY  @F@@@@      HX
)@@G@@    SA        A0,CTLINX,A1      . POST BIG BUDDY CTL INDEX  @F@@@@      HY
)@@G@@    LA        A2,,A1            . SAVE CURRENT CONTROL WORD @H@@@@      HZ
)@@G@@    LR,U      R1,040            . ASSUME OLD BUFFER WAS LITTLE BUDDY    IA
)@@G@@@C@@@@          TP        A2                . WAS IT? @G@@@@          LRIB
)@@G@@,U      R1,060            . NO, GET BIG BUDDY MEMORY BITS   @E@@@@      IC
)@@G@@    SR        R1,CTLBIT,A1      . POST BIG BUDDY BITS @F@@@@          LRID
)@@G@@        R1,A2             . SAVE CONTROL BITS STILL   @F@@@@          LMIE
)@@G@@J       X11,LINK          . LINK IN NEW BIG BUDDY     @F@@@@          AAIF
)@@G@@        A1,FIBSIZ,A0      . = LITTLE BUDDY ADDRESS    @E@@@@          ANIG
)@@G@@,U      A0,1              . = SIZE KEY FOR SAME @F@@@@          SZ      IH
)@@G@@  0,A1              . CLEAR NEW CONTROL WORD    @D@@@@          SA      II
)@@G@@  A0,CTLINX,A1      . POST SIZE KEY @F@@@@          LA        A2,R1     IJ
)@@G@@        . RESTORE OLD CONTROL BITS  @G@@@@          LSSL      A2,1      IK
)@@G@@        . ISOLATE ANCESTOR MEMORY BIT     @B@@@@          SSL       A2,3IL
)@@G@@1             .   @G@@@@          SA        A2,CTLBIT,A1      . POST LITIM
)@@G@@TLE BUDDY BITS (00, 01) @F@@@@          LMJ       X11,LINK          . LIIN
)@@G@@NK IN THE LITTLE BUDDY  @E@@@@          LA        A0,PSGTMP         . REIO
)@@G@@STORE REQUEST SIZE@E@@@@          J         PSG020            . NOW GO FIP
)@@G@@IND A BUFFER@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. A0 HAS SIZE KEY AND A1 ADDRESS OF BUFFERIQ
)@@G@@ TO RETURN TO USER.     @[@@@@.     @]@@@@PSG060    . @B@@@@          $IIR
)@@G@@F       DEBUG             .   @F@@@@          L         R1,PSGLNK       IS
)@@G@@  . SET ADDRESS OF CALLER     @F@@@@          S,H2      R1,0,A1         IT
)@@G@@  . INTO H2 OF CONTROL WORD   @B@@@@          $ENDF     DEBUG           IU
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@          S         A0,CTLFRE,A1      . SET BUFFIV
)@@G@@ER AS ALLOCATED   @G@@@@          LXI       A1,FIBSIZ,A0      . GET ACTUIW
)@@G@@AL BUFFER LENGTH TOO    @H@@@@          AH        A1,(-1,1)         . MAIX
)@@G@@KE ACCESS WORD TO BUFFER FOR USER   @ @@@@          $IF       DEBUG     IY
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LR        R1,FIBSIZ,A0      . GET BUFFER LENGTH   @E@@@@IZ
)@@G@@          JGD       R1,$+1            . COUNT CONTROL WORD  @E@@@@      JA
)@@G@@    LA,U      A2,,A1            . GET BUFFER ADDRESS  @D@@@@          LXJB
)@@G@@I,U     A2,1              . PLUS INCREMENT@C@@@@          LA,U      A3,(JC
)@@G@@0)            . CLEAR   @F@@@@          BT        A2,,*A3           . MOJD
)@@G@@VE ZEROES TO BUFFER     @ @@@@          $ENDF     DEBUG     @F@@@@      JE
)@@G@@    L         A0,PSGTMP+1       . GET REQUESTED LENGTH AGAIN@F@@@@      JF
)@@G@@    GETTRACE                    . TRACE BUFFER ALLOCATION   @E@@@@      JG
)@@G@@    L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR FLAG    @]@@@@PSG999    . JH
)@@G@@@D@@@@          DL        A2,PSGSAV         . RESTORE A2A3  @E@@@@      JI
)@@G@@    L         X11,PSGLNK        . GET RETURN ADDRESS  @C@@@@          J JJ
)@@G@@        0,X11             . RETURN  @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. RELEJK
)@@G@@ASE A CORE BUFFER @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         L         A0,ADDRESS@C@@@@JL
)@@G@@.         LMJ       X11,M$COREPRMREL        .   @B@@@@.         JNZ     JM
)@@G@@  A5,ERROR          .   @^@@@@.         NORMAL RETURN @[@@@@.     @^@@@@JN
)@@G@@M$COREPRMREL*       .   @E@@@@          S         X11,PSGLNK        . SAJO
)@@G@@VE RETURN ADDRESS @F@@@@          DS        A2,PSGSAV         . SAVE IMPJP
)@@G@@ORTANT REGISTERS  @B@@@@          RELTRACE                    .   @D@@@@JQ
)@@G@@          SNOOPY    REL999+2          . TURN ON SNOOPY@F@@@@          ANJR
)@@G@@U,U     A0,1              . CONTROL WORD ADDRESS TO A1@E@@@@          L JS
)@@G@@        A0,CTLINX,A1      . GET CONTROL INDEX   @F@@@@          L       JT
)@@G@@  A5,PSGERF         . ERROR IN FREE MESSAGE     @E@@@@          TE      JU
)@@G@@  A0,CTLFRE,A1      . IS BUFFER ALLOCATED @D@@@@          J         REL9JV
)@@G@@99            . NO - ERROR OFF@E@@@@          LA,U      A1,,A1          JW
)@@G@@  . CLEAR INCREMENT     @G@@@@          TLE       A1,M$PSGNXT       . ISJX
)@@G@@ ADDRESS IN PERM CORE AREA?   @H@@@@          TLE       A1,M$COREPRMORG JY
)@@G@@  . MUST BE M$COREPRMORG<=A1<M$MSGPNXT    @D@@@@          J         REL9JZ
)@@G@@99            . NO, ERROR     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. A0 HAS SIZE INDEX OF BKA
)@@G@@UFFER IN A1, TO BE RELEASED.  @[@@@@.     @]@@@@REL010    . @F@@@@      KB
)@@G@@    TP        0,A1              . IS BUFFER A LITTLE BUDDY  @B@@@@      KC
)@@G@@    J         REL020            . NO@G@@@@          A,U       A0,1      KD
)@@G@@        . YES - GET INDEX OF BIG BUDDY    @F@@@@          ANU       A1,FKE
)@@G@@IBSIZ,A0      . ADDRESS OF BUDDY TO A2    @C@@@@          J         REL0KF
)@@G@@30            . AND SKIP@[@@@@.     @D@@@@. BUFFER IS BIG BUDDY - FIND AKG
)@@G@@DDRESS OF LITTLE ONE    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@REL020    . @E@@@@          AUKH
)@@G@@        A1,FIBSIZ,A0      . FIND BUDDY ADDRESS  @C@@@@          AN,U    KI
)@@G@@  A0,1              . AND SIZE@[@@@@.     @B@@@@. BUDDY ADDRESS IN A2 ANKJ
)@@G@@D SIZE KEY IN A0  @[@@@@.     @]@@@@REL030    . @E@@@@          TNZ     KK
)@@G@@  CTLFRE,A2         . IS BUDDY ALLOCATED  @F@@@@          TE        A0,CKL
)@@G@@TLINX,A2      . OR HAS HE BEEN BROKEN     @F@@@@          J         REL0KM
)@@G@@40            . YES - DROP OUT AND LINK   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. BUDDY IS FKN
)@@G@@REE.  UNLINK FROM FREE STORAGE TABLE.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          DSKO
)@@G@@C       A1,36             . SWAP BUDDY INTO R1  @G@@@@          L,U     KP
)@@G@@  R1,0,A2           . SAVE ORIGINAL BUFFER ADDRESS    @F@@@@          LMKQ
)@@G@@J       X11,UNLINK        . UNLINK BUDDY FROM STORE   @F@@@@          L KR
)@@G@@        A2,R1             . RECOVER ORIGINAL BUFFER   @E@@@@          TNKS
)@@G@@        0,A1              . PUT BIG BUDDY IN A1 @B@@@@          DSC     KT
)@@G@@  A1,36             .   @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. COMPRESS TWO BUDDYS INTO A BKU
)@@G@@IGGER BUFFER.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@          L         A2,CTLBIT,A2    KV
)@@G@@  . GET CTL BIT OF SMALL BUDDY@B@@@@          SSL       A2,1            KW
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          OR        A2,CTLBIT,A1      .   @B@@@@          LSKX
)@@G@@SL      A3,1              .   @F@@@@          S         A3,CTLBIT,A1    KY
)@@G@@  . SET COMBINED CONTROL BITS @F@@@@          L         A0,CTLINX,A1    KZ
)@@G@@  . GET CONTROL INDEX OF BIG  @D@@@@          A,U       A0,1            LA
)@@G@@  . BUFFER AND    @C@@@@          S         A0,CTLINX,A1      . SET IT  LB
)@@G@@@F@@@@          J         REL010            . AND CHECK ITS BUDDY NOW   LC
)@@G@@@[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. THE BUDDY TO THIS BUFFER IS NOT AVAILABLLD
)@@G@@E.  CLEAR IT.     @[@@@@.     @]@@@@REL040    . @D@@@@          L       LE
)@@G@@  A0,CTLINX,A1      . GET FIB INDEX @C@@@@          $IF       DEBUG     LF
)@@G@@        . CLEAR IT@E@@@@          AU,U      A1,1              . USER ADDLG
)@@G@@RESS TO A1  @D@@@@          LXI,U     A2,1              . SET INCREMENT LH
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LA,U      A3,(-0)           . GET CLEAR WORD@D@@@@      LI
)@@G@@    L         R1,FIBSIZ,A0      . GET COUNT     @E@@@@          JGD     LJ
)@@G@@  R1,$+1            . COUNT CONTROL WORD  @D@@@@          BT        A2,,LK
)@@G@@*A3           . CLEAR THE CORE@C@@@@          $ENDF     DEBUG           LL
)@@G@@  . CLEAR IT@[@@@@.     @A@@@@. CHAIN IT IN TO FREE STORAGE POOL. @[@@@@LM
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@          SZ        CTLFRE,A1         . MARK BUFFER AS FREE LN
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LMJ       X11,LINK          . LINK IT INTO FREESTORE    LO
)@@G@@@E@@@@          L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR CODE    @]@@@@LP
)@@G@@REL999    . @E@@@@          DL        A2,PSGSAV         . RECOVER REGISTLQ
)@@G@@ERS   @E@@@@          L         X11,PSGLNK        . GET RETURN ADDRESS  LR
)@@G@@@D@@@@          J         0,X11             . RETURN TO USER@[@@@@.     LS
)@@G@@@F@@@@. LINK BUFFER IN A1 INTO STORAGE POOL OF A0 SIZE.  DESTROYS A2 A3.LT
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @]@@@@LINK      . @G@]@@          LA        A2,UX(FRELNK-1,ALU
)@@G@@0,U) . GET ADDRESS FOR BACKLINK     @F@#@]          LA,U      A2,UX(FRELLV
)@@G@@NK-1),A0 . GET ADDRESS FOR BACKLINK @G@@@#          LA,U      A2,M$BUFPOLW
)@@G@@L-M$MININX-1,A0 . GET ADDRESS FOR BACKLINK@F@@@@          L         A3,FLX
)@@G@@RELNK,A0      . GET FORWARD ADDRESS TOO   @H@@@@          S         A2,BLY
)@@G@@L,A1          . SET BACK LINK TO POINT TO FREE ARRAY  @G@@@@          S LZ
)@@G@@        A3,FL,A1          . SET FORWARD LINK TO OLD FIRST   @F@@@@      MA
)@@G@@    S         A1,FL,A2          . SET THIS BUFFER AS FIRST  @E@@@@      MB
)@@G@@    JZ        A3,0,X11          . IF NO FORWARD EXIT  @G@@@@          S MC
)@@G@@        A1,BL,A3          . ELSE SET BACKLINK OF FORWARD    @D@@@@      MD
)@@G@@    J         0,X11             . AND RETURN    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. UNLIME
)@@G@@NK BUFFER IN A1 FROM ITS CHAIN.  A2 AND A3 DESTROYED. @[@@@@.     @]@@@@MF
)@@G@@UNLINK    . @E@@@@          L         A2,BL,A1          . GET PREVIOUS BMG
)@@G@@UFFER @F@@@@          L         A3,FL,A1          . GET POSSIBLE NEXT BUMH
)@@G@@FFER  @H@@@@          S         A3,FL,A2          . UNCHAIN BY POINTING MI
)@@G@@PREV AT NEXTEXT   @E@@@@          JZ        A3,0,X11          . AND IF NMJ
)@@G@@EXT THEN    @E@@@@          S         A2,BL,A3          . POINT NEXT AT MK
)@@G@@PREV  @D@@@@          J         0,X11             . AND RETURN    @[@@@@ML
)@@G@@/.    @C@@@@. M$COREPRMALL - RELEASE ALL OF ACQUIRED CORE.  @[@@@@.     MM
)@@G@@@F@@@@. THIS ROUTINE SHOULD BE CALLED ONLY FOR A "COLD-START" RECOVERY. MN
)@@G@@@F@@@@. ALL OF THE ACQUIRED CORE IS RELEASED VIA LCORE$, AND THE BUFFER MO
)@@G@@@#@@@@. POOL IS ZEROED. @[@@@@.     @#@@@@M$COREPRMALL*     @B@@@@      MP
)@@G@@    SNOOPY    ALL999            .   @G@@@@          SZ        M$PSGNXT  MQ
)@@G@@        . CLEAR NEXT AVAILABLE ADDRESS    @E@@@@          LA        A0,MMR
)@@G@@$COREPRMORG   . GET PERM CORE ORIGIN@H@@@@          TLE,U     A0,LASTD$ MS
)@@G@@        . DON'T RELEASE REAL DBANK THOUGH..     @B@@@@          LA,U    MT
)@@G@@  A0,LASTD$         .   @E@@@@          ER        LCORE$            . REMU
)@@G@@LEASE THE MEMORY  @D@@@@          LA,U      A0,(0)            . GET ZEROMV
)@@G@@ES    @H@@@@          MOVE      A1,M$BUFPOL *A0 MAXINX-MININX+1 H2 . ERAMW
)@@G@@SE BUFFER LINKS   @C@@@@          LA,U      A5,0              . NO ERRORMX
)@@G@@@C@@@@ALL999    J         0,X11             . ALL DONE@[@@@@.     @C@@@@MY
)@@G@@PSGLNK    VAR       1                 . LINK    @D@@@@PSGSAV    VAR     MZ
)@@G@@  2                 . SAVE FOR A2 A3@G@@@@PSGTMP    VAR       2         NA
)@@G@@        . REQUESTED SIZE KEY, SIZE WORDS  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          LINB
)@@G@@TS                        .   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@PSGSZE    PCW       'PERNC
)@@G@@MANENT CORE REQUEST TOO LARGE.'     @C@@@@PSGMCE    PCW       'MCORE$ REND
)@@G@@QUEST REJECTED.'  @E@@@@PSGERF    PCW       'RELEASE OF ILLEGAL BUFFER ANE
)@@G@@TTEMPTED.'  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          END                         .   NF

)@@G@@C- F@)DDI^[ADDMETO^[RD9M*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/         M$DEF   @[@@@@.     KR
)@@G@@@E@@@@. THIS CLASS OF FUNCTIONS DOES A PARTIAL WORD LOAD FROM AN  @B@@@@KS
)@@G@@. ARGUMENT AND TYPES THE RESULT INTEGER   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@M$FUNTHRDWD*KT
)@@G@@        .   @F@@@@          TRDMODE                     . GO INTO THIRD KU
)@@G@@WORD MODE   @^@@@@M$FUNQRTRWD*        .   @#@#@@          ROUTINE @^@@@#KV
)@@G@@          SUBROUTINE    @G@@@@PWDEXL    LOCAL                       . EXKW
)@@G@@ECUTE CELL TO LOAD PARTWORD   @E@@@@          LA        A0,VDM+SRA      KX
)@@G@@  . GET RIGHT ARG MODE  @D@@@@          LA        A5,PCL('DATA ITEM REQUKY
)@@G@@IRED.')     @F@[@@          JOP,U     A0,PSVBIT PWD999  . CHECK FOR PSUEKZ
)@@G@@DOVALUE     @G@]@[          TVAL      A0 PWD999         . MUST HAVE A VALA
)@@G@@LUE TO OBTAIN FROM@G@@@]          TDAT      A0 PWD999         . MUST HAVLB
)@@G@@E A VALUE TO OBTAIN FROM@D@^@@          TGET      1                 . GELC
)@@G@@T TEMP SPACE@E@^@@          JNZ       A5,PWD999         . IF ERROR RETURLD
)@@G@@N     @D@@@^          M$TGET    PWD999 1          . GET A WORD    @F@@@@LE
)@@G@@          L         A0,VDFS+SFN       . GET J DESIG FOR PW LOAD   @D@@@@LF
)@@G@@          LSSL      A0,26             . MAKE INSTR    @B@@@@          A LG
)@@G@@        A0,(LA A0,0,A0)   .   @B@@@@          S         A0,PWDEXL       LH
)@@G@@  .   @F@@@@          L         A0,VDA+SRA        . GET ADDRESS OF OPERALI
)@@G@@ND    @D@@@@          EX        PWDEXL            . GET PW INTO A0@D@@@@LJ
)@@G@@          S         A0,0,A1           . STORE RESULT  @F@@@@          SALK
)@@G@@        A1,VDAW+SLA       . POST ACCESS WORD TO RESULT@E@@@@          L,LL
)@@G@@U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR FLAG    @]@@@@PWD999    . @G@@@@LM
)@@G@@          QTRMODE                     . GO BACK INTO QUARTER WORD MODE  LN
)@@G@@@B@@@@          RETURN                      .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@      LO
)@@G@@    END                         .   ___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@LP
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@LQ
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@#/         M$DEF   @[@@@#.     @D@@@#. THIS FUNCTIONS HLR
)@@G@@ANDLES THE CLOSE BRACKET OPERATOR.  @[@@@#.     @G@@@#. THIS OPERATOR PRLS
)@@G@@OVIDES A GENERAL INDEXING CAPABILITY. ALL DATA TYPES  @B@@@#. MAY BE INDLT
)@@G@@EXED FOR VARIOUS RESULTS:     @[@@@#.     @F@@@#.  A)  NUMERIC VECTORS MLU
)@@G@@AY BE INDEXED FOR ONE OR MORE ELEMENTS.   @F@@@#.  B)  STRINGS (CHARACTELV
)@@G@@R VECTORS) MAY BE INDEXED FOR SUBSTRINGS. @G@@@#.  C)  LISTS MAY BE INDELW
)@@G@@XED FOR A SUBLIST (ONE OR MORE LIST ELEMENTS),  @G@@@#.      OR FOR A SILX
)@@G@@NGLE ELEMENT WITH THE MODE OF THE ELEMENT RESULTING.  @E@@@#.  D)  TABLELY
)@@G@@S MAY BE INDEXED FOR A GIVEN ORDINAL SUBSCRIPT. @[@@@#.     @H@@@#. IN ALZ
)@@G@@LL CASES, THE INDEX MAY CONSIST OF A SINGLE INTEGER VALUE, INDICATING   MA
)@@G@@@H@@@#. THE ORDINAL POSITION OF THE ELEMENT, CHARACTER, OR SUBSCRIPT.  TMB
)@@G@@HIS VALUE   @H@@@#. IS POSITIVE TO INDICATE INDEXING FROM THE LEFT-MOST MC
)@@G@@(ASCENDING NUMERICAL    @G@@@#. INDEXES) POSITION, OR MAY BE NEGATIVE TOMD
)@@G@@ INDICATE INDEXING FROM THE   @H@@@#. RIGHT-MOST (DESCENDING NUMERICAL IME
)@@G@@NDEXES) POSITION.  IN EITHER CASE, THE    @H@@@#. ABSOLUTE VALUE OF THE MF
)@@G@@INDEX MUST FALL WITHIN THE RANGE [1,LEN(V)] WHERE     @A@@@#. V IS THE VMG
)@@G@@ALUE BEING INDEXED.     @[@@@#.     @H@@@#. IN ALL CASES EXCEPT THE TABLMH
)@@G@@E, THE INDEX VALUE MAY ALSO BE A TWO-ELEMENT    @G@@@#. INTEGER VECTOR WMI
)@@G@@ITH THE FIRST VALUE AS DESCRIBED ABOVE AND THE SECOND @H@@@#. VALUE INDIMJ
)@@G@@CATING THE NUMBER OF ELEMENTS OR CHARACTERS TO INCLUDE IN THE     @G@@@#MK
)@@G@@. RESULT.  IF A SECOND NUMBER IS GIVEN FOR A TABLE INDEX, AN ERROR WILL ML
)@@G@@@G@@@#. OCCUR.  THIS NUMBER MUST FALL WITHIN THE RANGE OF [0,LEN(V)+1-I]MM
)@@G@@ WHERE@G@@@#. V IS THE VALUE BEING INDEXED AND I IS THE EFFECTIVE INDEX MN
)@@G@@(I.E., IF   @D@@@#. E IS THE ACTUAL INDEX, I:=LEN(V)+1-(1-2*(E<0))*E ). MO
)@@G@@@[@@@#.     @[@@@#.     @]@@@#M$SEMOPENBR*@#@A@#          ROUTINE @^@@@AMP
)@@G@@          SUBROUTINE    @E@@@#OBRTMP    LOCAL     2                 . TEMQ
)@@G@@MPORARY STORAGE   @C@@@#OBRTBL    LOCAL     2                 . TABLE VDMR
)@@G@@@F@@@#OBRRES    LOCAL     2                 . THE RESULT DESCRIPTOR     MS
)@@G@@@E@@@#OBRNDX    LOCAL                       . SUBSCRIPT INDEX     @F@@@#MT
)@@G@@OBRSUB    LOCAL                       . SUBSCRIPT NODE ADDRESS    @H@@@#MU
)@@G@@          LA        A0,VDOI+SVD         . GET THE OPERATOR WE JUST SCANNMV
)@@G@@ED    @D@@@#          LA        A5,PCL('MISSING RIGHT BRACKET.')  @G@@@#MW
)@@G@@          JNE,U     A0,M$OPERCLOSEB OBR999 . TAKE AN ERROR IF NOT ']'   MX
)@@G@@@F@@@#          SZ        VDA+SVD           . NULL OUT THE CLOSE BRACKETMY
)@@G@@@F@@@#          LA,U      A0,VD+SLA         . GET THE LEFT ARG DESCR PTRMZ
)@@G@@@G@@@#          LA,U      A1,VD+SRA         . GET THE RIGHT ARG DESCR PTNA
)@@G@@R     @G@@@#          CALL      M$INDEXCHECK      . CHECK & COMPUTE EFFENB
)@@G@@CTIVE INDEX @B@@@#          JNZ       A5,OBR999         .   @G@@@#      NC
)@@G@@    JE,U      A0,MODTBL OBR060  . IF INDEXING A TABLE, GO DO IT   @E@@@^ND
)@@G@@          SA        A2,VDL+SLA        . SET RESULT LENGTH   @G@@@^      NE
)@@G@@    PIKITEM   OBR999 VD+SLA     . COMPUTE EFFECTIVE WORD INDEX    @F@@@^NF
)@@G@@          SA        A0,VDA+SLA        . POST UPDATED WORD ADDRESS @E@@@^NG
)@@G@@          LA        A2,VDM+SLA        . GET THE MODE AGAIN  @F@@@^      NH
)@@G@@    JNE,U     A2,MODLST OBR010  . IF NOT A LIST, SKIP AHEAD @H@@@^      NI
)@@G@@    LA        A3,VDL+SRA        . RECOVER THE ORIGINAL INDEX LENGTH     NJ
)@@G@@@H@@@^          JNB       A3,OBR100         . IF LENGTH GIVEN, STILL A LNK
)@@G@@IST RESULT  @F@@@^          DL        A0,VD,A0          . GET THE DESCRINL
)@@G@@PTOR INDEXED@H@@@^          CALL      M$VDVDL           . ADJUST THE LENNM
)@@G@@GTH FIELD IF NECESSARY  @F@@@^          DS        A0,VD+SLA         . PONN
)@@G@@ST AS THE ACTUAL RESULT @C@@@^          J         OBR100            . DONO
)@@G@@NE    @]@@@^          . @C@@@^          .         PERFORM INDEX ON DATA NP
)@@G@@ITEM  @]@@@^          . @F@@@^OBR010    LA        A3,VMPWX,A2       . GENQ
)@@G@@T THE PARTWORD INDEX    @I@@@^          JE,U      A3,5 OBR100       . IFNR
)@@G@@ WHOLE WORDS, UPDATED ADDRESS IS ENUF     @G@@@^          DS        A0,ONS
)@@G@@BRTMP         . TEMP SAVE PARTWORD FETCH INDEXES@G@@@^          PUTANS  NT
)@@G@@  OBR999 VDM+SLA VDL+SLA . SETUP NEW RESULT SPACE     @F@@@^          PUNU
)@@G@@TITEM   OBR999 VD+SLA 0,,U VDL+SLA . SETUP STASH REGS @E@@@^          DLNV
)@@G@@        A0,OBRTMP         . RECOVER FETCH REGS  @E@@@^          LR      NW
)@@G@@  R1,A4             . GET FETCH LENGTH    @D@@@^          CALL      M$ITNX
)@@G@@EMCOPY        . COPY THE DATA @E@@@^          LA        A0,VDM+SLA      NY
)@@G@@  . GET THE MODE AGAIN  @F@@@^          TNSTR     A0                . ISNZ
)@@G@@ THE RESULT A STRING?   @D@@@^          CALL      M$BLANKWORD       . CLOA
)@@G@@EAN IT UP   @C@@@^          J         OBR100            . DONE    @F@^@#OB
)@@G@@          JOP,U     A0,ALPBIT OBR010  . IF ALPHA ITEM, GO DO IT   @]@^@#OC
)@@G@@          . @D@^@#          .         INDEXING A LIST OR NUMERIC VECTOR OD
)@@G@@@]@^@#          . @E@^@#          S         A2,VDL+SLA        . SET LENGOE
)@@G@@TH OF RESULT+@@@@[@J@^@#^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)ES)^@)^@)^@)^@)CC2 -QC-G TND-[^@)OF
)@@G@@^@)^@)^@) 0)ET E))D- D1BE-C^[JC0)EL ETPD-O+@@@@@@F@^@#          TE,U    OG
)@@G@@  A0,MODLST         . IS THE LEFT ARG A LIST?   @F@^@#          TEP,U   OH
)@@G@@  A0,DBLBIT         . IS IT DOUBLE PRECISION    @F@^@#          LSSL    OI
)@@G@@  A1,1              . YES - DOUBLE SUBSCRIPT    @F@^@#          A       OJ
)@@G@@  A1,VDA+SLA        . GET ADDRESS OF FIRST ITEM @F@^@#          S       OK
)@@G@@  A1,VDA+SLA        . SET ADDRESS OF RESULT     @E@^@#          TG,U    OL
)@@G@@  A0,MODDFL+1       . IF NUMERIC VECTOR   @F@^@#          TG,U      A2,2OM
)@@G@@              . OR IF SUBLIST LENGTH > 1  @E@^@#          J         OBR0ON
)@@G@@90            . THEN WE'RE DONE     @F@^@#          LA        A3,VDL+SRAOO
)@@G@@        . RECOVER RIGHT ARG LENGTH  @H@^@#          JNB       A3,OBR090 OP
)@@G@@        . IF LENGTH GIVEN, STILL A LIST RESULT  @F@^@#          DL      OQ
)@@G@@  A0,VD,A1          . GET THE DESCRIPTOR INDEXED@G@^@#          CALL    OR
)@@G@@  M$VDVDL           . ADJUST THE LENGTH IF NECESSARY  @G@^@#          DSOS
)@@G@@        A0,VD+SLA         . & POST AS THE ACTUAL RESULT     @D@^@#      OT
)@@G@@    J         OBR090            . AND RETURN    @]@^@#          . @B@^@#OU
)@@G@@          .         STRING INDEX OPERATION@]@^@#          . @F@^@#OBR010OV
)@@G@@    S         A2,VDL+SLA        . STORE LENGTH OF RESULT    @E@^@#      OW
)@@G@@    S         A1,OBRTMP         . TEMP SAVE INDEX     @G@^@#          SSOX
)@@G@@L       A2,2              . WORST CASE ASCII = 4 PER WORD   @D@^@#      OY
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,3,A2           . GET TEMP SPACE@D@^@#          TGET    OZ
)@@G@@                    . FOR RESULT    @C@^@#          JNZ       A5,OBR999 PA
)@@G@@        . ERROR   @D@^@#          L         A0,OBRTMP         . RECOVER PB
)@@G@@INDEX @E@^@#          S         A1,OBRTMP         . SAVE RESULT ADDRESS PC
)@@G@@@E@^@#          L         A1,VDM+SLA        . RECOVER RESULT MODE @H@^@#PD
)@@G@@          JEP,U     A1,ASCBIT OBR020  . IF ASCII BIT CLEAR, GO DO FIELDAPE
)@@G@@TA    @]@^@#          . @A@^@#          .         ASCII STRING    @]@^@#PF
)@@G@@          . @D@^@#          DSL       A0,2              . DIVIDE BY 4   PG
)@@G@@@B@^@#          SSL       A1,34             .   @D@^@#          A       PH
)@@G@@  A1,M$XASL         . GET LOAD INDEX@E@^@#          L         A3,M$XASS PI
)@@G@@        . AND STORE INDEX     @E@^@#          J         OBR030          PJ
)@@G@@  . AND COPY N CHARS    @]@^@#          . @A@^@#          .         FIELPK
)@@G@@DATA STRING @]@^@#          . @D@^@#OBR020    DSL       A0,36           PL
)@@G@@  . DIVIDE BY 6   @B@^@#          DI,U      A0,6              .   @D@^@#PM
)@@G@@          A         A1,M$XFDL         . GET LOAD INDEX@E@^@#          L PN
)@@G@@        A3,M$XFDS         . AND STORE INDEX     @F@^@#OBR030    A       PO
)@@G@@  A0,VDA+SLA        . GET LOAD WORD POINTER     @F@^@#          L       PP
)@@G@@  A2,OBRTMP         . GET STORE WORD POINTER    @E@^@#          S       PQ
)@@G@@  A2,VDA+SLA        . SET NEW POINTER     @E@^@#          L         R1,VPR
)@@G@@DL+SLA        . GET RESULT LENGTH   @E@^@#          CALL      M$COPYSTR PS
)@@G@@        . COPY THE STRING     @F@^@#          CALL      M$BLANKWORD     PT
)@@G@@  . BLANK OUT THE LAST WORD   @C@^@#          J         OBR090          PU
)@@G@@  . DONE    @]@@@#          . @A@@@#          .         <TABLE>[<INDEX>]PV
)@@G@@@]@@@#          . @F@@@#OBR060    AA,U      A1,1              . MAKE ORIPW
)@@G@@GIN ONE INDEX     @E@@@#          SA        A1,OBRNDX         . SAVE THEPX
)@@G@@ INDEX VALUE@G@@@#          LA,U      A1,OBRNDX         . MAKE AN ACCESSPY
)@@G@@ WORD TO THE INDEX@B@@@#          LXI,U     A1,1              .   @F@@@#PZ
)@@G@@          LA        A4,VDL+SRA        . GET ORIGINAL INDEX LENGTH @E@@@#QA
)@@G@@          SA        A1,VDAW+SRA       . POST AS THE INDEX   @E@@@#      QB
)@@G@@    DL        A0,VD+SLA         . GET THE TABLE VD    @G@@@#          DSQC
)@@G@@        A0,OBRTBL         . POST THE TABLE IN OUR PLACE     @E@@@#      QD
)@@G@@    LA,U      A3,OBRRES         . DEFAULT DESTINATION @G@@@#          JBQE
)@@G@@        A4,OBR080         . GO COPY SINGLE SUBSCRIPT VALUE  @F@@@#      QF
)@@G@@    LA        A0,A2             . GET THE RESULT LENGTH     @F@@@#      QG
)@@G@@    LA,U      A1,MODLST         . GET THE MODE OF THE RESULT@F@@@#      QH
)@@G@@    SA        A0,VDL+OBRRES     . POST THE RESULT LENGTH    @E@@@#      QI
)@@G@@    SA        A1,VDM+OBRRES     . POST THE RESULT MODE@F@@@#          LSQJ
)@@G@@SL      A0,1              . COMPUTE # WORDS IN LIST   @E@B@#          TGQK
)@@G@@ET                        . GET THE SPACE FOR IT@E@@@B          M$TGET  QL
)@@G@@  OBR999            . GET THE SPACE FOR IT@F@@@#          SA        A1,VQM
)@@G@@DA+OBRRES     . POST THE RESULT ADDRESS   @E@@@#          LA,U      A3,,QN
)@@G@@A1            . MAKE AN ACCESS WORD @C@@@#          LXI,U     A3,VDSIZE QO
)@@G@@        . SET INCR@E@@@#          LA        A2,VDL+OBRRES     . RECOVER QP
)@@G@@ELT COUNT   @G@@@#          J         OBR080            . COPY ALL INDEXQQ
)@@G@@ED SUBSCRIPTS     @G@@@#OBR070    DS        A2,OBRTMP         . SAVE COUQR
)@@G@@NT & LIST ELT INDEX     @E@@@#          LA,U      A0,OBRTBL         . GEQS
)@@G@@T THE TABLE DESCR @E@@@#          LA,U      A1,VD+SRA         . GET THE QT
)@@G@@INDEX DESCR @G@@@#          CALL      M$SSENTRY         . GET THE ENTRY QU
)@@G@@FOR THIS INDEX    @C@@@#          JNZ       A5,OBR999         . ERROR   QV
)@@G@@@D@@@#          LA        A5,PCL('INDEX OUT OF RANGE.')     @E@@@#      QW
)@@G@@    JZ        A2,OBR999         . NO FIND IF A2 = 0   @F@@@#          SAQX
)@@G@@        A2,OBRSUB         . SAVE THE SUBSCRIPT ADDR   @H@@@#          LAQY
)@@G@@        A1,SSM,A2         . CREATE A NEW VALUE FROM THE SUBSCRIPT @D@@@#QZ
)@@G@@          LA        A2,SSL,A2         . THE LENGTH    @G@@@#          PURA
)@@G@@TANS    OBR999            . CREATE NEW SPACE & SET VD+SLA   @G@@@#      RB
)@@G@@    LA        A2,OBRSUB         . RECOVER SUBSCRIPT NODE ADDRESS  @G@@@#RC
)@@G@@          MOVE      *A1 A2,SSD,A2,U 0,A0,U . MOVE THE SUBSCRIPT DATA    RD
)@@G@@@G@@@#          DL        A2,OBRTMP         . RECOVER COUNT & LIST ELT IRE
)@@G@@NDEX  @G@@@#          DL        A0,VD+SLA         . GET THE NEW ELEMENT RF

)@@G@@@A@@@E. CATENATION OF STRINGS AND INTEGERS@F@@@E. THIS ELEMENT PERFORMS SG

)@@G@@TR,2*2        . NEXT ARG@E@@@F          ANX,U     STKPTR,2*STKINC   . SKAD
)@@G@@IP TO NEXT ARG    @F@F@E          JGD       R1,CAT210         . COUNT ARAE
)@@G@@GS & LOOP IF MORE @F@@@F          JGD       R1,CAT210         . COUNT ARAF
)@@G@@GS & LOOP IF MORE @F@@@E          L         STKPTR,CATSPS     . RESTORE AG
)@@G@@STACK POINTER     @E@F@E          SA        A0,VDL+CATRES-1   . POST THEAH
)@@G@@ LENGTH     @E@@@F          SA        A0,CATLEN         . POST THE LENGTAI
)@@G@@H     @E@@@E          LSSL      A0,1              . COMPUTE A WORD COUNTAJ
)@@G@@@E@H@E          TGET                        . GET THAT MUCH SPACE @E@@@HAK
)@@G@@          M$TGET    CAT999            . GET THAT MUCH SPACE @F@F@E      AL
)@@G@@    SA        A1,VDA+CATRES-1   . POST THE ADDRESS OF RESULT@F@@@F      AM
)@@G@@    SA        A1,CATADR         . POST THE ADDRESS OF RESULT@E@@@E      AN
)@@G@@    LA,U      A2,,A1            . GET DESTINATION ADDR@C@@@E          LXAO
)@@G@@I,U     A2,VDSIZE         . SET INCR@D@@@F          LR        R2,CATNUM AP
)@@G@@        . GET # OF ARGS @E@@@F          JGD       R2,$+1            . COAQ
)@@G@@UNT THE FIRST ARG @E@F@ECAT220    LA        A1,VDM+SRA        . GET THE AR
)@@G@@ARG MODE    @E@@@FCAT220    LA        A1,VDM+SRA        . GET THE ARG MOAS
)@@G@@DE    @D@F@E          JE,U      A1,MODNUL CAT250  . SKIP NULL ARGS@D@@@FAT
)@@G@@          JE,U      A1,MODNUL CAT250  . SKIP NULL ARGS@F@@@E          LAAU
)@@G@@,U      A3,VD+SRA         . ASSUME ARG IS NOT A LIST  @B@@@E          LRAV
)@@G@@,U      R1,1              .   @F@F@E          JNE,U     A1,MODLST CAT240AW
)@@G@@  . IF NOT A LIST, GO COPY ARG@F@@@F          JNE,U     A1,MODLST CAT240AX
)@@G@@  . IF NOT A LIST, GO COPY ARG@E@@@E          LA        A3,VDA+SRA      AY
)@@G@@  . GET THE LIST ADDRESS@C@@@E          LXI,U     A3,VDSIZE         . SEAZ
)@@G@@T INCR@F@@@E          LR        R1,VDL+SRA        . GET THE # ELTS TO COBA
)@@G@@PY    @E@F@E          J         CAT240            . START COPY LOOP     BB
)@@G@@@E@@@F          J         CAT240            . START COPY LOOP     @D@F@EBC
)@@G@@CAT230    DL        A0,VD,*A3         . GET AN ELEMENT@D@@@FCAT230    DLBD
)@@G@@        A0,VD,*A3         . GET AN ELEMENT@E@@@E          DS        A0,VBE
)@@G@@D,*A2         . POST IT IN NEW LIST @D@F@ECAT240    JGD       R1,CAT230 BF
)@@G@@        . COPY ALL ELTS @D@@@FCAT240    JGD       R1,CAT230         . COBG
)@@G@@PY ALL ELTS @C@F@ECAT250    A,U       STKPTR,2*2        . NEXT ARG@E@@@FBH
)@@G@@CAT250    ANX,U     STKPTR,2*STKINC   . SKIP TO NEXT ARG    @F@F@E      BI
)@@G@@    JGD       A7,CAT220         . COPY ALL ARGS TO NEW LIST @F@@@F      BJ
)@@G@@    JGD       R2,CAT220         . COPY ALL ARGS TO NEW LIST @E@F@E      BK
)@@G@@    LA,U      A6,MODLST         . SET RESULT MODE     @[@F@E/.    @[@F@EBL
)@@G@@.     @F@F@E. END OF CATENATION.  STORE IS INTO RIGHTARG BECAUSE STACK HBM
)@@G@@AS    @B@F@E. ALREADY BEEN POPPED. (NOTE FALL-THRU).  @[@F@E.     @]@F@EBN
)@@G@@CAT300    . @]@@@F          . @F@@@F          .         END OF CATENATIOBO
)@@G@@N OPERATOR. STORE RESULT INTO @F@@@F          .         RIGHT ARG SINCE BP
)@@G@@STACK HAS ALREADY BEEN POPPED.@]@@@F          . @]@@@FCAT900    . @G@@@EBQ
)@@G@@          L         STKPTR,CATSPS     . RECOVER CORRECT STACK POINTER   BR
)@@G@@@D@@@F          DL        A0,CATRES         . GET THE RESULT@C@@@F      BS
)@@G@@    DS        A0,VD+SRA         . POST IT @C@F@E          S         A6,VBT
)@@G@@DM+SRA        . SET MODE@E@F@E          L         A0,CATRES         . GEBU
)@@G@@T RESULT VALUE    @C@F@E          S         A0,VDAW+SRA       . SET IT  BV
)@@G@@@B@@@E          L,U       A5,0              .   @#@@@ECAT999    RETURN  BW
)@@G@@@]@@@E          . @B@@@E          END                         .   ___@@@BX
)@@G@@ING IN.     @[@F@E.     @F@F@ECAT130    L,U       A0,VD+SRA         . GEBY
)@@G@@T DESCR TO BE EDITED    @D@F@E          LMJ     *[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/     BZ
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. THIS ROUTINE IMPLEMENTS THE LIST OPERATOCA
)@@G@@R: ';'.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. THE LIST OPERATOR HAS A "PUSH PRECEDENCECB
)@@G@@" THAT IS HIGHER THAN ITS     @G@@@@. "POP PRECEDENCE" SO THAT AN EXPRESCC
)@@G@@SION LIKE: 'A,B,C,D,E' WILL PUSH    @F@@@@. THE FIVE VALUES BEFORE EVALUCD
)@@G@@ATING THE LIST OPERATOR.  THIS IS AN@G@@@@. OPTIMIZATION TO AVOID CREATICE
)@@G@@NG A LIST WITH TWO ITEMS, THEN A LIST     @F@@@@. WITH THREE ITEMS, THENCF
)@@G@@ A LIST WITH FOUR ITEMS, THEN A LIST WITH @^@@@@. FIVE ITEMS, AND SO ON.CG
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @H@@@@. THE ELEMENTS OF A LIST MAY BE ANY VALUE EXCEPT A NULCH
)@@G@@L, WHICH IS IGNORED.    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@M$SEMLIST*  @E@@@@          LACI
)@@G@@,U      A3,M$SEMLIST      . GET OUR ADDRESS     @F@@@@          JE      CJ
)@@G@@  A3,VDOR+SVD M$SCANSTACK . IF SAME, STACK AGAIN@#@]@@          ROUTINE CK
)@@G@@@^@@@]          SUBROUTINE    @E@@@@LISTSP    LOCAL                     CL
)@@G@@  . STACK POINTER VALUE @G@@@@LISTNUM   LOCAL                       . NUCM
)@@G@@MBER OF ITEMS IN THE LIST     @H@@@@LISTARGC  LOCAL                     CN
)@@G@@  . # OF ARGS TO EXAMINE FOR THE LIST     @G@@@@          DSL       A0,7CO
)@@G@@2             . A0 = LIST LENGTH; A1 = ARG COUNT@E@@@@LIST010   LA      CP
)@@G@@  A2,VDM+SRA        . GET RIGHT ARG MODE  @E@@@@          TE,U      A2,MCQ
)@@G@@ODNUL         . IS THIS ARG NULL?   @F@@@@          AA,U      A0,1      CR
)@@G@@        . NO, INCR THE LIST LENGTH  @G@@@@          JNE       A3,VDOR+SOCS
)@@G@@P LIST020 . ESCAPE IF NOT OUR OPERATOR    @E@@@@          AA,U      A1,1CT
)@@G@@              . INCR THE ARG COUNT  @F@@@@          POP       2         CU
)@@G@@        . EXAMINE NEXT OPER+ARG DOWN@C@@@@          J         LIST010   CV
)@@G@@        . GO TRY  @F@@@@LIST020   S         STKPTR,LISTSP     . SAVE CORCW
)@@G@@RECT STACK POINTER@G@@@@          DS        A0,LISTNUM        . SAVE LISCX
)@@G@@T LENGTH, ARG COUNT     @D@@@@          LSSL      A0,1              . = CY
)@@G@@LENGTH*2    @E@#@@          TGET                        . GET THE TEMP SCZ
)@@G@@PACE  @B@#@@          JNZ       A5,LIST999        .   @E@@@#          M$DA
)@@G@@TGET    LIST999           . GET THE TEMP SPACE  @E@@@@          LR      DB
)@@G@@  R1,LISTARGC       . GET THE ARG COUNT   @E@@@@          LA,U      A2,,DC
)@@G@@A1            . GET THE RESULT AREA @D@@@@          LXI,U     A2,2      DD
)@@G@@        . SET INCREMENT @F@@@@LIST030   LA        A0,VDM+SRA        . GEDE
)@@G@@T THE RIGHT ARG MODE    @G@@@@          DL        A3,VD+SRA         . GEDF
)@@G@@T THE RIGHT ARG DESCRIPTOR    @E@@@@          TE,U      A0,MODNUL       DG
)@@G@@  . IS THIS ARG NULL?   @G@@@@          DS        A3,0,*A2          . NODH
)@@G@@, POST AS NEXT LIST ELEMENT   @E@[@@          A,U       STKPTR,2*2      DI
)@@G@@  . LOOK AT NEXT ARG UP @E@@@[          ANX,U     STKPTR,2*STKINC   . SKDJ
)@@G@@IP TO NEXT ARG    @G@@@@          JGD       R1,LIST030        . COUNT ARDK
)@@G@@GS & CONTINUE IF MORE   @F@@@@          LXI       A1,LISTNUM        . SEDL
)@@G@@T LENGTH OF THE LIST    @D@@@@          LA,U      A0,MODLST         . SEDM
)@@G@@T LIST MODE @C@@@@          LSSL      A0,30             . ALIGN   @G@@@@DN
)@@G@@          L         STKPTR,LISTSP     . RECOVER CORRECT STACK POINTER   DO
)@@G@@@E@@@@          DS        A0,VD+SRA         . POST RESULT DESCR   @C@@@@DP
)@@G@@LIST999   RETURN                      . DONE    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@      DQ
)@@G@@    END     ___@@@C@K@[GC8@ +=%8K@@[C8@ +2C@)@@G&;)@@[C80^_0&;0@@[N8K@@DDR
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@]/         M$DEF   @[@@@].     @G@@@]. THIS ELEMENT CONDS
)@@G@@TAINS ROUTINES TO FACILITATE THE CREATION OF VALUE    @G@@@]. DESCRIPTORDT
)@@G@@S FOR FUNCTION, OPERATOR, AND EXECUTED-VARIABLE RESULTS.    @[@@@].     DU
)@@G@@@C@@@]. TO CREATE A SINGLE VALUE, NUMERIC RESULT:     @[@@@].     @^@@@]DV
)@@G@@.  A0 (,A1) = VALUE     @B@@@].  LMJ  X11,M$RESULT(INT,SFL,DFL,DIN)     DW
)@@G@@@^@@@].  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @A@@@].  A0,A1 = RESULT VALUE DESCRIPTOR  DX
)@@G@@@[@@@].     @G@@@]M$RESULTINT* LA,U   A2,MODSIN         . MAKE A SINGLE DY
)@@G@@INTEGER RESULT    @F@@@]          J         NUMRESULT         . GO MAKE DZ
)@@G@@A NUMERIC RESULT  @G@@@]M$RESULTSFL* LA,U   A2,MODSFL         . MAKE A SEA
)@@G@@INGLE FLOATING RESULT   @B@@@]          J         NUMRESULT         .   EB
)@@G@@@G@@@]M$RESULTDFL* LA,U   A2,MODDFL         . MAKE A DOUBLE FLOATING RESEC
)@@G@@ULT   @B@@@]          J         NUMRESULT         .   @G@@@]M$RESULTDIN*ED
)@@G@@ LA,U   A2,MODDIN         . MAKE A DOUBLE INTEGER RESULT    @[@@@].     EE
)@@G@@@#@^@]NUMRESULT ROUTINE @^@@@^NUMRESULT SUBROUTINE    @^@@@]NUMVAL    LOEF
)@@G@@CAL     2   @#@@@]NUMMOD    LOCAL   @D@@@]          DS        A0,NUMVAL EG
)@@G@@        . POST THE VALUE@D@@@]          SA        A2,NUMMOD         . POEH
)@@G@@ST THE MODE @E@#@]          LA,U      A0,1              . GET THIS MANY EI
)@@G@@WORDS @G@#@]          TEP,U     A2,DBLBIT         . UNLESS IT'S DOUBLE PEJ
)@@G@@RECISION    @F@#@]          LA,U      A0,2              . THEN GET THIS EK
)@@G@@MANY WORDS  @G@@@#          LA        A0,VMEWS,A2       . GET THE WORD SEL
)@@G@@IZE OF THE ELEMENT@D@A@]          TGET                        . GO GET'EEM
)@@G@@M     @D@@@A          M$TGET    NUM999            . GET THE SPACE @E@A@]EN
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,NUM999         . CHECK FOR ERRORS    @E@@@]      EO
)@@G@@    DL        A2,NUMVAL         . GET THE RESULT VALUE@E@@@]          LAEP
)@@G@@        A0,NUMMOD         . GET THE RESULT MODE @E@@@]          LXI,U   EQ
)@@G@@  A1,1              . POST THE LENGTH     @G@@@]          SA        A2,,ER
)@@G@@A1            . POST THE FIRST WORD OF THE VALUE@G@#@]          TEP,U   ES
)@@G@@  A0,DBLBIT         . IS THERE ANOTHER WORD OF VALUE? @G@@@#          TNET
)@@G@@DBL     A0                . ARE THERE TWO WORDS OF VALUE?   @E@#@]      EU
)@@G@@    SA        A3,,A1            . YES, POST IT ALSO   @E@@@#          SAEV
)@@G@@        A3,1,A1           . YES, POST IT ALSO   @G@@@]          LSSL    EW
)@@G@@  A0,30             . SLIDE THE MODE INTO POSITION    @C@@@]NUM999    REEX
)@@G@@TURN                      . ALL DONE@[@@@].     @C@@@]. TO CREATE A CHAREY
)@@G@@ACTER VECTOR (STRING) RESULT: @[@@@].     @ @@@].  A0 = STRING BUFFER ADEZ
)@@G@@DRESS @A@@@].  A1 = MAXIMUM # OF CHARS IN STRING@ @@@].  LMJ  X11,M$RESUFA
)@@G@@LT(ASC,ALP) @[@@@].     @[@@@]. AND:@[@@@].     @ @@@].  A2 = MODE (MODAFB
)@@G@@SC, MODALP) @^@@@].  LMJ  X11,M$RESULTSTR @[@@@].     @]@@@]. RETURNS:  FC
)@@G@@@^@@@].  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @A@@@].  A0,A1 = RESULT VALUE DESCRIPTOR  FD
)@@G@@@[@@@].     @G@@@]M$RESULTALP* LA,U   A2,MODALP         . MAKE A FIELDATFE
)@@G@@A STRING RESULT   @ @@@]          J         STRRESULT @G@@@]M$RESULTASC*FF
)@@G@@ LA,U   A2,MODASC         . MAKE AN ASCII STRING RESULT     @]@@@]M$RESUFG
)@@G@@LTSTR*@#@^@]STRRESULT ROUTINE @^@@@^STRRESULT SUBROUTINE    @F@@@]STRADRFH
)@@G@@    LOCAL                       . ADDRESS OF THE STRING     @E@@@]STRLENFI
)@@G@@    LOCAL                       . LENGTH OF THE STRING@E@@@]STRMOD    LOFJ
)@@G@@CAL                       . MODE OF THE STRING  @E@@@]          SA      FK
)@@G@@  A0,STRADR         . SAVE THE ADDRESS    @D@@@]          SA        A2,SFL
)@@G@@TRMOD         . SAVE THE MODE @F@@@]          LA,U      A3,,A1          FM
)@@G@@  . GET THE MAX CHAR COUNT    @G@@@]          LA        A1,M$XFDL       FN
)@@G@@  . GET FIELDATA LOAD TABLE PTR     @E@@@]          LR,U      R1,' '    FO
)@@G@@        . AND A FIELDATA BLANK@F@@@]          LR        R2,M$FDBLANKS   FP
)@@G@@  . GET A WORD OF BLANKS TOO  @F@@@]          JE,U      A2,MODALP STR005FQ
)@@G@@  . SKIP IF FIELDATA STRING   @F@@@]          LA        A1,M$XASL       FR
)@@G@@  . GET ASCII LOAD ROUTINE    @E@@@]          LR,U      R1,$CAS(' ')    FS
)@@G@@  . AND AN ASCII BLANK  @E@@@]          LR        R2,M$ASBLANKS     . GEFT
)@@G@@T A WORD OF BLANKS@F@@@]STR005    LA,U      A2,0              . INITIALIFU
)@@G@@ZE CHAR COUNT     @G@@@]          LA,U      A4,0              . ASSUME MFV
)@@G@@INIMUM OF ZERO CHARS    @G@@@]          JNZ       A3,STR020         . IFFW
)@@G@@ # CHARS NONZERO, START SEARCH@G@@@]          SR        R2,0,A0         FX
)@@G@@  . MAX # CHARS = 0, BLANK IMAGE    @F@@@]          J         STR020    FY
)@@G@@        . SKIP TO COUNT FIRST LOAD  @D@@@]STR010    EX        0,*A1     FZ
)@@G@@        . GET NEXT CHAR @E@@@]          AA,U      A2,1              . COGA
)@@G@@UNT ANOTHER CHAR  @E@@@]          TE        A5,R1             . IS THIS GB
)@@G@@CHAR BLANK  @H@@@]          LA        A4,A2             . NO, REMEMBER LGC
)@@G@@AST NON-BLANK POSITION  @G@@@]STR020    JGD       A3,STR010         . COGD
)@@G@@UNT CHAR, & KEEP GOING IF MORE@E@@@]          SA        A4,STRLEN       GE
)@@G@@  . SAVE STRING LENGTH  @F@#@]          LUF       A0,A4             . A0GF
)@@G@@ = 0, A1 = CHAR COUNT   @E@@@#          LA        A0,A4             . A4GG
)@@G@@ = CHAR COUNT     @E@@@]          LA        A2,STRMOD         . RECOVER GH
)@@G@@THE MODE    @F@#@]          TNE,U     A2,MODALP         . IS THE STRING GI
)@@G@@FIELDATA?   @F@#@]          DI,U      A0,6              . YES, COMPUTE WGJ
)@@G@@ORD COUNT   @E@#@]          TNE,U     A2,MODASC         . IS THE STRING GK
)@@G@@ASCII?@F@#@]          LDSL      A0,36-2           . YES, COMPUTE WORD COGL
)@@G@@UNT   @H@@@#          MI        A0,VMEBS,A2       . COMPUTE TOTAL # OF BGM
)@@G@@ITS IN RESULT     @G@@@#          DI,U      A0,36             . A0 = # WGN
)@@G@@ORDS; A1 = REMAINDER    @E@@@]          TZ        A0                . NOGO
)@@G@@ WORDS IN RESULT? @E@@@]          TZ        A1                . NO, LEFTGP
)@@G@@ OVER CHARS?@F@@@]          AA,U      A0,1              . YES, ADD ANOTHGQ
)@@G@@ER WORD     @E@#@]          TGET                        . GET THAT MANY GR
)@@G@@WORDS @D@#@]          JNZ       A5,STR999         . DIE ON ERRORS @E@@@#GS
)@@G@@          M$TGET    STR999            . GET THAT MANY WORDS @E@#@]      GT
)@@G@@    MOVE      A2,0,A1,U A3,STRADR A0 . MOVE THE STRING@F@ @#          MOGU
)@@G@@VE      A2,0,A1,U A3,STRADR 0,A0,U . MOVE THE STRING  @G@@@           MOGV
)@@G@@VE      A2,0,A1,U A3,STRADR,,W 0,A0,U . MOVE THE STRING     @E@@@]      GW
)@@G@@    LXI       A1,STRLEN         . GET CHAR LENGTH     @ @@@]          LAGX
)@@G@@        A0,STRMOD @B@@@]          LSSL      A0,30             .   @C@@@]GY
)@@G@@STR999    RETURN                      . ALL DONE@[@@@].     @#@@@]      GZ
)@@G@@    END     ___@@@      ======@@^@@ @@@@@@@@@@@@@@ #J)@@@@@]@@@@@@@@@@@@HA
