)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@          M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. M$FUNPCT - IMPLEKR
)@@G@@MENTS THE $PCT FUNCTION.@[@@@@.     @ @@@@. $PCT(#WORDS;FIRST WORD)     KS
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @#@[@@M$FUNPCT* ROUTINE @^@@@[M$FUNPCT* SUBROUTINE    @E@@@@KT
)@@G@@PCTWRDS   LOCAL     2                 . # WORDS DESIRED     @E@@@@PCTFRSKU
)@@G@@T   LOCAL     2                 . FIRST WORD DESIRED  @D@@@@          ARKV
)@@G@@GCHK    PCT999 PCTWRDS PCTMSK 2 . TWO ARGS@E@@@@          LA        A3,VKW
)@@G@@DA+PCTWRDS    . GET # WORDS DESIRED @G@@@@          LMA       A2,,A3    KX
)@@G@@        . = # WORDS FROM THE PCT DESIRED  @E@@@@          TG,U      A2,0KY
)@@G@@1000          . SYSTEM DEFINED LIMIT@E@@@@          LA,U      A2,01000  KZ
)@@G@@        . CAN'T BE LARGER     @E@@@@          PUTANS    PCT999 MODSIN   LA
)@@G@@  . CREATE A RESULT AREA@F@@@@          LA,U      A0,,A1            . GELB
)@@G@@T DATA SPACE ADDRESS    @F@@@@          LXI,U     A1,,A2            . GELC
)@@G@@T WORD COUNT PROPERLY   @E@@@@          LA        A3,VDA+PCTFRST    . GELD
)@@G@@T FIRST ADDRESS   @F@@@@          LA        A2,,A3            . NO, GET LE
)@@G@@FIRST ADDRESS     @C@@@@          TZ        VDL+PCTFRST       . CORRECT?LF
)@@G@@@D@@@@          TP        A2                . IS IT VALID?  @E@@@@      LG
)@@G@@    LA,U      A2,0              . NO, DEFAULT IS ZERO @E@@@@          LXLH
)@@G@@M,U     A1,,A2            . GET FIRST ADDRESS   @F@@@@          ER      LI
)@@G@@  PCT$              . GET PROGRAM CONTROL TABLE @C@@@@          LA,U    LJ
)@@G@@  A5,0              . NO ERROR@C@@@@PCT999    RETURN                    LK
)@@G@@  . DONE    @]@@@@          . @G@@@@PCTMSK    ARGMSK    MODSIN,'CVT' MODLL
)@@G@@SIN,'CVT','OPT' . ARGUMENT MASK     @]@@@@          . @#@@@@          ENLM
)@@G@@D     ___@@@C@@DD+CDG@@AC@KDD<CDX@@A[DW@@A[DH@@ACDX@@AC@)@@LC[Y@@@[[L@@]LN
)@@G@@CC!@@ACC/@@AC[J@@@[[I@@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/         M$DEF   @[@@@@.     LO
)@@G@@@F@@@@. THIS ELEMENT CONTAINS ALL CODE RELATING TO THE USE OF AVL TREES.LP
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @H@@@@. AS CURRENTLY IMPLEMENTED IN THE AVL$ PACKAGE, THE KELQ
)@@G@@Y SIZE IS LIMITED TO    @B@@@@. A SIXTH-WORD VALUE, OR THE RANGE 0..63. LR
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@SSMAXS    EQU       63                . THE MAXIMUM SULS
)@@G@@BSCRIPT SIZE@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. M$NEWTABLE - CREATE A NEW TALT
)@@G@@BLE AND RETURN ITS ADDRESS IN A1.   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@. M$NEWMST - CREATLU
)@@G@@E A NEW MACRO SYMBOL TABLE AND RETURN ITS ADDRESS IN A1.    @[@@@@.     LV
)@@G@@@C@@@@. BOTH ROUTINES RETURN WITH A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0.@[@@@@.     @#@@@@LW
)@@G@@          INSTRS  @]@@@@M$NEWTABLE* @^@@@@          CALL,A3   NEW @E@@@@LX
)@@G@@M$DEFTABLE* AVL$PKT 0,0 '',M$SSCOMPARE . DEFAULT PACKET     @D@@@@M$DEFTLY
)@@G@@ABLEN* EQU    $-M$DEFTABLE      . TABLE LENGTH  @[@@@@.     @]@@@@M$NEWMLZ
)@@G@@ST*   @^@@@@          CALL,A3   NEW @D@@@@M$DEFMST* AVL$PKT   0,0 2     MA
)@@G@@        . DEFAULT PACKET@ @@@@M$DEFMSTLEN* EQU    $-M$DEFMST@[@@@@.     MB
)@@G@@@^@@@@NEW       SUBROUTINE    @#@@@@NEWTMP    LOCAL   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@MC
)@@G@@          SA        A3,NEWTMP         . SAVE LINK TO DEFAULT PACKET     MD
)@@G@@@E@@@@          M$PGET    NEW999 AVLPKL     . GET AN AVL$ PACKET  @I@@@@ME
)@@G@@          MOVE      A2,0,A1,U A3,NEWTMP,,W AVLPKL . MOVE DEF PACKET TO NMF
)@@G@@EW CORE     @D@@@@          LA,U      A5,0              . NO ERRORS     MG
)@@G@@@#@@@@NEW999    RETURN  @[@@@@/.    @C@@@@. M$SSCOMPARE - SUBSCRIPT COMPMH
)@@G@@ARISON ROUTINE    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.  A1 = ADDRESS OF SEARCH SUBSCRIPT MI
)@@G@@(M$SSMODE = MODE OF SAME)     @E@@@@.  A2 = ADDRESS OF CURRENT SUBSCRIPTMJ
)@@G@@ NODE BEING EXAMINED.   @^@@@@.  LMJ X11,M$SSCOMPARE  @]@@@@.  <EQUAL>  MK
)@@G@@@#@@@@.  <(A1) < (A2)>  @#@@@@.  <(A1) > (A2)>  @[@@@@.     @]@@@@M$SSCOML
)@@G@@MPARE @H@@@@          LA        A4,M$SSMODE       . GET CURRENT MODE OF MM
)@@G@@SEARCH SUBSCRIPT  @I@@@@          TNE       A4,SSM,A2         . IS CURREMN
)@@G@@NT NODE MODE SAME AS SEARCH MODE    @F@@@@          J         SSC010    MO
)@@G@@        . YES, DO NORMAL COMPARISON @G@@@@          TG        A4,SSM,A2 MP
)@@G@@        . NO, IS SEARCH MODE GREATER?     @E@@@@          J         2,X1MQ
)@@G@@1             . NO, IT'S LESSER     @E@@@@          J         1,X11     MR
)@@G@@        . YES, IT'S GREATER   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. PERFORM A COMPARISON BMS
)@@G@@ETWEEN SUBSCRIPTS;@[@@@@.     @[@@@@SSC010@D@@@@          DS        A1,SMT
)@@G@@SCA12         . SAVE A1,A2    @E@@@@          LR        R2,AVLKSZ,A2    MU
)@@G@@  . GET THE NODE KEYSIZE@F@@@@          LR        R1,M$SSKS         . GEMV
)@@G@@T THE SUBSCRIPT KEYSIZE @F@@@@          LA,U      A2,SSD,A2         . GEMW
)@@G@@T THE SUBSCRIPT ADDRESS @H@@@@          LA,U      A1,1,A1           . GEMX
)@@G@@T THE ADDRESS OF THE SUBSCRIPT DATA @B@@@@          LXI,U     A2,1      MY
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          LXI,U     A1,1              .   @[@@@@SSC020MZ
)@@G@@@G@@@@          JGD       R2,SSC030         . SKIP IF MORE NODE SUBSCRIPNA
)@@G@@T LEFT@G@@@@          JE,U      A2,,A2 SSC050     . IF NO INCR, THEN THENB
)@@G@@Y'RE EQUAL  @F@@@@          LR        R2,R1             . COPY OTHER REPNC
)@@G@@EAT COUNT   @G@@@@          LA,U      A2,AVLCEX,A0      . GET THE COMPARND
)@@G@@ISON EXTENSION    @D@@@@          J         SSC020            . TRY FOR NE
)@@G@@MORE  @[@@@@SSC030@G@@@@          JGD       R1,SSC040         . SKIP IF NF
)@@G@@MORE SUBSCRIPT LEFT     @H@@@@          JE,U      A1,,A1 SSC050     . IFNG
)@@G@@ NO INCR, THEN SUBSCRIPTS ARE EQUAL @F@@@@          LR        R1,R2     NH
)@@G@@        . COPY OTHER REPEAT COUNT   @E@@@@          LA,U      A1,AVLCEX,NI
)@@G@@A0      . EXTEND WITH FILLER  @[@@@@SSC040@G@@@@          LA        A5,,NJ
)@@G@@*A2           . GET A WORD FROM NODE SUBSCRIPT  @F@@@@          AN      NK
)@@G@@  A5,,*A1           . MINUS SEARCH SUBSCRIPT    @E@@@@          JZ      NL
)@@G@@  A5,SSC020         . LOOP UNTIL NOT EQUAL@G@@@@          JC        $+2 NM
)@@G@@              . NEW SUBSCRIPT < OLD SUBSCRIPTS  @G@@@@          AX,U    NN
)@@G@@  X11,1             . NEW SUBSCRIPT > OLD SUBSCRIPT   @D@@@@          AXNO
)@@G@@,U      X11,1             . (FUDGE RETURN)@[@@@@SSC050@D@@@@          DLNP
)@@G@@        A1,SSCA12         . RESTORE REGS  @E@@@@          J         0,X1NQ
)@@G@@1             . RETURN WITH RESULTS @[@@@@.     @E@@@@SSCA12    VAR     NR
)@@G@@  2                 . SAVE SPOT FOR A1,A2 @[@@@@.     @[@@@@/.    @C@@@@NS
)@@G@@. M$SSFIND - FIND A SUBSCRIPT WITHIN A TREE.    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.  A0 NT
)@@G@@= ADDRESS OF TABLE DESCRIPTOR @D@@@@.  A1 = ADDRESS OF VALUE DESCRIPTOR NU
)@@G@@TO SEARCH FOR     @^@@@@.  LMJ  X11,M$SSFIND    @E@@@@.  A2 = ADDRESS OFNV
)@@G@@ SUBSCRIPT DESCRIPTOR OR 0 IF NOT FOUND   @^@@@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  NW
)@@G@@@^@@@@.  A0,A1 UNCHANGED.     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@M$SSFIND* SUBROUTINE A0,NX
)@@G@@A1    @H@@@@          CALL      SSOI              . SUBSCRIPT OPERATION NY
)@@G@@INITIALIZATION    @E@@@@          JNZ       A5,SSF999         . CHECK FONZ
)@@G@@R ERRORS    @G@@@@          AN,U      A1,1              . SUBSCRIPT DATAOA
)@@G@@ IS AT ORIGIN 1   @D@@@@          AVLSK                       . SEARCH BOB
)@@G@@Y KEY @D@@@@          LA,U      A5,0              . NO ERRORS     @[@@@@OC
)@@G@@SSF999@E@@@@          RETURN                      . A2 HAS ADDRESS OR 0 OD
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. M$SSDELETE - DELETE A SUBSCRIPT WITHIN A TREE @[@@@@OE
)@@G@@.     @A@@@@.  A0 = TABLE DESCRIPTOR ADDRESS    @A@@@@.  A1 = VALUE DESCOF
)@@G@@RIPTOR ADDRESS    @^@@@@.  LMJ X11,M$SSDELETE   @^@@@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OG
)@@G@@OR 0. @[@@@@.     @^@@@@M$SSDELETE* SUBROUTINE  @C@@@@          CALL    OH
)@@G@@  SSOI              . INIT    @ @@@@          JNZ       A5,SSD999 @G@@@@OI
)@@G@@          AN,U      A1,1              . SUBSCRIPT DATA IS AT ORIGIN 1   OJ
)@@G@@@D@@@@          AVLDK                       . DELETE BY KEY @D@@@@      OK
)@@G@@    LA,U      A5,0              . NO ERRORS NOW @F@@@@          JZ      OL
)@@G@@  A2,SSD999         . QUIT IF NO NODE TO RELEASE@F@@@@          CALL    OM
)@@G@@  M$SSNERS          . ERASE A SUBSCRIPT NODE    @D@@@@SSD999    RETURN  ON
)@@G@@                    . THAT'S IT     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. M$SSNDELETE - DEOO
)@@G@@LETE A SUBSCRIPT NODE WITHIN A TREE @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.  A0 = TABLE DESCOP
)@@G@@RIPTOR ADDRESS    @ @@@@.  A1 = SUBSCRIPT NODE ADDRESS@^@@@@.  LMJ  X11,OQ
)@@G@@M$SSNDELETE @^@@@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@M$SSNDELETE*OR
)@@G@@ SUBROUTINE @E@@@@          LA        A2,VDM,A0         . GET MORE OF VAOS
)@@G@@LUE   @D@@@@          LA        A5,PCL('TABLE VALUE EXPECTED.')   @E@@@@OT
)@@G@@          JNE,U     A2,MODTBL SND999  . ERROR IF NOT TABLE  @F@@@@      OU
)@@G@@    LA        A0,VDA,A0         . GET THE TABLE ADDRESS     @E@@@@      OV
)@@G@@    AVLDN                       . DELETE THIS NODE    @F@@@@          CAOW
)@@G@@LL      M$SSNERS          . ERASE A SUBSCRIPT NODE    @#@@@@SND999    REOX
)@@G@@TURN  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. M$SSNERS - ROUTINE TO ERASE A SUBSCRIPT NODE  OY
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@.  A2 = SUBSCRIPT NODE ADDRESS (NOTE! NON-STANDARD CALOZ
)@@G@@LING SEQUENCE)    @^@@@@.  LMJ  X11,M$SSNERS    @^@@@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW PA
)@@G@@OR 0  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@M$SSNERS* ROUTINE @E@@@@SNEVL     LOCAL         PB
)@@G@@              . SAVE THE VALUE LINK @E@@@@          LA        A0,SSVL,A2PC
)@@G@@        . GET THE VALUE LINK  @C@@@@          SA        A0,SNEVL        PD
)@@G@@  . SAVE IT @F@@@@          M$PREL    SNE999 0,A2,U     . RELEASE THE SUPE
)@@G@@BSCRIPT NODE@F@@@@          LA        A0,SNEVL          . RECOVER THE VAPF
)@@G@@LUE LINK    @E@@@@          JZ        A0,SNE999         . IF NO VALUE, EPG
)@@G@@XIT   @F@@@@          DL        A0,VD,A0          . GET THE VALUE DESCRIPH
)@@G@@PTOR  @E@@@@          CALL      M$VDERS           . ERASE THE VALUE     PI
)@@G@@@H@@@@          LA        A0,SNEVL          . NOW ERASE THE VALUE DESCRIPJ
)@@G@@PTOR ITSELF @E@@@@          SA        A5,SNEVL          . SAVE ANY ERRORPK
)@@G@@ MSG  @F@@@@          M$PREL                      . RELEASE THE DESCRIPTPL
)@@G@@OR    @E@@@@          TZ        SNEVL             . PREVIOUS ERROR?     PM
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LA        A5,SNEVL          . YES, GET IT   @C@@@@SNE999PN
)@@G@@    RETURN                      . ALL DONE@[@@@@/.    @D@@@@. M$SSINSERTPO
)@@G@@ - INSERT A NEW SUBSCRIPT INTO A TABLE.   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.  A0 = ADDRPP
)@@G@@ESS OF TABLE DESCRIPTOR @E@@@@.  A1 = ADDRESS OF VALUE DESCRIPTOR TO BECPQ
)@@G@@OME NEW SUBSCRIPT @D@@@@.  A2 = ADDRESS OF NEW VALUE DESCRIPTOR FOR SUBSPR
)@@G@@CRIPT @^@@@@.  LMJ  X11,M$SSINSERT  @^@@@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0. @ @@@@PS
)@@G@@.  A1 = SUBSCRIPT NODE ADDRESS@[@@@@.     @]@@@@M$SSINSERT* @#@@@@      PT
)@@G@@    ROUTINE @E@@@@SSIARGS   LOCAL     2                 . ARGUMENT STORAPU
)@@G@@GE    @E@@@@SSIVDP    EQUF      SSIARGS,,H1       . VALUE DESCRIPTOR PTRPV
)@@G@@@E@@@@SSITDP    EQUF      SSIARGS,,H2       . TABLE DESCRIPTOR PTR@D@@@@PW
)@@G@@SSINA     EQUF      SSIARGS+1,,H1     . NODE ADDRESS  @F@@@@SSISDP    EQPX
)@@G@@UF      SSIARGS+1,,H2     . SUBSCRIPT DESCRIPTOR PTR  @D@@@@SSIERR    EQPY
)@@G@@UF      SSIARGS+1         . ERROR MSG     @G@@@@          DS        A0,SPZ
)@@G@@SIARGS        . SAVE TABLE AND SUBSCRIPT PTRS   @G@@@@          SA      QA
)@@G@@  A2,SSIVDP         . SAVE THE VALUE DESCRIPTOR PTR   @F@@@@          CAQB
)@@G@@LL      SSCHECK           . DO A SUBSCRIPT CHECK FIRST@E@@@@          JNQC
)@@G@@Z       A5,SSI999         . IF ERROR, GO HOME   @G@@@@          LA,U    QD
)@@G@@  A1,0              . INITIALIZE DEFAULT VALUE PTR    @G@@@@          LAQE
)@@G@@        A2,SSIVDP         . RECOVER THE VALUE DESCRIPTOR PTR@F@@@@      QF
)@@G@@    JZ        A2,SSI010         . SKIP IF NO INITIAL VALUE  @G@@@@      QG
)@@G@@    DL        A0,,A2            . GET THE VALUE DESCRIPTOR TO COPY@D@@@@QH
)@@G@@          CALL      M$VDCOPY          . COPY THE VALUE@E@@@@          JNQI
)@@G@@Z       A5,SSI999         . ERROR IF NO CAN DO  @H@@@@SSI010    SA      QJ
)@@G@@  A1,SSIVDP         . SAVE THE VALUE DESCRIPTOR POINTER     @H@@@@      QK
)@@G@@    DL        A0,SSIARGS        . RECOVER THE TABLE & SUBSCRIPT PTRS    QL
)@@G@@@C@@@@          CALL      SSOI              . INIT    @E@@@@          JNQM
)@@G@@Z       A5,SSI900         . CHECK FOR ERRORS    @F@@@@          LA,U    QN
)@@G@@  A0,SSHL,A3        . A0 = # WORDS PER NODE     @H@@@@          M$PGET  QO
)@@G@@  SSI900            . GET A NODE FOR THIS SUBSCRIPT DATA    @H@@@@      QP
)@@G@@    LA        A2,SSISDP         . GET THE ADDRESS OF VALUE DESCRIPTOR   QQ
)@@G@@@D@[@@          LA        A3,VDL,A2         . GET THE LENGTH@F@[@@      QR
)@@G@@    SA        A3,SSL,A1         . POST THE SUBSCRIPT  LENGTH@D@@@@      QS
)@@G@@    LA        A3,VDM,A2         . GET THE MODE  @E@[@@          SA      QT
)@@G@@  A3,SSM,A1         .  POST THE MODE ALSO @E@@@[          SA        A3,SQU
)@@G@@SM,A1         .  POST THE MODE      @H@@@[          LA        A4,M$SSKS QV
)@@G@@        . GET THE SUBSCRIPT KEY SIZE (WORDS)    @H@]@[          MSI,U   QW
)@@G@@  A4,36             . CONVERT TO # OF BITS IN SUBSCRIPT     @H@@@]      QX
)@@G@@    MI,U      A4,36             . CONVERT TO # OF BITS IN SUBSCRIPT     QY
)@@G@@@G@@@[          DI        A4,VMEBS,A3       . DIV BY ELT BIT SIZE = # OFQZ
)@@G@@ ELTS @F@@@#          TG        A4,VDL,A2         . IS ORIGINAL LENGTH LRA
)@@G@@ESS?  @D@@@#          LA        A4,VDL,A2         . YES, USE IT   @F@@@[RB
)@@G@@          SA        A4,SSL,A1         . POST SUBSCRIPT LENGTH     @G@@@@RC
)@@G@@          MOVE      A3,SSD,A1,U A2,VDA,A2 M$SSKS,,W . MOVE THE DATA     RD
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LXI       A1,M$SSKS         . GET # OF WORDS IN THE KEY RE
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LA        A0,SSITDP         . GET THE TABLE DESRIPTOR PTRF
)@@G@@R     @G@@@@          LA        A0,VDA,A0         . GET THE TABLE PACKETRG
)@@G@@ ADDRESS    @D@@@@          AVLIK                       . INSERT BY KEY RH
)@@G@@@G@@@@          JZ        A2,SSI020         . SKIP IF NEW NODE INSERTED RI
)@@G@@OK    @F@@@@          SA        A2,SSINA          . SAVE OLD NODE ADDRESRJ
)@@G@@S     @F@@@@          LA        A3,SSVL,A2        . GET PREVIOUS DATA LIRK
)@@G@@NK    @F@@@@          SZ        SSVL,A2           . & CLEAR TO BE CAREFURL
)@@G@@L     @H@@@@          SA        A3,SSVL,A1        . POST SO DELETE WILL RM
)@@G@@DELETE IT TOO     @E@@@@          LA,U      A2,,A1            . GET NEW RN
)@@G@@NODE ADDRESS@E@@@@          CALL      M$SSNERS          . ERASE THE NEW RO
)@@G@@NODE  @C@@@@          JNZ       A5,SSI900         . ERROR   @G@@@@      RP
)@@G@@    LA        A1,SSINA          . RECOVER THE OLD NODE ADDRESS    @G@@@@RQ
)@@G@@SSI020    LA        A0,SSIVDP         . RECOVER THE VALUE DESCRIPTOR PTRRR
)@@G@@@G@@@@          SA        A0,SSVL,A1        . POST THE SUBSCRIPT VALUE LRS
)@@G@@INK   @H@@@@          LA        A0,SSITDP         . RECOVER THE TABLE DERT
)@@G@@SCRIPTOR POINTER  @D@@@@          LA,U      A5,0              . NO ERRORRU
)@@G@@S     @ @@@@          J         SSI999    @G@@@@SSI900    LA        A0,SRV
)@@G@@SIVDP         . AN ERROR; ERASE COPY OF VALUE   @F@@@@          JZ      RW
)@@G@@  A0,SSI999         . IF NO VALUE, DON'T ERASE  @E@@@@          DL      RX
)@@G@@  A0,,A0            . GET THE DESCRIPTOR  @F@@@@          SA        A5,SRY
)@@G@@SIERR         . SAVE THE ERROR MESSAGE CW @E@@@@          CALL      M$VDRZ
)@@G@@ERS           . ERASE THE VALUE     @G@@@@          LA        A0,SSIVDP SA
)@@G@@        . ERASE THE DESCRIPTOR ITSELF     @B@@@@          M$PREL        SB
)@@G@@              .   @E@@@@          LA        A5,SSIERR         . RECOVER SC
)@@G@@THE ERROR   @D@@@@SSI999    RETURN                      . THAT'S ALL    SD
)@@G@@@[@@@@/.    @H@@@@. M$SSINDEX - ROUTINE TO COMPUTE AN ORDINAL INDEX FOR SE
)@@G@@A SUBSCRIPT IN A TABLE. @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.  A0 = TABLE DESCRIPTOR POINTSF
)@@G@@ER    @A@@@@.  A1 = VALUE DESCRIPTOR POINTER    @^@@@@.  LMJ  X11,M$SSINSG
)@@G@@DEX   @^@@@@.  A0,A1 UNCHANGED;     @A@@@@.  A2 = NODE INDEX OR 0 IF NOTSH
)@@G@@ FOUND@^@@@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0. @[@@@@.     @ @@@@M$SSINDEX* SUBROUTSI
)@@G@@INE A0,A1   @E@@@@          CALL      M$SSFIND          . FIND THE SUBSCSJ
)@@G@@RIPT  @E@@@@          JNZ       A5,SSX999         . CHECK FOR ERRORS    SK
)@@G@@@E@@@@          JZ        A2,SSX999         . CHECK FOR NO NODE   @F@@@@SL
)@@G@@          LA,U      A1,,A2            . XFER NODE ADDRESS TO A1   @E@@@@SM
)@@G@@          AVLCR                       . COMPUTE THE RANK    @D@@@@      SN
)@@G@@    LA,U      A5,0              . NO ERRORS     @C@@@@SSX999    RETURN  SO
)@@G@@                    . ALL DONE@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@. M$SSENTRY SP
)@@G@@- ROUTINE TO RETURN A SUBSCRIPT, GIVEN ITS INDEX, FROM A TABLE.   @[@@@@SQ
)@@G@@.     @^@@@@.  A0 = TABLE DESCRIPTOR@E@@@@.  A1 = VALUE DESCRIPTOR FOR TSR
)@@G@@HE INDEX (MUST BE NUMERIC)    @^@@@@.  LMJ  X11,M$SSENTRY   @^@@@@.  A0,SS
)@@G@@A1 UNCHANGED.     @D@@@@.  A2 = SUBSCRIPT DESCRIPTOR POINTER OR 0 IF NOTST
)@@G@@ FOUND@^@@@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @[@@@@.     @ @@@@M$SSENTRY* SUBROUTSU
)@@G@@INE A0,A1   @E@@@@          CALL      SSCHECK           . CHECK THE ARGUSV
)@@G@@MENTS @E@@@@          JNZ       A5,SSE999         . CHECK FOR ERRORS    SW
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A2,VDA,A1         . GET THE INDEX ADDRESS     SX
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LA        A1,,A2            . GET THE INDEX ITSELF@F@@@@SY
)@@G@@          LA        A0,VDA,A0         . GET THE TABLE ADDRESS     @D@@@@SZ
)@@G@@          AVLSR                       . SEARCH BY RANK@D@@@@          LATA
)@@G@@,U      A5,0              . NO ERRORS     @C@@@@SSE999    RETURN        TB
)@@G@@              . ALL DONE@[@@@@/.    @F@@@@. UTILITY ROUTINE TO INITIALIZTC
)@@G@@E THINGS FOR SUBSCRIPT OPERATIONS   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.  A0=TABLE DESCRITD
)@@G@@PTOR ADDR   @ @@@@.  A1=VALUE DESCRIPTOR ADDR   @#@@@@.  LMJ X11,SSOI   TE
)@@G@@@ @@@@.  A0=TABLE ADDRESS (AVL PKT) @ @@@@.  A1=(#WORDS,SUBSCRIPT ADDR) TF
)@@G@@@^@@@@.  A2=SUBSCRIPT MODE    @ @@@@.  A3=# WORDS IN SUBSCRIPT    @[@@@@TG
)@@G@@.     @^@@@@SSOI      SUBROUTINE    @^@@@@SSOITMP   LOCAL     2   @ @@@@TH
)@@G@@          DS        A0,SSOITMP@G@@@@          CALL      SSCHECK         TI
)@@G@@  . CHECK THE TABLE & SUBSCRIPT     @F@@@@          LA,U      A0,,A1    TJ
)@@G@@        . GET VALUE DESCRIPTOR TO A0@F@@@@          CALL      M$ITEMLENGTK
)@@G@@TH      . CALCULATE IT'S WORD LENGTH@E@@@@          JNZ       A5,SSO999 TL
)@@G@@        . CHECK FOR ERRORS    @H@@@@          TG,U      A0,SSMAXS       TM
)@@G@@  . IS LENGTH GTR THAN MAX SUBSRIPT SIZE? @F@@@@          LA,U      A0,STN
)@@G@@SMAXS         . YES, USE ONLY THIS MUCH   @E@@@@          SA        A0,MTO
)@@G@@$SSKS         . SAVE AS THE KEY SIZE@F@@@@          LA        A3,A0     TP
)@@G@@        . AND SAVE IT HERE ALSO     @D@@@@          DL        A0,SSOITMPTQ
)@@G@@        . RESTORE A0,A1 @G@@@@          LA        A2,VDM,A1         . GETR
)@@G@@T THE SUBSCIPT MODE AGAIN     @F@@@@          SA        A2,M$SSMODE     TS
)@@G@@  . POST FOR THE COMPARATOR   @F@@@@          LA,U      A4,0            TT
)@@G@@  . ASSUME NUMERIC SUBSCRIPT  @E@@@@          TNE,U     A2,MODALP       TU
)@@G@@  . FIELDATA SUBSCRIPT? @G@@@@          LA        A4,M$FDBLANKS     . YETV
)@@G@@S, GET COMPARISON EXTENSION   @E@@@@          TNE,U     A2,MODASC       TW
)@@G@@  . ASCII SUBSCRIPT?    @G@@@@          LA        A4,M$ASBLANKS     . YETX
)@@G@@S, GET COMPARISON EXTENSION   @G@@@@          LA        A0,VDA,A0       TY
)@@G@@  . GET THE PACKET ADDRESS IN A0    @G@@@@          SA        A4,AVLCEX,TZ
)@@G@@A0      . POST THE COMPARISON EXTENSION   @G@@@@          LA        A1,VUA
)@@G@@DA,A1         . GET THE SUBSCRIPT ADDRESS IN A1 @F@@@@          LXI     UB
)@@G@@  A1,A3             . & PLACE THE WORD COUNT TOO@^@@@@          LA,U    UC
)@@G@@  A5,0@#@@@@SSO999    RETURN  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@M$SSMODE  VAR           UD
)@@G@@              . SUBSCRIPT MODE@E@@@@M$SSKS    VAR                       UE
)@@G@@  . SUBSCRIPT KEY SIZE  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. SSCHECK - ENSURE THAT THE TAUF
)@@G@@BLE VD AND SUBSCRIPT VD ARE VALID.  @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.  A0 = TABLE DESCUG
)@@G@@RIPTOR PTR  @A@@@@.  A1 = SUBSCRIPT DESCRIPTOR PTR    @^@@@@.  LMJ  X11,UH
)@@G@@SSCHECK     @^@@@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @^@@@@.  A0,A1 UNCHANGED.     UI
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @]@@@@SSCHECK     @D@@@@          LA,U      A2,MODTBL       UJ
)@@G@@  . GET TABLE MODE@D@@@@          LA        A5,PCL('TABLE VALUE EXPECTEDUK
)@@G@@.')   @E@@@@          JNE       A2,VDM,A0 0,X11   . ERROR IF NOT A TABLEUL
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LA,U      A5,0              . CLEAR ERRORS  @E@@@@      UM
)@@G@@    LA        A2,VDM,A1         . GET SUBSCRIPT MODE  @H@@@@          TEUN
)@@G@@,U      A2,MODLST         . DO WE HAVE A LIST FOR A SUBSCRIPT?    @F@@@@UO
)@@G@@          TNZ       VMEBS,A2          . OR A NON-CANONICAL VALUE? @D@@@@UP
)@@G@@          LA        A5,PCL('ILLEGAL SUBSCRIPT VALUE.')@F@@@@          J UQ
)@@G@@        0,X11             . RETURN (MAYBE WITH ERROR) @]@@@@          . UR
)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     ___@@@    LA        A0,SSIVDP         . AN ERRORUS
)@@G@@; ERASE COPY OF VALUE   @F@@@@          JZ        A0,SSI999         . IFUT
)@@G@@ NO VALUE, DON'T ERASE  @E@@@@          DL      *[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/     UU
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THIS ROUTINE IMPLEMENTS THE 'CSC' COMMANUV
)@@G@@D ALLOWING THE USER TO  @B@@@@. CHANGE HIS SUBSTITUTION CHARACTERS.     UW
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @^@@@@. THE COMMAND SYNTAX IS:@[@@@@.     @^@@@@.   CSC <OPEUX
)@@G@@N> <CLOSE>  @[@@@@.     @G@@@]. WHERE <OPEN> IS THE BEGIN-SUBSTITUTION CUY
)@@G@@HARACTER, AND <CLOSE> IS THE  @G@@@]. END-SUBSTITUTION CHARACTER.  IF ONUZ
)@@G@@LY A SINGLE CHARACTER IS GIVEN, BOTH@C@@@]. BEGIN- AND END-SUBSTITUTION VA
)@@G@@ARE SET TO IT.    @H@]@@. THE <OPEN> IS THE START-SUBSTITUTION CHARACTERVB
)@@G@@; THE DEFAULT IS '[' UPON     @G@]@@. INITIALIZATION.  THE <CLOSE> IS THVC
)@@G@@E STOP-SUBSTITUTION CHARACTER; THE  @#@]@@. DEFAULT IS ']'. @[@@@@.     VD
)@@G@@@G@[@@. IF NO ARGUMENTS ARE GIVEN, THE CURRENT SUBSTITUTION CHARACTERS AVE
)@@G@@RE    @C@[@@. RESET TO THE DEFAULT VALUES OF '[' AND ']'.   @H@]@[. IF NVF
)@@G@@O ARGUMENTS ARE GIVEN, THE SUBSTITUTION CHARACTERS ARE SET TO ZERO,     VG
)@@G@@@H@@@]. IF NO ARGUMENTS ARE GIVEN, THE SUBSTITUTION CHARACTERS ARE SET TVH
)@@G@@O 0777,     @D@@@[. EFFECTIVELY TURNING OFF SYMBOLIC SUBSTITUTIONS.     VI
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @#@[@@M$COMCSC* ROUTINE @^@@@[M$COMCSC* SUBROUTINE    @E@@@@VJ
)@@G@@CSCOPEN   LOCAL                       . OPEN BRACKET CHAR   @E@@@@CSCCLOVK
)@@G@@S   LOCAL                       . CLOSE BRACKET CHAR  @F@@@@          CAVL
)@@G@@LL      M$MORECMD         . MORE COMMAND OUT THERE?   @E@[@@          LAVM
)@@G@@        A1,M$DEFOBC       . GET DEFAULT VALUES  @B@[@@          LA      VN
)@@G@@  A2,M$DEFCBC       .   @G@]@[          DSL       A1,72             . A1VO
)@@G@@,A2=0 (NO SUBSTITUTION CHARS) @E@@@]          LA,U      A1,0777         VP
)@@G@@  . GET IMPOSSIBLE CHAR @F@@@]          LA,U      A2,0777           . (NVQ
)@@G@@O SUBSTITUTION CHARS)   @I@@@@          JZ        A0,CSC010         . SKVR
)@@G@@IP AND STORE DEFAULTS IF NO MORE ARGS     @F@@@@          T$NFIND   ' ' VS
)@@G@@              . FIND THE NEXT NON-BLANK   @E@@@@          SA        A2,CVT
)@@G@@SCOPEN        . POST THE OPEN VALUE @F@@@@          T$NFIND   ' '       VU
)@@G@@        . FIND THE NEXT ONE ALSO    @F@@@@          TP        A3        VV
)@@G@@        . WAS THERE REALLY A CHAR?  @F@@@@          LA        A2,CSCOPENVW
)@@G@@        . NO, DEFAULT IS OPEN CHAR  @E@@@@          SA        A2,CSCCLOSVX
)@@G@@        . POST CLOSE CHAR     @E@@@@          DL        A1,CSCOPEN      VY
)@@G@@  . GET THE NEW CHARS   @F@#@@CSC010    SA        A1,M$OBC          . POVZ
)@@G@@ST THE GLOBAL CHARS     @C@#@@          SA        A2,M$CBC          . DOWA
)@@G@@NE    @F@@@#CSC010    DL        A0,A1             . GET OBC,CBC INTO A0,WB
)@@G@@A1    @D@^@#          CALL      M$SETCSC          . SET THE CHARS @D@@@^WC
)@@G@@          CALL      M$CSCSET          . SET THE CHARS @D@@@@          LAWD
)@@G@@,U      A5,0              . NO ERRORS     @C@@@@          RETURN        WE
)@@G@@              . ALL DONE@[@@@@.     @#@@@@          END     ___@@@R]0@[HWF
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@A/         M$DEF   @G@@@A          FIDEF$    M$ELT$    WG
)@@G@@        . GET EQUFS ON OUR ELT$ PACKET    @[@@@A.     @C@@@A. M$SCANCMD WH
)@@G@@- ROUTINE TO SCAN THE COMMAND FIELD.@[@@@A.     @^@@@A.  LMJ  X11,M$SCANWI
)@@G@@CMD   @^@@@A.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @E@@@A.  A0,A1 = COMMAND NAME OR 0 IWJ
)@@G@@F ANY FILENAME SPECS PRESENT. @A@@@A.  A2 = COMMAND NAME LENGTH (ALWAYS)WK
)@@G@@@[@@@A.     @G@@@A. IN ADDITION, M$COMMA MAY BE SET IF THE COMMAND WAS TWL
)@@G@@ERMINATED WITH    @H@@@A. AN OPTION FIELD; M$LABEL WILL CONTAIN THE 12 CWM
)@@G@@HARACTER FIELDATA LABEL IF    @[@@@A. ANY.@[@@@A.     @E@@@A. THE MACRO WN
)@@G@@COMPILER WILL CALL THE M$SCANCCMD ENTRY POINT.  @[@@@A.     @F@@@AM$SCANWO
)@@G@@CCMD* LA,U    A0,1              . SET THE COMPILER FLAG     @^@@@A      WP
)@@G@@    J         SCAN@F@@@AM$SCANCMD* LA,U     A0,0              . CLEAR THWQ
)@@G@@E COMPILER FLAG   @]@@@A          . @#@C@ASCAN      ROUTINE @^@@@CSCAN  WR
)@@G@@    SUBROUTINE    @F@@@ASCNCMP    LOCAL                       . SET THE WS
)@@G@@COMPILER FLAG     @F@@@A          SA        A0,SCNCMP         . POST THEWT
)@@G@@ COMPILER FLAG    @E@@@A          SZ        M$COMMA           . CLEAR DEWU
)@@G@@LIMITER     @D@@@A          SZ        M$LABEL           . CLEAR LABEL   WV
)@@G@@@ @@@B          SZ        M$LABEL+1 @F@@@A          SZ        M$SCANFLAGWW
)@@G@@        . CLEAR M$SCANPRIM FLAGS    @E@@@A          SZ        ELT$      WX
)@@G@@        . CLEAR ANY ELT$ STUFF@D@@@A          SZ        ELT$+1          WY
)@@G@@  . CLEAR THIS TOO@G@@@A          JNZ       A0,SCN010         . IF COMPIWZ
)@@G@@LING, DON'T PRESCAN     @F@@@A          LA        A0,M$PRESCAN      . GEXA
)@@G@@T THE PRESCAN ADDRESS   @F@@@A          JZ        A0,SCN010         . SKXB
)@@G@@IP IF NO PRESCAN ROUTINE@C@@@A          LMJ       X11,,A0           . CAXC
)@@G@@LL IT @E@@@A          JNZ       A5,SCN999         . CHECK FOR ERRORS    XD
)@@G@@@F@@@A          JNZ       A4,SCN999         . A4<>0 -> SCANNING IS DONE XE
)@@G@@@D@@@ASCN010    DL        A0,M$FDBLANKS     . GET BLANKS    @E@@@A      XF
)@@G@@    DS        A0,ENAME          . SET AS ELEMENT NAME @E@@@A          T$XG
)@@G@@NSEEK   ' ' SCN030        . SCAN FOR NON-BLANK  @F@@@A          T$COLN  XH
)@@G@@                    . GET THE COLUMN POSITION   @C@@@A          SA      XI
)@@G@@  A0,M$COMCOLUMN    . SAVE IT @G@@@A          TNZ       SCNCMP          XJ
)@@G@@  . IS THE COMPILER CALLING US?     @H@@@A          TZ        M$COMLINE XK
)@@G@@        . NO, IS THIS COMMAND FROM A MACRO?     @F@@@A          LA,U    XL
)@@G@@  A0,0              . YES, KILL EVAL EFFECTS    @E@@@A          TZ      XM
)@@G@@  M$CALCFLAG        . IS CALCULATOR ON?   @I@@@A          JNZ       A0,SXN
)@@G@@CN130         . YES, GO FUDGE COMMAND IF LEADING BLANKS     @E@@@A      XO
)@@G@@    T$NBRKF   ENAME NAMASK 13   . SCAN COMMAND NAME   @E@@@A          SAXP
)@@G@@        A4,ENL            . SAVE NAME LENGTH    @G@@@A          LA      XQ
)@@G@@  A5,PCL('COMMAND NAME TOO LONG') . GET ERR MESSAGE   @F@@@A          JZXR
)@@G@@        A2,SCN999         . ERROR IF END OF FIELD     @G@@@A          JEXS
)@@G@@,U      A2,2 SCN030       . SKIP IF EOC, ONLY COMMAND NAME  @F@@@A      XT
)@@G@@    LA,U      A2,,A3            . BREAK CHAR IS STILL IN A3 @F@@@A      XU
)@@G@@    TSE,S1    A2,0,A3 1,BRKTBL,BRKTAB  . FIND THE BREAK CHAR@F@B@A      XV
)@@G@@    J         SCN900            . NO FIND, SYNTAX ERROR     @H@@@B      XW
)@@G@@    LA,U      A3,BRKTAB         . USE DEFAULT BREAK CHAR FOR NO-FINDS   XX
)@@G@@@F@@@A          LA,S3     A5,0,A3           . GET BREAK CHAR TYPE FLAG  XY
)@@G@@@F@@@A          LX,H2     X11,0,A3          . GET THE BREAK CHAR ROUTINEXZ
)@@G@@@I@@@A          JZ        A5,0,X11          . IF TYPE=0, ALWAYS PROCESS YA
)@@G@@THE BREAK CHAR    @C@@@A          TNE,U     A5,1              . TYPE 1? YB
)@@G@@@H@@@A          JNZ       A4,SCN060         . YES, IF CHARS STORED, TRY YC
)@@G@@FILENAME    @C@@@A          TNE,U     A5,2              . TYPE 2? @H@@@AYD
)@@G@@          JNZ       A4,SCN900         . YES, IF CHARS STORED, SYNTAX ERRYE
)@@G@@OR    @C@@@A          TNE,U     A5,3              . TYPE 3? @H@@@A      YF
)@@G@@    JZ        A4,SCN900         . YES, IF NO CHARS STORED, SYNTAX ERROR YG
)@@G@@@G@@@A          J         0,X11             . OTHERWISE, PROCESS BREAK CYH
)@@G@@HAR   @]@@@A          . @B@@@A          .         BLANK BREAK CHARACTER YI
)@@G@@@]@@@A          . @G@@@ASCN020    T$SKIP    -1                . BACKUP FYJ
)@@G@@OR SUBSEQUENT SCANS     @]@@@A          . @H@@@A          .         NORMYK
)@@G@@AL COMMAND SCANNED; RETURN IT IN A0,A1 & LENGTH IN A2.@]@@@A          . YL
)@@G@@@E@@@ASCN030    T$COLN                      . GET CURRENT POSITION@E@@@AYM
)@@G@@          SA        A0,M$SCANCOLUMN   . POST FOR GLOBAL INFO@F@@@A      YN
)@@G@@    LA        A2,ENL            . GET LENGTH OF COMMAND NAME@D@@@A      YO
)@@G@@    DL        A0,ENAME          . GET THE NAME  @D@@@A          J       YP
)@@G@@  SCN990            . GO HOME NICELY@]@@@A          . @E@@@A          . YQ
)@@G@@        PERIOD BREAK CHARACTER ENCOUNTERED.     @]@@@A          . @F@B@AYR
)@@G@@SCN040    T$CHAR                      . GET THE NEXT CHAR AFTER   @F@@@BYS
)@@G@@SCN040    T$CHARN                     . GET THE NEXT CHAR AFTER   @C@@@BYT
)@@G@@          TP        A3                . EOC?    @F@@@B          LA,U    YU
)@@G@@  A3,' '            . YES, PRETEND IT'S BLANK   @D@@@A          LA,U    YV
)@@G@@  A2,,A3            . FD CHAR ONLY  @G@@@A          JNE,U     A2,' ' SCNYW
)@@G@@060     . IF NOT '. ', GO SCAN FILENAME   @F@@@A          LA,U      A2,'YX
)@@G@@.'            . RESTORE THE COMMAND CHAR  @]@@@A          . @F@@@A      YY
)@@G@@    .         BREAK-CHARACTER COMMAND FOUND (*, ., ?, !)    @]@@@A      YZ
)@@G@@    . @G@@@ASCN050    LA,U      A0,,A2            . GET THE FD BREAK CHAZA
)@@G@@R IN A0     @F@@@A          LA        A1,M$FDBLANKS     . GET SOME BLANKZB
)@@G@@S IN A1     @F@@@A          LDSL      A0,30             . LEFT JUSTIFY BZC
)@@G@@LANK FILL   @C@@@A          SA        A0,ENAME          . POST IT @D@@@AZD
)@@G@@          LA,U      A2,1              . GET LENGTH    @D@@@A          SAZE
)@@G@@        A2,ENL            . POST IT TOO   @D@@@A          J         SCN0ZF
)@@G@@30            . GO FINISH UP  @]@@@A          . @B@@@A          .       ZG
)@@G@@  SCAN FOR A FILENAME   @]@@@A          . @F@@@ASCN060    LA        A0,MZH
)@@G@@$COMCOLUMN    . GET ORIGINAL SCAN POSITION@F@@@A          T$COL         ZI
)@@G@@              . MOVE TO THAT POSITION     @E@@@A          LMJ       X11,ZJ
)@@G@@M$SCANFILE    . SCAN FOR A FILENAME @D@@@D          JNZ       A5,SCN999 ZK
)@@G@@        . IF ERROR, EXIT@E@@@A          T$COLN                      . GEZL
)@@G@@T CURRENT POSITION@E@@@A          SA        A0,M$SCANCOLUMN   . POST FORZM
)@@G@@ GLOBAL INFO@D@@@A          DSL       A0,72             . CLEAR THE NAMEZN
)@@G@@@D@@@A          LA        A2,ENL            . GET LENGTH    @F@@@D      ZO
)@@G@@    JNZ       A2,SCN990         . EXIT IF ELT NAME PRESENT  @D@@@D      ZP
)@@G@@    LA        A5,PCL('MISSING MACRO NAME.')     @E@@@D          J       ZQ
)@@G@@  SCN910            . GO PRODUCE ERRORS   @F@D@A          J         SCN9ZR
)@@G@@99            . RETURN (MAYBE WITH ERROR) @]@@@A          . @E@@@A      ZS
)@@G@@    .         COMMA BREAK CHARACTER; SET OPTIONS FLAG.@]@@@A          . ZT
)@@G@@@E@@@ASCN070    SA        A2,M$COMMA        . SET DELIMITER FLAG  @E@@@AZU
)@@G@@          J         SCN030            . RETURN SCANNED NAME @]@@@A      ZV
)@@G@@    . @H@@@A          .         COLON BREAK CHAR: CHECK FOR EITHER A LABZW
)@@G@@EL OR ASSIGNMENT. @]@@@A          . @H@@@ASCN080    JEZ       M$LETOPT SZX
)@@G@@CN090   . IF 'LET' NOT OPTIONAL, CHECK LABEL    @E@B@A          T$COLN  ZY
)@@G@@                    . GET CURRENT POSITION@E@B@A          SA        A0,AZZ
)@@G@@5             . SAVE IT TEMPORARILY @E@B@A          T$CHAR              AA
)@@G@@        . GET '=' (HOPEFULLY) @E@@@B          T$CHARN                   AB
)@@G@@  . GET '=' (HOPEFULLY) @E@@@A          LA,U      A2,,A3            . GEAC
)@@G@@T FD CHAR INTO A2 @G@@@A          JE,U      A2,'=' SCN110     . SKIP IF AD
)@@G@@IT'S ASSIGNMENT OPR     @]@@@A          . @ @@@A          .         A LAAE
)@@G@@BEL   @]@@@A          . @H@@@BSCN090    JNEZ      M$LABEL SCN900    . SYAF
)@@G@@NTAX ERROR IF LABEL ALREADY GIVEN   @G@B@ASCN090    JNEZ      M$LABEL SCAG
)@@G@@N100    . IF A LABEL ALREADY GIVEN, ERROR @D@@@A          DL        A0,EAH
)@@G@@NAME          . GET THE LABEL @C@@@A          DS        A0,M$LABEL      AI
)@@G@@  . POST IT @D@@@A          J         SCN010            . GO SCAN AGAIN AJ
)@@G@@@]@B@A          . @C@B@A          .         ILLEGAL LABEL OR MISSING LETAK
)@@G@@@]@B@A          . @F@B@ASCN100    T$COL     A5,,W             . REPOSITIAL
)@@G@@ON AT BAD CHAR    @G@B@A          J         SCN900            . GO PRODUAM
)@@G@@CE SYNTAX ERROR MESSAGE @]@@@A          . @D@@@A          .         ASSUAN
)@@G@@ME THE OMITTED 'LET' COMMAND. @]@@@A          . @G@@@ASCN110    T$COL   AO
)@@G@@  M$COMCOLUMN,,W    . REPOSITION PREVIOUS TO MAIN SCAN@E@@@A          DLAP
)@@G@@        A0,('LET'DL)      . GET ASSUMED COMMAND @B@@@A          LA,U    AQ
)@@G@@  A2,3              .   @E@@@A          DS        A0,ENAME          . POAR
)@@G@@ST FOR GOOD LUCK  @E@@@A          SA        A2,ENL            . POST THEAS
)@@G@@ LENGTH TOO @D@@@A          J         SCN030            . RETURN NICELY AT
)@@G@@@]@@@A          . @F@@@A          .         '[' OR '(' FOUND; ASSUME THEAU
)@@G@@ 'LET' COMMAND.   @]@@@A          . @G@@@ASCN120    JEZ       M$LETOPT SAV
)@@G@@CN900   . IF 'LET' NOT OPTIONAL, ERROR    @G@@@A          J         SCN1AW
)@@G@@10            . GO ASSUME THE 'LET' COMMAND     @]@@@A          . @E@@@AAX
)@@G@@          .         IN EVAL MODE: ASSUME "DISPLAY" COMMAND. @]@@@A      AY
)@@G@@    . @E@@@ASCN130    DL        A0,('DISPLAY'DL)  . GET THE COMMAND     AZ
)@@G@@@E@@@A          DS        A0,ENAME          . POST IN THE PACKET  @F@@@ABA
)@@G@@          LA,U      A2,7              . AND GET THE LENGTH TOO    @E@@@ABB
)@@G@@          SA        A2,ENL            . POST THE LENGTH     @D@@@A      BC
)@@G@@    J         SCN990            . WE'RE DONE    @]@@@A          . @A@@@ABD
)@@G@@          .         SYNTAX ERROR    @]@@@A          . @C@@@ASCN900    LABE
)@@G@@        A5,PCL('SYNTAX ERROR') .    @G@E@A          T$COLN              BF
)@@G@@        . GET CURRENT COLUMN POSITION     @G@@@ESCN910    T$COLN        BG
)@@G@@              . GET CURRENT COLUMN POSITION     @H@D@A          TNZ     BH
)@@G@@  SCNCMP            . IF COMPILING, DON'T PRODUCE ERROR     @H@E@DSCN910BI
)@@G@@    TNZ       SCNCMP            . IF COMPILING, DON'T PRODUCE ERROR     BJ
)@@G@@@H@@@E          TNZ       SCNCMP            . IF COMPILING, DON'T PRODUCBK
)@@G@@E ERROR     @F@@@A          CALL      M$ERRMSGBLD       . BUILD AN ERRORBL
)@@G@@ MESSAGE    @E@@@A          J         SCN999            . RETURN BAD NEWBM
)@@G@@S     @]@@@A          . @^@@@ASCN990    LA,U      A5,0@#@@@ASCN999    REBN
)@@G@@TURN  @[@@@A.     @F@@@A. NAMASK IS USED FOR THE INITIAL NAME SCAN. IT CBO
)@@G@@ONSISTS OF ONLY   @E@@@A. LEGAL ELEMENT NAME CHARACTERS: LETTERS, NUMBERBP
)@@G@@S, AND '$'. @H@@@A. OTHER CHARACTERS ACT AS BREAKCHARS WHICH ARE RECOGNIBQ
)@@G@@ZED IN THE BREAKCHAR    @#@@@A. TABLE BELOW.    @[@@@A.     @#@@@A      BR
)@@G@@    LITS    @E@@@ANAMASK    T$MASKR   'LET' 'NUM' '$'   . ELEMENT NAME SBS
)@@G@@TUFF  @[@@@A.     @F@@@A. BELOW IS A SPECIAL TABLE TO HANDLE BREAK CHARABT
)@@G@@CTER ANALYSIS     @[@@@A.     @B@@@A. S1 IS THE BREAK CHARACTER TO PROCEBU
)@@G@@SS.   @D@@@A. S2 IS A POSSIBLE MATCHING CHARACTER FOR BALANCING.  @A@@@ABV
)@@G@@. S3 IS A BREAK CHARACTER TYPE:     @C@@@A.    0 = ALWAYS PROCESS THE BRBW
)@@G@@EAK CHARACTER     @E@@@A.    1 = IF A4 (# CHARS STORED) <> 0, TRY FILENABX
)@@G@@ME SCAN     @A@@@A.    2 = IF A4 <> 0, SYNTAX ERROR   @A@@@A.    3 = IF BY
)@@G@@A4 = 0, SYNTAX ERROR    @C@@@A. H2 IS THE BREAK CHARACTER PROCESSING ROUBZ
)@@G@@TINE  @[@@@B.     @F@@@B. THE FIRST BREAK CHARACTER IN THE TABLE IS USEDCA
)@@G@@ AS A DEFAULT     @A@@@B. FOR UNRECOGNIZED BREAK CHARACTERS.@[@@@A.     CB
)@@G@@@ @@@ABC        FORM      6,6,6,18  +@@@@[@K@B@A^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)CL#^@)^@)CC
)@@G@@^@)^@)^8_^8? )2 -NCTIA@5A@)^@)^@) 0)D[DETOD9MFC)CTJD(HCDIC))EDPC(MFC)^@)CD
)@@G@@+@@@@@@F@@@BBRKTAB    BC        '?',,2,SCN050     . HISTORY COMMAND QUERCE
)@@G@@Y     @C@B@ABRKTAB    BC        ' ',,0,SCN020     . BLANK   @C@@@B      CF
)@@G@@    BC        ' ',,0,SCN020     . BLANK   @E@@@A          BC        '.',CG

)@@G@@^@)^@)CC0 -H^-SEDOD([CTM*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@          M$DEF   @[@@@@.     GO
)@@G@@@G@@@@. THIS PROGRAM ATTEMPTS TO ASSIGN THE FILE IN THE CURRENT ELTPKT PGP
)@@G@@ACKET @B@@@@. IT WILL DIAGNOSE A PERMISSIONS ERROR    @F@@@@. THE FILNAMGQ
)@@G@@E IS KEPT IN A GLOBAL CALLED M$FINAME AND THE FREE    @B@@@@. CODE IS KEGR
)@@G@@PT IN A GLOBAL CALLED M$FIFREE@[@@@@.     @B@@@@.  ON ENTRY A0 = FIASG PGS
)@@G@@ERMISSIONS BITS   @[@@@@.     @#@[@@M$ASGFILE* ROUTINE@^@@@[M$ASGFILE* SGT
)@@G@@UBROUTINE   @^@@@@ASGA3     LOCAL     1   @^@@@@ASGA5     LOCAL     1   GU
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LSSL      A0,18             . SHIFT BITS UP @D@@@@      GV
)@@G@@    LXM,U     A0,M$ELT$         . GET PACKET    @D@@@@          FIASG   GW
)@@G@@                    . CALL FIASG$   @D@@@@          DS        A1,M$FINAMGX
)@@G@@E       . STORE NAME    @E@@@@          S         A4,M$FIFREE       . STGY
)@@G@@ORE FREE CODE     @F@@@@          JN        A3,ASG910         . EXIT IF GZ
)@@G@@FILE NOT ASSIGNED @G@@@@          JZ        A5,ASG999         . RETURN IHA
)@@G@@F NO PERMISSIONS ERRORS @E@@@@          LA        A2,A5             . GEHB
)@@G@@T THE ERROR CODE  @F@@@@          LA        A5,ASGRWM-1,A2    . GET THE HC
)@@G@@APPROPRIATE WORD  @D@@@@          M$EOPEN   M$EPKT M$IMAGE    . OPEN EDIHD
)@@G@@TING  @E@@@@          E$FD1     A5                . INSERT READ OR WRITEHE
)@@G@@@E@@@@          E$MSG     (' PERMISSION NOT AVAILABLE ON &*&.&')  @E@@@@HF
)@@G@@          E$FD2     FIPKT$+4          . INSERT THE QUALIFIER@#@@@@      HG
)@@G@@    E$MSGR  @E@@@@          E$FD2     FIPKT$+2          . INSERT THE FILHH
)@@G@@ENAME @#@@@@          E$MSGR  @G@@@@          M$EAWX                    HI
)@@G@@  . GET ACESS WORD AND CLOSE EDIT   @E@@@@          LA,U      A3,0      HJ
)@@G@@        . CLEAR ANY CSF$ BITS @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. FREE THE FILE AND RETUHK
)@@G@@RN    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@ASG910.     @C@@@@          S         A3,ASGA3  HL
)@@G@@        . SAVE A3 @D@@@@          SA        A5,ASGA5          . SAVE A5 HM
)@@G@@TOO   @F@@@@          L,U       A0,M$FINAME       . GET ADDRESS OF PACKEHN
)@@G@@T     @D@]@@          LMJ       X11,M$FREEFILE    . FREE THE FILE @D@@@]HO
)@@G@@          CALL      M$FREEFILE        . FREE THE FILE @E@]@@          LMHP
)@@G@@J       X11,M$PRTCOM      . PRINT THE COMMAND   @G@@@]          TZ      HQ
)@@G@@  M$COMLINE         . IF COMMAND WITHIN MACRO, THEN...@E@@@]          CAHR
)@@G@@LL      M$PRTCOM          . PRINT THE COMMAND   @D@]@@          L       HS
)@@G@@  A3,ASGA3          . GET CSF$ BITS @D@@@]          LA        A1,ASGA3  HT
)@@G@@        . GET CSF$ BITS @E@@@@          LA        A5,ASGA5          . ANHU
)@@G@@D GET A5 BACK TOO @E@]@@          JZ        A3,ASG999         . QUIT IF HV
)@@G@@NO CSF$ BITS@E@@@]          JP        A1,ASG999         . QUIT IF NO CSFHW
)@@G@@$ BITS@E@@@]          LSSL      A1,1              . REMOVE UGLY BIT 35  HX
)@@G@@@E@@@]          SSL       A1,1              . OK, THAT'S BETTER   @F@]@@HY
)@@G@@          LA        A1,A3             . GET NEW CSF$ BITS HERE    @E@@@@HZ
)@@G@@          LA,U      A0,FIPKT$+2       . ADDRESS OF IMAGE    @E@]@@      IA
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,M$ERRCSF      . CALL THE ERROR REP  @E@@@]          CAIB
)@@G@@LL      M$ERRCSF          . CALL THE ERROR REP  @F@]@@          LA,U    IC
)@@G@@  A5,$              . NOTHING ERROR MESSAGE     @F@@@]          LA,U    ID
)@@G@@  A5,1              . NOTHING ERROR MESSAGE     @#@@@@ASG999    RETURN  IE
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @^@@@@. ROUTINE TO FREE A FILE@D@@@@.    PASS IT THE ADDRESSIF
)@@G@@ IN A0 OF A 3 WORD PACKET     @C@@@@.     THE FIRST TWO CONTAIN THE FILEIG
)@@G@@NAME AND THE@A@@@@.     THIRD CONTAINS THE FREE CODE  @[@@@@.     @^@[@@IH
)@@G@@M$FREEFILE* ROUTINE     @^@@@[M$FREEFILE* SUBROUTINE  @E@@@@          L II
)@@G@@        A3,A0             . GET PACKET ADDRESS  @D@@@@          DL      IJ
)@@G@@  A1,0,A3           . GET FILENAME  @E@@@@          L,S6      A0,2,A3   IK
)@@G@@        . GET THE FREE CODE   @E@@@@          SZ,S6     2,A3            IL
)@@G@@  . CLEAR THE FREE CODE @D@@@@          FIFREE                      . FRIM
)@@G@@EE THE FILE @#@@@@          RETURN  @[@@@@.     @ @@@@ASGRWM    'READ'  IN
)@@G@@  . A5 = 1  @ @@@@          'WRITE'   . A5 = 2  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     IO
)@@G@@@ @@@@. GLOBAL NAME AND FREE CODE   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. NOTE ORDERING ISIP
)@@G@@ IMPORTANT  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@M$FINAME* VAR       2                 . M$IQ
)@@G@@FIFREE MUST FOLLOW M$FINAME!  @F@@@@M$FIFREE* VAR       1               IR
)@@G@@  . THIS MUST FOLLOW INAME!   @B@@@@          END                       IS
)@@G@@  .   ___@@@@#5@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@5]@@@@@@@@@@@@@@#00;@#[L;:@@@@@@EWMGS'IT

)@@G@@.     @F@@@[. THIS IS CENTRAL PRINT CONTROL.  EVERYTHING COMES THROUGH HOA
)@@G@@ERE SO@G@@@[. ALTERNATE PRINT FILES (SITE,CSITE) MAY BE IMPLEMENTED. TYPOB
)@@G@@E IS A FLAG @G@@@[. AS TO WHETHER THE IMAGE IS A DATA (DUMP) TYPE PRINT OC
)@@G@@OR A DIAGNOSTIC   @G@@@[. TYPE PRINT, WHICH COMES OUT ON THE TERMINAL EVOD
)@@G@@EN THOUGH A SITE MAY BE @A@@@[. ACTIVE.  FLAG IS 0=DATA 1=DIAG    @[@@@[OE
)@@G@@.     @[@@@[.     @C@@@[. PRINT THE CURRENT COMMAND (IF NOT YET PRINTED)OF
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @B@]@[M$PRTCOM* ROUTINE                     .   @B@@@]M$PRTCOG
)@@G@@OM* SUBROUTINE                  .   @F@@@[PRTAW     LOCAL               OH
)@@G@@        . ORIGINAL IMAGE ACCESS WORD@F@@@[PRTLN     LOCAL               OI
)@@G@@        . LINE NUMBER OF COMMAND    @F@@@[PRTIMG    LOCAL     ASIMAX    OJ
)@@G@@        . A LITTLE IMAGE BUFFER     @G@@@[          L,S3      A0,M$PRTAXOK
)@@G@@W       . HAVE WE ALREADY PRINTED IT ?    @E@@@[          JZ        A0,POL
)@@G@@RT999         . YES - DONT AGAIN    @F@@@[          L         A1,M$PRTAXOM
)@@G@@W       . GET PRINT$ CONTROL WORD   @E@@@[          SA        A1,PRTAW  ON
)@@G@@        . SAVE ACCESS WORD    @F@@@[          LA        A0,M$XQTMACRO   OO
)@@G@@  . GET LINK TO CURRENT MACRO @G@@@[          JZ        A0,PRT010       OP
)@@G@@  . IF NO CURRENT MACRO, SKIP AHEAD @F@@@[          JEZ       M$COMLINE OQ
)@@G@@PRT010  . OR IF KEYBOARD COMMAND    @E@@@[          LA        A1,MXLN,A0OR
)@@G@@        . GET CURRENT LINE #  @E@@@[          SA        A1,PRTLN        OS
)@@G@@  . SAVE LINE NUMBER    @E@@@[          LA,U      A1,PRTIMG         . GEOT
)@@G@@T IMAGE ADDRESS   @G@@@[          LXI,U     A1,ASIMAX         . BUILD ANOU
)@@G@@ ACCESS CONTROL WORD    @E@@@[          M$EOPENA  M$EPKT            . OPOV
)@@G@@EN ASCII EDIT MODE@D@@@[          LA,U      A0,1              . GET A BIOW
)@@G@@T     @E@@@[          SA        A0,EASCIN         . SET ASCII INPUT     OX
)@@G@@@E@@@[          E$DECF    4,PRTLN           . INSERT THE LINE #   @ @@@[OY
)@@G@@          E$CHAR    $CAS(':') @B@ @[          E$SKIP    2               OZ
)@@G@@  .   @F@@@           E$COL     COMORIGIN         . GO TO THE COMMAND ORPA
)@@G@@IGIN  @G@ @[          E$COLN                      . GET THE CURRENT COLUPB
)@@G@@MN POSITION @E@]@[          AA        A0,M$SCNORIG      . INCREMENT THE PC
)@@G@@ORIGIN@E@#@]          AA        A0,M$SCANORIGIN   . INCREMENT THE ORIGINPD
)@@G@@@E@]@[          SA        A0,M$SCNORIG      . POST THE NEW ORIGIN @E@ @]PE
)@@G@@          SA        A0,M$SCANORIGIN   . POST THE NEW ORIGIN @G@@@[      PF
)@@G@@    LA,S3     A2,PRTAW          . GET THE COMMAND LENGTH IN WORDS @E@@@[PG
)@@G@@          TG,U      A2,ASIMAX-2       . IS IMAGE TOO LONG?  @F@@@[      PH
)@@G@@    LA,U      A2,ASIMAX-2       . YES, TRUNCATE TO THIS     @E@@@[      PI
)@@G@@    LN        A1,A2             . SET AS WORD COUNT   @G@@@[          LAPJ
)@@G@@,H2     A0,PRTAW          . GET THE ADDRESS OF THE COMMAND  @E@@@[      PK
)@@G@@    E$COPY                      . COPY THE COMMAND    @B@@@[          M$PL
)@@G@@EAWX                      .   @E@@@[          SA        A5,PRTAW        PM
)@@G@@  . SAVE THE ACCESS WORD@[@@@[PRT010@E@@@[          SZ,S3     M$PRTAXW  PN
)@@G@@        . FLAG LINE PRINTED   @E@@@[          M$APRINT,1 PRTAW          PO
)@@G@@  . PRINT THE IMAGE     @E@@@[          LA,U      A5,0              . CLPP
)@@G@@EAR ERROR REG     @C@@@[PRT999    RETURN                      . ALL DONEPQ
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @E@@@[. PRINT IMAGE.  PRINT$ CONTROL WORD IS IN A0, TYPE ANDPR
)@@G@@ ASCII@A@@@[. FLAG IN A1.  (NOTE FALL-THRU).    @[@@@[.     @]@@@[M$PRINPS
)@@G@@T*  . @F@@@[          TP        M$APFFLG          . IS LOCAL COPY TURNEDPT
)@@G@@ ON ? @G@@@[          JNB       A1,M$PRTALT       . NO - IF NOT DIAG ONLPU
)@@G@@Y PRINTA    @D@@@[          TOP,U     A1,2              . IMAGE IN FD ? PV
)@@G@@@C@@@[          ER        PRINT$            . YES     @E@@@[          TEPW
)@@G@@P,U     A1,2              . IMAGE IN ASCII ?    @C@@@[          ER      PX
)@@G@@  APRINT$           . YES     @[@@@[.     @B@@@[. PRINT IMAGE INTO ALTERPY
)@@G@@NATE FILE ONLY    @B@@@[. (ARGUMENTS AS ABOVE)  (NOTE FALL-THRU)  @[@@@[PZ
)@@G@@.     @B@@@[M$PRTALT*                             .   @F@@@[          S QA
)@@G@@        A0,XRCP           . SAVE PRNT CONTROL WORD    @E@@@[          TNQB
)@@G@@Z       M$APFFLG          . ALTERNATE FILE ON ? @B@@@[          J       QC
)@@G@@  XPR020            . NO@B@@@[          L,U       A0,XRCP           .   QD

)@@G@@    ER        PRNTA$            . YES     @E@@@[          TEP,U     A1,2QF
)@@G@@              . IMAGE IS ASCII ?    @C@@@[          ER        APRNTA$   QG
)@@G@@        . YES     @[@@@[.     @D@@@[. REQUIREMENT OF M$CPRT THAT LENGTH QH
)@@G@@COME BACK IN A0   @[@@@[.     @]@@@[XPR020    . @E@@@[          L,S3    QI

)@@G@@1             . RETURN  @[@@@[.     @E@@@[XRCP      VAR       3 0 'SITE$QK
)@@G@@'DL     . PRINTA$ CONTROL     @[@@@[.     @B@@@[          END           QL
)@@G@@              .   ___@@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@]/         M$DEF   @[@@@].     QM
)@@G@@@F@@@]. ROUTINE TO HANDLE THE CALL PARAMETER RETREIVER: ARG$(E1,E2)     QN
)@@G@@@[@@@].     @]@@@]M$FUNARG*   @#@#@]          ROUTINE @^@@@#          SUQO
)@@G@@BROUTINE    @F@@@]          DL        A0,VD+SRA         . GET RIGHT ARG QP
)@@G@@DESCRIPTOR  @F@@@]          LA        A3,M$XASS         . GET ASCII STORQQ
)@@G@@E ROUTINE   @D@@@]          LA,U      A2,M$RESULTBUF    . WORK PLACE    QR
)@@G@@@F@#@]          LR,U      R2,ASIMAX*4       . SIZE OF BUFFER IN CHARS   QS
)@@G@@@F@^@#          LR,U      R2,(ASIMAX*2)*4   . SIZE OF BUFFER IN CHARS   QT
)@@G@@@F@ @^          LR,U      R2,(ASIMAX)*4   . SIZE OF BUFFER IN CHARS     QU
)@@G@@@F@A@           LR,U      R2,(ASIMAX*2-1)*4   . SIZE OF BUFFER IN CHARS QV
)@@G@@@F@@@A          LR,U      R2,(ASIMAX*2)*4   . SIZE OF BUFFER IN CHARS   QW
)@@G@@@E@@@]          CALL      M$CALLARGGET      . GET THE PARAMETERS  @E@@@]QX
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,ARG999         . CHECK FOR ERROR     @G@@@]      QY
)@@G@@    JZ        A4,ARG010         . SKIP AHEAD IF STRING STORED     @]@@@]QZ
)@@G@@          . @A@@@]          .         NUMERIC RETURNED@]@@@]          . RA
)@@G@@@E@@@]          CALL      M$RESULTINT       . POST INTEGER RESULT @C@@@]RB
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,ARG999         . ERROR   @C@@@]          J       RC
)@@G@@  ARG900            . DONE    @]@@@]          . @C@@@]          .       RD
)@@G@@  SYMBOLIC IMAGE RETRIEVED    @]@@@]          . @F@#@]ARG010    LA,U    RE
)@@G@@  A0,M$RESULTBUF    . GET BUFFER ADDR AGAIN     @A@@@#ARG010    CALL    RF
)@@G@@  M$BLANKWORD     @F@@@#          LA,U      A0,M$RESULTBUF    . GET BUFFRG
)@@G@@ER ADDR AGAIN     @E@A@]          LA,U      A1,ASIMAX*4       . = MAX # RH
)@@G@@OF CHARS    @E@@@A          LA,U      A1,(ASIMAX*2)*4       . = MAX # OFRI
)@@G@@ CHARS@E@@@]          AN        A1,R2             . = # OF CHARS STORED RJ
)@@G@@@F@@@]          CALL      M$RESULTASC       . POST ASCII STRING RESULT  RK
)@@G@@@E@@@]          JNZ       A5,ARG999         . CHECK FOR ERROR     @D@@@]RL
)@@G@@ARG900    DS        A0,VD+SLA         . POST RESULT   @E@@@]ARG999    RERM
)@@G@@TURN                      . RETURN TO CALLER    @]@@@]          . @#@@@]RN
)@@G@@          END     _@@@@@@#@@@[          END     _@@@@@ST ASCII STRING RERO
)@@G@@SULT  @E@@@@          JNZ       A5,ARG999         . CHECK FOR ERROR     RP
)@@G@@@D@@@@ARG900    DS        A0,VD+SLA         . PO*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@ /     RQ
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@A.     @E@@@A. M$READMACRO - READ THE NEXT LINE FROM THRR
)@@G@@E CURRENT MACRO.  @[@@@A.     @^@@@A.   LMJ  X11,M$READMACRO@^@@@A.   A5RS
)@@G@@ = ERROR PCW OR 0 @F@@@A.   A4 = EOF FLAG OR 0 (CURRENT MACRO AUTOMATICART
)@@G@@LLY POPPED ON EOF)@^@@@A.   A0 = IMAGE LENGTH   @[@@@A.     @[@@@ .     RU
)@@G@@@[@A@ .     @D@A@ . THIS SUBROUTINE READS THE NEXT IMAGE FROM THE MACRO RV
)@@G@@@]@A@ . IT RETURNS@^@A@ .    A0 = IMAGE LENGTH  @ @A@ .     A5 > 0 => ERRW
)@@G@@ROR PCW     @^@A@ .     A4 > 0 => EOF     @ @A@ .     A5 = 0 => NORMAL RRX
)@@G@@ETURN @B@@@A. TO READ BACKWARDS (FOR GOTO COMMAND)    @[@@@A.     @ @@@ARY
)@@G@@.   LMJ  X11,M$READMACROB     @^@@@A.   A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0 @^@@@A.   A4RZ
)@@G@@ = EOF FLAG OR 0  @^@@@A.   A0 = IMAGE LENGTH   @[@@@A.     @G@@@A. ON BSA
)@@G@@ACKWARD EOF, THE MACRO IS *NOT* POPPED FROM THE EXECUTION STACK.  @[@@@ASB
)@@G@@.     @[@A@ .     @#@A@ M$READMACRO*.     @#@A@           ROUTINE @]@@@ASC
)@@G@@M$READMACRO*@ @@@A          LMJ       A3,READMAC@D@@@A          +       SD
)@@G@@  PSDFR             . READ FORWARDS @E@@@A          +         MAC910    SE
)@@G@@        . POP THE STACK ON EOF@]@@@A          . @#@@@AM$READMACROB*     SF
)@@G@@@ @@@A          LMJ       A3,READMAC@D@@@A          +         PSDFRB    SG
)@@G@@        . READ BACKWARDS@F@@@A          +         MAC911            . DOSH
)@@G@@N'T POP THE STACK ON EOF@]@@@A          . @^@@@AREADMAC   SUBROUTINE X9 SI
)@@G@@@E@@@AREADER    EQUF      *0,X9             . ROUTINE TO READ     @F@@@ASJ
)@@G@@EOFRTN    EQUF      *1,X9             . WHERE TO RETURN TO ON EOF @]@D@CSK
)@@G@@  SLJ TON$  @E@@@A          LX,U      X9,,A3            . PLACE LINK IN SL
)@@G@@X9    @E@A@           L,H2      A0,M$XQTMACRO     . GET PACKET ADDRESS  SM
)@@G@@@E@@@AMAC100    L,H2      A0,M$XQTMACRO     . GET PACKET ADDRESS  @D@A@ SN
)@@G@@          JZ        A0,0              . $$$ DEBUG $$$ @]@A@ MAC100.     SO
)@@G@@@G@@@A          LA        A1,MXADDR,A0      . GET THE CURRENT MACRO ADDRSP
)@@G@@ESS   @H@@@A          SA        A1,PIODA+M$CMPPKT . PLACE AS THE CURRENTSQ
)@@G@@ READ ADDRESS     @D@A@           SDFI      MXPKT MAC920,MAC910 . READ ISR
)@@G@@MAGE  @F@@@AMAC110    LA,U      A0,M$CMPPKT       . GET THE PACKET ADDRESS
)@@G@@SS    @F@@@A          LA        A1,M$RBAW         . AND THE IMAGE ACCESSST
)@@G@@ WORD @F@@@A          CALL      READER            . CALL THE READER ROUTSU
)@@G@@INE   @E@@@A          JNZ       A3,MAC920         . CHECK FOR ERRORS    SV
)@@G@@@E@@@A          JN        A1,EOFRTN         . CHECK FOR EOF'S     @E@A@ SW
)@@G@@          L         A1,10,A0          . GET CONTROL WORD    @E@A@       SX
)@@G@@    JN        A1,MAC100         . SKIP CONTROL WORDS  @E@@@A          JNSY
)@@G@@        A2,MAC110         . SKIP CONTROL WORDS  @E@@@           DSL     SZ
)@@G@@  A4,72             . CLEAR A4 AND A5     @E@@@A          LA,H2     A0,MTA
)@@G@@$XQTMACRO     . GET EXECUTION ENTRY @F@@@A          LA        A2,PIODA+MTB
)@@G@@$CMPPKT . GET NEXT READ ADDRESS     @D@A@           L         A1,M$COMLITC
)@@G@@NE      . LINE NUMBER TO@E@@@A          L         A3,M$COMLINE      . LITD
)@@G@@NE NUMBER TOO     @F@@@A          SA        A2,MXADDR,A0      . SAVE NEXTE
)@@G@@T READ ADDRESS    @E@A@           S         A1,MXLN,A0        . SAVE LINTF
)@@G@@E NUMBER    @E@@@A          S         A3,MXLN,A0        . SAVE LINE NUMBTG
)@@G@@ER    @E@A@           L,S2      A0,10,A0          . GET IMAGE LENGTH    TH
)@@G@@@F@A@           AN,U      A0,2              . SUBTRACT CONTROL WORDS    TI
)@@G@@@C@A@           JN        A0,0              . DEBUG   @E@@@A          LATJ
)@@G@@,U      A0,,A1            . GET RECORD LENGTH   @E@@@A          AN,U    TK
)@@G@@  A0,2              . MINUS CONTROL WORDS @C@@@           J         MAC9TL
)@@G@@99            . RETURN  @[@@@ .     @[@@@ .     @^@@@ . END OF FILE FROMTM
)@@G@@ MACRO@[@@@ .     @]@A@ MAC910.     @E@A@           LMJ       X11,M$XQTPTN
)@@G@@OPSTAK  . POP MACRO STACK     @E@@@AMAC910    LMJ       X11,M$XQTPOPSTAKTO
)@@G@@  . POP MACRO STACK     @D@A@           L,U       A4,1              . GETP
)@@G@@T EOF STATUS@D@@@AMAC911    L,U       A4,1              . GET EOF STATUSTQ
)@@G@@@D@@@           J         MAC999            . AND RETURN    @[@@@ .     TR
)@@G@@@ @@@ . IO ERROR ON SCRATCH FILE.   @[@@@ .     @]@A@ MAC920.     @G@@@ATS
)@@G@@MAC920    CALL      M$PSDFERR         . BUILD THE PSDFIO ERROR MESSAGE  TT
)@@G@@@E@A@           L         A5,ERMACR         . GET ERROR MESSAGE   @F@@@ATU

)@@G@@@[@@@ .     @[@A@ .     @]@A@ MAC999.     @#@A@           RETURN  @#@C@ATX

)@@G@@    END                         .   _@@@@@      PSDFW       M$LABEL     UC
)@@G@@PSDFR       M$IMAGE     M$EPKT      M$EDITOPEN  ECOPY$      EWRDN$      UD
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@T/         M$DEF   @[@@@T.     @H@@@T. THIS ELEMENT CONUE
)@@G@@TAINS THE INITIALIZATION ROUTINE FOR THE MACRO PACKAGE.     @[@@@T.     UF
)@@G@@@ @@@T.         LMJ       X11,M$INIT@ @@@T.         JNZ       A5,<ERROR>UG
)@@G@@@[@@@T.     @H@@@T. THE ROUTINE INITIALIZES ANY FREE CORE AREAS NEEDED FUH
)@@G@@OR THE MACRO PACKAGE,   @H@@@T. AS WELL AS THE COMPILER AND RUN-TIME STAUI
)@@G@@CKS. UPON RETURN, A5 WILL BE ZERO   @G@@@T. FOR NORMAL RETURNS, OR WILL UJ
)@@G@@CONTAIN A PRINT CONTROL WORD FOR ANY FATAL@]@@@T. ERRORS.   @[@@@T.     UK
)@@G@@@^@@@TM$INIT*   SAVER     X11 @E@@@T          LA        A0,PCL('MACRO PAUL
)@@G@@CKAGE REINITIALIZED.')  @E@@@T          TZ        COLDSTMSG         . FIUM
)@@G@@RST TIME THROUGH? @G@@@T          ER        PRINT$            . NOPE, PRUN
)@@G@@INT COLDSTART MESSAGE   @E@@@T          SA        A0,COLDSTMSG      . POUO
)@@G@@ST THE MESSAGE    @G@@@T          SA        A0,M$COLDSTART    . AND POSTUP
)@@G@@ THE COLD START FLAG    @F@@@T          SZ        M$WARMSTART       . CLUQ
)@@G@@EAR WARM START FLAG     @[@@@T.     @C@@@T. FIRST, ENSURE THAT WE'RE IN UR
)@@G@@QUARTER-WORD MODE @[@@@T.     @F@@@T          SPD       A0              US
)@@G@@  . SET QUARTER WORD MODE     @F@@@T          OR,U      A0,1*/3         UT
)@@G@@  . SET QUARTER-WORD BIT (D10)@D@@@T          LPD       0,A1            UU
)@@G@@  . POST NEW BITS @F@@@T          CALL      M$IALL            . TURN ON UV
)@@G@@CONTIGENCY HANDLER@F@@@U          CALL      M$RELSCRFILE      . RELEASE UW
)@@G@@THE SCRATCH FILE  @[@X@U.     @H@X@U.   THE NEXT TWO SUBROUTINE CALLS ARUX
)@@G@@E SPECIFICALLY TO TELL THE M$MATCH AND    @I@X@U.   M$CALLSUBST ROUTINESUY
)@@G@@ THAT THE BUFFER THEY HAVE ALLOCATED (AND WHOSE ADDRESS     @H@X@U.   ISUZ
)@@G@@ SAVED), IS GOING TO BE RELEASED.   AS SUCH THEY MUST CLEAR THE LOCAL   VA
)@@G@@@E@X@U.   STORAGE LOCATION CONTAINING THE ADDRESS OF THE POINTER. @H@X@UVB
)@@G@@.   THIS FIX IS ANTICIPATED AS BEING TEMPORARY.   THE LONG RANGE GOAL ISVC
)@@G@@ TO   @H@X@U.   HAVE THE M$INIT ROUTINE RELEASE ONLY THE MEMORY IT KNOWSVD
)@@G@@ ABOUT, LEAVING   @G@X@U.   ANY POINTERS TO BUFFERS ALLOCATED BY INDIVIDVE
)@@G@@UAL SUBROUTINES INTACT. @G@X@U.   THE EDITOR CAN SURVIVE WITH THIS "HOT VF
)@@G@@FIX", BUT OTHER USER PROGRAMS @I@X@U.   WHICH MAY USE THE MACRO PACKAGE VG
)@@G@@CANNOT AS THEY WILL BE CALLING THE ALLOCATE     @H@X@U.   AND DEALLOCATEVH
)@@G@@ ROUTINES THEMSELVES.   THERE IS NO GUARANTEE, THAT THE USER@H@X@U.   PRVI
)@@G@@OGRAM WILL KNOW WHEN THE RESET IS DONE, AND THEREFORE, NO GUARANTEE THATVJ
)@@G@@@H@X@U.   MEMORY RELEASED WHOLESALE (AS IS THE CASE HERE) WON'T BE CORRUVK
)@@G@@PTED BY     @A@X@U.   SOMEONE USING "FREE" MEMORY.    @[@X@U.     @H@X@UVL
)@@G@@.         CALL      M$MATCHREL        . TELL M$MATCH MEMORY IS TO BE TRAVM
)@@G@@SHED  @G@X@U.         CALL M$CSUBSTREL            . TELL M$CALLSUBST THEVN
)@@G@@ SAME THING @F@U@T          PRAL                        . RELEASE ALL OFVO
)@@G@@ PERM CORE  @F@X@U.         M$PRAL                      . RELEASE ALL OFVP
)@@G@@ PERM CORE  @[@X@U.     @[@@@X.     @D@X@U.   FIRST GET RID OF ANY MACROVQ
)@@G@@S THAT MAY BE AROUND    @D@@@X.   THEN GET RID OF ANY MACROS THAT MAY BEVR
)@@G@@ AROUND     @[@@@U.     @H@@@X          TNZ,H2    M$DEFMACRO        . CHVS
)@@G@@ECK TO SEE IF THERE IS A TREE AT ALL@G@@@X          J         INIT200   VT
)@@G@@        . IF NO TREE THEN SKIP THIS CODE. @]@@@UINIT100   . @G@@@U      VU
)@@G@@    L,U       A1,1              . GET THE FIRST ONE IN THE TREE   @B@@@UVV
)@@G@@          AVLSR     M$DEFMACRO,,H2    .   @G@@@U          JZ        A2,IVW
)@@G@@NIT200        . IF ZERO THEN THERE ARE NO MORE  @F@@@U          DL      VX
)@@G@@  A0,MDN,A2         . GRAB THE NAME OF THE THING@D@@@U          CALL    VY
)@@G@@  M$MDERASE         . GET RID OF IT @E@@@U          J         INIT100   VZ
)@@G@@        . REPEAT UNTIL DONE   @]@@@UINIT200   . @[@@@U.     @C@@@U.   PUWA
)@@G@@RGE ALL DICTIONARY LEVELS THAT MAY BE LEFT@[@@@U.     @D@@@U          LNWB
)@@G@@,U      A0,1              . GET RID OF ALL@C@@@U          LMJ       X11,WC
)@@G@@M$DLP         . BERZLAT @B@@@U          JNZ       A5,INIT999        .   WD
)@@G@@@G@W@U          STKTERM                     . GET RID OF SUBROUTINE STACWE
)@@G@@K     @G@@@W.         STKTERM                     . GET RID OF SUBROUTINWF
)@@G@@E STACK     @G@U@T          TNEW                        . RELEASE CURRENWG
)@@G@@T TEMP DATA STACK @G@@@U.         M$TNEW                      . RELEASE WH
)@@G@@CURRENT TEMP DATA STACK @I@@@U          STKINIT   INIT999 SSTKSIZ,SSTKINWI
)@@G@@C SSTKPTR . INITIALIZE SUBROUTINE STAC    @E@@@U          DL        A0,SWJ
)@@G@@TKCTL         . GET CONROL WORD     @G@@@U          DS        A0,SSTKCTLWK
)@@G@@        . POST FOR SUBROUTINE CONTROL     @F@U@T          PGET      M$STWL
)@@G@@ACKSIZE       . GET A NEW STACK BUFFER    @F@U@T          JNZ       A5,IWM
)@@G@@NIT999        . DON'T HANDLE ERRORS HERE  @G@U@T          LXI,U     A1,,WN
)@@G@@*A1           . A1 = (LOW ADDR,HIGH ADDR+1)     @G@U@T          SSC     WO
)@@G@@  A1,18             . A1 = (HIGH ADDR+1,LOW ADDR)     @G@U@T          SAWP
)@@G@@        A1,M$STACKCW      . POST NEW STACK CONTROL WORD     @F@@@T      WQ
)@@G@@    SPINIT                      . INITIALIZE STACK POINTER  @G@@@U      WR
)@@G@@    TZ        M$PAGES           . ARE THE PAGES ALREADY THERE?    @E@@@UWS
)@@G@@          J         INIT500           . YES, SKIP THIS CODE @H@@@U      WT
)@@G@@    LA        A1,(M$PSDFPAL,M$PSDFPA) . INITIALIZE PSDF PAGING AREA     WU
)@@G@@@F@@@U          LA        A2,M$PAGESIZE     . GET CONFIGURED PAGESIZE   WV
)@@G@@@F@@@U          SZ        M$PSDFPA          . CLEAR FIRST WORD FOR INIT WW
)@@G@@@G@@@U          CALL      PIOPAI$           . INITIALIZE PAGING AREA HEAWX
)@@G@@DER   @]@@@UINIT500.    @C@U@T          DSL       A0,72             . A0WY
)@@G@@,A1=0 @H@@@U          DS        A0,STKCTL         . ERASE CURRENT OTHER WZ
)@@G@@STACK CONTROL     @E@V@T          DS        A0,M$COMMANDQ     . CLEAR THXA
)@@G@@E QUEUES    @E@@@V          L,U       A0,M$COMMANDQ     . CLEAR THE QUEUXB
)@@G@@ES    @E@@@V          CALL      M$QPURGE          . CLEAR OUT THE QUEUE XC
)@@G@@@F@V@T          DS        A0,M$HISTORYQ     . CLEAR THE HISTORY QUEUE   XD
)@@G@@@F@@@V          L,U       A0,M$HISTORYQ     . CLEAR THE HISTORY QUEUE   XE
)@@G@@@E@@@V          CALL      M$QPURGE          . CLEAR OUT THE QUEUE @F@V@TXF
)@@G@@          DS        A0,M$INPUTQ       . CLEAR THE INPUT QUEUE     @F@@@VXG
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,M$INPUTQ       . CLEAR THE INPUT QUEUE     @E@@@VXH
)@@G@@          CALL      M$QPURGE          . CLEAR OUT THE QUEUE @G@V@U      XI
)@@G@@    DS        A0,M$TPKTQ        . CLEAR THE TIDE$ PACKET QUEUE    @G@@@VXJ
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,M$TPKTQ        . CLEAR THE TIDE$ PACKET QUEUE    XK
)@@G@@@E@@@V          CALL      M$QPURGE          . CLEAR OUT THE QUEUE @G@V@UXL
)@@G@@          DS        A0,M$EPKTQ        . CLEAR THE EDIT$ PACKET QUEUE    XM
)@@G@@@G@@@V          L,U       A0,M$EPKTQ        . CLEAR THE EDIT$ PACKET QUEXN
)@@G@@UE    @E@@@V          CALL      M$QPURGE          . CLEAR OUT THE QUEUE XO
)@@G@@@E@@@T          SZ        M$BREAK           . NO BREAK OUTSTANDING@E@@@TXP
)@@G@@          SZ        M$ABORT           . NO ABORT OUTSTANDING@E@@@T      XQ
)@@G@@    SZ        M$TRACE           . NO INITIAL TRACE    @F@@@T          SZXR
)@@G@@        M$SCANFLAG        . SO M$SCANPRIM WORKS NICELY@F@@@T          SZXS
)@@G@@        M$CALCFLAG        . NOT IN CALCULATOR MODE    @G@@@T          CAXT
)@@G@@LL      M$NEWMST          . GET A NEW MACRO SYMBOL TABLE    @G@@@T      XU
)@@G@@    SA        A1,M$DEFMACRO     . INITIALIZE THE MACRO DEFN TABLE @H@U@TXV
)@@G@@          SZ        M$SAVL            . CLEAR SECTOR ADDRESS IN SCRATCH XW
)@@G@@FILE  @G@U@T          CALL      M$NEWMST          . GET ANOTHER MACRO SYXX
)@@G@@MBOL TABLE  @H@U@T          SA        A1,M$GLOBALS      . INITIALIZE THEXY
)@@G@@ GLOBAL SYMBOL TABLE    @F@@@U          SZ        M$DICTIONARY      . CLXZ
)@@G@@EAR DICTIONARY LEVELS   @F@@@T          SZ        M$XQTMACRO        . CLYA
)@@G@@EAR EXECUTING MACRO LIST@F@@@U          ER        OPT$              . GEYB
)@@G@@T EXECUTION OPTIONS     @E@@@U          SA        A0,M$OPTION       . SAYC
)@@G@@VE THE OPTION BITS@F@@@T          SZ        M$COLDSTART       . CLEAR COYD
)@@G@@LD-START FLAG     @F@U@T          SZ        WARMSTCOUNT       . CLEAR WAYE
)@@G@@RM-START COUNT    @ @@@TINIT999   LOADR     M$INIT    @E@@@T          J YF
)@@G@@        0,X11             . THAT'S ALL RIGHT NOW@[@@@T.     @H@@@V.    TYG
)@@G@@HE FOLLOWING ROUTINE EMPTIES THE QUEUE WHOSE ADDRESS IS PASSED IN A0.   YH
)@@G@@@B@@@V.    EACH ITEM IN THE QUEUE IS RELEASED.  @[@@@V.     @B@@@VM$QPURYI
)@@G@@GE  SUBROUTINE                  .   @B@@@VQPRG      LOCAL     1         YJ
)@@G@@        .   @G@@@V          S         A0,QPRG           . SAVE THE QUEUEYK
)@@G@@ HEADER ADDRESS   @]@@@VQPRG100   . @F@@@V          L         A0,QPRG   YL
)@@G@@        . GET THE QUEUE ADDRESS     @G@@@V          QPULL               YM
)@@G@@        . GRAB THE NEXT ITEM ON THE QUEUE @F@@@V          JZ        A1,QYN
)@@G@@PRG999        . ZERO MEANS IT ISN'T THERE @F@@@V          L,U       A0,,YO
)@@G@@A1            . GET THE ADDRESS INTO A0   @E@@@V          M$PREL        YP
)@@G@@              . RELEASE THE THING   @F@@@V          JZ        A5,QPRG100YQ
)@@G@@        . IF NO ERROR, THEN GO AGAIN@]@@@VQPRG999     @#@@@V          REYR
)@@G@@TURN  @[@@@V.     @[@@@V.     @H@@@TCOLDSTMSG VAR       1 0             YS
)@@G@@  . INITIAL TIME IT'S ZERO (NO MESSAGE).  @[@@@T.     @F@@@T. THE 'RESETYT
)@@G@@' COMMAND ACTUALLY REINITIALIZES THE MACRO PACKAGE.   @[@@@T.     @]@@@TYU
)@@G@@M$COMRESET* @G@@@T          CALL      M$INIT            . INITIALIZE THEYV
)@@G@@ MACRO PACKAGE    @G@@@T          LX        X11,M$DRIVERRTN   . GET THE YW
)@@G@@TOP LEVEL RETURN ADDR   @F@@@T          J         M$DRIVER          . STYX
)@@G@@ART OVER AT THE TOP     @[@@@T/.    @E@@@T. M$RESET - ROUTINE TO PERFORMYY
)@@G@@ A "WARM-START" IF POSSIBLE.  @[@@@T.     @G@@@T. A WARM START MERELY DRYZ
)@@G@@AINS THE INPUT AND COMMAND QUEUES, MARKS THE    @D@@@T. CURRENT MACRO ASZA
)@@G@@ SUSPENDED, AND CLEARS SOME FLAGS.  @[@@@T.     @G@@@TM$RESET*  JNEZ    ZB
)@@G@@  M$COLDSTART M$INIT . IF COLD START SET, GO INIT     @F@U@TRESET     SAZC
)@@G@@VER     X11               . SAVE THE RETURN ADDRESS   @G@@@URESET     SAZD
)@@G@@VER     X11 X7            . SAVE THE RETURN ADDRESS AND X7  @G@U@T      ZE
)@@G@@    INC       A0,WARMSTCOUNT    . INCREMENT THE WARM START COUNT  @I@U@TZF
)@@G@@          JLE,U     A0,WARMSTLIMIT M$INIT . IF WE'RE PAST THE LIMIT, GO ZG
)@@G@@COLD STA    @E@@@T          SX        X11,M$WARMSTART   . POST WARM STARZH
)@@G@@T FLAG@H@@@T          SX        X11,M$COLDSTART   . & POST COLD START FLZI
)@@G@@AG IN CASE WE IGDM@G@@@T          SPINIT                      . REINITIAZJ
)@@G@@LIZE THE STACK POINTER  @H@@@T          CALL      M$ERRESCAPE       . CAZK
)@@G@@USE AN ERROR ESCAPE IN THE TOP MACRO@F@@@T          JNZ       A5,RESET90ZL
)@@G@@0       . IF ERROR, GO COLD-START   @[@@@T.     @G@@@T. NOW, LET'S LOOK ZM
)@@G@@AT THE COMMAND QUEUE.  THE COMMAND QUEUE WILL HAVE    @G@@@T. COMMANDS LZN
)@@G@@INKED IN, WITH ASSOCIATED TEMPORARY DATA STACKS HANGING IN  @A@@@T. THE ZO
)@@G@@RECORDS.  RELEASE THEM ALL.   @[@@@T.     @F@U@T          LA,U      A0,MZP
)@@G@@$COMMANDQ     . GET THE COMMAND QUEUE     @H@U@T          LX        X7,QZQ
)@@G@@HLAST         . START WITH THE MOST RECENT COMMAND    @F@U@TRESET010  JEZR
)@@G@@Z,U     0,X7 RESET020     . SKIP IF NO MORE COMMANDS  @G@@@URESET010  QPZS

)@@G@@  . RELEASE THE BUFFER  @C@@@U          RETURN                      . DOCI
)@@G@@NE    @[@U@T/.    @G@U@T. THIS CODE HANDLES OVERFLOWS OCCURING BECAUSE OCJ
)@@G@@F A PREAMBLE CHECK.     @G@U@T. A NEW STACK BUFFER OF TWICE THE SIZE OF CK
)@@G@@THE ONE BEFORE IS ACQUIRED    @G@U@T. AND THE OLD STACK IS BLOCK TRANSFECL
)@@G@@RED INTO THE NEW STACK. THE OLD     @F@U@T. STACK BUFFER IS THEN RELEASECM
)@@G@@D, AND WE POST THE NEW STACK BUFFER @G@U@T. LIMITS IN M$STACKCW. SIMPLE,CN
)@@G@@ HUH? IN THIS WAY, AN OVERFLOW ACTUALLY   @ @U@T. BECOMES AN ER-055 ERROCO
)@@G@@R.    @[@U@T.     @#@U@TM$PROFLO  SLJENTRY@A@U@TPRREGS    SAVER     A0,ACP
)@@G@@5 R1,R3     @D@U@T          SX        X11,PRX11         . SAVE USER X11 CQ
)@@G@@@F@U@T          LA,H1     A0,M$STACKCW      . A0=HIGH ADDRESS+1 OF STACKCR
)@@G@@@D@U@T          AN,H2     A0,M$STACKCW      . A0=STACKSIZE  @E@U@T      CS
)@@G@@    AA,U      A0,M$STACKSIZE    . A0=OLD+M$STACKSIZE  @H@U@T          PGCT
)@@G@@ET                        . A1=(ACTUAL SIZE,NEW STACK ADDRESS)    @E@U@TCU
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,PRO900         . CHECK FOR ERRORS    @F@U@T      CV

)@@G@@    AN,U      A0,1,SP$          . A0=# OF WORDS ON THE STACK ALLOCATED  CX
)@@G@@@F@U@T          LR,U      R1,,A0            . MOVE COUNT TO REPEAT REG  CY
)@@G@@@F@U@T          SPINIT                      . INIT SP$ TO OLD STACK     CZ
)@@G@@@F@U@T          LA        A2,SP$            . COPY THE STACK POINTER    DA
)@@G@@@I@U@T          LA,U      A0,,*A1           . A0=NEW LOW ADDRESS;A1=NEW DB
)@@G@@HIGH ADDRESS+1    @E@U@T          SA,H2     A0,M$STACKCW      . POST NEWDC
)@@G@@ LIMITS     @B@U@T          SA,H1     A1,M$STACKCW      .   @G@U@T      DD

)@@G@@STACK @E@U@T          PREL                        . RELEASE OLD STACK   DH

)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@A.     @G@@@A. THIS ELEMENT CONTAINS CODE ALLOWING RECULP
)@@G@@RSIVE CALLS TO THE EXPRESSION @H@@@A. AND COMMAND SCANNERS.  THE EXPRESSLQ
)@@G@@ION SCANNERS MERELY CREATE A NEW TIDE$    @G@@@A. PACKET AND STACK IT, ALR
)@@G@@LLOWING THE EXPRESSION EVALUATION PROCESS TO    @G@@@A. END UP EVALUATINLS
)@@G@@G A SUBEXPRESSION.  THIS IS NECESSARY FOR THE EVENTUAL@F@@@A. IMPLEMENTALT
)@@G@@TION OF USER FUNCTIONS (MACROS WHICH RETURN VALUES).  @G@@@A. THE COMMANLU
)@@G@@D SCANNER MUST ALSO STACK A COPY OF THE CURRENT COMMAND.    @[@@@A.     LV
)@@G@@@^@@@A. THE ENTRY POINTS:     @[@@@A.     @C@@@A.  M$EVALIMAGE - EVALUATLW
)@@G@@E THE ENTIRE IMAGE.     @G@@@A.  M$EVALEXPR  - EVALUATE AN EXPRESSION (SLX
)@@G@@TOP ON UNMATCHED ']' ')' '\').@D@@@A.  M$EVALFIELD - EVALUATE A FIELD (SLY
)@@G@@TOP ON BLANKS).   @F@B@A.  M$EVALSUBF  - EVALUATE A SUBFIELD (STOP ON COLZ
)@@G@@MMAS OR BLANKS).  @F@@@B.  M$EVALSUBFLD- EVALUATE A SUBFIELD (STOP ON COMA
)@@G@@MMAS OR BLANKS).  @[@@@A.     @B@@@A.   A0 = (IMAGE LENGTH,IMAGE ADDRESSMB
)@@G@@)     @A@@@B.   A1 = IMAGE ORIGIN (SCAN COLUMN) @B@B@A.   LMJ  X11,M$EVAMC
)@@G@@LEXPR\IMAGE\FIELD\SUBF  @B@@@B.   LMJ  X11,M$EVALEXPR\IMAGE\FIELD\SUBFLDMD
)@@G@@@^@@@A.   A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0 @#@@@A.   A0 = MODE     @#@@@A.   A1 = ADDME
)@@G@@RESS  @#@@@A.   A2 = LENGTH   @^@@@A.   A3 = SCAN TERM CHAR @[@@@A.     MF
)@@G@@@C@@@A.  M$EVALSTR - EVALUATE A STRING EXPRESSION.    @[@@@A.     @B@@@AMG
)@@G@@.   A0 = (IMAGE LENGTH,IMAGE ADDRESS)     @A@@@B.   A1 = IMAGE ORIGIN (SMH
)@@G@@CAN COLUMN) @^@@@A.   LMJ  X11,M$EVALSTR  @^@@@A.   A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0 MI
)@@G@@@^@@@A.   A0 = PCW FOR STRING @ @@@A.   A1 = MODE (MODASC,MODALP) @ @@@AMJ
)@@G@@.   A2 = CHARACTER LENGTH     @^@@@A.   A3 = WORD LENGTH    @[@@@A.     MK
)@@G@@@D@@@A.  M$EVALINT - EVALUATE A EXPRESSION FOR AN INTEGER.  @[@@@A.     ML
)@@G@@@B@@@A.   A0 = (IMAGE LENGTH, IMAGE ADDRESS)    +@@@@[@D@B@A 0)^@)CC1^@.MM
)@@G@@^[DD([C9 ^[JELDC9DD0) [NCT[D0)CTJD-PD(I C)+@@@@@@A@@@B.   A1 = IMAGE ORIMN
)@@G@@GIN (SCAN COLUMN) @^@@@A.   LMJ  X11,M$EVALINT  @^@@@A.   A5 = ERROR PCWMO
)@@G@@ OR 0 @ @@@A.   A0 = VALUE (FIRST WORD)   @ @@@A.   A1 = ADDRESS OF VALUMP
)@@G@@E     @#@@@A.   A2 = LENGTH   @[@@@A.     @F@@@A. IN ALL CASES, THE IMAGMQ
)@@G@@E LENGTH IS GIVEN AS A CHARACTER COUNT.   @ @@@A. THE IMAGE MUST BE IN AMR
)@@G@@SCII. @[@@@D.     @H@@@D. IF THE IMAGE ORIGIN IS ZERO, THE IMAGE WILL BEMS
)@@G@@ CONSIDERED AS A NEW IMAGE    @H@@@D. AND ANY ERRORS IN THE SCAN WILL CAMT
)@@G@@USE THE IMAGE TO PRINT ALONG WITH THE     @H@@@D. ERROR MESSAGE.  IF THEMU
)@@G@@ IMAGE ORIGIN IS NONZERO, THE IMAGE BEING SCANNED     @G@@@D. WILL BE COMV
)@@G@@NSIDERED AS PART OF THE PREVIOUS IMAGE, AND THE CURRENT SCAN@H@@@D. ORIGMW
)@@G@@IN WILL BE UPDATED WITH THE IMAGE ORIGIN; ERRORS WILL NOT BE PRINTED    MX
)@@G@@@ @@@D. BUT WILL BE PROPOGATED.     @[@@@A.     @E@B@AM$EVALEXPR* LA,U  MY
