)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@Y.     @F@@@Y. THIS ELEMENT CONTAINS CODE RESPONSIBLE FES
)@@G@@OR THE MANIPULATION OF  @^@@@Y. MACRO SYMBOL TABLES.  @[@@@Z.     @A@@@ZET
)@@G@@. M$DLF  - FIND A DICTIONARY LEVEL  @D@@@Z. M$DLFS - FIND A DICTIONARY LEU
)@@G@@EVEL FOR A SYMBOL SEARCH@E@@@Z. M$DLFI - FIND A DICTIONARY LEVEL FOR A SEV
)@@G@@YMBOL INSERTION   @[@@@Z.     +@@@@[@D@Z@Y 0)^[[A@)B*)D- E1 D)) [JEK)B)0EW
)@@G@@^[DC0)D- E1 D))C(MELJEK(@D@Z@Y 0)^[[A@)B*)D- E1 D)) [JEK)B)0^[DC0)D- E1 EX
)@@G@@D))C(MELJEK(+@@@@@@#@@@Z.  A0 = LEVEL     @#@@@Z.  LMJ  X11,M$DLF +@@@@[EY
)@@G@@@D@Z@Y 0)^[[A@)B*)D- E1 D)) [JEK)B)0^[DC0)D- E1 D))C(MELJEK(+@@@@@@A@@@ZEZ
)@@G@@.  A0 = LEVEL (OR <0 IF LEVEL ERROR)@^@@@Z.  A1 = PREDECESSOR LINK@E@@@ZFA
)@@G@@.  A2 = DICTIONARY ENTRY FOR A0 LEVEL OR 0 IF NO SUCH LEVEL @[@@@Z.     FB
)@@G@@@H@@@ZM$DLF*    LMJ       A3,MDLF           . GO DO FIND; POINT TO INSTRFC
)@@G@@S BELOW     @E@@@Z          NOP                         . DON'T AFFECT LFD
)@@G@@EVEL  @]@@@Z          . @G@@@ZM$DLFS*   LMJ       A3,MDLF           . GOFE
)@@G@@ DO FIND FOR SYMBOL SEARCH    @G@@@Z          AN        A0,DLDSL,A2     FF
)@@G@@  . ADJUST LEVEL BY SEARCH LEVEL    @]@@@Z          . @F@@@ZM$DLFD*     FG
)@@G@@                          . DO FIND FOR SYMBOL DELETE @G@@@ZM$DLFI*   LMFH
)@@G@@J       A3,MDLF           . GO DO FIND FOR SYMBOL INSERT    @G@@@Z      FI
)@@G@@    AN        A0,DLDIL,A2       . ADJUST LEVEL BY INSERTION LEVEL @]@@@ZFJ
)@@G@@          . @F@@@ZMDLF      LA,U      A2,M$DICTIONARY   . GET THE INITIAFK
)@@G@@L HEAD PTR  @F@@@ZDLF010    LA        A1,DLLINK,A2      . GET THE NEXT LFL
)@@G@@EVEL LINK   @H@@@Z          DSC       A1,36             . A1 = PREVIOUS;FM
)@@G@@ A2 = NEXT (CURRENT)    @E@@@Z          JZ        A2,0,X11          . IFFN
)@@G@@ NO NEXT, RETURN  @I@@@Z          JG        A0,DLLEVL,A2 DLF010 . KEEP LFO
)@@G@@OOKING FOR REQ. LEVEL OR HIGHER     @H@@@Z          JNE       A0,DLLEVL,FP
)@@G@@A2 DLF020 . IF LEVEL>CURRENT LEVEL, EXIT NO FIND@H@@@Z          EX      FQ
)@@G@@  0,A3              . ADJUST THE FIND/SEARCH/INSERT LEVEL   @F@@@Z      FR
)@@G@@    JE        A0,DLLEVL,A2 0,X11 . IF LEVEL FOUND, EXIT     @F@@@Z      FS
)@@G@@    JP        A0,DLF010         . IF LEVEL OK, KEEP LOOKING @E@@@ZDLF020FT
)@@G@@    LA,U      A2,0              . EXIT LEVEL NO FIND  @C@@@Z          J FU
)@@G@@        0,X11             . DONE    @[@@@Z.     @C@@@Z. M$CDLEV - RETURNFV
)@@G@@ CURRENT DICTIONARY LEVEL     @[@@@Z.     @^@@@Z.  LMJ  X11,M$CDLEV     FW
)@@G@@@^@@@Z.  A2 = CURRENT LEVEL   @[@@@Z.     @F@@@ZM$CDLEV*  LA        A2,MFX
)@@G@@$DICTIONARY   . GET CURRENT LEVEL PTR     @F@@@Z          JZ        A2,0FY
)@@G@@,X11          . IF NO DICTIONARY, LEVEL=0 @F@@@Z          LA        A2,DFZ
)@@G@@LLEVL,A2      . GET THE CURRENT LEVEL     @C@@@Z          J         0,X1GA
)@@G@@1             . ALL DONE@[@@@Z/.    @A@@@Z. M$DLC - CREATE A DICTIONARY GB
)@@G@@LEVEL @[@@@Z.     @#@@@Z.  A0 = LEVEL     @#@@@Z.  LMJ  X11,M$DLC @^@@@ZGC
)@@G@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @A@@@Z.  A1 = DICTIONARY LEVEL ENTRY PTR  @C@@@ZGD
)@@G@@.  A2 = SYMBOL TABLE PTR FOR REQUESTED LEVEL    @[@@@Z.     @#@)@ZM$DLC*GE
)@@G@@    ROUTINE @^@@@)M$DLC*    SUBROUTINE    @^@@@ZDLCTMP    LOCAL     2   GF
)@@G@@@F@@@Z          CALL      M$DLF             . FIND THE DICTIONARY LEVEL GG
)@@G@@@E@@@Z          JNZ       A2,DLC010         . IF FOUND, SKIP AHEAD@G@@@ZGH
)@@G@@          DS        A0,DLCTMP         . SAVE LEVEL, PREDECESSOR LINK    GI
)@@G@@@H@-@Z          PGET      DLSIZE            . NOT FOUND, CREATE A NEW LEGJ
)@@G@@VEL ENTRY   @B@-@Z          JNZ       A5,DLC999         .   @H@@@-      GK
)@@G@@    M$PGET    DLC999 DLSIZE     . NOT FOUND, CREATE NEW LEVEL ENTRY     GL
)@@G@@@G@@@Z          DL        A2,DLCTMP         . RECOVER LEVEL & PREDECESSOGM
)@@G@@R PTR @G@@@Z          LA        A0,DLLINK,A3      . GET SUCESSOR LINK OFGN
)@@G@@ PREDECESSOR@F@@@Z          SA        A1,DLLINK,A3      . NEW ENTRY IS NGO
)@@G@@OW SUCCESSOR@F@@@Z          SA        A0,DLLINK,A1      . POST NEW ENTRYGP
)@@G@@'S SUCCESSOR@F@@@Z          SA        A2,DLLEVL,A1      . POST NEW ENTRYGQ
)@@G@@'S LEVEL    @I@@@Z          MOVE      A0,DLMSTP,A1,U A2,M$DEFMST M$DEFMSGR
)@@G@@TLEN . MOVE THE SYMBOL TAB    @E@@@Z          LA,U      A2,,A1          GS
)@@G@@  . GET ENTRY PTR IN A2 @E@@@ZDLC010    LA,U      A1,,A2            . KEGT
)@@G@@EP ENTRY PTR IN A1@F@@@Z          LA,U      A2,DLMSTP,A2      . GET PACKGU
)@@G@@ET ADDRESS IN A2  @^@@@Z          LA,U      A5,0@#@@@ZDLC999    RETURN  GV
)@@G@@@[@@@Z.     @A@@@Z. M$DLP - PURGE DICTIONARY LEVELS   @[@@@Z.     +@@@@[GW
)@@G@@@C@Z@Y 0)^[[A@)B*)D-JE9 ETO^[GC(QC(G^[OD8)E[PELBC*)^@)@C@Z@Y 0)^[[A@)B*)GX
)@@G@@D-JE9 ETO^[GC(QC(G^[OD8)E[PELBC*)^@)@ @Z@Y 0)^[[A@)B*)D-JE9 ETO^[GC(QC(GGY
)@@G@@+@@@@@@B@@@Z.  A0 = LOWEST LEVEL (PURGE LOWER LEVELS) @#@@@Z.  LMJ  X11,GZ
)@@G@@M$DLP @^@@@Z.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @[@@@Z.     @#@)@ZM$DLP*    ROUTINE HA
)@@G@@@^@@@)M$DLP*    SUBROUTINE    @E@@@ZDLPLEV    LOCAL                     HB
)@@G@@  . LEVEL TO PURGE AT   @E@@@Z          SA        A0,DLPLEV         . SAHC
)@@G@@VE PURGE LEVEL    @E@@@Z          LA,U      A5,0              . NO ERRORHD
)@@G@@S AT FIRST  @E@@@ZDLP010    LA        A0,M$DICTIONARY   . GET THE HIGESTHE
)@@G@@ LEVEL@G@@@Z          JZ        A0,DLP999         . IF NO LEVELS, ALREADHF
)@@G@@Y PURGED    @G@@@Z          LA        A1,DLPLEV         . GET THE LOWESTHG
)@@G@@ LEVEL ALLOWED    @G@@@Z          JLE       A1,DLLEVL,A0 DLP999 . IF LOWHH
)@@G@@EST IS <= ALLOWED, QUIT @F@@@Z          LA        A2,DLLINK,A0      . GEHI
)@@G@@T LINK TO THE NEXT LEVEL@F@@@Z          SA        A2,M$DICTIONARY   . POHJ
)@@G@@ST NEW HIGHEST LEVEL    @G@@@Z          CALL      M$ERSDST          . ERHK
)@@G@@ASE A DICTIONARY SYMBOL TABLE @F@@@Z          JZ        A5,DLP010       HL
)@@G@@  . KEEP GOING IF NO ERRORS   @#@@@ZDLP999    RETURN  @[@@@Z/.    @A@@@ZHM
)@@G@@. M$DLS - SEARCH DICTIONARY LEVELS  @C@@@Z. M$DLSU - SEARCH DICTIONARY LHN
)@@G@@EVELS FOR UPDATE  @[@@@Z.     @^@@@Z.  A0,A1 = SYMBOL NAME  @ @@@Z.  A2 HO
)@@G@@= INITIAL SEARCH LEVEL  @^@@@Z.  LMJ  X11,M$DLS(U)    @^@@@Z.  A0,A1 = SHP
)@@G@@YMBOL NAME  +@@@@[@F@Z@Y 0)^[[AK)B*)D(Q^[^C(NCTMDDKE-JEK)E[OEK)D9M^@0^[DHQ
)@@G@@C0)D1JE))C1JE(IC))+@@@@@@C@@@Z.  A2 = MV DESCRIPTOR PTR OR 0 IF NOT FOUNHR
)@@G@@D     +@@@@[@H@Z@Y 0)^@)CC3^@.^[^DD#E-DD9ICDMFC)D- E1 D))E[JDDIE- EK)D9MHS
)@@G@@^@0^[DC0)D1JE))C1JE(IC))+@@@@@@D@@@Z.  A3 = DICTIONARY LEVEL POINTER OR HT
)@@G@@0 IF NOT FOUND    @[@@@Z.     @F@@@ZM$DLS*    LA,U      A3,M$DLFS       HU
)@@G@@  . FIND A LEVEL FOR SEARCHING@ @@@Z          J         DLSEARCH  @H@@@ZHV
)@@G@@M$DLSU*   LA        A3,(1*/12,M$DLFI) . UPDATE FLAG, ROUTINE FOR LEVEL FHW
)@@G@@IND   @]@@@Z          . @#@)@ZDLSEARCH  ROUTINE @^@@@)DLSEARCH  SUBROUTIHX
)@@G@@NE    @^@@@ZDLSNAM    LOCAL     2   @#@@@ZDLSLEV    LOCAL   @F@@@ZDLSDLPHY
)@@G@@    LOCAL                       . DICTIONARY LEVEL POINTER  @G@@@ZDLSRTNHZ
)@@G@@    LOCAL                       . DICTIONARY LEVEL FIND ROUTINE   @D@@@ZIA
)@@G@@DLSUPD    EQUF      DLSRTN,,S1        . UPDATE FLAG   @D@@@Z          DSIB
)@@G@@        A0,DLSNAM         . SAVE THE NAME @D@@@Z          SA        A2,DIC
)@@G@@LSLEV         . SAVE THE LEVEL+@@@@[@M@Z@Y^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)ETU^@)^@)^@)^@)ID
)@@G@@C-GET^D-K^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@) 0)DDIDDODD[D))C-DCTODDJD1[ELT^[GC(QC(G^[KD9DIE
)@@G@@D1OC(M+@@@@@@E@@@Z          SA        A3,DLSRTN         . POST ROUTINE AIF
)@@G@@DDRESS@G@@@Z          SZ        DLSDLP            . INITIAL DICTIONARY LIG
)@@G@@EVEL POINTER@E@@@ZDLS010    LA        A0,DLSLEV         . GET THE SEARCHIH
)@@G@@ LEVEL@F@@@Z          CALL      *DLSRTN           . FIND THE DICTIONARY II
)@@G@@LEVEL @E@@@Z          AN,U      A0,1              . DECREMENT THE LEVEL IJ
)@@G@@@G@@@Z          SA        A0,DLSLEV         . POST IN CASE OF CONTINUED IK
)@@G@@SEARCH@F@@@Z          JNZ       A2,DLS020         . SKIP AHEAD IF LEVEL IL
)@@G@@FOUND @G@@@Z          TNZ       DLSUPD            . PROCESSING AN UPDATEIM
)@@G@@ SEARCH?    @H@@@Z          JP        A0,DLS010         . NO, KEEP LOOKIIN
)@@G@@NG IF POSITIVE LEVEL    @C@@@Z          J         DLS999            . NOIO
)@@G@@ FIND @G@@@ZDLS020    LA,U      A0,DLMSTP,A2      . GET THE SYMBOL TABLEIP
)@@G@@ PKT PTR    @E@@@Z          LA,U      A1,DLSNAM         . GET THE SYMBOLIQ
)@@G@@ PTR  @E@@@Z          LXI,U     A1,MVNLEN         . SIZE OF THE SYMBOL  IR
)@@G@@@G@@@Z          SA        A2,DLSDLP         . SAVE DICTIONARY LEVEL POINIS
)@@G@@TER   @D@@@Z          AVLSK                       . FIND THE NAME @I@@@ZIT
)@@G@@          TNZ       DLSUPD            . IF UPDATE SEARCH, RETURN WITH A2IU
)@@G@@ INTACT     @F@@@Z          JZ        A2,DLS010         . IF NO FIND, TRIV
)@@G@@Y NEXT LEVEL@E@@@ZDLS999    DL        A0,DLSNAM         . RECOVER SYMBOLIW
)@@G@@ NAME @G@@@Z          LA        A3,DLSDLP         . RETURN DICTIONARY LEIX
)@@G@@VEL POINTER @C@@@Z          RETURN                      . DONE    @[@@@ZIY
)@@G@@.     @D@@@Z. M$DLI - INSERT A MACRO SYMBOL INTO THE DICTIONARY.  @[@@@ZIZ
)@@G@@.     @^@@@Z.  A0,A1 = MACRO SYMBOL @B@@@Z.  A2 = INITIAL LEVEL AT WHICHJA
)@@G@@ TO INSERT  @#@@@Z.  LMJ  X11,M$DLI @^@@@Z.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @^@@@ZJB
)@@G@@.  A0,A1 = SYMBOL NAME  @ @@@Z.  A2 = MV DESCRIPTOR PTR     @A@@@Z.  A3 JC
)@@G@@= DICTIONARY LEVEL POINTER    @[@@@Z.     @#@@@ZM$DLI*    ROUTINE @^@@@ZJD
)@@G@@DLINAM    LOCAL     2   @F@@@ZDLIDLP    LOCAL                       . DIJE
)@@G@@CTIONARY LEVEL POINTER  @D@@@Z          DS        A0,DLINAM         . SAJF
)@@G@@VE THE NAME @G@@@Z          LA        A0,A2             . GET THE INITIAJG
)@@G@@L INSERTION LEVEL @F@@@Z          CALL      M$DLFI            . FIND THEJH
)@@G@@ INSERTION LEVEL  @G@@@Z          JNZ       A2,DLI010         . IF LEVELJI
)@@G@@ FOUND, GO CREATE A VAR @D@@@Z          LA        A5,PCL('INSERTION LEVEJJ
)@@G@@L ERROR.')  @E@@@Z          JN        A0,DLI999         . IF LEVEL ERRORJK
)@@G@@, EXIT@H@@@Z          CALL      M$DLC             . CREATE A NEW LEVEL AJL
)@@G@@T WHICH TO INSERT @ @@@Z          JNZ       A5,DLI999 @F@@@Z          LAJM
)@@G@@,U      A2,,A1            . GET DICTIONARY LEVEL TO A2@E@@@ZDLI010    DLJN
)@@G@@        A0,DLINAM         . RECOVER THE NAME    @G@@@Z          SA      JO
)@@G@@  A2,DLIDLP         . SAVE DICTIONARY LEVEL POINTER   @G@@@Z          LAJP
)@@G@@,U      A3,DLMSTP,A2      . GET THE SYMBOL TABLE ADDRESS    @F@@@Z      JQ
)@@G@@    CALL      M$MVCREATE        . CREATE A MACRO VARIABLE   @G@@@Z      JR
)@@G@@    LA        A3,DLIDLP         . RETURN DICTIONARY LEVEL POINTER @C@@@ZJS
)@@G@@DLI999    RETURN                      . DONE    @[@@@Z/.    @D@@@Z. M$DLJT
)@@G@@D - DELETE A SYMBOL FROM THE DICTIONARY LEVELS. @[@@@Z.     @^@@@Z.  A0,JU
)@@G@@A1 = SYMBOL NAME  @ @@@Z.  A2 = INITIAL DELETION LEVEL@#@@@Z.  LMJ  X11,JV
)@@G@@M$DLD @^@@@Z.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @[@@@Z.     @#@@@ZM$DLD*    ROUTINE JW
)@@G@@@^@@@ZDLDNAM    LOCAL     2   @D@@@Z          DS        A0,DLDNAM       JX
)@@G@@  . SAVE THE NAME @F@@@Z          LA        A0,A2             . GET THE JY
)@@G@@INITIAL LEVEL     @G@@@Z          CALL      M$DLFD            . FIND THEJZ
)@@G@@ LEVEL FOR DELETION     @G@@@Z          JZ        A2,DLD900         . IFKA
)@@G@@ NO FIND ON LEVEL, NO DELETE  @F@@@Z          LA,U      A0,DLMSTP,A2    KB
)@@G@@  . GET THE SYMBOL TABLE PTR  @E@@@Z          LA,U      A1,DLDNAM       KC
)@@G@@  . GET THE NAME PTR    @D@@@Z          LXI,U     A1,MVNLEN         . NAKD
)@@G@@ME LENGTH   @F@@@Z          AVLDK                       . DELETE THE MACKE
)@@G@@RO VARIABLE @E@@@Z          JZ        A2,DLD900         . IF NOT FOUND, KF
)@@G@@OK    @F@@@Z          LA,U      A0,MV,A2          . GET THE VALUE DESCRIKG
)@@G@@PTOR  @B@@@Z          CALL      M$MVVD            .   @F@@@Z          DSKH
)@@G@@        A0,DLDNAM         . SAVE THE VALUE DESCRIPTOR @F@-@Z          PRKI
)@@G@@EL      0,A2,U            . RELEASE THE MV DESCRIPTOR @F@@@-          LAKJ
)@@G@@,U      A0,0,A2           . RELEASE THE MV DESCRIPTOR @#@@@-          M$KK
)@@G@@PREL  @D@@@Z          DL        A0,DLDNAM         . RECOVER THE VD@E@@@ZKL
)@@G@@          SA        A5,DLDNAM         . TEMP SAVE ANY ERROR @D@@@Z      KM
)@@G@@    CALL      M$VDERS           . ERASE THE DATA@E@@@Z          TZ      KN
)@@G@@  DLDNAM            . ANY PREVIOUS ERROR? @E@@@Z          LA        A5,DKO
)@@G@@LDNAM         . YES, RECOVER IT     @C@@@Z          J         DLD999    KP
)@@G@@        . DONE    @D@@@ZDLD900    LA,U      A5,0              . NO ERRORKQ
)@@G@@S     @C@@@ZDLD999    RETURN                      . BYE     @[@Z@Y.     KR
)@@G@@@[@@@Z/.    @D@@@Y. M$SYMBOL - ROUTINE TO RESOLVE A SCANNED SYMBOL.     KS
)@@G@@@[@@@Y.     @ @@@Y.  A0,A1 = MACRO SYMBOL NAME  @^@@@Y.  LMJ  X11,M$SYMBKT
)@@G@@OL    @^@Z@Y.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @A@Z@Y.  A4 = 1 (FOUND) OR 0 (NOT FOKU
)@@G@@UND)  @B@@@Z.  A2 = 0 IF NOT FOUND; NONZERO OTHERWISE.@B@@@Y.  A0,A1 = VKV
)@@G@@ALUE DESCRIPTOR IF FOUND.     @[@@@Y.     @#@)@YM$SYMBOL* ROUTINE @^@@@)KW
)@@G@@M$SYMBOL* SUBROUTINE    @E@@@YSYMNAM    LOCAL     2                 . THKX
)@@G@@E SYMBOL NAME     @E@@@Y          DS        A0,SYMNAM         . SAVE THEKY
)@@G@@ SYMBOL NAME@G@@@Y          LA,S1     A2,SYMNAM         . GET THE FIRST KZ
)@@G@@CHAR OF THE SYMBOL@H@@@Z          LA,H1     A3,SYMNAM         . GET THE LA
)@@G@@FIRST 3 CHARS OF THE SYMBOL   @G@Z@Y          JNE,U     A2,'$' SYM010   LB
)@@G@@  . SKIP IF NOT AN INTRINSIC SIGNAL @E@@@Z          TE,U      A3,'$  '  LC
)@@G@@        . IS THE SYMBOL '$'?  @G@@@Z          TE,U      A2,'$'          LD
)@@G@@  . NO, DOES IT HAVE THE '$' PREFIX @G@@@Z          J         SYM010    LE
)@@G@@        . THE '$' SYMBOL, OR NO '$' PREFIX@F@@@Y          LDSC      A0,6LF
)@@G@@              . SLIDE '$' TO END OF SYMBOL@F@@@Y          AN,U      A1,'LG
)@@G@@$'-' '        . TURN DOLLAR INTO BLANK    @G@@@Y          J         SYM0LH
)@@G@@50            . GO SEE IF IN INTRINSIC TABLE    @F@@@YSYM010    CALL    LI
)@@G@@  M$MVFIND          . SEE IF IT'S USER-DEFINED  @E@Z@Y          JNZ     LJ
)@@G@@  A5,SYM999         . CHECK FOR ERROR     @D@Z@Y          JNZ       A4,SLK
)@@G@@YM999         . CHECK FOR DONE@D@@@Z          JNZ       A2,SYM999       LL
)@@G@@  . IF FOUND, EXIT@G@@@Y          LA        A2,M$VAROTHER     . SEE IF ILM
)@@G@@N USER'S OTHER TABLES   @F@@@Y          JZ        A2,SYM020         . SKLN
)@@G@@IP IF NO OTHER TABLES   @F@@@Y          CALL      0,A2              . CALO
)@@G@@LL THE OTHER ROUTINES   @E@Z@Y          JNZ       A5,SYM999         . CHLP
)@@G@@ECK FOR ERROR     @D@Z@Y          JNZ       A4,SYM999         . CHECK FOLQ
)@@G@@R DONE@D@@@Z          JNZ       A2,SYM999         . EXIT IF FOUND @F@@@YLR
)@@G@@SYM020    CALL      M$IVFIND          . CHECK THE INTRINSIC TABLE @E@Z@YLS
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,SYM999         . CHECK FOR ERROR     @D@Z@Y      LT
)@@G@@    JNZ       A4,SYM999         . CHECK FOR DONE@D@@@Z          JNZ     LU
)@@G@@  A2,SYM999         . IF FOUND, EXIT@^@@@Y          LA,U      A3,0@E@@@YLV
)@@G@@SYM030    AND,U     A1,077            . GET THE LAST CHAR   @F@@@Y      LW
)@@G@@    JNE,U     A2,' ' SYM040     . IF NOT A BLANK, SKIP OUT  @E@@@Y      LX
)@@G@@    DSC       A0,6              . SLIDE CHAR AROUND   @D@@@Y          AALY
)@@G@@,U      A3,6              . AND COUNT THEM@E@@@Y          J         SYM0LZ
)@@G@@30            . CHECK NEXT CHAR     @G@Z@YSYM040    JNE,U     A2,'$' SYMMA
)@@G@@999     . IF NOT AN INTRINSIC SIGNAL, QUIT@G@@@ZSYM040    JNE,U     A2,'MB
)@@G@@$' SYM900     . IF NOT AN INTRINSIC SIGNAL, QUIT@G@@@Y          AN,U    MC
)@@G@@  A1,'$'-' '        . TURN THE DOLLAR INTO A BLANK    @E@@@Y          LDMD
)@@G@@SC      A0,,A3            . REALIGN CHARS AGAIN @E@@@Z          LA,U    ME
)@@G@@  A2,0              . CLEAR FOUND FLAG    @G@@@Z          DTE       A0,MMF
)@@G@@$FDBLANKS     . DON'T SEARCH FOR ALL BLANKS     @F@@@YSYM050    CALL    MG
)@@G@@  M$IVFIND          . TRY INTRINSIC TABLE AGAIN @E@Z@Y          JNZ     MH
)@@G@@  A5,SYM999         . CHECK FOR ERROR     @D@Z@Y          JNZ       A4,SMI
)@@G@@YM999         . CHECK FOR DONE@D@@@Z          JNZ       A2,SYM999       MJ
)@@G@@  . CHECK IF FOUND@E@@@Y          DL        A0,SYMNAM         . RESTORE MK
)@@G@@THE SYMBOL  @E@@@ZSYM900    LA,U      A2,0              . SET NOT FOUND ML
)@@G@@FLAG  @C@@@YSYM999    RETURN                      . DONE    @[@@@Y.     MM
)@@G@@@[@@@Y/.    @A@@@Y. M$MVFIND - FIND A MACRO VARIABLE. @[@@@Y.     @^@@@YMN
)@@G@@.  A0,A1=MACRO SYMBOL   @^@@@Y.  LMJ X11,M$MVFIND     @]@Z@Y.  A5 = 0   MO
)@@G@@@#@Z@Y.  A4 = 1 THEN:   @B@@@Z.  A2 = MACRO VARIABLE DESCRIPTOR (FOUND) MP
)@@G@@@D@@@Y.     A0,A1 = VALUE DESCRIPTOR FOR MACRO VARIABLE     @C@Z@Y.     MQ
)@@G@@A2 = MACRO VARIABLE DESCRIPTOR POINTER    @E@Z@Y.     A3 = MACRO EXECUTIMR
)@@G@@ON FRAME POINTER OR 0 FOR GLOBALS   @ @Z@Y.  A4 = 0 THEN: (NO FIND)     MS
)@@G@@@ @@@Z.  A2 = 0 THEN: (NO FIND)     @ @@@Y.     A0,A1 = MACRO SYMBOL    MT
)@@G@@@[@@@Y.     @#@Z@Y          INSTRS  @]@Z@YM$MVFIND*   @#@Z@Y          ROMU
)@@G@@UTINE @#@)@ZM$MVFIND* ROUTINE @^@@@)M$MVFIND* SUBROUTINE    @B@Z@YSYMBOLMV
)@@G@@    LOCAL     2                 .   @^@@@ZMVFNAM    LOCAL     2   @D@@@ZMW
)@@G@@          DS        A0,MVFNAM         . SAVE THE NAME @F@@@Z          LAMX
)@@G@@,H2     A3,M$XQTMACRO     . GET THE CURRENT MACRO LINK@G@@@Z          JZMY
)@@G@@        A3,MVF010         . IF NO MACRO, TRY SYMBOL TABLES  @F@@@Z      MZ
)@@G@@    LA        A0,MXMDL,A3       . GET THE DEFINITION LINK   @F@@@Z      NA
)@@G@@    LA        A0,MDLTL,A0       . GET ANY LABLE TABLE LINK  @G@@@Z      NB
)@@G@@    JZ        A0,MVF010         . IF NO TABLE, TRY DICTIONARY     @E@@@ZNC
)@@G@@          LA,U      A1,MVFNAM         . GET THE SYMBOL PTR  @B@@@Z      ND
)@@G@@    LXI,U     A1,MVNLEN         .   @E@@@Z          AVLSK               NE
)@@G@@        . FIND THE SYMBOL     @E@@@Z          JNZ       A2,MVF020       NF
)@@G@@  . IF FOUND, GO AHEAD  @F@@@ZMVF010    DL        A0,MVFNAM         . RENG
)@@G@@COVER THE SYMBOL NAME   @G@@@Z          LA        A2,M$SCANDL       . GENH
)@@G@@T THE SCAN DICTIONARY LEVEL   @G@@@Z          CALL      M$DLS           NI
)@@G@@  . SEARCH THE DICTIONARY LEVELS    @E@@@Z          JZ        A2,MVF999 NJ
)@@G@@        . IF NO FIND, EXIT    @F@@@ZMVF020    LA,U      A0,MV,A2        NK
)@@G@@  . GET THE DESCRIPTOR PTR    @G@@@Z          CALL      M$MVVD          NL
)@@G@@  . OBTAIN THE DESCRIPTOR IN A0,A1  @F@Z@YPTR       LOCAL               NM
)@@G@@        . TEMP SAVE FOR POINTER     @E@Z@Y          DS        A0,SYMBOL NN
)@@G@@        . SAVE THE SYMBOL NAME@E@Z@Y          LA        A3,M$XQTMACRO   NO
)@@G@@  . GET MACROS IN H2    @E@Z@Y          LXI       A3,M$GLOBALS      . GENP
)@@G@@T GLOBALS IN H1   @F@Z@Y          $IF       EDPROCS           . SUPPORTINQ
)@@G@@NG EDITOR PROCS?  @F@Z@Y          JEZ       M$EDPROCS MVF010  . SKIP OUTNR
)@@G@@ IF NO ED PROCS   @E@Z@Y          TZ,U      0,A3              . IS THERENS
)@@G@@ A MACRO?   @E@Z@Y          TNZ       MXPF,A3           . YES, IS IT A PNT
)@@G@@ROC?  @E@Z@Y          J         MVF010            . NO, DO NORMAL STUFF NU
)@@G@@@F@Z@Y          LA        A0,MXMDL,A3       . GET MACRO DEFINITION LINK NV
)@@G@@@F@Z@Y          LA        A0,MDLTL,A0       . GET THE LABEL TABLE LINK  NW
)@@G@@@F@Z@Y          JZ        A0,MVF010         . SKIP OUT IF NO LABELS     NX
)@@G@@@E@Z@Y          SA        A3,PTR            . SAVE THE POINTER    @E@Z@YNY
)@@G@@          LA,U      A1,SYMBOL         . GET ADDR OF SYMBOL  @D@Z@Y      NZ
)@@G@@    AVLSK                       . SEARCH FOR IT @F@Z@Y          JNZ     OA
)@@G@@  A2,MVF050         . IF FOUND, GO PROCESS IT   @E@Z@Y          LA      OB
)@@G@@  A3,PTR            . RESTORE POINTER     @E@Z@Y          $ENDF     EDPROC
)@@G@@OCS           . SPECIAL ED PROC CODE@F@Z@YMVF010    JNEZ,U    0,A3 MVF02OD
)@@G@@0       . SKIP IF WE HAVE MACROS    @F@Z@Y          JZ        A3,MVF060 OE
)@@G@@        . IF NO GLOBALS, GO FAIL    @F@Z@Y          LDSL      A2,18     OF
)@@G@@        . GLOBALS TO A2; CLEAR A3   @E@Z@Y          J         MVF040    OG
)@@G@@        . GO SEARCH GLOBALS   @F@Z@YMVF020    LA        A2,MXLTL,A3     OH
)@@G@@  . A2 = LOCAL TABLE LINK     @F@Z@Y          JNZ       A2,MVF040       OI
)@@G@@  . IF IT'S THERE, GO USE IT  @F@Z@YMVF030    LXM       A3,MXNML,A3     OJ
)@@G@@  . GET THE NEXT MACRO LINK   @D@Z@Y          J         MVF010          OK
)@@G@@  . TRY THIS MACRO@E@Z@YMVF040    SA        A3,PTR            . SAVE CUROL
)@@G@@RENT POINTER@F@Z@Y          LA,U      A1,SYMBOL         . GET THE SYMBOLOM
)@@G@@ ADDRESS    @E@Z@Y          LXI,U     A1,2              . LENGTH OF THE ON
)@@G@@NAME  @D@Z@Y          AVLSK     0,A2,U            . SEARCH FOR IT @E@Z@YOO
)@@G@@          JNZ       A2,MVF050         . IF FOUND, PROCESS IT@E@Z@Y      OP
)@@G@@    LA        A3,PTR            . RESTORE POINTER     @F@Z@Y          JZOQ
)@@G@@        A3,MVF060         . IF NO MACRO LINKS, GO FAIL@E@Z@Y          J OR
)@@G@@        MVF030            . TRY THE NEXT MACRO  @F@Z@YMVF050    LA,U    OS
)@@G@@  A0,,A2            . GET THE DESCRIPTOR ADDRESS@E@Z@Y          CALL    OT
)@@G@@  M$MVVD            . GET THE DESCRIPTOR  @H@Z@Y          LA,H2     A3,POU
)@@G@@TR            . GET THE MACRO LINK (OR 0 IF GLOBAL)   @G@Z@Y          DLOV
)@@G@@        A4,M$DONE         . SET 'FOUND' IN A4; CLEAR A5     @ @Z@Y      OW
)@@G@@    J         MVF999    @F@Z@YMVF060    DL        A0,SYMBOL         . REOX
)@@G@@STORE SYMBOL TO A0,A1   @G@Z@Y          DSL       A4,72             . SEOY
)@@G@@T 'NO FIND' IN A4; CLEAR A5   @C@Z@YMVF999    RETURN                    OZ
)@@G@@  . ALL DONE@E@@@Z          DS        A0,MVFNAM         . STASH THE DESCPA
)@@G@@RIPTOR@F@@@ZMVF999    DL        A0,MVFNAM         . RELOAD THE NAME/DESCPB
)@@G@@RIPTOR@C@@@Z          RETURN                      . DONE    @[@Z@Y.     PC
)@@G@@@[@@@Y/.    @C@Z@Y. M$MVLOCAL - DEFINE A LOCAL MACRO VARIABLE.    @[@Z@YPD
)@@G@@.     @ @Z@Y.  A0,A1 = MACRO SYMBOL NAME  @B@Z@Y.  A3 = MACRO EXECUTION PE
)@@G@@FRAME POINTER     @^@Z@Y.  LMJ  X11,M$MVLOCAL   @^@Z@Y.  A5 = ERROR PCW PF
)@@G@@OR 0  @ @Z@Y.  A0,A1 = MACRO SYMBOL NAME  @B@Z@Y.  A2 = MACRO VARIABLE DPG
)@@G@@ESCRIPTOR POINTER @B@Z@Y.  A3 = MACRO EXECUTION FRAME POINTER     @[@Z@YPH
)@@G@@.     @C@Z@Y. M$MVGLOBAL - DEFINE A GLOBAL MACRO VARIABLE.  @[@Z@Y.     PI
)@@G@@@ @Z@Y.  A0,A1 = MACRO SYMBOL NAME  @^@Z@Y.  LMJ  X11,M$MVGLOBAL  @^@Z@YPJ
)@@G@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @ @Z@Y.  A0,A1 = MACRO SYMBOL NAME  @B@Z@Y.  A2 PK
)@@G@@= MACRO VARIABLE DESCRIPTOR POINTER @[@Z@Y.     @G@@@Y. M$MVCREATE - CREPL
)@@G@@ATE A MACRO VARIABLE DEFINITION IN AN ARBITRARY TABLE.@[@@@Y.     @ @@@YPM
)@@G@@.  A0,A1 = MACRO SYMBOL NAME  @^@@@Y.  A3 = TABLE POINTER   @^@@@Y.  LMJPN
)@@G@@  X11,M$MVCREATE  @^@@@Y.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @^@@@Y.  A0,A1 = MACRO SPO
)@@G@@YMBOL @B@@@Y.  A2 = MACRO VARIABLE DEFINITION POINTER @[@@@Y.     @]@Z@YPP
)@@G@@M$MVGLOBAL* @A@Z@Y          LA        A3,M$GLOBALS    @D@Z@Y          J PQ
)@@G@@        M$MVCREATE        . GO CREATE     @]@Z@YM$MVLOCAL*  @E@Z@Y      PR
)@@G@@    LA        A3,MXLTL,A3       . GET LABEL TABLE LINK@]@Z@YM$MVCREATE* PS
)@@G@@@^@)@ZM$MVCREATE* ROUTINE     @^@@@)M$MVCREATE* SUBROUTINE  @#@Z@Y      PT
)@@G@@    ROUTINE @D@@@YSYMBOL    LOCAL     2                 . SYMBOL NAME   PU
)@@G@@@D@@@YMVPTR     LOCAL     1                 . MV POINTER    @D@@@YMTPTR PV
)@@G@@    LOCAL     1                 . TABLE  POINTER@E@@@Y          DS      PW
)@@G@@  A0,SYMBOL         . SAVE THE SYMBOL NAME@E@@@Y          SA        A3,MPX
)@@G@@TPTR          . SAVE TABLE POINTER  @G@-@Y          PGET      MVSIZE    PY
)@@G@@        . GET A MACRO VARIABLE BUFFER     @E@-@Y          JNZ       A5,MPZ
)@@G@@VL999         . CHECK FOR ERRORS    @E@@@-          M$PGET    MVL999 MVSQA
)@@G@@IZE     . GET MACRO VAR BUFFER@F@@@Y          LA,U      A0,MODNUL       QB
)@@G@@  . GET A NULL DESCRIPTOR     @E@@@Y          SA        A0,MVDM,A1      QC
)@@G@@  . POST THE DATA MODE  @F@@@Y          SZ        MVDAW,A1          . CLQD
)@@G@@EAR THE DATA ACCESS WORD@E@@@Y          DL        A2,SYMBOL         . GEQE
)@@G@@T THE SYMBOL NAME @D@@@Y          DS        A2,MVN,A1         . POST THEQF
)@@G@@ NAME @F@@@Y          SA        A1,MVPTR          . SAVE OUR NODE POINTEQG
)@@G@@R     @E@@@Y          LXI,U     A1,2              . SET SYMBOL LENGTH   QH
)@@G@@@F@@@Y          LA        A0,MTPTR          . GET THE TABLE POINTER     QI
)@@G@@@E@@@Y          AVLIK                       . INSERT THE SYMBOL   @E@@@YQJ
)@@G@@          JZ        A2,MVL010         . SKIP IF GOOD INSERT @E@@@Y      QK
)@@G@@    LA        A0,MVPTR          . GET USELESS VAR PTR @F@@@Y          SAQL
)@@G@@        A2,MVPTR          . SAVE PREVIOUS VAR PTR     @E@-@Y          PRQM
)@@G@@EL                        . RELEASE NEW VAR BUF @E@-@Y          JNZ     QN
)@@G@@  A5,MVL999         . CHECK FOR ERRRORS   @E@@@-          M$PREL    MVL9QO
)@@G@@99            . RELEASE NEW VAR BUF @F@@@YMVL010    DL        A2,MVPTR  QP
)@@G@@        . A2=VAR PTR;A3=MACRO LINK  @F@@@Y          DL        A0,MVN,A2 QQ
)@@G@@        . GET THE VARIABLE NAME     @B@@@Y          LA,U      A5,0      QR
)@@G@@        .   @#@@@YMVL999    RETURN  @[@@@Z.     @C@@@Z. M$MVERASE - ROUTQS
)@@G@@INE TO ERASE A MACRO VARIABLE.@[@@@Z.     @^@@@Z.  A0,A1 = SYMBOL NAME  QT
)@@G@@@^@@@Z.  LMJ  X11,M$MVERASE   @^@@@Z.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @[@@@Z.     QU
)@@G@@@]@@@ZM$MVERASE*  @G@@@Z          LA        A2,M$SCANDL       . GET THE QV
)@@G@@SCAN DICTIONARY LEVEL   @F@@@Z          J         M$DLD             . DEQW
)@@G@@LETE A DICTIONARY ITEM  @[@Z@Y/.    @C@Z@Y. M$MVERASE - ROUTINE TO ERASEQX
)@@G@@ A MACRO VARIABLE.@[@Z@Y.     @^@Z@Y.  A0,A1 = SYMBOL NAME  @^@Z@Y.  LMJQY
)@@G@@  X11,M$MVERASE   @^@Z@Y.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @[@Z@Y.     @]@Z@YM$MVERQZ
)@@G@@ASE*  @#@Z@Y          ROUTINE @E@Z@YMVEVD     LOCAL     2               RA
)@@G@@  . VALUE DESCRIPTOR    @E@Z@Y          LMJ       X11,M$MVFIND      . FIRB
)@@G@@ND THE SYMBOLS    @E@Z@Y          JZ        A4,MVE999         . IF NOT FRC
)@@G@@OUND, EXIT  @F@Z@Y          DS        A0,MVEVD          . SAVE VALUE DESRD
)@@G@@CRIPTOR     @E@Z@Y          LA        A0,M$GLOBALS      . GET GLOBALS TARE
)@@G@@BLE   @F@Z@Y          TZ,U      0,A3              . WAS SYMBOL FROM A MARF
)@@G@@CRO?  @F@Z@Y          LA        A0,MXLTL,A3       . YES, GET ITS LOCALS RG
)@@G@@TABLE @E@Z@Y          LA,U      A1,,A2            . GET THE NODE ADDRESSRH
)@@G@@@G@Z@Y          AVLDN                       . REMOVE THE NODE FROM THE TRI
)@@G@@REE   @E@Z@Y          PREL      0,A2,U            . RELEASE THE SPACE   RJ
)@@G@@@G@Z@Y          DL        A0,MVEVD          . RECOVER THE VALUE DESCRIPTRK
)@@G@@OR    @G@Z@Y          SA        A5,MVEVD          . TEMP SAVE POSSIBLE ERL
)@@G@@RROR PCW    @E@Z@Y          CALL      M$VDERS           . ERASE THE VALURM
)@@G@@E     @E@Z@Y          TZ        MVEVD             . ANY PREVIOUS ERROR? RN
)@@G@@@D@Z@Y          LA        A5,MVEVD          . YES, GET IT   @D@Z@YMVE999RO
)@@G@@    RETURN                      . THAT'S ALL    @[@@@Y/.    @B@@@Y. M$IVRP
)@@G@@FIND - FIND AN INTRINSIC VARIABLE   @[@@@Y.     @^@@@Y.  A0A1 = SYMBOL NRQ
)@@G@@AME   @^@@@Y.  LMJ  X11,M$IVFIND    @#@Z@Y.  A4 = 1 (FOUND) @B@@@Z.  A2 RR
)@@G@@= SYMBOL ENTRY POINTE (IF FOUND)    @ @@@Y.    A0A1 = VALUE DESCRIPTOR  RS
)@@G@@@B@Z@Y.    A2 = INTRINSIC SYMBOL ENTRY POINTER  @^@Z@Y.  A4 = 0 (NOT FOURT
)@@G@@ND)   @^@@@Z.  A2 = 0 (IF NOT FOUND)@^@@@Y.    A0A1 = SYMBOL NAME @[@@@YRU
)@@G@@.     @#@)@YM$IVFIND* ROUTINE @^@@@)M$IVFIND* SUBROUTINE    @D@@@YIVNAMERV
)@@G@@    LOCAL     2                 . SAVE THE NAME @ @@@Y          DS      RW
)@@G@@  A0,IVNAME @F@@@Y          LA,U      A1,IVNAME         . SEARCH STRING RX
)@@G@@IS THE NAME @F@@@Y          LXI,U     A1,1              . IT'S ONLY ONE RY
)@@G@@WORD LONG   @G@@@Y          AVLSK     M$IVTBL           . SEARCH THE INTRZ
)@@G@@RINSIC VAR TABLE  @F@Z@Y          DSL       A4,72             . ASSUME NSA
)@@G@@O FIND, NO ERROR  @E@@@Y          DL        A0,IVNAME         . RESTORE SB
)@@G@@THE NAME    @E@@@Y          JZ        A2,MIVF999        . IF A2=0, NO FISC
)@@G@@ND    @G@@@Y          LA        A0,IVH1W0,A2      . GET H1 WORD 0 OF DESSD
)@@G@@CRIPTOR     @F@@@Y          LSSL      A0,18             . PUT IN CORRECTSE
)@@G@@ POSITION   @F@@@Y          LA        A1,IVW1,A2        . GET WORD 1 OF SF
)@@G@@DESCRIPTOR  @E@Z@Y          LA,U      A4,1              . POST 'FOUND' FSG
)@@G@@LAG   @C@@@YMIVF999   RETURN                      . DONE    @[@@@Y.     SH
)@@G@@@[@@@Y/.    @C@@@Y. M$MVSET - SET A MACRO VARIABLE TO A NEW VALUE.@[@@@YSI
)@@G@@.     @C@@@Y.  A0 = ADDRESS OF MACRO VARIABLE DESCRIPTOR    @B@@@Y.  A1 SJ
)@@G@@= ADDRESS OF NEW VALUE DESCRIPTOR   @^@@@Y.  LMJ  X11,M$MVSET     @^@@@YSK
)@@G@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @[@@@Y.     @#@)@YM$MVSET*  ROUTINE @^@@@)M$MVSESL
)@@G@@T*  SUBROUTINE    @E@@@YMVSPTRS   LOCAL     3                 . OLD AND SM
)@@G@@NEW POINTERS@D@@@YMVSMVP    EQUF      MVSPTRS           . MACRO VAR PTR SN
)@@G@@@E@@@YMVSNEW    EQUF      MVSPTRS+1         . NEW VALUE DESCRIPTOR@E@@@YSO
)@@G@@MVSERR    LOCAL     1                 . ERROR PCW (MAYBE)   @F@@@Y      SP
)@@G@@    DS        A0,MVSPTRS        . POST OLD AND NEW PTRS     @E@@@Y      SQ
)@@G@@    DL        A0,VD,A1          . GET NEW DESCRIPTOR  @D@@@Y          CASR
)@@G@@LL      M$VDCOPYV         . COPY A VALUE  @D@@@Y          JNZ       A5,MSS
)@@G@@VS999         . IF ERROR, QUIT@E@@@Y          DS        A0,MVSNEW       ST
)@@G@@  . SAVE NEW DESCRIPTOR @F@@@Y          LA        A2,MVSMVP         . GESU
)@@G@@T POINTER TO MACRO VAR  @C@@@Y          LA        A0,MVDM,A2        . MOSV
)@@G@@DE    @C@@@Y          LSSL      A0,30             . ALIGN   @E@@@Y      SW
)@@G@@    LA        A1,MVDAW,A2       . OLD DATA ACCESS WORD@D@@@Y          CASX
)@@G@@LL      M$VDERS           . ERASE OLD DATA@D@@@Y          SA        A5,MSY
)@@G@@VSERR         . SAVE ERROR    @G@@@Y          LA        A1,MVSMVP       SZ
)@@G@@  . RESTORE MACRO DESCRIPTOR POINTER@D@@@Y          LA        A0,VDM+MVSTA
)@@G@@NEW     . GET NEW MODE  @E@@@Y          LA        A2,VDAW+MVSNEW    . GETB
)@@G@@T NEW ACCESS WORD @F@@@Y          SA        A0,MVDM,A1        . POST IT TC
)@@G@@IN MACRO DESCR    @E@@@Y          SA        A2,MVDAW,A1       . POST IN TD
)@@G@@MACRO DESCR @F@@@Y          LA        A5,MVSERR         . GET PREVIOUS ETE
)@@G@@RROR, IF ANY@#@@@YMVS999    RETURN  @[@@@Y.     @G@@@Y. M$MVVD - ROUTINETF
)@@G@@ TO RETURN A VALUE DESCRIPTOR FROM A MACRO VARIABLE.  @[@@@Y.     @C@@@YTG
)@@G@@.  A0 = ADDRESS OF A MACRO VARIABLE DESCRIPTOR. @#@@@Y.  LMJ  X11,M$MVVDTH
)@@G@@@ @@@Y.  A0,A1 = VALUE DESCRIPTOR   @^@@@Y.  USES ONLY X11,A0,A1  @[@@@YTI
)@@G@@.     @F@@@YM$MVVD*   LA        A1,MVDAW,A0       . GET THE DATA ACCESS TJ
)@@G@@WORD  @D@@@Y          LA        A0,MVDM,A0        . GET THE MODE  @D@@@YTK
)@@G@@          J         M$VDVDL+1         . FINISH UP     @[@@@Y/.    @D@@@YTL
)@@G@@. M$MDFIND - ROUTINE TO FIND A MACRO DEFINITION ENTRY.@[@@@Y.     @^@@@YTM
)@@G@@.  A0,A1 = MACRO NAME   @^@@@Y.  LMJ  X11,M$MDFIND    @]@@@Y.  A5 = 0   TN
)@@G@@@#@@@Y.  A4 = 1 THEN    @A@@@Y.    A2 = MACRO DEFINITION LINK     @#@@@YTO
)@@G@@.  A4 = 0 THEN    @^@@@Y.    A0,A1 = MACRO NAME @[@@@Y.     @#@)@YM$MDFITP
)@@G@@ND* ROUTINE @^@@@)M$MDFIND* SUBROUTINE    @^@@@YMFNAME    LOCAL     2   TQ
)@@G@@@E@@@Y          DS        A0,MFNAME         . SAVE THE MACRO NAME @F@@@YTR
)@@G@@          LA,U      A1,MFNAME         . GET THE ADDRESS OF SAME   @F@@@YTS
)@@G@@          LXI,U     A1,2              . = # WORDS IN MACRO NAME   @F@@@YTT
)@@G@@          AVLSK     M$DEFMACRO,,H2    . SEARCH DEFINED MACRO LIST @D@@@YTU
)@@G@@          LA,U      A4,1              . ASSUME FOUND  @D@@@Y          DLTV
)@@G@@        A0,MFNAME         . RESTORE NAME  @D@@@Y          TNZ       A2  TW
)@@G@@              . WAS IT FOUND? @F@@@Y          LA,U      A4,0            TX
)@@G@@  . NO, SET NO FOUND FLAG     @D@@@Y          LA,U      A5,0            TY
)@@G@@  . POST NO ERROR @C@@@Y          RETURN                      . DONE    TZ
)@@G@@@[@@@Y.     @F@@@Y. M$MDCREATE - ROUTINE TO CREATE A NEW MACRO DEFINITIOUA
)@@G@@N ENTRY.    @[@@@Y.     @^@@@Y.  A0,A1 = MACRO NAME   @#@@@Y.  A2 = PROCUB
)@@G@@ FLAG @^@@@Y.  A3 = STARTING ADDRESS@^@@@Y.  LMJ  X11,M$MDCREATE  @^@@@YUC
)@@G@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @ @@@Y.  A2 = MACRO DEFINITION LINK @[@@@Y.     UD
)@@G@@@^@)@YM$MDCREATE* ROUTINE     @^@@@)M$MDCREATE* SUBROUTINE  @^@@@YMCNAMEUE
)@@G@@    LOCAL     2   @^@@@YMCA2A3    LOCAL     2   @^@@@YMCPTR     LOCAL   UF
)@@G@@  1   @D@@@Y          DS        A0,MCNAME         . SAVE ARGS     @B@@@YUG
)@@G@@          DS        A2,MCA2A3         .   @H@@@Y          LMJ       X11,UH
)@@G@@M$MDERASE     . GET RID OF ANY CURRENT DEFINITIONS    @E@@@Y          JNUI
)@@G@@Z       A5,MDC999         . CHECK FOR ERRORS    @F@@@Y          LA      UJ
)@@G@@  A0,M$MDEFSIZE     . GET CONFIGURED DEF SIZE   @D@@@Y          TLE,U   UK
)@@G@@  A0,MDSIZE         . IS IT ENUF?   @D@@@Y          ER        ERR$      UL
)@@G@@        . NO, TOO BAD   @C@-@Y          PGET                        . GEUM
)@@G@@T CORE@B@-@Y          JNZ       A5,MDC999         .   @C@@@-          M$UN
)@@G@@PGET    MDC999            . GET CORE@E@@@Y          SA        A1,MCPTR  UO
)@@G@@        . SAVE OUR POINTER    @F@@@Y          DL        A2,MCNAME       UP
)@@G@@  . INITIALIZE THE DEFINITION @E@@@Y          DS        A2,MDN,A1       UQ
)@@G@@  . POST MACRO NAME     @F@@@Y          LXI,U     A1,2              . SEUR
)@@G@@T NAME SIZE IN WORDS    @E@@@Y          AVLIK     M$DEFMACRO,,H2    . INUS
)@@G@@SERT MACRO DEF    @E@@@Y          LA        A2,MCPTR          . RESTORE UT
)@@G@@POINTER     @D@@@Y          DL        A0,MCA2A3         . RESTORE ARGS  UU
)@@G@@@D@@@Y          SA        A0,MDPF,A2        . POST PROC FLAG@F@@@Y      UV
)@@G@@    SA        A1,MDA,A2         . POST STARTING ADDRESS     @H@Z@Y      UW
)@@G@@    $IF       EDPROCS           . ONLY IF SUPPORTING THE EDITOR STUFF   UX
)@@G@@@F@Z@Y          SZ        MDLTL,A2          . CLEAR LABEL TABLE LINK    UY
)@@G@@@F@Z@Y          JZ        A0,MDC010         . SKIP IF NO PROC THIS TIME UZ
)@@G@@@F@@@Y          LMJ       X11,M$NEWMST      . GET A NEW SYMBOL TABLE    VA
)@@G@@@E@@@Y          JNZ       A5,MDC999         . CHECK FOR ERROR     @E@@@YVB
)@@G@@          LA        A2,MCPTR          . RESTORE OUR POINTER @F@@@Y      VC
)@@G@@    SA        A1,MDLTL,A2       . POST THE LABEL TABLE LINK @[@Z@YMDC010VD
)@@G@@@#@Z@Y          $ENDF   @D@Z@Y          LA,U      A5,0              . POVE
)@@G@@ST NO ERRORS@D@@@ZMDC010    LA,U      A5,0              . POST NO ERRORSVF
)@@G@@@#@@@YMDC999    RETURN  @[@@@Y/.    @D@@@Y. M$MDERASE - ROUTINE TO ERASEVG
)@@G@@ A MACRO DEFINITION     @[@@@Y.     @^@@@Y.  A0,A1 = MACRO NAME   @^@@@YVH
)@@G@@.  LMJ  X11,M$MDERASE   @^@@@Y.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @[@@@Y.     @G@@@YVI
)@@G@@. IF THE ERASED MACRO IS ON THE EXECUTION STACK, IT AND ALL LOWER-LEVEL VJ
)@@G@@@D@@@Y. MACROS ARE 'RETURNED' (I.E., POPPED OFF THE STACK). @[@@@Y.     VK
)@@G@@@#@)@YM$MDERASE* ROUTINE@^@@@)M$MDERASE* SUBROUTINE   @E@@@YMENAME    LOVL
)@@G@@CAL     2                 . MACRO NAME TO ERASE @D@@@YMEPTR     LOCAL   VM
)@@G@@                    . DEFN POINTER  @C@@@YMETMP     LOCAL               VN
)@@G@@        . TEMP    @D@@@Y          DS        A0,MENAME         . SAVE OURVO
)@@G@@ NAME @E@@@Y          LA,U      A1,MENAME         . GET ITS ADDRESS     VP
)@@G@@@D@@@Y          LXI,U     A1,2              . GET WORD SIZE @G@@@Y      VQ
)@@G@@    AVLDK     M$DEFMACRO,,H2    . DELETE THE MACRO DEFINITION     @D@@@YVR
)@@G@@          LA,U      A5,0              . NO ERRORS     @D@@@Y          JZVS
)@@G@@        A2,MDE999         . IF NOT FOUND  @E@@@Y          SA        A2,MVT
)@@G@@EPTR          . SAVE OUR DEF LINK   @F@@@Y          LA,H2     A0,M$XQTMAVU
)@@G@@CRO     . SCAN EXECUTING MACROS     @D@@@Y          DSL       A3,72     VV
)@@G@@        . A3,A4 = 0     @E@@@YMDE010    JZ        A0,MDE020         . SKVW
)@@G@@IP IF NOT ON LIST @D@@@Y          AA,U      A3,1              . COUNT A VX
)@@G@@MACRO @G@@@Y          LA        A1,MXMDL,A0       . GET THE MACRO DEFINIVY
)@@G@@TION LINK   @E@@@Y          TNE,U     A1,,A2            . IS THIS OUR MAVZ
)@@G@@CRO?  @F@@@Y          LA        A4,A3             . YES, REMEMBER IT'S IWA
)@@G@@NDEX  @E@@@Y          LA        A0,MXNML,A0       . GET THE NEXT ON LISTWB
)@@G@@@F@@@Y          J         MDE010            . GO CHECK THE NEXT MACRO   WC
)@@G@@@H@@@YMDE020    JZ        A4,MDE040         . IF NOT IN XQT LIST, DON'T WD
)@@G@@POP ANY     @E@@@Y          SA        A4,METMP          . SAVE CURRENT IWE
)@@G@@NDEX  @E@@@Y          CALL      M$XQTPOPSTAK      . "RETURN" A MACRO    WF
)@@G@@@F@@@Y          JNZ       A5,MDE040         . IF ERROR, GO FINISH UP    WG
)@@G@@@D@@@Y          LA        A4,METMP          . RESTORE COUNT @F@@@Y      WH
)@@G@@    JGD       A4,MDE020         . COUNT AND TRY MORE MAYBE  @E@@@YMDE040WI
)@@G@@    SA        A5,METMP          . SAVE ERROR OR 0     @G@Z@Y          $IWJ
)@@G@@F       EDPROCS           . ONLY IF SUPPORTING ED PROCS     @E@@@Y      WK
)@@G@@    LA        A2,MEPTR          . RESTORE DEFN PTR    @G@@@Y          LAWL
)@@G@@        A0,MDLTL,A2       . GET LABEL TABLE LINK (IF ANY)   @E@@@Y      WM
)@@G@@    JZ        A0,MDE050         . SKIP OUT IF NO TABLE@G@@@Y          CAWN
)@@G@@LL      M$ERSMST          . ERASE THE MACRO SYMBOL TABLE    @D@@@Y      WO
)@@G@@    TNZ       METMP             . PREVIOUS ERROR@G@@@Y          SA      WP
)@@G@@  A5,METMP          . NO, POST NEW ERROR (IF ANY)     @ @Z@Y          $EWQ
)@@G@@NDF     EDPROCS   @F@-@YMDE050    PREL      MEPTR             . GET RID WR
)@@G@@OF DEFN (FINALLY) @F@@@-MDE050    LA        A0,MEPTR          . GET RID WS
)@@G@@OF DEFN (FINALLY) @#@@@-          M$PREL  @E@@@Y          TZ        METMWT
)@@G@@P             . PREVIOUS ERROR?     @F@@@Y          LA        A5,METMP  WU
)@@G@@        . YES, MAKE IT 'THE' ERROR  @C@@@YMDE999    RETURN              WV
)@@G@@        . DONE    @[@@@Y/.    @D@@@Y. M$ERSMST - ROUTINE TO ERASE A MACRWW
)@@G@@O SYMBOL TABLE.   @E@@@Z. M$ERSDST - ROUTINE TO ERASE A DICTIONARY SYMBOWX
)@@G@@L TABLE.    @[@@@Y.     @^@Z@Y.  A0 = SYMBOL TABLE PTR@C@@@Z.  A0 = SYMBWY
)@@G@@OL TABLE PTR/DICTIONARY ENTRY PTR   @^@@@Y.  LMJ  X11,M$ERSMST    @^@@@YWZ
)@@G@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0. @[@@@Y.     @F@@@ZM$ERSMST* LA,U      A1,,A0    XA
)@@G@@        . TABLE PTR IS = TO PTR     @ @@@Z          J         EMSTRTN   XB
)@@G@@@D@@@ZM$ERSDST* LA,U      A1,DLMSTP,A0      . TABLE PTR     @#@Z@YM$ERSMXC
)@@G@@ST* ROUTINE @#@)@ZEMSTRTN   ROUTINE @^@@@)EMSTRTN   SUBROUTINE    @D@Z@YXD
)@@G@@EMSTPTR   LOCAL                       . TABLE POINTER @D@@@ZEMSTPTR   LOXE
)@@G@@CAL                       . ENTRY POINTER @E@@@ZEMSTTBL   LOCAL         XF
)@@G@@              . SYMBOL TABLE POINTER@D@@@YEMSTNA    LOCAL               XG
)@@G@@        . NODE ADDRESS  @D@@@YEMSTERR   LOCAL                       . ERXH
)@@G@@ROR PCW OR 0@E@Z@Y          SA        A0,EMSTPTR        . SAVE TABLE POIXI
)@@G@@NTER  @F@@@Z          DS        A0,EMSTPTR        . SAVE ENTRY, TABLE INXJ
)@@G@@DEXES @E@@@Y          SZ        EMSTERR           . CLEAR ERROR PCW     XK
)@@G@@@F@@@YEMST010   LA,U      A1,1              . DELETE ONE NODE AT A TIME XL
)@@G@@@E@Z@Y          LA        A0,EMSTPTR        . GET TABLE POINTER   @E@@@ZXM
)@@G@@          LA        A0,EMSTTBL        . GET TABLE POINTER   @D@@@Y      XN
)@@G@@    AVLDR                       . DELETE BY RANK@E@@@Y          JZ      XO
)@@G@@  A2,EMST020        . SKIP OUT WHEN DONE  @E@@@Y          LA        A0,MXP
)@@G@@VDM,A2        . = MODE OF VARIABLE  @E@@@Y          LSSL      A0,30     XQ
)@@G@@        . ALIGN FOR DESCRIPTOR@E@@@Y          LA        A1,MVDAW,A2     XR
)@@G@@  . GET DATA ACCESS WORD@E@@@Y          SA        A2,EMSTNA         . SAXS
)@@G@@VE NODE ADDRESS   @F@@@Y          CALL      M$VDERS           . ERASE A XT
)@@G@@VALUE DESCRIPTOR  @E@@@Y          TNZ       EMSTERR           . ANY PREVXU
)@@G@@IOUS ERROR? @F@@@Y          SA        A5,EMSTERR        . NO, POST ERRORXV
)@@G@@ FLAG IF ANY@F@-@Y          PREL      EMSTNA            . RELEASE THE NOXW
)@@G@@DE SPACE NOW@F@@@-          LA        A0,EMSTNA         . RELEASE THE NOXX
)@@G@@DE SPACE NOW@#@@@-          M$PREL  @E@@@Y          TNZ       EMSTERR   XY
)@@G@@        . ANY PREVIOUS ERROR  @E@@@Y          SA        A5,EMSTERR      XZ
)@@G@@  . NO, POST ANY ERRORS @E@@@Y          J         EMST010           . DOYA
)@@G@@ REST OF TABLE    @F@Z@YEMST020   PREL      EMSTPTR           . RELEASE YB
)@@G@@THE TABLE ITSELF  @F@-@ZEMST020   PREL      EMSTPTR           . RELEASE YC
)@@G@@THE ENTRY ITSELF  @F@@@-EMST020   LA        A0,EMSTPTR        . RELEASE YD
)@@G@@THE ENTRY ITSELF  @#@@@-          M$PREL  @E@@@Y          TZ        EMSTYE
)@@G@@ERR           . ANY PREVIOUS ERRORS @D@@@Y          LA        A5,EMSTERRYF
)@@G@@        . YES, GET IT   @C@@@Y          RETURN                      . ALYG
)@@G@@L DONE@[@@@Z/.    @F@@@Z. M$COMFIND - ROUTINE TO FIND A COMMAND IN THE CYH
)@@G@@OMMAND TABLE.     @[@@@Z.     @^@@@Z.  A0,A1 = COMMAND NAME @^@@@Z.  LMJYI
)@@G@@  X11,M$COMFIND   @^@@@Z.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @#@@@Z.  A4 = 1 (FOUND) YJ
)@@G@@@ @@@Z.    A0 (A1) = ROUTINE CODE   @ @@@Z.    A2 = ROUTINE ADDRESS     YK
)@@G@@@^@@@Z.  A4 = 0 (NO FIND)     @ @@@Z.    A0,A1 = COMMAND NAME     @[@@@ZYL
)@@G@@.     @#@)@ZM$COMFIND* ROUTINE@^@@@)M$COMFIND* SUBROUTINE   @^@@@ZCOMNAMYM
)@@G@@E   LOCAL     2   @F@@@Z          DS        A0,COMNAME        . SAVE THEYN
)@@G@@ COMMAND NAME     @E@@@Z          LA,U      A4,7              . COUNT CHYO
)@@G@@ARS IN A0   @E@@@Z          LA,U      A5,7              . COUNT CHARS INYP
)@@G@@ A1   @F@@@ZCOM010    AND,U     A1,077            . GET LAST CHAR IN COMYQ
)@@G@@MAND  @E@@@Z          DSC       A0,6              . SLIDE IT AROUND     YR
)@@G@@@F@@@Z          TZ        A5                . ALL CHARS IN A1 GONE?     YS
)@@G@@@E@@@Z          AN,U      A5,1              . NO, COUNT THIS CHAR @F@@@ZYT
)@@G@@          TNZ       A5                . ALL CHARS IN A1 GONE?     @G@@@ZYU
)@@G@@          AN,U      A4,1              . YES, COUNT DOWN CHARS IN A0     YV
)@@G@@@E@@@Z          TE,U      A4,1              . ONLY 1 CHAR LEFT?   @G@@@ZYW
)@@G@@          TE,U      A2,' '            . NO, IS THIS CHAR NON-BLANK?     YX
)@@G@@@E@@@Z          J         $+2               . YES, STOP COUNTING  @I@@@ZYY
)@@G@@          J         COM010            . NO, KEEP LOOPING & SUBTRACTING FYZ
)@@G@@OR BLANK    @E@@@Z          DL        A0,COMNAME        . RESTORE COMMANZA
)@@G@@D NAME@H@@@Z          DL        A2,A4             . A2 = CHARS IN A0, A3ZB
)@@G@@ = CHARS IN A1    @G@@@Z          AU        A3,A2             . A4 = TOTZC
)@@G@@AL # OF CHAR IN COMMAND @[@@@Z.     @G@@@Z. NOW SEARCH THE CONFIGURED COZD
)@@G@@MMAND TABLE.  IF A COMMAND IS FOUND WITH  @H@@@Z. AN ABBREVIATION, MAKE ZE
)@@G@@SURE THAT IT MAY BE FOUND BY SUCH AN ABBREVIATION     @C@@@Z. THAT IS, IZF
)@@G@@F THE ABBREVIATION IS SUFFICIENT.   @[@@@Z.     @F@@@ZCOM020    TMSE    ZG
)@@G@@  A0,CTNAME,X11 CTSIZE,M$COMTABLE M$COMMSK,A2   @D@@@Z          J       ZH
)@@G@@  COM990            . NOT FOUND     @I@@@Z          JG        A4,CTABRL,ZI
)@@G@@X11 COM020 . KEEP SEARCHING IF INSUFFICIENT ABBR.     @G@@@Z          JZZJ
)@@G@@        A3,COM030         . FOUND IF NO MORE CHARS TO MATCH @C@@@Z      ZK
)@@G@@    LA        A0,M$COMMSK,A3    . GET MASK@D@@@Z          LA        A4,AZL
)@@G@@0             . DUPLICATE IT  @G@@@Z          AND       A0,A1           ZM
)@@G@@  . MASK OUT SECOND WORD OF COMMAND @H@@@Z          AND       A4,CTNAME+ZN
)@@G@@1,X11   . MASK OUT SECOND WORD OF TEST COMMAND  @D@@@Z          JE      ZO
)@@G@@  A1,A5 COM030      . SKIP IF FOUND @E@@@Z          DL        A0,COMNAMEZP
)@@G@@        . RELOAD COMMAND NAME @F@@@Z          AU        A3,A2           ZQ
)@@G@@  . RECOMPUTE TOTAL LENGTH    @E@@@Z          J         COM020          ZR
)@@G@@  . TRY NEXT COMMAND    @[@Z@Y.     @]@@@Z          . @B@@@Z          . ZS
)@@G@@        FOUND THE COMMAND     @]@@@Z          . @F@@@ZCOM030    LA      ZT
)@@G@@  A2,CTADDR,X11     . GET THE ROUTINE ADDRESS   @D@@@Z          LA      ZU
)@@G@@  A5,PCL('UNIMPLEMENTED COMMAND.')  @C@@@Z          JZ        A2,COM999 ZV
)@@G@@        . ERROR   @F@@@Z          LA        A0,CTCODL,X11     . GET THE ZW
)@@G@@CODE*/6+ABBR. LEN.@G@@@Z          SSL       A0,6              . GET RID ZX
)@@G@@OF ABBREVIATION LENGTH  @F@@@Z          LA        A1,A0             . DUZY
)@@G@@PLICATE FOR OLD ROUTINES@F@@@Z          DL        A4,M$DONE         . SEZZ
)@@G@@T FOUND, NO ERROR FLAGS @F@@@+          L         A3,X11            . COAA
)@@G@@PY POINTER TO THE ENTRY @ @@@Z          J         COM999    @E@@@ZCOM990AB
)@@G@@    DSL       A4,72             . NO FIND, NO ERRORS  @#@@@ZCOM999    REAC
)@@G@@TURN  @[@@@Z.     @B@@@Z. TABLE OF MASKS FOR COMMAND SEARCH EQUAL @[@@@ZAD
)@@G@@.     @B@@@Z          LITS                        .   @F@@@ZM$COMMSK* EQAE
)@@G@@U       $-1               . EXTERNALIZE THIS TABLE    @C@@@Z          + AF
)@@G@@        0770000000000     . ONE CHAR@C@@@Z          +         0777700000AG
)@@G@@000     . TWO CHAR@D@@@Z          +         0777777000000     . THREE CHAH
)@@G@@AR    @D@@@Z          +         0777777770000     . FOUR CHAR     @D@@@ZAI
)@@G@@          +         0777777777700     . FIVE CHAR     @C@@@Z          + AJ
)@@G@@        0777777777777     . SIX CHAR+@@@@[@G@Z@Y^@)^@)^@)^@)^@) S)^@)^@)AK
)@@G@@^@)^@)A@7A87A87A87A87A87A8)^@)^@) 0)ETDF@)CTCCDM+@@@@@@E@@@Z          + AL
)@@G@@        0777777777777     . SIX CHAR (AND MORE) @#@@@Z          INSTRS  AM
)@@G@@@]@@@Z          . @#@@@Y          END     _@@@@@C8@@@@C8@@@@C8@@@@C8@@@@AN

)@@G@@P         PROC      1,2 @#@@@RPUSH*     NAME    @C@@@R DO STKPTR=0 , $DIXF

)@@G@@CK; INITIALIZE THE STACK CONTROL WORD AND POINTER.    @[@@@R.     @E@@@RXM
)@@G@@.         STKINIT   <ERROR> <STKSIZE>,<STKINC> <STKPTR>     @[@@@R.     XN
)@@G@@@H@@@R. ALL FIELDS ARE OPTIONAL, AND THE DEFINITIONS ABOVE WILL SUPPLY AXO
)@@G@@S DEFAULTS. @[@@@R.     @^@@@RP         PROC      *3  @#@@@RSTKINIT*  NAXP
)@@G@@ME    @F@@@R DO P>3 ,STKPTR* EQU P(3,1)           . REDEFINE STACK POINTXQ
)@@G@@ER    @^@@@R          $IF       P>2 @F@@@R DO P(2)>1 ,STKINC* EQU P(2,2)XR
)@@G@@        . REDEFINE STACK INCREMENT  @E@@@RSTKSIZ*   EQU       P(2,1)    XS
)@@G@@        . REDEFINE STACK SIZE @#@@@R          $ENDF   @H@@@R          LAXT

)@@G@@,1)   @#@@@R          END     @[@@@R.     @H@@@R. RELEASE THE CURRENT STXW
)@@G@@ACK, AND RESTORE THE PREVIOUS STACK CONTROL WORD.     @[@@@R.     @ @@@RXX
)@@G@@.         STKTERM   <ERROR>   @[@@@R.     @^@@@RP         PROC      *1  XY

)@@G@@ DO P>1 , JNZ       A5,AF(P(1),1)   @#@@@R          END     @[@@@R/.    YA
)@@G@@@B@@@R. DEFINE THE SUBROUTINE STACKING PROCS    @[@@@R.     @D@@@R. SPINYB
)@@G@@IT - INITIALIZE THE SUBROUTINE STACK POINTER    @[@@@R.     @F@@@R. THE YC
)@@G@@SUBROUINE STACK POINTER IS (RE)INITIALIZED FROM THE CURRENT @F@@@R. SUBRYD
)@@G@@OUTINE STACK CONTROL WORD, WHICH, OF COURSE, MUST HAVE BEEN @ @@@R. PREVYE
)@@G@@IOUSLY INITIALIZED.     @[@@@R.     @^@@@RSPINIT*   PROC      0,1 @F@@@RYF
)@@G@@          LX        SSTKPTR,SSTKTOP   . LOAD THE STACK TOP ADDRESS@#@@@RYG
)@@G@@          END     @[@@@R.     @G@@@R. ROUTINE - PUSH THE STACK POINTER FYH
)@@G@@OR A RECURSIVE ROUTINE ENTRANCE.    @[@@@R.     @H@@@R. SUBROUTINE - SAVYI
)@@G@@E THE RETURN ADDRESS FOR A NON-RECURSIVE ROUTINE ENTRANCE.  @[@@@R.     YJ
)@@G@@@A@@@R.         (SUB)ROUTINE  <REG-LIST>  @[@@@R.     @E@@@RR$$PF     EQYK
)@@G@@U       0                 . ROUTINE PASS FLAG   @E@@@RR$$RT     EQU     YL
)@@G@@  $NODE             . ROUTINE TREE OF INFO@[@@@R.     @^@@@RP         PRYM
)@@G@@OC      *1  @E@@@RROUTINE*  NAME      1                 . RECURSIVE ROUTYN
)@@G@@INE   @F@@@RSUBROUTINE* NAME    0                 . NON-RECURSIVE ROUTINYO
)@@G@@E     @E@@@RRF        EQU       P(0,0)            . SET RECURSIVE FLAG  YP
)@@G@@@F@@@R          $IF       R$$PF=$LP         . FIRST TIME THIS PASS?     YQ
)@@G@@@D@@@RR$$PF*    EQU       \R$$PF            . FLIP FLAG     @F@@@RR$$RC*YR
)@@G@@    EQU       0                 . RESET ROUTINE COUNTER     @#@@@R      YS
)@@G@@    $ENDF   @F@@@RR$$RC*    EQU       R$$RC+1           . INCREMENT ROUTYT
)@@G@@INE COUNTER @F@@@RR$$LC*    EQU       0                 . SET LOCALS COUYU
)@@G@@NTER TO ZERO@G@@@RR$$LI*    EQU       0                 . SET LOCALS INCYV
)@@G@@REMENT TO ZERO    @D@@@R          $IF       \$LP              . IF FIRSTYW
)@@G@@ PASS @F@@@RRL        EQU       $NODE             . DEFAULT REGISTER LISYX
)@@G@@T     @F@@@RI         REPEAT    P(1)              . SCAN FOR REGS TO SAVYY
)@@G@@E     @E@@@RR(P(1,I)) EQU       0                 . SORT THE REGISTERS  YZ
)@@G@@@#@@@R          ENDR    @H@@@R DO \RF ,R(X11) EQU 0                 . IFZA
)@@G@@ 'SUBROUTINE', ALWAYS INCLUDE X11   @F@@@RI DO R ,RL(I) EQU $NS(R,I)    ZB
)@@G@@        . COMPRESS THE REGISTER LIST@F@@@RRSA       EQU       RF->0!$($LZC
)@@G@@CN=0->2!0) . REGISTER SAVE AREA OR 0@E@@@RR$$RT(R$$RC)* EQU   $L1(RF,RSAZD
)@@G@@,RL)    . SAVE INFO ON ROUTINE@C@@@R          $ELSE                     ZE
)@@G@@  . PASS TWO@G@@@RRSA       EQU       R$$RT(R$$RC,2)    . RECOVER REGISTZF
)@@G@@ER SAVE AREA OR 0 @E@@@RRL        EQU       R$$RT(R$$RC,3)    . RECOVER ZG
)@@G@@REG LIST    @B@@@R          $ENDF                       .   @E@@@R      ZH
)@@G@@    $IF       RF                . RECURSIVE ROUTINE?  @G@@@R          ROZI
)@@G@@UTINEPUSH R$$RT(R$$RC,2)+R$$RT(R$$RC,3) . PUSH A NEW FRAME  +@@@@[@I@R@QZJ
)@@G@@^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)ELJE(ODDIC(KE(ND@)ETAES)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@) 0)E[PETC^[[^[IZK
)@@G@@C(R^[AEL[D( +@@@@@@G@@@RRSA       EQUF      1,SSTKPTR         . POST CORZL
)@@G@@RECT REGISTER SAVE AREA @#@@@R          $ENDF   @F@@@RI         EQU     ZM
)@@G@@  1                 . NOW SAVE THE REGISTERS    @B@@@R          REPEAT  ZN
)@@G@@                    .   @F@@@R          I>RL->ENDI                   . QZO
)@@G@@UIT IF PAST END OF LIST @F@@@RF         EQU       A0<=RL(I)<=A15->I<RL->ZP
)@@G@@RL(I)+1=RL(I+1)!0!0     @F@@@R          F->DS!S   RL(I),RSA+I-1     . SAZQ
)@@G@@VE A REGISTER OR TWO    @F@@@RI         EQU       I+1+F             . INZR
)@@G@@CREMENT TO NEXT REG     @#@@@R          ENDR    @#@@@R          RF->END ZS
)@@G@@@F@@@R$($LCN=0->2!0) RES  RL                . RESERVE SPACE FOR REGS    ZT
)@@G@@@F@@@R$($ILCN)                              . BACK TO REGULAR STUFF     ZU
)@@G@@@#@@@R          END     @[@@@R/.    @D@@@R. LOCAL - PROC TO DEFINE LOCALZV
)@@G@@ STORAGE FOR ROUTINES.  @[@@@R.     @ @@@R. <LABEL>  LOCAL    <# WORDS> ZW
)@@G@@@[@@@R.     @G@@@R. IF THE LOCAL IS DEFINED IN A RECURSIVE ROUTINE, IT IZX
)@@G@@S BASED ON THE    @G@@@R. SUBROUTINE STACK; IF DEFINED IN A NON-RECURSIVZY
)@@G@@E SUBROUTINE, IT IS     @G@@@R. ALLOCATED UNDER LOCATION COUNTER ZERO (OZZ
)@@G@@R TWO IF CURRENTLY UNDER 0).  @B@@@R. LOCAL STORAGE MAY NOT BE INITIALIZAA

)@@G@@@H@@@RR$$LC*    EQU       R$$LC+R$$LI       . ACCUMULATE THE PREVIOUS INAC
)@@G@@CREMENT     @E@@@RR$$LI*    EQU       P>1->P(1,1)!1     . DEFAULT IS ONEAD
)@@G@@ WORD +@@@@[@J@R@Q^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)DDA^@)^@)^@)^@)EK=^-ME)*EK=^-MCS?AC(^@)AE
)@@G@@^@) 0)EL CTPELNDDQC*)ELJE(ODDIC*)^@)+@@@@@@E@@@R          IF        R$$RAF
)@@G@@T(R$$RC,1)    . RECURSIVE ROUTINE   @F@@@RR$$RT(R$$RC,2)* EQU R$$LC+R$$LAG
)@@G@@I       . POST CURRENT ALLOCATION   @G@@@R          $LF(1)=0->END       AH
)@@G@@        . IF NO LABEL, NO NEED TO DO THIS @H@@@RA         EQUF      R$$LAI
)@@G@@C+1+R$$RT(R$$RC,3),SSTKPTR . DEFINE OFFSET ON STACK   @E@@@R*         EQAJ
)@@G@@UF      A                 . DEFINE THE LABEL    @E@@@R          DISPLAY AK
)@@G@@  A                 . SHOW THE OFFSET     @#@@@R          1->END  @#@@@RAL
)@@G@@          ENDF    @#@@@R$($LCN=0->2!0)    @F@@@R*         $RES      R$$LAM
)@@G@@I             . SAVE SPACE FOR THE LOCAL  @]@@@R$($ILCN)    @#@@@R      AN
)@@G@@    END     @[@@@R.     @C@@@R. STATIC - DEFINE STATICALLY ALLOCATED VARAO
)@@G@@IABLES@[@@@R.     @D@@@R. <LABEL>  STATIC   <# WORDS> <INITIALIZATION> .AP
)@@G@@..    @[@@@R.     @^@@@RP         PROC      *80 @#@@@RSTATIC*   NAME    AQ
)@@G@@@#@@@R$($LCN=0->2!0)    @E@@@R*         EQUF      $                 . DEAR
)@@G@@FINE ANY LABEL    @F@@@RR         EQU       P>1->P(1,1)!1     . DEFAULT AS
)@@G@@RES IS 1 WORD     @F@@@RL         EQU       $                 . CAPTURE AT
)@@G@@CURRENT LC VALUE  @E@@@RI         REPEAT    2,P-1             . PROCESS AU
)@@G@@ALL FIELDS  @F@@@RV         EQU       'P(I,1)'          . INITIAL VALUE AV
)@@G@@OF A FIELD  @F@@@RJ         DO 2,P(I) ,V EQU V:',P(I,':$CD(J):')' . ADD AW
)@@G@@ON SUBFIELDS@E@@@R          GEN       [V]               . GENERATE THE FAX
)@@G@@IELD  @D@@@R          ENDR                        . DO MORE FIELDS@F@@@RAY
)@@G@@          RES       R-($-L)           . RESERVE ANY LEFT-OVERS    @E@@@RAZ
)@@G@@$($ILCN)                              . RETURN TO REGULAR LC@#@@@R      BA
)@@G@@    END     @[@@@R/.    @F@@@R. RETURN - RELOAD SAVE REGISTERS, POP STACBB
)@@G@@K IF 'ROUTINE', RETURN. @[@@@R.     @#@@@R.         RETURN  @[@@@R.     BC
)@@G@@@F@@@R. IF MATCHED BY A 'RETURN', THIS PROC GENERATES CODE TO RELOAD ANYBD
)@@G@@@G@@@R. SAVED REGISTERS, FOLLOWED WITH A TRANSFER TO THE POSTAMBLE ROUTIBE
)@@G@@NE    @F@@@R. WHICH POPS THE STACK FRAME AND RETURNS TO THE PREVIOUS CALBF
)@@G@@LER.  @F@@@R. IF MATCHED BY A 'SUBROUTINE', THE SAVED REGISTERS (AT LEASBG
)@@G@@T X11)@C@@@R. ARE RESTORED, AND A SIMPLE RETURN IS MADE.    @[@@@R.     BH
)@@G@@@^@@@RP         PROC      *0  @#@@@RRETURN*   NAME    @E@@@RT         EQBI
)@@G@@U       R$$RT(R$$RC)      . GET THE ROUTINE TREE@G@@@RSRA       EQUF    BJ
)@@G@@  [T(1)->'1,SSTKPTR'!'T(2)'] . SET SAVED REG AREA     @D@@@RRL        EQBK
)@@G@@U       T(3)              . REGISTER LIST @^@@@RI         EQU       1   BL
)@@G@@@#@@@R          REPEAT  @F@@@R          I>RL->ENDI                  . IFBM
)@@G@@ NO MORE REGS, EXIT     @F@@@RF         EQU       A0<=RL(I)<=A15->I<RL->BN
)@@G@@RL(I)+1=RL(I+1)!0!0     @F@@@R          F->DL!L   RL(I),SRA+I-1     . REBO
)@@G@@COVER SAVED REGISTERS   @E@@@RI         EQU       I+1+F             . INBP
)@@G@@CREMENT INDEX     @#@@@R          ENDR    @G@@@R          T(1)->ROUTINEPBQ
)@@G@@OP            . IF RECURSIVE, POP THE ROUTINE   @E@@@R          J       BR
)@@G@@  0,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    @#@@@R          END     @[@@@RBS
)@@G@@.     @F@@@R. ROUTINEPUSH - PROC TO GENERATE THE RECURSIVE ROUTINE PREAMBT
)@@G@@BLE.  @[@@@R.     @B@@@R.         ROUTINEPUSH <STACKFRAMESIZE>    @[@@@RBU
)@@G@@.     @[@@@R.     @G@@@R. THIS CODE IS IN A PROC TO ALLOW FOR THE FUTUREBV
)@@G@@ POSSIBILITY OF PREAMBLE@G@@@R. OPTIMIZATION, WITHOUT HAVING TO MODIFY EBW
)@@G@@LEMENTS WHICH CONTAIN CODE    @F@@@R. PERFORMING THIS SERVICE; MERELY REBX
)@@G@@ASSEMBLING THESE ELEMENTS WILL@#@@@R. BE SUFFICIENT.  @[@@@R.     @E@@@RBY
)@@G@@P         PROC      1,5               . STACK FRAME SIZE    @#@@@RROUTINBZ
)@@G@@EPUSH* NAME @ @@@RSFS       EQU       P(1,1)    @G@@@R          ANX,U   CA

)@@G@@EM      SSTKPTR,SSTKBOT   . OVERFLOW?     @D@@@R          SLJ       M$STCC

)@@G@@ST FRAME SIZE, RETURN ADDRESS @#@@@R          END     @[@@@R.     @D@@@RCF
)@@G@@. ROUTINEPOP - PROC TO GENERATE THE POSTAMBLE CODE    @[@@@R.     @G@@@RCG
)@@G@@. THIS CODE IS IN A PROC TO ALLOW FOR THE POSSIBIBILTY THAT, IN THE     CH
)@@G@@@G@@@R. FUTURE, THE POSTAMBLE CODE MAY BE OPTIMIZED. IN WHICH CASE, INSTCI
)@@G@@EAD   @H@@@R. OF HAVING TO LOCATE THOSE PLACES THAT PERFORM THE POSTAMBLCJ
)@@G@@E, AND CHANGE     @F@@@R. THE CODE, IT WILL BE POSSIBLE TO MERELY REASSECK

)@@G@@@#@@@R          END     @[@@@R/.    @C@@@R. PIKLEFT - SETUP ARGUMENT FETCO

)@@G@@@F@@@R. CONVRTN - PROC TO GENERATE CODE TO CALCULATE AND RETURN THE     EC
)@@G@@@G@@@R.           CONVERSION ROUTINE ADDRESS FROM A GIVEN MODE TO ANOTHEED
)@@G@@R     @#@@@R.           MODE. @[@@@R.     @D@@@R.         CONVRTN <REG>,EE
)@@G@@<TO-MODE>,<FROM-MODE> <ERROR> @[@@@R.     @F@@@R. IF <FROM-MODE> OMITTEDEF
)@@G@@, <REG> IS ASSUMED TO ALREADY CONTAIN IT. @[@@@R.     @^@@@RP         PREG
)@@G@@OC      *2  @#@@@RCONVRTN*  NAME    @D@@@RR         EQU       P(1,1)    EH
)@@G@@        . THE WORK REG  @D@@@R DO P(1)>2 , LA     R,AF(P(1),3,1)    . GEEI
)@@G@@T FROM-MODE @F@@@R          LSSL      R,2               . MULTIPLY 'FROMEJ

)@@G@@NETRUCTION  @E@@@R          LA        A5,M$CONVERR      . GET NO-CAN-DO EM

)@@G@@@#@@@R          END     @B@@@R. CONVINT - CONVERT A VALUE TO INTEGER.   EO
)@@G@@@C@@@R. CONVASC - CONVERT A VALUE TO AN ASCII STRING. @[@@@R.     @B@@@REP

)@@G@@MODE - ROUTINE TO CONVERT A VALUE TO A GIVEN MODE.    @[@@@R.     @C@@@REW
)@@G@@.         CONVMODE  <ERROR> <VD-ADDR> <MODE>    @[@@@R.     @^@@@RP     EX
)@@G@@    PROC      *3  @#@@@RCONVMODE* NAME    @D@@@R DO P>3 , LA        A1,AEY
)@@G@@F(P(3),*1)    . GET THE MODE  @E@@@R DO P>2 , LA        A0,AF(P(2),*1)  EZ

)@@G@@    END     @[@@@R/.    @D@@@R. ACCEPTM - PROC TO GENERATE A MODE ACCEPTFC
)@@G@@OR TABLE.   @D@@@R. REJECTM - PROC TO GENERATE A MODE REJECTOR TABLE.   FD
)@@G@@@[@@@R.     @ @@@R.  LMJ  <TABLE>,<MODE-INDEX>  @#@@@R.  <REJECTED>     FE
)@@G@@@#@@@R.  <ACCEPTED>     @[@@@R.     @B@@@R. THE <TABLE> IS GENERATED AS FF
)@@G@@FOLLOWS:    @[@@@R.     @E@@@R.         ACCEPTM,<MAX>,<MIN>  <MODE1> <MOFG
)@@G@@DE2> <MODE3> ...  @[@@@R.     @E@@@R.         REJECTM,<MAX>,<MIN>  <MODEFH
)@@G@@1> <MODE2> <MODE3> ...  @[@@@R.     @H@@@R. IF <MAX> OR <MIN> ARE OMITTEFI
)@@G@@D, THEN "MODNUL" AND "MODSIN" ARE ASSUMED BY    @^@@@R. DEFAULT, RESPECTFJ
)@@G@@IVELY.@[@@@R.     @^@@@RP         PROC      *16 @^@@@RACCEPTM*  NAME    FK
)@@G@@  1   @^@@@RREJECTM*  NAME      0   @ @@@RYES       EQU       P(0,0)    FL
)@@G@@@^@@@RNO        EQU       \YES@B@@@RMAX       EQU       P(0)>1->P(0,1)!MFM
)@@G@@$MNUL @B@@@RMIN       EQU       P(0)>2->P(0,2)!M$MSIN @B@@@RI         DOFN
)@@G@@ MIN,MAX ,T(I) $EQUF NO,X11   @F@@@RI         DO P-1 ,T(P(I,1)) $EQUF [PFO
)@@G@@(I)>1->'AF(P(I),2)'!'YES,X11']@ @@@RI         DO MIN,MAX , J T(I) @#@@@RFP
)@@G@@          END     @[@@@R.     @A@@@R. T<TYPE>  <R>[,<MODE>] [<ADDR>]    FQ
)@@G@@@[@@@R.     @G@@@R. SKIP NI IF <R> CONTAINS A MODE ACCEPTED BY <TYPE>; GFR
)@@G@@ENERATE A 'JUMP'  @#@@@R. IF <ADDR> GIVEN.@[@@@R.     @^@@@RP         PRFS
)@@G@@OC      *2  @ @@@RTDAT*     NAME      'M$QDAT'  @ @@@RTNOD*     NAME    FT

)@@G@@2 , J         AF(P(2),1)@#@@@R          END     @^@@@RP         PROC    FY

)@@G@@  P(0,0)(1)         . TEST INSTRUCTION    @D@@@RTV        EQU       P(0,GC

)@@G@@    END     @[@@@R/.    @E@@@R. ARGCHK - PROC TO GENERATE CALLING SEQUENGF
)@@G@@CE FOR M$ARGCHECK.@[@@@R.     @F@@@R.         ARGCHK    <ERROR> <LOCALS-GG
)@@G@@BASE> <MASKADDR> <MAX. # ARGS>@[@@@R.     @]@@@R. GENERATES:@[@@@R.     GH

)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@L/         M$DEF   @[@@@L.     @F@@@L. THIS ROUTINE IS KY
)@@G@@CALLED TO OPEN A 'CALLED' MACRO FOR EXECUTION.  @H@@@L. THE MACRO MUST BKZ
)@@G@@E ALREADY DEFINED AND COMPILED.  A1 IS ASSUMED TO POINT     @F@@@L. TO TLA
)@@G@@HE MACRO DEFINITION ENTRY, AND ITS INCREMENT SHOULD BE SET  @E@@@L. TO TLB
)@@G@@HE VALUE TO BE SET INTO MXFB.  A0 SHOULD BE SET TO THE@D@@@L. ARGUMENT PLC
)@@G@@OINTERS, IT WILL BE PLACED IN MXARGS.     @[@@@L.     @B@@@LM$XQTCALL*  LD
)@@G@@                          .   @B@@@L          $DO $PAR(4)='SNOOPY' , SLJLE
)@@G@@ TON$ @#@M@L          ROUTINE @^@@@M          SUBROUTINE    @E@@@L      LF
)@@G@@    DS        A0,CCMACR         . SAVE MACRO ADDRESS  @E@@@L          LALG
)@@G@@        A0,M$MXQTSIZE     . GET EXECUTION BUFFER@D@@@L          TLE,U   LH

)@@G@@    L,U       R1,11             . INITIALIZE IT @B@M@L          L       LN
)@@G@@  A2,(1,M$OUTPACKET) .  @B@M@L          L,U       A0,0,A1           .   LO
)@@G@@@B@M@L          LXI,U     A1,1              .   @B@M@L          BT      LP
)@@G@@  A1,0,*A2          .   @F@@@L          DL        A1,CCMACR         . SELQ
)@@G@@T LINK TO DEFINE ENTRY  @E@@@L          S         A2,MXMDL,A0       . SELR
)@@G@@T LINK TO DEF ITEM@F@@@L          S         A1,MXARGS,A0      . SET ARGULS
)@@G@@MENTS TO MACRO    @F@N@L          LA        A1,M$OBC          . GET CURRLT
)@@G@@ENT BRACKET DEFNS @B@N@L          LA        A3,M$CBC          .   @F@N@LLU

)@@G@@    LA,U      A3,DEFCSC         .   @[@@@LCAL010@#@@@L          $ENDF   MD

)@@G@@@E@@@L. THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED TO SEARCH THE COMMAND NAME TABLE.  @D@@@LPB
)@@G@@. IT IS CALLED WITH A0-A1 CONTAINING THE COMMAND NAME @A@@@L. AND A2 = CPC
)@@G@@OMMAND CHARACTER LENGTH @]@@@L. ON RETURN @ @@@L.   A5 = ERROR MESSAGE PPD

)@@G@@OF BUFFERS TO RELEASE   @[@@@L/.    @G@@@L          FIDEF$    M$ELT$    VL
)@@G@@        . GET ELT$ EQUFS ON OUR OWN PACKET@[@@@L.     @G@@@L. THIS ROUTIVM
)@@G@@NE IS CALLED TO SEARCH FOR AN UNDEFINED MACRO.  IT SEARCHES @G@@@L. THE VN

)@@G@@AT ROUTINE DETERMINES WHETHER OR NOT TO SEARCH EACH FILE.   @F@@@O.   IFWJ
)@@G@@ IT IS OK TO SEARCH, THE ROUTINE RETURNS TO 1,X11 ELSE 0,X11@[@@@O.     WK
)@@G@@@F@@@O          LMJ       X11,FILE$OK       . SHOULD WE USE THIS ONE?   WL
)@@G@@@E@@@O          J         SUM010            . NOPE, TRY NEXT ONE  @[@@@LWM
)@@G@@.     @D@@@L          ON        0                 . DEBUG CODE    @D@@@LWN
)@@G@@          AH        A0,(0102,4)       . PRINT FILENAME@B@@@L          ERWO
)@@G@@        PRINT$            .   @D@@@L          ANH       A0,(0102,4)     WP
)@@G@@  . PRINT FILENAME@B@@@L          OFF       0                 .   @[@@@LWQ
)@@G@@.     @E@@@L          LMJ       X11,M$FILESEARCH  . SEARCH MACRO FILE   WR
)@@G@@@F@@@L          JNZ       A5,SUM999         . IF ERROR RETURN NOFIND    WS
)@@G@@@E@@@L          JZ        A4,SUM010         . IF NOT FOUND LOOP   @E@@@LWT
)@@G@@          J         SUM999            . ELSE RETURN FOUND   @[@@@L.     WU
)@@G@@@C@@@L. SPECIFIC FILE NAME GIVEN - USE ELT$ PACKET.   @[@@@L.     @]@@@LWV
)@@G@@SUM020    . @E@@@L          L,U       A0,ELT$           . ELSE GET PACKEWW
)@@G@@T     @E@@@L          LMJ       X11,M$FILESEARCH  . AND SEARCH FILE     WX
)@@G@@@C@@@L          JNZ       A5,SUM999         . ERROR   @E@@@L          JNWY
)@@G@@Z       A4,SUM999         . IF FOUND RETURN     @[@@@L.     @#@@@L. MACRWZ
)@@G@@O NOT FOUND.@^@@@L. (NOTE FALL-THRU).     @[@@@L.     @]@@@LSUM900    . XA
)@@G@@@D@@@L          M$EOPEN   M$EPKT M$IMAGE    . OPEN EDIT     @E@@@L      XB
)@@G@@    E$MSG     NOTFND            . MACRO NOT FOUND     @E@@@L          E$XC
)@@G@@FD2     ENAME             . EDIT MACRO NAME     @D@@@L          E$MSGR  XD
)@@G@@                    . NOT FOUND     @F@@@L          M$EAWX              XE
)@@G@@        . CLOSE EDIT AND GET MSG    @]@@@LSUM999    . @#@@@L          REXF

)@@G@@.     @B@@@L          END                         .   _@@@@@        A1,MXH
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/         M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. THE 'RECOVER' COXI
)@@G@@MMAND UN-SUSPENDS THE CURRENT MACRO @[@@@@.     @^@@@@M$COMRECOVER*     XJ
)@@G@@  .   @#@]@@          ROUTINE @^@@@]          SUBROUTINE    @A@#@@      XK
)@@G@@    LA        A0,OBL('GST')   @A@@@#          LA        A0,OBL('GSTV')  XL
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$COMOPTS     . SCAN FOR OPTIONS    @E@@@@XM
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,REC999         . IF ERROR - QUIT NOW @F@@@@      XN
)@@G@@    CALL      M$MORECMD         . SEE IF ANYTHING OUT THERE?@G@@@@      XO
)@@G@@    LA,U      A4,0              . GET INFINITE SKIP COUNT FLAG    @D@@@@XP
)@@G@@          JZ        A0,REC010         . SKIP IF NOT   @E@@@[          CAXQ
)@@G@@LL      M$SCANINT         . SCAN FOR AN INTEGER @ @@@[          JNZ     XR
)@@G@@  A5,REC999 @E@@@[          TP        A0                . IS RESULT POSIXS
)@@G@@TIVE? @D@@@[          LA,U      A0,0              . NOW IT IS     @E@@@[XT
)@@G@@          LA        A4,A0             . SAVE COUNT HERE     @G@[@@      XU
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,M$SCANEXPR    . SCAN FOR A NUMERIC EXPRESSION   @E@[@@XV
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,REC999         . WATCH OUT FOR ERRORS@F@[@@      XW
)@@G@@    LA,U      A4,0              . THE DEFAULT SKIP VALUE    @E@[@@      XX
)@@G@@    LA        A0,VDM+SVD        . GET THE RESULT MODE @H@[@@          LAXY
)@@G@@        A5,PCL('SKIP COUNT MUST BE A POSITIVE INTEGER SCALAR')    @E@[@@XZ
)@@G@@          JNE,U     A0,MODSIN REC999  . CHECK FOR BAD SYNTAX@F@[@@      YA
)@@G@@    LA        A0,VDL+SVD        . GET THE ARGUMENT LENGTH   @G@[@@      YB
)@@G@@    JNE,U     A0,1 REC999       . TAKE ERROR IF NOT LENGTH OF ONE @G@[@@YC
)@@G@@          LA        A0,VDA+SVD        . GET THE ADDRESS OF THE VALUE    YD
)@@G@@@F@[@@          LA        A4,,A0            . GET THE INTEGER VALUE     YE
)@@G@@@H@[@@          JN        A4,REC999         . TAKE THE ERROR EXIT IF NONYF
)@@G@@-POSITIVE   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. A4 = SKIP COUNT OR 0  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@YG
)@@G@@REC010@D@@@@          L,H2      A0,M$XQTMACRO     . GET ENTRY     @E@@@@YH
)@@G@@          JZ        A0,REC900         . IF ZERO JUST IGNORE @E@@@@      YI
)@@G@@    SA        A4,MXSSC,A0       . POST THE SKIP COUNT @D@@@@          LAYJ
)@@G@@        A1,MXFB,A0        . GET FLAGS     @H@^@@          AND,U     A1,-YK
)@@G@@MXBSUS-MXBTRA . ENSURE THAT THESE TWO FLAGS ARE CLEAR @H@@@^          ANYL
)@@G@@D,U     A1,-MXBSUS-MXBTRA-MXBVER . ENSURE THESE FLAGS ARE CLEAR   @E@@@@YM
)@@G@@          LA        A5,M$OPTS         . GET THE CALL OPTIONS@F@@@@      YN
)@@G@@    TEP       A5,OBL('T')       . WAS THE 'T' OPTION GIVEN? @F@@@@      YO
)@@G@@    AA,U      A2,MXBTRA         . YES, SET THE TRACE BIT    @F@@@#      YP
)@@G@@    TEP       A5,OBL('V')       . WAS THE 'V' OPTION GIVEN? @F@@@#      YQ
)@@G@@    AA,U      A2,MXBVER         . YES, SET THE VERBOSE BIT. @G@@@@      YR
)@@G@@    TOP       A5,OBL('G')       . WAS THE GLOBAL OPTION GIVEN?    @H@@@@YS
)@@G@@          TOP       A5,OBL('S')       . NO, WAS THE SUSPEND OPTION OMITTYT
)@@G@@ED?   @G@@@@          TZ        A4                . YES, IS THE SKIP COUYU
)@@G@@NT CLEAR?   @F@@@@          AA,U      A2,MXBSUS         . NO, SET THE SUYV
)@@G@@SPEND BIT   @D@@@@          SA        A2,MXFB,A0        . POST NEW FLAG YW
)@@G@@@H@@@@          JEP       A5,OBL('G') REC900 . IF NO GLOBAL BIT, DON'T CYX
)@@G@@HANGE'EM    @F@@@@          AND,U     A2,-MXBGTR-MXBGSU . CLEAR THE GLOBYY
)@@G@@AL BITS     @G@@@@          TEP       A5,OBL('T')       . SHOULD THE 'T'YZ
)@@G@@ OPTION BE GLOBAL?@G@@@@          AA,U      A3,MXBGTR         . YES, SETZA
)@@G@@ THE GLOBAL T OPTION    @G@@@@          TEP       A5,OBL('S')       . SHZB
)@@G@@OULD THE 'S' OPTION BE GLOBAL?@G@@@@          AA,U      A3,MXBGSU       ZC
)@@G@@  . YES, SET THE GLOBAL S OPTION    @F@@@#          TEP       A5,OBL('V'ZD
)@@G@@)       . WAS THE V OPTION GIVEN?   @F@@@#          AA,U      A3,MXBGVE ZE
)@@G@@        . ADD THE GLOVAL VERBOSE BIT@E@@@@          SA        A3,MXFB,A0ZF
)@@G@@        . POST NEW FLAG BITS  @^@@@@REC900    LA,U      A5,0@#@@@@REC999ZG
)@@G@@    RETURN  @]@@@@          . @B@@@@          END                       ZH
)@@G@@  .   _@@@@@LOBAL?@G@@@@          AA,U      A3,MXBGSU         . YES, SETZI
)@@G@@ THE GLOBAL S OPTION    @F@@@#          TEP     *[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@]/     ZJ
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @H@@@]          FIDEF$    M$ELT$            . MAKE ELT$ EQUFZK
)@@G@@S ON OUR OWN PACKET     @[@@@].     @F@@@]. THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED TO HAZL
)@@G@@NDLE THE 'CALL' COMMAND. IT USES THE@F@@@]. SAME ROUTINES AS THE IMPLICIZM
)@@G@@T MACRO CALL IN ELEMENT M$EXECUTE.  @[@@@].     @#@#@]M$COMCALL* ROUTINEZN
)@@G@@@^@@@#M$COMCALL* SUBROUTINE   @F@@@]CALMAC    LOCAL     1               ZO
)@@G@@  . TYPE AND ADDRESS OF MACRO @E@#@]          LA        A0,OBL('GST')   ZP
)@@G@@  . GET LEGAL OPTIONS   @E@@@#          LA        A0,OBL('GSTV')     . GZQ
)@@G@@ET LEGAL OPTIONS  @E@@@]          CALL      M$COMOPTS         . GET COMMZR
)@@G@@AND OPTIONS @E@@@]          JNZ       A5,CAL999         . TAKE ERROR EXIZS
)@@G@@T     @[@@@].     @F@@@]. NOW POSSIBLY SET THE TRACE & SUSPEND BITS.  IFZT
)@@G@@ THE CALL COMMAND @G@@@]. WAS ENTERED FROM THE KEYBOARD, OR IF THERE AREZU
)@@G@@ OPTIONS SPECIFIED,     @F@@@]. THEN THE OPTIONS ALONE DETERMINE THE TYPZV
)@@G@@E OF CALL.  IF THE MACRO@F@@@]. IS CALLED WITHOUT OPTIONS, THE PREVIOUS ZW
)@@G@@MACRO'S GLOBAL TRACE &  @E@@@]. SUSPEND BITS ARE DESCENDED INTO THIS MACZX
)@@G@@RO'S CALL BITS.   @[@@@].     @D@@@]          DSL       A1,72           ZY
)@@G@@  . DEFAULT BITS  @]@A@# SLJ TON$   @H@@@]          JNZ       A0,CAL004 ZZ
)@@G@@        . IF OPTIONS SPECIFIED, DON'T COPY BITS @G@@@]          JEZ     AA
)@@G@@  M$COMLINE CAL002  . IF KEYBOARD COMMAND, NO MACRO   @G@@@]          LAAB
)@@G@@,H2     A3,M$XQTMACRO     . GET THE MACRO EXECUTION PTR     @E@@@]      AC
)@@G@@    JZ        A3,CAL002         . IF NO MACRO, NO BITS@F@@@]          LAAD
)@@G@@        A1,MXFB,A3        . GET THE CURRENT FLAG BITS @I@#@]          ANAE
)@@G@@D,U     A1,MXBGTR+MXBGSU  . EXTRACT THE GLOBAL TRACE & SUSPEND BITS     AF
)@@G@@@I@@@#          AND,U     A1,MXBGTR+MXBGSU+MXBGVE . EXTRACT THE GLOBAL TAG
)@@G@@RACE, SUSPEND     @E@@@#                                      . AND VERBAH
)@@G@@OSE BITS    @D@@@]          LA,U      A1,,A2            . COPY THEM     AI
)@@G@@@F@#@]          SSL       A2,2              . & TURN INTO THE LOCAL BITSAJ
)@@G@@@F@@@#          SSL       A2,3              . & TURN INTO THE LOCAL BITSAK
)@@G@@@F@@@]          AA,U      A1,,A2            . PUT ALL THE BITS TOGETHER AL
)@@G@@@F@@@]          LA,U      A2,,A1            . MAY SET SOME OTHER BITS   AM
)@@G@@@G@@@]CAL002    TZ        M$TRACE           . IS THE GLOBAL TRACE FLAG SAN
)@@G@@ET?   @G@@@]          OR,U      A1,MXBTRA         . YES, SET THE LOCAL TAO
)@@G@@RACE BIT    @G@@@]          TZ        M$SUSPEND         . IS THE GLOBAL AP
)@@G@@SUSPEND FLAG SET? @G@@@]          OR,U      A1,MXBSUS         . YES, SETAQ
)@@G@@ THE LOCAL SUSPEND BIT  @E@@@]          J         CAL006            . GOAR
)@@G@@ STORE CALL BITS  @E@@@]CAL004    TEP       A0,OBL('T')       . 'T' OPTIAS
)@@G@@ON GIVEN?   @F@@@]          AA,U      A1,MXBTRA         . YES, SET THE TAT
)@@G@@RACE BIT    @E@@@]          TEP       A0,OBL('S')       . 'S' OPTION GIVAU
)@@G@@EN?   @F@@@]          AA,U      A1,MXBSUS         . YES, SET THE SUSPENDAV
)@@G@@ BIT  @E@^@#          TEP       A0,IBL('V')       . 'V' OPTION GIVEN?   AW
)@@G@@@E@@@^          TEP       A0,OBL('V')       . 'V' OPTION GIVEN?   @F@ @#AX
)@@G@@          AA,U      A0,MXBVER         . YES, SET THE VERBOSE BIT  @F@@@ AY
)@@G@@          AA,U      A1,MXBVER         . YES, SET THE VERBOSE BIT  @D@@@]AZ
)@@G@@          LA,U      A2,,A1            . COPY THE BITS @F@#@]          LSBA
)@@G@@SL      A1,2              . TURN INTO THE GLOBAL BITS @F@@@#          LSBB
)@@G@@SL      A1,3              . TURN INTO THE GLOBAL BITS @G@@@]          TEBC
)@@G@@P       A0,OBL('G')       . SHOULD THE BITS BE GLOBAL TOO?  @F@@@]      BD
)@@G@@    OR,U      A1,,A2            . YES, PUT THEM TOGETHER    @F@@@]CAL006BE
)@@G@@    SA,H1     A2,CALMAC         . SET THE CALL TYPE BITS    @[@@@].     BF
)@@G@@@]@A@#  SLJ TOFF$ @C@@@]. SCAN MACRO NAME AND PLACE IN ELT$ PACKET.     BG
)@@G@@@[@@@].     @F@@@]          LMJ       X11,M$SCANFILE    . SCAN FILE NAMEBH
)@@G@@ TO ELT$    @D@@@]          JNZ       A5,CAL999         . HANDLE ERROR  BI

)@@G@@@[@@@].     @E@@@]          TNZ       ENL               . ELEMENT NAME GBK
)@@G@@IVEN  @D@@@]          J         CAL900            . NO - ERROR    @[@@@]BL

)@@G@@    TZ        CFN               . OR IMPLIED FILE NAME@D@@@]          J BP

)@@G@@              . OR ELEMENT CYCLE    @D@@@]          J         CAL010    BS
)@@G@@        . YES - SKIP    @[@@@].     @C@@@]. JUST MACRO NAME.  SEARCH DEFBT
)@@G@@INED TABLES FIRST.@[@@@].     @E@@@]          DL        A0,ENAME        BU
)@@G@@  . GET ELEMENT NAME    @F@@@]          LMJ       X11,M$XQTDEFMAC   . SEBV

)@@G@@ CALL IT    @[@@@].     @C@@@]. SEARCH LIBRARY FILES FOR UNDEFINED MACROBY
)@@G@@.     @[@@@].     @]@@@]CAL010    . @F@@@]          LMJ       X11,M$XQTUBZ
)@@G@@NDMAC   . SEARCH FOR UNDEFINED MACRO@E@@@]          JNZ       A5,CAL999 CA

)@@G@@E FOR ARGUMENTS.  @[@@@].     @]@@@]CAL020    . @E@@@]          S,H2    CD

)@@G@@@E@@@]          L         A1,CALMAC         . GET MACRO AND TYPE  @D@@@]CH

)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@U/         M$DEF   @B@@@U          T$DEF               CS
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@V.     @E@@@V. M$SCANPRIM - SCAN THE NEXT PRIMITIVE IN CT
)@@G@@AN EXPRESSION SCAN@F@@@V. M$SCANITEM - SCAN THE NEXT ITEM (USUALLY A NAMCU
)@@G@@E OR TOKEN ITEM)  @[@@@V.     @^@@@V.  LMJ  X11,M$SCANPRIM  @^@@@V.  A5 CV

)@@G@@PRIM*                           .   @^@V@U          ROUTINE   X9  @^@@@VDO
)@@G@@          SUBROUTINE X9 @E@@@UPRMTC     LOCAL                       . TEDP
)@@G@@RMINATION CODE    @D@@@VPRMTMP    LOCAL     1                 . TEMPOARIDQ

)@@G@@RATOR FLAG  @H@@@VPRMLAC    EQUF      PRMTMP,,H2        . LOOKAHEAD COUNDS

)@@G@@              . CLEAR OUT MODE@F@@@V          SZ        PRMLAC          DV
)@@G@@  . CLEAR LEADING-BLANK FLAG  @E@@@X          L,XU      A0,-1           DW
)@@G@@  . GET SCAN TERM FLAG  @B@@@X          S         A0,M$SCANTERM     .   DX

)@@G@@ERM CHAR    @G@@@V          CALL      M$CDLEV           . GET THE CURRENDZ

)@@G@@        . GET CURRENT COLUMN  @G@@@V          SA        A0,M$SCANCOLUMN ED
)@@G@@  . POST IT FOR END-OF-CARD RETURNS @]@V@UPRM010    . @]@@@V          . EE
)@@G@@@F@V@U          T$CHAR    PRM021            . GET NEXT INPUT CHARACTER  EF
)@@G@@@F@@@VPRM010    T$CHAR    PRM021            . GET NEXT INPUT CHARACTER  EG
)@@G@@@E@@@U          SSL       A3,18             . GET ASCII CHARACTER @F@@@UEH

)@@G@@          TNE,U     A3,ASCIBL         . BLANK?? @G@@@U          JNZ     EJ

)@@G@@        A0,TRMSBF         . CHECK FOR SUBFIELD BREAKS @F@@@U          TNEL
)@@G@@E,U     A3,ASCICOMMA      . IS IT AN ASCII COMMA?     @H@@@U          JNEM
)@@G@@Z       A0,PRM015         . YES, CAUSE SUBFIELD TERM IF FLAG SET  @D@V@UEN

)@@G@@        PRM010            . YES - TRY AGAIN     @F@V@U          TNE,U   EP
)@@G@@  A3,ASCICR         . IS IT CARRIAGE RETURN     @F@@@V.         TNE,U   EQ
)@@G@@  A3,ASCICR         . IS IT CARRIAGE RETURN     @E@V@U          J       ER
)@@G@@  PRM020            . YES - END OF CARD   @E@@@V.         J         PRM0ES
)@@G@@20            . YES - END OF CARD   @D@@@V          TE,U      A3,ASCIBL ET
)@@G@@        . IS IT A BLANK?@C@@@V          J         $+3               . NOEU
