)@@G@@30            . NOPE    @[@@@U.     @H@@@U. END OF LINE, I.E.  NO MORE CFD
)@@G@@HARS, CARRIAGE RETURN, OR SPACE PERIOD SPACE    @[@@@U.     @[@@@UPRM015FE
)@@G@@@F@@@U          SX        X11,TRMSCN        . POST THE TERM SCAN FLAG   FF
)@@G@@@]@@@UPRM020    . @G@@@U          T$SKIP    -1                . BACKUP OFG
)@@G@@VER THE CHAR FOR RECALLS@[@@@UPRM021@F@V@U          T$COLN              FH
)@@G@@        . COMPUTE CURRENT COLUMN    @G@V@U          SA        A0,M$SCANCFI
)@@G@@OLUMN   . POST WHERE TERM CHAR WAS SEEN   @G@@@U          L,U       A0,MFJ
)@@G@@$EOLADDR      . GET ADDRESS OF EOL OPERATOR     @F@@@U          CALL    FK
)@@G@@  M$OPVD            . CONVERT TO DESCRIPTOR     @C@@@U          DS      FL
)@@G@@  A0,VD+SVD         . STORE IT@C@@@U          J         PRM150          FM
)@@G@@  . EXIT    @]@@@UPRM030    . @C@@@U          T$SKIP    - 1             FN
)@@G@@  . BACK UP @E@@@U          T$COLN                      . GET COLUMN NUMFO
)@@G@@BER   @E@@@U          S         A0,M$SCANCOLUMN   . SAVE COLUMN NUMBER  FP
)@@G@@@D@V@U          TGET      ASIMAX            . GET SPACE     @D@V@U      FQ
)@@G@@    JNZ       A5,PRM999         . DIDNT HAVE IT @D@@@V          M$TGET  FR
)@@G@@  PRM999 ASIMAX     . GET SPACE     @D@@@U          S         A1,VDA+SVDFS
)@@G@@        . SET ADDRESS   @E@@@U          L,U       X9,0,A1           . POFT
)@@G@@INT REGISTER AT IT@B@@@U          LXI,U     X9,1              .   @]@@@UFU
)@@G@@PRM040    . @F@@@U          DL        A0,M$FDBLANKS    . CLEAR BUFFER FOFV
)@@G@@R NAME-LABEL@B@@@U          DS        A0,0,X9           .   @E@@@U      FW
)@@G@@    T$GNRV    0,*X9             . SCAN NEXT PRIMITIVE @F@@@U          SAFX
)@@G@@        A3,M$SCANTERM     . SAVE TERMINATION CHARACTER@D@@@U          JNFY
)@@G@@Z       A1,PRM900         . ERROR IN TIDE$@F@@@U          TZ        ALPHFZ
)@@G@@A             . IN CONTINUED ALPHA MODE ? @D@@@U          J         PRM0GA
)@@G@@40            . AND LOOP BACK @[@@@U.     @A@@@U. RELEASE ANY TEMP STORAGB
)@@G@@GE NOT USED.@[@@@U.     @F@@@U          L,U       A0,0,X9           . GEGC
)@@G@@T FIRST UNUSED WORD     @D@@@U          TZ        DOUBLE            . WAGD
)@@G@@S IT DP     @D@@@U          A,U       A0,1              . ADD ONE WORD  GE
)@@G@@@D@@@U          TNZ       MODE              . ANYTHING FOUND@E@@@U      GF
)@@G@@    L         A0,VDA+SVD        . NO - RELEASE IT ALL @E@@@U          SAGG
)@@G@@        A2,PRMTC          . SAVE THE TERMCODE   @B@V@U          TREL    GH
)@@G@@                    .   @E@V@U          JNZ       A5,PRM999         . IFGI
)@@G@@ ERROR RETURN     @D@@@V          M$TREL    PRM999            . RELEASE GJ
)@@G@@SPACE @E@V@U          LA        A2,PRMTC          . RECOVER TERMCODE    GK
)@@G@@@E@@@V          LMA       A2,PRMTC          . RECOVER TERMCODE    @F@@@UGL
)@@G@@          L         A0,MODE           . LOAD TIDE$ INPUT MODE     @E@@@UGM
)@@G@@          L,H1      A1,MODTAB,A0      . PICK UP SCANNER MODE@E@@@U      GN
)@@G@@    S         A1,VDM+SVD        . SET MODE OF THING   @F@V@U          L,GO
)@@G@@H2      A1,MODTAB,A0      . GET PROCESSING ROUTINE    @F@@@V          L,GP
)@@G@@H2      A0,MODTAB,A0      . GET PROCESSING ROUTINE    @D@V@U          J GQ
)@@G@@        0,A1              . PROCESS THING @D@@@V          J         0,A0GR
)@@G@@              . PROCESS THING @[@@@V.     @A@@@V. HANDLE ONE OF THE LEVEGS
)@@G@@L OPERATORS.@[@@@V.     @F@@@VPRM050    JNEZ      PRMDLO PRM910     . IFGT
)@@G@@ EXTRA LEVELS, ERROR    @I@@@V          SA        A1,PRMDLO         . POGU
)@@G@@ST THE DICTIONARY LEVEL OPERATOR FLAG     @G@@@V          LA        A0,MGV
)@@G@@$SCANDL       . GET THE CURRENT LEVEL VALUE     @G@@@V          AN,U    GW
)@@G@@  A0,1              . ASSUME IT'S THE LEVEL 1 OPERATOR@G@@@V          TNGX
)@@G@@E,U     A1,M$OPERLEVELG   . WAS IT THE GLOBAL OPERATOR?     @F@@@V      GY
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,0              . YES, GET THE GLOBAL LEVEL @G@@@V      GZ
)@@G@@    SA        A0,M$SCANDL       . POST THE SCAN DICTIONARY LEVEL  @E@@@VHA
)@@G@@          SZ        ASO               . CLEAR ASCII OUT FLAG@D@@@V      HB
)@@G@@    J         PRM010            . GO SCAN AGAIN @[@@@V.     @E@@@V. M$SCHC
)@@G@@ANPRMBRK - TIDE$ INTERRUPT ADDRESS FOR BREAKCHARS     @[@@@V.     @F@@@VHD
)@@G@@. WHEN IN NUMERIC SCANNING MODE, TIDE$ WILL INTERRUPT HERE WHEN   @H@@@VHE
)@@G@@. ENCOUNTERING A BREAKCHAR.  THE ONLY BREAKCHARS WE ARE INTERESTED IN ARHF
)@@G@@E     @F@@@V. '+' AND '-', WHICH MAY EITHER BE OPERATORS OR PART OF A NUHG
)@@G@@MBER. @H@@@V. THE RULE USED HERE IS IF '+' OR '-' IS PRECEEDED BY AT LEAHH
)@@G@@ST ONE BLANK,     @H@@@V. THEN IT BECOMES PART OF THE NUMBER, OTHERWISE HI
)@@G@@IT'S TREATED AS AN OPERATOR.  @[@@@V.     @#@@@VM$SCANPRMBRK*     @]@W@VHJ
)@@G@@  SLJ TON$ .@E@@@V          LA        A3,A7             . GET SCANNED CHHK
)@@G@@AR    @F@@@V          LA,U      A2,,A3            . GET FIELDATA PART ONHL
)@@G@@LY    @E@@@V          TE,U      A2,'+'            . IS IT A SIGN CHAR?  HM
)@@G@@@B@@@V          TNE,U     A2,'-'            .   @D@@@V          J       HN
)@@G@@  $+2               . YES, SKIP     @H@@@V          J         0,X7      HO
)@@G@@        . NO, RETURN TO TIDE$ WITH BREAKCHAR    @F@@@V          JNEZ    HP
)@@G@@  EXP BRK1          . SKIP IF IN EXPONENT MODE  @F@@@V          TNZ     HQ
)@@G@@  EXPSIGN           . TIDE$ GENERATED BREAK?    @H@@@V          TNZ     HR
)@@G@@  PRMLAC            . OR IS SIGN THE FIRST CHAR SCANNED?    @F@@@V      HS
)@@G@@    J         0,X7              . YES, TREAT AS BREAKCHAR   @E@@@V      HT
)@@G@@    SX,H2     X7,PRMLNK         . SAVE REENTRY LINK   @H@@@V          T$HU
)@@G@@CHARN   *PRMLNK           . GRAB THE NEXT CHAR TO SEE IF BLANK    @E@@@VHV
)@@G@@          LA,U      A2,,A3            . FIELDATA PART ONLY  @G@@@V      HW
)@@G@@    JE,U      A2,' ' *PRMLNK    . BREAK CHAR IF BLANK FOLLOWS     @F@@@VHX
)@@G@@          JE,U      A2,'>' *PRMLNK    . BREAK CHAR IF '>' FOLLOWS @D@@@VHY
)@@G@@          LA        A3,A7             . GET '+' OR '-'@E@@@V          J HZ
)@@G@@        T$SCAN1$          . OTHERWISE, PARSE IT @G@@@VBRK1      TZ      IA
)@@G@@  EXPSIGN           . EXPONENT MODE; SIGN SEEN YET?   @F@@@V          TNIB
)@@G@@Z       DIGITS            . YES, ANY DIGITS BETWEEN?  @G@@@V          TZIC
)@@G@@        INTEGER           . NO, ARE WE IN INTEGER MODE?     @G@@@V      ID
)@@G@@    J         0,X7              . YES, TREAT SIGN AS BREAK CHAR   @G@@@VIE
)@@G@@          J         T$SCAN1$          . NO, RETURN TO PARSE THE CHAR    IF
)@@G@@@[@@@U/.    @[@@@U.     @C@@@U. ITEM SCANNED IS A SINGLE ARITHMETIC ITEMIG
)@@G@@.     @[@@@U.     @]@@@UPRM070    . @B@@@U          L,U       A0,1      IH
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@U          S         A0,VDL+SVD        .   @D@@@U      II
)@@G@@    J         PRM140            . AND RETURN    @[@@@U.     @D@@@U. ITEMIJ
)@@G@@ SCANNED IS ALPHABETIC - COMPUTE CHARACTER COUNT@[@@@U.     @]@@@UPRM080IK
)@@G@@    . @E@@@V          TNE,U     A1,MODNAM         . WAS ITEM A NAME?    IL
)@@G@@@H@@@V          SZ        PRMDLO            . YES, CLEAR THE LEVEL OPERAIM
)@@G@@TOR FLAG    @F@V@U          L,U       A1,0,X9           . COMPUTE WORD CIN
)@@G@@OUNT - 1    @F@@@V          L,U       A0,0,X9           . COMPUTE WORD CIO
)@@G@@OUNT - 1    @B@V@U          AN        A1,VDA+SVD        .   @B@@@V      IP
)@@G@@    AN        A0,VDA+SVD        .   @B@V@U          AN,U      A1,1      IQ
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@V          AN,U      A0,1              .   @C@V@U      IR
)@@G@@    L         A0,VDM+SVD        . GET MODE@E@V@U          TEP,U     A0,AIS
)@@G@@SCBIT         . IS MODE ASCII ?     @D@@@V          TNE,U     A1,MODASC IT
)@@G@@        . ASCII STRING? @F@V@U          LSSL      A1,2              . YEIU
)@@G@@S - MAKE CHAR COUNT     @F@@@V          LSSL      A0,2              . YEIV
)@@G@@S - MAKE CHAR COUNT     @E@V@U          TOP,U     A0,ASCBIT         . ISIW
)@@G@@ MODE FIELDATA ?  @E@@@V          TNE,U     A1,MODALP         . FIELDATAIX
)@@G@@ STRING?    @E@V@U          MSI,U     A1,6              . MAKE CHAR COUNIY
)@@G@@T     @E@@@V          MSI,U     A0,6              . MAKE CHAR COUNT     IZ
)@@G@@@E@V@U          A         A1,A4             . ADD IN RESIDUAL     @E@@@VJA
)@@G@@          A         A0,A4             . ADD IN RESIDUAL     @E@V@U      JB
)@@G@@    S         A1,VDL+SVD        . SET LENGTH OF ITEM  @E@@@V          S JC
)@@G@@        A0,VDL+SVD        . SET LENGTH OF ITEM  @D@@@V          TNE,U   JD
)@@G@@  A1,MODNAM         . STRING ITEM?  @D@V@U          J         PRM140    JE
)@@G@@        . AND RETURN    @D@@@V          J         PRM140            . NOJF
)@@G@@, RETURN    @C@@@V          LA        A5,PCL('MISSING QUOTE.')    @G@@@VJG
)@@G@@          JE,U      A2,2 PRM990       . IF END-OF-CARD, ERROR IN STRING JH
)@@G@@@E@@@V          J         PRM140            . GO CHECK BREAK CHAR @[@@@UJI
)@@G@@.     @E@@@U. THIS IS AN OPERATOR (WHICH ARE ALL SET AS BREAK CHARS)    JJ
)@@G@@@[@@@U.     @]@@@UPRM090    . @G@@@V          JNEG      M$SCANTERM PRM02JK
)@@G@@0 . IF END-OF-CARD, GO RETURN EOL   @H@@@U          T$SKIP    -1        JL
)@@G@@        . BACKUP OVER FIRST CHAR OF OPERATOR    @D@@@U          LA,U    JM
)@@G@@  A0,1              . GET A BIT     @F@@@U          SA        A0,ASO    JN
)@@G@@        . POST ASCII OUTPUT FLAG    @F@@@U          SZ        SVD       JO
)@@G@@        . CLEAR OPERATOR FOUND ADDR @E@@@U          SZ        SVD+1     JP
)@@G@@        . CLEAR OPERATOR CACHE@E@@@U          T$NBRKF   SVD+1 M$OPERMASKJQ
)@@G@@ 1 . SCAN AN OPERATOR   @H@@@U          JZ        A4,PRM900         . IFJR
)@@G@@ NOTHING ACCEPTED, LEXICAL ERROR    @E@@@U          SA        A0,A5     JS
)@@G@@        . SAVE FOR REENTRY    @E@@@U          LA,Q1     A3,SVD+1        JT
)@@G@@  . GET THE OPERATOR    @G@@@UPRM100,   TSE       A3,OTNAME,A0 OTSIZE,M$JU
)@@G@@OPERTABLE . FIND THE OPERATOR @E@@@U          J         PRM120          JV
)@@G@@  . SKIP IF NO FIND     @E@@@U          SA        A0,SVD            . SAJW
)@@G@@VE FOUND ADDRESS  @E@@@V          SZ        PRMLAC            . KILL LOOJX
)@@G@@KAHEAD COUNT@G@@@U          JEZ       OTMCF,A0 PRM130   . SKIP IF NO CONJY
)@@G@@TINUATION OF SCAN @D@V@UPRM110    LA        A0,A5             . RESCAN TJZ
)@@G@@IME   @D@@@VPRM110    LA        A0,A5             . RESCAN TIME   @F@@@UKA
)@@G@@          T$SCNRF   1                 . SCAN ANOTHER CHARACTER    @G@@@VKB
)@@G@@          JE,U      A2,2 PRM130       . IF END-OF-CARD, DON'T SEARCH    KC
)@@G@@@E@@@U          LA        A5,A0             . SAVE REENTRY WORD   @G@@@VKD
)@@G@@          INC       A0,PRMLAC         . INCREMENT THE LOOKAHEAD COUNT   KE
)@@G@@@G@@@U          JZ        A4,PRM130         . IF NOT ACCEPTED, DON'T SEAKF
)@@G@@RCH   @E@@@U          LA        A3,SVD+1          . GET THE OPERATOR    KG
)@@G@@@E@@@U          TNZ,Q4    SVD+1             . 3 CHAR OPERATOR?    @C@@@UKH
)@@G@@          SSL       A3,9              . YES     @E@@@U          TNZ,Q3  KI
)@@G@@  SVD+1             . 2 CHAR OPERATOR?    @C@@@U          SSL       A3,9KJ
)@@G@@              . YES     @E@@@U          J         PRM100            . GOKK
)@@G@@ FIND THE OPERATOR@F@@@UPRM120    LA        A0,SVD            . RECOVER KL
)@@G@@ANY FOUND ADDRESS @G@@@U          TZ,Q4     SVD+1             . WAS NO FKM
)@@G@@IND ON 4-CHAR OPER?     @G@@@U          JZ        A0,PRM900         . YEKN
)@@G@@S, IF NOT ANY FINDS, ERROR    @G@@@U          JZ        A0,PRM110       KO
)@@G@@  . NO, IF NO FINDS YET, KEEP TRYING@H@@@U          LA,U      A2,1      KP
)@@G@@        . FLAG LAST CHAR SEEN AS BREAK CHAR     @E@V@UPRM130    LA      KQ
)@@G@@  A0,SVD            . GET FOUND ADDRESS   @F@@@VPRM130    LN        A0,PKR
)@@G@@RMLAC         . GET THE LOOKAHEAD COUNT   @G@@@V          TZ        A0  KS
)@@G@@              . IS IT NECESSARY TO BACK UP?     @D@@@V          T$SKIP  KT
)@@G@@                    . YES, DO SO    @E@@@V          LA        A0,SVD    KU
)@@G@@        . GET FOUND ADDRESS   @C@@@U          JZ        A0,PRM900       KV
)@@G@@  . NO GOOD @G@@@U          CALL      M$OPVD            . TURN TABLE ENTKW
)@@G@@RY INTO DESCRIPTOR@D@@@U          DS        A0,SVD            . POST RESKX
)@@G@@ULT   @F@@@V          LA,U      A1,,A1            . GET THE OPERATOR ID KY
)@@G@@ONLY  @H@@@V          TE,U      A1,M$OPERLEVEL1   . IS THIS ONE OF THE LKZ
)@@G@@EVELING OPERATORS?@G@@@V          TNE,U     A1,M$OPERLEVELG   . OR THE GLA
)@@G@@LOBAL LEVEL OPERATOR    @F@@@V          J         PRM050            . YELB
)@@G@@S, GO HANDLE IT NOW     @D@@@V          J         PRM150            . FILC
)@@G@@NISH UP     @[@@@U.     @E@@@U. CHECK FOR BREAKCHARACTER AS TERMINATOR -LD
)@@G@@ IF SO THEN WE    @^@@@U. MUST BACKSPACE ONE.   @[@@@U.     @]@@@UPRM140LE
)@@G@@    . @E@V@U          LM        A2,A2             . GET TERMINATION CODELF
)@@G@@@E@@@U          TE,U      A2,1              . WAS IT TERMCHAR ?   @B@@@ULG
)@@G@@          J         PRM150            . NO@E@@@U          T$SKIP    - 1 LH
)@@G@@              . YES - SKIP BACK     @[@@@U/.    @^@@@U. RESTORE AND RETULI
)@@G@@RN    @[@@@U.     @]@@@UPRM150    . @H@@@V          JNEZ      PRMDLO PRMLJ
)@@G@@910     . IF LEVEL OPERATOR UNFUFILLED, ERROR   @E@@@U          L,U     LK
)@@G@@  A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR FLAG    @D@@@U          J         PRM9LL
)@@G@@99            . AND RETURN    @[@@@U.     @C@@@U. ERROR - ILLEGAL CHARACLM
)@@G@@TER AT CURRENT COLUMN   @[@@@U.     @]@V@UPRM900    . @D@V@U          L LN
)@@G@@        A5,PRMLEX         . LEXICAL ERROR @D@@@VPRM900    L         A5,PLO
)@@G@@RMLEX         . LEXICAL ERROR @B@@@V          J         PRM990          LP
)@@G@@  .   @]@@@V          . @C@@@VPRM910    LA        A5,PCL('SYNTAX ERROR.'LQ
)@@G@@)     @]@@@V          . @]@V@UPRM990    . @F@V@U          L         A0,MLR
)@@G@@$SCANCOLUMN   . RECOVER COLUMN NUMBER     @F@@@VPRM990    L         A0,MLS
)@@G@@$SCANCOLUMN   . RECOVER COLUMN NUMBER     @F@@@U          LMJ       X11,LT
)@@G@@M$ERRMSGBLD   . GENERATE ERROR MESSAGE    @]@V@UPRM999    . @]@@@V      LU
)@@G@@    . @E@V@U          SZ        ASO               . CLEAR ASCII OUT FLAGLV
)@@G@@@E@@@VPRM999    SZ        ASO               . CLEAR ASCII OUT FLAG@E@@@ULW
)@@G@@          L         A1,VDA+SVD        . LOAD RETURN ARGS    @C@@@U      LX
)@@G@@    L         A0,VDM+SVD        . AND MODE@D@@@U          L         A2,VLY
)@@G@@DL+SVD        . AND LENGTH    @E@@@U          L         A3,M$SCANTERM   LZ
)@@G@@  . SAVE TERMINATOR     @E@@@U          L         A4,M$SCANCOLUMN   . GEMA
)@@G@@T COLUMN SEEN AT  @#@@@U          RETURN  @[@@@U.     @E@@@U. THIS SUBROMB
)@@G@@UTINE CONVERTS AN OPERATOR TABLE ENTRY INTO     @^@@@U. A DESCRIPTOR FORMC
)@@G@@MAT   @E@@@U. IT EXPECTS THE ADDRESS OF THE OPERATOR IN A0, AND RETURNS MD
)@@G@@@ @@@U. THE DESCRIPTOR IN A0-A1     @[@@@U.     @]@@@UM$OPVD*     @H@@@UME
)@@G@@          L,U       A1,0,A0           . GET OPERATOR ID (OP TABLE ADDRESMF
)@@G@@S)    @H@@@U          LXI       A1,OTSRA,A0       . GET OPERATOR SEMANTIMG
)@@G@@C ROUTINE ADDRESS @E@@@U          LA,H1     A0,,A1            . GET THE MH
)@@G@@PRIORITIES  @G@@@U          SSL       A0,6              . POSITION PRIORMI
)@@G@@ITIES CORRECTLY   @D@@@U          AA,U      A0,MODOPR*/12     . GET MODEMJ
)@@G@@ IN S4@E@@@U          LSSL      A0,18             . CREATE MODE WORD    MK
)@@G@@@C@@@U          J         0,X11             . RETURN  @[@@@U.     @G@@@UML
)@@G@@. DECLARE THE TWO SPECIAL "OPERATORS" FOR BEGINING AND ENDING OF LINE   MM
)@@G@@@[@@@U.     @]@@@UM$BGLADDR*  @F@@@UM$OPERBGL* OPR      '',01,01,M$SEMBGMN
)@@G@@L . BEGIN OF LINE OPERATOR    @]@@@UM$EOLADDR*  @E@@@UM$OPEREOL* OPR    MO
)@@G@@  '',00,00,M$SEMEOL . END OF LINE OPERATOR@[@@@U/.    @[@@@U.     @B@@@UMP
)@@G@@. JUMP TABLE DEPENDING ON TIDE$ MODES     @[@@@U.     @B@@@U          LIMQ
)@@G@@TS                        .   @]@@@UMODTAB    . @F@@@U          +       MR
)@@G@@  MODOPR,PRM090     . NOTHING FOUND, MUST BE OPR@G@@@U          +       MS
)@@G@@  MODSFL,PRM070     . SINGLE PRECISION FLOATING POINT @G@@@U          + MT
)@@G@@        MODDFL,PRM070     . DOUBLE PRECISION FLOATING POINT @F@@@U      MU
)@@G@@    +         MODSIN,PRM070     . SINGLE PRECISION INTEGER  @F@@@U      MV
)@@G@@    +         MODDIN,PRM070     . DOUBLE PRECISION INTEGER  @F@@@U      MW
)@@G@@    +         MODSIN,PRM070     . SINGLE PRECISION INTEGER  @F@@@U      MX
)@@G@@    +         MODDIN,PRM070     . DOUBLE PRECISION INTEGER  @E@@@U      MY
)@@G@@    +         MODALP,PRM080     . FIELDATA ALPHABETIC @E@@@U          + MZ
)@@G@@        MODALP,PRM080     . FIELDATA ALPHABETIC @E@@@U          +       NA
)@@G@@  MODASC,PRM080     . ASCII ALPHABETIC    @E@@@U          +         MODANB
)@@G@@SC,PRM080     . ASCII ALPHABETIC    @D@@@U          +         MODNAM,PRMNC
)@@G@@080     . NAME-LABEL    @[@@@U.     @B@@@U          LITS                ND

)@@G@@@^@@@]^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)C(IC))^@)_@@@@@E[GDC0AC0^@)*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@A/     GM
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@A.     @G@@@A. THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED WITH TIDE$ OPEN TGN
)@@G@@O BUILD AN ARGUMENT BUFFER    @F@@@A. CONTAINING POINTERS TO THE CALL IMGO
)@@G@@AGE AND THE CALL IMAGE ITSELF.@F@@@A. THE WORD RETURNED IN A0 SHOULD BE GP
)@@G@@PLACED IN CXARGS OF THE MACRO @F@@@A. EXECUTION ENTRY FOR SYMBOLIC SUBSTGQ
)@@G@@ITUTION TO WORK PROPERLY.     @[@@@A.     @A@B@A. BUILD POINTER BUFFER IGR
)@@G@@N M$STAK.   @[@B@A.     @D@B@AAPTR      EQUF      M$STAK+2*(STKMAX-2) . GS
)@@G@@POINTER     @G@B@AFRST      EQUF      APTR,,H1          . START COLUMN (GT
)@@G@@AND COUNTERS)     @D@B@ALAST      EQUF      APTR,,H2          . END COLUGU
)@@G@@MN    @[@B@A.     @B@@@B. DEFINE STACK ITEMS FOR CALL SCANNER.    @[@@@BGV
)@@G@@.     @B@@@ASTKPTR    EQU       X1                .   @F@@@BSTKSIZ    EQGW
)@@G@@U       64                . ALLOW 64 FIELDS+SUBFIELDS @D@@@BSTKINC    EQGX
)@@G@@U       1                 . ONE WORD ITEMS@[@@@B.     @D@@@BAPTR      EQGY
)@@G@@UF      0                 . A POINTER     @G@@@BFRST      EQUF      APTRGZ
)@@G@@,,H1          . START COLUMN (AND COUNTERS)     @D@@@BLAST      EQUF    HA
)@@G@@  APTR,,H2          . END COLUMN    @[@@@A.     @B@@@AM$CALLSCAN*       HB
)@@G@@                    .   @ @B@A          ROUTINE   X1,X2,X3  @A@@@B      HC
)@@G@@    SUBROUTINE   X1,X2,X3     @F@@@AMCSCHR    LOCAL     1               HD
)@@G@@  . CHAR THAT TERMINATED FIELD@D@@@BMCSERR    LOCAL                     HE
)@@G@@  . ERROR PCW WORD@[@@@A.     @B@@@A. X1 POINTS TO THE CURRENT SUBFIELD HF
)@@G@@WORD. @B@@@A. X2 POINTS TO THE CURRENT FIELD WORD.    @C@@@A. X3  POINTSHG
)@@G@@ TO THE MACRO BUFFER BEING BUILT.   @[@@@A.     @G@@@B          STKINIT HH
)@@G@@  MCS999            . INITIALIZE THE STACK POINTER    @F@@@B          PUHI
)@@G@@SH      MCS090            . PUSH AN INITIAL ENTRY     @E@B@A          L HJ
)@@G@@        STKPTR,MCSSTK     . GET INITIAL STACK   @E@@@A          L,U     HK
)@@G@@  X3,0,X1           . GET BUFFER ADDRESS  @F@@@A          SZ        APTRHL
)@@G@@,X3           . CLEAR COUNTER AND END     @[@@@A.     @C@@@A. $$$TEMP KLHM
)@@G@@UGE TO FIND IF OPTIONS PRESENT.     @[@@@A.     @C@@@A          T$SKIP  HN
)@@G@@  -1                . BACK ONE@D@@@A          T$CHAR    MCS080          HO
)@@G@@  . GET CHARACTER @D@@@A          LXI,U     A3,0              . CLEAR UPHP
)@@G@@PER   @D@D@A          TNE,U     A3,','            . WAS IT A COMMA@D@@@DHQ
)@@G@@          TE,U      A3,','            . WAS IT A COMMA@F@@@D          J HR
)@@G@@        MCS005            . NOT A COMMA, FAKE OPTIONS @E@@@D          T$HS
)@@G@@CHARN   MCS005            . GET NEXT CHARACTER  @G@@@D          L,U     HT
)@@G@@  A3,,A3            . GET JUST THE FLDATA VERSION     @D@@@D          TEHU
)@@G@@,U      A3,' '            . IS IT A BLANK?@F@@@D          J         MCS0HV
)@@G@@10            . NO, SCAN OPTIONS FIELD    @F@D@A          J         MCS0HW
)@@G@@10            . YES - SCAN OPTIONS FIELD  @[@@@A.     @A@@@A. SYNTHESIZEHX
)@@G@@ NULL FIELD FOR OPTIONS.@[@@@A.     @]@@@CMCS005    . @D@@@A          PUHY
)@@G@@SH      MCS090            . PUSH DOWN     @G@@@A          L,U       X2,0HZ
)@@G@@,X1           . POINT FIELD POINTER AT ENTRY    @E@@@A          SZ      IA
)@@G@@  APTR,X2           . CLEAR FIELD ENTRY   @E@@@A          T$COLN        IB
)@@G@@              . GET COLUMN NUMBER   @E@@@A          SZ        MCSCHR    IC
)@@G@@        . CLEAR CHARACTER     @D@@@A          J         MCS075          ID
)@@G@@  . THEN CLOSE IT @[@@@A.     @B@@@A. SCAN PAST BLANKS UNTIL NEXT FIELD IE
)@@G@@FOUND.@[@@@A.     @]@@@AMCS010    . @E@C@A          T$NFIND   ' ' MCS080IF
)@@G@@        . FIND NEXT NONBLANK  @E@D@C          T$NFIND   ' ' MCS005      IG
)@@G@@  . FIND NEXT NONBLANK  @E@@@D          T$NFIND   ' ' MCS080        . FIIH
)@@G@@ND NEXT NONBLANK  @E@@@A          LA,U      A3,,A3            . ONLY THEII
)@@G@@ CHARACTER  @D@@@A          S         A3,MCSCHR         . SAVE CHARACTERIJ
)@@G@@@H@@@A          JEZ       M$SPSSTOP MCS020  . SKIP IF NO SPACE-PERIOD-SPIK
)@@G@@ACE CHECK   @E@@@A          TE,U      A3,'.'            . WAS TERMED BY IL
)@@G@@PERIOD@E@@@A          J         MCS020            . NO - NOT END OF CARDIM
)@@G@@@F@@@A          T$CHARN   MCS080            . GET NEXT CHAR NO LOOKAHEADIN
)@@G@@@D@@@A          L,U       A3,0,A3           . REAL CHARACTER@E@@@A      IO
)@@G@@    TNE,U     A3,' '            . SPACE PERIOD SPACE  @E@@@A          J IP
)@@G@@        MCS080            . YES - DONE SCAN     @[@@@A.     @F@@@A. NOT IQ
)@@G@@TERMINATION.  PUSH ANOTHER FIELD AND ITS FIRST SUBFIELD     @C@@@A. ONTOIR
)@@G@@ STACK AFTER INCREMENTING FIELD COUNTER.  @[@@@A.     @]@@@AMCS020    . IS
)@@G@@@E@@@A          PUSH      MCS090            . PUSH ONTO STACK     @G@@@AIT
)@@G@@          L,U       X2,0,X1           . POINT FIELD POINTER AT ENTRY    IU
)@@G@@@E@@@A          PUSH      MCS090            . PUSH FIRST SUBFIELD @G@@@AIV
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,1              . SET SUBFIELD COUNTER TO ONE     IW
)@@G@@@B@@@A          S         A0,FRST,X2        .   @G@@@A          T$COLN  IX
)@@G@@                    . GET COLUMN NUMBER WE ARE AT     @F@@@A          ANIY
)@@G@@,U      A0,1              . GET WHERE THIS CHAR WAS   @F@@@A          S IZ
)@@G@@        A0,FRST,X1        . SET SUBFIELD START COLUMN @E@@@A          L JA
)@@G@@        A3,MCSCHR         . GET CHARACTER AGAIN @[@@@A/.    @[@@@A.     JB
)@@G@@@G@@@A. WITHIN A FIELD.  SKIP PAST DULL DRAB ORDINARY CHARACTERS WITH NEJC
)@@G@@W     @A@@@A. IMPROVED TIDE$. (NOTE FALL-THRU). @[@@@A.     @]@@@AMCS030JD
)@@G@@    . @E@@@A          TNE,U     A3,' '            . WAS CHARACTER BLANK JE
)@@G@@@E@@@A          J         MCS075            . YES - END OF FIELD  @G@@@AJF
)@@G@@          JEZ       M$CALLSTR MCS035  . SKIP IF NO STRINGS RECOGNIZED   JG
)@@G@@@F@@@A          TNE,U     A3,FDQUOTE        . WAS IT A FIELDATA QUOTE?  JH
)@@G@@@E@@@A          J         MCS050            . YES - FIND ITS MATE @F@@@AJI
)@@G@@          TNE,U     A3,ASQUOTE        . WAS IT ASCII QUOTE (MAJIC)@E@@@AJJ
)@@G@@          J         MCS060            . YES - FIND ITS MATE @[@@@AMCS035JK
)@@G@@@E@@@A          TE,U      A3,','            . IS IT COMMA THEN    @E@@@AJL
)@@G@@          J         MCS040            . NO - SKIP FIELD     @[@@@A.     JM
)@@G@@@D@@@A. COMMA SEEN.  CLOSE OLD SUBFIELD AND OPEN NEW ONE.   @[@@@A.     JN
)@@G@@@E@@@A          T$COLN                      . GET COLUMN WE ARE AT@F@@@AJO
)@@G@@          ANU,U     A0,2              . MINUS TWO FOR OLD FIELD   @E@@@AJP
)@@G@@          S         A1,LAST,X1        . SAVE END OF SUBFIELD@G@@@A      JQ
)@@G@@    PUSH      MCS090            . PUSH NEW SUBFIELD ONTO STACK    @G@@@AJR
)@@G@@          S         A0,FRST,X1        . SET BEGINNING OF SUBFIELD ONTO  JS
)@@G@@@E@@@A          L         A0,FRST,X2        . INCREMENT COUNT OF  @E@@@AJT
)@@G@@          A,U       A0,1              . SUBFIELDS IN THE    @D@@@A      JU
)@@G@@    S         A0,FRST,X2        . FIELD ENTRY   @F@E@A          T$NSEEK JV
)@@G@@  ' ' MCS070        . FIND START OF SUBFIELD    @F@@@E.          T$NSEEKJW
)@@G@@   ' ' MCS070        . FIND START OF SUBFIELD   @E@E@A          T$COLN  JX
)@@G@@                    . FIND ITS POSITION   @E@@@E.          T$COLN       JY
)@@G@@               . FIND ITS POSITION  @G@E@A          S         A0,FRST,X1JZ
)@@G@@        . SET BEGINNING OF SUBFIELD ONTO  @G@@@E.          S         A0,KA
)@@G@@FRST,X1        . SET BEGINNING OF SUBFIELD ONTO @F@@@E          T$CHARN KB
)@@G@@  MCS070            . GET THE NBEXT CHARACTER   @E@@@E          L,U     KC
)@@G@@  A3,,A3            . THEN GET ONLY FLDATA@E@@@E          TNE,U     A3,'KD
)@@G@@ '            . WAS IT A BLANK?     @F@@@E          J         MCS070    KE
)@@G@@        . YES, IT IS END OF FIELD.  @]@@@AMCS040    . @E@@@A          T$KF
)@@G@@SCANV   0 MCSMSK          . SKIP DULL CHARS     @E@@@A          JN      KG
)@@G@@  A3,MCS070         . IF DONE CLOSE IMAGE @E@@@A          L,U       A3,0KH
)@@G@@,A3           . ELSE GET CHARACTER  @E@@@A          J         MCS030    KI
)@@G@@        . RETURN TO CHECK     @[@@@A.     @E@@@A. IF A FIELDATA QUOTE ISKJ
)@@G@@ SEEN THIS CODE SKIPS UNTIL MATE.   @[@@@A.     @]@@@AMCS050    . @E@@@AKK
)@@G@@          T$FIND    FDQUOTE MCS091    . ERROR IF NOT CLOSED @E@@@A      KL
)@@G@@    J         MCS040            . ELSE RETURN TO CHECK@[@@@A.     @D@@@AKM
)@@G@@. IF AN ASCII QUOTE (TIDE$ ASQUOTE) SKIP UNTIL MATE.  @[@@@A.     @]@@@AKN
)@@G@@MCS060    . @D@@@A          T$FIND    ASQUOTE MCS091    . FIND ITS MATE KO
)@@G@@@D@@@A          J         MCS040            . AND RETURN    @[@@@A/.    KP
)@@G@@@[@@@A.     @E@@@A. AT END OF FIELD THIS CODE CLOSES THE SUBFIELD AND FIKQ
)@@G@@ELD.  @[@@@A.     @ @@@A. END OF FIELD AND END OF CARD@[@@@A.     @]@@@AKR
)@@G@@MCS070.     @F@@@A          S         A3,MCSCHR         . STORE EOF TERMKS
)@@G@@INATION CODE@E@@@A          T$COLN                      . GET COLUMN NUMKT
)@@G@@BER   @F@@@A          AN,U      A0,1              . DECREMENT TO FIND LEKU
)@@G@@NGTH  @C@@@A          J         MCS078            . CONTINUE@[@@@A.     KV
)@@G@@@A@@@A. END OF FIELD AND NOT END OF CARD  @[@@@A.     @]@@@AMCS075    . KW
)@@G@@@D@@@A          S         A3,MCSCHR         . SAVE CHARACTER@E@@@A      KX
)@@G@@    T$COLN                      . GET COLUMN NUMBER   @B@@@A          ANKY
)@@G@@,U      A0,2              .   @D@@@AMCS078    S         A0,LAST,X1      KZ
)@@G@@  . CLOSE SUBFIELD@D@@@A          S         A0,LAST,X2        . CLOSE FILA

)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@]/         M$DEF   @[@@@].     @D@@@]. DISPLAY - COMMANGL
)@@G@@D TO EVALUATE AND PRINT EXPRESSIONS.@[@@@].     @^@#@]M$COMDISPLAY* ROUTGM
)@@G@@INE   @^@@@#M$COMDISPLAY* SUBROUTINE@]@A@    SLJ TON$ @E@@@]          CAGN
)@@G@@LL      M$SCANLINE        . SCAN AN EXPRESSION  @]@A@    SLJ TOFF$@E@@@]GO
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,DISP999        . CHECK FOR ERRORS    @F@@@]      GP
)@@G@@    JE,U      A0,MODNUL DISP999 . IF NULL, SIMPLY RETURN    @E@@@^      GQ
)@@G@@    M$EOPENA  M$EPKT M$IMAGE    . OPEN EDIT$ PACKAGE  @F@@@]          COGR
)@@G@@NVASC   DISP999 VD+SVD    . CONVERT THE VALUE TO ASCII@F@@@^          DLGS
)@@G@@        A0,VD+SVD         . GET THE CONVERTED VALUE   @G@@@^          CAGT
)@@G@@LL      M$EDITSTR         . EDIT A STRING INTO THE BUFFER   @E@@@^      GU
)@@G@@    E$COLN                      . GET CURRENT COLUMN  @F@@@^          JZGV
)@@G@@        A0,DISP010        . SKIP IF NOTHING IN IT     @E@@@^          M$GW
)@@G@@EPRT                      . PRINT THE IMAGE     @D@@@^DISP010   M$ECLOSEGX
)@@G@@                    . FINISH EDITING@C@@@^          LA,U      A5,0      GY
)@@G@@        . ALL DONE@H@^@]          AA,U      A2,3              . CONVERT GZ
)@@G@@CHAR LENGTH TO WORD LENGTH    @D@^@]          SSL       A2,2            HA
)@@G@@  . A2 = # WORDS  @F@^@]          LXI       A1,M$PLIMIT       . GET PRINHB
)@@G@@T LIMIT (IN WORDS)@D@^@]          LA        A3,A1             . KEEP HERHC
)@@G@@E     @F@^@]DISP010   LA,U      A0,,*A3           . GET THE NEXT BUFFER HD
)@@G@@FULL  @E@^@]          LXI,U     A0,,A2            . SET THE WORD COUNT  HE
)@@G@@@G@^@]          AN        A2,M$PLIMIT       . SUBTRACT STANDARD PRINT LIHF
)@@G@@MIT   @E@^@]          TN        A2                . IS BUFFER TOO BIG?  HG
)@@G@@@F@^@]          LXI       A0,M$PLIMIT       . YES, SET STANDARD LIMIT   HH
)@@G@@@D@^@]          AA        A0,(0100,0)       . SET LINE SKIP @E@^@]      HI
)@@G@@    M$APRINT                    . PRINT THE IMAGE     @D@^@]          JPHJ
)@@G@@        A2,DISP010        . KEEP GOING    @D@@@]DISP999   RETURN        HK
)@@G@@              . THAT'S ALL    @]@@@]          . @#@@@]          END     HL
)@@G@@_@@@@@D1B^[[CL]EK,@O@@@@^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^-NES*CS1 )1 -#CDG C/B1OEK*CT[ C!HM
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/         M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@. M$FUNTD - FUNCTIHN
)@@G@@ON TO PERFORM TIME & DATE EDITING ON A TDATE$ ARGUMENT.     @[@@@@.     HO
)@@G@@@F@@@@. THE FUNCTION SUBCODE DETERMINES WHICH EDITING ROUTINE TO USE.   HP
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@TDMAXI    EQU       9                 . MAXIMUM INDEX HQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @#@[@@M$FUNTD*  ROUTINE @^@@@[M$FUNTD*  SUBROUTINE    @E@@@@HR
)@@G@@          LA        A0,VDM+SRA        . GET ARGUMENT MODE   @E@@@@      HS
)@@G@@    JE,U      A0,MODNUL TD010   . SKIP IF NULL ARG    @E@@@@          PIHT
)@@G@@KRITE   TD999             . GET THE ARGUMENT    @E@]@@          LA      HU
)@@G@@  A0,,X7            . GET THE TDATE$ WORD @F@]@@          JNZ       A0,$HV
)@@G@@+2            . SKIP TDATE$ IF NONZERO ARG@E@@@#          L         A0,,HW
)@@G@@X7            . GET THE ARGUMENT    @D@@@]          J         TD020     HX
)@@G@@        . SKIP ER TDATE$@E@@@@TD010     ER        TDATE$            . GEHY
)@@G@@T TODAY'S DATE    @F@]@@          LA        A1,VDFS+SFN       . GET THE HZ
)@@G@@FUNCTION SUBCODE  @F@@@]TD020     LA        A1,VDFS+SFN       . GET THE IA
)@@G@@FUNCTION SUBCODE  @D@@@@          LA        A5,PCL('FUNCTION CALL ERROR.IB
)@@G@@')    @E@@@@          JZ        A1,TD999          . CHECK FOR RANGE     IC
)@@G@@@B@@@@          JLE,U     A1,TDMAXI TD999   .   @G@@@@          CALL    ID
)@@G@@  M$XVARTD          . PERFORM THE EDITING FUNCTION    @E@@@@          JNIE
)@@G@@Z       A5,TD999          . CHECK FOR ERRORS    @E@@@@          DS      IF
)@@G@@  A0,VD+SLA         . POST THE RESULT     @#@@@@TD999     RETURN  @[@@@@IG
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@          END     _@@@@@ SUBROUTINE ENTRY * * * *     @C@]@@IH

)@@G@@          $FDATA  @G@@@(M$FDBLANKS* '            'DL          . TWO WORDMS

)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@D/         M$DEF   @[@@@D.     @C@@@D. THIS ROUTINE IMPMX
)@@G@@LEMENTS THE INDEX FUNCTION.   @[@@@D.     @A@@@D.  INDEX(<TARGET STR>;<SMY
)@@G@@EARCH STR>) @[@@@D.     @B@@@D.  INDEX(<TARGET VECTOR>;<SEARCH VALUE>)  MZ
)@@G@@@[@@@D.     @ @@@D.  INDEX(<TABLE>;<SUBSCRIPT>) @[@@@D.     @G@@@D. THE NA
)@@G@@FIRST FORMAT, WITH STRING ARGUMENTS, COMPUTES A NUMERIC RESULT    @F@@@DNB
)@@G@@. EQUAL TO THE INDEX OF THE FIRST CHARACTER OF THE FIRST OCCURANCE@F@@@DNC
)@@G@@. OF <SEARCH STR> WITHIN <TARGET STR>.  IF "RINDEX", THEN THE LAST@ @@@DND
)@@G@@. OCCURANCE INDEX IS RETURNED.@[@@@D.     @F@@@D. THE SECOND FORMAT, WITNE
)@@G@@H NUMERIC ARGUMENTS, COMPUTES THE INDEX OF@F@@@D. THE FIRST OCCURANCE OFNF
)@@G@@ THE FIRST VALUE OF <SEARCH VALUE> WITHIN @F@@@D. <TARGET VECTOR>.  IF "NG
)@@G@@RINDEX", THEN THE LAST OCCURANCE INDEX IS @F@@@D. RETURNED.  <SEARCH VALNH
)@@G@@UE> MAY BE ONE OR MORE NUMERIC VALUES.    @[@@@D.     @F@@@D. THE THIRD NI
)@@G@@FORMAT, WITH A TABLE AND SUBSCRIPT ARGUMENTS, COMPUTES@G@@@D. THE ORDINANJ
)@@G@@L INDEX OF THE SUBSCRIPT WITHIN THE TABLE, IF IT EXISTS,    @F@@@D. OTHENK
)@@G@@RWISE, ZERO IS RETURNED.  THE SUBSCRIPTS ARE ORDERED WITHIN @F@@@D. THE NL
)@@G@@TABLE IN ASCENDING SEQUENCE BASED ON THE BINARY VALUE OF THE@G@@@D. SUBSNM
)@@G@@CRIPT (I.E., INTEGER SUBSCRIPTS WILL USUALLY PRECEDE ASCII STRING @C@@@DNN
)@@G@@. SUBSCRIPTS, EXCEPT FOR VERY LARGE VALUES).    @[@@@D.     @^@@@DM$FUNINO
)@@G@@NDEX* SUBROUTINE  @E@@@DINDREV    LOCAL                       . REVERSE NP
)@@G@@INDEX FLAG  @E@@@DINDLFT    LOCAL     2                 . LEFT ARG DESCRNQ
)@@G@@IPTOR @E@@@DINDRIT    LOCAL     2                 . RITE ARG DESCRIPTOR NR
)@@G@@@^@@@DINDA0A1   LOCAL     2   @#@@@DINDA4     LOCAL   @B@@@DINDR1     LONS
)@@G@@CAL     . TEMP SAVE SPACE     @F@@@D          LA        A0,VDFS+SFN     NT
)@@G@@  . GET THE FUNCTION SUBCODE  @F@@@D          SA        A0,INDREV       NU
)@@G@@  . POST REVERSE-INDEX FLAG   @E@@@D          ARGCHK    IND999 INDLFT INNV
)@@G@@DMSK 2 . PROCESS ARGS   @F@@@D          LA        A0,VDM+INDLFT     . GENW
)@@G@@T THE LEFT ARG MODE     @G@@@D          TNNUM     A0 IND100         . IFNX
)@@G@@ NUMERIC, DO NUMERIC INDEX    @F@@@D          JE,U      A0,MODTBL IND200NY
)@@G@@  . IF TABLE, DO TABLE INDEX  @[@@@D/.    @ @@@D.  INDEX(<STRING1>;<STRINZ
)@@G@@NG2>) @[@@@D.     @H@@@D. ALPHANUMERIC INDEX ROUTINE. FIND FIRST (OR LASOA
)@@G@@T, IF 'RINDEX') OCCURANCE     @ @@@D. OF <STRING2> IN <STRING1>.  @[@@@DOB
)@@G@@.     @H@@@D          CONVASC   IND999 INDLFT     . ENSURE THAT ALL STRIOC
)@@G@@NGS ARE ASCII     @B@@@D          CONVASC   IND999 INDRIT     .   @F@@@DOD
)@@G@@          LA        A0,VDA+INDLFT     . GET THE LEFT ARG ADDRESS  @F@@@DOE
)@@G@@          LR        R1,VDL+INDLFT     . GET THE LEFT ARG COUNT    @F@@@DOF
)@@G@@          LA        A1,M$XASL         . GET THE ASCII LOAD TABLE  @G@@@DOG
)@@G@@          LA,U      A4,0              . INITIALIZE THE INDEX COUNTER    OH
)@@G@@@H@F@D          DS        A0,INDA0A1        . SAVE THE POINTER VALUES INOI
)@@G@@TO LEFT ARG @B@F@D          S         A4,INDA4          .   @B@F@D      OJ
)@@G@@    S         R1,INDR1          .   @F@@@D          LX,U      X11,0     OK
)@@G@@        . CLEAR REVERSE-INDEX RESULT@E@@@G          J         IND015    OL
)@@G@@        . START THE SEARCH    @[@@@FIND010@F@F@DIND010    LR,U      R3,0OM
)@@G@@              . INITIALIZE CURRENT INDEX  @F@F@D          LA        A2,VON
)@@G@@DA+INDRIT     . GET THE RIGHT ARG ADDRESS @F@F@D          LR        R2,VOO
)@@G@@DL+INDRIT     . GET THE RIGHT ARG COUNT   @G@F@D          LA        A3,MOP
)@@G@@$ASTE         . SET CHAR INDEX FOR TEST TABLE   @E@@@D          DL      OQ
)@@G@@  A0,INDA0A1        . GET SAVED VALUES    @B@@@D          L         A4,IOR
)@@G@@NDA4          .   @B@@@D          L         R1,INDR1          .   @D@@@DOS
)@@G@@          EX        0,*A1             . GET THE CHAR  @E@E@D          DSOT
)@@G@@        AO,INDA0A1        . SAVE UPDATED VALUES @E@F@E          DS      OU
)@@G@@  A0,INDA0A1        . SAVE UPDATED VALUES @F@@@D          A,U       A4,1OV
)@@G@@              . ADJUST THE INDEX VALUE    @G@@@F          JNGD      R1,IOW
)@@G@@ND300         . YES, COUNT LEFT ARG CHARS TOO   @[@@@FIND015@F@G@F      OX
)@@G@@    LR,U      R3,0              . INITIALIZE CURRENT INDEX  @F@G@F      OY
)@@G@@    LA        A2,VDA+INDRIT     . GET THE RIGHT ARG ADDRESS @F@G@F      OZ
)@@G@@    LR        R2,VDL+INDRIT     . GET THE RIGHT ARG COUNT   @G@G@F      PA
)@@G@@    LA        A3,M$ASTE         . SET CHAR INDEX FOR TEST TABLE   @F@F@DPB
)@@G@@          S         A4,INDA4          . AND SAVE TH ENEW VALUE    @H@F@DPC
)@@G@@          JNGD      R1,IND300         . DECREMENT REMANINING REPEAT COUNPD
)@@G@@T     @B@F@D          S         R1,INDR1          /   @H@@@F          DSPE
)@@G@@        A0,INDA0A1        . SAVE THE POINTER VALUES INTO LEFT ARG @B@@@FPF
)@@G@@          S         A4,INDA4          .   @B@@@F          S         R1,IPG
)@@G@@NDR1          .   @F@@@G          LR,U      R3,0              . INITIALIPH
)@@G@@ZE CURRENT INDEX  @F@@@G          LA        A2,VDA+INDRIT     . GET THE PI
)@@G@@RIGHT ARG ADDRESS @F@@@G          LR        R2,VDL+INDRIT     . GET THE PJ
)@@G@@RIGHT ARG COUNT   @G@@@G          LA        A3,M$ASTE         . SET CHARPK
)@@G@@ INDEX FOR TEST TABLE   @G@@@DIND020    JNGD      R2,IND030         . ANPL
)@@G@@Y CHARS FROM RIGHT ARG LEFT?  @G@@@D          JNGD      R1,IND300       PM
)@@G@@  . YES, COUNT LEFT ARG CHARS TOO   @D@@@D          AA,U      A4,1      PN
)@@G@@        . BUMP THE INDEX@E@@@D          EX        0,*A1             . GEPO
)@@G@@T THE LEFT CHAR   @G@@@D          EX        0,*A3             . COMPARE PP
)@@G@@WITH THE RIGHT CHAR     @G@@@D          J         IND010            . NOPQ
)@@G@@T EQUAL - FIND NEXT SUBSTRING @F@@@D          TNZ       R3              PR
)@@G@@  . IS THERE A CURRENT INDEX? @D@@@D          LR        R3,A4           PS
)@@G@@  . NO, SET IT    @F@@@D          J         IND020            . COMPARE PT
)@@G@@THIS SUBSTRING    @[@@@D.     @H@@@DIND030    JEZ       INDREV IND310   PU
)@@G@@  . IF NOT REVERSE-INDEX, GO STASH RESULT @E@@@D          LX        X11,PV
)@@G@@R3            . SAVE CURRENT INDEX  @E@@@D          J         IND010    PW
)@@G@@        . FIND NEXT SUBSTRING @[@@@D/.    @E@@@D. NUMERIC INDEX. FIND FIPX
)@@G@@RST OCCURANCE OF RIGHT ARG VECTOR IN@D@@@D. LEFT ARG VECTOR. AUTOMATIC TPY
)@@G@@YPE CONVERSION IS DONE. @[@@@D.     @F@@@DIND100    LA        A1,VDM+INDPZ
)@@G@@LFT     . GET THE LEFT ARG MODE     @F@@@D          LA,U      A0,INDRIT QA
)@@G@@        . CONVERT TO LEFT ARG MODE  @D@@@D          CALL      M$CONVMODEQB
)@@G@@        . CONVERT IT    @B@@@D          JNZ       A5,IND999         .   QC
)@@G@@@E@@@D          LX        X9,VDA+INDLFT     . GET LEFTARG ADDRESS @C@@@DQD
)@@G@@          LXI,U     X9,1              . SET INCR@D@@@D          TNDBL   QE
)@@G@@  A0                . DP VALUE?     @C@@@D          LXI,U     X9,2      QF
)@@G@@        . YES     @F@@@D          LX        X7,X9             . SET UP RQG
)@@G@@IGHT ARG INDEX    @D@@@D          LXM       X7,VDA+INDRIT     . GET BASEQH
)@@G@@ ADDR @F@@@D          LX,U      X11,0             . CLEAR REVERSE-INDEX QI
)@@G@@RESULT@E@@@D          ANX,U     X9,1              . BACKUP INITIAL INDEXQJ
)@@G@@@E@@@D          LR        R1,VDL+INDLFT     . GET LEFT ARG LENGTH @G@@@DQK
)@@G@@IND110    LA        A1,X7             . RESET TO BEGINNING OF RIGHT ARG QL
)@@G@@@E@@@D          LR,U      R3,0              . CLEAR INDEX RESULT  @E@@@DQM
)@@G@@          LR        R2,VDL+INDRIT     . GET RIGHT ARG LENGTH@E@@@D      QN
)@@G@@    JNGD      R2,IND300         . COUNT FIRST VALUE   @E@@@D          DLQO
)@@G@@        A3,,*A1           . GET FIRST VALUE     @E@@@DIND120    SE      QP
)@@G@@  A3,1,*X9          . FIND FIRST VALUE    @E@@@D          J         IND3QQ
)@@G@@00            . QUIT IF NOT FOUND   @E@@@D          TNDBL     A0        QR
)@@G@@        . DOUBLE PRECISION?   @F@@@D          TNE       A4,0,X9         QS
)@@G@@  . YES, 2ND WORD UNEQUAL?    @F@@@D          J         $+2             QT
)@@G@@  . NO, CHECK FOLLOWING WORDS @E@@@D          J         IND120          QU
)@@G@@  . YES, KEEP SEARCHING @F@@@D          LA        A2,X9             . GEQV
)@@G@@T THE CURRENT INDEX     @E@@@D          ANU       A2,VDA+INDLFT     . COQW
)@@G@@MPUTE WORD INDEX-1@E@@@D          LA,U      A3,1,A3           . A3 = WORQX
)@@G@@D INDEX     @E@@@D          TNDBL     A0                . DOUBLE PRECISIQY
)@@G@@ON?   @E@@@D          SSL       A3,1              . A3 = ELEMENT INDEX  QZ
)@@G@@@D@@@D          LR,U      R3,,A3            . SAVE INDEX    @G@@@DIND130RA
)@@G@@    JNGD      R2,IND140         . IF NO MORE RIGHT ARG - FOUND IT @E@@@DRB
)@@G@@          DL        A3,0,*A1          . GET THE NEXT ELEMENT@E@@@D      RC
)@@G@@    TNDBL     A0                . DOUBLE PRECISION?   @F@@@D          TNRD
)@@G@@E       A4,2,A2           . YES, 2ND WORD UNEQUAL?    @F@@@D          TERE
)@@G@@        A3,1,*A2          . NO, 1ST WORD UNEQUAL?     @H@@@D          J RF
)@@G@@        IND110            . YES, NO FIND - TRY NEXT SUBSTRING     @F@@@DRG
)@@G@@          J         IND130            . NO, SO FAR ALL ARE EQUAL  @H@@@DRH
)@@G@@IND140    JEZ       INDREV IND310     . IF NOT REVERSE-INDEX, GO STASH RRI
)@@G@@ESULT @E@@@D          LX        X11,R3            . SAVE LATEST INDEX   RJ
)@@G@@@E@@@D          J         IND110            . FIND NEXT SUBSTR    @[@@@DRK
)@@G@@/.    @A@@@D. $INDEX( <TABLE> ; <SUBSCRIPT> )   @[@@@D.     @H@@@D. COMPRL
)@@G@@UTE ORDINAL INDEX OF A <SUBSCRIPT> IN A <TABLE> OR ZERO IF NO FIND.     RM
)@@G@@@[@@@D.     @F@@@DIND200    LA,U      A0,INDLFT         . GET THE TABLE RN
)@@G@@DESCR PTR   @G@@@D          LA,U      A1,INDRIT         . GET THE SUBSCRRO
)@@G@@IPT DESCR PTR     @E@@@D          CALL      M$SSINDEX         . COMPUTE RP
)@@G@@AN INDEX    @E@@@D          JNZ       A5,IND999         . CHECK FOR ERRORQ
)@@G@@RS    @D@@@D          LR,U      R3,,A2            . SAVE THE INDEX@H@@@DRR
)@@G@@          SZ        INDREV            . REVERSE-INDEX HERE IS MEANINGLESRS
)@@G@@S     @E@@@D          J         IND310            . GO SHOW SUCCESS     RT
)@@G@@@[@@@D.     @^@@@D. NO SUBSTRING FOUND    @[@@@D.     @D@@@DIND300    LRRU
)@@G@@,U      R3,0              . POST NO INDEX @[@@@D.     @C@@@D. IF NORMAL RV
)@@G@@INDEX, R3 HAS CURRENT INDEX OR ZER0;@D@@@D. IF REVERSE INDEX, X11 HAS CURW
)@@G@@RRENT INDEX OR ZERO.    @[@@@D.     @D@@@DIND310    TZ        INDREV    RX
)@@G@@        . REVERSE INDEX?@G@@@D          LR        R3,X11            . YERY
)@@G@@S, SAVE CURRENT INDEX HERE    @E@@@D          LA        A0,R3           RZ
)@@G@@  . GET RESULT ANSWER   @F@@@D          CALL      M$RESULTINT       . CRSA
)@@G@@EATE AN INTEGER RESULT  @C@@@D          JNZ       A5,IND999         . ERSB
)@@G@@ROR   @E@@@D          DS        A0,VD+SLA         . POST THE RESULT     SC
)@@G@@@#@@@DIND999    RETURN  @]@@@D          . @E@@@DINDMSK    ARGMSK    *MODSD
)@@G@@LST 'DAT'     . DEFINE ARG LIST     @]@@@D          . @ @@@DM$ASTE    + SE
)@@G@@        1,TE020   @[@@@D.     @C@@@DTE010     TNE,Q4    A5,,A2          SF
)@@G@@  . EQUAL?  @F@@@D          AA,U      A3,1              . YES, CAUSE SKISG
)@@G@@P ON RETURN @E@@@D          AA,U      A2,1              . INCREMENT WORDSH
)@@G@@ INDEX@G@@@D          LMJ       A3,,A3            . RETURN AND RESET CHASI
)@@G@@R INDEX     @ @@@DTE020     TE,Q1     A5,,A2    @ @@@D          TE,Q2   SJ
)@@G@@  A5,,A2    @ @@@D          TE,Q3     A5,,A2    @F@@@D          LMJ     SK
)@@G@@  A3,TE010          . BREAK OUT AND COMPARE LAST@]@@@D          . @#@@@DSL
)@@G@@          END     _@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@SM
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@SN
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/         M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THESE ROUTINES CSO
)@@G@@OMPILE THE LOOP CONTROL STATEMENTS.  THE FORMAT @^@@@@. FOR LOOP CONTROLSP
)@@G@@ IS : @[@@@@.     @#@@@@.         REPEAT  @^@@@@.           (BLOCK1)    SQ
)@@G@@@ @@@@.         WHILE <EXPRESSION>  @^@@@@.           (BLOCK2)    @#@@@@SR
)@@G@@.         ENDREP  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. BLOCK1 IS EXECUTED, THEN THE EXPRESS
)@@G@@SSION IS EVALUATED.  IF IT EVALUATES@F@@@@. TO A TRUE VALUE BLOCK2 IS EXST
)@@G@@ECUTED, FOLLOWED BY BLOCK1 AGAIN AD @F@@@@. NAUSEUM.  WHEN THE EXPRESSIOSU
)@@G@@N EVALUATES TO A FALSE VALUE CONTROL@C@@@@. PASSES TO THE STATEMENT FOLLSV
)@@G@@OWING THE ENDREP. @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE WHILE MAY BE REPLACED BY AN UNSW
)@@G@@TIL, WHICH HAS THE EFFECT OF  @F@@@@. REVERSING THE SENSE OF THE TEST, ISX
)@@G@@.E., EXIT WILL OCCUR WHEN THE @^@@@@. EXPRESSION GOES TRUE. @[@@@@.     SY
)@@G@@@ @@@@. COMPILE 'REPEAT' STATEMENT  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @^@]@@M$CMPRSZ
)@@G@@EPEAT* ROUTINE    @^@@@]M$CMPREPEAT* SUBROUTINE @E@@@@          PUSH    TA
)@@G@@  REP900            . PUSH DATA ONTO STACK@G@[@@          SDFOGA    M$OUTB
)@@G@@TPACKET       . GET ADDRESS OF 'REPEAT' IMAGE   @G@@@[          LA      TC
)@@G@@  A1,PSNWA+M$CMPPKT . GET ADDRESS OF 'REPEAT' IMAGE   @D@@@@          L TD
)@@G@@        A0,M$YLIN         . GET LINE #    @F@@@@          LXI,U     A0,MTE
)@@G@@SGREP         . SET STACK TYPE 'REPEAT'   @D@@@@          DS        A0,MTF
)@@G@@SSTAK         . STACK ENTRY   @D@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$CMPOUTPUT TG
)@@G@@  . OUTPUT IMAGE  @E@@@@          J         REP999            . RETURN TTH
)@@G@@O COMPILER  @G@@@@REP900    LA        A5,M$CPSOVR       . COMPILE TIME STI
)@@G@@TACK OVERFLOW     @#@@@@REP999    RETURN  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. COMPILE 'WTJ
)@@G@@HILE' AND 'UNTIL' STATEMENTS  @[@@@@.     @]@@@@M$CMPWHILE* @]@@@@M$CMPUTK
)@@G@@NTIL* @#@]@@          ROUTINE @^@@@]          SUBROUTINE    @G@@@@      TL
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,MSGREP         . IS STACKTOP REPEAT WITHOUT CONDN@B@@@@TM
)@@G@@          TE        A0,MSTYPE         .   @D@@@@          J         UNT9TN
)@@G@@10            . NO - ERROR    @F@@@@          PUSH      UNT900          TO
)@@G@@  . PUSH WHILE ONTO STACK     @G@[@@          SDFOGA    M$OUTPACKET     TP
)@@G@@  . GET ADDR OF 'WHILE' OR 'UNTIL'  @G@@@[          LA        A1,PSNWA+MTQ
)@@G@@$CMPPKT . GET ADDR OF 'WHILE' OR 'UNTIL'  @E@@@@          L         A0,MTR
)@@G@@$YLIN         . GET IMAGE NUMBER    @E@@@@          LXI,U     A0,MSGWHU TS
)@@G@@        . SET CONDITION SEEN  @E@@@@          DS        A0,MSSTAK       TT
)@@G@@  . SET IT ONTO STACK   @D@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$CMPOUTPUT   . OUTU
)@@G@@TPUT IMAGE  @D@@@@          J         UNT999            . AND RETURN    TV
)@@G@@@D@@@@UNT900    LA        A5,M$CPSOVR       . STACK OVERFLOW@ @@@@      TW
)@@G@@    J         UNT999    @F@@@@UNT910    LMJ       X11,M$ERRMSGCMP   . GETX
)@@G@@NERATE ERROR MESSAGE    @#@@@@UNT999    RETURN  @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. COMPTY
)@@G@@ILE 'ENDREP' STATEMENT  @[@@@@.     @^@]@@M$CMPENDREP* ROUTINE    @^@@@]TZ
)@@G@@M$CMPENDREP* SUBROUTINE @E@@@@ENRTMP    LOCAL     1                 . TEUA
)@@G@@MPORARY STORAGE   @F@@@#          L,U       A0,MSGREP         . GET TYPEUB
)@@G@@ OF CONDITION     @F@@@#          TNE       A0,MSTYPE         . IZS THE UC
)@@G@@TOP A REPEAT?     @C@@@#          J         ENR900            . YES.    UD
)@@G@@@F@@@@          L,U       A0,MSGWHU         . GET TYPE CONDITION SEEN   UE
)@@G@@@E@@@@          TE        A0,MSTYPE         . WAS CONDITION SEEN  @C@@@@UF
)@@G@@          J         ENR910            . NOPE    @G@@@@          L       UG
)@@G@@  A0,MSMSAD         . GET MASS STORAGE ADDR OF 'WHILE'@D@@@@          S UH
)@@G@@        A0,ENRTMP         . SAVE IT TEMP  @E@@@@          POP       1   UI
)@@G@@              . GET TO REPEAT ENTRY @F@@@@          L         A2,MSMSAD UJ
)@@G@@        . GET ADDRESS OF REPEAT     @F@@@@          S         A2,M$YADR UK
)@@G@@        . POINT 'LOOP' AT 'REPEAT'  @D@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$CMPOUL
)@@G@@UTPUT   . OUTPUT IMAGE  @G@[@@          SDFOGA    M$OUTPACKET       . GEUM
)@@G@@T ADDR OF IMAGE AFTER 'LOOP'  @G@@@[          LA        A1,PSNWA+M$CMPPKUN
)@@G@@T . GET ADDR OF IMAGE AFTER 'LOOP'  @E@@@@          L         A2,ENRTMP UO
)@@G@@        . GET ADDRESS OF WHILE@G@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$CMPUPDATE UP
)@@G@@  . POINT 'REPEAT' AFTER 'LOOP'     @D@@@@          POP       1         UQ
)@@G@@        . POP STACK     @E@@@@          J         ENR999            . REUR
)@@G@@TURN TO COMPILER  @]@@@#ENR900    . @E@^@#          POP       1         US
)@@G@@        . GET RID OF REPEAT   @F@@@^          SZ        MSTYPE          UT
)@@G@@  . CLEAR TYPE ON TOP OF STACK@F@@@#          L,U       A0,MSGWHU       UU
)@@G@@  . GET RIGHT ERROR MESSAGE   @F@@@@ENR910    LMJ       X11,M$ERRMSGCMP UV
)@@G@@  . GENERATE ERROR MESSAGE    @#@@@@ENR999    RETURN  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@UW
)@@G@@          LITS                        .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@MSGREP    'RUX
)@@G@@EPEAT&WHILE\UNTIL&'       .   @B@@@@MSGWHU    'WHILE\UNTIL&ENDREP&'     UY
)@@G@@    . @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          END                         .   _@@@@@UZ
)@@G@@@#@@@@.         ELSE    @^@@@@.           (BLOCK2)    @#@@@@.         ENVA
)@@G@@DIF   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@*[S@@[*SDFF*@^@@@@ 8)^@)^@)^@)^@)D*=C- C0)@[@@@@VB
