)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. THIS ROUTINE WILL RETURN A0 NONZERO IF THO
)@@G@@HERE IS MORE STUFF@F@@@@. ON THE CURRENT COMMAND LINE. DOES NOT AFFECT THP
)@@G@@HE CURRENT COLUMN @]@@@@. POSITION. @[@@@@.     @]@@@@M$MORECMD*  @#@[@@HQ
)@@G@@          ROUTINE @^@@@[          SUBROUTINE    @E@@@@          T$COLN  HR
)@@G@@                    . GET CURRENT POSITION@C@@@@          SA        A0,MHS
)@@G@@ORCOL         . SAVE IT @F@@@@          LA,U      A5,0              . ASHT
)@@G@@SUME NO MORE ON LINE    @E@@@@          T$NFIND   ' ' MOR010        . FIHU
)@@G@@ND A NON-BLANK    @G@@@@          LA,U      A5,1              . THERE'S HV
)@@G@@SOMETHING OUT THERE     @[@@@@MOR010@E@@@@          T$COL     MORCOL,,W HW
)@@G@@        . POST PREVIOUS COLUMN@ @@@@          LA        A0,A5     @#@@@@HX
)@@G@@          RETURN  @[@@@@.     @[@@@].     @F@@@].  THIS ROUTINE RETURNS HY
)@@G@@A0 NON-ZERO IF THERE IS MORE STUFF ON THE @G@@@]. CURRENT COMMAND LINE AHZ
)@@G@@S LONG AS IT ISN'T A COMMENT.   THIS ROUTINE    @G@@@]. SHOULD BE USED IIA
)@@G@@F A COMMENT SHOULD BE IGNORED.  M$MORECMD SHOULD BE   @G@@@]. USED IF THIB
)@@G@@E COMMENT SHOULD BE INCLUDED AS PART OF THE COMMAND ARGS.   @[@@@].     IC
)@@G@@@]@@@]M$MOREARGS* @^@@@]          SUBROUTINE    @E@@@]          T$COLN  ID
)@@G@@                    . GET CURRENT POSITION@C@@@]          SA        A0,MIE
)@@G@@ORCOL         . SAVE IT @F@@@]          LA,U      A5,0              . ASIF
)@@G@@SUME NO MORE ON LINE    @E@@@]          T$NFIND   ' ' MARG020       . FIIG
)@@G@@ND A NON-BLANK    @E@@@#          L,U       A3,,A3            . GET RID IH
)@@G@@OF ASCII    @G@@@]          TE,U      A3,'.'            . IS IT A  COMMEII
)@@G@@NT CHARACTER ?    @F@@@]          J         MARG010           . NO, RETUIJ
)@@G@@RN A0 NON-ZERO    @F@@@]          T$CHAR                      . GET THE IK
)@@G@@NEXT CHARACTER    @E@@@#          L,U       A3,,A3            . GET RID IL
)@@G@@OF ASCII    @D@@@]          TE,U      A3,' '            . IS IT A BLANK?IM
)@@G@@@]@@@]MARG010   . @E@@@]          L,U       A5,1              . GET NON-IN
)@@G@@ZERO FLAG   @]@@@]MARG020   . @E@@@]          T$COL     MORCOL,,W       IO
)@@G@@  . POST PREVIOUS COLUMN@ @@@]          LA        A0,A5     @#@@@]      IP
)@@G@@    RETURN  @[@@@].     @F@@@@MORCOL    LOCAL     1                 . PLIQ
)@@G@@ACE TO SAVE A COLUMN    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@          END                 IR
)@@G@@        . OF THIS LITTLE ELEMENT    _@@@@@@#@@@@PLS$UGETC$  @]'@@@PLS$UGIS
)@@G@@ETV$  @]'@@[PLS$UMVCC$  @#%@@]PLS$UMVCD$  @#%@@EPLS$UMVCV$  @#%@@@PLS$UMIT
)@@G@@VVC$  @#%@@#PLS$UMVVD$  *[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/         M$DEF   @[@@@@.     IU
)@@G@@@G@@@@. THIS ELEMENT CONTAINS THE ROUTINES TO SETUP FOR OPERATOR & FUNCTIV
)@@G@@ION   @B@@@@. ARGUMENT FETCHES AND RESULT STORES.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@IW
)@@G@@. PIKARG - PROC TO GENERATE THE CODE TO PICK UP AN ARG.     @[@@@@.     IX
)@@G@@@D@@@@.         PIKARG    <FETCH XREG>,<VD ADDR> <ERROR>    @[@@@@.     IY
)@@G@@@^@[@@P         PROC      2,11@^@@@[P         PROC      2,9 @#@@@@PIKARGIZ
)@@G@@*   NAME    @D@@@@X         EQU       P(1,1)            . THE FETCH REG JA
)@@G@@@F@@@@A         EQU       AF(P(1),2)        . THE DESCRIPTOR ADDRESS    JB
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA,U      A0,VD+A           . GET THE DESCRIPTOR ADDRESSJC
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$ITEMLENGTH  . COMPUTE WORDS IN DATA     JD
)@@G@@@D@@@@          JNZ       A5,AF(P(2),1)     . XFER ON ERRORS@D@@@@      JE
)@@G@@    LA        A1,VDM+A          . GET THE MODE  @F@@@@          LX      JF
)@@G@@  X,VDA+A           . GET THE FETCH ADDRESS     @G@[@@          LXI,U   JG
)@@G@@  X,1               . SET THE INCREMENT CORRECTLY     @E@[@@          TEJH
)@@G@@P,U     A1,DBLBIT         . DOUBLE PRECISION?   @E@[@@          LXI,U   JI
)@@G@@  X,2               . YES, SET IT RIGHT   @G@@@[          LXI       X,VMJJ
)@@G@@EWS,A1        . SET THE INCR WITH WORD SIZE     @D@@@@          LA      JK
)@@G@@  A2,VDL+A          . GET THE LENGTH@F@@@@          TNE,U     A2,1      JL
)@@G@@        . IS THERE ONLY ONE ITEM?   @I@@@@          LXI,U     X,0       JM
)@@G@@        . YES, KILL INCREMENT FOR SCALAR EXTENSION    @#@@@@          ENJN
)@@G@@D     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. M$PIKLEFT - SETUP FOR LEFT ARG FETCHING.@[@@@@JO
)@@G@@.     @^@@@@.  LMJ  X11,M$PIKLEFT   @#@@@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW @^@@@@.  A0 JP
)@@G@@= CORE LENGTH     @^@@@@.  A1 = LEFT ARG MODE   @^@@@@.  A2 = LEFT ARG LJQ
)@@G@@ENGTH @#@@@@.  X9 = (1,ADDR)  @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         PIKLEFT   <ERRJR
)@@G@@OR>   @[@@@@.     @#@#@@M$PIKLEFT* ROUTINE@^@@@#M$PIKLEFT* SUBROUTINE   JS
)@@G@@@E@@@@          PIKARG    X9,VD+SLA PKL999  . PICK THE ARG UP     @#@@@@JT
)@@G@@PKL999    RETURN  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. M$PIKRITE - ROUTINE TO SETUP FOR FJU
)@@G@@ETCHING THE RIGHT ARGUMENT.   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@.  LMJ  X11,M$PIKRITE   JV
)@@G@@@^@@@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @^@@@@.  A0 = CORE LENGTH     @^@@@@.  A1 JW
)@@G@@= RIGHT ARG MODE  @^@@@@.  A2 = RIGHT ARG LENGTH@#@@@@.  X7 = (1,ADDR)  JX
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         PIKRITE   <ERROR>   @[@@@@.     @#@#@@M$PIKRJY
)@@G@@ITE* ROUTINE@^@@@#M$PIKRITE* SUBROUTINE   @E@@@@          PIKARG    X7,VJZ
)@@G@@D+SRA PKR999  . PICK THE ARG UP     @#@@@@PKR999    RETURN  @[@@@@.     KA
)@@G@@@D@@@@. M$PIKVAL - ROUTINE TO SETUP FOR FETCHING A VALUE    @[@@@@.     KB
)@@G@@@A@@@@.  A0 = ADDR OF VALUE DESCRIPTOR    @^@@@@.  LMJ  X11,M$PIKVAL    KC
)@@G@@@^@@@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @^@@@@.  A0 = CORE LENGTH     @]@@@@.  A1 KD
)@@G@@= MODE@#@@@@.  A2 = LENGTH    @^@@@@.  A3 = (INCR,ADDR)     @[@@@@.     KE
)@@G@@@#@#@@M$PIKVAL* ROUTINE @^@@@#M$PIKVAL* SUBROUTINE    @E@@@@PKVDESC   LOKF
)@@G@@CAL     2                 . VALUE DESCRIPTOR    @F@@@@          DL      KG
)@@G@@  A1,VD,A0          . GET THE VALUE DESCRIPTOR  @C@@@@          DS      KH
)@@G@@  A1,PKVDESC        . POST IT @B@@@@          PIKARG    A3,PKVDESC PKV99KI
)@@G@@9 .   @#@@@@PKV999    RETURN  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. M$PUTANS - ROUTINE TO KJ
)@@G@@SETUP FOR STORING THE RESULT. @[@@@@.     @^@@@@.  A1 = RESULT MODE     KK
)@@G@@@^@@@@.  A2 = RESULT LENGTH   @^@@@@.  LMJ  X11,M$PUTANS    @^@@@@.  A5 KL
)@@G@@= ERROR PCW OR 0  @ @@@@.  A1 = (1,ADDR) OR RESULT    @ @@@@.  A2 = RESUKM
)@@G@@LT ITEM LENGTH    @B@@@@.  VD+SLA IS SETUP ALSO WITH RESULT INFO. @[@@@@KN
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@.         PUTANS  <ERROR> <MODE> <LENGTH> @[@@@@.     @#@#@@KO
)@@G@@M$PUTANS* ROUTINE @^@@@#M$PUTANS* SUBROUTINE    @F@@@@          SZ      KP
)@@G@@  VD+SLA            . CLEAR MODE WORD OF RESULT @E@@@@          SA      KQ
)@@G@@  A1,VDM+SLA        . POST RESULT MODE    @E@@@@          SA        A2,VKR
)@@G@@DL+SLA        . POST RESULT LENGTH  @E@@@^          L         A5,PUTITL KS
)@@G@@        . GET ERROR MESSAGE   @H@@@^          SSL       A2,18           KT
)@@G@@  . SEE IF LENGTH IS MORE THAN 18 BITS    @H@@@^          TZ        A2  KU
)@@G@@              . IF ZERO THEN LENGTH IS WITHIN RANGE   @F@@@^          J KV
)@@G@@        PUT999            . NOPE, EXIT WITH MESSAGE   @G@@@]          LAKW
)@@G@@        A0,VDCC+SOP       . GET SCANNED OPERATOR POSITION   @F@@@]      KX
)@@G@@    SA        A0,VDCC+SLA       . POST AS RESULT POSITION   @F@@@@      KY
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,VD+SLA         . NOW COMPUTE # WORDS NEEDED@B@@@@      KZ
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,M$ITEMLENGTH  .   @D@@@@          JNZ       A5,PUT999 LA
)@@G@@        . CHECK ERRORS  @E@]@@          TGET                        . GELB
)@@G@@T THAT MANY WORDS @E@]@@          JNZ       A5,PUT999         . CHECK ERLC
)@@G@@RORS AGAIN  @E@@@]          M$TGET    PUT999            . GET SOME TEMP LD
)@@G@@SPACE @E@@@@          LXI,U     A1,1              . GET THE INCREMENT   LE
)@@G@@@F@@@@          SA        A1,VDA+SLA        . POST THE RESULT ADDRESS   LF
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A2,VDL+SLA        . RETRIEVE RESULT LENGTH    LG
)@@G@@@#@@@@PUT999    RETURN  @[@@@@.     @C@@@^PUTITL    PCW       'RESULT LELH
)@@G@@NGTH TOO LONG'    @#@@@@          END     _@@@@@ISJ[8N@S:]C=#T2[8J]C[#8]LI
)@@G@@[8J[SC@CL@@BCSN@D^[8FBC]]CF@CL@@B]C@@)L[)J[SC@CL@KBCCN@D^[8FBS]]CF@CL@@BLJ
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@]/         M$DEF   @[@@@].     @G@@@]. THIS PROCEDURE ILK
)@@G@@S CALLED TO PERFORM THE REPLICATION OPERATOR (#).     @G@@@]. THE EXPRESLL
)@@G@@SION N # E RESULTS IN N COPIES OF E CATENATED WITH EACH     @G@@@]. OTHELM
)@@G@@R.  THE LENGTH OF THE RESULT IS THE PRODUCT OF N AND THE LENGTH   @E@@@]LN
)@@G@@. OF E.  THE TYPE OF THE RESULT IS THE SAME AS THAT OF E.   @[@@@].     LO
)@@G@@@^@@@]M$SEMREPLIC*       .    @#@^@]          ROUTINE @^@@@^          SULP
)@@G@@BROUTINE    @F@#@]DUPRCL    LOCAL                       . RIGHT ARG CORELQ
)@@G@@ LENGTH     @D@@@#DUPTMP    LOCAL     3                 . TEMPORARIES   LR
)@@G@@@F@@@]DUPCC     LOCAL                       . LEFT ARG VALUE: COPY COUNTLS
)@@G@@@E@#@]DUPLTP    LOCAL                       . LOAD TABLE POINTER  @[@@@]LT
)@@G@@.     @B@@@]. LEFTARG MUST BE INTEGER OF LENGTH ONE.  @[@@@].     @]@A@ LU
)@@G@@   SLJ TON$ @E@@@]          L         A0,VDM+SLA        . GET LEFTARG TYLV
)@@G@@PE    @E@@@]          L         A1,VDL+SLA        . GET LEFTARG LENGTH  LW
)@@G@@@F@@@]          L         A5,DUPLAE         . LEFTARG ERROR MESSAGE     LX
)@@G@@@E@@@]          TNE,U     A0,MODSIN         . MUST BE INTEGER     @D@@@]LY
)@@G@@          TE,U      A1,1              . LENGTH ONE    @E@@@]          J LZ
)@@G@@        DUP999            . OOPS - BAD LEFTARG  @D@@@]          L       MA
)@@G@@  A1,VDA+SLA        . PICKUP LEFTARG@D@@@]          L         A0,0,A1   MB
)@@G@@        . GET COPY COUNT@F@@@]          JN        A0,DUP999         . ERMC
)@@G@@ROR IF NOT POSITIVE     @C@@@]          SA        A0,DUPCC          . SAMD
)@@G@@VE IT @E@@@]          LA        A2,VDL+SRA        . GET THE ARG LENGTH  ME
)@@G@@@F@@@]          MSI       A2,A0             . COMPUTE THE NEW LENGTH    MF
)@@G@@@F@@@]          PUTANS    DUP999 VDM+SRA    . CREATE A RESULT SPACE     MG
)@@G@@@E@@@A          L         A4,A2             . COPY RESULT LENGTH  @E@@@]MH
)@@G@@          PUTITEM   DUP999 VD+SLA 0,,U . SETUP STASH REGS   @F@@@]      MI
)@@G@@    PIKITEM   DUP999 VD+SRA 0,,U VDL+SRA . SETUP FETCH REGS @E@@@]      MJ
)@@G@@    DS        A0,DUPTMP         . SAVE FETCH REGS     @B@@@]          SRMK
)@@G@@        R1,DUPTMP+2       .   @E@@@]          LR        R3,DUPCC        ML
)@@G@@  . GET COPY COUNT HERE @E@@@]          J         DUP020            . STMM
)@@G@@ART COPY LOOP     @E@@@]DUP010    DL        A0,DUPTMP         . RELOAD FMN
)@@G@@ETCH REGS   @A@@@]          LR        R1,DUPTMP+2     @D@@@]          CAMO
)@@G@@LL      M$ITEMCOPY        . COPY THE ITEM @F@@@]DUP020    JGD       R3,DMP
)@@G@@UP010         . KEEP GOING UNTIL DONE     @E@@@]          LA        A0,VMQ
)@@G@@DM+SLA        . GET RESULT MODE     @D@@@]          TNSTR     A0        MR
)@@G@@        . STRING RESULT?@E@@@]          CALL      M$BLANKWORD       . YEMS
)@@G@@S, CLEAN IT UP    @D@@@]          POP       2                 . POP THE MT
)@@G@@STACK @D@@@]          LA,U      A5,0              . NO ERRORS     @#@ @]MU
)@@G@@DUP999    RETURN  @[@@@ DUP999@^@A@           SLJ TOFF$ .   @#@@@       MV
)@@G@@    RETURN  @[@@@].     @B@@@]          LITS                        .   MW
)@@G@@@E@@@]DUPLAE    PCW       'LEFT ARG NOT SINGLE POSITIVE INTEGER.' @[@@@]MX
)@@G@@.     @B@@@]          END                         .   _@@@@@)@U[UK[@@^@@MY
)@@G@@;*)@@MC@-@@ /K@@@\:8)@@C;K)@@V;*)@@MC@-@@ /K@@@@C8@@[*/K@@@\%8)@[#AD@@@@MZ
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@ /         M$DEF   @[@@@ .     @G@@@ . M$READLINE - THINA
)@@G@@S ROUTINE WILL READ THE NEXT KEYBOARD INPUT LINE FROM @F@@@ .           NB
)@@G@@   THE USER AND RETURN THE NUMBER OF WORDS READ IN A0.@[@@@ .     @^@@@ NC
)@@G@@.  A0 = BUFFER ADDRESS  @^@@@ .  LMJ  X11,M$READLINE  @A@D@ .  A4 = 1 ONND
)@@G@@ EOF, ZERO OTHERWISE.   @B@@@D.  A4 = 1,2, OR 3 ON EOF, ZERO OTHERWISE. NE
)@@G@@@H@@@D.       1 ON SOFT EOF, 2 ON HARD EOF, 3 ON ATTEMPT TO READ AFTER HNF
)@@G@@ARD EOF     @^@@@ .  A0 = # WORDS READ.   @[@@@ .     @#@@@           ASNG
)@@G@@CII   @B@C@ PROMPT    EQU       '*':4:4:4         .   @ @C@ CPROMPT   EQNH
)@@G@@U       '?':4:4:4 @[@@@ .     @^@@@ M$READLINE* SUBROUTINE  @D@@@ READPKNI
)@@G@@    LOCAL     2                 . ATREAD$ PACKET@G@D@           JNEZ    NJ
)@@G@@  M$REOF READEOF    . IF FLAG SET, DON'T READ AGAIN   @G@@@D          JNNK
)@@G@@EZ      M$REOF READEOFA   . IF FLAG SET, DON'T READ AGAIN   @E@@@       NL
)@@G@@    LXI,U     A0,READEOF        . OUR OWN EOF RETURN  @F@@@           SANM
)@@G@@        A0,READPK+1       . POST READ PART OF PACKET  @E@@@           LANN
)@@G@@,U      A1,1              . GET NEW SCAN ORIGIN @C@@@           SA      NO
)@@G@@  A1,M$SCANORIGIN   . POST IT @D@@@           M$EOPENA  M$EPKT M$IMAGE  NP
)@@G@@  . OPEN EDITING  @D@@@C          M$EASCIN  1                 . ASCII INNQ
)@@G@@PUT   @D@@@           LA,U      A4,$CAS('*')      . GET THE PROMPT@E@@@ NR
)@@G@@          TZ        M$CALCFLAG        . IN 'EVAL' MODE?     @A@@@       NS
)@@G@@    LA,U      A4,$CAS('?')    @F@@@           LA,H2     A5,M$XQTMACRO   NT
)@@G@@  . GET ANY XQT'ING MACRO LINK@E@A@ READ010   E$CHAR    A4              NU
)@@G@@  . INSERT PROMPT CHAR  @E@@@AREAD010   E$CHAR    A4,,W             . INNV
)@@G@@SERT PROMPT CHAR  @H@@@           JZ        A5,READ020        . GET OUT NW
)@@G@@OF LOOP IF NO MORE MACROS     @C@@@           LA        A0,A5           NX
)@@G@@  . GET LINK@G@@@           LA        A5,MXNML,A0       . LINK TO NEXT (NY
)@@G@@IF ANY) MACRO     @G@@@           J         READ010           . A PROMPTNZ
)@@G@@ CHAR FOR EVERY MACRO   @F@@@ READ020   E$CHAR    4                 . INOA
)@@G@@SERT PRINT STOP CHAR    @H@@@           M$EAWX                      . GEOB
)@@G@@T ACCESS WORD AND CLOSE EDITING     @E@B@           SA        A0,READPK OC
)@@G@@        . POST PACKET ADDR    @E@@@B          SA        A5,READPK       OD
)@@G@@  . POST APRINT$ STUFF  @D@@@           ATREAD$   READPK            . REOE
)@@G@@AD THE IMAGE@D@B@           LA,U      A4,0              . CLEAR EOF     OF
)@@G@@@E@@@B          DSL       A4,72             . CLEAR EOF, ERR FLAGS@C@@@ OG
)@@G@@          J         READ999           . DONE    @D@@@ READEOF   LA,U    OH
)@@G@@  A4,1              . GET EOF FLAG  @G@@@D          TP        A0        OI
)@@G@@        . ER READ$ STATUS SAY HARD EOF?   @F@@@D          L,U       A4,2OJ
)@@G@@              . YES, SET FLAG ACCORDINGLY @]@@@DREADEOFA  . @H@@@D      OK
)@@G@@    L         A0,M$REOF         . GET THE FLAG AS OF PRIOR THE READ     OL
)@@G@@@I@@@D          TNE,U     A0,2              . IF IT WAS HARD, SET THE FLOM
)@@G@@AG THAT ANOTHE    @D@@@D          L,U       A4,3              . GET THE ON
)@@G@@FLAG  @H@@@           SA        A4,M$REOF         . POST FLAG SO WE DON'OO
)@@G@@T DO IT AGAIN     @E@@@           LA,U      A0,0              . FOR COMPOP
)@@G@@LETENESS    @C@@@ READ999   RETURN                      . ALL DONE@[@@@ OQ
)@@G@@.     @#@@@           END     _@@@@@^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)OR
)@@G@@^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@]/         M$DEF   @[@@@].     OS
)@@G@@@E@@@]. M$FUNQUERY - PERFORM A READ WITH OR WITHOUT A PROMPT.     @[@@@]OT
)@@G@@.     @A@@@].  QUERY(<PROMPT>)   OR   QUERY     @[@@@].     @G@@@]. THE OU
)@@G@@RESULT OF THIS FUNCTION IS THE ASCII STRING RETURNED IN RESPONSE  @B@@@]OV
)@@G@@. TO THE QUERY TO THE USER'S TERMINAL.    @[@@@].     @H@@@]. THE RESULTOW
)@@G@@ WILL BE AN INTEGER IF AN END-OF-FILE CONDITION IS ENCOUNTERED.   @G@@@]OX
)@@G@@. IN THIS CASE, A VALUE OF -1 WILL INDICATE A SO-CALLED 'SOFT' EOF, LIKEOY
)@@G@@@H@@@]. "@EOF", AND A VALUE OF -2 WILL INDICATE A 'HARD' EOF.  IF -2 IS OZ
)@@G@@RETURNED,   @A@@@]. DO NOT ATTEMPT TO READ AGAIN.     @[@@@].     @^@^@]PA
)@@G@@M$FUNQUERY* ROUTINE     @^@@@^M$FUNQUERY* SUBROUTINE  @E@@@]QRYPKT    LOPB
)@@G@@CAL     2                 . THE ATREAD$ PACKET  @E@ @]          LN      PC
)@@G@@  A0,M$REOF         . GET THE EOF FLAG    @E@@@           L        A0,M$PD
)@@G@@REOF         . GET THE EOF FLAG     @F@ @]          JNZ       A0,QRY020 PE
)@@G@@        . IF NONZERO, TAKE EOF EXIT @F@@@           JNZ       A0,QRY025 PF
)@@G@@        . IF NONZERO, TAKE EOF EXIT @F@@@]          LA        A0,VDM+SRAPG
)@@G@@        . GET THE RIGHT ARG MODE    @G@@@]          SZ        QRYPKT    PH
)@@G@@        . DEFAULT PROMPT IS NO PROMPT     @F@@@]          JE,U      A0,MPI
)@@G@@ODNUL QRY010  . IF NO ARGUMENT, NO PROMPT @E@@@]          CONVASC   QRY9PJ
)@@G@@99 VD+SRA     . ENSURE ARG IS ASCII @G@@@]          PIKRITE   QRY999    PK
)@@G@@        . SETUP FOR THE RIGHT ARG FETCH   @F@@@]          LR        R1,APL
)@@G@@2             . GET STRING LENGTH HERE    @E@@@]          LA        A0,XPM
)@@G@@7             . GET BASE ADDRESS    @E@@@]          LA        A1,M$XASL PN
)@@G@@        . GET LOAD TABLE INDEX@G@@@]          LA,U      A2,M$RESULTBUF  PO
)@@G@@  . GET PLACE TO STASH THE IMAGE    @F@@@]          LA        A3,M$XASS PP
)@@G@@        . GET STORE TABLE INDEX     @E@#@]          CALL      M$COPYITEMPQ
)@@G@@        . COPY THE STRING     @E@@@#          CALL      M$ITEMCOPY      PR
)@@G@@  . COPY THE STRING     @E@@@]          LA,U      A5,4              . GEPS
)@@G@@T PRINT STOP CHAR @E@@@]          EX        0,*A3             . STASH THPT
)@@G@@E PRINT STOP@E@@@]          CALL      M$BLANKWORD       . FINISH UP THE PU
)@@G@@STRING@G@@@]          ANU,U     A0,M$RESULTBUF    . COMPUTE # OF WORDS IPV
)@@G@@N THE IMAGE @F@@@]          LA,U      A0,M$RESULTBUF    . GET THE STRINGPW
)@@G@@ ADDRESS    @G@@@]          LXI,U     A0,0100,A1        . CREATE THE PRIPX
)@@G@@NT CONTROL WORD   @H@@@]          SA        A0,QRYPKT         . POST THEPY
)@@G@@ PCW IN THE ATREAD$ PACKET    @H@@@]QRY010    LA        A0,(QRY020,M$RESPZ
)@@G@@ULTBUF) . GET THE AREAD$ CONTROL WORD     @F@@@]          SA        A0,QQA
)@@G@@RYPKT+1       . POST IT IN THE PACKET     @F@@@]          LA,U      A0,QQB
)@@G@@RYPKT         . GET THE PACKET ADDRESS    @E@@@]          ER        ATREQC
)@@G@@AD$           . DO A TYPE AND READ  @G@@@]          LSSL      A0,2      QD
)@@G@@        . COMPUTE THE ASCII CHAR COUNT    @F@@@]          LA,U      A1,,QE
)@@G@@A0            . SET AS MAX CHAR COUNT     @F@@@]          LA,U      A0,MQF
)@@G@@$RESULTBUF    . GET THE BUFFER ADDRESS    @F@@@]          CALL      M$REQG
)@@G@@SULTASC       . SETUP THE ASCII RESULT    @ @@@]          JNZ       A5,QQH
)@@G@@RY999 @E@@@]          J         QRY040            . GO STORE RESULT     QI
)@@G@@@]@@@]          . @A@@@]          .         EOF ON READ     @]@@@]      QJ
)@@G@@    . @E@ @]QRY020    LN,U      A1,1              . ASSUME 'SOFT' EOF   QK
)@@G@@@E@@@ QRY020    L,U       A1,1              . ASSUME 'SOFT' EOF   @C@ @]QL
)@@G@@          JP        A0,QRY030         . TRUE?   @C@@@           TP      QM
)@@G@@  A0                . TRUE?   @E@@@           L,U       A1,2            QN
)@@G@@  . GET HARD EOPF FLAG  @]@@@ QRY025    . @E@@@           L         A0,MQO
)@@G@@$REOF         . GET THE EOF FLAG    @F@@@           TNE,U     A0,2      QP
)@@G@@        . IS IT HARD EOF ALREADY?   @F@@@           L,U       A1,3      QQ
)@@G@@        . GET READ AFTER EOF FLAG   @H@@@           TE,U      A1,1      QR
)@@G@@        . SET FLAG FROM QUERY FOR HARD ONLY     @F@@@           S       QS
)@@G@@  A1,M$REOF         . POST EOF ON FILE FLAG     @G@ @]          SN      QT
)@@G@@  A1,M$REOF         . NO, POST FLAG FOR 'HARD' EOF    @G@ @]          LNQU
)@@G@@,U      A1,2              . GET THE FLAG RESULT FOR HARD EOF@E@ @]QRY030QV
)@@G@@    LA        A0,A1             . GET THE EOF FLAG    @E@A@ QRY030    LNQW
)@@G@@        A0,M$REOF         . GET THE EOF FLAG    @E@@@A          LN      QX
)@@G@@  A0,A1             . GET THE EOF FLAG    @F@@@]          CALL      M$REQY
)@@G@@SULTINT       . CREATE AN INTEGER RESULT  @ @@@]          JNZ       A5,QQZ
)@@G@@RY999 @E@@@]QRY040    DS        A0,VD+SLA         . POST THE RESULT     RA
)@@G@@@C@@@]QRY999    RETURN                      . ALL DONE@]@@@]          . RB
)@@G@@@#@@@]          END     _@@@@@@@@QTK[@@@@@@@[QM[@@@QTJ[@@@@@@@[QM^@@@QTIRC
)@@G@@[@@@@@@@[QMB@@@PL?@@@PKB*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@ /         M$DEF   @[@@@ .     RD
)@@G@@@D@@@ . THIS IS THE MAIN DRIVER LOOP FOR THE MACRO PACKAGE. @G@@@ . CALLRE
)@@G@@ THIS ROUTINE TO FETCH, EXECUTE, FETCH, EXECUTE, ETC. COMMANDS;   @G@@@ RF
)@@G@@. A RETURN IS MADE UPON AN EOF RETURN TO A READ, OR UPON AN ERROR WHEN  RG
)@@G@@@^@@@ . M$ERREXIT IS NONZERO. @[@@@ .     @]@@@ M$DRIVER*   @E@@@       RH
)@@G@@    SX,H2     X11,M$DRIVERRTN   . SAVE FOR ERRORS     @G@@@           SPRI
)@@G@@INIT                      . INITIALIZE THE STACK POINTER    @F@@@ DRI010RJ
)@@G@@    CALL      M$FETCH           . FETCH THE NEXT INPUT IMAGE@E@@@       RK
)@@G@@    JNZ       A5,DRI900         . CHECK FOR ERRORS    @B@C@B  TNE,U A4,3RL
)@@G@@        . IF HARD, THEN SNOOPY@B@D@C  TNE,U A4,2        . IF HARD, THEN RM
)@@G@@SNOOPY@]@D@B  SLJ TON$  @E@@@           JE,U      A4,3 DRI999         . RN
)@@G@@IF EOF, EXIT NOW  @G@@@           JNEZ      M$COMLINE DRI030  . IF MACRORO
)@@G@@ COMMAND, DON'T REMEMBER@F@@@           SA        A0,DRIIAW         . SARP
)@@G@@VE IMAGE ACCESS WORD    @E@@@           TNE,U     A0,,A0            . ZERQ
)@@G@@RO LENGTH IMAGE?  @F@@@           LXI,U     A0,1              . YES, SETRR
)@@G@@ DEFAULT LENGTH   @F@@@           QPUSH     M$HISTORYQ A0     . PLACE ONRS
)@@G@@TO HISTORY QUEUE  @C@@@           JNZ       A5,DRI900         . BAD NEWSRT
)@@G@@@G@@@           L         A0,M$COMCNT       . GET COUNT OF COMMANDS SO FRU
)@@G@@AR    @D@@@           AA,U      A0,1              . BUMP IT BY ONE@E@@@ RV
)@@G@@          S         A0,M$COMCNT       . SAVE THE NEW VALUE  @F@@@       RW
)@@G@@    LA        A0,DRIIAW         . RESTORE IMAGE ACCESS WORD @E@@@ DRI030RX
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,M$EXECUTE     . EXECUTE THE COMMAND @E@@@           JNRY
)@@G@@Z       A5,DRI900         . COUGH ON ERRORS     @F@@@           JNZ     RZ
)@@G@@  A0,DRI999         . IF ABORT FLAG SET, QUIT   @G@@@           LA,U    SA
)@@G@@  A0,M$HISTORYQ     . GET THE HISTORY QUEUE HEADER    @G@@@           LASB
)@@G@@        A1,QHCOUNT        . GET THE # OF IMAGES ON THE QUEUE@G@@@       SC
)@@G@@    JZ        A1,DRI010         . IF NO HISTORY, GO BACK TO INPUT @H@@@ SD
)@@G@@          JGE       A1,M$HISTLIMIT DRI010 . IF NOT OVER THE LIMIT, LOOP SE
)@@G@@BACK  @F@@@           QPULL                       . PULL OFF THE OLDEST SF
)@@G@@IMAGE @F@@@           JZ        A1,DRIBHQ         . DETECT BAD HISTORY QSG
)@@G@@UEUE  @E@@@           LA,U      A0,0,A1           . RELEASE THE IMAGE   SH
)@@G@@@B@@@           M$PREL                      .   @E@@@           JZ      SI
)@@G@@  A5,DRI010         . IF OK, LOOP BACK    @D@@@ DRI900    LA        A0,ASJ
)@@G@@5             . GET ERROR PCW @D@@@           TE,U      A0,,A0          SK
)@@G@@  . H1 CLEAR?     @G@@@           LMJ       X11,M$ERRMSGPRT   . NO, PRINSL
)@@G@@T THE ERROR MESSAGE     @H@@@           JEZ       M$ERREXIT DRI010  . IFSM
)@@G@@ ERROR-EXIT FLAG CLEAR, KEEP GOING  @F@@@ DRI999    LX        X11,M$DRIVSN
)@@G@@ERRTN   . RECOVER OUR RETURN ADDRESS@C@@@           J         0,X11     SO
)@@G@@        . RETURN  @[@@@ .     @C@@@ DRIBHQ    PRINT     'BAD HISTORY IMASP
)@@G@@GE QUEUE!'  @E@@@           SA        A0,M$ABORT        . POST ABORT FLASQ
)@@G@@G     @ @@@           J         DRI999    @[@@@ .     @E@@@ DRIIAW    VASR
)@@G@@R       1                 . IMAGE ACCESS WORD   @[@@@ .     @#@@@       SS
)@@G@@    END     _@@@@@^@)^@)*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@A/         M$DEF   @[@@@A.     ST
)@@G@@@D@@@A. M$FETCH - ROUTINE TO FETCH THE NEXT INPUT IMAGE.    @[@@@A.     SU
)@@G@@@^@@@A.  LMJ  X11,M$FETCH     @C@@@A.  A4 = 1 = EOF (NO MORE IMAGES); ZESV
)@@G@@RO OTHERWISE@B@@@A.  A0 = (LENGTH, ADDRESS) OF NEXT IMAGE   @[@@@A.     SW
)@@G@@@F@@@A. THE NEXT INPUT IMAGE NORMALLY COMES FROM THE USER KEYBOARD; IF ASX
)@@G@@@F@@@A. MACRO IS ACTIVE, HOWEVER, READ THE NEXT IMAGE FROM THE MACRO ANDSY
)@@G@@@G@@@A. RETURN IT AS THE COMMAND.  IF THE MACRO IS SUSPENDED, THEN READ SZ
)@@G@@A     @G@@@A. COMMAND FROM THE USER: IF THE COMMAND IS A BLANK LINE, EXETA
)@@G@@CUTE THE    @F@@@A. NEXT COMMAND IN THE MACRO, OTHERWISE EXECUTE THE USETB
)@@G@@R COMMAND.  @[@@@A.     @^@@@AM$FETCH*  SUBROUTINE    @F@@@AFETLEN    LOTC
)@@G@@CAL                       . # WORDS IN FETCHED IMAGE  @F@B@A          TRTD
)@@G@@AL                        . RELEASE ALL TEMP SPACE    @F@@@B          M$TE
)@@G@@TRAL                      . RELEASE ALL TEMP SPACE    @E@@@A          SZTF
)@@G@@        M$ABORT           . CLEAR ABORT FLAG    @D@@@A          L       TG
)@@G@@  A5,M$BREAK        . GET ERROR FLAG@E@@@A          SZ        M$BREAK   TH
)@@G@@        . CLEAR IT IF SET     @F@@@A          SZ        M$SCANORIGIN    TI
)@@G@@  . RESET THE COMMAND ORIGIN  @F@@@A          SZ        M$ERRECHO       TJ
)@@G@@  . RESET THE ERROR ECHO FLAG @E@@@A          JNZ       A5,FET999       TK
)@@G@@  . IF ERROR SAY SO     @[@@@A.     @A@@@A. LOOP UP TO HERE ON EOF IN MATL
)@@G@@CRO   @[@@@A.     @H@@@AFET010    LA        A0,(0100,M$READBUFFER) . RESTM
)@@G@@ET PRINT FLAG & ACCESS WORD   @C@@@A          SA        A0,M$PRTAXW     TN
)@@G@@  . POST IT @E@@@A          LA,U      A0,M$INPUTQ       . GET THE INPUT TO
)@@G@@QUEUE @H@@@A          JNEZ      QHCOUNT FET030    . IF IMAGE ALREADY ON TP
)@@G@@QUEUE, GO GET IT  @F@@@A          L,H2      A0,M$XQTMACRO     . IS THERETQ
)@@G@@ A CURRENT MACRO  @F@@@A          JZ        A0,FET040         . IF NOT PTR
)@@G@@ROMPT THE USER    @C@@@A          LA        A1,MXFB,A0        . GET FLAGTS
)@@G@@@D@@@A          TOP,U     A1,MXBSUS         . SUSPENDED?    @E@@@A      TT
)@@G@@    J         FET020            . NO - GO READ CARD   @G@@@A          LATU
)@@G@@        A1,MXSSC,A0       . GET THE SUSPENDED SKIP COUNT    @H@@@A      TV
)@@G@@    JZ        A1,FET040         . IF NO SKIP COUNT, GO READ FROM USER   TW
)@@G@@@E@@@A          AN,U      A1,1              . DECREMENT THE COUNT @E@@@ATX
)@@G@@          SA        A1,MXSSC,A0       . POST THE NEW COUNT  @[@@@A.     TY
)@@G@@@^@@@A. READ IMAGE FROM MACRO @[@@@A.     @E@@@AFET020    CALL      M$RETZ
)@@G@@ADMACRO       . READ NEXT IMAGE     @ @@@A          JNZ       A5,FET999 UA
)@@G@@@E@@@A          JNZ       A4,FET010         . ON EOF, START OVER  @E@@@AUB
)@@G@@          J         FET050            . GO JOIN COMMON CODE @[@@@A.     UC
)@@G@@@A@@@A. GET NEXT IMAGE FROM INPUT QUEUE   @[@@@A.     @F@@@AFET030    QPUD
)@@G@@OP                        . POP THE NEXT INPUT IMAGE  @G@@@A          JZUE
)@@G@@        A1,FET900         . IF NO IMAGE, QUEUE IS IN ERROR  @E@@@A      UF
)@@G@@    LA        A0,QRLINE,A1      . GET ANY LINE NUMBER @C@@@A          SAUG
)@@G@@        A0,M$COMLINE      . POST IT @E@@@A          LA        A0,M$RBX  UH
)@@G@@        . GET READBUFFER INDEX@H@@@A          MOVE      *A0 A3,QRBUF,A1,UI
)@@G@@U 0,A2,U . MOVE THE IMAGE TO M$READBUFFER @E@@@A          SA        A2,FUJ
)@@G@@ETLEN         . SAVE THE LENGTH     @F@B@A          PREL      0,A1,U    UK
)@@G@@        . RELEASE THE INPUT RECORD  @F@@@B          M$PREL    FET999 0,AUL
)@@G@@1,U     . RELEASE THE INPUT RECORD  @ @B@A          JNZ       A5,FET999 UM
)@@G@@@F@@@A          LA        A0,FETLEN         . RECOVER THE IMAGE LENGTH  UN
)@@G@@@F@@@A          J         FET050            . GO SUBSTITUTE THE IMAGE   UO
)@@G@@@[@@@A.     @B@@@A. READ THE NEXT IMAGE FROM THE KEYBOARD   @[@@@A.     UP
)@@G@@@D@C@AFET040    JNEZ      M$REOF FET990     . IF EOF, QUIT  @D@@@CFET040UQ
)@@G@@    JNEZ      M$REOF FET995     . IF EOF, QUIT  @E@@@A          SZ      UR
)@@G@@  M$COMLINE         . ZERO THE LINE NUMBER@H@@@A          LA        A3,MUS
)@@G@@$KBDINPUT     . GET THE KEYBOARD INPUT ROUTINE ADDR   @E@@@C          L,UT
)@@G@@U       A4,1              . PRETEND A SOFT EOF  @G@@@A          JZ      UU
)@@G@@  A3,FET990         . IF NONE, WE JUST GOT AN EOF     @G@@@A          LAUV
)@@G@@,U      A0,M$READBUFFER   . PASS THE INPUT BUFFER ADDRESS   @E@@@A      UW
)@@G@@    CALL      0,A3              . CALL INPUT ROUTINE  @D@@@A          JNUX
)@@G@@Z       A4,FET990         . CHECK FOR EOFS@G@@@A          TZ        M$XQUY
)@@G@@TMACRO        . IS THERE A MACRO EXECUTING?     @H@@@A          JZ      UZ
)@@G@@  A0,FET020         . YES, BLANK LINE MEANS EXECUTE ONE     @[@@@A.     VA
)@@G@@@D@@@A. A0 = IMAGE LENGTH; M$READBUFFER CONTAINS THE IMAGE. @[@@@A.     VB
)@@G@@@H@@@AFET050    SA,S3     A0,M$PRTAXW       . POST LENGTH FOR POSSIBLE DVC
)@@G@@IAGNOSTIC   @F@@@A          CALL      M$CALLSUBST       . SUBSTITUTE IN VD
)@@G@@THE IMAGE   @B@@@A          JNZ       A5,FET999         .   @I@@@A      VE
)@@G@@    SA,S3     A0,M$PRTAXW       . POST THE LENGTH FOR POSSIBLE DIAGNOSTIVF
)@@G@@C     @F@@@A          SA        A0,FETLEN         . AND SAVE HERE AS WELVG
)@@G@@L     @F@@@A          JEZ       M$COMLINE FET070  . SKIP IF KEYBOARD COMVH
)@@G@@MAND  @F@@@A          LA        A0,M$XQTMACRO     . GET THE CURRENT MACRVI
)@@G@@O LINK@E@@@A          LA        A1,MXFB,A0        . GET ANY FLAG BITS   VJ
)@@G@@@G@@@A          TNZ       MXSSC,A0          . IS THERE A SUSPENDED SKIP VK
)@@G@@COUNT?@E@@@A          TOP,U     A1,MXBSUS         . NO, IS IT SUSPENDED?VL
)@@G@@@D@@@A          TEP,U     A1,MXBTRA         . OR TRACED?    @F@@@A      VM
)@@G@@    J         FET060            . YES, GO PRINT THE COMMAND @F@@@A      VN
)@@G@@    TZ        M$TRACE           . IS GLOBAL TRACE FLAG SET? @F@@@AFET060VO
)@@G@@    CALL      M$PRTCOM          . YES, PRINT THE COMMAND    @F@@@AFET070VP
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,M$READBUFFER   . RETURN AN ACCESS WORD     @E@@@A      VQ
)@@G@@    LXI       A0,FETLEN         . LENGTH OF THE IMAGE @D@@@A          LAVR
)@@G@@,U      A5,0              . POST NO ERRORS@C@@@A          J         FET9VS
)@@G@@99            . ALL DONE@[@@@A.     @E@@@A. ERROR IN INPUT QUEUE; CLEAR VT
)@@G@@IT AND RETURN ERROR MESSAGE   @[@@@A.     @F@@@AFET900    LA        A5,PVU
)@@G@@CL('INPUT QUEUE HEADER IS IN ERROR!')     @E@@@A          SA        A5,MVV
)@@G@@$ABORT        . POST THE ABORT FLAG @C@@@A          J         FET999    VW
)@@G@@        . DONE    @[@@@A.     @^@@@A. EOF ON M$READLINE     @[@@@A.     VX
)@@G@@@F@C@AFET990    LA,U      A0,0              . RETURN ZERO ACCESS WORD   VY
)@@G@@@[@@@CFET990@E@E@D          L         A0,M$REOF         . GET THE EOF FLVZ
)@@G@@AG    @F@E@D          TNE,U     A0,2              . IF ALREADY READ EOF.WA
)@@G@@..    @D@E@D          L,U       A4,3              . SET OTHER FLAG@D@C@AWB
)@@G@@          LA,U      A4,1              . GET EOF FLAG  @F@@@A          SAWC
)@@G@@        A4,M$REOF         . POST THE READ EOF FLAG    @E@@@A          LAWD
)@@G@@,U      A5,0              . NO REAL ERROR THOUGH@]@@@CFET995    . @E@@@EWE
)@@G@@          L         A0,M$REOF         . GET THE EOF FLAG    @F@@@E      WF
)@@G@@    TNE,U     A0,2              . IF ALREADY READ EOF...    @E@@@E      WG
)@@G@@    A,U       A0,1              . SET M$REOF TO 3     @B@@@E          S WH
)@@G@@        A0,M$REOF         .   @F@@@C          LA,U      A0,0            WI
)@@G@@  . RETURN ZERO ACCESS WORD   @F@@@AFET999    LA        A4,M$REOF       WJ
)@@G@@  . LOAD THE READ EOF FLAG    @#@@@A          RETURN  @[@@@A.     @B@@@AWK
)@@G@@          END                         .   _@@@@@ K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K%WL

)@@G@@@A@[@@^T0G-0 -!^[!^-0IL\GT3 -!^-0IL\GT3^@)@A@@@[C[0G-0 -!^[!^-0IL\GT3 -!WR
)@@G@@^-0IL\GT3^@)@^@[@@^T!GD3H*)H*=I[2H9<IS)^@)@^@@@[C[!GD3H*)H*=I[2H9<IS)^@)WS
)@@G@@@#@[@@^T!GD3H*)H*=G->G0)@#@@@[C[!GD3H*)H*=G->G0)@^@@@[C[!GD3H*)H*=GT\H1&WT
)@@G@@HD$^@)_@@@@@^@)^@)^@) 0)*[S@@@*SDFF*@^@@@@M$DEF*    PROC      *0  @ @@@@WU
)@@G@@          INCLUDE   'FUNCS'   @ @@@@          INCLUDE   'M$DEF'   @#@@@@WV
)@@G@@          $BRIEF  @#@@@@$(LCLITS) $LIT    @]@@@@$(LCINST)   @#@@@@      WW
)@@G@@    END     _@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@WX
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@WY
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@@        DEF                           .   @[@@@@.     WZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@. DEFINE FIELDS AND BITS FOR FIASG$ FAMILY OF SUBROUTINES.  @[@@@@XA
)@@G@@.     @A@@@@. FIELDS IN FITEM$ PACKET FIPKT$.   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@FINAMEXB
)@@G@@  EQUF    FIPKT$+0              . INTERNAL FILE NAME  @E@@@@FXFILE  EQUFXC
)@@G@@    FIPKT$+2              . EXTERNAL FILE NAME  @D@@@@FXQUAL  EQUF    FIXD
)@@G@@PKT$+4              . QUALIFIER     @D@@@@FXEQUP  EQUF    FIPKT$+6,,S1  XE
)@@G@@        . EQUIPMENT CODE@E@@@@FXFLAG  EQUF    FIPKT$+6,,S2          . PEXF
)@@G@@RMISSIONS FLAGS   @E@@@@FXFRCY  EQUF    FIPKT$+6,,S4          . RELATIVEXG
)@@G@@ F CYCLE    @G@@@@FXFCYC  EQUF    FIPKT$+6              . ABSOLUTE FCYCLXH
)@@G@@E (ACTUALLY T3)   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@. BITS FOR FXFLAG @[@@@@.     @E@@@@XI
)@@G@@FXBXCL  EQU     040                   . HAVE EXCLUSIVE USE  @E@@@@FXBRKNXJ
)@@G@@  EQU     020                   . READ KEY NEEDED     @E@@@@FXBWKN  EQU XK
)@@G@@    010                   . WRITE KEY NEEDED    @D@@@@FXBWIN  EQU     00XL
)@@G@@4                   . WRITE INHIBIT @D@@@@FXBRIN  EQU     002           XM
)@@G@@        . READ INHIBIT  @C@@@@FXBWAD  EQU     001                   . WAXN
)@@G@@D FILE@[@@@@.     @B@@@@. DEFINE BITS PASSED BY USER IN UPPER A0. @[@@@@XO
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@FIUFOR  EQU     001                   . USE NAME FORCED     XP
)@@G@@@F@@@@FIUGIV  EQU     002                   . USE NAME PASSED IN A1-A2  XQ
)@@G@@@G@@@@FIUXCL  EQU     004                   . USER REQUIRES EXCLUSIVE USXR
)@@G@@E     @G@@@@FIUPRD  EQU     010                   . USER REQUIRES READ PXS
)@@G@@ERMISSION   @G@@@@FIUPWR  EQU     020                   . USER REQUIRES XT
)@@G@@WRITE PERMISSION  @F@@@@FIUOPT  EQU     040                   . USER PASXU
)@@G@@SES OPTIONS IN A3 @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. DEFINE FREE BITS.  NOTE THAT THESEXV
)@@G@@ DETERMINE THE ORDER    @F@@@@. OF THE FREE OPTIONS VECTOR, AND THAT SOMXW
)@@G@@E PEOPLE DO ODD/EVEN    @ @@@@. TESTS TO TEST FOR FIFUSE.   @[@@@@.     XX
)@@G@@@D@@@@FIFUSE  EQU     001                   . FREE USE NAME @D@@@@FIFASGXY
)@@G@@  EQU     002                   . FREE FILE     @E@@@@FIFXCL  EQU     00XZ
)@@G@@4                   . FREE EXCLUSIVE USE  @F@@@@FIFUIF  EQU     010     YA
)@@G@@              . FREE FILE THRU USENAME    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. THE ABOVE YB
)@@G@@ARE CALLED IN BY: FIDEF$.     @D@@@@. IF ARGUMENT IS GIVEN PRODUCE ELT$ YC
)@@G@@PACKET EQUFS.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC      *1              YD
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@FIDEF$*   NAME      0                 .   @D@@@@          ONYE
)@@G@@        P(1)>0            . IF ARG GIVEN  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@ELT$*     EQYF
)@@G@@UF      P(1,1),P(1,2)     . OFFSET,INDEX  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@FQL*      EQYG
)@@G@@UF      ELT$,,S1          . FILE QUALIFIER LENGTH     @E@@@@FNL*      EQYH
)@@G@@UF      ELT$,,S2          . FILE NAME LENGTH    @D@@@@FCL*      EQUF    YI
)@@G@@  ELT$,,S3          . F-CYCLE LENGTH@E@@@@RKL*      EQUF      ELT$,,S4  YJ
)@@G@@        . READ KEY LENGTH     @E@@@@WKL*      EQUF      ELT$,,S5        YK
)@@G@@  . WRITE KEY LENGTH    @F@@@@IQF*      EQUF      ELT$,,S6          . IMYL
)@@G@@PLIED QUALIFIER FLAG    @E@@@@ENL*      EQUF      ELT$+1,,S1        . ELYM
)@@G@@EMENT NAME LENGTH @F@@@@EVL*      EQUF      ELT$+1,,S2        . ELEMENT YN
)@@G@@VERSION LENGTH    @E@@@@ECL*      EQUF      ELT$+1,,S3        . ELEMENT YO
)@@G@@CYCLE LENGTH@G@@@@CFN*      EQUF      ELT$+1,,S4        . CONTINUATION FYP
)@@G@@ILE FIELD NUMBER  @G@@@@ECC*      EQUF      ELT$+1,,S5        . ELEMENT YQ
)@@G@@CYCLE SIGNAL CHARACTER  @E@@@@BEC*      EQUF      ELT$+1,,S6        . BIYR
)@@G@@NARY ELEMENT CYCLE@[@@@@.     @D@@@@FQUAL*    EQUF      ELT$+2          YS
)@@G@@  . FILE QUALIFIER@D@@@@FNAME*    EQUF      ELT$+4            . FILE NAMYT
)@@G@@E     @C@@@@FCYC*     EQUF      ELT$+6            . F-CYCLE @C@@@@RKEY* YU
)@@G@@    EQUF      ELT$+7            . READ KEY@D@@@@WKEY*     EQUF      ELT$YV
)@@G@@+8            . WRITE KEY     @D@@@@ENAME*    EQUF      ELT$+9          YW
)@@G@@  . ELEMENT NAME  @E@@@@EVER*     EQUF      ELT$+11           . ELEMENT YX
)@@G@@VERSION     @D@@@@ECYC*     EQUF      ELT$+13           . ELEMENT CYCLE YY
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@          OFF       P(1)>0            .   @B@@@@      YZ
)@@G@@    END                         .   @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. FIBIZA
)@@G@@TS WRITTEN BY MIKE MCAMIS     @A@@@@. FIASG  WRITTEN BY ALAN STEBBENS   ZB
)@@G@@@A@@@@. FIFREE WRITTEN BY BEN CRANSTON    @A@@@@. FIPFIL WRITTEN BY BEN ZC
)@@G@@CRANSTON    @A@@@@. FIPELT WRITTEN BY BEN CRANSTON    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ZD
)@@G@@. FIASG UPDATED TO WORK IN ASCII OR FIELDATA - 2/11/76, AKS.@[@@@@.     ZE
)@@G@@@A@@@@.         DEFINE BITS FOR FIASG$    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          DEZF
)@@G@@F                         .   @D@@@@FBIT      EQU       001             ZG
)@@G@@  . FORCE USE NAME@D@@@@UBIT      EQU       002               . USE NAMEZH
)@@G@@ GIVEN@D@@@@XBIT      EQU       004               . GET ASG,AX    @E@@@@ZI
)@@G@@RBIT      EQU       010               . GET READ PERMISSION @E@@@@WBIT  ZJ
)@@G@@    EQU       020               . GET WRITE PERMISSION@D@@@@OBIT      EQZK
)@@G@@U       040               . OPTIONS IN A3 @B@@@@FIBITS*   PROC      0,0 ZL
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@ZM
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@. TO ASSIGN A FILE@[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         FIASG,'OPTS' PZN
)@@G@@ACKET,BITS NAME   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC      *2              ZO
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@FIASG*    NAME                        .   @E@@@@N         EQZP
)@@G@@U       6+3*(' '=040)     . # OF BITS PER CHAR  @E@@@@C         EQU     ZQ
)@@G@@  077+0700*(N=9)    . SET PROPER MASK     @D@@@@          ON        P(1)ZR
)@@G@@>0            . ANY SPEC1 ?   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. FUNCTION TO GET BIT FOZS
)@@G@@R 'BITS' LETTER.  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@F         FUNC      *               ZT
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@PBIT*     NAME                        .   @E@@@@I         DOZU
)@@G@@      6 , DO M(0)*/(N-N*I)**C=F(1) , END F(2)   @D@@@@          END     ZV
)@@G@@  +0                . STRANGE BITS  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@M(0)      EQU     ZW
)@@G@@  P(1,2)+0D         . PICK UP MODE LETTERS@F@@@@B(0)      EQU       PBITZX
)@@G@@('F',1)+PBIT('U',2)+PBIT('X',4)+; F,U,X   @F@@@@                    PBITZY
)@@G@@('R',8)+PBIT('W',16)+PBIT('O',32)++; R,W,O@G@@@@                    2*(PZZ
)@@G@@(2)>0)+32*(P(0)>1) . FORCE BITS IF NECESSARY    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. NOW AA
)@@G@@GENERATE CODE     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          LA,U      A0,P(1,1)       AB
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          DO (B(0)=0)=0 , LXI,U A0,B(0) . @D@@@@          OFAC
)@@G@@F       P(1)>0            . ANY SPEC1 ?   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@ DO P(2)>0 ,AD
)@@G@@ DL A1,P(2,1),P(2,2)      . GET FILENAME  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          ONAE
)@@G@@        P(0)>1            . ANY OPTIONS ? @E@@@@          ON        (P(0AF
)@@G@@,1)=0)=0      . SOMETHING THERE?    @E@@@@          ON        N=9       AG
)@@G@@        . ASCII CHARACTERSET? @G@@@@F         FUNC      *               AH
)@@G@@  . ASCII TO FIELDATA MAPPING FUNC  @B@@@@ATOF*     NAME                AI
)@@G@@        .   @D@@@@        DO (F(1)=' ')++(F(1)=0) , END +0 . ABLANK     AJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          DO        (F(1)<'A')++(F(1)>'Z') , END +09) . BAD NEWS  AK
)@@G@@@F@@@@          END       F(1)-'A'+6        . CHANGE TO FIELDATA   A    AL
)@@G@@@E@@@@I         DO        6 ,;                MAXIMUM OF 6 CHARS  @I@@@@AM
)@@G@@P(0,1)    EQU       (P(0,1)**-(C*/(I*9-9)))+ATOF(P(0,1)*/(9-9*I)**C)*/(IAN
)@@G@@*6-6) .     @E@@@@          OFF       N=9               . ASCII CHARACTEAO
)@@G@@RSET? @G@@@@I DO 6 , DO P(0,1)**C*/30=0 ,P(0,1) EQU P(0,1)*/6+5 . FILL TAP
)@@G@@HE FIELDATA @F@@@@G         FORM      36                . WE WANT ONLY OAQ
)@@G@@NE WORD     @D@@@@          L         A3,(G P(0,1))       . LOAD LITERALAR
)@@G@@@B@@@@          OFF       (P(0,1)=0)=0      .   @F@@@@          DO      AS
)@@G@@  P(0,1)=0 , LA,U   A3,0 . CLEAR OPTIONS REG    @D@@@@          OFF     AT
)@@G@@  P(0)>1            . ANY OPTIONS ? @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. FINALLY, CALL SUAU
)@@G@@BROUTINE    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          LMJ       X11,FIASG$        . ASAV
)@@G@@SIGN FILE   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          END                         .   AW
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THIS PROCEDURE IS USED TO CALL THE DIAGNOSTIC ROUTINAX
)@@G@@E FIDIAG$   @F@@@@. IF A CSF$ ERROR IS DETECTED THE ERROR$ REP IS CALLEDAY
)@@G@@.  IF THE   @D@@@@. ERROR IS PERMISSIONS FIDIAG PRINTS THE MESSAGE.     AZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC      *0,1              .   @B@@@@FIDIAGBA
)@@G@@*   NAME      FIDIAG$           .   @D@@@@          LMJ       X11,P(0,0)BB
)@@G@@        . CALL ROUTINE  @B@@@@          END                         .   BC
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO FREE A FILE WHICH HAS BEBD
)@@G@@EN ASSIGNED @ @@@@. VIA FIASG$. THE CALL IS:    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.     BE
)@@G@@    FIFREE    NAME FREECODE   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC      *2  BF
)@@G@@              .   @D@@@@FIFREE*   NAME      FIFREE$           . NORMAL FBG
)@@G@@REE   @E@@@@FIFRIM*   NAME      FIFRIM$           . RETURN FREE IMAGE   BH
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@ DO P(1)>0 , DL A1,P(1,1),P(1,2)      . GET FILE NAME BI
)@@G@@@E@@@@ DO P(2)>0 , L  A0,P(2,1),P(2,2),P(2,3) . GET FREE CODE     @F@@@@BJ
)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,P(0,0)        . CALL SELECTED ROUTINE     @[@@@@BK
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@BL
)@@G@@. GENERATE FIASG$ PACKET.  THE CALLS ARE: @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         FIBM
)@@G@@PFIL    'Q','QUAL' 'F','FILE' ....  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE FIRST SUBFIEBN
)@@G@@LD OF EACH FIELD IS A CODE LETTER, IN QUOTES :  @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.     BO
)@@G@@    'Q' - QUALIFIER     @^@@@@.         'F' - FILENAME@^@@@@.         'RBP
)@@G@@' - READKEY @^@@@@.         'W' - WRITEKEY@ @@@@.         'C' - FILECYCLBQ
)@@G@@E     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. IF THE PROCEDURE FIPELT IS CALLED THE FULL 14 BR
)@@G@@WORD ELT$ PACKET  @F@@@@. IS GENERATED AND THE FOLLOWING ADDITION FIELDSBS
)@@G@@ ARE ALLOWED.     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         'E' - ELEMENT NAME  @ @@@@BT
)@@G@@.         'V' - VERSION NAME  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE SECOND SUBFIELD OFBU
)@@G@@ EACH FIELD IS A STRING OF NOT MORE THAN  @F@@@@. 6 OR 12 LETTERS (DEPENBV
)@@G@@DING ON THE NORMAL LENGTH OF THAT FIELD)  @ @@@@. ENCLOSED IN QUOTATION BW
)@@G@@MARKS.@[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC      *8                .   @E@@@@BX
)@@G@@FIPFIL*   NAME      0                 . ONLY FILE PORTION   @G@@@@FIPELTBY
)@@G@@*   NAME      1                 . BOTH FILE AND ELEMENT PORTIONS  @[@@@@BZ
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@B(1)      EQU       0D                . PRESENCE BITS (2 WORCA
)@@G@@DS)   @D@@@@Q(1)      EQU       0D                . QUALIFIER (2) @D@@@@CB
)@@G@@F(1)      EQU       0D                . FILENAME (2)  @D@@@@R(1)      EQCC
)@@G@@U       0                 . READKEY (1)   @D@@@@W(1)      EQU       0   CD
)@@G@@              . WRITEKEY (1)  @D@@@@C(1)      EQU       0               CE
)@@G@@  . CYCLE (1)     @E@@@@E(1)      EQU       0D                . ELEMENT CF
)@@G@@NAME (2)    @E@@@@V(1)      EQU       0D                . VERSION NAME(2CG
)@@G@@)     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@I DO P-1 , FISCAN   .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@      CH
)@@G@@    +         B(1)              .   @B@@@@          +         Q(1)      CI
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          +         F(1)              .   @B@@@@      CJ
)@@G@@    +         C(1)              .   @B@@@@          +         R(1)      CK
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          +         W(1)              .   @B@@@@      CL
)@@G@@    ON        P(0,0)            .   @B@@@@          +         E(1)      CM
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          +         V(1)              .   @B@@@@      CN
)@@G@@    +         0                 .   @B@@@@          OFF       P(0,0)    CO
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          END       .   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@CP
)@@G@@. PROCEDURE TO PROCESS EACH FIELD.  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@FISCAN*   PROC    CQ
)@@G@@  *0,0              . SECOND GLOBAL PASS ONLY   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@ DO P(CR
)@@G@@I,1)='Q' ,Q*(1) FIW2 66 .     @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='F' ,F*(1) FIW2 60 .     CS
)@@G@@@A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='C' ,C*(1) FIW1 54 .     @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='R' ,R*(1) FICT
)@@G@@W1 48 .     @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='W' ,W*(1) FIW1 42 .     @B@@@@          ONCU
)@@G@@        P(0,0)            .   @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='E' ,E*(1) FIW2 30 .     CV
)@@G@@@A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='V' ,V*(1) FIW2 24 .     @B@@@@          OFF       P(0,CW
)@@G@@0)            .   @B@@@@ DO FOUND(1)=0 , +09                  .   @B@@@@CX
)@@G@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. PROCEDURE CY
)@@G@@TO LEFT JUSTIFY AND STORE THE COMPONENT.  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@Z         PRCZ
)@@G@@OC      *1,0              .   @B@@@@FIW2*     NAME                      DA
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@P**(I,2)  EQU       P(I,2)++0D        .   @F@@@@ DO 12 , DO DB
)@@G@@(P(I,2)*/-66)**077=0 ,P**(I,2) EQU P(I,2)*/6+05 .     @B@@@@FIW1*     NADC
)@@G@@ME                        .   @F@@@@ DO 06 , DO (P(I,2)*/-30)**077=0 ,P*DD
)@@G@@*(I,2) EQU P(I,2)*/6+05 .     @B@@@@*         EQU       P(I,2)          DE
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@B**(1)    EQU       B(1)++1D*/Z(1,1)   .  @B@@@@FOUND*(1) EQDF
)@@G@@U       1                 .   @^@@@@          END       .   _@@@@@@F@@@@DG
)@@G@@. 6 OR 12 LETTERS (DEPENDING ON THE NORMAL LENGTH OF THAT FIELD)  @ @@@@DH
)@@G@@. ENCLOSED IN QUOTATION MARKS.@[@@@@.     @B@@@@*[S@@[*SDFF*@^@@@@ 8)^@)DI
)@@G@@^@)^@)^@)^-^C(A^@)@A@@@@^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^-GC(QC(G^@)^@) )1^@)@[@@@@ 0)^@)DJ
)@@G@@@J@@@@ 0)^[QCDMDDJE(N^[KELJCTN^[PET C))DDI ))CDIC))CLT^[PET ELN^[JC0)E-CDK

)@@G@@DDN^[[^[QC(#E-JEK(BS)D@2^[DES)E-CC*)B-[C-^EK" 0)@[@@@@ 0)^@)@H@@@@ 0)D9IEB
)@@G@@D-T^[[ES)D([D1T^[RD9MC-N^[[ES)DDIC- F[ ES)C9DE1 D0)CDMC*)C9 D1 EL[E- C),EC
)@@G@@@[@@@@ 0)^@)@[@@@@ 0)^@)@A@@@@E@)^@)^@)^@)^@)E[MD9#^@)^@)^@) K3AK)@^@@@@ED

)@@G@@ *"^8%^9XE@*DC?AK(@B@@@@^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^- D-NC*)^@)^@)E@*DC(B*3^@)@L@@@@EH

)@@G@@@@E@@N@@@@#F)@@@@@@@@@@GM$MXQTSIZE  ERR$        M$COREPRMGETM$DEFOBC    ZK
)@@G@@M$DEFCBC    M$PRTENTERM M$XQTMACRO  M$CDLEV     M$DLC       M$DLI       ZL
)@@G@@M$MVSET     M$PRECALL   M$XQTCOM    M$COMFIND   M$CMPTABLE  M$MDFIND    ZM
)@@G@@M$POSTRTN   M$PRTEXITM  M$DLP       M$COREPRMRELM$PRTREENTM M$ELT$      ZN
)@@G@@M$MACLIB    FILE$OK     M$FILESEARCHM$IMAGE     M$EPKT      M$EDITOPEN  ZO
)@@G@@EMSG$       EFD2$       EMSGR$      M$EDITAW    M$EDITCLOSE M$COMCOMMENTZP
)@@G@@@@[@@@@@@@[GM$XQTCALL   @@[@@@@@@@@@M$XQTCOMMAND@@[@@@@@@@[@M$XQTCONTROLZQ
)@@G@@@@[@@@@@@@[LM$XQTDEFMAC @@[@@@@@@@[ZM$XQTESCAPE @@[@@@@@@@[>M$XQTPOPSTAKZR
)@@G@@@@[@@@@@@@[$M$XQTUNDMAC @@[@@@@@@@]WA_A__@A_A__@A_A__@A_A__@A_A__@A_A__@ZS
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@F/         M$DEF   @#@@@J          LIBRARY @[@@@F.     ZT
)@@G@@@D@@@F. THIS IS THE INTERRUPT HANDLER FOR THE MACRO PACKAGE.@[@@@F.     ZU
)@@G@@@G@@@F. WHEN AN INTERRUPT IS TAKEN, THE USER INTERRUPT VECTOR IS SEARCHEZV
)@@G@@D FOR @H@@@F. A CONTINGENCY HANDLER, ERROR TYPE HANDLER, OR ERROR CODE HZW
)@@G@@ANDLER. IF FOUND  @H@@@F. IT IS INVOKED, OTHERWISE, THE INTERRUPT IS FIEZX
)@@G@@LDED BY THE MACRO PACKAGE     @G@@@F. ITSELF.  IF THE INTERRUPT RETURNS ZY
)@@G@@NORMALLY, IT IS TO THE INTSTRUCTION @A@@@F. FOLLOWING THE ONE INTERRUPTEZZ
)@@G@@D.    @[@@@F.     @#@@@F          INSTRS  @[@@@F.     @B@@@F. M$IALL - TAA
)@@G@@URN ON CONTINGENCY HANDLER    @[@@@F.     @E@@@FM$IALL*   LA        A0,MAB
)@@G@@$IALLMASK     . GET THE BIT MASK    @B@@@F          $DO $PAR(4)='OFF' , AC
)@@G@@LA,U A0,0   @B@@@F          ER        IALL$             .   @C@@@F      AD
)@@G@@    J         0,X11             . DONE    @[@@@F.     @D@@@FM$IALLMASK* AE
)@@G@@VAR     1 0772700,M$CPKT  . IALL$ MASK    @[@@@F.     @F@@@FM$CPKT*   VAAF
)@@G@@R       3 0 0 +(J M$INTERRUPTS) . CONTINGENCY PACKET  @[@@@F.     @]@@@FAG
)@@G@@M$INTERRUPTS@D@@@F          DS        A0,ERPA0A1        . SAVE A0 A1    AH
)@@G@@@D@@@F          SX        X11,ERPX11        . SAVE USER X11 @D@@@F      AI
)@@G@@    DS        A2,INTRA2A3       . SAVE A2,A3    @C@@@F          SR      AJ
)@@G@@  R1,INTRR1         . SAVE R1 @F@@@F          LA        A1,M$UIVECT     AK
)@@G@@  . GET USER INTERRUPT VECTOR @E@@@F          LMJ       X11,FIELDINTR   AL
)@@G@@  . FIELD THE INTERRUPT @H@@@F          LA,U      A1,M$MIVECT       . USAM
)@@G@@ER DIDN'T HANDLE THIS ONE, WE DO IT @E@@@F          LMJ       X11,FIELDIAN
)@@G@@NTR     . FIELD THE INTERRUPT @[@@@F.     @G@@@F. WE DIDN'T HANDLE EITHEAO
)@@G@@R. LET'S CALL THE ERROR REP TO DIAGNOSE THE     @A@@@F. PROBLEM, THEN REAP
)@@G@@TURN IN ERROR.    @[@@@F.     @F@@@FERRCALL   DL        A0,M$CPKT       AQ
)@@G@@  . GET THE CONTINGENCY PACKET@F@@@F          LMJ       X11,M$IALLERR   AR
)@@G@@  . DIAGNOSE AN IALL$ ERROR   @E@@@F          LA,U      A0,0            AS
)@@G@@  . POST NO CONTINGENCY @C@@@F          J         CRTN010           . REAT
)@@G@@TURN  @[@@@F.     @D@@@FINTRA2A3  VAR       2                  . USER A2AU
)@@G@@A3    @C@@@FINTRR1    VAR       1                 . USER R1 @[@@@F.     AV
)@@G@@@A@@@F. NORMAL RETURN FROM CONTINGENCY    @[@@@F.     @F@@@FCRTN      LAAW
)@@G@@,H2     A0,M$CPKT         . GET THE RETURN ADDRESS    @E@@@F          TZAX
)@@G@@,U      0,A0              . IS ADDRESS THERE?   @G@@@F          AA,U    AY
)@@G@@  A0,1              . YES, BUMP THE RETURN ADDRESS    @E@@@FCRTN010   SAAZ
)@@G@@,H2     A0,M$CPKT         . POST IN THE PACKET  @D@@@F          DL      BA
)@@G@@  A0,ERPA0A1        . RESTORE REGS  @ @@@F          LX        X11,ERPX11BB
)@@G@@@A@@@F          DL        A2,INTRA2A3     @ @@@F          LR        R1,IBC
)@@G@@NTRR1 @F@@@F          TZ,H2     M$CPKT            . STILL IN CONTINGENCYBD
)@@G@@ MODE @G@@@F          ER        CRTN$             . YES, MAKE A CONTINGEBE
)@@G@@NCY RETURN  @[@@@F.     @F@@@F. ERROR RETURN FROM CONTIGENCY PROCESSING.BF
)@@G@@ USE THE CONFIGURED     @G@@@F. RETURN ADDRESS FOR ERRORS IF IT'S THERE,BG
)@@G@@ OTHERWISE, USE THE RETURN    @ @@@F. ADDRESS GIVEN TO M$DRIVER.  @[@@@FBH
)@@G@@.     @F@@@FERTN      TZ        M$ERROR           . ERROR RETURN CONFIGUBI
)@@G@@RED?  @D@@@F          J         *M$ERROR          . YES, USE IT   @G@@@FBJ
)@@G@@          LX        X11,M$DRIVERRTN   . OTHERWISE, USE TOP-LEVEL RETURN BK
)@@G@@@B@@@F          J         0,X11             .   @[@@@F/.    @G@@@F. FIELBL
)@@G@@DINTR - ROUTINE TO FIELD AN INTERRUPT TYPE (A0) THROUGH AN INDEX  @A@@@FBM
)@@G@@.             VECTOR TABLE (A1).    @[@@@F.     @^@@@FFIELDINTR SUBROUTIBN
)@@G@@NE    @F@@@F          LA        A2,(1,FLDLDS)     . GET INDEX TO LOAD TABO
)@@G@@BLE   @F@@@FFLDI010   JZ        A1,FLDI020        . IF NO VECTOR TABLE, BP
)@@G@@EXIT  @H@@@F          EX        0,*A2             . LOAD NEXT TYPE FROM BQ
)@@G@@CONTINGENCY PACKET@G@@@F          LR        R1,0,A1           . = # OF IBR
)@@G@@NDEXES IN THE TABLE     @E@@@F          LXI,U     A1,1              . SEBS
)@@G@@T THE INCREMENT   @D@@@F          SE,S1     A0,1,*A1          . FIND THEBT
)@@G@@ INDEX@C@@@F          J         FLDI020           . NO FIND @F@@@F      BU
)@@G@@    LA,S2     A0,0,A1           . GET VECTOR TABLE FLAG     @F@@@F      BV
)@@G@@    LA,H2     A1,0,A1           . GET ADDRESS AT THE INDEX  @H@@@F      BW
)@@G@@    JZ        A1,CRTN           . IF ZERO ADDRESS, MEANS DON'T BOTHER   BX
)@@G@@@G@@@F          JNZ       A0,FLDI010        . LOOP IF ANOTHER VECTOR TABBY
)@@G@@LE    @D@@@F          SA        A1,FLDIADDR       . POST ADDRESS  @E@@@FBZ
)@@G@@          DL        A0,ERPA0A1        . RESTORE USER REGS   @A@@@F      CA
)@@G@@    DL        A2,INTRA2A3     @ @@@F          LX        X11,ERPX11@ @@@FCB
)@@G@@          LR        R1,INTRR1 @F@@@F          LMJ       X11,*FLDIADDR   CC
)@@G@@  . CALL INTERRUPT ADDRESS    @H@@@F          J         CRTN            CD
)@@G@@  . RETURN TO 0,X11 SAYS EXIT QUIETLY     @#@@@FFLDI020   RETURN  @[@@@FCE
)@@G@@.     @E@@@FFLDLDS    LA,S3     A0,M$CPKT         . GET CONTINGENCY TYPECF
)@@G@@@D@@@F          LA,S1     A0,M$CPKT         . GET ERROR TYPE@D@@@F      CG
)@@G@@    LA,S2     A0,M$CPKT         . GET ERROR CODE@H@@@F          J       CH
)@@G@@  ERRCALL           . SOMETHING GOOFED- CALL ERROR$ REP     @[@@@F.     CI
)@@G@@@D@@@FFLDIADDR  VAR       1 0,$-$           . FIELD ADDRESS @[@@@F.     CJ
)@@G@@@C@@@F. DEFINE THE CONTINGENCIES TO BE HANDLED BY US. @[@@@F.     @E@@@FCK
)@@G@@. THIS TABLE DEFINES THE HANDLERS FOR THE CONTINGENCY TYPES.@F@@@F. IF ICL
)@@G@@T'S NOT IN THE TABLE, IT DEFAULTS TO CALLING THE ERROR$ REP.@[@@@F.     CM
)@@G@@@F@@@FM$MIVECT  M$IVECT                     ; DEFINE INTERRUPT TABLE    CN
)@@G@@@E@@@F                    1,INTIOPR         ; ILLEGAL OPERATION   @D@@@FCO
)@@G@@                    2,INTIGDM         ; IN GUARD MODE @F@@@F            CP
)@@G@@        3,CRTN            ; FLOATING POINT OVERFLOW   @F@@@F            CQ
)@@G@@        4,CRTN            ; FLOATING POINT UNDERFLOW  @D@@@F            CR
)@@G@@        5,CRTN            ; DIVIDE FAULT  @D@@@F                    010,CS
)@@G@@*INTCK        ; CONSOLE KEYIN @D@@@F                    012,*INTEM      CT
)@@G@@  . ERROR MODE    @D@@@FINTCK     M$IVECT   1,CRTN            ; CONSOLE CU
)@@G@@KEYIN @C@@@F                    2,INTBREAK        . @@X C   @D@@@FINTEM CV
)@@G@@    M$IVECT   1,INTIO           ; I/O ERROR     @D@@@F                  CW
)@@G@@  2,*INTSYMB        ; SYMBIONT ERROR@C@@@F                    4,*INTERERCX
)@@G@@R       . ER ERROR@E@@@FINTSYMB   M$IVECT   2,INT2NDEOF       ; 2ND EOF CY
)@@G@@ON READ$    @F@@@F                    5,INTATADD        ; @ADD ERROR IN CZ
)@@G@@RUNSTREAM   @E@@@F                    010,017,INTCSFADD ; @ADD ERROR IN DA
)@@G@@CSF$  @G@@@F                    041,042,CRTN      ; MAX PAGES, MAX CARDSDB
)@@G@@ (IGNORE)   @F@@@F                    043,CRTN          . IGNORE PRTCN$ DC
)@@G@@ERRORS TOO  @D@@@FINTERERR  M$IVECT   040,042,INTCSFERR ; CSF$ ERROR    DD
)@@G@@@E@@@F                    053,INTMCORE      ; ER MCORE$ FAILED    @E@@@FDE
)@@G@@                    055,INTMCORE      . ER MCORE$ FAILED    @[@@@F/.    DF
)@@G@@@B@@@F. THESE ARE THE VARIOUS INTERRUPT HANDLERS@[@@@F.     @[@@@F.     DG
)@@G@@@ @@@F. INTIOPR - ILLEGAL OPERATION @[@@@F.     @G@@@FINTIOPR   JNEZ    DH
)@@G@@  M$WARMSTART ERTN  . IF WARM-STARTING, RETURN QUICKLY@G@@@F          J DI
)@@G@@        ERRCALL           . OTHERWISE, REPORT THE ERROR     @[@@@F.     DJ
)@@G@@@F@@@F. INTIGDM - IN GUARD MODE (REFERENCE OUTSIDE USER STORAGE LIMITS).DK
)@@G@@@[@@@F.     @G@@@FINTIGDM   JNEZ      M$WARMSTART ERTN  . IF WARM-STARTIDL
)@@G@@NG, RETURN QUICKLY@F@@@F          DEC       A0,IGDMCOUNT      . DECREMENDM
)@@G@@T THE # OF IGDMS  @F@@@F          JP        A0,ERRCALL        . GO DIAGNDN
)@@G@@OSE THE ERROR     @H@@@F          SZ        M$IALLMASK        . CLEAR FUDO
)@@G@@RTHER CONTINGENCY HANDLING    @F@@@F          J         ERRCALL         DP
)@@G@@  . GO DIAGNOSE ONE MORE TIME @[@@@F.     @E@@@FIGDMCOUNT VAR       1 IGDQ
)@@G@@DMLIMIT       . DEFINE IGDM COUNT   @[@@@F.     @A@@@F. INTBREAK - MARK DR
)@@G@@A BREAK KEYIN     @[@@@F.     @C@@@FINTBREAK  LA        A0,PCL('REMOTE BDS
)@@G@@REAK') .    @E@@@F          SA        A0,M$BREAK        . POST THE BREAKDT
)@@G@@ FLAG @E@@@F          J         CRTN              . RETURN NORMALLY     DU
)@@G@@@[@@@F.     @A@@@F. INTIO - PROCESS AN IO INTERRUPT   @[@@@F.     @F@@@FDV
)@@G@@INTIO     LA,H2     A0,M$CPKT+1       . GET IO PACKET ADDRESS     @E@@@FDW
)@@G@@          LA,S2     A1,M$CPKT         . GET THE ERROR CODE  @F@@@F      DX
)@@G@@    TE,U      A1,023            . WAS ERROR CODE BAD PACKET?@H@@@F      DY
)@@G@@    SA,S1     A1,3,A0           . NO, STASH ERROR CODE INTO THE PACKET  DZ
)@@G@@@E@@@F          J         ERRCALL           . CALL THE ERROR REP  @[@@@FEA
)@@G@@.     @ @@@F. INT2NDEOF - MARK EOF FLAG   @[@@@F.     @D@I@FINT2NDEOF LAEB
)@@G@@,U      A0,1              . GET A BIT     @D@@@IINT2NDEOF LA,U      A0,2EC
)@@G@@              . GET A BIT     @F@@@F          SA        A0,M$REOF       ED
)@@G@@  . SAYS DON'T READ ANY MORE  @D@@@F          SZ        ERPA0A1         EE
)@@G@@  . CLEAR USER A0 @E@@@F          J         CRTN              . RETURN "EF
)@@G@@NORMALLY"   @[@@@F.     @A@@@F. INTATADD - RUNSTREAM @ADD ERROR   @[@@@FEG
)@@G@@.     @F@@@FINTATADD  JEZ       M$DEMAND ERRCALL  . IF BATCH MODE, ERROREH
)@@G@@ OFF  @E@@@F          J         CRTN              . OTHERWISE, IT'S OK  EI
)@@G@@@[@@@F.     @B@@@F. INTCSFADD - @ADD ERROR IN CSF$ REQUEST  @[@@@F.     EJ
)@@G@@@G@@@FINTCSFADD LA        A0,(6*/33)        . SYNTAX ERROR IN CSF$ REQUEEK
)@@G@@ST    @D@@@F          SA        A0,ERPA0A1        . POST USER A0  @F@@@FEL
)@@G@@          J         CRTN              . RETURN TO INTERRUPTED CODE@[@@@FEM
)@@G@@.     @A@@@F. INTCSFERR - ERROR IN CSF$ REQUEST @[@@@F.     @D@@@FINTCSFEN
)@@G@@ERR EQU       INTCSFADD         . SAME AS ABOVE @[@@@F.     @A@@@F. INTMEO
)@@G@@CORE - ERROR IN MCORE$ REQUEST@[@@@F.     @D@@@FINTMCORE  SZ        ERPAEP
)@@G@@0A1           . CLEAR USER A0 @E@@@F          J         CRTN            EQ
)@@G@@  . RETURN NORMALLY     @[@@@F/.    @D@@@F. THIS ENTRY POINT IS FOR ANYOER
)@@G@@NE WITH AN IALL$ ERROR. @G@@@F. A0,A1 SHOULD LOOK LIKE THE FIRST TWO WORES
)@@G@@DS OF THE IALL$ PACKET BEING  @]@@@F. DIAGNOSED.@[@@@F.     @^@@@FM$IALLET
)@@G@@ERR* SUBROUTINE   @E@@@F          DS        A0,ERPERRW        . POST THEEU
)@@G@@ ERROR WORDS@I@H@F          LA,U      A0,TALK2+LIJRTN+IALLERR   . GET BIEV
)@@G@@TS THAT TELL ERROR$ WHAT T    @I@@@H          LA,U      A0,TALK1+LIJRTN+EW
)@@G@@IALLERR   . GET BITS THAT TELL ERROR$ WHAT T    @F@@@F          LMJ     EX
)@@G@@  X11,LINK          . LINK TO THE ERROR$ BANK   @#@@@F          RETURN  EY
)@@G@@@[@@@F.     @C@@@F. M$ERRCSF - ROUTINE TO DIAGNOSE CSF$ ERRORS    @[@@@FEZ
)@@G@@.     @ @@@F. A0 = A0 BEFORE CSF$ REQUEST @ @@@F. A1 = A0 AFTER CSF$ REQFA
)@@G@@UEST  @[@@@F.     @^@@@FM$ERRCSF* SUBROUTINE    @E@@@F          DS      FB
)@@G@@  A0,ERPERRW        . POST THE ERROR WORDS@E@@@F          LA,U      A0,TFC
)@@G@@ALK1+LIJRTN+CSFERR . CALL PARAMETERS@F@@@F          LMJ       X11,LINK  FD
)@@G@@        . LINK TO THE ERROR$ BANK   @#@@@F          RETURN  @[@@@F.     FE
)@@G@@@A@@@F. M$PFXXXERR - PROCESS PFP$ ERRORS  @[@@@F.     @B@@@F.  A2 = ERROFF
)@@G@@R CODE RETURNED FROM EXEC     @ @@@F.  A0 = PFX$ PACKET ADDRESS   @[@@@FFG
)@@G@@.     @B@@@F.   LMJ  X11,M$PFSERR\M$PFIERR\M$PFWLERR  @[@@@F.     @D@@@FFH
)@@G@@M$PFSERR* LA,U      A1,1              . GET PFS$ FLAG @D@@@F          J FI
)@@G@@        PFERROR           . PROCESS ERROR @D@@@FM$PFIERR* LA,U      A1,2FJ
)@@G@@              . GET PFI$ FLAG @D@@@F          J         PFERROR         FK
)@@G@@  . PROCESS ERROR @D@@@FM$PFWLERR* LA,U     A1,5              . GET PFWLFL
)@@G@@$ FLAG@D@@@F.         J         PFERROR           . PROCESS ERROR @^@@@FFM
)@@G@@PFERROR   SUBROUTINE    @E@@@F          SA        A2,ERPA0AFTER     . POFN
)@@G@@ST ERRO RESULT    @E@@@F          SA        A0,ERPA0BEFORE    . POST PACFO
)@@G@@KET ADDRESS @F@@@F          LA,U      A0,TALK1+LIJRTN+PFERR,A1 . SET LINFP
)@@G@@K PARAMETERS@E@@@F          LMJ       X11,LINK          . CALL ERROR$ BAFQ
)@@G@@NK    @#@@@F          RETURN  @[@@@F/.    @E@@@F. LINK - THE ROUTINE THAFR
)@@G@@T ACTUALLY LINKS TO THE ERROR$ BANK @[@@@F.     @C@@@F.  A0 = ERROR TYPEFS
)@@G@@ + RETURN TYPE + SPEAK LEVEL  @#@@@F.  LMJ  X11,LINK  @[@@@F.     @ @@@FFT
)@@G@@. DEFINE THE CALL PARAMETERS  @[@@@F.     @D@@@FIALLERR   EQU       1   FU
)@@G@@              . IALL$ ERROR   @D@@@FCSFERR    EQU       2               FV
)@@G@@  . CSF$ ERROR    @D@@@FPFERR     EQU       20                . PFP$ ERRFW
)@@G@@OR    @D@@@FTALK1     EQU       1*/12             . TALK LEVEL 1  @D@G@FFX
)@@G@@TALK2     EQU       1*/12             . TALK LEVEL 2  @D@H@GTALK2     EQFY
)@@G@@U       2*/12             . TALK LEVEL 2  @D@@@FTALK20    EQU       20*/FZ
)@@G@@12            . TALK LEVEL 20 @D@@@FLIJRTN    EQU       7*/6            GA
)@@G@@  . LIJ RETURN    @[@@@FLINK  @D@@@F          LA        A1,(1,LINKREGS) GB
)@@G@@  . SAVE USER REGS@E@@@F          MOVE      *A1 A2,X1,,U 11   . SAVE X1 GC
)@@G@@THRU X11    @E@@@F          MOVE      *A1 A2,A6,,U 10   . SAVE A6 THRU AGD
)@@G@@15    @E@@@F          MOVE      *A1 A2,R4,,U 12   . SAVE R4 THRU R15    GE
)@@G@@@C@@@F          TNZ       M$DEMAND          . DEMAND? @F@@@F          A,GF
)@@G@@U       A0,TALK20         . NO, INCREASE TALK LEVEL   @E@@@F          SAGG
)@@G@@        A0,ERPKT          . POST INTO THE PACKET@F@@@F          LXI,U   GH
)@@G@@  A0,1*/17          . GET CURRENT DBANK BDI     @E@@@F          ER      GI
)@@G@@  BANK$             . H2[A0] = DBANK BDI  @F@@@F          LXI,U     A0,1GJ
)@@G@@*/17+1        . GET STORAGE LIMITS TO A0  @D@@@F          ER        BANKGK
)@@G@@$             . A0 = (HI,LOW) @E@@@F          DSL       A0,18           GL
)@@G@@  . A1 = LOW ADDRESS    @B@@@F          SSL       A1,18             .   GM
)@@G@@@F@@@F          AN        A0,A1             . COMPUTE LENGTH OF DBANK   GN
)@@G@@@E@@@F          SA        A0,ERPDBLIM       . POST DBANK LIMIT    @E@@@FGO
)@@G@@          LA,U      A1,ERPKT          . GET PACKET ADDRESS  @D@@@F      GP
)@@G@@    LXI,U     X11,E$RROR$       . GET ERROR$ BDI@D@@@F          LIJ     GQ
)@@G@@  X11,ERROR$$       . CALL ERROR REP@F@@@F          LMJ       X11,M$IALLGR
)@@G@@        . TURN CONTINGENCIES BACK ON@E@@@F          LA        A1,(1,LINKGS
)@@G@@REGS)   . RESTORE USER REGS   @E@@@F          MOVE      A2,X1,,U *A1 11 GT
)@@G@@  . RESTORE X1 THRU X11 @E@@@F          MOVE      A2,A6,,U *A1 10   . REGU
)@@G@@STORE A6 THRU A15 @E@@@F          MOVE      A2,R4,,U *A1 12   . RESTORE GV
)@@G@@R4 THRU R15 @C@@@F          J         0,X11             . DONE    @[@@@FGW
)@@G@@.     @D@@@FLINKREGS  VAR       11+10+12          . USER'S REGS   @[@@@FGX
)@@G@@.     @#@@@F          VARS    @[@@@F.     @ @@@F. DEFINE THE ERROR$ PACKGY
)@@G@@ET    @[@@@F.     @D@@@FERPKT     BASE                        . DEFINE AGZ
)@@G@@ND GEN@D@@@FERPARG    WORD      0                 . CALL ARGUMENT @^@@@FHA
)@@G@@          WORD      0   @E@@@FERPERRW   DWORD     0                 . A0HB
)@@G@@ BEFORE; A0 AFTER @D@@@FERPA0BEFORE EQUF    ERPERRW           . A0 BEFORHC
)@@G@@E     @C@@@FERPA0AFTER EQUF     ERPERRW+1         . A0 AFTER@D@@@FERPA0AHD
)@@G@@1   DWORD     0                 . USER A0,A1    @D@@@FERPAN     WORD    HE
)@@G@@  0                 . ACTIVITY NAME @E@@@FERPIBLW   WORD      LASTI$-FRSHF
)@@G@@TI$,FRSTI$ . LENGTH, START    @D@@@FERPDBLW   WORD      $-$,FRSTD$      HG
)@@G@@  . LENGTH, START @D@@@FERPDBLIM  FIELD     H1                . DBANK LIHH
)@@G@@MIT   @I@@@F          WORD      -1                . DIAG$ ADDRESS OF IBAHI
)@@G@@NK (-0 = DON'T SAVE)    @C@@@FERPX11    WORD      $-$               . USHJ
)@@G@@ER X11@F@@@FERPSLOP   AREA      50                . SCRATCH AREA FOR ERRHK
)@@G@@OR$   @F@@@F          ENDBASE                     . GENERATE THE PACKET HL
)@@G@@NOW   @[@@@F.     @#@@@F          END     _@@@@@    WORD      $-$       HM
)@@G@@        . USER X11>@@@@D@G@@@E@@@@@@ERPSLOP   AREA      50              HN
