)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@R/         M$DEF   @[@@@R.     @E@@@R. M$CONVMODE - ROUNT
)@@G@@TINE TO CONVERT A VALUE TO A GIVEN MODE.  @E@@@R. M$CONVINT  - ROUTINE TNU
)@@G@@O CONVERT A VALUE TO AN INTEGER.    @F@@@R. M$CONVASC  - ROUTINE TO CONVNV
)@@G@@ERT A VALUE TO AN ASCII STRING.     @[@@@R.     @A@@@R.  A0 = VALUE DESCNW
)@@G@@RIPTOR ADDRESS    @^@@@R.  A1 = DESIRED MODE    @^@@@R.  LMJ  X11,M$CONVNX
)@@G@@MODE  @^@@@R.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @]@@@R.  A0 = MODE@^@@@R.  A1 = (LENNY
)@@G@@GTH, ADDR)  @#@@@R.  A2 = LENGTH    @A@@@R.  A3 = MODIFIED DESCRIPTOR ADNZ
)@@G@@DRESS @[@@@R.     @E@@@RM$CONVINT* LA,U     A1,MODSIN         . GET DESIOA
)@@G@@RED MODE    @D@@@R          J         M$CONVMODE        . GO CONVERT    OB
)@@G@@@D@@@RM$CONVASC* LA,U     A1,MODASC         . GET ASCII MODE@]@@@R      OC
)@@G@@    . @^@@@RM$CONVMODE* SUBROUTINE  @F@@@RCVTVDA    LOCAL               OD
)@@G@@        . VALUE DESCRIPTOR ADDRESS  @D@@@RCVTMOD    LOCAL               OE
)@@G@@        . DESIRED MODE  @E@@@RCVTADR    LOCAL                       . ADOF
)@@G@@DRESS OF RESULT   @E@@@RCVTEDR    STATIC    1 0,$-$           . INDIRECTOG
)@@G@@ION CELL    @D@@@RCVTTMP    LOCAL     2                 . SOME TEMPS    OH
)@@G@@@H@@@UCVTDIN    LOCAL                       . INDICATE CONVERT FROM DOUBOI
)@@G@@LE INTEGER  @#@@@R          SNOOPY  @E@@@R          DS        A0,CVTVDA OJ
)@@G@@        . POST VD ADDR, MODE  @E@@@RCVT001    LA        A2,VDM,A0       OK
)@@G@@  . A2 = ACTUAL MODE    @G@@@R          JE,U      A1,,A2 CVT400     . IFOL
)@@G@@ MODES SAME, EASY CONVERT!    @G@@@S          TE,U      A1,MODNUL       OM
)@@G@@  . IF EITHER 'TO' MODE IS NULL     @F@@@S          TNE,U     A2,MODNUL ON
)@@G@@        . OR 'FROM' MODE IS NULL    @E@@@S          J         $+2       OO
)@@G@@        . THEN EASY TO CONVERT@E@@@S          J         CVT010          OP
)@@G@@  . NON-NULL CONVERSIONS@G@@@S          SZ        VDAW,A0           . CLOQ
)@@G@@EAR LENGTH & ADDRESS VALUES   @F@@@S          SA        A1,VDM,A0       OR
)@@G@@  . POST 'TO' MODE AS RESULT  @H@S@R          JE,U      A1,MODNUL CVT005OS
)@@G@@  . IF 'TO' MODE IS NULL, EASY CONVERSION @H@S@R          JNE,U     A2,MOT
)@@G@@ODNUL CVT010  . IF 'FROM' MODE NOT NULL, SKIP AHEAD   @H@S@RCVT005    SZOU
)@@G@@        VDAW,A0           . EASY TO CONVERT TO NULL OF ANY MODE   @E@S@ROV
)@@G@@          LA,U      A1,MODNUL         . GET NULL MODE TYPE  @D@S@R      OW
)@@G@@    SA        A1,VDM,A0         . POST NEW MODE @C@@@R          J       OX
)@@G@@  CVT400            . DONE    @B@@@RCVT010    LA        A5,M$CONVERR    OY
)@@G@@  .   @G@@@R          JLE,U     A2,M$MMAX+1 CVT999 . IF NOT A DEFINED MOOZ
)@@G@@DE, EXIT    @F@@@R          TUSR      A1                . CONVERTING TO PA
)@@G@@USER-MODE?  @G@@@R          TNUSR     A2                . NO, CONVERTINGPB
)@@G@@ FROM USER-MODE?  @F@@@R          J         CVT300            . YES, GO PC
)@@G@@HANDLE USER-MODE  @]@@@R          . @A@@@R          .         NOT A USERPD
)@@G@@ MODE @]@@@R          . @F@@@RCVT020    TSTR      A1 CVT100         . SKPE
)@@G@@IP OUT IF NOT A STRING  @]@@@R          . @B@@@R          .         CONVPF
)@@G@@ERTING TO STRING  @]@@@R          . @F@@@R          TDAT      A2 CVT999 PG
)@@G@@        . MAKE SURE ITEM IS A VALUE @E@@@R          LA        A0,VDL,A0 PH
)@@G@@        . GET ITEM LENGTH     @E@@@R          TSTR      A2              PI
)@@G@@  . IS ITEM A NUMBER?   @F@@@R          MSI,U     A0,13             . ALPJ
)@@G@@LOW 13 CHARS PER NUMBER @H@@@R          TE,U      A2,MODDIN         . ISPK
)@@G@@ ITEM DOUBLE PRECISION INTEGER?     @C@@@R          TNE,U     A2,MODDFL PL
)@@G@@        . OR REAL?@F@@@R          LSSL      A0,1              . YES, DOUPM
)@@G@@BLE YOUR MONEY    @G@@@R          AA,U      A0,3              . ROUND TOPN
)@@G@@ NEAREST WORD LENGTH    @^@@@R          SSL       A0,2@D@@@R          M$PO
)@@G@@TGET    CVT999            . GET TEMP CORE @E@@@R          SA        A1,CPP
)@@G@@VTADR         . POST THE TEMP ADDR  @G@@@R          LA        A0,A1     PQ
)@@G@@        . GET IMAGE ACCESS WORD IN A0     @E@@@R          LA        A2,CPR
)@@G@@VTMOD         . GET THE VALUE MODE  @E@@@R          LA,U      A1,1      PS
)@@G@@        . ASSUME ASCII RESULT @G@@@R          TNE,U     A2,MODALP       PT
)@@G@@  . UNLESS EXPLICIT CONVERSION TO FD@F@@@R          LA,U      A1,0      PU
)@@G@@        . GET FIELDATA IMAGE MODE   @H@@@R          M$EINITAX CVT999    PV
)@@G@@        . INITIALIZE EDITING ON A NEW PACKET    @E@@@R          LA      PW
)@@G@@  A3,CVTVDA         . GET DESCRIPTOR ADDR @E@@@R          LA        A2,VPX
)@@G@@DM,A3         . GET 'FROM' MODE     @G@@@R          TSTR      A2 CVT030 PY
)@@G@@        . GO PROCESS NUMERICS ELSEWHERE   @E@@@R          LA,U      A0,1PZ
)@@G@@              . ASSUME ASCII STRING @C@@@R          TE,U      A2,MODASC QA
)@@G@@        . RIGHT?  @E@@@R          LA,U      A0,0              . NO, FIELQB
)@@G@@DATA STRING @F@@@R          M$EASCIN                    . POST INPUT STRQC
)@@G@@ING MODE    @E@@@R          LA        A1,VDL,A3         . GET STRING LENQD
)@@G@@GTH   @E@@@R          LA        A0,VDA,A3         . GET STRING ADDRESS  QE
)@@G@@@E@@@R          E$COPY                      . COPY THE STRING     @D@@@RQF
)@@G@@          J         CVT060            . GO FINISH UP  @]@@@R          . QG
)@@G@@@D@@@R          .         CONVERTING FROM NUMERIC TO STRING @]@@@R      QH
)@@G@@    . @G@@@RCVT030    LXI       A3,VMEWS,A2       . GET WORD INCREMENT FQI
)@@G@@OR MODE     @D@@@U          SZ        CVTDIN            . CLEAR THE FLAGQJ
)@@G@@@F@@@U          TNE,U     A2,MODDIN         . IF IT IS DOUBLE INTEGER   QK
)@@G@@@D@@@U          S         A2,CVTDIN         . SET THE FLAG  @F@@@R      QL
)@@G@@    LSSL      A2,1              . DOUBLE THE NUMERIC MODE   @H@@@R      QM
)@@G@@    AA,U      A2,CVTNER         . ADD ADDRESS OF NUMERIC EDITING ROUTINEQN
)@@G@@@G@@@R          SA,H2     A2,CVTEDR         . SAVE EDITING ROUTINE ADDREQO
)@@G@@SS    @F@@@R          LA        A4,VDL,A3         . GET THE NUMERIC LENGQP
)@@G@@TH    @F@@@R          LXM       A3,VDA,A3         . GET THE NUMERIC ADDRQQ
)@@G@@ESS   @E@@@R          J         CVT050            . START COPY LOOP     QR
)@@G@@@E@@@RCVT040    DL        A1,,*A3           . GET NEXT VALUE(S)   @F@@@RQS
)@@G@@          DS        A3,CVTTMP         . TEMP SAVE ADDRESS & COUNT @G@@@RQT
)@@G@@          CALL      *CVTEDR           . INVOKE NUMERIC EDITING ROUTINE  QU
)@@G@@@[@@@U.     @F@@@U          TNZ       CVTDIN            . IS IT DOUBLE IQV
)@@G@@NTEGER?     @E@@@U          J         CVT045            . NOPE, SKIP THIQW
)@@G@@S CODE@F@@@U          E$SKIP    -1                . BACK UP ONE CHARACTEQX
)@@G@@R     @E@@@U          E$CHAR    'D'               . REPLACE '.' WITH 'D'QY
)@@G@@@]@@@UCVT045    . @[@@@U.     @D@@@R          LA,U      A0,' '          QZ
)@@G@@  . GET A BLANK   @E@@@R          TZ        CVTTMP+1          . UNLESS WRA
)@@G@@E'RE DONE   @D@@@R          E$CHAR                      . MAKE A BLANK  RB
)@@G@@@F@@@R          DL        A3,CVTTMP         . RESTORE ADDRESS & COUNT   RC
)@@G@@@G@@@RCVT050    JGD       A4,CVT040         . COUNT ELTS & CONTINUE IF MRD
)@@G@@ORE   @E@@@RCVT060    E$WRDN                      . COMPUTE # WORDS USEDRE
)@@G@@@D@@@R          AA        A0,CVTADR         . = LAST ADDR+1 @F@@@R      RF
)@@G@@    M$TREL    CVT999            . RELEASE ANY UNUSED SPACE  @F@@@R      RG
)@@G@@    E$COLN                      . NOW COMPUTE STRING LENGTH @E@@@R      RH
)@@G@@    LA        A1,CVTADR         . RECOVER NEW ADDRESS @E@@@R          LXRI
)@@G@@I,U     A1,,A0            . POST LENGTH IN INCR @F@@@R          LA      RJ
)@@G@@  A0,CVTVDA         . RECOVER DESCRIPTOR ADDRESS@E@@@R          LA      RK
)@@G@@  A2,CVTMOD         . AND THE NEW MODE    @D@@@R          SA        A1,VRL
)@@G@@DAW,A0        . POST RESULTS  @ @@@R          SA        A2,VDM,A0 @G@@@RRM
)@@G@@          M$ETERM   CVT999            . DONE EDITING (RELEASE PACKET)   RN
)@@G@@@C@@@R          J         CVT400            . ALL DONE@]@@@R          . RO
)@@G@@@C@@@R          .         NUMERIC EDITING ROUTINES    @]@@@R          . RP
)@@G@@@E@@@RCVTNER    LA        A0,A1             . EDIT INTEGER VALUE  @ @@@RRQ
)@@G@@          J         EDECV$    @E@@@R          LA,U      A0,7            RR
)@@G@@  . EDIT REAL VALUE     @ @@@R          J         EFLG1$    @E@T@R      RS
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,1*/12+1        . EDIT DOUBLE INTEGER @E@@@T          LART
)@@G@@,U      A0,1*/12+0        . EDIT DOUBLE INTEGER @ @@@R          J       RU
)@@G@@  EFLF2$    @E@@@R          LA,U      A0,16             . EDIT DOUBLE RERV
)@@G@@AL    @ @@@R          J         EFLG2$    @]@@@R          . @C@@@R      RW
)@@G@@    .         CHECK FOR LIST CONVERSION   @]@@@R          . @]@@@R      RX
)@@G@@    . @G@@@RCVT100    JE,U      A1,MODLST CVT200  . IF CONVERTING TO A LRY
)@@G@@IST, SKIP   @]@@@R          . @B@@@R          .         CONVERTING TO NURZ
)@@G@@MERIC @]@@@R          . @F@@@R          TNUM      A2 CVT130         . IFSA
)@@G@@ NOT NUMERIC, SKIP AHEAD@F@@@R          CONVRTN   A2,A1 CVT999      . GESB
)@@G@@T CONVERSION ROUTINE    @G@@@R          SA        A2,CVTTMP         . POSC
)@@G@@ST THE TRANSLATION INSTRUCTION@E@@@R          LA        A0,VDL,A0       SD
)@@G@@  . GET LENGTH OF RESULT@F@@@R          TNDBL     A1                . SKSE
)@@G@@IP IF NOT DP NUMBER     @F@@@R          LSSL      A0,1              . YESF
)@@G@@S, ACTUAL WORD LENGTH   @D@@@R          M$TGET    CVT999            . GESG
)@@G@@T TEMP SPACE@F@@@R          LA        A2,CVTVDA         . RECOVER DESCRISH
)@@G@@PTOR ADDR   @E@@@R          LA        A0,VDA,A2         . GET OLD DATA ASI
)@@G@@DDR   @E@@@R          SA        A1,VDA,A2         . POST NEW DATA ADDR  SJ
)@@G@@@D@@@R          LA        A3,VDM,A2         . GET OLD MODE  @H@@@R      SK
)@@G@@    LXI       A0,VMEWS,A3       . SET INPUT ELT SIZE IN WORDS AS INCR   SL
)@@G@@@E@@@R          LA        A3,CVTMOD         . GET NEW DATA MODE   @G@@@RSM
)@@G@@          LXI       A1,VMEWS,A3       . SET OUTPUT ELEMENT SIZE AS INCR SN
)@@G@@@F@@@R          SA        A3,VDM,A2         . POST NEW DATA MODE TOO    SO
)@@G@@@G@@@R          LR        R1,VDL,A2         . GET # OF ELEMENTS TO TRANSSP
)@@G@@LATE  @F@@@R          J         CVT120            . START TRANSLATION LOSQ
)@@G@@OP    @E@@@RCVT110    DL        A3,,*A0           . GET NEXT ELEMENT    SR
)@@G@@@E@@@R          EX        CVTTMP            . CONVERT TO NEW MODE @F@@@RSS
)@@G@@          DS        A3,,*A1           . POST NEW NEXT ELEMENT     @D@@@RST
)@@G@@CVT120    JGD       R1,CVT110         . COUNT ELEMENTS@C@@@R          J SU
)@@G@@        CVT400            . DONE    @]@@@R          . @E@@@R          . SV
)@@G@@        CONVERT A NODE TO NUMERIC (# OF ELTS)   @]@@@R          . @H@@@RSW
)@@G@@CVT130    TNOD      A2 CVT999         . UNLESS ITEM IS A NODE, IT'S AN ESX
)@@G@@RROR  @E@@@R          DL        A0,VD,A0          . GET VALUE DESCRIPTORSY
)@@G@@@E@@@R          CALL      M$VDVDL           . GET CORRECT LENGTH  @F@@@RSZ
)@@G@@          LDSL      A0,18             . MOVE H1(A1) TO H2(A0)     @D@@@RTA
)@@G@@          LA,U      A0,,A0            . CLEAN UP A0   @F@@@R          CATB
)@@G@@LL      M$RESULTINT       . CREATE INTEGER RESULT     @ @@@R          JNTC
)@@G@@Z       A5,CVT999 @F@@@R          LA        A2,CVTVDA         . RECOVER TD
)@@G@@DESCRIPTOR ADDR   @F@@@R          LXM       A0,VDCC,A2        . MAINTAINTE
)@@G@@ COLUMN NUMBER    @E@@@R          DS        A0,VD,A2          . POST THETF
)@@G@@ RESULT     @F@@@R          LA,U      A0,,A2            . GET THE DESCRITG
)@@G@@PTOR HERE   @F@@@R          LA        A1,CVTMOD         . RECOVER THE 'TTH
)@@G@@O' MODE     @D@@@R          J         CVT001            . START OVER    TI
)@@G@@@]@@@R          . @B@@@R          .         CONVERTING TO A LIST  @]@@@RTJ
)@@G@@          . @E@@@RCVT200    M$TGET    CVT999 VDSIZE     . GET A LIST ELETK
)@@G@@MENT  @D@@@R          LXI,U     A1,1              . ONLY 1 ELT    @F@@@RTL
)@@G@@          LA        A0,CVTVDA         . GET ITEM DESCRIPTOR ADDR  @E@@@RTM
)@@G@@          DL        A2,VD,A0          . GET THE DATA VD     @E@@@R      TN
)@@G@@    LA        A4,CVTMOD         . GET THE RESULT MODE @F@@@R          DSTO
)@@G@@        A2,VD,A1          . POST NEW ELEMENT OF LIST  @E@@@R          SATP
)@@G@@        A4,VDM,A0         . POST THE RESULT MODE@E@@@R          SA      TQ
)@@G@@  A1,VDAW,A0        . UPDATE DESCRIPTOR   @ @@@R          J         CVT4TR
)@@G@@00    @]@@@R          . @B@@@R          .         USER CONFIGURED MODE  TS
)@@G@@@]@@@R          . @F@@@RCVT300    LA        A3,M$USERMCVT     . GET USERTT
)@@G@@ MODE CONVERTER   @F@@@R          JZ        A3,CVT999         . ERROR IFTU
)@@G@@ NO CONVERTER     @E@@@R          CALL      0,A3              . CALL USETV
)@@G@@R CONVERTER @ @@@R          JNZ       A5,CVT999 @]@@@R          . @ @@@RTW
)@@G@@          .         ALL DONE  @]@@@R          . @G@@@RCVT400    LA      TX
)@@G@@  A3,CVTVDA         . GET VALUE DESCRIPTOR ADDRESS    @C@@@R          LATY
)@@G@@        A0,VDM,A3         . MODE    @D@@@R          LA        A1,VDAW,A3TZ
)@@G@@        . (LENGTH, ADDR)@C@@@R          LA        A2,VDL,A3         . LEUA
)@@G@@NGTH  @C@@@R          LA,U      A5,0              . NO ERROR@B@@@RCVT999UB
)@@G@@    RETURN                      .   @]@@@R          . @D@V@RM$CONVERR* PUC
)@@G@@CW      'CANNOT PERFORM MODE CONVERSION.' @B@@@VM$CONVERR* PCW      'CANUD
)@@G@@NOT CONVERT VALUE'@]@@@R          . @#@@@R          END     _@@@@@C[@I[[UE
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@K/         M$DEF   @[@@@K.     @G@@@K. M$ARGCHECK - ROUUF
)@@G@@TINE TO CHECK THE NUMBER AND TYPE OF ARGUMENTS TO A   @H@@@K.           UG
)@@G@@   FUNCTION.  THE RIGHT ARGUMENT MUST BE DEFINED AS AN ARGUMENT   @ @@@KUH
)@@G@@.              LIST (MODLST). @[@@@K.     @C@@@K.  A0 = LOCAL COPY ARGUMUI
)@@G@@ENT VD BASE ADDRESS     @B@@@K.  A1 = ARGUMENT ACCEPTOR MASK ADDRESS    UJ
)@@G@@@ @@@K.  A2 = MAX # OF ARGUMENTS    @^@@@K.  LMJ  X11,M$ARGCHECK  @^@@@KUK
)@@G@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @^@@@K.  A0 = # OF ACTUAL ARGS@[@@@K.     @^@@@KUL
)@@G@@M$ARGCHECK* SUBROUTINE  @E@@@KARGVDC    LOCAL                       . VDUM
)@@G@@ BASE ADDRESS     @F@@@KARGMSK    LOCAL                       . ACCEPTORUN
)@@G@@ MASK ADDRESS     @D@@@KARGREGS   LOCAL     5                 . A0 THRU UO
)@@G@@A3, R1@G@@@K          LXI,U     A1,0              . CLEAR INCREMENT FOR UP
)@@G@@INDIRECTIONS@D@@@K          DS        A0,ARGVDC         . SAVE ADDRESSESUQ
)@@G@@@F@@@K          LA,U      A3,ARGMSKGET      . INITIALIZE COROUTINE ADDR UR
)@@G@@@F@@@K          LA        A4,VDM+SRA        . GET THE FUNC/OPER MODE    US
)@@G@@@E@@@K          TNE,U     A4,MODNUL         . IS ARGLIST NULL?    @F@@@KUT
)@@G@@          LA,U      A4,MODLST         . YES, ASSUME LIST MODE     @D@O@KUU
)@@G@@          LA        A5,PCL('ARGUMENT MODE ERROR!')    @C@@@O          LAUV
)@@G@@        A5,PCL('ARGUMENT ERROR.')   @F@@@K          JNE,U     A4,MODLST UW
)@@G@@ARG999  . MUST BE ARGUMENT LIST     @E@@@K          LR        R1,VDL+SRAUX
)@@G@@        . GET # OF ARGUMENTS  @D@@@K          LA        A5,PCL('TOO MANYUY
)@@G@@ ARGUMENTS.')     @G@@@K          JG        A2,R1 ARG999      . IF # GIVUZ
)@@G@@EN>MAX. # THEN ERROR    @F@@@K          LA        A1,VDA+SRA        . GEVA
)@@G@@T FIRST ARG ADDRESS     @F@@@K          LXI,U     A1,VDSIZE         . SEVB
)@@G@@T LIST MODE INCREMENT   @G@@@K          J         ARG030            . STVC
)@@G@@ART ARG MODE CHECK & COPY LOOP@G@@@KARG010    SZ        VDAW,A0         VD
)@@G@@  . INITIALIZE COPY TO A NULL ARG   @G@@@K          LA,U      A4,MODNUL VE
)@@G@@        . WHICH INDICATES OMITTED ARG     @ @@@K          SA        A4,VVF
)@@G@@DM,A0 @F@@@K          CALL,A3   0,A3              . GET NEXT ACCEPTOR MAVG
)@@G@@SK    @E@@@K          TG        A2,R1             . # OF ARGS < MAX?    VH
)@@G@@@F@@@K          TOP       A4,BML(MODNUL)    . YES, CAN WE OMIT THIS ARG?VI
)@@G@@@D@@@K          J         $+2               . NO, CAN'T OMIT@E@@@K      VJ
)@@G@@    J         ARG020            . YES, OMIT THIS ARG  @E@@@K          LAVK
)@@G@@        A5,PCL('MISSING REQUIRED ARGUMENT.')    @G@@@K          JNGD    VL
)@@G@@  R1,ARG999         . ACCEPT THE ARG (IF NONE, ERROR) @D@@@K          LXVM
)@@G@@        X11,VDM,A1        . GET THE MODE  @G@@@K          JOP       A4,BVN
)@@G@@ML(17) ARG015 . SKIP IF AUTO-CONVERT BIT SET    @G@@@K          SSL     VO
)@@G@@  A4,,X11           . ADJUST THE MASK BY THE MODE     @E@@@K          LAVP
)@@G@@        A5,PCL('AN ARGUMENT IS INCORRECT.')     @G@@@K          JNB     VQ
)@@G@@  A4,ARG999         . IF NO BIT FOR MODE, ARG ERROR   @E@@@KARG015    SXVR
)@@G@@        X11,VDM,A0        . POST THE COPY MODE  @E@@@K          LA      VS
)@@G@@  A5,VDCC,A1        . GET THE POSITION    @C@@@K          SA        A5,VVT
)@@G@@DCC,A0        . POST IT @E@@@K          LA        A5,VDAW,*A1       . GEVU
)@@G@@T THE DATA WORD   @E@@@K          SA        A5,VDAW,A0        . POST THEVV
)@@G@@ COPY DATA  @H@@@K          JEP       A4,BML(17) ARG020 . IF AUTO-CONVERVW
)@@G@@T OFF, GO TO NEXT ARG   @E@@@K          DS        A0,ARGREGS        . SAVX
)@@G@@VE REGS A0-A3,R1  @A@@@K          DS        A2,ARGREGS+2    @A@@@K      VY
)@@G@@    SR        R1,ARGREGS+4    @E@@@K          AND       A4,BML(17,MODNULVZ
)@@G@@) . EXTRACT THESE BITS  @E@@@K          AN        A4,A5             . ANWA
)@@G@@D REMOVE THEM     @D@@@K          LSC       A2,A4             . A3 = 34-WB
)@@G@@MODE  @ @@@K          LA,U      A1,34     @D@@@K          AN        A1,AWC
)@@G@@3             . COMPUTE MODE  @F@@@K          CONVMODE  ARG999          WD
)@@G@@  . CONVERT TO DESIRED MODE   @E@@@K          DL        A0,ARGREGS      WE
)@@G@@  . RELOAD REGS A0-A3,R1@A@@@K          DL        A2,ARGREGS+2    @A@@@KWF
)@@G@@          LR        R1,ARGREGS+4    @E@@@KARG020    AA,U      A0,VDSIZE WG
)@@G@@        . SKIP TO NEXT COPY VD@G@@@KARG030    JGD       A2,ARG010       WH
)@@G@@  . COUNT COPY MASK ELTS & CONTINUE @D@@@K          LA,U      A5,0      WI
)@@G@@        . NO ERRORS     @F@@@K          LA        A0,VDL+SRA        . REWJ
)@@G@@TURN # OF ARGS AGAIN    @B@@@KARG999    RETURN                      .   WK
)@@G@@@]@@@K          . @F@@@K          .         COROUTINE TO EXTRACT ACCEPTOWL
)@@G@@R MASK ELEMENTS   @]@@@K          . @E@@@KARGMSKGET LA,H1     A4,*ARGMSKWM
)@@G@@        . GET THE NEXT MASK   @E@@@K          CALL,A3   0,A3            WN
)@@G@@  . RETURN TO CALLER    @F@@@K          LX        X11,ARGMSK        . GEWO
)@@G@@T THE CURRENT ADDRESS   @E@@@K          LA,H2     A4,,X11           . GEWP
)@@G@@T THE NEXT MASK   @F@@@K          LX,U      X11,1,X11         . INCREMENWQ
)@@G@@T THE ADDRESS     @E@@@K          SX        X11,ARGMSK        . POST FORWR
)@@G@@ NEXT TIME  @E@@@K          CALL,A3   0,A3              . RETURN TO CALLWS
)@@G@@ER    @C@@@K          J         ARGMSKGET         . LOOP    @]@@@K      WT
)@@G@@    . @[@@@K/.    @G@@@K. M$BLANKWORD - A ROUTINE TO FINISH THE CREATIONWU
)@@G@@ OF A CHARACTER STRING  @B@@@K. RESULT BY BLANK FILLING THE LAST WORD.  WV
)@@G@@@[@@@K.     @E@@@K.  A2,A3 = STORE INDEXES INTACT FROM STASHING A STRINGWW
)@@G@@.     @^@@@K.  LMJ  X11,M$BLANKWORD @]@@@K.  A5 = 0   @E@@@K.  A0 = ADDRWX
)@@G@@ESS+1 OF LAST WORD STORED (BEFORE BLANK FILL).  @[@@@K.     @]@@@KM$BLANWY
)@@G@@KWORD*@F@@@K          ANU       A3,M$XASS         . SUBTRACT STORE TABLEWZ
)@@G@@ BASE @E@@@K          JN        A4,BW010          . SKIP IF FIELDATA    XA
)@@G@@@G@@@K          LA,U      A0,4              . COMPUTE # CHARS TO BLANK FXB
)@@G@@ILL   @D@@@K          AN        A0,A4             . A0 = [1..4]   @D@@@KXC
)@@G@@          AND,U     A0,3              . A1 = [0..3]   @D@@@K          LAXD
)@@G@@,U      A5,$CAS(' ')      . ASCII BLANK   @C@@@K          J         BW02XE
)@@G@@0             . GO BLANK@H@@@KBW010     ANU       A3,M$XFDS         . SUXF
)@@G@@BTRACT FIELDATA STORE TABLE BASE    @G@@@K          LA,U      A0,6      XG
)@@G@@        . COMPUTE # CHARS TO BLANK FILL   @D@@@K          AN        A0,AXH
)@@G@@4             . A0 = [1..6]   @E@@@K          DSL       A0,36           XI
)@@G@@  . A0=0, A1 = [1..6]   @D@@@K          DI,U      A0,6              . A1XJ
)@@G@@ = [0..5]   @E@@@K          LA,U      A5,$CFS(' ')      . GET FIELDATA BXK
)@@G@@LANK  @G@@@KBW020     LA,U      A0,1,A2           . GET LAST WORD STOREDXL
)@@G@@ PLUS ONE   @H@@@K          TNZ       A1                . DOES LAST WORDXM
)@@G@@ REALLY HAVE STUFF?     @E@@@K          AN,U      A0,1              . NOXN
)@@G@@, DON'T COUNT IT  @E@@@K          J         $+2               . START BLXO
)@@G@@ANK LOOP    @C@@@K          EX        0,*A3             . BLANK   @D@@@KXP
)@@G@@          JGD       A1,$-1            . DO ENTIRE WORD@E@@@K          LAXQ
)@@G@@,U      A5,0              . KILL ERROR FLAG     @C@@@K          J       XR
)@@G@@  0,X11             . ALL DONE@[@@@N/.    @D@@@N. M$CSCGET - RETRIEVE THXS
)@@G@@E CURRENT CSC CHARS IN A0,A1  @B@@@N. M$CSCSET - SET NEW CSC CHARS FROM XT
)@@G@@A0,A1 @[@@@N.     @ @@@N.  A0 = OBC OR 0777 (NONE)    @ @@@N.  A1 = CBC XU
)@@G@@OR 0777 (NONE)    @^@@@N.  LMJ  X11,M$CSCSET    @[@@@N.     @]@@@NM$CSCSXV
)@@G@@ET*   @G@@@N          LA,H2     A3,M$XQTMACRO     . GET CURRENTLY EXECUTXW
)@@G@@ING MACRO   @E@@@N          JZ        A3,CSET010        . SKIP IF NO MACXX
)@@G@@RO    @F@@@N          SA        A0,MXOBC,A3       . POST OPEN BRACKET CHXY
)@@G@@AR    @F@@@N          SA        A1,MXCBC,A3       . POST CLOSE BRACKET CXZ
)@@G@@HAR   @C@@@N          J         0,X11             . RETURN  @E@@@NCSET01YA
)@@G@@0   SA        A0,M$OBC          . POST KEYBOARD CHARS @B@@@N          SAYB
)@@G@@        A1,M$CBC          .   @C@@@N          J         0,X11           YC
)@@G@@  . RETURN  @[@@@N.     @^@@@N.  LMJ  X11,M$CSCGET    @^@@@N.  A0 = OBC YD
)@@G@@OR 0777     @^@@@N.  A1 = CBC OR 0777     @[@@@N.     @]@@@NM$CSCGET*   YE
)@@G@@@G@@@N          LA,H2     A1,M$XQTMACRO     . GET CURRENTLY EXECUTING MAYF
)@@G@@CRO   @E@@@N          JZ        A1,CGET010        . SKIP IF NO MACRO    YG
)@@G@@@F@@@N          LA        A0,MXOBC,A1       . GET OPEN BRACKET CHAR     YH
)@@G@@@F@@@N          LA        A1,MXCBC,A1       . GET CLOSE BRACKET CHAR    YI
)@@G@@@C@@@N          J         0,X11             . DONE    @F@@@NCGET010   LAYJ
)@@G@@        A0,M$OBC          . GET OPEN BRACKET CHAR     @F@@@N          LAYK
)@@G@@        A1,M$CBC          . GET CLOSE BRACKET CHAR    @C@@@N          J YL
)@@G@@        0,X11             . DONE    @[@@@K/.    @H@@@K. M$INDEXCHECK - RYM
)@@G@@OUTINE TO VERIFY AND VALIDATE THE INDEXES TO A GIVEN VALUE. @[@@@K.     YN
)@@G@@@ @@@K.  A0 = VALUE DESCRIPTOR PTR  @ @@@K.  A1 = INDEX DESCRIPTOR PTR  YO
)@@G@@@^@@@K.  LMJ  X11,M$INDEXCHECK@^@@@K.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @^@@@K.  A0 YP
)@@G@@= MODE OF VALUE   @E@@@K.  A1 = EFFECTIVE INDEX (ORIGIN ZERO) [0..LEN(VAYQ
)@@G@@LUE)-1]     @^@@@K.  A2 = EFFECTIVE LENGTH@[@@@K.     @^@@@KM$INDEXCHECKYR
)@@G@@* SUBROUTINE@C@@@KINDVAL    LOCAL     2                 . VALUE   @C@@@KYS
)@@G@@INDEX     LOCAL     2                 . INDEX   @E@@@K          DL      YT
)@@G@@  A2,VD,A0          . GET DESCR OF VALUE  @E@@@K          DL        A4,VYU
)@@G@@D,A1          . GET DESCR OF INDEX  @E@@@K          DS        A2,INDVAL YV
)@@G@@        . POST IN OUR SPACE   @ @@@K          DS        A4,INDEX  @E@@@KYW
)@@G@@          LA        A0,VDM+INDVAL     . GET MODE OF VALUE   @D@@@K      YX
)@@G@@    LA        A5,PCL('ITEM CANNOT BE INDEXED.') @F@@@K          TNUSR   YY
)@@G@@  A0                . IS ITEM A KNOWN MODE TYPE?@E@@@K          TZ      YZ
)@@G@@  VMPWX,A0          . NO, IS IT CANONICAL?@E@@@K          LA,U      A5,0ZA
)@@G@@              . YES, CAN BE INDEXED @F@@@K          JNZ       A5,IND999 ZB
)@@G@@        . IF A5 <> 0, CAN'T DO IT   @F@@@K          LA        A1,VDM+INDZC
)@@G@@EX      . GET THE MODE OF THE INDEX @D@@@K          LA        A5,PCL('INZD
)@@G@@DEX MUST BE INTEGER.')  @D@@@K          JNE,U     A1,MODSIN IND999  . ERZE
)@@G@@ROR IF NOT  @B@@@K          LA        A5,PCL('INDEX ERROR.')@G@@@K      ZF
)@@G@@    LA        A3,VDL+INDEX      . GET THE LENGTH OF THE INDEX     @H@@@KZG
)@@G@@          TLE,U     A3,3              . MAKE RANGE CHECK ON THE INDEX LEZH
)@@G@@NGTH  @D@@@K          TLE,U     A3,1              . MUST BE [1..2]@D@@@KZI
)@@G@@          J         IND999            . INDEX IS BAD  @G@@@K          LAZJ
)@@G@@        A1,VDA+INDEX      . GET THE ADDRESS OF THE INDEX    @F@@@K      ZK
)@@G@@    DL        A1,0,A1           . GET THE INDEX & LENGTH    @G@@@K      ZL
)@@G@@    TE,U      A3,2              . IS THERE REALLY A LENGTH FIELD? @F@@@KZM
)@@G@@          LA,U      A2,1              . NO, DEFAULT LENGTH IS ONE @G@@@KZN
)@@G@@          JP        A1,IND010         . SKIP IF INDEXING FROM THE LEFT  ZO
)@@G@@@G@@@K          AA        A1,VDL+INDVAL     . COMPUTE INDEX FROM THE RIGZP
)@@G@@HT    @E@@@K          AA,U      A1,1              . MAKE ORIGIN ONE     ZQ
)@@G@@@G@@@KIND010    AN,U      A1,1              . MAKE ORIGIN ZERO [0..LENGTZR
)@@G@@H-1]  @D@@@K          LA        A5,PCL('INDEX OUT OF RANGE.')     @F@@@KZS
)@@G@@          JN        A1,IND999         . IF NEGATIVE, BAD NEWS     @F@@@KZT
)@@G@@          LA        A3,VDL+INDVAL     . COMPUTE REMAINING LENGTH  @ @@@KZU
)@@G@@          AN        A3,A1     @F@@@K          TNE       A2,M$STARVAL    ZV
)@@G@@  . WAS LENGTH GIVEN AS '*'?  @G@@@K          LA        A2,A3           ZW
)@@G@@  . YES, USE REMAINDER AS LENGTH    @F@@@K          JN        A2,IND999 ZX
)@@G@@        . IF NEGATIVE, OUT OF RANGE @D@@@K          LA,U      A5,0      ZY
)@@G@@        . KILL ERRORS   @F@@@K          TLE       A3,A2             . ISZZ
)@@G@@ LENGTH <= REMAINDER?   @E@@@K          LA        A5,PCL('INDEX EXCEEDS AA
)@@G@@ITEM LENGTH.')    @C@@@KIND999    RETURN                      . DONE    AB
)@@G@@@[@L@K/.    @E@L@K. M$RETURNPOP - POSTAMBLE ROUTINE FOR RECUSIVE ROUTINEAC
)@@G@@S.    @[@L@K.     @F@L@K. THE EFFECT OF THIS ROUTINE IS TO POP THE CURREAD
)@@G@@NT STACK FRAME    @F@L@K. FROM THE SUBROUTINE STACK, VERIFY THE UPDATE SAE
)@@G@@TACK POINTER, AND @C@L@K. RETURN TO THE CALLER OF THE ORIGINAL ROUTINE. AF
)@@G@@@[@L@K.     @#@L@KM$ROUTINEPOP*     @G@L@K          ROUTINEPOP          AG
)@@G@@        . GENERATE THE POSTAMBLE CODE     @[@@@K/.    @E@@@K. M$STKINIT AH
)@@G@@- CREATE A NEW OPERATOR/COMPILER/SCANNER STACK. @[@@@K.     @A@@@K.  A0 AI
)@@G@@= (STKSIZE, STKINC*/6+STKPTR) @^@@@K.  LMJ  X11,M$STKINIT   @^@@@K.  A5 AJ
)@@G@@= ERROR PCW OR 0  @C@@@K.  STKPTR = (-STKINC,STKTOP) . PUSH-DOWN STACK  AK
)@@G@@@[@@@K.     @^@@@KM$STKINIT* SUBROUTINE   @#@@@KSTIARG    LOCAL   @ @@@KAL
)@@G@@STIPTR    EQUF      STIARG,,S6@ @@@KSTIINC    EQUF      STIARG,,S5@ @@@KAM
)@@G@@STISIZ    EQUF      STIARG,,H1@D@@@K          SA        A0,STIARG       AN
)@@G@@  . SAVE ARGUMENT @E@@@K          LA        A0,STISIZ         . GET REQUAO
)@@G@@ESTED SIZE  @F@@@K          AA,U      A0,2              . ADD FOR CONTROAP
)@@G@@L WORD SPACE@D@M@K          PGET                        . GO GET IT     AQ
)@@G@@@ @M@K          JNZ       A5,STI999 @D@@@M          M$PGET    STI999    AR
)@@G@@        . GO GET IT     @F@@@K          DL        A2,STKCTL         . GEAS
)@@G@@T CURRENT CONTROL WORD  @H@@@K          DS        A2,,A1            . POAT
)@@G@@ST IN FIRST WORDS OF STACK SPACE    @G@@@K          SA        A1,STKADR AU
)@@G@@        . SAVE THE STACK BASE ADDRESS     @H@@@K          LA,U      A0,2AV
)@@G@@,*A1          . GET THE STACK BOTTOM; A1=STACK TOP    @G@@@K          AAAW
)@@G@@        A0,STIINC         . ADD IN INCREMENT SO NO OVERFLOW @E@@@K      AX
)@@G@@    SA        A1,STKTOP         . POST THE STACK TOP  @F@@@K          SAAY
)@@G@@        A0,STKBOT         . POST THE STACK BOTTOM     @F@@@K          LNAZ
)@@G@@        A1,STIINC         . GET THE NEGATIVE INCREMENT@G@@@K          LXBA
)@@G@@I       A1,STKTOP         . AND THE INITIAL STACK ADDRESS   @E@@@K      BB
)@@G@@    SSC       A1,18             . = -STKINC,STKTOP    @F@@@K          LABC
)@@G@@        A0,STIPTR         . GET THE STACK POINTER     @F@@@K          SABD
)@@G@@        A1,,A0            . POST THE STACK POINTER    @C@@@KSTI999    REBE
)@@G@@TURN                      . DONE    @[@@@K.     @F@@@K. M$STKTERM - RELEBF
)@@G@@ASE THE CURRENT STACK; RESTORE THE PREVIOUS ONE.@[@@@K.     @^@@@K.  LMJBG
)@@G@@  X11,M$STKTERM   @^@@@K.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @[@@@K.     @^@@@KM$STKTBH
)@@G@@ERM* SUBROUTINE   @F@@@K          LA        A5,PCL('NO STACK TO RELEASE!BI
)@@G@@ (M$STKTERM)')    @F@@@K          LA        A0,STKADR         . GET THE BJ
)@@G@@CURRENT STACK BASE@F@@@K          JZ        A0,STT999         . ERROR IFBK
)@@G@@ NO CURRENT STACK @G@@@K          DL        A1,,A0            . GET THE BL
)@@G@@PREVIOUS CONTROL INFO   @C@@@K          DS        A1,STKCTL         . POBM
)@@G@@ST IT @F@M@K          PREL                        . RELEASE THE CURRENT BN
)@@G@@STACK @F@@@M          M$PREL                      . RELEASE THE CURRENT BO
)@@G@@STACK @C@@@KSTT999    RETURN                      . DONE    @]@@@K      BP
)@@G@@    . @#@@@K          END     _@@@@@C[@C[@C[@C[@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/     BQ
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. M$VDCOPY - ROUTINE TO COPY A VALUE.     BR
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @ @@@@.  A0,A1 = DESCRIPTOR TO COPY @^@@@@.  LMJ X11,M$VDCOPBS
)@@G@@Y     @^@@@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @ @@@@.  A1 = NEW DESCRIPTOR POINTERBT
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@. OR: @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.  A0,A1 = DESCRIPTOR TO COPY BU
)@@G@@@^@@@@.  LMJ  X11,M$VDCOPYV   @^@@@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @ @@@@.  A0,BV
)@@G@@A1 = NEW DESCRIPTOR     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. M$VDCOPYV COPIES ONLY THE VABW
)@@G@@LUE OF THE DESCRIPTOR AND RETURNS THE     @G@@@@. DESCRIPTOR OF THE NEW BX
)@@G@@COPY OF THE DATA IN A0,A1.  M$VDCOPY COPIES     @G@@@@. THE VALUE OF THEBY
)@@G@@ DESCRIPTOR AND ALSO CREATES A NEW DESCRIPTOR AND     @B@@@@. RETURNS THBZ
)@@G@@E ADDRESS OF THE DESCRIPTOR.  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. THIS ROUTINE HANDLES ACA
)@@G@@LL DATA TYPES: NUMBERS, CHARACTERS, LISTS, AND  @G@@@@. TABLES.  LISTS ACB
)@@G@@ND TABLES ARE COPIED RECURSIVELY ELEMENT BY ELEMENT,  @G@@@@. SUBSCRIPT CC
)@@G@@BY SUBSCRIPT, RESPECTIVELY, SO THAT THERE ARE NO MULTIPLE   @B@@@@. REFECD
)@@G@@RENCES TO THE SAME DATA CREATED.    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@M$VDCOPY* LA,U    CE
)@@G@@  A2,1              . SET DESCRIPTOR COPY FLAG  @C@@@@          J       CF
)@@G@@  VDCOPY            . GO DO IT@F@@@@M$VDCOPYV* LA,U     A2,0            CG
)@@G@@  . CLEAR DESCRIPTOR COPY FLAG@B@@@@VDCOPY    ROUTINE                   CH
)@@G@@  .   @F@@@@VDCADDR   LOCAL                       . PREVIOUS VALUE ADDRECI
)@@G@@SS    @E@@@@VDCNEW    LOCAL     2                 . NEW VALUE DESCRIPTORCJ
)@@G@@@E@@@@VDCFLAG   LOCAL                       . DESCRIPTOR COPY FLAG@F@@@@CK
)@@G@@VDCLEN    LOCAL                       . CORE LENGTH OF NORMAL DATA@F@@@@CL
)@@G@@VDCADRS   LOCAL     2                 . NEW, OLD LIST ADDRESSES   @E@@@@CM
)@@G@@VDCCNT    EQUF      VDCLEN            . LIST ELEMENT COUNT  @E@@@@VDCTRPCN
)@@G@@    EQUF      VDCLEN            . TRAVERSAL PARAMETER @F@@@@VDCSSVD   EQCO
)@@G@@UF      VDCADRS           . TABLE SUBSCRIPT DESCRIPTOR@F@@@@          SACP
)@@G@@        A2,VDCFLAG        . POST DESCRIPTOR COPY FLAG @E@@@@          SACQ
)@@G@@        A1,VDCADDR        . SAVE ORIGNAL ADDRESS@H@@@@          DS      CR
)@@G@@  A0,VDCNEW         . POST AS NEW VALUE (ADDR WILL CHANGE)  @E@@@@      CS
)@@G@@    SSL       A0,30             . UNALIGN THE MODE    @D@@@@          TNCT
)@@G@@E,U     A0,MODNUL         . NULL MODE?    @H@@@@          SZ        VDAWCU
)@@G@@+VDCNEW       . YES, MAKE SURE ACCESS WORD IS NULL TOO@E@@@@          JECV
)@@G@@,U      A0,MODNUL MVDC010 . ALL DONE, IF NULL   @F@@@@          JE,U    CW
)@@G@@  A0,MODTBL MVDC050 . GO HANDLE TABLE SEPERATELY@I@@@[          JEZ     CX
)@@G@@  VMEBS,A0 MVDC070  . IF ELEMENT SIZE ZERO, GO HANDLE USER-MOD    @G@@@@CY
)@@G@@          LA,U      A0,VDCNEW         . GET PTR TO VALUE DESCRIPTOR     CZ
)@@G@@@G@@@@          CALL      M$ITEMLENGTH      . CALCULATE THE # WORDS NEEDDA
)@@G@@ED    @ @@@@          JNZ       A5,MVDC999@E@@@@          SA        A0,VDB
)@@G@@DCLEN         . SAVE CORE LENGTH    @E@#@@          PGET                DC
)@@G@@        . GET PERM CORE SPACE @B@#@@          JNZ       A5,MVDC999      DD
)@@G@@  .   @E@@@#          M$PGET    MVDC999           . GET PERM CORE SPACE DE
)@@G@@@F@@@@          SA        A1,VDA+VDCNEW     . POST NEW DATA ADDRESS     DF
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LA        A0,VDM+VDCNEW     . GET THE VALUE MODE  @F@@@@DG
)@@G@@          JE,U      A0,MODLST MVDC020 . NOW HANDLE LIST SEPERATELY@F@@@@DH
)@@G@@          MOVE      A1 A0,VDCADDR,,H2 VDCLEN,,W . MOVE THE DATA   @F@@@@DI
)@@G@@MVDC010   DL        A0,VDCNEW         . GET THE NEW DESCRIPTOR    @D@@@@DJ
)@@G@@          LA,U      A5,0              . POST NO ERRORS@F@@@@          JEDK
)@@G@@Z       VDCFLAG MVDC999   . DONE IF NO DESCRIPTOR     @E@#@@          PGDL
)@@G@@ET      VDSIZE            . GET THE DESCRIPTOR  @D@#@@          JNZ     DM
)@@G@@  A5,MVDC900        . SKIP IF NOT OK@E@@@#          M$PGET    MVDC900 VDDN
)@@G@@SIZE    . GET THE DESCRIPTOR  @F@@@@          DL        A2,VDCNEW       DO
)@@G@@  . RECOVER THE NEW DESCRIPTOR@H@@@@          DS        A2,VD,A1        DP
)@@G@@  . POST THE DESCRIPTOR IN ITS NEW PLACE  @C@@@@          J         MVDCDQ
)@@G@@999           . DONE    @]@@@@          . @D@@@@          .         COPYDR
)@@G@@ A LIST, ELEMENT BY ELEMENT.  @]@@@@          . @E@@@@MVDC020   LA      DS
)@@G@@  A2,VDA+VDCNEW     . GET THE NEW ADDRESS @E@@@@          LA        A3,VDT
)@@G@@DCADDR        . GET THE OLD ADDRESS @D@@@@          LXI,U     A2,VDSIZE DU
)@@G@@        . SET INCRS     @ @@@@          LXI,U     A3,VDSIZE @D@@@@      DV
)@@G@@    LA        A4,VDL+VDCNEW     . GET THE LENGTH@F@@@@          J       DW
)@@G@@  MVDC040           . START THE LIST COPY LOOP  @G@@@@MVDC030   DL      DX
)@@G@@  A0,VD,*A3         . GET THE CURRENT ELT DESCRIPTOR  @D@@@@          DSDY
)@@G@@        A2,VDCADRS        . SAVE ADDRESSES@D@@@@          SA        A4,VDZ
)@@G@@DCCNT         . SAVE THE COUNT@D@@@@          CALL      M$VDCOPYV       EA
)@@G@@  . COPY THE VALUE@F@@@@          JNZ       A5,MVDC910        . IF ERROREB
)@@G@@, EXIT CAREFULLY  @G@@@@          DL        A2,VDCADRS        . RECOVER EC
)@@G@@THE ELEMENT INDEXES     @F@@@@          LA        A4,VDCCNT         . REED
)@@G@@COVER THE ELEMENT COUNT @G@@@@          DS        A0,VD,*A2         . POEE
)@@G@@ST NEW LIST ELEMENT DESCRIPTOR@H@@@@MVDC040   JGD       A4,MVDC030      EF
)@@G@@  . COUNT ELEMENTS & CONTINUE IF MORE     @D@@@@          J         MVDCEG
)@@G@@010           . GO FINISH UP  @]@@@@          . @E@@@@          .       EH
)@@G@@  COPY A TABLE, SUBSCRIPT BY SUBSCRIPT    @]@@@@          . @G@@@@MVDC05EI
)@@G@@0   LA        A0,AVLNN,A1       . GET # OF NODES IN THE TABLE     @G@@@@EJ
)@@G@@          SA        A0,VDL+VDCNEW     . POST A CORRECT LENGTH FIELD     EK
)@@G@@@E@@@@          CALL      M$NEWTABLE        . GET A NEW TABLE     @B@@@@EL
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,MVDC999        .   @F@@@@          SA        A1,VEM
)@@G@@DA+VDCNEW     . POST NEW TABLE ADDRESS    @F@@@@          LA        A0,VEN
)@@G@@DCADDR        . GET OLD TABLE ADDRESS     @E@@@@          LA        A0,AEO
)@@G@@VLROOT,A0     . GET THE ROOT NODE   @F@@@@          LXI,U     A0,INORDEREP
)@@G@@        . GET THE TRAVERSAL TYPE    @G@@@@          SA        A0,VDCTRP EQ
)@@G@@        . INIT THE TRAVERSAL PARAMETER    @F@@@@MVDC060   AVLTRA    VDCTER
)@@G@@RP MVDC010    . TRAVERSE ENTIRE OLD TREE  @E@@@@          SA        A0,VES
)@@G@@DCTRP         . POST NEXT PARAMETER @H@@@@          LA        A1,SSM,A0 ET
)@@G@@        . CONSTRUCT A DESCRIPTOR FOR SUBSCRIPT  @ @@@@          LSSL    EU
)@@G@@  A1,30     @F@@@@          LA,U      A2,SSD,A0         . THE SUBSCRIPT EV
)@@G@@ADDRESS     @D@@@@          LXI       A2,SSL,A0         . LENGTH OF SAMEEW
)@@G@@@E@@@@          DS        A1,VDCSSVD        . SAVE SUBSCRIPT VD   @G@@@@EX
)@@G@@          LA        A2,SSVL,A0        . GET LINK TO SUBSCRIPT VALUE     EY
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LA,U      A0,VDCNEW         . GET THE DESCRIPTOR OF TABLEZ
)@@G@@E     @G@@@@          LA,U      A1,VDCSSVD        . GET THE SUBSCRIPT DEFA
)@@G@@SCRIPTOR    @G@@@@          CALL      M$SSINSERT        . INSERT THE SUBFB
)@@G@@SCRIPT WITH VALUE @F@@@@          JNZ       A5,MVDC900        . IF ERRORFC
)@@G@@, EXIT CAREFULLY  @G@@@@          J         MVDC060           . COPY MORFD
)@@G@@E UNTIL TRAVERSAL DONE  @]@@@[          . @B@@@[          .         COPYFE
)@@G@@ A USER-MODE VALUE@]@@@[          . @E@@@[MVDC070   LA        A3,M$USERVFF
)@@G@@DCOPY   . GET USER COPIER     @F@^@[          LA        A5,PCL('USER-MODFG
)@@G@@E VALUE CANNOT BE COPIED.')   @E@@@^          LA        A5,PCL('USER VALFH
)@@G@@UE CANNOT BE COPIED.')  @E@@@[          JZ        A3,MVDC999        . CHFI
)@@G@@ECK OUT ON ERRORS @F@@@[          DL        A0,VDCNEW         . GET DESCFJ
)@@G@@RIPTOR TO COPY    @E@@@[          CALL      0,A3              . CALL USEFK
)@@G@@R COPIER    @ @@@[          JNZ       A5,MVDC999@D@@@[          DS      FL
)@@G@@  A0,VDCNEW         . POST RESULT   @D@@@[          J         MVDC010   FM
)@@G@@        . GO FINISH UP  @]@@@@          . @G@@@@          .         ERROFN
)@@G@@R ACQUIRING NEW DESCRIPTOR - RELEASE NEW VALUE  @]@@@@          . @D@@@@FO
)@@G@@MVDC900   SA        A5,VDCADDR        . SAVE ERROR PCW@F@@@@          DLFP
)@@G@@        A0,VDCNEW         . RECOVER NEW DESCRIPTOR    @D@@@@          CAFQ
)@@G@@LL      M$VDERS           . ERASE NEW DATA@E@@@@          LA        A5,VFR
)@@G@@DCADDR        . GET PREVIOUS ERROR  @E@@@@          J         MVDC999   FS
)@@G@@        . RETURN WITH BAD NEWS@]@@@@          . @D@@@@          .       FT
)@@G@@  ERROR CREATING A LIST ELEMENT COPY@]@@@@          . @G@@@@MVDC910   LAFU
)@@G@@        A0,VDL+VDCNEW     . GET # OF SUPPOSED ELTS IN LIST  @F@@@@      FV
)@@G@@    AN        A0,VDCCNT         . = ACTUAL # OF ELTS IN LIST@G@@@@      FW
)@@G@@    SA        A0,VDL+VDCNEW     . UPDATE DESCRIPTOR FOR RELEASE   @F@@@@FX
)@@G@@          J         MVDC900           . GO RELEASE NEW LIST COPY  @]@@@@FY
)@@G@@          . @C@@@@MVDC999   RETURN                      . ALL DONE@[@@@@FZ
)@@G@@/.    @C@@@@. M$VDERS - ROUTINE TO ERASE A VALUE DESCRIPTOR @[@@@@.     GA
)@@G@@@ @@@@.  A0,A1 = VALUE DESCRIPTOR   @^@@@@.  LMJ  X11,M$VDERS     @^@@@@GB
)@@G@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0. @[@@@@.     @#@@@@M$VDERS*  ROUTINE @D@@@@MVDPTRGC
)@@G@@    LOCAL                       . TABLE POINTER @G@@@@MVDCNT    LOCAL   GD
)@@G@@  2                 . COUNT & INDEX FOR LIST ERASE    @E@@@@          LAGE
)@@G@@,U      A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR REG     @D@@@@          SSL     GF
)@@G@@  A0,30             . A0 = MODE     @D@@@@          JE,U      A0,MODLST GG
)@@G@@MVDE020 . SKIP IF A LIST@F@@@@          JNE,U     A0,MODTBL MVDE060 . SKGH
)@@G@@IP AHEAD IF NOT A TABLE @]@@@@          . @A@@@@          .         ERASGI
)@@G@@E A TABLE   @]@@@@          . @E@@@@          SA        A1,MVDPTR       GJ
)@@G@@  . SAVE TABLE ADDRESS  @H@@@@MVDE010   LA,U      A1,1              . DEGK
)@@G@@LETE THE FIRST NODE IN THE TABLE    @F@@@@          LA        A0,MVDPTR GL
)@@G@@        . GET THE TABLE ADDRESS     @D@@@@          AVLDR               GM
)@@G@@        . DELETE BY RANK@F@@@@          JZ        A2,MVDE050        . SKGN
)@@G@@IP IF NO MORE DELETED   @D@@@@          CALL      M$SSNERS          . ERGO
)@@G@@ASE THE NODE@F@@@@          J         MVDE010           . DO UNTIL NO MOGP
)@@G@@RE NODES    @]@@@@          . @A@@@@          .         ERASE A LIST    GQ
)@@G@@@]@@@@          . @F@@@@MVDE020   DSL       A1,18             . A1 = LENGR
)@@G@@GTH, A2 = ADDR*/18@D@@@@          SSL       A2,18             . A2 = ADDGS
)@@G@@R     @F@@@@          SA        A2,MVDPTR         . SAVE LIST BASE ADDREGT
)@@G@@SS    @E@@@@          J         MVDE040           . START RELEASE LOOP  GU
)@@G@@@F@@@@MVDE030   DS        A1,MVDCNT         . SAVE COUNT & CURRENT INDEXGV
)@@G@@@F@@@@          DL        A0,VD,A2          . GET THE CURRENT DESCRIPTORGW
)@@G@@@E@@@@          CALL      M$VDERS           . ERASE THAT VALUE    @E@@@@GX
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,MVDE999        . CHECK OUT ON ERRORS @F@@@@      GY
)@@G@@    DL        A1,MVDCNT         . RECOVER COUNT & INDEX     @G@@@@      GZ
)@@G@@    AA,U      A2,VDSIZE         . SKIP TO THE NEXT DESCRIPTOR     @F@@@@HA
)@@G@@MVDE040   JGD       A1,MVDE030        . COUNT EACH DESCRIPTOR     @F@@@@HB
)@@G@@MVDE050   LA        A1,MVDPTR         . RESTORE TREE/LIST ADDRESS @D@@@[HC
)@@G@@          J         MVDE070           . GO FINISH UP  @]@@@[          . HD
)@@G@@@B@@@[          .         NORMAL OR USER VALUE  @]@@@[          . @G@@@[HE
)@@G@@MVDE060   JNEZ      VMEBS,A0 MVDE070  . IF ELEMENT BIT SIZE DEFINED, OK HF
)@@G@@@E@@@]          JE,U      A0,MODNUL MVDE999 . IF NULL MODE, DONE  @]@@@[HG
)@@G@@          . @C@@@[          .         ERASE A USER-MODE VALUE     @]@@@[HH
)@@G@@          . @G@@@[          LA        A3,M$USERVDERS    . GET USER-MODE HI
)@@G@@VD ERASER ROUTINE @E@^@[          LA        A5,PCL('CANNOT ERASE USER-MOHJ
)@@G@@DE VALUE.') @D@@@^          LA        A5,PCL('CANNOT ERASE USER VALUE.')HK
)@@G@@@F@@@[          JZ        A3,MVDE999        . ERROR OUT IF NO ROUTINE   HL
)@@G@@@H@@@[          LSSL      A0,30             . REALIGN MODE FOR NORMAL DEHM
)@@G@@SCRIPTOR    @E@@@[          CALL      0,A3              . CALL ERASER ROHN
)@@G@@UTINE @F@@@[          J         MVDE999           . OK OR RETURN WITH ERHO
)@@G@@ROR   @]@@@[          . @D@@@[          .         ERASE NORMAL VALUE (NOHP
)@@G@@N-USER)     @]@@@[          . @E@[@@MVDE060   LA,U      A0,,A1          HQ
)@@G@@  . GET DATA ADDRESS    @E@@@[MVDE070   LA,U      A0,,A1            . GEHR
)@@G@@T DATA ADDRESS    @E@@@@          JZ        A0,MVDE999        . QUIT IF HS
)@@G@@NO DATA     @E@#@@          PREL                        . RELEASE THE DAHT
)@@G@@TA    @E@@@#          M$PREL                      . RELEASE THE DATA    HU
)@@G@@@C@@@@MVDE999   RETURN                      . DONE    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@HV
)@@G@@/.    @F@@@@. M$VDVDL - ROUTINE TO CORRECT THE LENGTH FIELD OF A DESCRIPHW
)@@G@@TOR.  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@.  A0,A1 = DESCRIPTOR   @^@@@@.  LMJ  X11,M$VDVDHX
)@@G@@L     @A@@@@.  A0,A1 = DESCRIPTOR (VDL UPDATED) @[@@@@.     @E@@@@M$VDVDHY
)@@G@@L*  SSL       A0,30             . UNALIGN THE MODE    @E@@@@          TNHZ
)@@G@@E,U     A0,MODTBL         . TABLE DESCRIPTOR?   @H@@@@          LXI     IA
)@@G@@  A1,AVLNN,A1       . YES, CORRECTLY SET THE LENGTH FIELD   @E@@@@      IB
)@@G@@    LSSL      A0,30             . REALIGN THE MODE    @C@@@@          J IC
)@@G@@        0,X11             . ALL DONE@]@@@@          . @#@@@@          ENID
)@@G@@D     _@@@@@C[JC[@C[@C[@C[@C[@C[@C[@C[@C@ @-@[@[C[@C[@C[@C[@C[@C[@C[@C[@IE

)@@G@@M$CONVMODE  M$XASS      M$XFDS      M$XQTMACRO  M$OBC       M$CBC       LO
)@@G@@M$MODETABLE M$STARVAL   M$COREPRMGETM$STACKCTL  M$COREPRMRELM$ARGCHECK  LP
)@@G@@@@[@@@@@@@@@M$BLANKWORD @@[@@@@@@@[^M$CSCGET    @@[@@@@@@@[-M$CSCSET    LQ
)@@G@@@@[@@@@@@@[TM$INDEXCHECK@@[@@@@@@@[(M$STKINIT   @@[@@@@@@@]LM$STKTERM   LR
)@@G@@@@[@@@@@@@]>@F@@@F          LA,S2     A0,0,A1           . GET VECTOR TABLS
)@@G@@LE FLAG     @F@@@F          LA,H2     A1,0,A1           . GET ADDRESS ATLT
)@@G@@ THE INDEX  @H@@@F      *[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@M/         M$DEF   @H@@@M      LU
)@@G@@    E$FIELDS  0,X1              . DEFINE THE FIELDS IN THE EDIT$ PACKET LV
)@@G@@@[@@@M.     @F@@@M. ?<NUM> - PRINTS THE LAST <NUM> COMMANDS FROM THE HISLW
)@@G@@TORY QUEUE. @[@@@M.     @F@@@M. !<NUM> - EXECUTES THE <NUM>'TH COMMAND FLX
)@@G@@ROM THE HISTORY QUEUE.  @[@@@M.     @B@@@M. ? - PRINTS THE LAST COMMAND LY
)@@G@@ENTERED.    @[@@@M.     @B@@@M. ! - EXECUTES THE LAST COMMAND ENTERED.  LZ
)@@G@@@[@@@M.     @#@@@MM$COMHISTORY*     @^@@@M          SUBROUTINE    @E@@@MMA
)@@G@@HISTXQTF  LOCAL                       . HISTORY EXECUTE FLAG@E@@@MHISTLIMB
)@@G@@NK  LOCAL                       . LINK TO A RECORD    @E@@@MHISTINDEX LOMC
)@@G@@CAL                       . INDEX OF A RECORD   @D@@@MHISTSAVE  LOCAL   MD
)@@G@@  2                 . SAVE SPACE    @D@@@MHISTCHAR  LOCAL     . SPACE FOME
)@@G@@R THE EXTENSION CHAR    @E@@@M          SA        A0,HISTXQTF       . SAMF
)@@G@@VE THE XQT FLAG   @H@@@M          JNEZ      M$COMLINE HIST005 . IF WE'REMG
)@@G@@ A MACRO COMMAND, DON'T POP   @E@@@M          QPOP      M$HISTORYQ      MH
)@@G@@  . POP OUR COMMAND     @E@@@M          JNZ       A5,HIST999        . CHMI
)@@G@@ECK FOR ERRORS    @F@@@M          PREL      0,A1,U            . RELEASE MJ
)@@G@@THE BUFFER FOR IT @D@@@M          JNZ       A5,HIST999        . CHECK ERMK
)@@G@@RORS  @E@@@M          L         A0,M$COMCNT       . GET COMMAND COUNT   ML
)@@G@@@I@@@M          AN,U      A0,1              . DECREMENT BY ONE, WE DON'TMM
)@@G@@ COUNT THIS 1     @F@@@M          S         A0,M$COMCNT       . SAVE THEMN
)@@G@@ NEW REDUCED VALUE@F@@@MHIST005   CALL      M$MORECMD         . SEE IF TMO
)@@G@@HERE'S AN ARGUMENT@F@@@M          JNZ       A0,HIST010        . IF ARG PMP
)@@G@@RESENT, SKIP AHEAD@E@N@M          LA,U      A0,0              . DEFAULT MQ
)@@G@@ARG IS 1.   @E@@@N          LA        A0,M$COMCNT       . DEFAULT ARG ISMR
)@@G@@ 1.   @E@@@P          TNZ       HISTXQTF          . ARE WE LISTING?     MS
)@@G@@@H@@@P          L,U       A0,1              . ASSUME ONLY LISTING MOST RMT
)@@G@@ECENT CMND  @D@@@M          J         HIST020           . SKIP AHEAD    MU
)@@G@@@E@@@MHIST010   CALL      M$SCANINT         . SCAN AN INTEGER     @ @@@MMV
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,HIST999@]@@@MHIST020   . @C@Q@M          LA      MW
)@@G@@  A5,PCL('DOMAIN ERROR.')     @E@@@Q          LA        A5,PCL('HISTORY MX
)@@G@@INDEX OUT OF RANGE.')   @ @@@M          JN        A0,HIST999@F@@@M      MY
)@@G@@    LA        A1,UX(QHLAST)+M$HISTORYQ . GET THE LAST LINK  @E@@@M      MZ
)@@G@@    JEZ       HISTXQTF HIST100  . IF LISTING, GO LIST @E@O@M          ANNA
)@@G@@        A0,M$COMCNT       . CALC RELATIVE VALUE @F@@@O          LA      NB
)@@G@@  A2,M$COMCNT       . GET COUNT OF COMMANDS     @F@@@O          ANA,U   NC
)@@G@@  A2,,A0            . SUBTRACT TO GET RELATIVE  @D@@@O          L       ND
)@@G@@  A0,A2             . COPY VALUE    @C@@@M          JN        A0,HIST999NE
)@@G@@        . ERROR   @E@@@MHIST030   JZ        A1,HIST999        . ERROR IFNF
)@@G@@ NOT THERE  @G@@@M          JZ        A0,HIST040        . SKIP OUT IF ATNG
)@@G@@ DESIRED RECORD   @F@@@M          LA        A1,QRPREV,A1      . LINK TO NH
)@@G@@PREVIOUS RECORD   @E@@@M          JGD       A0,HIST030        . COUNT & NI
)@@G@@TRY AGAIN   @F@@@MHIST040   LXI       A1,QRLEN,A1       . POST THE RECORNJ
)@@G@@D LENGTH    @F@@@M          LXM,U     A1,QRBUF,A1       . GET THE RECORDNK
)@@G@@ ADDRESS    @G@@@M          QPUSH     M$INPUTQ          . PUSH IMAGE ONTNL
)@@G@@O THE INPUT QUEUE @E@@@M          JNZ       A5,HIST999        . IF ERRORNM
)@@G@@, CHECK OUT @G@@@M          LA        A2,M$COMLINE      . GET LAST COMMANN
)@@G@@ND LINE NUMBER    @F@@@M          SA        A2,QRLINE,A1      . POST LINNO
)@@G@@E # OF NEW COMMAND@D@@@M          LA,U      A4,1              . SET DONENP
)@@G@@ FLAG @C@@@M          J         HIST999           . QUIT    @[@@@M.     NQ
)@@G@@@^@@@M. LIST THE HISTORY QUEUE@[@@@M.     @F@@@MHIST100   JZ        A1,HNR
)@@G@@IST150        . EXIT QUIETLY IF NO HISTORY@D@@@M          LA        A2,MNS
)@@G@@$COMCNT       . COUNT RECORDS @F@@@M          AA,U      A2,1            NT
)@@G@@  . BUMP THE VALUE BY ONE     @F@@@M          JGD       A0,HIST110      NU
)@@G@@  . DECREMENT REPEAT COUNT    @G@@@MHIST110   JZ        A1,HIST120      NV
)@@G@@  . IF NO MORE LINKS, GET FIRST     @E@@@M          AN,U      A2,1      NW
)@@G@@        . COUNT ANOTHER RECORD@H@@@M          JZ        A0,HIST130      NX
)@@G@@  . IF ZERO, WE'RE AT DESIRED START RECORD@F@@@M          LA        A1,QNY
)@@G@@RPREV,A1      . LINK TO PREVIOUS RECORD   @F@@@M          JGD       A0,HNZ
)@@G@@IST110        . COUNT & CHECK NEXT RECORD @F@@@MHIST120   LA        A1,UOA
)@@G@@X(QHFIRST)+M$HISTORYQ . START AT THE TOP  @F@@@M          JZ        A1,HOB
)@@G@@IST150        . IF NONE, QUIT QUIETLY     @E@@@MHIST130   DS        A1,HOC
)@@G@@ISTLINK       . SAVE LINK AND INDEX @D@@@M          M$EOPENA  M$EPKT M$IOD
)@@G@@MAGE    . OPEN EDITING  @D@@@M          LA,U      A0,1              . GEOE
)@@G@@T A BIT     @F@@@M          SA        A0,EASCIN         . SAY WE'VE GOT OF
)@@G@@ASCII INPUT @]@@@MHIST140     @E@@@M          L,U       A0,$CAS(':')    OG
)@@G@@   . GET INITIAL MARKER @E@@@M          S         A0,HISTCHAR       . SAOH
)@@G@@VE IT FOR EDIT$   @G@@@M          L         A2,HISTLINK       . GET POINOI
)@@G@@TER TO CURRENT ENTRY    @F@@@M          L,U       A1,QRBUF,A2       . GEOJ
)@@G@@T ADDRESS OF THE THING  @F@@@M          L         A0,QRLEN,A2       . ANOK
)@@G@@D GET THE LENGTH TOO    @E@@@M          DS        A0,HISTSAVE       . SAOL
)@@G@@VE THE VALUES     @[@@@M.     @E@@@M.  HERE WE LOOP UNTIL THE ENTIRE IMAOM
)@@G@@GE HAS BEEN PRINTED.    @H@@@M.  THIS IS JUST IN CASE THE IMAGE IS LONGEON
)@@G@@R THAN CAN BE PRINTED BY A SINGLE   @^@@@M.   PRINT$/APRINT$.     @[@@@MOO
)@@G@@.     @]@@@MHIST145   . @G@@@M          L         A0,HISTINDEX      . GEOP
)@@G@@T THE INDEX OF THIS COMMAND   @D@@@M          E$DECF    4               OQ
)@@G@@  . PUT IT IN     @F@@@M          L         A0,HISTCHAR       . GET THE OR
)@@G@@CHAR TO INSERT    @F@@@M          E$CHAR                      . PUT IN EOS
)@@G@@ITHER A ":" OR ">"@E@@@M          E$SKIP    2                 . THEN TWOOT
)@@G@@ SPACES     @D@@@M          L         A0,HISTSAVE       . GET THE LENGTHOU
)@@G@@@E@@@M          TG,U      A0,18             . IS IT TOO LONG?     @F@@@MOV
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,18             . DECREMENT THE WORD COUNT  @E@@@MOW
)@@G@@          L         A1,HISTSAVE       . GET THE WORD COUNT  @F@@@M      OX
)@@G@@    ANU,U     A1,,A0            . GET THE NEW WORD COUNT    @F@@@M      OY
)@@G@@    S         A2,HISTSAVE       . SAVE THE NEW WORD COUNT   @E@@@M      OZ
)@@G@@    L         A1,HISTSAVE+1     . GET THE ADDRESS     @E@@@M          AUPA
)@@G@@,U      A1,18             . GET THE NEW ADDRESS @F@@@M          TNE,U   PB
)@@G@@  A0,18             . IS IT THE MAX LENGTH?     @E@@@M          S       PC
)@@G@@  A2,HISTSAVE+1     . SAVE THENEW ADDRESS @D@@@M          DSC       A0,3PD
)@@G@@6             . SWAP A0/A1    @D@@@M          LN,U      A1,,A1          PE
)@@G@@  . GET CHAR COUNT@G@@@M          E$COPY                      . COPY THEPF
)@@G@@ STUFF INTO THE BUFFER  @C@@@M          M$EPRT                      . PRPG
)@@G@@INT IT@B@@@M          E$RASE                      .   @E@@@M          L,PH
)@@G@@U       A0,$CAS('>')      . GET OTHER CHARACTER @C@@@M          S       PI
)@@G@@  A0,HISTCHAR       . SAVE IT @F@@@M          TZ        HISTSAVE        PJ
)@@G@@  . IS THE WORD COUNT ZERO?   @F@@@M          J         HIST145         PK
)@@G@@  . NOPE, PRINT SOME MORE     @E@@@M          L         A2,HISTLINK     PL
)@@G@@  . GET CURRENT INDEX   @F@@@M          LA        A2,QRNEXT,A2      . LIPM
)@@G@@NK TO THE NEXT RECORD   @E@@@M          SA        A2,HISTLINK       . REPN
)@@G@@PLACE THE LINK    @F@@@M          LA        A0,HISTINDEX      . GET THE PO
)@@G@@CURRENT INDEX     @E@@@M          AA,U      A0,1              . COUNT ITPP
)@@G@@ DOWN TO A1 @E@@@M          SA        A0,HISTINDEX      . POST THE NEXT PQ
)@@G@@INDEX @E@@@M          JNEZ      HISTLINK HIST140  . LOOP IF MORE RECORDSPR
)@@G@@@E@@@M          M$ECLOSE                    . TURN OFF EDITING    @C@@@MPS
)@@G@@HIST150   DL        A4,M$DONE         . ALL DONE@[@@@M.     @#@@@MHIST99PT
)@@G@@9   RETURN  @[@@@M.     @#@@@M          END     _@@@@@UNT ZERO?   @F@@@MPU
)@@G@@          J         HIST*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@U/         M$DEF   @[@@@U.     PV
)@@G@@@H@@@U. M$CALLSUBST - ROUTINE TO PERFORM SYMBOLIC SUBSTITUTION ON CURRENPW
)@@G@@T IMAGE.    @[@@@U.     @B@@@U.  A0 = M$READBUFFER IMAGE WORD LENGTH.   PX
)@@G@@@^@@@U.  LMJ  X11,M$CALLSUBST @^@@@U.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @F@@@U.  A0 PY
)@@G@@= RESULTING IMAGE WORD LENGTH (IMAGE IS IN M$READBUFFER).   @[@@@U.     PZ
)@@G@@@I@@@U. THE CURRENT IMAGE IS EXAMINED FOR THE OPEN AND CLOSE SUBSTITUTIOQA
)@@G@@N CHARACTERS.     @G@@@U. WHEN AN OPEN SUBSTITUTION CHARACTER IS FOUND, QB
)@@G@@THE STRING OF CHARACTERS@H@@@U. BETWEEN IT AND THE MATCHING CLOSE SUB CHQC
)@@G@@AR IS TRANSFERED TO A TEMPORARY     @G@@@U. BUFFER TO BE EVALUATED BY M$QD
)@@G@@EVALIMAGE.  THE RESULTING VALUE IS THEN   @H@@@U. CONVERTED TO ASCII ANDQE
)@@G@@ SUBSTITUTED BACK INTO THE INPUT IMAGE IN PLACE OF    @B@@@U. THE ORIGINQF
)@@G@@AL SUBSTITUTION EXPRESSION.   @[@@@U.     @F@@@U. IF THE OPEN AND CLOSE QG
)@@G@@SUBSTITUTION CHARACTERS ARE THE SAME, THEN@G@@@U. SUBSTITUTION EXPRESSIOQH
)@@G@@NS MAY NOT BE NESTED WITHIN EACH OTHER.  IF THE @G@@@U. OPEN SUBSTITUTIOQI
)@@G@@N CHARACTER IS 0777 (AS SET BY THE 'CSC' COMMAND WITH @G@@@U. NO ARGUMENQJ
)@@G@@TS), THEN NO SUBSTITUTIONS WILL BE PERFORMED; ESSENTIALLY,  @B@@@U. SYMBQK
)@@G@@OLIC SUBSTITUTIONS ARE TURNED OFF.  @[@@@U.     @#@@@U          ASCII   QL
)@@G@@@C@@@UAST       EQU       '*'               . ASTERISK@^@@@UACOMMA    EQQM
)@@G@@U       ',' @#@@@U          FDATA   @[@@@U.     @^@@@UP         PROC    QN
)@@G@@  *1  @#@@@UGETCHAR*  NAME    @D@@@U          LMJ       X11,GETCHAR     QO
)@@G@@  . FETCH THE CHAR@F@@@U DO P>1 , J         P(1,1)            . IF NO MOQP
)@@G@@RE CHARS, EXIT    @#@@@U          END     @[@@@U.     @^@@@U. TEMP STACKQQ
)@@G@@ DEFINITION.@[@@@U.     @D@@@UTSFLAG    EQUF      0,,Q1             . * QR
)@@G@@SEEN FLAG   @F@@@UTSSTOR    EQUF      0,,Q2             . REMAINING CHARQS
)@@G@@S TO STORE  @E@@@UTSLINK    EQUF      0,,H2             . LINK TO NEXT BQT
)@@G@@UFFER @C@@@UTSPTRS    EQUF      1                 . POINTERS@E@@@UTSLINEQU
)@@G@@    EQUF      2                 . START OF LINE BUFFER@[@@@U.     @B@@@UQV
)@@G@@M$CALLSUBST*                          .   @ @@@U          SUBROUTINE   XQW
)@@G@@9     @F@@@USWBLEN    EQU       ASIMAX*2          . REASONABLE WORKBUFFEQX
)@@G@@R     @E@@@USUBBUFW   STATIC    1 0               . WORK BUFFER CONTROL QY
)@@G@@@F@@@USUBBUFCL  EQUF      SUBBUFW,,H1       . CHAR LENGTH OF WORK BUFFERQZ
)@@G@@@E@@@USUBBUF    EQUF      SUBBUFW,,H2       . WORK BUFFER ADDRESS @B@@@URA
)@@G@@SUBTMP    LOCAL                       .   @F@@@USUBLEN    EQUF      SUBTRB
)@@G@@MP,,H1        . LENGTH OF INPUT IMAGE     @E@@@USUBSCO    EQUF      SUBTRC
)@@G@@MP,,H2        . SCAN ORIGIN OFFSET  @E@@@USUBLDC    LOCAL               RD
)@@G@@        . LOAD COUNTER SAVE   @E@@@USUBLDX    LOCAL     2               RE
)@@G@@  . LOAD INDEX SAVE     @E@@@USUBCSC    LOCAL                       . SURF
)@@G@@BSTITUTION CHARS  @E@@@USUBOBC    EQUF      SUBCSC,,Q1        . OPEN BRARG
)@@G@@CKET CHAR   @E@@@USUBCBC    EQUF      SUBCSC,,Q2        . CLOSE BRACKET RH
)@@G@@CHAR  @ @@@U          $IF       EDPROCS   @D@@@USUBOLD    LOCAL         RI
)@@G@@              . OLD PROC FLAG @#@@@U          $ENDF   @F@@@U          SARJ
)@@G@@        A0,R1             . TEMP SAVE IMAGE LENGTH    @G@@@U          CARK
)@@G@@LL      M$CSCGET          . GET CURRENT SUBSTITUTION CHARS  @D@@@U      RL
)@@G@@    SA        A0,SUBOBC         . SAVE THE CHARS@ @@@U          SA      RM
)@@G@@  A1,SUBCBC @E@@@U          LA        A0,R1             . RESTORE IMAGE RN
)@@G@@LENGTH@H@@@U          JE,U      A1,0777 SUB990    . RETURN IF NO SUBSTITRO
)@@G@@UTION POSSIBLE    @E@@@U          L,U       X9,0              . SET STACRP
)@@G@@K EMPTY     @F@@@U          LSSL      A0,2              . GET INPUT CHARRQ
)@@G@@ACTER COUNT @F@@@U          SA        A0,SUBLEN         . TEMP SAVE INPURR
)@@G@@T COUNT     @G@@@U          JG        A0,SUBBUFCL SUB020 . SKIP IF WORK RS
)@@G@@BUFFER BIGGER     @H@@@USUB010    AA,U      A0,SWBLEN*4-1     . GET NEXTRT
)@@G@@ STANDARD WORK BUFFER SIZE    @B@@@U          DSL       A0,36           RU
)@@G@@  .   @A@@@U          DI,U      A0,SWBLEN*4     @G@@@U          MSI,U   RV
)@@G@@  A0,SWBLEN*4       . A0 = DESIRED BUF SIZE IN CHARS  @D@@@U          SSRW
)@@G@@L       A0,2              . GET WORD COUNT@F@@@U          M$PGET    SUB9RX
)@@G@@99            . GET THE DESIRED BUFFER    @F@@@U          LA        A0,SRY
)@@G@@UBBUF         . GET ANY PREVIOUS BUFFER   @F@@@U          SA        A1,SRZ
)@@G@@UBBUF         . SAVE WORK BUFFER ADDRESS  @F@@@U          SSL       A1,1SA

)@@G@@LEASE PREVIOUS BUFFER   @E@@@USUB020    LR        R1,SUBLEN         . GESF
)@@G@@T INPUT CHAR COUNT@F@@@U          L,U       A0,M$READBUFFER   . IMAGE INSG
)@@G@@ MACRO BUFFER     @E@@@U          L         A1,M$XASL         . ASCII LOSH
)@@G@@AD ROUTINE  @F@@@U          LR        R2,SUBBUFCL       . GET WORKBUFFERSI
)@@G@@ CHAR LENGTH@D@@@U          LA        A2,SUBBUF         . TO WORK BUFFERSJ
)@@G@@@E@@@U          L         A3,M$XASS         . ASCII STORE ROUTINE @ @@@USK
)@@G@@          $IF       EDPROCS   @G@@@U          SZ        SUBOLD          SL
)@@G@@  . CLEAR OLD PROC SUBSTITUTION FLAG@#@@@U          $ENDF   @[@@@U.     SM
)@@G@@@C@@@U. TRANSFER CHARACTERS UNTIL EOL, '[', OR ']'    @[@@@U.     @E@@@USN
)@@G@@SUB030    GETCHAR   SUB110            . FETCH THE NEXT CHAR @G@@@USUB040SO
)@@G@@    CALL      SUBCHK            . CHECK FOR SUBSTITUTION CHARS    @F@@@USP

)@@G@@          J         SUB100            . CLOSE BRACKET - POP STACK @F@@@USR
)@@G@@.         J         SUB050            . NORMAL CHAR - FALL THRU   @[@@@USS
)@@G@@.     @^@@@U. STORE NORMAL CHARACTER@[@@@U.     @[@@@USUB050@E@@@U      ST
)@@G@@    JGD       R2,SUB060         . COUNT CHARACTER     @E@@@U          LASU
)@@G@@        A5,SUBLER         . GET ERROR MESSAGE   @H@@@U          JNEZ,U  SV
)@@G@@  0,X9 SUB999       . IF OVERFLOW IN TEMP BUF, ERROR OUT    @F@@@U      SW
)@@G@@    LA        A0,SUBBUFCL       . GET CURRENT BUFFERSIZE    @E@@@U      SX
)@@G@@    LSSL      A0,2              . DOUBLE YOUR MONEY   @G@@@U          J SY
)@@G@@        SUB010            . START OVER WITH BIGGER BUFFER   @]@@@USUB060SZ
)@@G@@    . @E@@@U          EX        0,*A3             . STASH CHARACTER     TA
)@@G@@@ @@@U          $IF       EDPROCS   @E@@@U          TZ        M$EDPROCS TB
)@@G@@        . SUPPORTING ED PROCS?@E@@@U          TNZ       SUBOLD          TC

)@@G@@.     @B@@@U. OLD PROC - WE MUST TURN %N INTO %N,*%   @[@@@U.     @G@@@UTF
)@@G@@          SZ        SUBOLD            . CLEAR THE FLAG THAT GOT US HERE TG
)@@G@@@E@@@U          JE,U      A5,AST SUB100     . IF %*, MAKE IT %*%  @E@@@UTH

)@@G@@ET    @#@@@U          $ENDF   @[@@@U/.    @[@@@U.     @D@@@U. THIS ROUTITM

)@@G@@    AN        A1,M$XASL         . = CHAR OFFSET @D@@@U          LSSL    TR

)@@G@@        . SAVE CURRENT SCAN OFFSET  @ @@@U          $IF       EDPROCS   TU
)@@G@@@F@@@U          LA,H2     A0,M$XQTMACRO     . GET LINK TO CURRENT MACRO TV
)@@G@@@G@@@U          JZ        A0,SUB090         . SKIP PROC TEST IF NOT XQTITW
)@@G@@NG    @F@@@U          TZ        M$EDPROCS         . SUPPORTING EDITOR PRTX

)@@G@@@F@@@U          J         SUB090            . NO, DON'T TREAT AS A PROC TZ

)@@G@@TEMP STORAGE BUFFER FOR EXPRESSION TO BE SCANNED.     @[@@@U.     @F@@@UUN

)@@G@@          M$TGET    SUB999 ASIMAX*2   . GET MAXIMUM LENGTH IMAGE  @F@@@UUP

)@@G@@        .   @[@@@U.     @A@@@U. CHECK FOR [* ... IF SO SET TSFLAG @[@@@UUY

)@@G@@,U      A5,AST            . IS IT STAR    @F@@@U          J         SUB0VD

)@@G@@SFLAG,X9      . SET FLAG ON STACK   @E@@@U          GETCHAR   SUB110    VF

)@@G@@U     @[@@@U/.    @[@@@U.     @D@@@U. THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED WHEN A CLOSVO
)@@G@@E BRACKET IS SEEN.@[@@@U.     @]@@@USUB100    . @E@@@U          DS      VP

)@@G@@E WERE TOO MANY CLOSE BRACKETS.     @[@@@U.     @D@@@U          L       VS

)@@G@@  . IF NOT ERROR  @[@@@U.     @ @@@U. SCAN EXPRESSION FOR VALUE.  @[@@@UVV
)@@G@@.     @F@@@U          CALL      M$BLANKWORD       . BLANK OUT THE CURRENVW
)@@G@@T WORD@E@@@U          AN,U      A0,TSLINE,X9      . COMPUTE WORD COUNT  VX
)@@G@@@E@@@U          LXI,U     A0,TSLINE,X9      . FORM ACCESS WORD    @E@@@UVY

)@@G@@A2            . SETUP THE DESCRIPTOR@F@@@U          LSSL      A0,30     WD

)@@G@@X9      . THE OUTPUT CHAR INDEX     @D@@@U          LA,H1     A2,TSPTRS,WF

)@@G@@D IINCREMENT@D@@@U          LR        R2,TSSTOR,X9      . CHAR COUNTER  WH
)@@G@@@F@@@U          LX,U      X11,M$CALLARGSUB  . DEFAULT IS ARG SUBSTITUTERWI
)@@G@@@E@@@U          TZ        TSFLAG,X9         . WAS [*...] SEEN?    @G@@@UWJ

)@@G@@@E@@@U          JNZ       A5,SUB999         . CHECK FOR ERRORS    @[@@@UWM
)@@G@@.     @E@@@U. SUBSTITUTION DONE.  POP STACK AND RETURN TO FETCH LOOP.   WN
)@@G@@@[@@@U.     @E@@@U          L,U       A0,0,X9           . GET OLD STACK WO
)@@G@@ENTRY @C@@@U          L         X9,TSLINK,X9      . UNSTACK @F@@@U      WP
)@@G@@    TREL                        . RELEASE CORE UNTIL HERE   @C@@@U      WQ

)@@G@@D REENTER STASH LOOP    @[@@@U/.    @[@@@U.     @F@@@U. CONTROL PASSES HWU
)@@G@@ERE WHEN THE LAST CHARACTER IS FETCHED FROM THE @F@@@U. IMAGE BEING SUBSWV
)@@G@@TITUTED.  STACK MUST BE EMPTY OR NOT ENUF ']'.  @[@@@U.     @]@@@USUB110WW
)@@G@@    . @F@@@U          L         A5,SUBLBR         . TOO MANY LEFT BRACKEWX

)@@G@@          J         SUB999            . NO - ERROR    @[@@@U.     @A@@@UWZ
)@@G@@. BLANK FILL REMAINDER OF IMAGE.    @[@@@U.     @F@@@U          CALL    XA
)@@G@@  M$BLANKWORD       . BLANK OUT THE CURRENT WORD@E@@@U          AN      XB
)@@G@@  A0,SUBBUF         . COMPUTE WORD COUNT  @F@@@U          TG,U      A0,AXC
)@@G@@SIMAX*2-3       . IS THE BUFFER TOO FULL? @H@@@U          L,U       A0,AXD
)@@G@@SIMAX*2-3       . YES, ONLY USE THE RIGHT AMOUNT.     @B@@@U          L,XE
)@@G@@U       R1,0,A0           .   @E@@@U          LA        A1,SUBBUF       XF
)@@G@@  . GET WORKBUFFER INDEX@C@@@U          LXI,U     A1,1              . SEXG
)@@G@@T INCR@E@@@U          L         A2,M$RBX          . GET READBUFFER INDEXXH
)@@G@@@G@@@U          BT        A2,0,*A1          . MOVE IMAGE BACK TO MACRO BXI
)@@G@@UFFER @G@@@U          ANU,U     A0,ASIMAX*2-3       . A1 = -REMAINING WOXJ
)@@G@@RD COUNT    @E@@@U          SN        A1,R1             . R1 = + WORD COXK
)@@G@@UNT   @E@@@U          LA,U      A1,M$ASBLANKS     . NOW POINT TO BLANKS XL
)@@G@@@F@@@U          BT        A2,,*A1           . CLEAR REMAINING IMAGE     XM
)@@G@@@B@W@V          L         A1,SUBBUF         .   @B@@@W.         L       XN
)@@G@@  A1,SUBBUF         .   @F@W@V          S         A0,SUBBUFW        . BLXO
)@@G@@AST H1 AND H2 OF SUBBUFW@F@@@W.         S         A0,SUBBUFW        . BLXP
)@@G@@AST H1 AND H2 OF SUBBUFW@D@W@V          DSC       A0,36             . SWXQ
)@@G@@AP A0 AND A1@D@@@W.         DSC       A0,36             . SWAP A0 AND A1XR
)@@G@@@E@W@V          M$PREL    SUB999            . RELEASE THE BUFFER  @E@@@WXS
)@@G@@.         M$PREL    SUB999            . RELEASE THE BUFFER  @F@W@V      XT
)@@G@@    L         A0,SUBBUFW        . GET A0 BACK THE WAY IT WAS@F@@@W.     XU
)@@G@@    L         A0,SUBBUFW        . GET A0 BACK THE WAY IT WAS@I@W@V      XV
)@@G@@    SZ        SUBBUFW           . SET IT SO WE ALLOCATE A NEW BUFFER LATXW
)@@G@@ER    @I@@@W.         SZ        SUBBUFW           . SET IT SO WE ALLOCATXX
)@@G@@E A NEW BUFFER LATER    @E@@@USUB990    L,U       A5,0              . CLXY
)@@G@@EAR ERROR FLAG    @]@@@USUB999 .    @#@@@U          RETURN  @[@@@W.     XZ
)@@G@@@H@@@W.   THE FOLLOWING ENTRY POINT SHOULD BE USED WHEN REINITIALIZING TYA
)@@G@@HE MACRO    @H@@@W. PACKAGE.   ALL OF THE MEMORY IS ABOUT TO BE RELEASEDYB
)@@G@@ AND SO, M$CALLSUBST    @H@@@W. SHOULD NOT USE THE POINTER TO THE BUFFERYC
)@@G@@ IT HAS ALLOCATED.  IT IS ABOUT TO  @C@@@W. GO AWAY.   THE SZ CLEARS  THYD
)@@G@@E BUFFER ADDRESS. @[@@@W.     @C@@@W.   THIS ENTRY POINT IS REFERENCED IYE
)@@G@@N M$INIT.   @[@@@W.     @^@@@WM$CSUBSTREL*        .   @B@@@W          SUYF
)@@G@@BROUTINE                  .   @H@X@W          SZ        SUBBUF          YG
)@@G@@  . CLEAR BOTH LEN AND ADDR OF BUFFER     @H@@@X          SZ        SUBBYH
)@@G@@UFW           . CLEAR BOTH LEN AND ADDR OF BUFFER     @ @@@W          REYI
)@@G@@TURN    . GO BACK @[@@@W.     @[@@@U.     @#@@@U          LITS    @[@@@UYJ
)@@G@@.     @D@Y@USUBLBR    PCW           'TOO MANY OPEN BRACKETS.'   . @G@@@YYK
)@@G@@SUBLBR    PCW           'TOO MANY OPEN SUBSTITUTION CHARACTERS.'   .    YL
)@@G@@@C@Y@USUBRBR    PCW       'TOO MANY CLOSE BRACKETS.'  @F@@@YSUBRBR    PCYM
)@@G@@W       'TOO MANY CLOSE SUBSTITUTION CHARACTERS.'     @D@@@USUBLER    PCYN
)@@G@@W       'ARGUMENT EXPRESSION TOO LONG.'   @[@@@U.     @D@@@U. GETCHAR - YO
)@@G@@UTILITY SUBROUTINE TO FETCH THE NEXT CHAR @[@@@U.     @^@@@U.  LMJ  X11,YP
)@@G@@GETCHAR     @#@@@U.  <NO MORE CHARS>@#@@@U.  <A5 = CHAR>    @[@@@U.     YQ
)@@G@@@G@@@UGETCHAR   JNGD      R1,0,X11          . TAKE NO MORE CHARS EXIT, IYR
)@@G@@F R1<0@D@@@U          EX        0,*A1             . FETCH THE CHAR@E@@@UYS
)@@G@@          J         1,X11             . TAKE NORMAL RETURN  @[@@@U.     YT
)@@G@@@C@@@U. SUBCHK - CHECK FOR SUBSTITUTION CHARACTERS    @[@@@U.     @#@@@UYU
)@@G@@.  LMJ  X11,SUBCHK@^@@@U.  <OPEN SUBSTITUTION>  @^@@@U.  <CLOSE SUBSTITUYV
)@@G@@TION> @#@@@U.  <NORMAL CHAR>  @[@@@U.     @F@@@USUBCHK    JNEZ      M$OBYW
)@@G@@CEQCBC SBC010 . SKIP IF OBC CAN = CBC     @F@@@U          JE        A5,SYX
)@@G@@UBOBC 0,X11   . IF CHAR IS '[' - EXIT     @F@@@U          J         SBC0YY
)@@G@@20            . IT'S NOT, TRY CLOSE CHAR  @E@@@USBC010    JNE       A5,SYZ
)@@G@@UBOBC SBC020  . IS IT THE '[' CHAR? @E@@@U          TZ,U      0,X9      ZA
)@@G@@        . YES, IS STACK EMPTY?@H@@@U          TE        A5,SUBCBC       ZB
)@@G@@  . NO, ARE OPEN & CLOSE CHARS DIFFERENT? @F@@@U          J         0,X1ZC
)@@G@@1             . YES, EXIT WITH OPEN CHAR  @F@@@U          J         1,X1ZD
)@@G@@1             . NO, EXIT WITH CLOSE CHAR  @E@@@USBC020    JE        A5,SZE
)@@G@@UBCBC 1,X11   . IF ']', EXIT WITH IT@F@@@U          J         2,X11     ZF
)@@G@@        . EXIT WITH NORMAL CHAR     @[@@@U.     @B@@@U          END     ZG
)@@G@@                    .   _@@@@@          L         A3,M$XASS         . ASZH
)@@G@@CII STORE ROUTINE >@@@@F@A@@@T@@@@@@          $I*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@H/     ZI
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@H.     @ @@@H.  A0,A1 = ARGUMENT DESCRIPTOR@^@@@H.  A2,ZJ
)@@G@@A3 = STORE INDEXES@C@@@H.  R2    = REMAINING CHAR COUNT IN OUTPUT IMAGE ZK
)@@G@@@[@@@H.     @I@@@H.  LMJ  X11,M$CALLARGGET              . WILL GET 'CALLZL

)@@G@@.     @[@@@H.     @#@@@H          IBANK   @#@@@HM$CALLARGGET*     @F@@@HZS

)@@G@@.     @^@@@HCALLARG   SUBROUTINE    @[@@@H.     @D@@@HARGSTX    LOCAL   ZZ
)@@G@@  2                 . STORE INDEX   @E@@@HARGADS    LOCAL     2         AA

)@@G@@DL+ARGADS     . AND LENGTH OF ARG   @E@@@H          JE,U      A0,MODNUL AM

)@@G@@  ARG020            . REAL NON-NULL VALUE @[@@@H.     @^@@@H. NULL ARGUMAU
)@@G@@ENT VALUE   @[@@@H.     @E@@@HARG010    LA,H2     A0,M$XQTMACRO     . GEAV
