)@@G@@RESSION NOT INTEGER.'   @C@L@HARGLER    PCW       'EXPRESSION IS TOO LONGE
)@@G@@G.'   @B@@@LARGLER    PCW       'EXPRESSION TOO LONG.'@D@L@HARGLEN    PCGF
)@@G@@W       'ARGUMENT EXPRESSION IS TOO LONG.'@D@@@LARGLEN    PCW       'ARGGG
)@@G@@UMENT EXPRESSION TOO LONG.'   @F@@@HARGFEX    PCW       'SPECIFIED FIELDGH
)@@G@@ OR SUBFIELD NOT PRESENT.'    @[@@@H.     @B@@@H          END           GI
)@@G@@              .   _@@@@@/K@@]TA)[@R!#B@@@@C@%@@W@@[@R,#@@@@@G@%@@#@@[@R\GJ
)@@G@@#B@@@@C[E@@W@@[@R0#@@@@@G[E@@#@@[@R1#B@@@@C[%@@Z@@[@R2#@@@@@G[%@@#@@[@R3GK
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/         M$DEF   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. THIS FUNCTION HAGL
)@@G@@NDLES THE LEFT-PAREN DYADIC OPERATOR. IF THE LEFTARG  @H@@@@. DATATYPE IGM
)@@G@@S NULL, THEN THIS IS A SET OF ARITHMETIC PARENTHESIS AND THE VALUE@F@@@@GN
)@@G@@. ON THE STACK IS MERELY LEFT THERE.  IF THE LEFTARG IS A TABLE   @G@@@@GO
)@@G@@. THEN ASSOCIATIVE INDEXING IS INVOKED.  THE RIGHTPAREN OPERATOR HAS    GP
)@@G@@@^@@@@. JUST BEEN SCANNED,    @E@@@@. AND MUST BE NULLED OUT TO FORCE THGQ
)@@G@@E SCANNER TO SCAN AGAIN.@[@@@@.     @^@@@@M$SEMOPENPA*       .    @#@@@@GR
)@@G@@          ROUTINE @E@@@@OPRTMP    LOCAL     3                 . SOME TEMGS
)@@G@@PORARIES    @E@@@@OPRTBL    LOCAL     2                 . TABLE DESCRIPTGT
)@@G@@OR    @H@@@@          L         A0,VDOI+SVD         . GET THE OPERATOR WGU
)@@G@@E JUST SCANNED    @G@@@@          L         A5,OPRELP         . GET TOO GV
)@@G@@MANY LEFTPAREN MESSAGE  @G@@@@          TE,U      A0,M$OPERCLOSEP   . ITGW
)@@G@@ BETTER HAD BE A CLOSE PAREN  @F@@@@          J         OPR999          GX
)@@G@@  . ELSE IT IS A BIG BAD ERROR@D@@@@          SZ        VDA+SVD         GY
)@@G@@  . NULL IT OUT   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. IF USER SUBSCRIPTING CALL USER ROUGZ
)@@G@@TINE. @[@@@@.     @G@]@@          JEZ       M$EXTSUB OPR010   . SKIP IF HA
)@@G@@NO USER-SUBSCRIPTING    @D@]@@          LX        X11,M$EXTSUB      . GEHB
)@@G@@T ADDRESS   @E@]@@          LMJ       X11,,X11          . CALL USER ROUTHC
)@@G@@INE   @E@]@@          J         OPR090            . HE DID IT - POP     HD
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. IF LEFT ARG IS NULL THEN THESE ARE ARITHMETIC PARENSHE
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@]@@OPR010@E@@@@          L         A0,VDM+SLA      HF
)@@G@@  . GET MODE OF LEFTARG @C@@@@          TNE,U     A0,MODNUL         . A HG
)@@G@@NULL ?@F@@@@          J         OPR070            . YES - DO ARITH PARENHH
)@@G@@S     @F@@@@          TNE,U     A0,MODFUN         . IS LEFTARG A FUNCTIOHI
)@@G@@N     @E@@@@          J         OPR060            . YES - CALL FUNCTION HJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @A@@@@. LEFT ARG MUST BE A TABLE REFERENCE@[@@@@.     @D@@@@HK
)@@G@@          LA        A5,PCL('ITEM IS NOT A TABLE.')    @G@@@@          JNHL
)@@G@@E,U     A0,MODTBL OPR999  . TAKE ERROR EXIT IF NOT TABLE    @F@@@@      HM
)@@G@@    DL        A0,VD+SLA         . SAVE THE TABLE DESCRIPTOR @B@@@@      HN
)@@G@@    DS        A0,OPRTBL         .   @F@@@@          LA,U      A2,VD+SLA HO
)@@G@@        . SET DEFAULT RESULT AREA   @F@@@@          LA,U      A3,VD+SRA HP
)@@G@@        . DEFAULT SUBSCRIPT ADDR    @E@@@@          LA,U      A4,1      HQ
)@@G@@        . DEFAULT LOOP COUNT  @F@@@@          LA        A1,VDM+SRA      HR
)@@G@@  . GET THE RIGHT ARG MODE    @H@@@@          JNE,U     A1,MODLST OPR030HS
)@@G@@  . IF NOT A LIST, GO SUBSCRIPT A VALUE   @G@@@@          LA        A2,VHT
)@@G@@DL+SRA        . GET THE # OF ELTS IN THE RESULT @E@@@@          PUTANS  HU
)@@G@@  OPR999            . SETUP RESULT AREA   @F@@@@          LA,U      A2,,HV
)@@G@@A1            . GET DESTINATION INDEX     @E@@@@          LA        A3,VHW
)@@G@@DA+SRA        . GET SOURCE INDEX    @D@@@@          LXI,U     A2,VDSIZE HX
)@@G@@        . SET INCRS     @ @@@@          LXI,U     A3,VDSIZE @E@@@@      HY
)@@G@@    LA        A4,VDL+SRA        . SET # ELTS AS COUNT @E@@@@          J HZ
)@@G@@        OPR030            . START SUBSCRIPT LOOP@E@@@@OPR020    LA,U    IA
)@@G@@  A0,OPRTBL         . GET THE TABLE ADDR  @H@@@@          LA,U      A1,VIB
)@@G@@D,*A3         . GET THE ADDRESS OF CURRENT SUBSCRIPT  @E@@@@          DSIC
)@@G@@        A2,OPRTMP         . SAVE INDEXES & COUNT@B@@@@          SA      ID
)@@G@@  A4,OPRTMP+2       .   @E@@@@          CALL      M$SSFIND          . FIIE
)@@G@@ND THE SUBSCRIPT  @C@@@@          JNZ       A5,OPR999         . ERROR   IF
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LA        A5,PCL('SUBSCRIPT NOT FOUND.')    @E@@@@      IG
)@@G@@    JZ        A2,OPR999         . IF NO FIND, ERROR   @E@@@@          LAIH
)@@G@@        A2,SSVL,A2        . GET THE VALUE LINK  @F@@@@          DL      II
)@@G@@  A0,VD,A2          . GET THE DESCRIPTOR FROM IT@H@@@@          CALL    IJ
)@@G@@  M$VDVDL           . ADJUST THE LENGTH FIELD IF NECESSARY  @F@@@@      IK
)@@G@@    DL        A2,OPRTMP         . RECOVER INDEXES & COUNT   @A@@@@      IL
)@@G@@    LA        A4,OPRTMP+2     @F@@@@          DS        A0,VD,*A2       IM
)@@G@@  . POST NEXT ELEMENT ADDRESS @H@@@@OPR030    JGD       A4,OPR020       IN
)@@G@@  . COUNT ELEMENTS & CONTINUE IF MORE     @C@@@@          J         OPR0IO
)@@G@@80            . DONE    @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. LEFTARG IS FUNCTIP
)@@G@@ION NAME.  FUNCTION CALL IS THRU TABLE OF FUNCTIONS   @ @@@@. IN INTERNAIQ
)@@G@@L VARIABLE TABLE. @[@@@@.     @]@@@@OPR060    . @H@@@@          L       IR
)@@G@@  A0,VDFA+SFN       . GET CORE ADDRESS OF FUNCTION TEXT     @D@@@@      IS
)@@G@@    L         A5,OPRUIF         . UNIMPL MESSAGE@F@@@@          JZ      IT
)@@G@@  A0,OPR999         . UNIMPLEMENTED FUNCTION    @F@@@@          LA      IU
)@@G@@  A1,VDFAM+SFN      . GET THE ARGUMENT MODE     @E@@@@          JE,U    IV
)@@G@@  A1,MODNUL OPR065  . SKIP IF NULL MODE   @F@[@@          LA,U      A0,VIW
)@@G@@D+SRA         . GET ARGUMENT DESCRIPTOR   @D@[@@          LMJ       X11,IX
)@@G@@M$CONVMODE    . AUTO-CONVERT  @E@[@@          JNZ       A5,OPR999       IY
)@@G@@  . CHECK FOR ERRORS    @F@@@[          CONVMODE  OPR999 VD+SRA     . AUIZ
)@@G@@TO-CONVERT THE ARGUMENT @F@@@@          LA        A0,VDFA+SFN       . GEJA
)@@G@@T FUNCTION ADDRESS AGAIN@[@@@@OPR065@E@@@@          LA        A1,VDFRM+SJB
)@@G@@FN      . GET THE RESULT MODE @E@[@@          LSSL      A1,30           JC
)@@G@@  . CREATE A DESCIPTOR  @H@[@@          SA        A1,VD+SLA         . POJD
)@@G@@ST THE FIRST WORD OF THE DESCIPTOR  @E@@@[          SA        A1,VDM+SLAJE
)@@G@@        . POST THE RESULT MODE@D@@@@          LMJ       X11,0,A0        JF
)@@G@@  . CALL FUNCTION @C@@@@          JNZ       A5,OPR999         . ERROR   JG
)@@G@@@E@@@@          J         OPR080            . END OF FUNCTION     @[@@@[JH
)@@G@@.     @E@@@[. M$FUNCONVERT - IMPLEMENT THE TRIVIAL CONVERSION FUNCTIONS:JI
)@@G@@@B@@@[.  $CI, $CDI, $CFL, $CDFL, $CFD, $CASC    @[@@@[.     @G@@@[. THESJJ
)@@G@@E FUNCTIONS ARE CONFIGURED WITH AN AUTO-CONVERSION INVOCATION,    @G@@@[JK
)@@G@@. SO THAT THEIR ARGUMENTS HAVE ALREADY BEEN CONVERTED. THEREFORE, ALL   JL
)@@G@@@G@@@[. THEY MUST DO IS COPY THEIR RIGHT ARG TO THE RESULT (THE LEFT ARGJM
)@@G@@).    @ @@@[. ERGO, THE ENTRANCE BELOW:   @[@@@[.     @#@@@[M$FUNCONVERTJN
)@@G@@*     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. ARITHMETIC PARENS.  JUST COPY RITEARG TO LEFTAJO
)@@G@@RG.   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@OPR070    . @B@@@@          DL        A0,VD+SRA JP
)@@G@@        .   @C@@@@          DS        A0,VD+SLA         . EASY HUH@[@@@@JQ
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@. END OF OPEN PAREN OPERATION.@[@@@@.     @]@@@@OPR080    . JR
)@@G@@@E@@@@          L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR FLAG    @]@@@@JS
)@@G@@OPR090    . @D@@@@          POP       2                 . POP THE STACK JT
)@@G@@@]@@@@OPR999    . @#@@@@          RETURN  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. CLOSE PAREJU
)@@G@@N SHOULD NEVER BE EXECUTED    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@M$SEMCLOSEP*       .    JV
)@@G@@@F@@@@          L         A5,CPRERP         . TOO MANY RIGHT PARENS     JW
)@@G@@@D@@@@          J         0,X11             . ERROR RETURN  @[@@@@.     JX
)@@G@@@B@@@@          LITS                        .   @[@@@@.     @C@@@@OPRELPJY
)@@G@@    PCW       'TOO MANY OPEN PARENS.'     @C@#@@OPRUIF    PCW       'UNIJZ
)@@G@@PLEMENTED FUNCTION.'    @C@@@#OPRUIF    PCW       'UNIMPLEMENTED FUNCTIOKA
)@@G@@N.'   @C@@@@CPRERP    PCW       'TOO MANY CLOSE PARENS.'    @[@@@@.     KB
)@@G@@@B@@@@          END                         .   _@@@@@DSIZE @E@@@@      KC
)@@G@@    LA        A4,VDL+SRA        . SET # ELTS AS COUNT @E@@@@          J KD
)@@G@@        OPR030            . START SUBSCRIPT LOOP@E@@@@OPR020    LA,U    KE
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@D/         M$DEF   @[@@@D.     @G@@@D. THIS ELEMENT CONKF
)@@G@@TAINS ROUTINES TO SCAN SPECIFIC TYPES OF EXPRESSIONS. @[@@@D.     @[@@@DKG
)@@G@@.     @A@@@D. M$SCANBOOL - SCAN A BOOLEAN VALUE.@[@@@D.     @C@@@D. IF VKH
)@@G@@ALUE IS INTEGER, USE THE FIRST VALUE;     @E@@@D. OTHERWISE, THE LENGTH KI
)@@G@@OF THE VALUE DETERMINES THE RESULT. @^@@@D. ALWAYS, A0=1 OR 0.    @[@@@DKJ
)@@G@@.     @^@@@DM$SCANBOOL* SUBROUTINE  @E@@@D          LMJ       X11,M$SCANKK
)@@G@@EXPR    . SCAN FOR EXPRESSION @E@@@D          JNZ       A5,BOOL999      KL
)@@G@@  . IF ERROR RETURN     @E@@@D          JNE,U     A0,MODSIN BOOL010 . SKKM
)@@G@@IP IF NOT INTEGER @F@@@D          JZ        A2,BOOL010        . IF NO LEKN
)@@G@@NGTH, RESULT=0    @D@@@D          L         A0,0,A1           . GET VALUKO
)@@G@@E     @D@@@D          J         BOOL020           . GO FIX IT     @H@@@DKP
)@@G@@BOOL010   LA,U      A0,,A2            . USE LENGTH AS RESULT FOR OTHER MKQ
)@@G@@ODES  @D@@@DBOOL020   JZ        A0,BOOL999        . ALLOW ZERO    @E@@@DKR
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,1              . ELSE FORCE IT TO ONE@#@@@DBOOL99KS
)@@G@@9   RETURN  @[@@@D.     @A@@@D. M$SCANINT - SCAN FOR AN INTEGER.  @H@@@DKT
)@@G@@.             RETURNS WITH A0 = VALUE; A1 = ADDRESS OF VALUE; A2 = LENGTKU
)@@G@@H.    @[@@@D.     @^@@@DM$SCANINT* SUBROUTINE   @F@@@D          LMJ     KV
)@@G@@  X11,M$SCANEXPR    . SCAN FOR AN EXPRESSION    @B@@@D          JNZ     KW
)@@G@@  A5,INT999         .   @F@@@D          TE,U      A0,MODSIN         . WAKX
)@@G@@S AN INTEGER GIVEN?     @E@G@D          LA        A5,PCL('INTEGER EXPRESKY
)@@G@@SION EXPECTED.')  @D@@@G          LA        A5,PCL('INTEGER VALUE EXPECTKZ
)@@G@@ED.') @D@@@D          LA        A0,0,A1           . GET THE VALUE @E@@@DLA
)@@G@@          JZ        A5,INT999         . IF NO ERROR, EXIT   @F@@@D      LB
)@@G@@    LA        A0,M$EXPRCOLUMN   . GET THE EXPRESSION ORIGIN @A@@@D      LC
)@@G@@    CALL      M$ERRMSGBLD     @D@@@DINT999    RETURN                    LD
)@@G@@  . THAT'S ALL    @[@@@D.     @A@@@D. M$SCANSTR - SCAN FOR A STRING.    LE
)@@G@@@H@@@D.             RETURNS WITH A0 = PCW FOR STRING; A1 = MODE (MODASC,LF
)@@G@@MODALP)     @D@@@D.             A2 = CHARACTER LENGTH; A3 = WORD LENGTH.LG
)@@G@@@[@@@D.     @^@@@DM$SCANSTR* SUBROUTINE   @E@@@D          LMJ       X11,LH
)@@G@@M$SCANEXPR    . SCAN AN EXPRESSION  @B@@@D          JNZ       A5,STR999 LI
)@@G@@        .   @E@H@D          LA        A5,PCL('STRING EXPRESSION EXPECTEDLJ
)@@G@@.')   @D@@@H          LA        A5,PCL('STRING VALUE EXPECTED.')  @E@@@DLK
)@@G@@          TE,U      A0,MODALP         . ALPHANUMERIC STRING?@F@@@D      LL
)@@G@@    TNE,U     A0,MODASC         . NO, ASCII ALPHA STRING?   @D@@@D      LM
)@@G@@    LA,U      A5,0              . YES, NO ERROR @E@@@D          JNZ     LN
)@@G@@  A5,STR900         . IF ERROR, GO AHEAD  @F@@@D          DSC       A0,3LO
)@@G@@6             . A0 = ADDRESS, A1 = MODE   @E@@@D          LA        A3,ALP
)@@G@@2             . A3 = CHAR LENGTH    @E@@@D          MI        A3,VMEBS,ALQ
)@@G@@1       . = # BITS IN RESULT  @H@@@D          DI,U      A3,36           LR
)@@G@@  . = # WORDS IN RESULT; A4 = REMAINDER   @D@@@D          TZ        A4  LS
)@@G@@              . REMAINDER?    @F@@@D          AA,U      A3,1            LT
)@@G@@  . YES, COUNT AN EXTRA WORD  @F@@@D          LXI,U     A0,0100,A3      LU
)@@G@@  . SET # WORDS + SKIP COUNT  @C@@@D          J         STR999          LV
)@@G@@  . EXIT OK @F@@@DSTR900    LA        A0,M$EXPRCOLUMN   . GET EXPRESSIONLW
)@@G@@ ORIGIN     @B@@@D          CALL      M$ERRMSGBLD       .   @D@@@DSTR999LX
)@@G@@    RETURN                      . WITH STUFF    @[@@@D.     @C@@@D. M$SCLY
)@@G@@ANONOFF - SCAN FOR AN 'ON' OR AN 'OFF'.   @[@@@D.     @^@@@DM$SCANONOFF*LZ
)@@G@@ SUBROUTINE @F@@@D          CALL      M$MORECMD         . CHECK FOR MOREMA
)@@G@@ COMMAND    @E@@@D          LN,U      A1,1              . ASSUME NO MOREMB
)@@G@@ STUFF@E@@@D          JZ        A0,ONOFF010       . SKIP IF NO STUFF    MC
)@@G@@@E@@@D          CALL      M$SCANITEM        . GET NEXT PRIMITIVE  @B@@@DMD
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,ONOFF999       .   @G@@@D          LA        A5,PME
)@@G@@CL('SYNTAX ERROR - ''ON'' OR ''OFF'' EXPECTED.')@E@@@D          JNE,U   MF
)@@G@@  A0,MODNAM ONOFF999 . CHECK FOR BAD STUFF@D@@@D          LA        A0,,MG
)@@G@@A1            . GET THE NAME  @D@@@D          LN,U      A1,1            MH
)@@G@@  . ASSUME ERROR  @D@@@D          TNE       A0,('ON'L)        . WAS IT 'MI
)@@G@@ON'?  @D@@@D          LA,U      A1,1              . YES, GET FLAG @D@@@DMJ
)@@G@@          TNE       A0,('OFF'L)       . WAS IT 'OFF'? @D@@@D          LAMK
)@@G@@,U      A1,0              . YES, GET FLAG @C@@@D          JN        A1,OML
)@@G@@NOFF999       . ERROR   @F@@@DONOFF010  LA        A0,A1             . GEMM
)@@G@@T ANSWER (-1, 0, 1)     @D@@@D          LA,U      A5,0              . ANMN
)@@G@@D NO ERRORS @#@@@DONOFF999  RETURN  @[@@@D/.    @G@@@D.   THIS ROUTINE RMO
)@@G@@ETURNS IN A0 EITHER A 1 OR 0 DEPENDING ON WHETHER     @C@@@D.  THE NEXT MP
)@@G@@ITEM SCANNED IS A COMMENT OR NOT.   @G@@@D.  IF ANY CHARACTER SEQUENCE OMQ
)@@G@@THER THAN A '. ' OCCURS A0 RETURNS 0.     @A@@@D.  OTHERWISE A0 HAS 1 ASMR
)@@G@@ THE RESULT.@[@@@D.     @^@@@D          ASCII     .   @^@@@DASCIBL    EQMS
)@@G@@U       ' ' @B@@@DASCIPD    EQU       '.'               .   @^@@@D      MT
)@@G@@    FDATA     .   @#@@@DM$SCANCOMMENT*    @B@@@D          SUBROUTINE    MU
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@DCOMMSAVE  LOCAL     1                 .   @G@@@DMV
)@@G@@          T$COLN                      . SAVE THE CURRENT COLUMN NUMBER  MW
)@@G@@@B@@@D          S         A0,COMMSAVE       .   @]@@@DCOM010    . @F@@@DMX
)@@G@@          T$CHAR    COM900            . GET THE NEXT CHARACTER    @F@@@DMY
)@@G@@          SSL       A3,18             . GET THE ASCII VERSION     @F@@@DMZ
)@@G@@          TNE,U     A3,ASCIBL         . IF IT IS A BLANK, CONTINUE@B@@@DNA
)@@G@@          J         COM010            .   @H@@@D          TNE,U     A3,ANB
)@@G@@SCIPD         . IT ISN'T A BLANK, IS IT A PERIOD?     @G@@@D          J NC
)@@G@@        COM020            . YES, CHECK THE NEXT CHARACTER   @I@@@D      ND
)@@G@@    J         COM900            . IT IS NOT A PERIOD, ITCAN'T BE A COMMENE
)@@G@@NT    @]@@@DCOM020    . @F@@@D          T$CHAR    COM025            . GENF
)@@G@@T THE NEXT CHARACTER    @F@F@D          SSL       A0,18             . GENG
)@@G@@T THE ASCII VERSION     @F@@@F          SSL       A3,18             . GENH
)@@G@@T THE ASCII VERSION     @C@@@D          TE,U      A3,ASCIBL         . BLNI
)@@G@@ANK?  @F@@@D          J         COM900            . NOPE, IT'S NOT A COMNJ
)@@G@@MENT  @]@@@DCOM025    . @F@E@D          L,U       A0,1              . SENK
)@@G@@T FLAG FOR A COMMENT    @F@@@E          L,U       A1,1              . SENL
)@@G@@T FLAG FOR A COMMENT    @D@@@D          J         COM999            . ANNM
)@@G@@D LEAVE     @C@@@DCOM900    . THE IS THE NOT A COMMENT RETURN     @D@E@DNN
)@@G@@          SZ        A0                . CLEAR THE FLAG@D@@@E          SZNO
)@@G@@        A1                . CLEAR THE FLAG@]@@@DCOM999    . @B@@@D      NP
)@@G@@    L         A0,COMMSAVE       .   @F@@@D          S         A1,COMMSAVNQ
)@@G@@E       . SAVE THE RETURN STATUS    @I@@@D          T$COL               NR
)@@G@@        . MOVE THE SCAN BACK TO THE STARTUING POIN    @B@@@D          L NS
)@@G@@        A0,COMMSAVE       .   @^@@@D          RETURN    .   @H@@@D. THISNT
)@@G@@ ROUTINE SCANS A LIST OF USER MACRO OR VARIABLE NAMES, SEPERATED WITH   NU
)@@G@@@^@@@D. BLANKS OR COMMAS.     @[@@@D.     @A@@@D.         LMJ       X11,NV
)@@G@@M$SCANLIST  @ @@@D.         A5=0 OR ERROR PCW   @F@@@D.         A4=1 WHENW
)@@G@@N A0,A1 HAS NAME; A4=0 WHEN LIST IS EXHAUSTED   @[@@@D.     @^@@@D.  LMJNX
)@@G@@ X11,M$SCANVLIST  @^@@@D.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @#@@@D.  A0,A1 = NAME   NY
)@@G@@@E@@@D.  A3 = ASCII TERMCHAR: ONLY ' ' ',' '[' OR '(' ALLOWED.    @[@@@DNZ
)@@G@@.     @#@@@D          ASCII   @^@@@DBLANK     EQU       ' ' @^@@@DCOMMA OA
)@@G@@    EQU       ',' @^@@@DPAREN     EQU       '(' @^@@@DBRACKET   EQU     OB
)@@G@@  '[' @#@@@D          FDATA   @]@@@D          . @]@@@DM$SCANLIST* @E@@@DOC
)@@G@@          LA,U      A0,0              . CLEAR VAR LIST FLAG @^@@@D      OD
)@@G@@    J         LIST@]@@@DM$SCANVLIST*@E@@@D          LA,U      A0,1      OE
)@@G@@        . SET VAR LIST FLAG   @^@@@DLIST      SUBROUTINE    @D@@@DLSTFLGOF
)@@G@@    LOCAL     1                 . VAR LIST FLAG @D@@@DLSTNAM    LOCAL   OG
)@@G@@  1                 . NAME POINTER  @D@@@D          SA        A0,LSTFLG OH
)@@G@@        . POST LIST FLAG@F@@@DLST010    CALL      M$SCANITEM        . GEOI
)@@G@@T THE NEXT PRIMITIVE    @E@@@D          JNZ       A5,LST999         . IFOJ
)@@G@@ ERROR, QUIT NOW  @E@@@D          LA,U      A4,0              . SET END OK
)@@G@@OF LIST FLAG@F@@@D          JE,U      A1,M$OPEREOL LST999 . QUIT IF NO MOL
)@@G@@ORE NAMES   @D@@@D          LA        A5,PCL('ERROR IN NAME LIST.')     OM
)@@G@@@F@@@D          SSA       A3,18             . SLIDE THE BREAKCHAR DOWN  ON
)@@G@@@G@@@D          JNE,U     A0,MODOPR LST020  . IF NOT AN OPERATOR, SKIP AOO
)@@G@@HEAD  @E@@@D          TE,U      A3,BLANK          . WAS IT A BLANK?     OP
)@@G@@@D@@@D          TNE,U     A3,COMMA          . OR A COMMA?   @E@@@D      OQ
)@@G@@    J         LST010            . YES, SCAN AGAIN     @D@@@D          J OR
)@@G@@        LST990            . NO, ERROR OFF @F@@@DLST020    JNE,U     A0,MOS
)@@G@@ODNAM LST990  . ERROR IF NOT MODE NAME    @G@@@D          JN        A3,LOT
)@@G@@ST040         . IF EOL TERMCHAR, SKIP AHEAD     @F@@@D          TE,U    OU
)@@G@@  A3,BLANK          . WAS IT A BLANK TERMCHAR?  @E@@@D          TNE,U   OV
)@@G@@  A3,COMMA          . NO, HOW ABOUT COMMA?@D@@@D          J         LST0OW
)@@G@@30            . YES, IT'S OK  @D@@@D          TE,U      A3,BRACKET      OX
)@@G@@  . IS IT A '['   @D@@@D          TNE,U     A3,PAREN          . NO, IS IOY
)@@G@@T '(' @D@@@D          TNZ       LSTFLG            . YES, IS IT OK?@E@@@DOZ
)@@G@@          J         LST990            . NO, BAD TERMCHAR    @F@@@DLST030PA
)@@G@@    SA        A1,LSTNAM         . TEMP SAVE NAME POINTER    @E@@@D      PB
)@@G@@    SA        A3,LSTFLG         . SAVE THE TERMCHAR   @D@@@D          T$PC
)@@G@@SKIP    1                 . SKIP THE PAREN@F@@@D          LA        A1,LPD
)@@G@@STNAM         . RECOVER THE NAME POINTER  @F@@@D          LA        A3,LPE
)@@G@@STFLG         . RECOVER THE TERM CHAR TOO @D@@@DLST040    DL        A0,,PF
)@@G@@A1            . GET THE NAME  @F@@@D          DL        A4,M$DONE       PG
)@@G@@  . GET FLAG FOR GOOD STUFF   @C@@@D          J         LST999          PH
)@@G@@  . GO HOME @F@@@DLST990    LA        A0,M$SCANCOLUMN   . GET ERROR COLUPI
)@@G@@MN NUMBER   @H@@@D          CALL      M$ERRMSGBLD       . BUILD THE ERROPJ
)@@G@@R MESSAGE W/POINTER     @#@@@DLST999    RETURN  @[@@@D/.    @F@@@D. M$SCPK
)@@G@@ANVARSUB - SCAN A SUBSCRIPTED/INDEXED VARIABLE REFERENCE.   @[@@@D.     PL
)@@G@@@A@@@D.  A0 = VALUE DESCRIPTOR ADDRESS    @C@@@D.  A1 = OPERATOR ID OF IPM
)@@G@@NITIAL SUBSCRIPT/INDEX  @^@@@D.  LMJ  X11,M$SCANVARSUB@^@@@D.  A5 = ERROPN
)@@G@@R PCW OR 0  @ @@@D.  A0,A1 = SUBSCRIPT/INDEX VD @C@@@D.  A2 = SUBSCRIPT PO
)@@G@@INDEX OPERATOR ('[' OR '(')   @B@@@D.  A3 = ADDRESS TO FINAL VALUE DESCRPP
)@@G@@IPTOR @ @@@D.  A4 = SUBSCRIPT COLUMN #    @[@@@D.     @^@@@DM$SCANVARSUBPQ
)@@G@@* SUBROUTINE@D@@@DSVSLS     LOCAL     4                 . LOCAL STORAGE PR
)@@G@@@E@@@DSVSVAL    EQUF      SVSLS,,H1         . VALUE DESCRIPTOR PTR@E@@@DPS
)@@G@@SVSOPR    EQUF      SVSLS,,H2         . SUBSCRIPT OPERATOR  @F@@@DSVSCOLPT
)@@G@@    EQUF      SVSLS+1,,Q1       . CURRENT COLUMN POSITION   @F@@@DSVSSCOPU
)@@G@@L   EQUF      SVSLS+1,,Q2       . SUBSCRIPT COLUMN POSITION @F@@@DSVSVDPPV
)@@G@@    EQUF      SVSLS+1,,H2       . LAST VALUE DESCRIPTOR PTR @D@@@DSVSSUBPW
)@@G@@    EQUF      SVSLS+2           . SUBSCRIPT VD  @E@@@D          SA      PX
)@@G@@  A0,SVSVAL         . POST THE VALUE PTR  @F@@@D          SA        A1,SPY
)@@G@@VSOPR         . POST THE INITIAL OPERATOR @H@@@D          SA        A0,SPZ
)@@G@@VSVDP         . SAVE ORIGINAL VALUE DESCRIPTOR PTR    @G@@@D          LAQA
)@@G@@        A0,M$SCANCOLUMN   . GET THE LAST COLUMN SCANNED     @C@@@D      QB
)@@G@@    SA        A0,SVSCOL         . POST IT @F@@@DSVS010    AA,U      A0,1QC
)@@G@@              . GET SUBSCRIPT POSITION    @C@@@D          SA        A0,SQD
)@@G@@VSSCOL        . POST IT @G@@@D          CALL      M$SCANEXPR        . SCQE
)@@G@@AN THE SUBSCRIPT EXPRESSION   @ @@@D          JNZ       A5,SVS999 @F@@@DQF
)@@G@@          LA        A0,M$SCANCOLUMN   . GET THE COLUMN POSITION   @C@@@DQG
)@@G@@          SA        A0,SVSCOL         . POST IT @F@@@D          DL      QH
)@@G@@  A0,VD+SVD         . GET THE SUBSCRIPT VALUE   @C@@@D          DS      QI
)@@G@@  A0,SVSSUB         . SAVE IT @F@@@D          LA        A1,SVSOPR       QJ
)@@G@@  . GET THE PREVIOUS OPERATOR @G@@@D          DL        A4,DPLR($CFS(')'QK
)@@G@@),PCL('MISSING CLOSE PARENTHESIS.'))@C@@@D          TE,U      A1,M$OPEROQL
)@@G@@PENPA   . CORRECT?@G@@@D          DL        A4,DPLR($CFS(']'),PCL('MISSIQM
)@@G@@NG CLOSE BRACKET.'))    @F@@@D          JNE,U     A4,0,A3 SVS900    . ERQN
)@@G@@ROR IF NOT MATCHING CHAR@E@@@D          CALL      M$SCANITEM        . GEQO
)@@G@@T THE NEXT TOKEN  @B@@@D          JNZ       A5,SVS999         .   @E@@@DQP
)@@G@@          SA        A4,SVSCOL         . POST THE COLUMN #   @F@@@D      QQ
)@@G@@    JNE,U     A0,MODOPR SVS040  . QUIT IF NOT AN OPERATOR   @D@@@D      QR
)@@G@@    TE,U      A1,M$OPEROPENPA   . IF EITHER '(' @C@@@D          TNE,U   QS
)@@G@@  A1,M$OPEROPENBR   . OR '['  @G@@@D          J         $+2             QT
)@@G@@  . YES, THEN COMPUTE A NEW VALUE   @C@@@D          J         SVS040    QU
)@@G@@        . NO, QUIT@F@@@D          LA        A0,SVSOPR         . GET THE QV
)@@G@@PREVIOUS OPERATOR @F@@@D          SA        A1,SVSOPR         . POST THEQW
)@@G@@ NEW OPERATOR     @F@@@D          JE,U      A0,M$OPEROPENPA SVS020 . GO QX
)@@G@@SUBSCRIPT IF '('  @]@@@D          . @C@@@D          .         PERFORM INQY
)@@G@@DEX ON A LIST     @]@@@D          . @E@@@D          LA        A3,SVSVAL QZ
)@@G@@        . GET THE VALUE PTR   @F@@@D          LA        A0,VDM,A3       RA
)@@G@@  . GET THE MODE OF THE VALUE @D@@@D          LA        A5,PCL('ITEM IS RB
)@@G@@NOT A LIST.')     @G@@@D          JNE,U     A0,MODLST SVS910  . ERROR INRC
)@@G@@ VALUE IF NOT A LIST    @F@@@D          LA        A0,VDL+SVSSUB     . GERD
)@@G@@T THE SUBSCIPT LENGTH   @B@@@D          LA        A5,PCL('INDEX ERROR.')RE
)@@G@@@D@@@D          JNE,U     A0,1 SVS920       . ERROR IN INDEX@E@@@D      RF
)@@G@@    LA        A0,SVSVAL         . GET THE VALUE PTR   @E@@@D          LARG
)@@G@@,U      A1,SVSSUB         . GET THE INDEX PTR   @E@@@D          CALL    RH
)@@G@@  M$INDEXCHECK      . CHECK THE INDEX     @D@@@D          JNZ       A5,SRI
)@@G@@VS920         . ERROR IN INDEX@E@@@D          LSSL      A1,1            RJ
)@@G@@  . COMPUTE A WORD INDEX@F@@@D          LA        A0,SVSVAL         . GERK
)@@G@@T THE VALUE PTR AGAIN   @E@@@D          AU        A1,VDA,A0         . A2RL
)@@G@@ = ELEMENT ADDRESS@D@@@D          J         SVS030            . GO STUFFRM
)@@G@@ IT   @]@@@D          . @D@@@D          .         PEFORM A TABLE SUBSCRIRN
)@@G@@PT OPERATION@]@@@D          . @E@@@DSVS020    LA        A0,SVSVAL       RO
)@@G@@  . GET THE VALUE PTR   @F@@@D          LA        A1,VDM,A0         . GERP
)@@G@@T THE MODE OF THE VALUE @D@@@D          LA        A5,PCL('ITEM IS NOT A RQ
)@@G@@TABLE.')    @D@@@D          JNE,U     A1,MODTBL SVS910  . ERROR IN VALUERR
)@@G@@@F@@@D          LA,U      A1,SVSSUB         . GET THE SUBSCRIPT PTR     RS
)@@G@@@E@@@D          CALL      M$SSFIND          . FIND THE SUBSCRIPT  @E@@@DRT
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,SVS920         . ERROR IN SUBSCRIPT  @D@@@D      RU
)@@G@@    LA        A5,PCL('SUBSCRIPT NOT FOUND.')    @B@@@D          JZ      RV
)@@G@@  A2,SVS920         .   @E@@@D          LA        A2,SSVL,A2        . GERW
)@@G@@T THE VALUE LINK  @F@@@DSVS030    SA        A2,SVSVDP         . SAVE VALRX
)@@G@@UE DESCRIPT PTR   @E@@@D          DL        A0,VD,A2          . GET THE RY
)@@G@@VALUE ITSELF@F@@@D          CALL      M$VDVDL           . ADJUST THE LENRZ
)@@G@@GTH FIELD   @F@@@D          LA        A2,SVSVAL         . GET THE VALUE SA
)@@G@@PTR AGAIN   @E@@@D          DS        A0,VD,A2          . POST THE NEW VSB
)@@G@@ALUE  @F@@@D          LA        A0,SVSCOL         . GET THE OPERATOR POSSC
)@@G@@ITION @F@@@D          J         SVS010            . START PROCESS ALL OVSD
)@@G@@ER    @]@@@D          . @F@@@D          .         END OF VALUE RESOLUTIOSE
)@@G@@N SUBSCRIPTING/INDEXING.@]@@@D          . @F@@@DSVS040    DL        A0,SSF
)@@G@@VSSUB         . SET UP REGS FOR RETURN    @E@@@D          LA        A2,SSG
)@@G@@VSOPR         . GET THE OPERATOR    @G@@@D          LA        A3,SVSVDP SH
)@@G@@        . GET THE VALUE DESCRIPTOR PTR    @F@@@D          LA        A4,SSI
)@@G@@VSSCOL        . GET THE SUBSCRIPT COLUMN  @D@@@D          LA,U      A5,0SJ
)@@G@@              . NO ERRORS     @C@@@D          J         SVS999          SK
)@@G@@  . BYE     @]@@@D          . @ @@@D          .         ERRORS    @]@@@DSL
)@@G@@          . @F@@@DSVS900    LA        A0,SVSCOL         . ERROR AT CURRESM
)@@G@@NT POSITION @ @@@D          J         SVS930    @D@@@DSVS910    LA      SN
)@@G@@  A0,SVSSCOL        . ERROR IN VALUE@B@@@D          AN,U      A0,2      SO
)@@G@@        .   @ @@@D          J         SVS930    @F@@@DSVS920    LA      SP
)@@G@@  A0,SVSSCOL        . ERROR IN SUBSCRIPT/INDEX  @]@@@D          . @F@@@DSQ
)@@G@@SVS930    CALL      M$ERRMSGBLD       . BUILD AN ERROR MESSAGE    @ @@@DSR
)@@G@@SVS999    RETURN    . ALL DONE@]@@@D          . @#@@@D          END     SS
)@@G@@_@@@@@>@@@@^@]@@@C@@@@@@/.    >@@@@]@H@@@C@@@@@@.   THIS ROUTINE RETURNSST
)@@G@@ IN A0 EITHER A 1 OR 0 DEPENDING ON WHETHER     >@@@@H@D@@@C@@@@@@.  THESU
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@]/         M$DEF   @[@@@].     @E@@@]. EXECUTION TIME HSV
)@@G@@ANDLERS FOR CONTROL STRUCTURE COMPONENTS. @[@@@].     @B@@@]. MACRO COMMSW
)@@G@@AND FROM MACROS IS IGNORED.   @D@@@]. MACRO COMMAND FROM USER EDITS AND SX
)@@G@@RECOMPILES MACRO. @[@@@].     @^@#@]M$COMMACRO* ROUTINE     @^@@@#M$COMMSY
)@@G@@ACRO* SUBROUTINE  @D@@@]          LA,U      A5,0              . KILL ERRSZ
)@@G@@ORS   @H@@@]          JNEZ      M$COMLINE MAC999  . IF COMMAND FROM MACRTA
)@@G@@O - IGNORE IT     @E@@@]          LMJ       X11,M$EDITMACRO   . EDIT THETB
)@@G@@ MACRO NAMED@ @@@]          JNZ       A5,MAC999 @ @@@]          JZ      TC
)@@G@@  A4,MAC999 @D@@@]          LA,U      A0,M$ELT$         . GET THE PACKETTD
)@@G@@@F@@@]          CALL      M$FILESEARCH      . FIND & COMPILE THE MACRO  TE
)@@G@@@ @@@]          JNZ       A5,MAC999 @#@@@]MAC999    RETURN  @[@@@].     TF
)@@G@@@F@@@]. IF AND WHILE HANDLERS TAKE JUMP ONLY IF EXPRESSION IS FALSE.    TG
)@@G@@@[@@@].     @^@@@]M$COMWHILE*         .   @]@@@]M$COMIF*  . @#@#@]      TH
)@@G@@    ROUTINE @^@@@#          SUBROUTINE    @F@@@]          LA        A5,MTI
)@@G@@ACONL         . GET MACRO ONLY MESSAGE    @G@@@]          JEZ       M$COTJ
)@@G@@MLINE IFW999  . IF COMMAND FROM KEYBOARD - ERROR@E@@@]          LMJ     TK
)@@G@@  X11,M$SCANBOOL    . GET BOOLEAN VALUE   @C@@@]          JNZ       A5,ITL
)@@G@@FW999         . ERROR   @F@@@]          JNZ       A0,IFW010         . IFTM
)@@G@@ TRUE,JUST CONTINUE     @F@@@]          LMJ       X11,COMXFER       . MOTN
)@@G@@VE TO TRANFER ADDRESS   @ @@@]          JNZ       A5,IFW999 @D@@@]IFW010TO
)@@G@@    LA,U      A5,0              . NO ERRORS     @#@@@]IFW999    RETURN  TP
)@@G@@@[@@@].     @D@@@]. UNTIL HANDLER TAKES JUMP ONLY IF EXPRESSION IS TRUE.TQ
)@@G@@@[@@@].     @^@#@]M$COMUNTIL* ROUTINE     @^@@@#M$COMUNTIL* SUBROUTINE  TR
)@@G@@@F@@@]          LA        A5,MACONL         . GET MACRO ONLY MESSAGE    TS
)@@G@@@G@@@]          JEZ       M$COMLINE UNT999  . ERROR IF COMMAND FROM KEYBTT
)@@G@@OARD  @E@@@]          LMJ       X11,M$SCANBOOL    . GET BOOLEAN VALUE   TU
)@@G@@@C@@@]          JNZ       A5,UNT999         . ERROR   @E@@@]          JZTV
)@@G@@        A0,UNT010         . IF FALSE CONTINUE   @D@@@]          LMJ     TW
)@@G@@  X11,COMXFER       . MAKE TRANSFER @E@@@]          JNZ       A5,UNT999 TX
)@@G@@        . CHECK FOR ERROR     @C@@@]UNT010    LA,U      A5,0            TY
)@@G@@  . NO ERROR@#@@@]UNT999    RETURN  @[@@@].     @C@@@]. HANDLERS FOR REPTZ
)@@G@@EAT AND ENDIF JUST RETURN.    @[@@@].     @^@@@]M$COMREPEAT*        .   UA
)@@G@@@^@@@]M$COMENDIF*         .   @#@#@]          ROUTINE @^@@@#          SUUB
)@@G@@BROUTINE    @D@@@]          LA,U      A5,0              . NO ERRORS     UC
)@@G@@@H@@@]          TNZ       M$COMLINE         . WAS COMMAND EXECUTED FROM UD
)@@G@@KEYBOARD?   @E@@@]          LA        A5,MACONL         . YES, IT IS ILLUE
)@@G@@EGAL  @F@@@]          RETURN                      . RETURN WITH/OUT ERROUF
)@@G@@R     @[@@@].     @C@@@]. HANDLER FOR ENDREP AND ELSE ALWAYS TAKES JUMP.UG
)@@G@@@[@@@].     @^@@@]M$COMELSE*          .   @^@@@]M$COMENDREP*        .   UH
)@@G@@@#@#@]          ROUTINE @^@@@#          SUBROUTINE    @F@@@]          LAUI
)@@G@@        A5,MACONL         . GET MACRO ONLY MESSAGE    @F@@@]          JEUJ
)@@G@@Z       M$COMLINE ELS999  . ERROR IF KEYBOARD COMMAND @D@@@]          LMUK
)@@G@@J       X11,COMXFER       . MAKE TRANSFER @#@@@]ELS999    RETURN  @[@@@]UL
)@@G@@.     @F@@@]. TAKE THE JUMP TO THE ADDRESS IN M$COMXFER BY POSTING THE NUM
)@@G@@EXT   @D@@@]. READ ADDRESS IN THE MACRO EXECUTION ENTRY, MXADDR.  @[@@@]UN
)@@G@@.     @#@#@]COMXFER   ROUTINE @^@@@#COMXFER   SUBROUTINE    @E@@@]      UO
)@@G@@    L         A1,M$COMXFER      . GET TRANSFER ADDRES @D@@@]          LAUP
)@@G@@        A5,PCL('NO TRANSFER ADDRESS!')    @G@@@]          JZ        A1,XUQ
)@@G@@FR999         . SHOULD NOT HAPPEN IF IN MACRO   @F@@@]          LA,H2   UR
)@@G@@  A0,M$XQTMACRO     . GET MACRO EXECUTION ENTRY @D@@@]          JZ      US
)@@G@@  A0,0              . ***DEBUG***   @F@@@]          SA        A1,MXADDR,UT
)@@G@@A0      . POST ADDRESS FOR NEXT READ@E@@@]          L,U       A5,0      UU
)@@G@@        . CLEAR ERROR FLAG    @D@^@]          J         XFR999          UV
)@@G@@  . AND RETURN    @[@^@].     @^@^@]. IO ERROR FROM SDFIM   @[@^@].     UW
)@@G@@@D@^@]XFR990    SLJ       M$IOERR           . AN IO ERROR   @E@^@]      UX
)@@G@@    LA,U      A5,1              . SET NO-MESSAGE ERROR@#@@@]XFR999    REUY
)@@G@@TURN  @[@@@].     @B@@@]          LITS                        .   @[@@@]UZ
)@@G@@.     @G@^@]MACONL    PCW       'COMMAND MAY ONLY BE EXECUTED FROM MACROVA
)@@G@@ MODE.'     @]@@@ M$MACONL*   @F@A@^MACONL    PCW       'COMMAND MAY ONLVB

)@@G@@M$SCANVLIST @@[@@@@@@@[V/,0J@[C8@@@@/,0^Z"'=@@@QA]0^+T9*)^+U9(@^+W[@K^+ZBR
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@^/         M$DEF   @[@@@^.     @C@@@^. THIS ROUTINE HANBS
)@@G@@DLES THE HISTORY FUNCTION.    @[@@@^.     @ @@@^.  $HIST(<NUM>)   OR  $HBT
)@@G@@IST   @[@@@^.     @H@@@^. THIS FUNCTION RETURNS THE SPECIFIED COMMAND FRBU
)@@G@@OM THE HISTORY QUEUE; <NUM>   @B@@@^. MUST BE IN THE RANGE OF [1..$HIST]BV
)@@G@@.     @H@@@^. IF <NUM> IS 1, THE MOST RECENT COMMAND IS RETURNED; IF NO BW
)@@G@@ARGUMENTS ARE     @D@@@^. GIVEN, THE # OF COMMANDS IN THE HISTORY IS RETBX
)@@G@@URNED.@[@@@^.     @#@@@^M$FUNHISTORY*     @^@@@^          SUBROUTINE    BY
)@@G@@@F@@@^          LA        A0,VDM+SRA        . GET THE RIGHT ARG MODE    BZ
)@@G@@@D@@@^          JE,U      A0,MODNUL HIST100 . SKIP IF NO ARG@F@B@^      CA
)@@G@@    LA        A5,PCL('ARGUMENT MUST BE SINGLE INTEGER.')    @F@C@B      CB
)@@G@@    LA        A5,PCL('ARGUMENT MUST BE A SINGLE INTEGER.')  @D@@@C      CC
)@@G@@    LA        A5,PCL('ARGUMENT MUST BE SCALAR.')@D@@@^          LA      CD
)@@G@@  A1,VDL+SRA        . GET THE LENGTH@E@@@^          TNE,U     A0,MODSIN CE
)@@G@@        . IS MODE CORRECT?    @F@@@^          TE,U      A1,1            CF
)@@G@@  . YES, IS LENGTH CORRECT?   @D@@@^          J         HIST999         CG
)@@G@@  . NO, ERROR OUT @G@@@^          LA        A0,VDA+SRA        . GET THE CH
)@@G@@ADDRESS OF THE VALUE    @F@@@^          LA        A1,M$COMCNT       . GECI
)@@G@@T COUNT OF COMMANDS     @D@@@^          ANA       A1,,A0            . GECJ
)@@G@@T THE VALUE @F@@@^          LA,U      A0,M$HISTORYQ     . GET THE HISTORCK
)@@G@@Y COUNT     @B@@@^          LA        A2,QHCOUNT        .   @E@@@^      CL
)@@G@@    AN,U      A2,,A1            . SUBTRACT THE INDEX  @G@@@^          LACM
)@@G@@        A1,M$RESULTBAW    . GET WORK BUFFER ACCESS WORD     @F@@@^      CN
)@@G@@    QCOPY                       . COPY THE QUEUE RECORD     @C@A@^      CO
)@@G@@    LA        A5,PCL('DOMAIN ERROR.')     @E@@@A          LA        A5,PCP
)@@G@@CL('HISTORY INDEX OUT OF RANGE.')   @F@@@^          JZ        A4,HIST999CQ
)@@G@@        . IF NOT FOUND, DOMAIN ERROR@E@@@^          LDSL      A1,36+2   CR
)@@G@@        . A1 = MAX CHAR LENGTH@F@@@^          LA,U      A0,M$RESULTBUF  CS
)@@G@@  . GET ADDRESS OF WORK BUFFER@F@@@^          CALL      M$RESULTASC     CT
)@@G@@  . POST THE STRING RESULTS   @D@@@^          JNZ       A5,HIST999      CU
)@@G@@  . EXIT ON ERRORS@C@@@^          J         HIST900           . GO EXIT CV
)@@G@@@[@@@^.     @ @@@^. $HIST  WITH NO ARGUMENTS    @[@@@^.     @E@@@^HIST10CW
)@@G@@0   LA,U      A0,M$HISTORYQ     . GET THE QUEUE HEADER@F@@@^          LACX
)@@G@@        A0,QHCOUNT        . & GET THE RESULT VALUE    @H@@@           ANCY
)@@G@@,U      A0,1              . DECREMENT BY ONE, DON'T COUNT CURRENT @F@@@^CZ
)@@G@@          CALL      M$RESULTINT       . GET AN INTEGER RESULT     @E@@@^DA
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,HIST999        . CHECK FOR ERROR     @[@@@^.     DB
)@@G@@@D@@@^. RETURN WITH A5,A0,A1 SET FROM M$INTANS OR M$STRANS  @[@@@^.     DC
)@@G@@@E@@@^HIST900   DS        A0,VD+SLA         . POST THE RESULT     @#@@@^DD
)@@G@@HIST999   RETURN  @[@@@^.     @#@@@^          END     _@@@@@        . GEDE
)@@G@@T THE VALUE @H@^@#          AN        A1,M$COMCN*[S@@[*SDFF*@^@@@@ 8)^@)DF
)@@G@@^@)^@)^@)D*=C- C0)@[@@@@ 0)^@)@L@@@@ 0)E-*HD3^[2H95I-(H1>^[(H(0H->H(>H14DG
)@@G@@IS)I-*G*)C-GD))G15H1<I-(H9,^@*C-(GT4HD\H1-IL9^[GG(6G(?^[GHD3I)( 0)@[@@@@DH
)@@G@@ 0)^@)@K@@@@ 0)C-GD)*B-?G(6G(?B0(^[2G(4I(2H13^[-^[?HD3I))H9&^[3I-2HD,G93DI

)@@G@@RESSION>    @[@@@S.     @E@@@S. WHERE <VAR-REF>    ::= <IDENT> ! <ARRAY-HM
)@@G@@REF> ! <TABLE-REF>@[@@@S.     @C@@@S.       <ARRAY-REF>  ::= <IDENT>[<ARHN
)@@G@@RAY-SUBS>]  @F@@@S.       <ARRAY-SUBS> ::= <INDEX> ! <INDEX>,<LENGTH> ! HO

)@@G@@.     @^@@@SM$COMLET* SUBROUTINE    @E@@@SLETNAM    LOCAL     2         HS
)@@G@@        . NAME OF VARIABLE    @F@@@SLETDL     LOCAL                     HT

)@@G@@DDRESS@D@@@SLETOPR    EQUF      LETTMP,,H2        . AN OPERATOR   @E@@@SIA
)@@G@@LETLS     LOCAL     1                 . SOME LOCAL STORAGE  @D@@@SLETINLIB
)@@G@@    EQUF      LETLS,,H1         . INDEX LENGTH  @C@@@SLETCOL    EQUF    IC
)@@G@@  LETLS,,Q3         . COLUMN #@F@@@SLETSCOL   EQUF      LETLS,,Q4       ID
)@@G@@  . SUBSCRIPT/INDEX COLUMN #  @]@@@S          . @E@@@S          SZ      IE
)@@G@@  LETVAD            . CLEAR LOCAL COPY    @B@@@S          SZ        LETVIF

)@@G@@BER   @D@@@S          TZ        M$LETAT           . ALLOW LET @?  @F@@@SIJ
)@@G@@          JNE,U     A1,M$OPERAT LET010 . SKIP IF NOT '@' OPERATOR @F@@@SIK

)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,,X11          . CALL THE SUBROUTINE @D@@@S      IM
)@@G@@    J         LET999            . AND RETURN    @D@@@SLET010    LA      IN
)@@G@@  A5,PCL('MISSING IDENTIFIER.')     @G@@@S          JNE,U     A0,MODNAM IO
)@@G@@LET900  . IF NOT NAME-LABEL, SYNTAX ERROR @E@@@S          DL        A0,0IP
)@@G@@,A1           . GET NAME OF IDENT   @H@@@S          LA        A2,M$SCANDIQ
)@@G@@L       . GET THE DICTIONARY LEVEL OF THE REF   @F@@@S          DS      IR

)@@G@@  A2,LETDL          . SAVE THE LEVEL ALSO @E@@@S          CALL      M$SCIT
)@@G@@ANITEM        . GET THE NEXT TOKEN  @ @@@S          JNZ       A5,LET999 IU
)@@G@@@F@@@S          SA        A4,LETCOL         . POST THE CURRENT COLUMN   IV
)@@G@@@D@@@S          AA,U      A4,1              . INCREMENT     @G@@@S      IW
)@@G@@    SA        A4,LETSCOL        . POST INITIAL SUBSCRIPT COLUMN   @H@@@SIX
)@@G@@          JNE,U     A0,MODOPR LET020  . IF NOT AN OPERATOR, GO CAUSE ERRIY
)@@G@@ORS   @H@@@S          JE,U      A1,M$OPEROPENPA LET300 . IF '(', GO STARIZ
)@@G@@T SUBSCRIPTING    @G@@@S          JE,U      A1,M$OPEROPENBR LET100 . IF JA
)@@G@@'[', GO START INDEXING  @G@@@SLET020    CALL      LET500            . CHJB
)@@G@@ECK OUT REMAINING EXPRESSION  @]@@@S          . @G@@@S          .       JC
)@@G@@  NORMAL (UNSUBSCRIPTED/UNINDEXED) STORE OPERATION.   @]@@@S          . JD
)@@G@@@F@@@S          $IF       EDPROCS           . ONLY IF OLD PROCS ARE ON  JE
)@@G@@@E@@@S          JEZ       M$EDPROCS LET030  . SKIP IF NO PROCS    @E@@@SJF
)@@G@@          LA,H2     A1,M$XQTMACRO     . GET THE CURRENT DEFN@E@@@S      JG
)@@G@@    JZ        A1,LET030         . SKIP IF NONE OPEN   @H@@@S          JEJH
)@@G@@Z       MXPF,A1 LET030    . IF NOT A PROC, STORE NORMAL VALUE     @E@@@SJI
)@@G@@          LA        A0,VDM+SVD        . GET THE RESULT MODE @C@@@S      JJ
)@@G@@    LA        A5,PCL('SYNTAX ERROR.')     @F@@@S          JNE,U     A0,MJK
)@@G@@ODSIN LET900  . IT'S GOTTA BE A NUMBER    @D@@@S          LA,U      A0,1JL
)@@G@@              . GET LENGTH    @E@@@S          SA        A0,VDL+SVD      JM
)@@G@@  . FORCE IT'S LENGTH   @[@@@SLET030@#@@@S          $ENDF   @F@@@S      JN
)@@G@@    DL        A0,LETNAM         . GET THE NAME TO BE STORED @G@@@S      JO
)@@G@@    LA        A2,LETDL          . AND THE DICTIONARY LEVEL FOR IT @F@@@SJP
)@@G@@          CALL      M$DLI             . INSERT AT THE PROPER LEVEL@C@@@SJQ
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,LET900         . ERROR   @F@@@S          LA,U    JR
)@@G@@  A0,,A2            . GET THE MV DESCRIPTOR     @D@@@S          LA,U    JS
)@@G@@  A1,VD+SVD         . THE VALUE PTR @D@@@S          CALL      M$MVSET   JT
)@@G@@        . SET THE VALUE @ @@@S          JNZ       A5,LET900 @C@@@S      JU

)@@G@@TIAL LIST REF: <IDENT>[ ...   @[@@@S.     @C@@@SLET100    DL        A0,LJW
)@@G@@ETNAM         . GET NAME@D@@@S          LA        A2,LETDL          . ANJX

)@@G@@. TABLE SUBSCRIPTING    @[@@@S.     @[@@@SLET300@E@@@S          DL      PN

)@@G@@LET320  . IF NOT NULL, DON'T DEFAULT TO TABLE   @F@@@S          CALL    PX
)@@G@@  M$XVARTABLE       . CREATE A TABLE DESCRIPTOR @ @@@S          JNZ     PY

)@@G@@TURN  @[@@@S/.    @B@@@S. COMMON CODE FOR SUBSCRIPTING/INDEXING.  @[@@@SRK

)@@G@@  LET110            . GO DO '['     @[@@@S.     @G@@@S. THIS ROUTINE EXASC
)@@G@@MINES THE CURRENT TOKEN FOR THE STORE OPERATOR, AND   @A@@@S. THEN SCANSSD
)@@G@@ THE VALUE TO BE STORED.@[@@@S.     @E@@@SLET500    SX        X11,LETRTNSE

)@@G@@LET505@F@@@S          $ENDF                       . OF SPECIAL ED PROC CSS

)@@G@@OWING ':='  @ @@@S          JNZ       A5,LET999 @F@@@S          LX      SV

)@@G@@@G@@@S          .         GENERATE ERROR MESSAGE FROM A5 PCW AT COLUMN LSY
)@@G@@ETCOL.@]@@@S          . @B@@@SLET900    L         A0,LETCOL         .   SZ

)@@G@@MP SAVE ERROR PCW @H@@@S          DL        A0,LETVAD         . GET ORIGTH
)@@G@@INAL VALUE DESCRIPTOR (IF ANY)@E@@@S          DJZ       A0,$+2          TI
)@@G@@  . SKIP IF NO COPY     @E@@@S          CALL      M$VDERS           . ERTJ
)@@G@@ASE THE VALUE NOW @G@@@S          TZ        LETTMP            . WAS ERROTK
)@@G@@R PCW THERE BEFORE?     @D@@@S          LA        A5,LETTMP         . YETL
)@@G@@S, GET IT   @#@@@SLET999    RETURN  @]@@@S          . @#@@@S          ENTM
)@@G@@D     _@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@TN

)@@G@@M$SCANITEM  M$LETAT     M$OPERAT    M$SCANDL    M$OPEROPENPAM$OPEROPENBRVM

)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@/         M$DEF   @[@@@@.     VS
)@@G@@@D@@@@. M$EXECUTE - ROUTINE TO EXECUTE A COMMAND IMAGE.     @[@@@@.     VT
)@@G@@@ @@@@.  A0 = (IMAGE LEN,IMAGE ADDR)@^@@@@.  LMJ  X11,M$EXECUTE   @^@@@@VU
)@@G@@.  A5 = ERROR PCW OR 0  @A@@@@.  A0 = ABORT FLAG (0 = NO ABORT)   @[@@@@VV
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@. THE IMAGE MUST BE IN ASCII, AND MUST CONFORM TO THE COMMANVW
)@@G@@D     @B@@@@. SYNTAX OF THE CONFIGURED MACRO PACKAGE. @[@@@@.     @#@[@@VX
)@@G@@M$EXECUTE* ROUTINE@^@@@[M$EXECUTE* SUBROUTINE   @B@@@@EXCTMP    LOCAL   VY
)@@G@@  1                 .   @#@@@@          SNOOPY  @G@@@@          LA      VZ
)@@G@@  A1,A0             . GET IMAGE ACCESS WORD TO A1     @F@@@@          T$WA
)@@G@@OPENA   M$TPKT            . OPEN TIDE$ ON NEW IMAGE   @[@@@@.     @C@@@@WB
)@@G@@. SCAN COMMAND AND FIND COMMAND OR MACRO NAME.  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@      WC
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,M$SCANCMD     . SCAN COMMAND  @F@@@@          JNZ     WD
)@@G@@  A5,EXC990         . ERROR IN COMMAND NAME     @E@@@@          JZ      WE
)@@G@@  A2,EXC999         . NO COMMAND FOUND    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. IF ANY FILWF
)@@G@@E PORTIONS OTHER THAN ELEMENT NAME GIVEN THEN   @ @@@@. M$SCANCMD RETURNWG
)@@G@@S A0A1 ZERO.@[@@@@.     @G@@@@          DJZ       A0,EXC010         . IFWH
)@@G@@ FILE GIVEN DO UNDEF SEARCH   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. FIRST CHECK TO SEE IF WI
)@@G@@CONTROL STRUCTURE COMMAND     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          LMJ       X11,WJ
)@@G@@M$XQTCONTROL  .   @C@@@@          JNZ       A5,EXC990         . ERROR   WK
)@@G@@@C@@@@          JNZ       A4,EXC999         . DID IT  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@WL
)@@G@@. COMMAND NAME IN A0-A1 CHAR COUNT IN A2. @[@@@@.     @F@@@@          LMWM
)@@G@@J       X11,M$XQTDEFMAC   . SEARCH FOR DEFINED MACRO  @E@@@@          JNWN
)@@G@@Z       A5,EXC990         . ERROR SOMEWHERE     @F@@@@          JNZ     WO
)@@G@@  A4,EXC020         . IF FOUND CALL IT PLEASE   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. IF NWP
)@@G@@OT DEFINED MACRO TRY COMMAND.  THIS ALLOWS DEFINED MACROS   @F@@@@. TO OWQ
)@@G@@VERRIDE COMMANDS OF THE SAME NAME.  NOT ABBREVIATED THO.    @[@@@@.     WR
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$XQTCOMMAND  . SEARCH COMMAND TABLE@E@@@@WS
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,EXC990         . ERROR SOMEWHERE     @G@@@@      WT
)@@G@@    JNZ       A4,EXC999         . COMMAND DONE - NEXT COMMAND     @[@@@@WU
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@. IF IT'S NOT A COMMAND EITHER WE SEARCH SEVERAL FILES FOR  WV
)@@G@@@F@@@@. SYMBOLIC ELEMENTS BY THAT NAME.  THIS ALLOWS NEW COMMANDS TO    WW
)@@G@@@A@@@@. BE BUILT TRANSPARENT TO THE USER. @[@@@@.     @]@@@@EXC010    . WX
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$XQTUNDMAC   . SEARCH FOR UNDEFINED MACROWY
)@@G@@@E@@@@          JNZ       A5,EXC990         . IF ERROR SAY SO     @[@@@@WZ
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@. MACRO FOUND IN SOME TABLE OR OTHER.  SCAN IMAGE AND CALL MXA
)@@G@@ACRO. @[@@@@.     @]@@@@EXC020    . @E@@@@          S         A0,EXCTMP XB
)@@G@@        . SAVE MACRO ENTRY    @F@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$CALLSCAN  XC
)@@G@@  . SCAN MACRO CALL IMAGE     @E@@@@          JNZ       A5,EXC990       XD
)@@G@@  . IF ERROR SAY SO     @D@@@@          DSL       A1,72             . DEXE
)@@G@@FAULT BITS  @I@@@@          JEZ       M$COMLINE EXC030  . IF KEYBOARD COXF
)@@G@@MMAND, DON'T DESCEND BITS     @E@@@@          LA,H2     A3,M$XQTMACRO   XG
)@@G@@  . GET THE MACRO LINK  @G@@@@          JZ        A3,EXC030         . IFXH
)@@G@@ NO MACRO, DON'T DESCEND BITS @G@@@@          LA        A1,MXFB,A3      XI
)@@G@@  . GET PREVIOUS MACRO FLAG BITS    @I@]@@          AND,U     A1,MXBGTR+XJ
)@@G@@MXBGSU  . EXTRACE THE GLOBAL TRACE & SUSPEND BITS     @I@@@]          ANXK
)@@G@@D,U     A1,MXBGTR+MXBGSU+MXBGVE . EXTRACE THE GLOBAL TRACE, SUSPEND     XL
)@@G@@@ @@@]          . AND VERBOSE BITS  @D@@@@          LA,U      A1,,A2    XM
)@@G@@        . COPY THEM     @G@]@@          SSL       A2,2              . TUXN
)@@G@@RN THESE INTO THE LOCAL BITS  @G@@@]          SSL       A2,3            XO
)@@G@@  . TURN THESE INTO THE LOCAL BITS  @F@@@@          AA,U      A1,,A2    XP
)@@G@@        . PUT THEM ALL TOGETHER     @G@@@@          LA,U      A2,,A1    XQ
)@@G@@        . MAY SET SOME BITS ALREADY SET   @G@@@@EXC030    TZ        M$TRXR
)@@G@@ACE           . IS THE GLOBAL TRACE FLAG SET?   @G@@@@          OR,U    XS
)@@G@@  A1,MXBTRA         . YES, SET THE LOCAL TRACE BIT    @G@@@@          TZXT
)@@G@@        M$SUSPEND         . IS THE GLOBAL SUSPEND FLAG SET? @G@@@@      XU
)@@G@@    OR,U      A1,MXBSUS         . YES, SET THE LOCAL SUSPEND BIT  @E@@@@XV
)@@G@@          L,H2      A1,EXCTMP         . GET MACRO ENTRY     @F@@@@      XW
)@@G@@    LXI,U     A1,,A2            . SET MACRO CALL TYPE BITS  @D@@@@      XX
)@@G@@    CALL      M$XQTCALL         . CALL MACRO    @E@@@@          JZ      XY
)@@G@@  A5,EXC999         . IF NO ERROR, OK     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. ERROR ENCOXZ
)@@G@@UNTERED. PRINT THE ERROR & MAYBE THE COMMAND LINE.    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@YA
)@@G@@EXC990    LMJ       X11,M$ERRMSGPRT   . PRINT THE CURRENT ERROR MESSAGE YB
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA,U      A5,1              . GET NON-MESSAGE ERROR     YC
)@@G@@@D@@@@EXC999    SA        A5,EXCTMP         . SAVE ERROR PCW@D@@@@      YD
)@@G@@    T$CLOSE                     . CLOSE TIDE$   @D@@@@          LA      YE
)@@G@@  A5,EXCTMP         . GET ERROR BACK@E@@@@          L         A0,M$ABORTYF
)@@G@@        . LOAD ABORT FLAG     @#@@@@          RETURN  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@YG
)@@G@@          END                         .   _@@@@@IL\^[>H1<H95H14G(2G(=^[-YH
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*+@@@@[@]@O@NG0)IT-I1>GC0+@@@@@@#@@@N/         M$DEF   @[@@@NYI
)@@G@@.     @G@@@N. THIS  ROUTINE  PERFORMS AN ERROR ESCAPE SEQUENCE. THE CURRYJ
)@@G@@ENT MACRO IS@G@@@N. MARKED AS SUSPENDED UNLESS THE 'ESCAPE' FLAG IS SET YK
)@@G@@ AND  THE  'TRACE'@G@@@N. AND  'SUSPENDED'  FLAGS ARE CLEAR, IN WHICH CAYL
)@@G@@SE, THE MACRO IS QUIETLY@G@@@N. POPPED FROM THE EXECUTION  STACK,  AND  YM
)@@G@@THE  NEXT  MACRO  IS  EXAMINED@]@@@N. SIMILARLY.@[@@@N.     @]@@@NM$ERREYN
)@@G@@SCAPE*@#@O@N          ROUTINE @^@@@O          SUBROUTINE    @E@@@N      YO
)@@G@@    LA,U      A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR REG     @F@@@N          TNYP
)@@G@@Z       M$COMLINE         . WAS COMMAND FROM A MACRO? @E@@@N          J YQ
)@@G@@        ERR999            . NO, DO NOTHING.     @[@@@NERE010@E@@@N      YR
)@@G@@    LA,H2     A0,M$XQTMACRO     . GET CURRENT MACRO   @E@@@N          JZYS
)@@G@@        A0,ERR999         . QUIT NOW IF NO MORE @D@@@N          LA      YT
)@@G@@  A1,MXFB,A0        . GET THE FLAGS @H@@@N          AND,U     A1,MXBSUS+YU
)@@G@@+MXBTRA . CHECK THE TRACE AND SUSPEND FLAGS     @G@@@N          JNZ     YV
)@@G@@  A2,ERE020         . IF EITHER FLAG SET GO SUSPEND   @G@@@N          JEYW
)@@G@@P,U     A1,MXBESC ERE020  . OR IF ESCAPE OFF GO SUSPEND     @E@@@N      YX
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,M$XQTPOPSTAK  . MAKE MACRO FADE AWAY@D@@@N          JNYY
)@@G@@Z       A5,ERR999         . QUIT ON ERRORS@D@@@N          J         ERE0YZ
)@@G@@10            . TRY NEXT LEVEL@[@@@NERE020@E@@@N          OR,U      A1,MZA
)@@G@@XBSUS         . SET SUSPENDED FLAG  @E@@@N          SA        A2,MXFB,A0ZB
)@@G@@        . POST THE NEW FLAGS  @G@@@N          SZ        MXSSC,A0        ZC
)@@G@@  . CLEAR ANY SUSPENDED SKIP COUNT  @B@@@N          M$EOPEN   M$EPKT M$IZD
)@@G@@MAGE    .   @D@@@N          L,H2      A0,M$XQTMACRO     . GET PROC ENTRYZE
)@@G@@@E@@@N          L         A0,MXMDL,A0       . GET MACRO DEF LINK  @B@@@NZF
)@@G@@          E$FD2     MDN,A0            .   @B@@@N          E$CHAR    '(' ZG
)@@G@@              .   @A@@@N          LA,H2     A0,M$XQTMACRO   @B@@@N      ZH
)@@G@@    E$DECV    MXLN,A0           .   @B@@@N          E$CHAR    ')'       ZI
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@N          M$EPRTX,U                   .   @^@@@N      ZJ
)@@G@@    LA,U      A5,0@[@@@NERR999@#@@@N          RETURN  @[@@@N.     @[@@@NZK
)@@G@@/.    @H@@@O. M$ERRMSGBLD - ROUTINE TO CONSTRUCT ERROR MESSAGE POINTING ZL
)@@G@@TO A GIVEN COLUMN.@[@@@O.     @^@@@O.  A0 = ERROR COLUMN    @^@@@O.  A5 ZM
)@@G@@= ERROR MESSAGE   @^@@@O.  LMJ  X11,M$ERRMSGBLD @^@@@O.  A5 = NEW ERR MSZN
)@@G@@G PCW @[@@@O.     @F@O@N. THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED TO GENERATE AN ERROR MEZO
)@@G@@SSAGE POINTING    @F@O@N. TO A PARTICULAR CARD COLUMN.  THE COLUMN NUMBEZP
)@@G@@R COMES IN A0     @B@O@N. AND THE MESSAGE IN AXW FORMAT IN A5.    @[@O@NZQ
)@@G@@.     @^@@@NM$ERRMSGBLD*        .   +@@@@[@ @O@N^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)ETPCLMD9PZR
)@@G@@E-DD1 +@@@@@@#@O@N          ROUTINE @D@O@NERBCOL    LOCAL     1         ZS
)@@G@@        . COLUMN NUMBER @D@O@NERBERM    LOCAL     1                 . ERZT
)@@G@@ROR MESSAGE @[@O@N.     @D@O@N          S         A0,ERBCOL         . SEZU
)@@G@@T COLUMN    @E@O@N          S         A5,ERBERM         . SET ERROR MESSZV
)@@G@@AGE   @D@O@N          LMJ       X11,M$PRTCOM      . PRINT COMMAND @F@@@OZW
)@@G@@          JNEZ      M$COMLINE ERB010  . SKIP IF MACRO COMMAND     @F@@@OZX
)@@G@@          TNZ       M$ERRECHO         . KEYBOARD COMMAND ECHOED?  @H@@@OZY
)@@G@@          AA        A0,M$SCANORIGIN   . NO, ADJUST CARAT BY COMMAND ORIGZZ
)@@G@@IN    @E@@@O          J         M$ERRCARAT        . GO PUT THE CARAT IN AA
)@@G@@@G@@@OERB010    AA,U      A0,COMORIGIN      . MACRO COMMANDS AT FIXED COAB
)@@G@@LUMN  @D@@@O.         J         M$ERRCARAT        . FALL THROUGH  @D@O@NAC
)@@G@@          M$EOPEN   M$EPKT M$IMAGE    . OPEN EDITING  @E@O@N          L AD
)@@G@@        A0,ERBCOL         . GET COLUMN NUMBER   @E@O@N          AA      AE
)@@G@@  A0,M$SCNORIG      . ADD THE SCAN ORIGIN @E@O@N          JLE,U     A0,AAF
)@@G@@SIMAX ERB010  . SKIP IF IT'S TOO BIG@E@O@N          E$COL               AG
)@@G@@        . GO TO THAT COLUMN   @B@O@N          E$MSG     POINTR          AH
)@@G@@  .   @D@O@NERB010    LN,S3     A1,ERBERM         . GET WORD COUNT@E@O@NAI
)@@G@@          L,H2      A0,ERBERM         . AND MESSAGE TEXT    @D@O@N      AJ
)@@G@@    E$COPY                      . COPY MESSAGE  @D@O@N          M$EAWX  AK
)@@G@@                    . CLOSE GET AXW @#@O@N          RETURN  @[@@@O.     AL
)@@G@@@E@@@O. M$ERRCARAT - ROUTINE TO EDIT A CARAT INTO AN ERROR MESSAGE@[@@@OAM
)@@G@@.     @ @@@O.  A0 = COLUMN (ORIGIN 0)     @B@@@O.  A5 = ERROR PCW (H1=0 AN
)@@G@@-> CARAT ONLY)    @#@@@O.  LMJ  M$ERRCARAT@ @@@O.  A0 = A5 = NEW ERROR MAO
)@@G@@SG PCW@[@@@O.     @]@@@OM$ERRCARAT* @^@@@O          SUBROUTINE    @F@@@OAP
)@@G@@          SA        A0,ERBCOL         . SAVE THE ERROR COLUMN     @F@@@OAQ
)@@G@@          SA        A5,ERBERM         . SAVE THE ERROR MESSAGE    @G@@@OAR
)@@G@@          LA,H2     A0,ERBERM         . GET THE ERROR BUFFER ADDRESS    AS
)@@G@@@G@@@O          JE,U      A0,M$EDITBUFFER ERCA999 . EXIT IF MSG IN EDIT AT
)@@G@@BUFFER@D@@@O          M$EOPEN   M$EPKT M$IMAGE    . OPEN EDITING  @E@@@OAU
)@@G@@          L         A0,ERBCOL         . GET COLUMN NUMBER   @E@@@O      AV
)@@G@@    TLE,U     A0,ASIMAX*4       . IS COLUMN IN RANGE? @E@@@O          E$AW
)@@G@@COL                       . GO TO THAT COLUMN   @E@@@O          E$MSG   AX
)@@G@@  ('^ &'L)          . INSERT THE POINTER  @D@@@O          LN,S3     A1,EAY
)@@G@@RBERM         . GET WORD COUNT@E@@@O          L,H2      A0,ERBERM       AZ
)@@G@@  . AND MESSAGE TEXT    @F@@@O          TZ,S3     ERBERM            . IFBA
)@@G@@ NO WORD COUNT, SKIP IT @D@@@O          E$COPY                      . COBB
)@@G@@PY MESSAGE  @D@@@O          M$EAWX                      . CLOSE GET AXW BC
)@@G@@@F@@@OERCA999   LA        A0,A5             . RETURN MSG PTR IN A0 TOO  BD
)@@G@@@#@@@O          RETURN  @[@@@N.     @D@@@OERBCOL    VAR       1         BE
)@@G@@        . ERROR COLUMN  @D@@@OERBERM    VAR       1                 . ERBF
)@@G@@ROR MESSAGE @B@O@NPOINTR    '^ &   '                    .   @[@@@N.     BG
)@@G@@@[@@@N/.    @D@@@N. THIS SUBROUTINE IS CALLED TO PRINT THE ERROR MESSAGEBH
)@@G@@@E@@@N. WHICH IS PASSED IN A5.  THE CURRENT MACRO (IF ANY) IS     @^@@@NBI
)@@G@@. MARKED AS SUSPENDED.  @[@@@N.     @^@@@NM$ERRMSGPRT*        .   @#@O@NBJ
)@@G@@          ROUTINE @^@@@O          SUBROUTINE    @C@@@NERPMSG    LOCAL   BK
)@@G@@  1                 . TEMP    @E@@@O          SZ        ERPMSG          BL
)@@G@@  . CLEAR INITIAL ERROR @F@@@OERP010    JE        A5,ERPMSG ERP999  . IFBM
)@@G@@ SAME ERROR, QUIT LOOP  @[@O@N.     @[@O@NERP010@E@O@N          S       BN
)@@G@@  A5,ERPMSG         . SAVE ERROR MESSAGE  @E@@@O          S         A5,EBO
)@@G@@RPMSG         . SAVE ERROR MESSAGE  @D@@@O          TNZ       M$ERRECHO BP
)@@G@@        . ERROR ECHO?   @F@O@N          TZ        M$COMLINE         . WABQ
)@@G@@S COMMAND FROM A MACRO? @G@@@O          TZ        M$COMLINE         . NOBR
)@@G@@, WAS COMMAND FROM A MACRO?   @G@@@N          LMJ       X11,M$PRTCOM    BS
)@@G@@  . YES, PRINT THE COMMAND LINE     @D@@@N          M$PRINT,1 ERPMSG    BT
)@@G@@        . PRINT MESSAGE @E@@@N          LMJ       X11,M$ERRESCAPE   . MABU
)@@G@@KE AN ERROR ESCAPE@F@@@N          JNZ       A5,ERP010         . IF ERRORBV
)@@G@@ HERE, TRY AGAIN  @#@O@N          RETURN  @#@@@OERP999    RETURN  @[@@@NBW
)@@G@@.     @H@@@O. M$ERRPRINT - ROUTINE TO PRINT ANY ERROR IN A5, AND ERROR IBX
)@@G@@MAGE IN TIDE$ BUF.@[@@@O.     @#@@@O.  A5 = ERROR PCW @^@@@O.  LMJ  X11,BY
)@@G@@M$ERRPRINT  @]@@@O.  A5 = 1   @[@@@O.     @F@@@O          T$FIELDS  0,X4BZ
)@@G@@              . GET TIDE$ PACKET DEFS     @]@@@OM$ERRPRINT* @^@@@O      CA
)@@G@@    SUBROUTINE    @F@@@O          LA        A0,BUFADR         . GET THE CB
)@@G@@BUFFER ADDRESS    @E@@@O          LXI       A0,BUFLNG         . AND THE CC
)@@G@@IMAGE LENGTH@F@@@O          M$APRINT,U                  . PRINT THE ERROCD
)@@G@@NEOUS IMAGE @E@@@O          M$PRINT,U A5                . PRINT THE ERROCE
)@@G@@R MSG @F@@@O          LA,U      A5,1              . RETURN ERROR NON-MESCF
)@@G@@SAGE  @D@@@O          SA        A5,M$ERRECHO      . POST ECHO FLAG@#@@@OCG
)@@G@@          RETURN  @[@@@N/.    @F@@@O. M$ERRMSGCMP - CALLED WHEN CONTROL CH
)@@G@@STRUCTURE ERRORS ARE DETECTED.@[@@@O.     @ @@@O. IF THE STACK TYPE IS ZCI
)@@G@@ERO:  @G@@@O.   NO (IF\REPEAT) FOR (ELSE\WHILE\UNTIL) OF LINE (###) IN MCJ
)@@G@@ACRO (XYZ)  @^@@@O. IF STACK TYPE NONZERO:@D@@@O.  (IF\REPEAT) OF LINE (CK
)@@G@@###) NOT CLOSED IN MACRO (XYZ)@[@@@O.     @F@@@O. M$CCMAC - MUST HAVE LICL
)@@G@@NK TO CURRENT COMPILING MACRO DEFINITION  @[@@@O.     @F@O@N. THIS ROUTICM
)@@G@@NE IS CALLED TO CREATE A DIAGNOSTIC ERROR MESSAGE WHEN@G@O@N. THE NESTINCN
)@@G@@G IS DISCOVERED TO BE IN ERROR.  IF THE STACK TYPE IS ZERO  @E@O@N. THENCO
)@@G@@ THE DIAGNOSTIC SEZ NO (IF) FOR (ELSE) OF LINE (NNN). @G@O@N. IF THE STACP
)@@G@@CKTYPE IS NONZERO IT SEZ (IF) OF LINE (NNN) NOT CLOSED.     @[@O@N.     CQ
)@@G@@@^@O@NM$ERRMSGCMP*        .   @^@@@OM$ERRMSGCMP* SUBROUTINE @#@O@N      CR
)@@G@@    ROUTINE @D@@@NERCTMP    LOCAL     1                 . TEMP SAVE     CS
)@@G@@@[@O@N.     @D@@@N          S         A0,ERCTMP         . SAVE TYPE     CT
)@@G@@@D@@@N          M$EOPEN   M$EPKT M$IMAGE    . OPEN EDIT     @F@@@N      CU
)@@G@@    L         A0,MSTYPE         . GET TYPE ON THE STACK     @F@@@N      CV
)@@G@@    JNZ       A0,ERC010         . IF NONZERO SAY NOT CLOSED @B@O@N      CW
)@@G@@    E$COPY    3,NONONO          .   @B@@@O          E$COPY    3,('NO 'L)CX
)@@G@@        .   @C@@@N          L         A0,ERCTMP         . GET TYPE@B@@@NCY
)@@G@@          E$MSG                       .   @B@O@N          E$COPY    5,FOCZ
)@@G@@RFOR          .   @B@@@O          E$COPY    5,(' FOR 'L)      .   @B@@@NDA
)@@G@@          E$MSGR                      .   @D@@@N          E$MSG     OFLIDB
)@@G@@NE            . 'OF LINE'     @F@@@N          E$DECV    M$YLIN          DC
)@@G@@  . EDIT IN CURRENT LINE #    @D@@@N          J         ERC020          DD
)@@G@@  . AND CLOSE     @[@@@N.     @ @@@N. SOMETHING ALREADY THERE     @[@@@NDE
)@@G@@.     @]@@@NERC010    . @D@@@N          E$MSG                       . EDDF
)@@G@@IT TYPE     @D@@@N          E$MSG     OFLINE            . 'OF LINE'     DG
)@@G@@@D@@@N          E$DECV    MSLINE            . LINE ON STACK @E@@@N      DH
)@@G@@    E$MSGR                      . 'IS NOT CLOSED'     @]@O@NERC020    . DI
)@@G@@@]@@@O          . @B@@@O          .         EDIT IN MACRO NAME    @]@@@ODJ
)@@G@@          . @A@@@OERC020    E$MSG     (' IN MACRO &'L)@G@@@O          LADK
)@@G@@        A3,M$CCMAC        . GET LINK TO CURRENT MACRO DEF   @F@@@O      DL
)@@G@@    E$FD2     MDN,A3            . INSERT THE MACRO NAME     @C@@@N      DM
)@@G@@    M$EAWX                      . GET AXW @#@@@N          RETURN  @[@@@NDN
)@@G@@.     @B@@@NOFLINE    ' OF LINE & IS NOT CLOSED&' .   @[@@@P/.    @C@@@PDO
)@@G@@. M$PSDFERR - ROUTINE TO DIAGNOSE PSDFIO ERRORS @[@@@P.     @^@@@P.  A0 DP
)@@G@@= PACKET ADDRESS  @ @@@P.  A3 = PSDFIO ERROR STATUS   @^@@@P.  LMJ  X11,DQ
)@@G@@M$PSDFERR   @#@@@P.  A5 = ERROR PCW @[@@@P.     @^@@@QM$PSDFERR* SUBROUTDR
)@@G@@INE   @D@@@QPSDPKT    LOCAL                       . PACKET ADDRESS@D@@@QDS
)@@G@@PSDEST    LOCAL                       . I/O STATUS    @D@@@QPSDFIL    LODT
)@@G@@CAL     2                 . FILE TYPE     @E@@@Q          SA        A0,PDU
)@@G@@SDPKT         . SAVE PACKET ADDRESS @E@@@Q          SA        A3,PSDEST DV
)@@G@@        . SAVE ERROR STATUS   @F@@@Q          DL        A2,,A0          DW
)@@G@@  . GET THE INTERNAL FILENAME @E@@@Q          DL        A0,('SCRATCH'DL)DX
)@@G@@  . GET THE FILE TYPE   @F@@@Q          DTE       A2,M$SCRFIL       . ISDY
)@@G@@ IT OUR SCRATCH FILE?   @G@@@Q          DL        A0,('SOURCE'DL)   . NODZ
)@@G@@, MUST BE THE SOURCE FILE     @E@@@Q          DS        A0,PSDFIL       EA
)@@G@@  . SAVE THE FILE TYPE  +@@@@[@I@Q@N^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)D*=C(JE[ D0)^@)D*=C(KEB
)@@G@@DTO^[H^-DD([C9 ^@)^@) 0)CL C9DD0)C(^DDODDIC8)^@)+@@@@@@D@@@Q          M$EC
)@@G@@EOPEN   M$EPKT M$IMAGE    . BEGIN EDITING @E@@@Q          LA        A3,PED
)@@G@@SDEST         . RECOVER ERROR STATUS@E@@@Q          JN        A3,PSD010 EE
)@@G@@        . SKIP IF USAGE ERROR @E@@@Q          E$MSG     ('I/O ERROR & &GEF
)@@G@@ MACRO & & FILE&'L)     @E@@@Q          E$OCTV    PSDEST            . INEG
)@@G@@SERT ERROR STATUS @#@@@Q          E$MSGR  @F@@@Q          LA        A3,PEH
)@@G@@SDPKT         . GET THE PACKET ADDRESS    @B@@@Q          DL        A0,(EI
)@@G@@'READINFROM'L)    @G@@@Q          LA        A2,PIOFNC,A3      . GET THE EJ
)@@G@@MOST RECENT FUNCTION    @F@@@Q          TNE,U     A2,W$             . WAEK
)@@G@@S IT THE WRITE FUNCTION?@C@@@Q          DL        A0,('WRITINTO'L)  . YEEL
)@@G@@S     @G@@@Q          SA        A1,PSDEST         . TEMP SAVE THE 'FROM'EM
)@@G@@ OR 'TO'    @G@@@Q          E$FD1                       . INSERT 'READINEN
)@@G@@' OR 'WRITIN'     @#@@@Q          E$MSGR  @F@@@Q          E$FD1     PSDEEO
)@@G@@ST            . NOW INSERT 'FROM' OR 'TO' @#@@@Q          E$MSGR  @E@@@QEP
)@@G@@          E$FD2     PSDFIL            . INSERT TYPE OF FILE @#@@@Q      EQ
)@@G@@    E$MSGR  @C@@@Q          J         PSD020            . ALL DONE@]@@@QER
)@@G@@          . @B@@@Q          .         PSDFIO USAGE ERROR    @]@@@Q      ES
)@@G@@    . @E@@@QPSD010    LN        A3,A3             . REVERSE SIGN OF FLAGET
)@@G@@@G@@@Q          LA        A0,PSDFERRS,A3    . GET THE APPROPRIATE MESSAGEU
)@@G@@E     @C@@@Q          SA        A0,PSDEST         . SAVE IT @B@@@Q      EV
)@@G@@    E$MSG     ('PSDFIO ERROR: &'L)  @E@@@Q          E$FD2     PSDFIL    EW
)@@G@@        . INSERT THE FILE TYPE+@@@@[@K@Q@N^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)C*=D(NC8)^@)^@)EX
)@@G@@E[NC- ETO )?D@2^@)^@)^@)^@) 0)D1JE8)DDIET ELO^[OD[ ^[HC(NET[C9 ^@)+@@@@@EY
)@@G@@@F@@@Q          E$MSG     PSDEST,,H2        . NOW INSERT THE MESSAGE    EZ
)@@G@@@G@@@QPSD020    M$EAWX                      . GET ACCESS WORD & TERM EDIFA
)@@G@@TING  @C@@@Q          RETURN                      . ALL DONE@]@@@Q      FB
)@@G@@    . @^@@@QPSDFERRS  EQUF      $+1 @A@R@Q          +         ('NOT OPENFC
)@@G@@ED&'L)@B@@@R          +         0,('NOT OPENED&'L)    @A@R@Q          + FD
)@@G@@        ('NOT CLOSED&'L)@B@@@R          +         0,('NOT CLOSED&'L)    FE
)@@G@@@C@R@Q          +         ('NOT OPENED FOR READING&'L)@D@@@R          + FF
)@@G@@        0,('NOT OPENED FOR READING&'L)    @C@R@Q          +         ('NOFG
)@@G@@T OPENED FOR WRITING&'L)@D@@@R          +         0,('NOT OPENED FOR WRIFH
)@@G@@TING&'L)    @D@R@Q          +         ('HAS NO BACKSPACE RECORDS&'L)    FI
)@@G@@@D@@@R          +         0,('HAS NO BACKSPACE RECORDS&'L)  @#@Q@P. ALTEFJ
)@@G@@RNATE ENTRY:@[@Q@P.     @^@Q@P.  A0 = PACKET ADDRESS  @^@Q@P.  A1 = MESSFK
)@@G@@AGE ADDRESS @ @Q@P.  A3 = PSDFIO ERROR STATUS   @^@Q@P.  LMJ  X11,M$PSDFFL
)@@G@@ERRA  @#@Q@P.  A5 = ERROR PCW @[@Q@P.     @B@O@NNONONO    'NO    '      FM
)@@G@@              .   @B@O@NFORFOR    ' FOR  '                    .   @[@O@NFN
)@@G@@/.    @E@O@N. M$IOERR - SLJ ENTRY POINT FOR IO ERRORS DURING MACRO READ.FO
)@@G@@@[@O@N.     @E@O@NM$IOERR*  VAR       1 +(J MIOREGS)    . AN SLJ ENTRY PFP
)@@G@@OINT  @G@O@NMIOREGS   SAVER     X11 A0            . SAVE LINK REG AND PAFQ
)@@G@@CKET ADDRESS@G@O@N          LA        A5,PCL('IO ERROR READING MACRO FROFR
)@@G@@M SCRATCH FILE')  @F@O@N          CALL      M$ERRMSGPRT       . PRINT THFS
)@@G@@E ERROR MESSAGE   @E@O@N          LOADR     MIOREGS           . RESTORE FT
)@@G@@USER REGS   @E@O@N          J         M$IOERR           . RETURN INDIRECFU
)@@G@@TLY   @[@@@O/.    @^@@@O. STACK OVERFLOW RETURN @[@@@O.     @#@@@OM$STOFFV
)@@G@@LO* SLJENTRY@ @@@O          SLJ       STACKEDIT @#@@@O          'OVER'  FW
)@@G@@@F@@@O          J         PAERR             . TAKE PREAMBLE ERROR EXIT  FX
)@@G@@@[@@@O.     @^@@@O. STACK UNDERFLOW RETURN@[@@@O.     @#@@@OM$STUFLO* SLFY
)@@G@@JENTRY+@@@@[@G@O@N^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^-DC0)^@)^@)^@)^9PD1^C(MC1GD9R^[#D[ CTFFZ
)@@G@@DDIC8$B*$D9AC0$^@)+@@@@@@ @@@O          SLJ       STACKEDIT @#@@@O      GA
)@@G@@    'UNDER' @[@@@O.     @H@@@OPAERR     TZ        M$ERROR           . ISGB
)@@G@@ THERE A CONFIGURED ERROR ADDRESS?  @E@@@O          J         *M$ERROR  GC
)@@G@@        . YES, THAT'S IT THEN @G@@@O          J         *M$DRIVERRTN    GD
)@@G@@  . NO, USE DRIVER ERROR RETURN     @[@@@O.     @#@@@OSTACKEDIT SLJENTRYGE
)@@G@@@B@@@OREGS      SAVER     X1,X3 X11,A5 R1,R3    @D@@@O          E$DIT   GF
)@@G@@  EDPKT             . OPEN EDITING  @F@@@O          E$MSG     ('STACK &FGG
)@@G@@LOW AT &; ':EREG(SSTKPTR):'=&')     @F@@@O          LA        A3,STACKEDGH
)@@G@@IT      . GET ADDRESS OF STACK ERROR@G@@@O          E$FD1     0,A3      GI
)@@G@@        . EDIT IN THE 'OVER' OR 'UNDER'   @E@@@O          E$MSGR        GJ
)@@G@@              . RESUME THE MESSAGE  @F@@@O          LA        A3,STACKEDGK
)@@G@@IT      . GET RETURN LINK AGAIN     @F@@@O          LA,S1     A2,,A3    GL
)@@G@@        . FIRST CHAR OF ARGUMENT    @F@@@O          LA,U      A4,1,A3   GM
)@@G@@        . A4=CORRECT RETURN ADDRESS @E@@@O          SA,H2     A4,STACKEDGN
)@@G@@IT      . POST CORRECT RETURN @F@@@O          LA        A3,M$STOFLO     GO
)@@G@@  . ASSUME IT WAS OVERFLOW    @C@@@O          TE,U      A2,'O'          GP
)@@G@@  . WAS IT? @F@@@O          LA        A3,M$STUFLO       . NO, IT WAS AN GQ
)@@G@@UNDERFLOW   @H@@@O          E$OCTF    6,0,A3,U          . INSERT THE ADDGR
)@@G@@RESS OF THE SLJ ERROR   @D@@@O          E$MSGR                      . MOGS
)@@G@@RE MESSAGE  @G@@@O          E$OCTF    12,SSTKPTR        . INSERT THE STAGT
)@@G@@CK POINTER ITSELF @E@@@O          E$PRT     0,1               . PRINT WHGU
)@@G@@AT WE HAVE  @D@@@O          LOADR     REGS              . RESTORE REGS  GV
)@@G@@@E@@@O          J         *STACKEDIT        . RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@OGW
)@@G@@.     @#@@@O          VARS    @C@@@OPRX11     RES       1               GX
)@@G@@  . USER X11@ @@@OEDPKT     E$PKT     14,EDBUF  @^@@@OEDBUF     RES     GY
