)@@G@@EFD2$       ECHAR$      EDECV$      M$EDITAW    M$PRINT     M$EDITCLOSE IS
)@@G@@M$ERRECHO   M$SCANORIGINM$EDITBUFFERECOL$       EMSG$       ECOPY$      IT
)@@G@@M$PRTCOM    EMSGR$      M$YLIN      M$CCMAC     M$SCRFIL    EOCTV$      IU
)@@G@@W$          EFD1$       M$ERROR     M$DRIVERRTN EDIT$       EOCTF$      IV
)@@G@@EPRT$       M$ERRCARAT  @@[@@@@@@@@,M$ERRESCAPE @@[@@@@@@@@@M$ERRMSGBLD IW
)@@G@@@@[@@@@@@@@*M$ERRMSGCMP @@[@@@@@@@[<M$ERRMSGPRT @@[@@@@@@@[CM$ERRPRINT  IX
)@@G@@@@[@@@@@@@[RM$PSDFERR   @@[@@@@@@@]JM$STOFLO    @@@@@@@@@@@IM$STUFLO    IY
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@KKW@@@@KQ@@@@KG@@@@KO@@@@LGL@@@KQ@@@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@=/     IZ
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @[@@@=.     @F@@@=. THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED TO COMPILE THE MAJA
)@@G@@CRO INTO THE SCRATCH    @F@@@=. FILE.  THE SECTOR ADDRESS IS IN A0 AND TJB
)@@G@@HE INTERNAL FILE NAME   @F@@@=. IS IN A1-A2.  RETURNS A0 POINTING TO THEJC
)@@G@@ DEFINE ENTRY FOR THE   @^@@@=. FIRST MACRO FOUND.    @^@@@=. ADDRESS ISJD
)@@G@@ IN A0.     @[@@@=.     @ @@@=M$COMPILER* SUBROUTINE STKPTR @#@@@=      JE
)@@G@@    SNOOPY  @H@@@=          MSI,U     A0,28             . MAKE SECTOR ADJF
)@@G@@DRESS A WORD ADDRESS    @F@@@=          S         A0,PIODA+MINPKT   . SEJG
)@@G@@T INPUT SECTOR ADDRESS  @E@@@=          DS        A1,PIOFN+MINPKT   . SEJH
)@@G@@T INPUT FILE NAME @G@@@=          M$TINIT   CMP999B (ASIMAX,M$YBUF) . OPJI
)@@G@@EN TIDE$ ON OUR BUFFER  @G@@@=          STKINIT   CMP999A           . INJJ
)@@G@@ITIALIZE THE COMPILER STACK   @F@@@=          PUSH      CMP999A         JK
)@@G@@  . PUSH AN INITIAL ENTRY     @]@@@=          . @D@@@=          .       JL
)@@G@@  OPEN INPUT ON MACRO SOURCE FILE.  @]@@@=          . @G@@@=          PSJM
)@@G@@DFRO    CMP900 MINPKT PIODA+MINPKT . OPEN READ ON INPUT FILE@F@@@=      JN
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,M$ASGSCRFILE  . ASSIGN THE SCRATCH FILE   @]@@@=      JO
)@@G@@    . @C@@@=          .         BUILD MACRO DEFINITION ENTRY@]@@@=      JP
)@@G@@    . @]@*@&   SLJ TON$ @F@@@=          DL        A0,PFPELT         . FIJQ
)@@G@@RST GET THE MACRO NAME  @ @@@=          $IF       EDPROCS   @E@@@=      JR
)@@G@@    LA,U      A2,EDPTYPE        . GET EDITOR PROC TYPE@E@@@=          TZJS
)@@G@@        M$EDPROCS         . SUPPORTING ED PROCS?@E@@@=          TE      JT
)@@G@@  A2,PFPSST         . YES, IS THIS ONE?   @B@@@=          $ENDF         JU
)@@G@@              .   @E@@@=          LA,U      A2,0              . NO, CLEAJV
)@@G@@R PROC FLAG @E@@@=          LA        A3,PSNWA+M$CMPPKT . GET STARTING AJW
)@@G@@DDRESS@E@@@=          LMJ       X11,M$MDCREATE    . MAKE A NEW MACRO DEFJX
)@@G@@@D@@@=          JNZ       A5,CMP999         . QUIT ON ERRORS@G@@@=      JY
)@@G@@    S         A2,CCMACR         . SET CURRENTLY COMPILING MACRO   @E@@@=JZ
)@@G@@          S         A2,FSMACR         . SET FIRST MACRO     @]@@@=      KA
)@@G@@    . @E@@@=          .         CREATE ADDITIONAL PAGES, IF NECESSARY   KB
)@@G@@@]@@@=          . @G@@@=          .         THE PAGE ALLOCATION IS BASEDKC
)@@G@@ UPON THE RELATION:     @]@@@=          . @ @@@=          .         TTA KD
)@@G@@<= TPA@]@@@=          . @H@@@=          .         WHERE TTA IS THE TOTALKE
)@@G@@ TEXT AREA IN THE MACRO SCRATCHFILE,@H@@@=          .         AND TPA ISKF
)@@G@@ THE TOTAL PAGE AREA, WHICH IS CALCULATED BY:   @G@@@=          .       KG
)@@G@@  TPA = M$PAGES * (M$PAGESIZE-PAGHL) * M$PAGEFACT     @]@@@=          . KH
)@@G@@@I@@@=CMP005    LA        A0,M$PAGES        . GET NUMBER OF PAGES CURRENKI
)@@G@@TLY ALLOCATED     @H@@@=          JG        A0,M$MINPAGES CMP007 . IF NOKJ
)@@G@@T ENOUGH DEFINED, CREATE NOW  @G@@@=          JLE       A0,M$MAXPAGES CMKK
)@@G@@P010 . IF ENOUGH CREATED, SKIP THIS @F@@@=          MSI       A0,M$PAGEFKL
)@@G@@ACT     . = M$PAGES * M$PAGEFACT    @F@@@=          LA        A1,M$PAGESKM
)@@G@@IZE     . GET (M$PAGESIZE-PAGHL)    @ @@@=          AN,U      A1,PAGHL  KN
)@@G@@@I@@@=          MSI       A0,A1             . = M$PAGES*M$PAGEFACT*(M$PAKO
)@@G@@GESIZE-PAGHL)     @H@@@=          LA        A1,PFPLEN         . GET SECTKP
)@@G@@OR LENGTH OF CURRENT MACRO    @E@@@=          MSI,U     A1,28           KQ
)@@G@@  . COMPUTE # WORDS     @C@@@=          L         A2,A1             . COKR
)@@G@@PY A1 @G@@@=          MSI       A2,M$PAGEFACT     . ADJUST TO MATCH UNITKS
)@@G@@S IN A0     @H@@@=          JLE       A2,A0             CMP007 . IF A2 <KT
)@@G@@ A0 GET ANOTHER PAGE    @G@@@=          AA        A1,PSNWA+M$CMPPKT . ADKU
)@@G@@D TEXT LENGTH ALREADY IN FILE @H@@@=          JGE       A1,A0 CMP010    KV
)@@G@@  . IF ENUF ROOM, DON'T GET MORE PAGES    @F@@@=CMP007    LA        A0,MKW
)@@G@@$PAGESIZE     . GET CONFIGURED PAGESIZE   @E@@@=          M$PGET    CMP9KX
)@@G@@99            . GET PERMANENT MEMORY@G@@@=          PIONP$    M$PSDFPA AKY
)@@G@@1       . INSERT INTO THE PAGING AREA     @F@@@=          INC       A0,MKZ
)@@G@@$PAGES        . ACCOUNT FOR A NEW PAGE    @D@@@=          J         CMP0LA
)@@G@@05            . TRY AGAIN     @]@@@=          . @B@@@=          .       LB
)@@G@@  WRITE INITIAL LABEL   @]@@@=          . @H@@@=CMP010    PSDFW     CMP9LC
)@@G@@00 M$CMPPKT (1,('*SDFF*')) (050,,,,,1) . WRITE LABEL  @E@@@=          SZLD
)@@G@@        M$YLIN            . CLEAR MACRO LINE #  @F@@@=          SZ      LE
)@@G@@  MINFLG            . CLEAR ASCII MODE FLAG     @E@@@=          SZ      LF
)@@G@@  MSTYPE            . CLEAR STACKED TYPE  @]@&@>   SLJ TON$ @E@@@=      LG
)@@G@@    J         CMP020            . GO READ FIRST IMAGE @]@@@=          . LH
)@@G@@@F@@@=          .         COMMENT COMPILER. CURRENTLY, COMMENTS ARE NOT LI
)@@G@@@F@@@=          .         OUTPUT TO THE SCRATCH FILE (UNLESS LABLED).   LJ
)@@G@@@]@@@=          . @F@@@=M$CMPCOMMENT* JNEZ  M$LABEL CMP080    . IF LINE LK
)@@G@@LABLED, OUTPUT IT @]@@@=          . @E@@@=          .         READ NEXT LL
)@@G@@IMAGE FROM MACRO SOURCE FILE. @]@@@=          . @]@@@=CMP020    . @E@@@=LM
)@@G@@          PSDFR     CMP900,CMP090 MINPKT BUFINAW . READ     @F@@@=      LN
)@@G@@    JP        A2,CMP030         . SKIP AHEAD IF DATA IMAGE  @D@@@=      LO
)@@G@@    L,S1      A0,PSRCW+MINPKT   . GET IMAGE TYPE@H@@@=          L,S6    LP
)@@G@@  A1,PSRCW+MINPKT   . AND ASCII/FDATA SWITCH IF 042 OR 050  @E@@@=      LQ
)@@G@@    AND,U     A1,1              . KEEP LAST BIT ONLY  @D@@@=          TELR
)@@G@@,U      A0,050            . HEADER LABEL? @F@@@=          TNE,U     A0,0LS
)@@G@@42            . ASCII/FD SWITCH IMAGE ?   @F@@@=          S         A2,MLT
)@@G@@INFLG         . YES - SET ASCII/FD FLAG   @D@@@=          J         CMP0LU
)@@G@@20            . NEXT LINE     @]@@@=          . @ @@@=          .       LV
)@@G@@  DATA IMAGE@]@@@=          . @]@@@=CMP030    . @G@@@=          JNEZ,S4 LW
)@@G@@  PSRCW+MINPKT CMP020 . IF IMAGE DELETED, IGNORE IT   @G@@@=          INLX
)@@G@@C       A0,M$YLIN         . INCREMENT THE MACRO LINE NUMBER @F@@@=      LY
)@@G@@    SZ        M$YADR            . CLEAR STRUCTURE ADDRESS   @E@@@=      LZ
)@@G@@    SA        A1,BUFOUTLEN      . SAVE WORD COUNT     @E@@@=          TZMA
)@@G@@        MINFLG            . IS INPUT IMAGE ASCII@E@@@=          J       MB
)@@G@@  CMP040            . YES - SKIP TRANSLATE@]@@@=          . @C@@@=      MC
)@@G@@    .         CONVERT IMAGE TO ASCII.     @]@@@=          . @D@@@=      MD
)@@G@@    M$EOPENA  M$EPKT M$IMAGE    . OPEN EDIT$    @E@@@=          LN      ME
)@@G@@  A1,BUFOUTLEN      . RESTORE WORD COUNT  @B@@@=          L,U       A0,MMF
)@@G@@$YBUF         .   @G@@@=          E$COPY                      . JEFF'S EMG
)@@G@@DIT$ CAN DO ANYTHING    @E@@@=          E$WRDN                      . GEMH
)@@G@@T A WORD COUNT    @F@@@=          SA        A0,BUFOUTLEN      . POST NEWMI
)@@G@@ BUFFER LENGTH    @E@@@=          LR        R1,A0             . USE FOR MJ
)@@G@@XFER COUNT  @B@@@=          LA        A0,M$IMAGE        .   @C@@@=      MK
)@@G@@    LXI,U     A0,1              . SET INCR@B@@@=          L         A1,(ML
)@@G@@1,M$YBUF)     .   @E@@@=          BT        A1,0,*A0          . TRANSFERMM
)@@G@@ TO JLINE   @B@@@=          M$ECLOSE                    .   @]@@@=      MN
)@@G@@    . @D@@@=          .         OPEN INPUT SCAN FOR COMMAND NAME. @E@@@=MO
)@@G@@          .         BUT FIRST, STRIP OF TRAILING BLANKS.    @]@@@=      MP
)@@G@@    . @F@@@=CMP040    LA        A0,BUFOUTLEN      . GET THE INPUT IMAGE MQ
)@@G@@LENGTH@D@@@=          LA        A4,M$ASBLANKS     . LOOK FOR THESE@F@@@=MR
)@@G@@CMP050    JZ        A0,CMP060         . SKIP TRIM IF NO IMAGE     @E@@@=MS
)@@G@@          TNE       A4,M$YBUF-1,A0    . LAST WORD BLANK?    @G@@@=      MT
)@@G@@    JGD       A0,CMP050         . YES, DECR COUNT & LOOK AGAIN    @F@@@=MU
)@@G@@CMP060    SA        A4,M$YBUF,A0      . BLANK LAST WORD FOR TIDE$ @H@@@=MV
)@@G@@          S,S3      A0,M$MYPR         . SET LENGTH IN CASE WE PRINT IMAGMW
)@@G@@E     @G@@@=          AU,U      A0,2              . ADD TWO FOR BEGINNINMX
)@@G@@G WORDS     @F@@@=          SA        A1,BUFOUTLEN      . POST OUTPUT BUMY
)@@G@@FFER LENGTH @E@@@=          L,U       A1,0,A0           . GET IMAGE LENGMZ
)@@G@@TH    @F@@@=          T$CLR                       . TELL TIDE$ WATS HAPNNA
)@@G@@IN    @G@@@=          CALL      M$SCANCCMD        . GET THE COMPILED COMNB
)@@G@@MAND NAME   @G@@@=          JNZ       A5,CMP080         . ANY ERRORS - JNC
)@@G@@UST OUTPUT LINE   @]@@@=          . @E@@@=          .         IF A LABELND
)@@G@@ WAS FOUND, INSERT IT INTO THE@E@@@=          .         LABEL SYMBOL TABNE
)@@G@@LE CHAINED OFF THE MACRO@B@@@=          .         DEFINITION ENTRY.     NF
)@@G@@@]@@@=          . @G@@@=          JEZ       M$LABEL CMP070    . IF NO LANG
)@@G@@BEL, IGNORE ALL THIS    @F@@@=          DS        A0,CMPCOM         . SANH
)@@G@@VE THE COMMAND NAME     @D@@@=          DL        A0,M$LABEL        . GENI
)@@G@@T THE LABEL @F@@@=          LA        A3,CCMACR         . GET CURRENT MANJ
)@@G@@CRO DEFN    @F@@@=          LA        A3,MDLTL,A3       . GET THE LABEL NK
)@@G@@TABLE LINK  @E@@@=          LMJ       X11,M$MVCREATE    . MAKE A LABEL DNL
)@@G@@EF    @F@@@=          JNZ       A5,CMP999         . TAKE ERROR EXIT MAYBNM
)@@G@@E     @F@@@=          LA        A0,A2             . GET NEW DESCRIPTOR INN
)@@G@@N A0  @G@@@=          LA,U      A1,CMPLABL        . DEFINE LABEL WITH CUNO
)@@G@@RRENT LINE #@E@@@=          LMJ       X11,M$MVSET       . SET THE VARIABNP
)@@G@@LE    @G@@@=          JNZ       A5,CMP999         . TAKE ERROR EXIT IF NNQ
)@@G@@ECESSARY    @E@@@=          DL        A0,CMPCOM         . RESTORE THE CONR
)@@G@@MMAND @F@@@=          DTE       A0,('            ') . IS THERE A COMMANDNS
)@@G@@?     @E@@@=          J         CMP070            . YES, SEARCH FOR IT  NT
)@@G@@@E@@@=          L         A0,($CAS('.   ')) . GET ASCII PERIOD    @E@@@=NU
)@@G@@          L         X11,BUFOUTLEN     . GET LENGTH OF IMAGE @F@@@=      NV
)@@G@@    S         A0,M$YBUF-2,X11     . ADD COMMENT TO THE IMAGE@B@@@=      NW
)@@G@@    A,U       X11,1             .   @B@@@=          S         X11,BUFOUTNX
)@@G@@LEN     .   @B@@@=          DL        A0,('.           ')   @]@@@=      NY
)@@G@@    . @#@@@=          LITS    @G@@@=CMPLABL   VD        MODSIN 1,M$YLIN NZ
)@@G@@  . GENERATE A VALUE DESCRIPTOR     @#@@@=          INSTRS  @]@@@=      OA
)@@G@@    . @G@@@=          .         LOOK FOR THE COMMAND IN THE COMPILED COMOB
)@@G@@MAND LIST.  @]@@@=          . @[@@@=CMP070@I@@@=          TSE       A0,COC
)@@G@@CNAME,A2 CCSIZE,M$CMPTABLE . SEARCH COMPILED COMMAND TAB    @D@@@=      OD
)@@G@@    J         CMP080            . JUST XFER     @F@@@=          LA      OE
)@@G@@  A0,CCADRC,A2      . GET COMPILATION ROUTINE   @G@@@=          JZ      OF
)@@G@@  A0,CMP080         . IF NOT CONFIGURED, JUST XFER    @F@@@=          LMOG
)@@G@@J       X11,0,A0          . CALL COMPILER ROUTINE     @E@@@=          JNOH
)@@G@@Z       A5,CMP999         . IF ERROR IN COMPILER@E@@@=          J       OI
)@@G@@  CMP020            . ELSE NEXT COMMAND   @]@@@=          . @F@@@=      OJ
)@@G@@    .         NON-COMPILED IMAGE: OUTPUT TO SCRATCH FILE.   @]@@@=      OK
)@@G@@    . @]@@@=CMP080    . @G@@@=          LMJ       X11,M$CMPOUTPUT   . OUOL
)@@G@@TPUT IMAGE TO SCRATCH FILE    @E@@@=          JNZ       A5,CMP999       OM
)@@G@@  . IF ERROR RETURN     @D@@@=          J         CMP020            . NEON
)@@G@@XT IMAGE    @]@@@=          . @D@@@=          .         END OF FILE ON MOO
)@@G@@ACRO SOURCE FILE. @]@@@=          . @]@@@=CMP090    . @F@@@=          PSOP
)@@G@@DFW     CMP900 M$CMPPKT 0,,U (0770000,0) . WRITE EOF  @]@>@=   SLJ TON$ OQ
)@@G@@@B@@@=          SZ,S3     M$PRTAXW          .   @E@@@=          TNZ     OR
)@@G@@  MSTYPE            . IS STACK EMPTY ?    @E@@@=          J         CMP1OS
)@@G@@00            . YES - FINISH UP     @E@@@=          LMJ       X11,M$ERRMOT
)@@G@@SGCMP   . BUILD ERROR MESSAGE @D@@@=          J         CMP999          OU
)@@G@@  . AND ERROR OFF @]@@@=          . @H@@@=          .         ALL DONE. OV
)@@G@@RETURN MACRO DEFINITION ADDRESS OF FIRST MACRO. @]@@@=          . @]@@@=OW
)@@G@@CMP100    . @B@@@=          L         A0,FSMACR         .   @E@@@=      OX
)@@G@@    L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR FLAG    @D@@@=          J OY
)@@G@@        CMP999            . AND RETURN    @]@@@=/         . @C@@@=      OZ
)@@G@@    .         ERRORS IN PSDFIO COME HERE. @]@@@=          . @F@@@=CMP900PA
)@@G@@    CALL      M$PSDFERR         . DIAGNOSE PSDFIO ERRORS    @]@@@=      PB
)@@G@@    . @F@@@=          .         EXIT THROUGH HERE, WITH A5 = ERROR PCW OPC
)@@G@@R 0.  @]@@@=          . @C@@@=CMP999    S         A5,CMPTMP         . SAPD
)@@G@@VE PCW@F@@@=          STKTERM                     . RELEASE CURRENT STACPE
)@@G@@K     @D@@@=          TNZ       CMPTMP            . ANY ERROR?    @E@@@=PF
)@@G@@          SA        A5,CMPTMP         . NO, MAYBE NOW YES   @G@@@=      PG
)@@G@@    PSDFRCE   CMP900 MINPKT     . CLOSE THE SOURCE FILE INPUT     @E@@@=PH
)@@G@@          JEZ       CMPTMP CMP999A    . SKIP IF NO ERRORS   @]@@@=      PI
)@@G@@    . @D@@@=          .         ERRORS - DELETE THE CURRENT MACRO.@]@@@=PJ
)@@G@@          . @G@@@=          LA        A0,CCMACR         . GET THE CURRENPK
)@@G@@T MACRO POINTER   @E@@@=          DL        A0,MDN,A0         . GET THE PL
)@@G@@MACRO NAME  @E@@@=          LMJ       X11,M$MDERASE     . ERASE THE DEFIPM
)@@G@@NITION@D@@@=                                      . IGNORE ERRORS @E@@@=PN
)@@G@@          LA        A5,CMPTMP         . RESTORE ERROR PCW   @E@@@=CMP999PO
)@@G@@A   SA        A5,CMPTMP         . SAVE ANY ERRORS     @E@@@=          M$PP
)@@G@@TTERM                     . TERMINATE TIDE$     @G@@@=          TZ      PQ
)@@G@@  CMPTMP            . WAS THERE A PREVIOUS ERROR?     @D@@@=          L PR
)@@G@@        A5,CMPTMP         . GET ERROR FLAG@E@@@=          L         A0,FPS
)@@G@@SMACR         . GET FIRST MACRO     @]@*@$  SLJ TOFF$ @B@@@=CMP999B   REPT
)@@G@@TURN                      .   @]@@@=          . @A@@@=          .       PU
)@@G@@  COMPILER DATA.  @]@@@=          . @D@@@=CMPTMP    LOCAL     2         PV
)@@G@@        . TEMP STORAGE  @D@@@=CCMACR    LOCAL     1                 . CUPW
)@@G@@RRENT MACRO @G@@@=M$CCMAC*  EQU       CCMACR            . EXTERNALIZE CUPX
)@@G@@RRENT MACRO LINK  @D@@@=FSMACR    LOCAL     1                 . FIRST MAPY
)@@G@@CRO   @E@@@=MINFLG    LOCAL     1                 . ASCII/FD INPUT FLAG PZ
)@@G@@@E@@@=CMPCOM    LOCAL     2                 . SCANNED COMMAND     @]@@@=QA
)@@G@@          . @#@@@=          VARS    @F@@@=M$MYPR    +         0100,M$YBUQB
)@@G@@F               . PRINT INPUT BUFFER@G@@@=BUFOUTAW  +         $-$,M$YADRQC
)@@G@@        . I/O ACCESS WORD FOR SCRATCH FILE@E@@@=BUFOUTLEN EQUF      BUFOQD
)@@G@@UTAW,,H1      . OUTPUT BUFFER LENGTH@E@@@=M$YADR*   RES       1         QE
)@@G@@        . STRUCTURE ADDRESS   @F@@@=M$YLIN*   RES       1               QF
)@@G@@  . LINE NUMBER WITHIN MACRO  @E@@@=M$YBUF*   RES       ASIMAX+1        QG
)@@G@@      . INPUT BUFFER    @]@@@=          . @B@@@=MINPKT    PSDFPKT   '-FIQH
)@@G@@LENAME-' M$PSDFPA @]@@@=          . @^@@@=          LITS      .   @]@@@=QI
)@@G@@          . @G@@@=BUFINAW   +         ASIMAX,M$YBUF     . ACCESS WORD FOQJ
)@@G@@R SOURCE FILE READ@]@@@=          . @D@@@=M$CPSOVR* PCW       'MACRO COMQK
)@@G@@PILER STACK OVERFLOW.'  @#@@@=          INSTRS  @]@@@=/         . @G@@@=QL
)@@G@@          .         COMPILE  THE 'MACRO' COMMAND. THE STACK MUST AT THISQM
)@@G@@@G@@@=          .         POINT BE TYPE MACRO, BECAUSE THE  INITIAL  PUSQN
)@@G@@H  WAS@G@@@=          .         DONE  WHEN PSDF INPUT WAS OPENED. CREATEQO
)@@G@@ A NEW MACRO@B@@@=          .         DEFINITION ENTRY.     @]@@@=      QP
)@@G@@    . @^@@@=M$CMPMACRO* SUBROUTINE  @E@@@=          TNZ       MSTYPE    QQ
)@@G@@        . IS STACK EMPTY ?    @D@@@=          J         CMA010          QR
)@@G@@  . YES - SKIP    @E@@@=          LMJ       X11,M$ERRMSGCMP   . GEN ERROQS
)@@G@@R MESSAGE   @D@@@=          J         CMA999            . AND ERROR     QT
)@@G@@@E@@@=CMA010    CALL      M$SCANITEM        . SCAN FOR MACRO NAME @C@@@=QU
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,CMA999         . OOPS    @D@@@=          L       QV
)@@G@@  A5,PCL('ILLEGAL MACRO NAME.')     @D@@@=          TE,U      A0,MODNAM QW
)@@G@@        . NAME-LABEL ?  @C@@@=          J         CMA999            . OOQX
)@@G@@PS    @F@@@=          PSDFW     CMA900 M$CMPPKT 0,,U (0770000,0) . WRITEQY
)@@G@@ EOF  @G@@@=          LA        A0,VDA+SVD        . GET THE ADDRESS OF TQZ
)@@G@@HE NAME     @E@@@=          DL        A0,,A0            . GET THE MACRO RA
)@@G@@NAME  @G@@@=          LA,U      A2,0              . INTERNAL MACROS CANNRB
)@@G@@OT BE PROCS @E@@@=          LA        A3,PSNWA+M$CMPPKT . GET STARTING ARC
)@@G@@DDRESS@F@@@=          LMJ       X11,M$MDCREATE    . CREATE A NEW MACRO DRD
)@@G@@EF    @D@@@=          JNZ       A5,CMA999         . DIE ON ERRORS @G@@@=RE
)@@G@@          S         A2,CCMACR         . SET CURRENT COMPILING MACRO     RF
)@@G@@@H@@@=          PSDFW     CMA900 M$CMPPKT (1,('*SDFF*')) (050,,,,,1) . WRG
)@@G@@RITE LABEL  @E@@@=          L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR FLRH
)@@G@@AG    @ @@@=          J         CMA999    @G@@@=CMA900    CALL      M$PSRI
)@@G@@DFERR         . PRODUCE PSDFIO ERROR MESSAGE    @#@@@=CMA999    RETURN  RJ
)@@G@@@]@@@=          . @H@@@=          .         OUTPUT CURRENT IMAGE; CONTRORK
)@@G@@L WORD IN PSRCW+M$CMPPKT.     @]@@@=          . @^@@@=M$CMPOUTPUT* SUBRORL
)@@G@@UTINE @F@@@=          PSDFW     CMPO900 M$CMPPKT BUFOUTAW (0) . WRITE IMRM
)@@G@@AGE   @E@@@=          L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR FLAG    RN
)@@G@@@C@@@=          J         CMPO999           . QUIT    @F@@@=CMPO900   CARO
)@@G@@LL      M$PSDFERR         . PRODUCE PSDFIO ERROR MSG  @#@@@=CMPO999   RERP
)@@G@@TURN  @]@@@=          . @E@@@=          .         UPDATE STRUCTURE CONTRRQ
)@@G@@OL WORD OF RECORD.@E@@@=          .         A2 = RECORD ADDRESS; A1 = NERR
)@@G@@W VALUE     @]@@@=          . @^@@@=M$CMPUPDATE* SUBROUTINE @F@@@=UPDVALRS
)@@G@@    LOCAL                       . VALUE TO USE FOR UPDATE   @E@@@=      RT
)@@G@@    SA        A1,UPDVAL         . SAVE UPDATE VALUE   @I@@@=          AARU
)@@G@@,U      A2,1              . INCREMENT RECORD ADDRESS TO STRUCTURE WO    RV
)@@G@@@E@@@=          SA        A2,PIODA+M$CMPPKT . POST DISK ADDRESS   @G@@@=RW
)@@G@@          LA,U      A1,UPDVAL         . GET ADDRESS OF WORD TO UPDATE   RX
)@@G@@@D@@@=          LXI,U     A1,1              . # WORDS UPDATE@F@@@=      RY
)@@G@@    SA        A1,PIOBAW+M$CMPPKT . POST BUFFER ACCESS WORD  @F@@@=      RZ
)@@G@@    PIOW$     PIOPKT+M$CMPPKT   . WRITE THE UPDATE WORD     @E@@@=      SA
)@@G@@    LA,U      A5,0              . ASSUME NO ERRORS    @E@@@=          JZSB
)@@G@@        A3,CMPU999        . QUIT IF NO ERROR    @C@@@=          CALL    SC
)@@G@@  M$PSDFERR         . ERROR   @#@@@=CMPU999   RETURN  @[@@@=/.    @D@@@=SD
)@@G@@. M$ASGSCRFILE - ROUTINE TO ASSIGN THE SCRATCH FILE.  @H@@@=. M$RELSCRFISE
)@@G@@LE - ROUTINE TO RELEASE THE SCRATCH FILE (FOR REINITIALIZATION).  @[@@@=SF
)@@G@@.     @#@@@=M$ASGSCRFILE*     @F@@@=          JNEZ      PSMODE+M$CMPPKT SG
)@@G@@0,X11 . IF FILE OPENED, EXIT  @^@@@=          SUBROUTINE    @G@@@=      SH
)@@G@@    DL        A0,M$SCRFIL       . GET USER-DEFINED SCRATCH FILE   @G@@@=SI
)@@G@@          DS        A0,ASGPKT+4       . POST INTO THE FILENAME POSITION SJ
)@@G@@@E@@@=          FIASG,'T' ASGPKT            . ASSIGN SCRATCH FILE @H@@@=SK
)@@G@@          DS        A1,M$CMPPKT       . SAVE FILENAME INTO THE COMPILER SL
)@@G@@PACKET@E@@@=          JN        A3,0              . ERROR IF BAD ASSIGN SM
)@@G@@@F@@@=          PSDFWO    ASG900 M$CMPPKT 0,,U . START WRITING HERE     SN
)@@G@@@ @@@=          J         ASG999    @G@@@=ASG900    CALL      M$PSDFERR SO
)@@G@@        . PRODUCE PSDFIO ERROR MESSAGE    @#@@@=ASG999    RETURN  @]@@@=SP
)@@G@@          . @#@@@=          VARS    @E@@@=ASGPKT    FIPELT    'F','-FILESQ
)@@G@@NAME-'  . BUILD ELT$ PACKET   @]@@@=          . @#@@@=          INSTRS  SR
)@@G@@@]@@@=          . @#@@@=M$RELSCRFILE*     @^@@@=          SUBROUTINE    SS
)@@G@@@C@@@=RELCOM    LOCAL                       . @FREE   @C@@@=RELFIL    LOST
)@@G@@CAL     2                 . FILENAME@G@@@=          JEZ       PSMODE+M$CSU
)@@G@@MPPKT REL010 . SKIP IF FILE NOT OPENED    @D@@@=          PSDFWCE   REL0SV
)@@G@@10 M$CMPPKT   . CLOSE THE FILE@E@@@=REL010    DL        A0,M$SCRFIL     SW
)@@G@@  . GET THE SCRATCH FILE@F@@@=          DS        A0,RELFIL         . SASX
)@@G@@VE THE FILENAME IN SITU @E@@@=          LA        A0,('@FREE ')     . GESY
)@@G@@T THE CSF$ COMMAND@B@@@=          SA        A0,RELCOM         .   @E@@@=SZ
)@@G@@          LA,U      A0,RELCOM         . GET THE ADDRESS     @E@@@=      TA
)@@G@@    LXI,U     A0,3              . SET WORD LENGTH     @^@@@=          ERTB
)@@G@@        CSF$@#@@@=          RETURN  @]@@@=          . @#@@@=          RETC
)@@G@@SUME  @B@@@=          END                         .   _@@@@@DMTYPE      TD
)@@G@@  . ASSUME MACRO  @G@@@B          LA,S3     A1,PFPTDW         . GET YEARTE
)@@G@@ MOD 64 FROM TDATE$ WORD@H@@@B          TLE,U   )@@[##@[#@@JA@0@JA@0@K0#TF

)@@G@@/K@@#4%8)@@(/K@@ $:8)@[W/,0@CLQBU@@^[C0@@FBP@@@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@C/     SJ
)@@G@@    M$DEF   @#@@@C          FIDEF$  @[@@@C.     @F@@@C. THIS ROUTINE IS SK
)@@G@@CALLED TO SEARCH A FILE FOR A SYMBOLIC ELEMENT  @E@@@C. THE FILE NAME ANSL
)@@G@@D ELEMENT NAME ARE PASSED IN A FULL FIASG @E@@@C. PACKET WHOSE ADDRESS ISM
)@@G@@S PASSED IN A0.  UPON NORMAL RETURN @E@@@C. (A5 ZERO) A4 WILL BE SET TO SN
)@@G@@ONE IF THE MACRO WAS FOUND.   @F@@@C. IN THIS CASE THE COMPILER WILL HAVSO
)@@G@@E BEEN CALLED AND A0 WILL     @E@@@C. CONTAIN THE MACRO DEF ENTRY FOR THSP
)@@G@@E STAND ALONE SECTION OF@]@@@C. THE MACRO.@E@@@C. NOTE THAT IF THE FILE SQ
)@@G@@DOES NOT EXIST A NORMAL RETURN WITH @^@@@C. A4 ZERO WILL BE MADE. @[@@@CSR
)@@G@@.     @^@@@CM$FILESEARCH*       .   @^@@@C          SUBROUTINE    @E@@@CSS
)@@G@@MFSFRE    LOCAL     1                 . @FREE CODE FOR FILE @G@@@CMFSTMPST
)@@G@@    LOCAL     3                 . SAVE FOR A4,A5 OVER FILE FREE   @[@@@CSU
)@@G@@.     @H@@@C          LXI,U     A0,FIUPRD+FIUFOR  . WANT READ PERMISSIONSV
)@@G@@S & FORCED USENAME@D@@@C          LMJ       X11,FIASG$        . ASSIGN FSW
)@@G@@ILE   @]@D@C  SLJ TON$  @F@@@C          DS        A1,PFPFIL         . SASX
)@@G@@VE INTERNAL FILE NAME   @E@@@C          S         A4,MFSFRE         . SASY
)@@G@@VE @FREE CODE     @E@@@C          JP        A3,MFS020         . IF FILE SZ
)@@G@@GOTTEN SKIP @[@@@C.     @ @@@C. PROBLEMS ASSIGNING FILE.    @[@@@C.     TA
)@@G@@@G@@@C          TOP       A3,BML(13)        . IF IT IS A PRIVATE FILE, OTB
)@@G@@R ... @E@@@C          TEP       A3,BML(21)        . FILE DOES NOT EXIST TC
)@@G@@@F@@@C          J         MFS010            . THEN - SKIP ERROR MESSAGE TD
)@@G@@@F@@@C          DL        A1,4,A0           . GET EXTERNAL FILE NAME    TE
)@@G@@@D@@@C          DS        A1,MFSFAF         . SAVE FILE NAME@E@@@C      TF
)@@G@@    M$PRINT,U MFSEFA            . PRINT ERROR MESSAGE @E@@@C          L TG
)@@G@@        A0,A3             . GET A0 AFTER CSF$   @E@@@C          AND     TH
)@@G@@  A0,CBML(35)       . MASK OFF BIT 35     @E@@@C          L,U       A0,FTI
)@@G@@IPKT$+2       . GET A0 BEFORE CSF$  @D@@@C          LMJ       X11,M$ERRCTJ
)@@G@@SF      . CALL ERROR REP@]@@@CMFS010    . @F@@@C          DSL       A4,7TK
)@@G@@2             . SET NO ERROR AND NO FIND  @D@@@C          J         MFS9TL
)@@G@@99            . AND RETURN    @]@@@CMFS020    . @G@@@C          JZ      TM
)@@G@@  A5,MFS030         . IF NO PERMISSIONS ERROR CONTINUE@F@@@C          DLTN
)@@G@@        A1,FIPKT$+2       . GET EXTERNAL FILE NAME    @F@@@C          DSTO
)@@G@@        A1,MFSRPF         . STORE IN ERROR MESSAGE    @F@@@C          M$TP
)@@G@@PRINT,U MFSERP            . PRINT PERMISSIONS ERROR   @G@@@C          DSTQ
)@@G@@L       A4,72             . CLEAR ERROR AND FOUND FLAGS     @D@@@C      TR
)@@G@@    J         MFS999            . AND RETURN    @]@@@CMFS030    . @E@@@CTS
)@@G@@          DL        A1,9,A0           . GET ELEMENT NAME    @E@@@C      TT
)@@G@@    L         A5,MFSEEN         . ELEMENT NAME MESSAGE@D@@@C          TNTU
)@@G@@Z,S1    1,A0              . WAS IT GIVEN  @D@@@C          J         MFS9TV
)@@G@@99            . NO - ERROR    @[@@@C.     @E@@@C. NOTE THAT LACK OF ELEMTW
)@@G@@ENT NAME IS A REAL ERROR AS IT IS   @E@@@C. ASSUMED THAT THE CALLER CHECTX
)@@G@@KED THIS BEFORE CALLING US.   @[@@@C.     @E@@@C          DS        A1,PTY
)@@G@@FPELT         . SAVE ELEMENT NAME   @E@@@C          DL        A1,11,A0  TZ
)@@G@@        . GET VERSION NAME    @D@@@C          TNZ,S2    1,A0            UA
)@@G@@  . WAS IT GIVEN  @D@@@C          DL        A1,M$FDBLANKS     . NO USE SUB

)@@G@@@E@@@C          L,U       A1,1              . SET TYPE TO SYMBOLIC@B@@@CUD
)@@G@@          S         A1,PFPTYP         .   @E@@@C          L,U       A0,PUE

)@@G@@    DSL       A4,72             . CLEAR ERROR AND FOUND FLAGS     @E@@@CUL
)@@G@@          TNE,U     A2,1              . WAS ERROR NOT FOUND @F@@@C      UM

)@@G@@        MFS999            . AND RETURN    @]@@@CMFS050    . @E@@@C      UP
)@@G@@    LA        A0,PFPET          . GET ELEMENT TYPE    @F@@@C          JNUQ
)@@G@@E,U     A0,1 MFS900       . IF NOT SYMBOLIC, BAD NEWS @E@@@C          LAUR
)@@G@@        A0,PFPSST         . GET SYMBOLIC SUBTYPE@D@@@C          TE,U    US
)@@G@@  A0,EDPTYPE        . IS IT EDP?    @D@@@C          TNE,U     A0,EDMTYPEUT
)@@G@@        . IS IT EDM?    @D@@@C          J         MFS060            . YEUU
)@@G@@S, GO AHEAD @D@@@C          TE,U      A0,1              . ELT TYPE?     UV
)@@G@@@G@@@C          JNZ       A0,MFS900         . NO, IF NOT UNTYPED SYM, ERUW
)@@G@@ROR   @D@@@C          LA,U      A0,EDMTYPE        . ASSUME MACRO  @G@@@CUX

)@@G@@@G@@@V. THIS ELEMENT CONTAINS THE CODE TO SUPPORT THE DEFAULT MACRO INTRXE
)@@G@@INSIC @^@@@V. EXECUTED VARIABLES.   @[@@@V.     @B@@@V. TABLE$ - RETURN XF
)@@G@@A TABLE DESCRIPTOR.     @[@@@V.     @]@@@VM$XVARTABLE*@^@@@V          SUXG
)@@G@@BROUTINE    @E@@@V          M$TGET    TAB999 M$DEFTABLEN . GET DEFAULT TXH
)@@G@@ABLE  @E@@@V          LA,U      A1,,A1            . CLEAR INCREMENT     XI
)@@G@@@H@@@V          MOVE      A0,0,A1,U A2,M$DEFTABLE M$DEFTABLEN . INITIALIXJ
)@@G@@ZE THE TABLE@E@@@V          LA,U      A0,MODTBL         . GET THE RESULTXK

)@@G@@@C@@@VTAB999    RETURN                      . DONE    @[@@@V.     @H@@@VXM

)@@G@@TURN AN INTEGER   @[@@@V.     @F@@@V.   SUP$ - RETURN THE VALUES RETURNEXQ
)@@G@@D BY THE INFO$ SUP$ FUNCTION  @[@@@V.     @^@@@VM$XVARSUP*         .    XR
)@@G@@@B@@@V          SUBROUTINE                  .   @E@@@V          M$TGET  XS
)@@G@@  SUPS999           9 . GET SOME SPACE    @G@@@V          L,U         A0XT
)@@G@@,,A1            . SAVE THE ADDRESS OF THE SPACE @B@@@V          LXI,U   XU
)@@G@@  A0,2              .   @G@@@V          L,U       A1,2,A0           . GEXV
)@@G@@T ADDRESS OF SPACE FOR INFO   @G@@@V          LXI,U     A1,7            XW
)@@G@@  . GET ALL SEVEN WORDS OF INFO     @G@@@V          S         A1,1,A0   XX
)@@G@@        . PLACE ADDRESS INTO THE PACKET   @F@@@V          L,U       A1,SXY
)@@G@@UP$           . GET SUP$ FUNCTION CODE    @F@@@V          LSSL      A1,6XZ
)@@G@@              . SHIFT TO PUT IT INTO T1   @G@@@V          S,H1      A1,,YA
)@@G@@A0            . PUT FUNCTION CODE INTO PACKET   @E@@@V          ER      YB

)@@G@@,A0            . GET ADDRESS OF BUFFER    @D@@@V          LXI,U     A1,1YD
)@@G@@              . SET INCREMENT @D@@@V          L,U       R1,6            YE
)@@G@@  . REPEAT COUNT  @]@@@VSUPS010   . @E@@@V          L         A3,0,A1   YF
)@@G@@        . GET THE NEXT VALUE  @C@@@V          SSL       A2,36           YG
)@@G@@  . CLEAR A3@H@@@V          DI,U      A2,5              . CONVERT FROM SYH
)@@G@@UPS TO MICROSECONDS     @E@@@V          S         A2,0,*A1          . SEYI

)@@G@@ THE REST   @E@@@V          L,U       A1,2,A0           . GET ADDRESS AGYK
)@@G@@AIN   @F@@@V          L,U       A0,MODSIN         . GET SINGLE INTEGER MYL
)@@G@@ODE   @F@@@V          LSSL      A0,30             . PUT MODE IN RIGHT PLYM

)@@G@@SUPS999     @B@@@V          RETURN                      .   @[@@@Y.     YO
)@@G@@@G@@@Y.   SITEID$ - RETURN THE VALUES RETURNED BY THE INFO$ SITEID$ FUNCYP
)@@G@@TION  @[@@@Y.     @^@@@YM$XVARSITEID*         . @B@@@Y          SUBROUTIYQ
)@@G@@NE                  .   @E@@@Y          M$TGET    SITE999 3          . GYR

)@@G@@OUTINE TO EDIT THE DATE IN MM/DD/YY FORMAT@E@@@V. DATE2$ - ROUTINE TO EDBQ

)@@G@@NE    @F@@@VTDARGS    LOCAL     2                 . A0,A1=TDATE$ WORD,INBZ
)@@G@@DEX   @D@@@V          DS        A0,TDARGS         . SAVE ARGUMENTS@D@@@VCA
)@@G@@          M$EOPENA  M$EPKT M$RESULTBAW . LET'S EDIT   @E@@@V          DLCB
)@@G@@        A0,TDARGS         . RECOVER ARGUMENTS   @G@@@V          CALL    CC
)@@G@@  *TDRTNS,A1        . EXECUTE THE CORRECT ROUTINE     @E@@@V          E$CD
)@@G@@COLN                      . GET THE CHAR COUNT. @C@@@V          SA      CE
)@@G@@  A0,TDARGS         . SAVE IT @D@@@V          M$ECLOSE                  CF
)@@G@@  . STOP EDITING  @E@@@V          LA        A1,TDARGS         . GET # CHCG
)@@G@@ARS IN IMAGE@E@@@V          LA,U      A0,M$RESULTBUF    . GET BUFFER ADDCH
)@@G@@RESS  @F@@@V          CALL      M$RESULTASC       . CREATE A STRING DESCCI
)@@G@@RIPTOR@D@@@V          RETURN                      . THAT'S ALL    @[@@@VCJ
)@@G@@.     @C@@@VTDRTNS    $EQU      $-1               . ORIGIN 1@F@@@V      CK
)@@G@@    +         ETIME$            . EDIT THE TIME HH:MM:SS    @F@@@V      CL
)@@G@@    +         EDAY1$            . EDIT THE DATE MM/DD/YY    @F@@@V      CM
)@@G@@    +         EDAY2$            . EDIT THE DATE DD MMM YY   @G@@@V      CN
)@@G@@    +         EDAY3$            . EDIT THE DATE MMMMMMM DD, YYYY  @F@@@VCO
)@@G@@          +         EDAY4$            . EDIT THE DATE YYYYMMDD    @E@@@VCP
)@@G@@          +         EDAY5$            . EDIT THE DATE YYMMDD@G@@@V      CQ
)@@G@@    +         EWDAY1$           . EDIT THE ABBR. WEEKDAY NAME     @G@@@VCR
)@@G@@          +         EWDAY2$           . EDIT THE LONG  WEEKDAY NAME     CS
)@@G@@@[@@@V.     @B@@@V. ACCT$ - RETURN THE USER'S ACCOUNT NUMBER@A@@@V. RUNICT
)@@G@@D$ - RETURN THE USER'S RUNID  @B@@@V. PROJ$ - RETURN THE USERS' PROJECT CU
)@@G@@ID    @B@@@V. QUAL$ - RETURN THE USER'S QUALIFIER     @[@@@V.     @]@@@VCV
)@@G@@M$XVARACCT* @E@@@V          PCT$      M$RESULTBUF,2,023 . FETCH THE ACCOCW
)@@G@@UNT   @D@@@V          LA,U      A0,' '            . GET A BLANK   @F@@@VCX
)@@G@@          TNZ,S6    M$RESULTBUF+1     . IS USER IN UOM-PRIVL MODE?@E@@@VCY
)@@G@@          SA,S6     A0,M$RESULTBUF+1  . YES, BLANK THE '@'  @G@@@V      CZ
)@@G@@    J         XVAR010           . RETURN WITH 2 WORDS OF STRING   @[@@@VDA
)@@G@@.     @]@@@VM$XVARRUNID*@E@@@V          PCT$      M$RESULTBUF,1,1   . GEDB
)@@G@@T GENERATED RUNID @D@@@V          LA,U      A1,6              . MAX CHARDC
)@@G@@S     @D@@@V          J         XVAR020           . GO FINISH     @[@@@VDD
)@@G@@.     @]@@@VM$XVARPROJ* @D@@@V          PCT$      M$RESULTBUF,1,5   . GEDE
)@@G@@T WORD FIVE @G@@@V          LA,H1     A1,M$RESULTBUF    . GET THE QUALIFDF
)@@G@@IER TABLE LINK    @E@@@V          AA,U      A1,1              . GET ONE DG
)@@G@@WORD PAST IT@F@@@V          LXI,U     A1,2              . WE WANT TWO WODH
)@@G@@RDS THERE   @D@@@V          LA,U      A0,M$RESULTBUF    . BUFFER ADDRESSDI
)@@G@@@C@@@V          ER        PCT$              . RETRIEVE@E@@@V          J DJ
)@@G@@        XVAR010           . RETURN W/12 CHARS   @[@@@V.     @]@@@VM$XVARDK
)@@G@@QUAL* @G@@@V          PCT$      M$RESULTBUF,1,0336 . GET POINTER TO THE DL
)@@G@@QUALIFIER   @B@@@V          L,H1      A1,M$RESULTBUF    .   @E@@@V      DM
)@@G@@    A,U       A1,01000          . MAKE IT RELATIVE    @F@@@V          LXDN
)@@G@@I,U     A1,3              . GET THREE WORDS WORTH     @B@@@V          L,DO
)@@G@@U       A0,M$RESULTBUF    .   @B@@@V          ER        PCT$            DP
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@V          DL        A0,M$RESULTBUF+1  .   @B@@@V          DSDQ
)@@G@@        A0,M$RESULTBUF    .   @[@@@V.     @A@@@V. RETURN 12 CHARS FROM TDR
)@@G@@HE BUFFER   @[@@@V.     @D@@@VXVAR010   LA,U      A1,12             . MADS
)@@G@@X # OF CHARS@C@@@VXVAR020   LA,U      A0,M$RESULTBUF    . BUFFER  @E@@@VDT

)@@G@@M$SUBNULL   @@@@@@@@@@E+M$UIVECT    @@@@@@@@@@EGM$USERMCVT  @@@@@@@@@@E>AH
)@@G@@M$USERVDCOPY@@@@@@@@@@E&M$USERVDEDIT@@@@@@@@@@E$M$USERVDERS @@@@@@@@@@E*AI
)@@G@@M$VAROTHER  @@@@@@@@@@E=M$XQTCOM    @@@@@@@@@@E(*     @G@@@U          L AJ
)@@G@@        A0,M$PLIMIT       . GET THE CURRENT PRINT LIMIT     @E@@@U      AK
)@@G@@    J         M$RESULTIN*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@C/         M$DEF   @G@@@C      AL
)@@G@@    FIDEF$    M$ELT$            . GET ELT$ EQUFS ON OUR OWN PACKET@[@@@CAM
)@@G@@.     @E@@@C. THIS ELEMENT CONTAINS A SCANNER FOR EXEC8 FILE NAMES.     AN
)@@G@@@[@@@C.     @D@@@C. THE FILE NAME SCANNED IS LEFT IN THE ELT$ PACKET.   AO
)@@G@@@[@@@C.     @ @@@C. MASKS OF LEGAL CHARACTERS   @[@@@C.     @E@@@CNAMASKAP
)@@G@@    T$MASKR   'NUM' 'LET' '$' '-' . FILENAME MASK     @F@@@CNUMASK    T$AQ
)@@G@@MASKR   'NUM' '-' '+' . FCYCLE AND ELEMENT CYCLE MASK @H@@@CKEYMASK   T$AR
)@@G@@MASKR 'LET' 'NUM' 'SP' *'.' *' ' *'/' *',' . READ/WRITE KEY MASK  @[@@@CAS
)@@G@@.     @E@@@C. DEFINE LOCATION COUNTERS TO BE USED IN GENERATING TABLES. AT
)@@G@@@[@@@C.     @F@@@CLCNODE    EQU       5                 . NODES LOCATIONAU
)@@G@@ COUNTER    @F@@@CLCST1     EQU       7                 . STORE ONE LOCAAV
)@@G@@TION COUNTER@F@@@CLCST2     EQU       9                 . STORE TWO LOCAAW
)@@G@@TION COUNTER@[@@@C.     @G@@@CDATSTO    EQU       $(LCST1)          . EXAX
)@@G@@ECUTE TABLE TO STORE ITEM DATA@G@@@CLENSTO    EQU       $(LCST2)        AY
)@@G@@  . EXECUTE TABLE TO STORE ITEM LEN @G@@@CNODES     EQU       $(LCNODE) AZ
)@@G@@        . DATA TABLE TO DRIVE SCANNER     @[@@@C.     @ @@@C. FIELDS IN BA
)@@G@@'NODE' OF TABLE.  @[@@@C.     @E@@@CNODSTO    EQUF      NODES,,S1       BB
)@@G@@  . STORE TABLE INDEX   @F@@@CNODMAX    EQUF      NODES,,S2         . MABC
)@@G@@XIMUM LENGTH OF ITEM    @G@@@CNODARC    EQUF      NODES,,S3         . NUBD
)@@G@@MBER OF ARCS LEAVING THIS NODE@G@@@CNODMSK    EQUF      NODES,,H2       BE
)@@G@@  . LEGAL CHARACTER MASK ADDRESS    @[@@@C.     @ @@@C. FIELDS IN 'ARC' BF
)@@G@@OF TABLE.   @[@@@C.     @F@@@CARCCHR    EQUF      NODES,,S1         . CHBG
)@@G@@ARACTER LABELING ARC    @F@@@CARCNOD    EQUF      NODES,,S2         . NEBH
)@@G@@W NODE POINTER FOR ARC  @G@@@CARCRTN    EQUF      NODES,,H2         . ARBI
)@@G@@C TRANSITION ROUTINE ADDRESS  @[@@@C/.    @[@@@C.     @G@@@CN(1)      EQBJ
)@@G@@U       0                 . SET NUMBER OF NODES TO ZERO     @[@@@C.     BK
)@@G@@@D@@@C. THIS PROC BUILDS THE 'NODE' PORTION OF THE TABLE.   @[@@@C.     BL
)@@G@@@E@@@C.   NODE-NAME   NODE   CHAR-MASK,MAX-CHARS ITEM-LOC ITEM-LEN@[@@@CBM
)@@G@@.     @D@@@C.  NODE-NAME       IS THE NAME OF THE CURRENT NODE    @F@@@CBN
)@@G@@.  CHAR-MASK       IS THE ADDRESS OF A MASK OF LEGAL CHARACTERS   @E@@@CBO
)@@G@@.  MAX-CHARS       IS THE MAXIMUM CHARACTERS IN THE FIELD   @D@@@C.  ITEBP
)@@G@@M-LOC        IS WHERE THE NAME IS TO BE STORED  @G@@@C.  ITEM-LEN       BQ
)@@G@@ IS WHERE TO STORE THE CHARACTER LENGTH OF THE ITEM   @[@@@C.     @B@@@CBR
)@@G@@P         PROC      *3                .   @B@@@CNODE*     NAME          BS
)@@G@@              .   @[@@@C.     @F@@@CN*(1)     EQU       N(1)+1          BT
)@@G@@  . INCREMENT CURRENT NODE    @[@@@C.     @^@@@C. BUILD THE NODE WORD   BU
)@@G@@@[@@@C.     @B@@@C. S1 = STORE TABLE INDEX FOR THIS NODE.   @B@@@C. S2 =BV
)@@G@@ MAXIMUM ITEM LENGTH IN CHARACTERS  @A@@@C. S3 = NUMBER OF ARCS IN THIS BW
)@@G@@NODE  @E@@@C. H2 = ADDRESS OF MASK OF LEGAL CHARACTERS FOR THIS ITEM    BX
)@@G@@@[@@@C.     @F@@@C$(LCNODE).                            . NODE LOCATION BY
)@@G@@COUNTER     @E@@@C*         EQU       $-NODES           . DEFINE CURRENTBZ
)@@G@@ NODE @D@@@CNF        FORM      6,6,6,18          . NODE FORM     @D@@@CCA
)@@G@@          NF        N(1)-1,P(1,2)+1,A(N(1)),P(1,1) .  @[@@@C.     @C@@@CCB
)@@G@@. EXECUTE TABLE ENTRY TO STORE THE ITEM'S DATA. @[@@@C.     @G@@@C$(LCSTCC
)@@G@@1).                             . DATA STORE LOCATION COUNTER     @F@@@CCD
)@@G@@          ON        P(2)              . IF DATA ADDRESS GIVEN     @F@@@CCE
)@@G@@ DO P(1,2)>6 , DS A0,P(2,1),P(2,2)        . IF TWO WORDS STORE    @F@@@CCF
)@@G@@ DO P(1,2)<7 , S  A0,P(2,1),P(2,2),P(2,3) . IF ONE WORD STORE     @F@@@CCG
)@@G@@          OFF       P(2)              . IF DATA ADDRESS GIVEN     @G@@@CCH
)@@G@@ DO P(2)=0 , NOP                      . IF NOT GIVEN GENERATE NO-OP     CI
)@@G@@@[@@@C.     @F@@@C. BUILD EXECUTE TABLE ENTRY TO STORE ITEM'S CHARACTER CJ
)@@G@@LENGTH.     @[@@@C.     @]@@@C$(LCST2).   @G@@@C DO (P(3)=0)=0 , S  A4,PCK
)@@G@@(3,1),P(3,2),P(3,3) . IF GIVEN GENERATE STORE   @E@@@C DO P(3)=0 , NOP  CL
)@@G@@                    . ELSE GENERATE NO-OP @[@@@C.     @^@@@C          ENCM
)@@G@@D       .   @[@@@C/.    @[@@@C.     @F@@@C. THIS PROC BUILDS THE ARCS WHCN
)@@G@@ICH GOVERN THE NODE TRANSITIONS     @[@@@C.     @D@@@C.      ARC  'TRANSCO
)@@G@@-CHAR',NEW-NODE     TRANS-ROUTINE   @[@@@C.     @F@@@C.  TRANS-CHAR     CP
)@@G@@  IS A SINGLE CHARACTER WHICH LABELS THE ARC.   @E@@@C.  NEW-NODE       CQ
)@@G@@  IS THE NAME OF THE NEW NODE TO GO TO.   @F@@@C.  TRANS-ROUTINE    IS TCR
)@@G@@HE ROUTINE TO BE CALLED IN TRANSITION.    @[@@@C.     @B@@@CP         PRCS
)@@G@@OC      *2                .   @B@@@CARC*      NAME                      CT
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@C.     @G@@@CA*(N(1))  EQU       A(N(1))+1         . INCREMENCU
)@@G@@T ARCS FOR THIS NODE    @[@@@C.     @G@@@C DO P(2)=0 ,P(2,1) EQU ARCSTO CV
)@@G@@        . DEFINE DEFAULT TRANS ROUTINE    @[@@@C.     @^@@@C. BUILD THE CW
)@@G@@ARC WORD    @[@@@C.     @E@@@C. S1 = DISTINGUISHING CHARACTER WHICH WILLCX
)@@G@@ CAUSE TRANSITION @C@@@C. S2 = NAME OF NEW NODE (RELATIVE TO NODES)     CY
)@@G@@@#@@@C. S3 = NOT USED   @A@@@C. H2 = ADDRESS OF TRANSITION ROUTINE@[@@@CCZ
)@@G@@.     @F@@@C$(LCNODE).                            . NODE LOCATION COUNTEDA
)@@G@@R     @B@@@CAF        FORM      6,6,6,18          .   @C@@@C          AFDB
)@@G@@        P(1,1),P(1,2),0,P(2,1) .    @[@@@C.     @B@@@C          END     DC
)@@G@@                    .   @[@@@C/.    @[@@@C.     @F@@@C. DEFINE THE DATA DD
)@@G@@TABLE WHICH CONTROLS THIS TABLE DRIVEN SCANNER. @[@@@C.     @E@@@CNQUAL DE
)@@G@@    NODE      NAMASK,12 FQUAL FQL . QUALIFIER NODE    @E@@@C          ARDF
)@@G@@C       '*',NFILE ARCQUL  . STORE QUALIFIER     @E@@@C          ARC     DG
)@@G@@  '(',NFILE ARCNUL  . NEXT NODE NO STORE  @B@@@C          ARC       '/',DH
)@@G@@NFILE ARCNUL  .   @F@@@C          ARC       '.',NFILE ARCFIL  . HANDLE LDI
)@@G@@EADING PERIOD     @[@@@C.     @E@@@CNFILE     NODE      NAMASK,12 FNAME DJ
)@@G@@FNL . FILE NAME NODE    @B@@@C          ARC       '(',NFCYC         .   DK
)@@G@@@B@@@C          ARC       '/',NRKEY         .   @B@@@C          ARC     DL
)@@G@@  '.',NELT          .   @[@@@C.     @E@@@CNFCYC     NODE      NUMASK,4 FDM
)@@G@@CYC FCL . FILE CYCLE NODE     @B@@@C          ARC       ')',NFNUL       DN
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@C.     @D@@@CNFNUL     NODE      NUMASK,0          . NULL NODDO
)@@G@@E     @B@@@C          ARC       '/',NRKEY         .   @B@@@C          ARDP
)@@G@@C       '.',NELT          .   @[@@@C.     @D@@@CNRKEY     NODE      KEYMDQ
)@@G@@ASK,6 RKEY RKL . READ KEY NODE@B@@@C          ARC       '/',NWKEY       DR
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@C          ARC       '.',NELT          .   @[@@@C.     @E@@@CDS
)@@G@@NWKEY     NODE      KEYMASK,6 WKEY WKL . WRITE KEY NODE     @B@@@C      DT
)@@G@@    ARC       '.',NELT          .   @[@@@C.     @E@@@CNELT      NODE    DU
)@@G@@  NAMASK,12 ENAME ENL . ELEMENT NAME NODE @B@@@C          ARC       '/',DV
)@@G@@NVER          .   @B@@@C          ARC       '(',NECYC         .   @[@@@CDW
)@@G@@.     @F@@@CNVER      NODE      NAMASK,12 EVER EVL . ELEMENT VERSION NODDX
)@@G@@E     @B@@@C          ARC       '(',NECYC         .   @[@@@C.     @E@@@CDY
)@@G@@NECYC     NODE      NUMASK,3 ECYC ECL . ELEMENT CYCLE NODE  @B@@@C      DZ
)@@G@@    ARC       ')',NENUL         .   @[@@@C.     @E@@@CNENUL     NODE    EA
)@@G@@  NUMASK,0          . NULL NODE FOR CYCLE @[@@@C/.    @E@@@C          INEB
)@@G@@STRS                      . NORMAL COUNTERS     @[@@@C.     @^@@@CM$SCANEC
)@@G@@FILE*         .   @^@@@C          SUBROUTINE X9 @E@@@C          DSL     ED
)@@G@@  A4,72             . CLEAR A4 AND A5     @F@@@C          DS        A4,EEE
)@@G@@LT$           . CLEAR FLAGS IN ELT$ PACKET@E@@@C          T$COLN        EF
)@@G@@              . GET COLUMN NUMBER   @C@@@C          S,H2      A0,ITEM+2 EG
)@@G@@        . STORE IT@[@@@C.     @C@@@C. SKIP LEADING BLANKS BEFORE FILE NAEH
)@@G@@ME FIELD.   @[@@@C.     @F@@@C          T$NFIND   ' ' SCF060        . IFEI
)@@G@@ NOTHING JUST RETURN    @H@@@C          LMJ       X11,CHRFIX        . TUEJ
)@@G@@RN COMMA AND BLANK INTO TERM CHAR   @G@@@C          JN        A3,SCF050 EK
)@@G@@        . IF ONE OF THESE THEN RETURN     @F@@@C          L         X9,(EL
)@@G@@1,NQUAL)      . START SCANNING FILE NAME  @[@@@C.     @G@@@C. LOOK AHEADEM
)@@G@@ TO SEE IF THERE IS A PERIOD OR AN ASTERISK IN THIS SPEC.   @B@@@C. IF TEN
)@@G@@HERE IS WE START IN FILENAME MODE.  @B@@@C. IF NOT WE START IN ELEMENT NEO
)@@G@@AME MODE.   @[@@@C.     @E@@@C          T$COLN                      . GEEP
)@@G@@T CURRENT COLUMN  @E@@@C          AN,U      A0,1              . POINT ATEQ
)@@G@@ LAST BLANK @F@@@C          S,H2      A0,ITEM+2         . SAVE ACROSS LOER
)@@G@@OK AHEAD    @F@@@C          L,H1      A3,ITEM+2         . GET CHAR STOREES
)@@G@@D BY CHRFIX @]@@@CSCF010    . @D@@@C          TE,U      A3,'*'          ET
)@@G@@  . IS IT ASTERISK@D@@@C          TNE,U     A3,'.'            . OR PERIOEU
)@@G@@D     @H@@@C          J         SCF020            . YES - EXIT WITH X9  EV
)@@G@@POINTING TO NQUAL @D@@@C          T$CHAR                      . GET CHAREW
)@@G@@ACTER @F@@@C          LMJ       X11,CHRFIX        . TURN BLANK COMMA INTEX
)@@G@@O TERM@F@@@C          JP        A3,SCF010         . IF NOT TERMINATOR LOEY
)@@G@@OP    @[@@@C.     @D@@@C. NO PERIOD OR ASTERISK FOUND - POINT SCAN AT ELEZ
)@@G@@EMENT.@[@@@C.     @E@@@C          LXM,U     X9,NELT           . LOAD ELEFA
)@@G@@MENT STATE  @[@@@C.     @A@@@C. BACK UP TO ORIGINAL POSITION.     @[@@@CFB
)@@G@@.     @]@@@CSCF020    . @E@@@C          T$COL     ITEM+2,,H2        . MOFC
)@@G@@VE TIDE$ BACKWARDS@[@@@C/.    @[@@@C.     @#@@@C. MAIN SCAN LOOP. @^@@@CFD
)@@G@@. (NOTE FALL-THRU).     @[@@@C.     @]@@@CSCF030    . @E@@@C          DLFE
)@@G@@        A0,M$FDBLANKS     . GET FIELDATA BLANKS @E@@@C          DS      FF
)@@G@@  A0,ITEM           . INITIALIZE ITEM     @F@@@C          L         A0,NFG
)@@G@@ODMSK,X9      . GET MASK FOR CURRENT NODE @E@@@C          DL        A2,0FH
)@@G@@,A0           . INTO DOUBLE A2-A3   @D@@@C          L,U       A0,ITEM   FI
)@@G@@        . PUT IT IN ITEM@D@@@C          L         A1,NODMAX,X9      . GEFJ
)@@G@@T MAX LENGTH@D@@@C          T$NBRKF                     . SCAN NEXT ITEMFK
)@@G@@@G@@@C          LMJ       X11,CHRFIX        . TURN BLANK COMMA INTO TERMFL
)@@G@@INATOR@E@@@C          L         A5,ERRLEN         . GET ERROR MESSAGE   FM
)@@G@@@E@@@C          JZ        A2,SCF900         . WAS TERM COUNT-DOWN @F@@@CFN
)@@G@@          DL        A0,ITEM           . NO - GET ITEM SCANNED     @[@@@CFO
)@@G@@.     @D@@@C. SEARCH ARCS FOR ONE MARKED WITH TERM CHAR FOUND.    @[@@@CFP
)@@G@@.     @]@@@CARCNUL    . @E@@@C          L         A2,NODSTO,X9      . GEFQ
)@@G@@T STORE INDEX     @G@@@C          L         R1,NODARC,X9      . GET NUMBFR
)@@G@@ER OF ARCS TO SEARCH    @D@@@C          SE        A3,ARCCHR+1,*X9   . SEFS
)@@G@@ARCH ARCS   @F@@@C          J         SCF040            . NOT FOUND - CHFT
)@@G@@ECK FOR TERM@E@@@C          L         X11,ARCRTN,X9     . GET ARC ROUTINFU
)@@G@@E     @F@@@C          LXM       X9,ARCNOD,X9      . AND MOVE TO NEXT NODFV
)@@G@@E     @E@@@C          J         0,X11             . PROCESS ARC ROUTINE FW
)@@G@@@[@@@C.     @E@@@C. TERM CHAR NOT FOUND.  IF TERMINATOR WE ARE DONE, ELSFX
)@@G@@E IT  @A@@@C. IS AN ILLEGAL CHARACTER ERROR.    @[@@@C.     @]@@@CSCF040FY
)@@G@@    . @F@@@C          JN        A3,ARCSTO         . IF TERM STORE AND GEFZ
)@@G@@T OUT @E@@@C          L         A5,ERRCHR         . GET ERROR MESSAGE   GA
)@@G@@@D@@@C          J         SCF900            . ELSE IS ILCHAR@[@@@C.     GB
)@@G@@@B@@@C. ARC ROUTINE TO HANDLE LEADING PERIOD.   @[@@@C.     @]@@@CARCFILGC
)@@G@@    . @F@@@C          JNZ       A4,ARCNUL         . IF FILENAME SKIP THIGD
)@@G@@S     @D@@@C          L,U       A5,1              . ELSE GET ONE  @G@@@CGE
)@@G@@          S         A5,CFN            . AND SET LEADING PERIOD FLAG     GF
)@@G@@@D@@@C          J         ARCNUL            . AND CONTINUE  @[@@@C.     GG
)@@G@@@ @@@C. ARC ROUTINE FOR QUALIFIER.  @[@@@C.     @]@@@CARCQUL    . @F@@@CGH
)@@G@@          JNZ       A4,ARCSTO         . IF QUAL SEEN STORE IT     @D@@@CGI
)@@G@@          L,U       A5,1              . ELSE GET ONE  @F@@@C          S GJ
)@@G@@        A5,IQF            . AND SET IMPLIED QUALIFIER @[@@@C.     @C@@@CGK
)@@G@@. ARC ROUTINE FOR STORING CURRENT COMPONENT.    @^@@@C. (NOTE FALL-THRU)GL
)@@G@@.     @[@@@C.     @]@@@CARCSTO    . @E@@@C          EX        LENSTO,A2 GM
)@@G@@        . STORE ITEM LENGTH   @E@@@C          EX        DATSTO,A2       GN
)@@G@@  . STORE DATA ITEM     @F@@@C          JP        A3,SCF030         . IFGO
)@@G@@ MORE TO SCAN THEN LOOP @[@@@C/.    @[@@@C.     @#@@@C. DONE SCANNING.  GP
)@@G@@@^@@@C. (NOTE FALL-THRU).     @[@@@C.     @]@@@CSCF050    . @F@@@C      GQ
)@@G@@    L,H1      A3,ITEM+2         . RECOVER LAST CHAR SCANNED @[@@@C.     GR
)@@G@@@D@@@C. NOTHING FOUND BY T$NFINDA - A3 IS ALREADY LOADED.   @[@@@C.     GS
)@@G@@@]@@@CSCF060    . @E@@@C          L,H2      A4,ITEM+2         . LOAD COLGT
)@@G@@UMN NUMBER  @E@@@C          L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR COGU
)@@G@@DE    @D@@@C          J         SCF999            . AND RETURN    @[@@@CGV
)@@G@@.     @ @@@C. GENERATE ERROR MESSAGE.     @[@@@C.     @]@@@CSCF900    . GW
)@@G@@@F@@@C          T$COLN                      . GET CURRENT COLUMN NUMBER GX
)@@G@@@D@@@C          AN,U      A0,1              . INCREMENTED   @F@@@C      GY
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,M$ERRMSGBLD   . AND GENERATE ERROR MESSAGE@[@@@C.     GZ
)@@G@@@#@@@C. RETURN TO CALLER@[@@@C.     @]@@@CSCF999    . @I@@@C          TNHA
)@@G@@Z       ECL               . IF A CYCLE WAS GIVEN, CONVERT IT TO BINA    HB
)@@G@@@D@@@C          J         SCF999A           . ELSE FORGET IT@]@E@C  SLJ HC
)@@G@@TON$  @C@@@C          SSL       A2,36             . CLEAR A2@H@D@C      HD
)@@G@@    L         A0,ECC            . GET FIRST CHARACTER OF CYCLE SPEC     HE
)@@G@@@H@@@D          L         A0,ECYC           . GET FIRST CHARACTER OF CYCHF
)@@G@@LE SPEC     @G@E@C          SSL       A0,030            . SHIFT OFF ALL HG
)@@G@@BUT THE FIRST CHAR@G@@@E          SSL       A0,30             . SHIFT OFHH
)@@G@@F ALL BUT THE FIRST CHAR@D@@@C          TE,U      A0,'+'            . IFHI
)@@G@@ RELATIVE + @C@@@C          TNE,U     A0,'-'            . OR MINUS@E@@@CHJ
)@@G@@          J         RELATIVE          . DO SPECIAL STUFF    @F@D@C      HK
)@@G@@    L         A1,ECC            . GET THE WHOLE CYCLE SPEC  @F@@@D      HL
)@@G@@    L         A1,ECYC           . GET THE WHOLE CYCLE SPEC  @F@@@C      HM
)@@G@@    L         R1,ECL            . AND THE NUMBER OF CHARS   @E@@@C      HN
)@@G@@    JGD       R1,CVTLOOP        . DO THE CONVERSION   @]@@@CRELATIVE  . HO
)@@G@@@E@D@C          L         A1,ECC            . GET THE WHOLE SPEC  @E@@@DHP
)@@G@@          L         A1,ECYC           . GET THE WHOLE SPEC  @F@@@C      HQ
)@@G@@    LSSL      A1,6              . SHIFT OFF THE '+' OR '-'  @E@F@C      HR
)@@G@@    LSSL      A0,030            . SHIFT TO BE LJZF    @E@G@F          LSHS
)@@G@@SL      A0,30             . SHIFT TO BE LJZF    @E@D@C          S       HT
)@@G@@  A0,ECC            . SAVE THE '+' OR '-' @E@F@D          S         A0,EHU
)@@G@@CYC           . SAVE THE '+' OR '-' @E@@@F          S         A0,ECC    HV
)@@G@@        . SAVE THE '+' OR '-' @D@@@C          L         R1,ECL          HW
)@@G@@  . GET THE LENGTH@D@@@C          JGD       R1,$+1. WE NEED TO DECREMENTHX
)@@G@@ TWICE@B@@@C          JGD       R1,CVTLOOP        .   @]@@@CCVTLOOP   . HY
)@@G@@@C@@@C          SSL       A0,36             . CLEAR A0@E@@@C          LDHZ
)@@G@@SL      A0,6              . GET THE NEXT CHAR   @G@@@C          AN,U    IA
)@@G@@  A0,060            . SUBTRACT TO GET BINARY VALUE    @C@@@C          MSIB
)@@G@@I,U     A2,10             . MULTIPLY@E@@@C          A,U       A2,,A0    IC
)@@G@@        . INCREASE THE SUM    @C@@@C          JGD       R1,CVTLOOP      ID
)@@G@@  . REPEAT  @D@@@C          S         A2,BEC            . SAVE THE VALUEIE
)@@G@@@]@E@C SLJ TOFF$  @]@@@CSCF999A     @#@@@C          RETURN  @[@@@C.     IF
)@@G@@@D@@@C. SUBROUTINE TO FORCE TERMINATION ON COMMA OR BLANK.  @[@@@C.     IG
)@@G@@@]@@@CCHRFIX    . @E@@@C          S,H1      A3,ITEM+2         . STORE REIH
)@@G@@AL CHARACTER@F@@@C          JN        A3,0,X11          . RETURN IF TERMII
)@@G@@ ALREADY    @E@@@C          LXI,U     A3,0              . CLEAR INCREMENIJ
)@@G@@T     @C@@@C          TE,U      A3,' '            . IF BLANK@C@@@C      IK
)@@G@@    TNE,U     A3,','            . IF COMMA@D@@@C          LN,U      A3,1IL
)@@G@@              . SET TERM CHAR @E@@@C          J         0,X11           IM
)@@G@@  . RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@C.     @D@@@CITEM      LOCAL     3         IN
)@@G@@        . SCAN BUFFER   @[@@@C.     @B@@@C          LITS                IO
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@C.     @B@@@CERRCHR    PCW       'ILLEGAL CHARACTER.'  IP
)@@G@@@B@@@CERRLEN    PCW       'COMPONENT TOO LONG.' @[@@@C.     @B@@@C      IQ
)@@G@@    END                         .   _@@@@@@@@@@@)O@@@^@]M@@[@@[@@C)[_"@@IR
